 get the five points looking forward towards hopefully making the semi-final,’ Tuilagi said. </font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Double delight: Manu Tuilagi of Leicester scored twice to send a reminder to the England selectors\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"427\" id=\"i-5d5a0d3a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DB44D00000578-440_634x427.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Double delight: Manu Tuilagi of Leicester scored twice to send a reminder to the England selectors</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Danger man: Tuilagi of Leicester breaks clear with the ball at Welford Road\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"343\" id=\"i-5bf50d2a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E4A7400000578-206_634x343.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Danger man: Tuilagi of Leicester breaks clear with the ball at Welford Road</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603298/Gloucester-17-18-Bath-Kingsholm-boils-two-red-four-yellow-cards.html\"> Gloucester 17-18 Bath: Kingsholm boils over after two red and five yellow cards</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602861/Sale-12-27-Harlequins-Sharks-outclassed-Salford-Quins-alive-play-hopes.html\"> Sale 12-27 Harlequins: Sharks outclassed in Salford as Quins keep alive play-off hopes</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\"> France scrum-half (and scourge of England) Yachvili reveals he will hang up his boots</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602735/Steve-Borthwicks-time-high-Saracens-lock-prepares-break-Premiership-appearance-record.html\"> Borthwick\'s all-time high as Saracens lock prepares to league break appearance record</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602908/Tim-Visser-targets-Scotlands-summer-tour-seven-month-absence.html\"> Edinburgh flyer Visser targets Scotland\'s summer tour after seven-month absence</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’m definitely feeling like I’m getting my match fitness back. It was really frustrating to be out for as long as I was. Watching your team-mates train while you’re in the physio room is hard. You just don’t feel like you’re part of the team. It’s been really frustrating.’</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Leicester’s win, which was not always as comfortable as the final score line suggested, moves them to within two points of second placed east midland rivals Northampton, who face top-of-the-table Saracens on Sunday, while Tuilagi’s return to form could not have come at a better time.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">His first try came from a flat pass across the gain line from scrum-half Ben Youngs which allowed the centre to crash over under the posts while his second, early in the second half, saw him swat aside James Short before powering over with three Wasps defenders on his back.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With Luther Burrell excelling in the England No13 shirt during the Six Nations, Tuilagi’s performance at inside centre yesterday will have impressed Lancaster.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fijian flyer: Vereniki Goneva of Leicester breaks clear to score a try on the day he agreed a new contract\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"409\" id=\"i-5d8e0d41\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DF00E00000578-198_634x409.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fijian flyer: Vereniki Goneva of Leicester breaks clear to score a try on the day he agreed a new contract</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wales hopeful: Owen Williams of Leicester takes on Ed Jackson at Welford Road\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"497\" id=\"i-505d0d04\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E3E9000000578-61_634x497.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wales hopeful: Owen Williams of Leicester takes on Ed Jackson at Welford Road</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’m just as happy at 12 or 13,’ Tuilagi said. ‘If I was picked on the wing for England I’d be happy.’</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Fijian winger Niki Goneva, who earlier in the day signed a contract extension, scored one Leicester’s other try before replacement David Mele claimed the bonus-point score with two minutes left on the clock.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It was a case of ‘job done’,’ said Tigers boss Richard Cockerill. ‘It wasn’t much of an event but we’ll take the five points. It’s nice to have Manu back playing like that.’ </font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Leicester and England lock Geoff Parling made his first appearance following a six-month injury lay-off to provide Lancaster and Cockerill with another boost.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wasps’ main focus now is trying to claim seventh place in order to gain the final European spot for next season and next week’s Twickenham clash now takes on huge significance for both clubs.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘We’re disappointed we didn’t even get a bonus point,’ said Wasps boss Dai Young, whose side’s only try came through flanker Guy Thompson.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Momentum is massive in this game and if we’d have come here and had our trousers pulled down it wouldn’t have done us any good for next week.’</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Skipper: Ed Slater of Leicester breaks through the Wasps defence in the Aviva Premiership match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"327\" id=\"i-5d8b0d3c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DB08F00000578-414_634x327.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Skipper: Ed Slater of Leicester breaks through the Wasps defence in the Aviva Premiership match</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the charge: Jordan Crane of Leicester is tackled by Nathan Hughes (L) and Guy Thompson\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"361\" id=\"i-527a0d14\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DAF8700000578-58_634x361.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the charge: Jordan Crane of Leicester is tackled by Nathan Hughes (L) and Guy Thompson</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603298/Gloucester-17-18-Bath-Kingsholm-boils-two-red-four-yellow-cards.html\"> Gloucester 17-18 Bath: Kingsholm boils over after two red and five yellow cards</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602861/Sale-12-27-Harlequins-Sharks-outclassed-Salford-Quins-alive-play-hopes.html\"> Sale 12-27 Harlequins: Sharks outclassed in Salford as Quins keep alive play-off hopes</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\"> France scrum-half (and scourge of England) Yachvili reveals he will hang up his boots</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602735/Steve-Borthwicks-time-high-Saracens-lock-prepares-break-Premiership-appearance-record.html\"> Borthwick\'s all-time high as Saracens lock prepares to league break appearance record</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602908/Tim-Visser-targets-Scotlands-summer-tour-seven-month-absence.html\"> Edinburgh flyer Visser targets Scotland\'s summer tour after seven-month absence</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603319/Leicester-27-15-Wasps-Manu-Tuilagi-strikes-twice-Tigers-push-home-play-semi-final.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603319/Leicester-27-15-Wasps-Manu-Tuilagi-strikes-twice-Tigers-push-home-play-semi-final.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Leicester 27-15 Wasps: Tuilagi strikes twice as Tigers push for home play-off semi-final\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603319/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DB44D00000578-824_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:40','2014-04-12 21:02:18'),(9,'fa0d80900159529e4668d7ee9720461fb9f7dc86d728b399f2527f3525ddbfb5','dailymail',NULL,'MASTERS 2014: Phil Mickelson forced to watch climax on TV after bunker misery on famous 12th hole','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603179/MASTERS-2014-Phil-Mickelson-forced-watch-climax-TV-bunker-misery-famous-12th-hole.html',' By Larry Fine, Reuters Published: 08:57 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 13:51 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments Three-times champion Phil Mickelson missed his first cut at the Masters in 17 years, the victim of another calamitous hole at Augusta National on Friday. Mickelson, who posted a pair of sevens during Thursday\'s opening-round 76, finished outside the cut by one stroke, undone by a triple-bogey six at the par-three 12th. \'I just had one bad hole there at 12,\' said the 43-year-old left-hander. \'And I keep making these triples. They\'re tough to overcome.\'  Early bath: Phil Mickelson walks off the 18th green after completing his second round at Augusta   Bunker misery part I: Mickelson hit his tee shot into the front sand trap on the short 12th hole   Bunker misery part II: The Open champion overhit his escape into the back trap  The world No 5 took a triple-bogey seven at the par-four seventh on Thursday, and a double-bogey seven at the par-five 15th. More... MASTERS LIVE: All the third-round action as it happens at Augusta National Bubba: I didn\'t know how to handle being Masters champion last year... but now I\'m ready to win back the green jacket MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy will tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut by skin of his teeth It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink The reigning Open champion, one of the most popular players among the galleries at Augusta National, has been a consistent performer at the Masters with 10 top-five finishes and 14 top-10s in his 21 previous visits. Mickelson said that outside of those three holes, he played solid golf and had no excuses. \'Why couldn\'t I get it going? I don\'t really have a great answer for you,\' he told reporters. \'I\'ve actually played reasonably well for a majority of the holes and then the ones that I let slide I end up making a big number. So it\'s tough to overcome those big numbers.\' Mickelson spent most of his time at the pesky 12th, the shortest hole at Augusta, playing in the sand. \'What happened at 12 was I hit in the front bunker and there was no sand where I was at,\' explained Mickelson, who contended he could not slide his wedge far enough under the ball. \'I caught the liner of the bunker and bladed it across the green and the same thing happened on the other side. It went back and forth, three bunkers, before I finally got it to stay on grass.\'  All in vain: The three-time Masters champion hits his approach on the second hole on Friday   Off the leaderboard: Mickelson was unable to hit the heights after several big scores this week   Cut: The American legend walks off the 18th green after failing with his final birdie attempt of the week  Mickelson needed a big finish to slip inside the cut line of four under par. Lefty put on a desperate charge, registering three birdies in four holes from the 14th and needed another birdie at the 18th to qualify for the last two rounds. Mickelson found the final green with his approach, but it bounded far past the cup leaving him a monster putt for birdie which he was unable to convert, taking a par for 73 and a five-over 149 total. Asked if he would watch the rest of the tournament on television, Mickelson said: \'I probably will. It will kind of be my punishment.  Early exit: Britain\'s Luke Donald also missed the cut after picking up a two-stroke penalty  Jason Dufner, who won the US PGA title last summer, missed the cut with rounds of 80 and 74, for an aggregate score of  10-over par. Britain’s Luke Donald also went home, counting the cost of a two-shot penalty for grounding a club in a bunker. ‘As soon as I did it, I knew that wasn’t the right thing to do,’ said Donald after he followed his first round 79 with a 70. ‘It was stupid on  my part.’   More... MASTERS LIVE: All the third-round action as it happens at Augusta National Bubba: I didn\'t know how to handle being Masters champion last year... but now I\'m ready to win back the green jacket MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy will tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut by skin of his teeth It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Larry+Fine,+Reuters\" rel=\"nofollow\">Larry Fine, Reuters</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 08:57 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 13:51 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603179/MASTERS-2014-Phil-Mickelson-forced-watch-climax-TV-bunker-misery-famous-12th-hole.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603179/MASTERS-2014-Phil-Mickelson-forced-watch-climax-TV-bunker-misery-famous-12th-hole.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Mickelson forced to watch Masters climax on TV after misery on famous 12th hole... where he went from one bunker to another!\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603179/MASTERS-2014-Phil-Mickelson-forced-watch-climax-TV-bunker-misery-famous-12th-hole.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Three-times champion Phil Mickelson missed his first cut at the Masters in 17 years, the victim of another calamitous hole at Augusta National on Friday.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mickelson, who posted a pair of sevens during Thursday\'s opening-round 76, finished outside the cut by one stroke, undone by a triple-bogey six at the par-three 12th.</font></p>\n<p>\'<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I just had one bad hole there at 12,\' said the 43-year-old left-hander. \'And I keep making these triples. They\'re tough to overcome.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Early bath: Phil Mickelson walks off the 18th green after completing his second round at Augusta\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"413\" id=\"i-ab960e7e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D09EDE400000578-291_634x413.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Early bath: Phil Mickelson walks off the 18th green after completing his second round at Augusta</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bunker misery part I: Mickelson hit his tee shot into the front sand trap on the short 12th hole\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"462\" id=\"i-a9cd0e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D09C08F00000578-552_634x462.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bunker misery part I: Mickelson hit his tee shot into the front sand trap on the short 12th hole</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bunker misery part II: The Open champion overhit his escape into the back trap\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"407\" id=\"i-a9830e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D09C0B300000578-887_634x407.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bunker misery part II: The Open champion overhit his escape into the back trap</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The world No 5 took a triple-bogey seven at the par-four seventh on Thursday, and a double-bogey seven at the par-five 15th.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\"> MASTERS LIVE: All the third-round action as it happens at Augusta National</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html\"> Bubba: I didn\'t know how to handle being Masters champion last year... but now I\'m ready to win back the green jacket</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\"> MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy will tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut by skin of his teeth</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html\"> It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602945/Masters-2014-Second-round-leaderboard-Bubba-Watson-holds-halfway-lead-Augusta.html\"> Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\"> Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The reigning Open champion, one of the most popular players among the galleries at Augusta National, has been a consistent performer at the Masters with 10 top-five finishes and 14 top-10s in his 21 previous visits.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mickelson said that outside of those three holes, he played solid golf and had no excuses.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Why couldn\'t I get it going? I don\'t really have a great answer for you,\' he told reporters.</font></p>\n<p>\'<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I\'ve actually played reasonably well for a majority of the holes and then the ones that I let slide I end up making a big number. So it\'s tough to overcome those big numbers.\'</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mickelson spent most of his time at the pesky 12th, the shortest hole at Augusta, playing in the sand.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'What happened at 12 was I hit in the front bunker and there was no sand where I was at,\' explained Mickelson, who contended he could not slide his wedge far enough under the ball.</font></p>\n<p>\'<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I caught the liner of the bunker and bladed it across the green and the same thing happened on the other side. It went back and forth, three bunkers, before I finally got it to stay on grass.\'</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All in vain: The three-time Masters champion hits his approach on the second hole on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-a8890e5e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D090CD000000578-622_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All in vain: The three-time Masters champion hits his approach on the second hole on Friday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Off the leaderboard: Mickelson was unable to hit the heights after several big scores this week\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"438\" id=\"i-aa7a0e7e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D09E2E500000578-796_634x438.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Off the leaderboard: Mickelson was unable to hit the heights after several big scores this week</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Cut: The American legend walks off the 18th green after failing with his final birdie attempt of the week\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"417\" id=\"i-9ced0e42\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D09E48E00000578-80_634x417.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Cut: The American legend walks off the 18th green after failing with his final birdie attempt of the week</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mickelson needed a big finish to slip inside the cut line of four under par.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Lefty put on a desperate charge, registering three birdies in four holes from the 14th and needed another birdie at the 18th to qualify for the last two rounds.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mickelson found the final green with his approach, but it bounded far past the cup leaving him a monster putt for birdie which he was unable to convert, taking a par for 73 and a five-over 149 total.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Asked if he would watch the rest of the tournament on television, Mickelson said: \'I probably will. It will kind of be my punishment. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Early exit: Britain\'s Luke Donald also missed the cut after picking up a two-stroke penalty\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a8e80e69\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D097F8100000578-573_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Early exit: Britain\'s Luke Donald also missed the cut after picking up a two-stroke penalty</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Jason Dufner, who won the US PGA title last summer, missed the cut with rounds of 80 and 74, for an aggregate score of  10-over par. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Britain’s Luke Donald also went home, counting the cost of a two-shot penalty for grounding a club in a bunker. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘As soon as I did it, I knew that wasn’t the right thing to do,’ said Donald after he followed his first round 79 with a 70.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It was stupid on  my part.’<br/></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\"> MASTERS LIVE: All the third-round action as it happens at Augusta National</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html\"> Bubba: I didn\'t know how to handle being Masters champion last year... but now I\'m ready to win back the green jacket</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\"> MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy will tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut by skin of his teeth</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html\"> It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602945/Masters-2014-Second-round-leaderboard-Bubba-Watson-holds-halfway-lead-Augusta.html\"> Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\"> Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603179/MASTERS-2014-Phil-Mickelson-forced-watch-climax-TV-bunker-misery-famous-12th-hole.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603179/MASTERS-2014-Phil-Mickelson-forced-watch-climax-TV-bunker-misery-famous-12th-hole.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Mickelson forced to watch Masters climax on TV after misery on famous 12th hole... where he went from one bunker to another!\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603179/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603179-1D09C0B300000578-792_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:41','2014-04-12 20:51:20'),(10,'2d0341b6e2abf9110daafd2a56893debfd28e373d6b3e8d65b850d9d8a62432d','dailymail',NULL,'Worcester 33-38 Exeter match report: Chiefs weather late Warriors fightback for bonus point win','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603285/Worcester-33-38-Exeter-match-report-Chiefs-weather-late-Warriors-fightback-bonus-point-win.html',' By David Kent Published: 13:33 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 13:33 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments Exeter took five Aviva Premiership points from victory at Worcester, although the home side came within a converted try of grabbing a dramatic win in a thrilling encounter. Worcester were languishing 21-3 behind at one stage but fought back bravely to get two bonus points, through four tries and finishing within seven points of the Chiefs. Scrum-half Dave Lewis, centre Sam Hill, fly-half Gareth Steenson and hooker Jack Yeandle got first-half tries for Exeter, while full-back Chris Pennell and David Lemi crossed for Worcester.  Close call: Exeter held on to claim a bonus point 38-33 victory over Worcester in the Aviva Premiership game   Sandwich making: Exeter\'s Don Armand is tackled by Worcester\'s Ofa Fainga\'anuku and Mike Williams   No cigar: Ryan Lamb of Worcester Warriors drops to his knees after coming close to a comeback victory  But the home side, bottom of the table and facing relegation, battled brilliantly in the second half through tries by hooker Agustin Creevy and Lemi\'s second against another Yeandle try. Ryan Lamb kicked three penalties and two conversions as well while Steenson ended on 18 points by adding a penalty and five conversions to his touchdown.   More... Wigan 36-14 London Broncos: Warriors bounce back for fourth straight victory Gloucester 17-18 Bath: Kingsholm boils over after two red and five yellow cards Sale 12-27 Harlequins: Sharks outclassed in Salford as Quins keep alive play-off hopes Hodgson signs on with Saracens as fly-half insists he is in no rush to hang up his boots Leicester close to signing Barbieri as Tigers CEO Cohen reveals Italian transfer targets Despite the Warriors\' late fightback, the relegation trapdoor now seems wide open and they must have been fearing the worst after just 24 minutes as Exeter strolled past some weak defence to rack up three tries and that 21-3 lead.  Bonus points: David Lemi of Worcester Warriors celebrates his try against Exeter Chiefs   Touchdown! Chris Pennell of Worcester Warriors crosses for a try in front of a home crowd  Lewis raced over for the first after nine minutes as he nipped past home prop Ofa Fainga\'anuku to race to the line, with Pennell forlornly chasing. Steenson converted but Lamb added Worcester\'s opening points with a 40-metre penalty. Hill\'s try soon followed as he was put over from two metres by his fly-half after an initial charge from Fetu\'u Vainikolo, and with Steenson converting, Exeter\'s lead was stretched again. It got worse for Worcester as Lamb missed another long-range attempt before Steenson rounded off another break into home territory for his own converted try. Catch me if you can: Carl Rimmerbeaks away leaving Warriors in his wake   The Worcester defence was almost non-existent and, when they had some possession inside the opposition 22, the Chiefs stood strong. It seemed how many for the Chiefs. But suddenly the game was on. Worcester grabbed their first try when scrum-half Jonny Arr fed Pennell to score. Then wing Lemi kicked upfield from just inside his own half and followed up to beat wing Matt Jess for pace and grab the converted try.  Pile driver: Sam Betty evades Exeter\'s Gareth Steensonto as the Warriors stage a thrilling comeback  Exeter dented the comeback, though, as Yeandle scored two tries either side of the break, both converted by Steenson, to put his side in command, the first of which also claimed the try bonus point. But Worcester, to their credit, would not lay down. Lamb booted a penalty just before Yeandle\'s second score.  Helping hand: Augustin Creevy of Worcester passes out of the tackle by Matt Jess of Exeter  Creevy\'s 53rd-minute try, that his stand-off converted, plus Lemi\'s second on the left moments - all after Exeter replacement James Scaysbrook was sin-binned for pulling down a maul on his own line - gave the Warriors a try bonus point. The momentum had switched and Worcester had Exeter on the rack even when they were back up to a full complement of players. And, after Lamb\'s third penalty put Worcester within five points, the match came down to one cross kick by the fly-half which wing Josh Drauniniu failed to grab with the line at his mercy to finish a great game.   More... Wigan 36-14 London Broncos: Warriors bounce back for fourth straight victory Gloucester 17-18 Bath: Kingsholm boils over after two red and five yellow cards Sale 12-27 Harlequins: Sharks outclassed in Salford as Quins keep alive play-off hopes Hodgson signs on with Saracens as fly-half insists he is in no rush to hang up his boots Leicester close to signing Barbieri as Tigers CEO Cohen reveals Italian transfer targets   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=David+Kent\" rel=\"nofollow\">David Kent</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 13:33 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 13:33 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603285/Worcester-33-38-Exeter-match-report-Chiefs-weather-late-Warriors-fightback-bonus-point-win.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603285/Worcester-33-38-Exeter-match-report-Chiefs-weather-late-Warriors-fightback-bonus-point-win.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Worcester 33-38 Exeter: Chiefs weather late Warriors fightback to edge bonus point win\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603285/Worcester-33-38-Exeter-match-report-Chiefs-weather-late-Warriors-fightback-bonus-point-win.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Exeter took five Aviva Premiership points from victory at Worcester, although the home side came within a converted try of grabbing a dramatic win in a thrilling encounter.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Worcester were languishing 21-3 behind at one stage but fought back bravely to get two bonus points, through four tries and finishing within seven points of the Chiefs.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Scrum-half Dave Lewis, centre Sam Hill, fly-half Gareth Steenson and hooker Jack Yeandle got first-half tries for Exeter, while full-back Chris Pennell and David Lemi crossed for Worcester.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Close call: Exeter held on to claim a bonus point 38-33 victory over Worcester in the Aviva Premiership game\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5d040d3a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E5C7600000578-395_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Close call: Exeter held on to claim a bonus point 38-33 victory over Worcester in the Aviva Premiership game</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Sandwich making: Exeter\'s Don Armand is tackled by Worcester\'s Ofa Fainga\'anuku and Mike Williams\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5d680d3a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E5AB500000578-360_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Sandwich making: Exeter\'s Don Armand is tackled by Worcester\'s Ofa Fainga\'anuku and Mike Williams</p> </div></div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"No cigar: Ryan Lamb of Worcester Warriors drops to his knees after coming close to a comeback victory\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5a090d17\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E622500000578-310_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">No cigar: Ryan Lamb of Worcester Warriors drops to his knees after coming close to a comeback victory</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But the home side, bottom of the table and facing relegation, battled brilliantly in the second half through tries by hooker Agustin Creevy and Lemi\'s second against another Yeandle try.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ryan Lamb kicked three penalties and two conversions as well while Steenson ended on 18 points by adding a penalty and five conversions to his touchdown.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602877/Wigan-36-14-London-Broncos-Warriors-bounce-fourth-straight-victory.html\"> Wigan 36-14 London Broncos: Warriors bounce back for fourth straight victory</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603298/Gloucester-17-18-Bath-Kingsholm-boils-two-red-four-yellow-cards.html\"> Gloucester 17-18 Bath: Kingsholm boils over after two red and five yellow cards</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602861/Sale-12-27-Harlequins-Sharks-outclassed-Salford-Quins-alive-play-hopes.html\"> Sale 12-27 Harlequins: Sharks outclassed in Salford as Quins keep alive play-off hopes</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2601052/Charlie-Hodgson-signs-Saracens-fly-half-insists-no-rush-hang-boots.html\"> Hodgson signs on with Saracens as fly-half insists he is in no rush to hang up his boots</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602065/Leicester-close-signing-Italy-international-Robert-Barbieri-Simon-Cohen-reveals-transfer-targets.html\"> Leicester close to signing Barbieri as Tigers CEO Cohen reveals Italian transfer targets</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Despite the Warriors\' late fightback, the relegation trapdoor now seems wide open and they must have been fearing the worst after just 24 minutes as Exeter strolled past some weak defence to rack up three tries and that 21-3 lead.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bonus points: David Lemi of Worcester Warriors celebrates his try against Exeter Chiefs\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5faa0d52\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DED5C00000578-374_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bonus points: David Lemi of Worcester Warriors celebrates his try against Exeter Chiefs</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Touchdown! Chris Pennell of Worcester Warriors crosses for a try in front of a home crowd\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-60030d57\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DED4F00000578-467_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Touchdown! Chris Pennell of Worcester Warriors crosses for a try in front of a home crowd</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Lewis raced over for the first after nine minutes as he nipped past home prop Ofa Fainga\'anuku to race to the line, with Pennell forlornly chasing.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Steenson converted but Lamb added Worcester\'s opening points with a 40-metre penalty.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Hill\'s try soon followed as he was put over from two metres by his fly-half after an initial charge from Fetu\'u Vainikolo, and with Steenson converting, Exeter\'s lead was stretched again.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It got worse for Worcester as Lamb missed another long-range attempt before Steenson rounded off another break into home territory for his own converted try.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Catch me if you can: Carl Rimmerbeaks away leaving Warriors in his wake\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-52b10d19\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E8D7E00000578-76_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Catch me if you can: Carl Rimmerbeaks away leaving Warriors in his wake</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Worcester defence was almost non-existent and, when they had some possession inside the opposition 22, the Chiefs stood strong. It seemed how many for the Chiefs.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But suddenly the game was on.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Worcester grabbed their first try when scrum-half Jonny Arr fed Pennell to score. Then wing Lemi kicked upfield from just inside his own half and followed up to beat wing Matt Jess for pace and grab the converted try.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pile driver: Sam Betty evades Exeter\'s Gareth Steensonto as the Warriors stage a thrilling comeback\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5c4c0d2f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DD64400000578-424_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pile driver: Sam Betty evades Exeter\'s Gareth Steensonto as the Warriors stage a thrilling comeback</p> </div></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Exeter dented the comeback, though, as Yeandle scored two tries either side of the break, both converted by Steenson, to put his side in command, the first of which also claimed the try bonus point.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But Worcester, to their credit, would not lay down.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Lamb booted a penalty just before Yeandle\'s second score.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Helping hand: Augustin Creevy of Worcester passes out of the tackle by Matt Jess of Exeter\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5ef00d4d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DEF2900000578-956_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Helping hand: Augustin Creevy of Worcester passes out of the tackle by Matt Jess of Exeter</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Creevy\'s 53rd-minute try, that his stand-off converted, plus Lemi\'s second on the left moments - all after Exeter replacement James Scaysbrook was sin-binned for pulling down a maul on his own line - gave the Warriors a try bonus point.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The momentum had switched and Worcester had Exeter on the rack even when they were back up to a full complement of players.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And, after Lamb\'s third penalty put Worcester within five points, the match came down to one cross kick by the fly-half which wing Josh Drauniniu failed to grab with the line at his mercy to finish a great game.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602877/Wigan-36-14-London-Broncos-Warriors-bounce-fourth-straight-victory.html\"> Wigan 36-14 London Broncos: Warriors bounce back for fourth straight victory</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603298/Gloucester-17-18-Bath-Kingsholm-boils-two-red-four-yellow-cards.html\"> Gloucester 17-18 Bath: Kingsholm boils over after two red and five yellow cards</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602861/Sale-12-27-Harlequins-Sharks-outclassed-Salford-Quins-alive-play-hopes.html\"> Sale 12-27 Harlequins: Sharks outclassed in Salford as Quins keep alive play-off hopes</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2601052/Charlie-Hodgson-signs-Saracens-fly-half-insists-no-rush-hang-boots.html\"> Hodgson signs on with Saracens as fly-half insists he is in no rush to hang up his boots</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602065/Leicester-close-signing-Italy-international-Robert-Barbieri-Simon-Cohen-reveals-transfer-targets.html\"> Leicester close to signing Barbieri as Tigers CEO Cohen reveals Italian transfer targets</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603285/Worcester-33-38-Exeter-match-report-Chiefs-weather-late-Warriors-fightback-bonus-point-win.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603285/Worcester-33-38-Exeter-match-report-Chiefs-weather-late-Warriors-fightback-bonus-point-win.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Worcester 33-38 Exeter: Chiefs weather late Warriors fightback to edge bonus point win\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603285/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E5C7600000578-857_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:43','2014-04-12 20:33:55'),(11,'880b8e9fe4954526c51a13e23f562c4074c0a07b5b518ccb08a43123fbb44147','dailymail',NULL,'Catalan 42-20 Widnes: Whitehead scores hat-trick as dominant Dragons slay Vikings','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/article-2603277/Catalan-42-20-Widnes-Whitehead-scores-hat-trick-dominant-Dragons-slay-Vikings.html','  Published: 13:29 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 13:29 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments  Catalan Dragons maintained their mid-season return to form with a resounding 42-20 win over Widnes as Elliott Whitehead registered his first hat-trick for the club. Ben Pomeroy and Vincent Duport also crossed for two tries each in the Super League rout, which was on the cards from the early stages. The home side almost scored after 60 seconds and would have but for a last-gasp tackle by Paddy Flynn on Morgan Escare.  Rout: Elliott Whitehead crossed for his first try triple for Catalan Dragons in their flogging of Widnes    The Dragons did open the scoring on five minutes though, Eloi Pelissier scooting away from the acting half and offloading to Pomeroy who barged his way over to score. Thomas Bosc missed the goal. Five minutes later, and Catalan were in again, Jason Baitieri and Olivier Elima doing the hard work in the middle before Eloi Pelissier and Leon Pryce combined to send Whitehead in for his first try of the afternoon. Bosc again missed the conversion. Catalan scored their third and best try of the match in the 17th minute, Escare and Daryl Millard combining to go the length of the field as they returned Kevin Brown\'s kick down-field. Bosc this time added the goal to take the score to 14-0.   More... Leeds legend Peacock \'humbled\' by crowd reaction to 500th career appearance Castleford 28-30 St Helens: Saints skipper Wellens sparks comeback on record-breaking appearance Warrington 12-25 Hull: Wolves suffer third home defeat of the season as KR prove too strong Leeds 42-6 Wakefield: Peacock marks landmark night with try as hosts run riot Wigan 36-14 London Broncos: Warriors bounce back for fourth straight victory Bradford 24-38 Salford: Harris gets off to winning start against struggling Bulls Dominant: Dragons\' Australian centre Ben Pomeroy scored two tries in his side\'s convincing victory  Widnes came back at Catalan, scoring their first try when Declan Hulme and Rhys Hanbury combined to send in Paddy Flynn to score. Danny Tickle missed the goal. Widnes narrowed the gap to four points as Jack Owens pounced on Brown\'s kick to the right, with Tickle\'s conversion narrowing the Catalan lead. Catalan coach Laurent Frayssinous looked furious as he marched pitch-side to blast his troops. That appeared to work as Whitehead latched onto Pryce\'s pass to scored his second try of the afternoon. Bosc missed another shot at goal. After half-time, the home side ran riot, Duport scoring seven minutes in after a long pass from Whitehead. Bosc again missed the goal. Pomeroy scored his second 10 minutes later, powering his way over from short range from Escare\'s pass. Escare missed the goal. From the restart, Dragons pounced on a Brown error, Whitehead picking up the loose ball and racing 40 metres to score under the posts. Bosc converted to take the scores to 32-10. With 14 minutes remaining, Widnes registered a consolation effort, Flynn offloading for Lloyd White to score in the corner. Tickle converted the goal.      Catalan quickly stamped their authority back on the game, Duport chasing his own kick through to score down the right. Escare converted to take the scores to 38-16. Catalan went back up the field and threw the ball around for fun, Millard the next scorer five minutes from time, Pryce and Garcia sending the winger in at the corner. Escare missed the conversion. Widnes were well beaten but had the final say on the scoreboard, Hep Cahill sending Owens in for his second try in the left corner, Tickle failing to add the touchline conversion.  More... Leeds legend Peacock \'humbled\' by crowd reaction to 500th career appearance Castleford 28-30 St Helens: Saints skipper Wellens sparks comeback on record-breaking appearance Warrington 12-25 Hull: Wolves suffer third home defeat of the season as KR prove too strong Leeds 42-6 Wakefield: Peacock marks landmark night with try as hosts run riot Wigan 36-14 London Broncos: Warriors bounce back for fourth straight victory Bradford 24-38 Salford: Harris gets off to winning start against struggling Bulls   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 13:29 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 13:29 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/article-2603277/Catalan-42-20-Widnes-Whitehead-scores-hat-trick-dominant-Dragons-slay-Vikings.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/article-2603277/Catalan-42-20-Widnes-Whitehead-scores-hat-trick-dominant-Dragons-slay-Vikings.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Catalan 42-20 Widnes: Whitehead scores hat-trick as dominant Dragons slay Vikings\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2603277/Catalan-42-20-Widnes-Whitehead-scores-hat-trick-dominant-Dragons-slay-Vikings.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Catalan Dragons maintained their mid-season return to form with a resounding 42-20 win over Widnes as Elliott Whitehead registered his first hat-trick for the club.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ben Pomeroy and Vincent Duport also crossed for two tries each in the Super League rout, which was on the cards from the early stages.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The home side almost scored after 60 seconds and would have but for a last-gasp tackle by Paddy Flynn on Morgan Escare.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rout: Elliott Whitehead crossed for his first try triple for Catalan Dragons in their flogging of Widnes\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"385\" id=\"i-aad70e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603277-1D0F15EE00000578-513_634x385.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rout: Elliott Whitehead crossed for his first try triple for Catalan Dragons in their flogging of Widnes<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Dragons did open the scoring on five minutes though, Eloi Pelissier scooting away from the acting half and offloading to Pomeroy who barged his way over to score. Thomas Bosc missed the goal.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Five minutes later, and Catalan were in again, Jason Baitieri and Olivier Elima doing the hard work in the middle before Eloi Pelissier and Leon Pryce combined to send Whitehead in for his first try of the afternoon. Bosc again missed the conversion.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Catalan scored their third and best try of the match in the 17th minute, Escare and Daryl Millard combining to go the length of the field as they returned Kevin Brown\'s kick down-field. Bosc this time added the goal to take the score to 14-0.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport