t><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Widnes narrowed the gap to four points as Jack Owens pounced on Brown\'s kick to the right, with Tickle\'s conversion narrowing the Catalan lead.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Catalan coach Laurent Frayssinous looked furious as he marched pitch-side to blast his troops. That appeared to work as Whitehead latched onto Pryce\'s pass to scored his second try of the afternoon. Bosc missed another shot at goal.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">After half-time, the home side ran riot, Duport scoring seven minutes in after a long pass from Whitehead. Bosc again missed the goal.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Pomeroy scored his second 10 minutes later, powering his way over from short range from Escare\'s pass. Escare missed the goal.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">From the restart, Dragons pounced on a Brown error, Whitehead picking up the loose ball and racing 40 metres to score under the posts. Bosc converted to take the scores to 32-10.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With 14 minutes remaining, Widnes registered a consolation effort, Flynn offloading for Lloyd White to score in the corner. Tickle converted the goal.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Catalan quickly stamped their authority back on the game, Duport chasing his own kick through to score down the right. Escare converted to take the scores to 38-16.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Catalan went back up the field and threw the ball around for fun, Millard the next scorer five minutes from time, Pryce and Garcia sending the winger in at the corner. Escare missed the conversion.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Widnes were well beaten but had the final say on the scoreboard, Hep Cahill sending Owens in for his second try in the left corner, Tickle failing to add the touchline conversion.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602937/Jamie-Peacock-humbled-crowd-reaction-500th-career-appearance.html\"> Leeds legend Peacock \'humbled\' by crowd reaction to 500th career appearance</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602855/Castleford-28-30-St-Helens-Saints-skipper-Paul-Wellens-sparks-comeback-record-breaking-appearance.html\"> Castleford 28-30 St Helens: Saints skipper Wellens sparks comeback on record-breaking appearance</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602875/Warrington-12-25-Hull-Wolves-suffer-home-defeat-season-KR-prove-strong.html\"> Warrington 12-25 Hull: Wolves suffer third home defeat of the season as KR prove too strong</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602847/Leeds-42-6-Wakefield-Peacock-marks-landmark-night-try-hosts-run-riot.html\"> Leeds 42-6 Wakefield: Peacock marks landmark night with try as hosts run riot</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602877/Wigan-36-14-London-Broncos-Warriors-bounce-fourth-straight-victory.html\"> Wigan 36-14 London Broncos: Warriors bounce back for fourth straight victory</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyleague/article-2602876/Bradford-24-38-Salford-Harris-gets-winning-start-against-struggling-Bulls.html\"> Bradford 24-38 Salford: Harris gets off to winning start against struggling Bulls</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/article-2603277/Catalan-42-20-Widnes-Whitehead-scores-hat-trick-dominant-Dragons-slay-Vikings.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/article-2603277/Catalan-42-20-Widnes-Whitehead-scores-hat-trick-dominant-Dragons-slay-Vikings.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Catalan 42-20 Widnes: Whitehead scores hat-trick as dominant Dragons slay Vikings\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/article-2603277/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603277-1D0F15EE00000578-359_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:43','2014-04-12 20:29:16'),(12,'2dab1a51863c440aaecebd9d42c21312171800c92305a85ce5a966425e1c8f5d','dailymail',NULL,'Rock legend Robert Plant joins Wolves\' promotion party after victory over Crewe','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603308/Rock-legend-Robert-Plant-joins-Wolves-promotion-party-victory-Crewe.html','  Published: 13:28 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 13:28 EST, 12 April 2014 18 shares 2 View comments Former Led Zeppelin singer Robert Plant watched Wolves clinch promotion to the Championship with a 2-0 win at 10-man Crewe in Sky Bet League One. Kevin McDonald and Dave Edwards grabbed the decisive goals for Kenny Jackett\'s men. The game drifted away from Crewe in the closing stages of the first half with Chuks Aneke sent off moments after McDonald had opened the scoring.  Going up: Wolves celebrate promotion after a 2-0 win at Crewe Alexandra  Rock ans roll: Former lead singer of Led Zeppelin and Wolves fan Robert Plant (centre) celebrates promotion Second-placed Brentford slipped up as they went down 1-0 at Swindon, where Louis Thompson scored the only goal. Michael Smith had earlier missed a penalty for the Robins. The Bees still have a seven-point advantage over third-placed Leyton Orient but their frustration was compounded when Adam Forshaw was dismissed for two bookable offences. Orient moved into third on the back of a 5-1 thrashing of Gillingham at the Matchroom Stadium. David Mooney scored two for the east London team with Dean Cox, Kevin Lisbie and Chris Dagnall also on target before Craig Fagan hit a late Gills consolation. Peterborough, in the final play-off position, opened up a seven-point lead over the chasing pack with a 1-0 win over Coventry at London Road. Kgosi Ntlhe scored the only goal after just six minutes.  Stunned: Coventry City\'s Nathan Ecclestone misses a chance against Peterborough   On the ball: Peterborough United\'s Danny Swanson (left) challenges Coventry City\'s Mark Marshall Preston consolidated their position among the play-off places with a 6-1 hammering of struggling Carlisle, who slipped into the relegation places. Craig Davies scored a hat-trick in the final 33 minutes for North End after Stuart Beavon, Alan Browne and Lee Holmes had earlier found the net. Gary Madine scored Carlisle\'s reply. Notts County were the big movers at the bottom of the table, climbing three places to 20th and out of the relegation zone by coming from behind to beat Port Vale 4-2 at Meadow Lane. The Magpies fell behind after a Curtis Thompson own goal and Gavin Tomlin effort but Jimmy Spencer struck twice to level. Another two from Jamal Campbell-Ryce completed the comeback. Stevenage remained bottom as they lost 3-2 at home to Colchester. Freddie Sears struck twice either side of an Jabo Ibehre effort as Colchester recovered from conceding early to Michael Doughty. Luke Freeman scored a late consolation for the hosts. Shrewsbury slipped a place to 23rd with a 2-1 loss to improving Tranmere. Junior Brown scored the 85th-minute winner for the Wirral side after the Shrews\' Paul Parry had cancelled out Max Power\'s opener. Crawley won 2-0 at MK Dons with goals from Andy Drury and Michael Jones while Sam Baldock\'s penalty saw Bristol City win 1-0 at Walsall. The Saddlers had a spot-kick of their own but Simon Moore saved from Sam Mantom.    More... Burnley 0-1 Middlesbrough: Butterfield gives Clarets no chance of promotion party Spectator left with bloodied nose at Fulham game... after sitting in front of sign warning: \'Please be aware of flying balls\'   Share or comment on this article 18shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 13:28 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 13:28 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-callt