t the Sale lock wants a World Cup call-up from Lancaster</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\"> France scrum-half (and scourge of England) Yachvili reveals he will hang up his boots</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Centre Harry Trinder\'s 71st-minute try looked to have edged Gloucester home - fly-half Billy Twelvetrees chipped in with four penalties - while Bath captain Stuart Hooper scored a try and George Ford kicked two penalties before an incident-packed finale.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bath forwards Carl Fearns, Matt Garvey and Dave Attwood were all yellow-carded, meaning Bath played 30 minutes of the game a man down, while the game went to uncontested scrums shortly after Puafisi departed.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Tonga international Puafisi received a red card from referee Tim Wigglesworth for a dangerous high tackle on Bath full-back Nick Abendanon, then Wales international Knoyle was sent off after he threw punches at Bath number eight Leroy Houston.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Knoyle incident provided a spiteful end to a contest when neither side took a backward step, and Bath remain fourth going into next week\'s home appointment with relegation favourites Worcester.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Gloucester boss Nigel Davies made four changes from the side beaten by Amlin Challenge Cup quarter-final opponents Wasps last weekend, including number eight Gareth Evans replacing England international Ben Morgan, and Tindall returning in midfield.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bath, meanwhile, welcomed back Test props Paul James and David Wilson, with a solitary switch behind the scrum seeing Kyle Eastmond taking over from centre Gavin Henson.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wales hooker Richard Hibbard, one of Gloucester\'s major signings for next term, was among a bumper crowd that saw Twelvetrees kick his team into an early lead.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Trouble: A plastic bottle appears to be thrown in the direction of match officials as they make their way down the tunnel\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"440\" id=\"i-5b190d23\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0E956000000578-438_634x440.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Trouble: A plastic bottle appears to be thrown in the direction of match officials as they make their way down the tunnel</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Sin bin: Referee Tim Wigglesworth shows Huia Edmonds of Gloucester a yellow card during the Aviva Premiership match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-52080d0a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0EBB8800000578-35_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Sin bin: Referee Tim Wigglesworth shows Huia Edmonds of Gloucester a yellow card during the Aviva Premiership match</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The visitors continued to press following a Matt Banahan kick deep into Gloucester\'s 22, yet they were denied a try for wing Horacio Agulla - hat-trick hero of last Sunday\'s Amlin Challenge Cup quarter-final victory over Brive - when Wigglesworth ruled midfield obstruction.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And that was the cue for Gloucester to regroup as they responded impressively through two more Twelvetrees penalties during a three-minute spell that also saw Fearns sin-binned following a technical infringement.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bath only had themselves to blame as Wigglesworth punished their poor discipline - James proved a consistent transgressor - yet Ford\'s second penalty made it 9-6 as half-time approached.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It proved a false dawn from Bath\'s perspective, though, and Fearns\' fellow flanker Garvey was yellow-carded just before the break for a high tackle on Evans that could yet attract attention from the match citing commissioner.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Evans was forced off injured as a result of the challenge, and Morgan entered the action with Gloucester three points clear halfway through a typically feisty derby.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Boiling point: Fighting breaks out between the Gloucester and Bath players after Bath are awarded a penalty try\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"405\" id=\"i-5c7c0d30\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0EA10A00000578-912_634x405.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Boiling point: Fighting breaks out between the Gloucester and Bath players after Bath are awarded a penalty try</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rising above: Bath captain Stuart Hooper claims clean ball in the line-out\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"385\" id=\"i-5f7f0d54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0EBBA700000578-745_634x385.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rising above: Bath captain Stuart Hooper claims clean ball in the line-out</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Matters deteriorated early in the second period for Gloucester when Puafisi received his marching orders just eight minutes after going on as a replacement for Shaun Knight.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Abendanon was able to continue after treatment, but Bath then wiped out Gloucester\'s advantage when Hooper was driven over from a lineout to claim a try which had been on the cards once Puafisi was dismissed.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ford missed the conversion, and then the game went to an unedifying sight of uncontested scrums as Gloucester had run out of tighthead prop options.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But Bath could not make the game safe, and they completed a trio of yellow cards when Attwood was sin-binned for not rolling away after a tackle.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wigglesworth allowed neither side a chance to build momentum, yet Gloucester had Twelvetrees\' goalkicking to fall back on, and his fourth successful penalty edged the home team back in front before a dramatic finish unfolded that was littered with red and yellow cards.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Relief: George Ford and Peter Stringer of Bath celebrate at the final whistle\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"418\" id=\"i-5e5e0d48\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0EC7E100000578-973_634x418.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Relief: George Ford and Peter Stringer of Bath celebrate at the final whistle</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602908/Tim-Visser-targets-Scotlands-summer-tour-seven-month-absence.html\"> Edinburgh flyer Visser targets Scotland\'s summer tour after seven-month absence</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602735/Steve-Borthwicks-time-high-Saracens-lock-prepares-break-Premiership-appearance-record.html\"> Borthwick\'s all-time high as Saracens lock prepares to league break appearance record</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602861/Sale-12-27-Harlequins-Sharks-outclassed-Salford-Quins-alive-play-hopes.html\"> Sale 12-27 Harlequins: Sharks outclassed in Salford as Quins keep alive play-off hopes</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602584/Paterson-All-Black-qualified-Wales-Sharks-lock-wants-Lancaster-call.html\"> Paterson was a junior All Black and almost qualified for Wales but the Sale lock wants a World Cup call-up from Lancaster</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\"> France scrum-half (and scourge of England) Yachvili reveals he will hang up his boots</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603298/Gloucester-17-18-Bath-Kingsholm-boils-two-red-four-yellow-cards.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603298/Gloucester-17-18-Bath-Kingsholm-boils-two-red-four-yellow-cards.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Gloucester 17-18 Bath: Kingsholm boils over after two red and five yellow cards\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2603298/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603298-1D0F0E6800000578-816_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:45','2014-04-12 20:17:46'),(14,'e72105b973e596e9873bd4a8240de6e3e5f8c4b634ea61f391a6ccaa629d9605','dailymail',NULL,'Burnley 0-1 Middlesbrough: Butterfield gives Clarets no chance of promotion party','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603087/Burnley-0-1-Middlesbrough-Butterfield-gives-Clarets-no-chance-promotion-party.html','  Published: 11:10 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 12:48 EST, 12 April 2014 7 shares 3 View comments Burnley\'s Premier League party was put on hold after Jacob Butterfield\'s strike condemned the Clarets to a 1-0 defeat against Middlesbrough at Turf Moor as Derby beat Huddersfield. A win for Sean Dyche\'s side, and a defeat for the Rams, could have guaranteed automatic promotion back to the top flight for the first time since the 2009/10 season. But the Rams won comfortably against Huddersfield, while Burnley came unstuck against an in-form Boro side who have won now won four games on the spin. Both sides struggled to dominate the opening minutes but it was Burnley who looked the more threatening.  On the break: Jacob Butterfield scores for Middlesbrough against Burnley after a counter-attack by Lee Tomlin Upset: Butterfield wheels away after finding the net for Middlesbrough in their win at Turf Moor  Match factsBurnley: Heaton, Trippier, Mee, Jones, Duff, Shackell, Kightly (Wallace 80\'), Marney, Barnes, Ings, Arfield (Stanislas 80\')Subs: Wallace, Stanislas, Cisak, Edgar, Baird, Treacy, LongMiddlesbrough: Konstantopoulos, Adomah, Ledesma, Ayala, Chalobah, Woodgate, Whitehead, Leadbitter, Tomlin (Williams 82\'), Graham (Main 90\'), Butterfield (Varga 72\')Subs: Steele, Varga, Williams, Main, Morris, Jackson, AtkinsonGoal: ButterfieldBooked: Ayala, WhiteheadSent off: AyalaClick HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship Michael Kightly found space on the right early on before sending a teasing delivery towards Ashley Barnes but last-ditch defending denied the former Brighton man. That move sparked Dyche\'s men into life and they came close to breaking the deadlock in the 17th minute. Kieran Trippier burst down the right channel and produced a trademark inch-perfect delivery to Danny Ings but the striker was unable to hit the target with his left-footed volley. Despite the pressure, Aitor Karanka\'s men showed their attacking prowess in the 19th minute - Lee Tomlin finding space on the edge of the box before rifling an effort just wide of Tom Heaton\'s post. But moments later the Clarets thought they had broken the deadlock after Kightly\'s looping header beat Dimi Konstantopoulos but hit the bar, Barnes followed up but failed to hit the target.  Tight tussle: Burnley\'s Ashley Barnes (right) battles to dispossess Middlesbrough\'s Butterfield Spectacular: Ben Mee takes flight for a bicycle attempt while Danny Ings gets primed to head towards goal Pressing hard: Ings challenges Middlesbrough\'s Dean Whitehead for possession in the box    Much of the same continued and neat link-up play between Dean Marney and Ings presented the latter with a glorious chance for his 21st league goal of the season.However, determined defending from Nathaniel Chalobah somehow ensured the striker\'s effort trickled wide. Shortly after, Albert Adomah surged into the Burnley half and down the right flank and found Danny Graham just yards out - but his first-time volley flashed over the bar. After the interval, the hosts came out pressing and should have scored when Kightly weaved into the box and found Ings but Adomah somehow blocked his effort. But Butterfield sent the away crowd into ecstasy in the 51st minute. Tomlin carried the ball into the Burnley half and released Butterfield, who made no mistake to calmly slot his left-footed strike past Heaton. High hopes: Kieran Trippier\'s Clarets will have to wait to celebrate their likely promotion to the Premier League Denied: Boro keeper Dimi Konstantopoulos saves a shot from Burnley\'s Ashley Barnes Both ends: Goal stopper and scorer Konstantopoulos (right) and Butterfield embrace after the match   It was almost 2-0 four minutes later as Tomlin curled his effort wide but Burnley looked to respond and almost equalised on 72 minutes, Trippier again charging forward and finding Ings - the striker\'s snap-shot going wide to Dyche\'s despair. The hosts continued to press and came close again in the closing stages but Ings again failed to convert from Trippier\'s teasing cross. Konstantopoulos remained unflappable in the Boro goal and despite the dismissal of defender Daniel Ayala late on, they were not to be denied another impressive scalp.    More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article 7shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:10 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:48 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603087/Burnley-0-1-Middlesbrough-Butterfield-gives-Clarets-no-chance-promotion-party.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603087/Burnley-0-1-Middlesbrough-Butterfield-gives-Clarets-no-chance-promotion-party.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Burnley 0-1 Middlesbrough: Butterfield gives Clarets no chance of promotion party\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 7</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603087/Burnley-0-1-Middlesbrough-Butterfield-gives-Clarets-no-chance-promotion-party.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">3</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Burnley\'s Premier League party was put on hold after Jacob Butterfield\'s strike condemned the Clarets to a 1-0 defeat against Middlesbrough at Turf Moor as Derby beat Huddersfield.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A win for Sean Dyche\'s side, and a defeat for the Rams, could have guaranteed automatic promotion back to the top flight for the first time since the 2009/10 season.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But the Rams won comfortably against Huddersfield, while Burnley came unstuck against an in-form Boro side who have won now won four games on the spin.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Both sides struggled to dominate the opening minutes but it was Burnley who looked the more threatening.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the break: Jacob Butterfield scores for Middlesbrough against Burnley after a counter-attack by Lee Tomlin\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a8b30e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E1C0800000578-256_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the break: Jacob Butterfield scores for Middlesbrough against Burnley after a counter-attack by Lee Tomlin</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Upset: Butterfield wheels away after finding the net for Middlesbrough in their win at Turf Moor\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-aa390e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E599A00000578-866_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Upset: Butterfield wheels away after finding the net for Middlesbrough in their win at Turf Moor</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\">Match facts<br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Burnley:</b> Heaton, Trippier, Mee, Jones, Duff, Shackell, Kightly (Wallace 80\'), Marney, Barnes, Ings, Arfield (Stanislas 80\')<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Subs: Wallace, Stanislas, Cisak, Edgar, Baird, Treacy, Long</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Middlesbrough:</b> Konstantopoulos, Adomah, Ledesma, Ayala, Chalobah, Woodgate, Whitehead, Leadbitter, Tomlin (Williams 82\'), Graham (Main 90\'), Butterfield (Varga 72\')<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Subs: Steele, Varga, Williams, Main, Morris, Jackson, Atkinson</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Goal: Butterfield</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Booked: Ayala, Whitehead</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sent off: Ayala<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Michael Kightly found space on the right early on before sending a teasing delivery towards Ashley Barnes but last-ditch defending denied the former Brighton man.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">That move sparked Dyche\'s men into life and they came close to breaking the deadlock in the 17th minute.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Kieran Trippier burst down the right channel and produced a trademark inch-perfect delivery to Danny Ings but the striker was unable to hit the target with his left-footed volley.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Despite the pressure, Aitor Karanka\'s men showed their attacking prowess in the 19th minute - Lee Tomlin finding space on the edge of the box before rifling an effort just wide of Tom Heaton\'s post.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But moments later the Clarets thought they had broken the deadlock after Kightly\'s looping header beat Dimi Konstantopoulos but hit the bar, Barnes followed up but failed to hit the target.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tight tussle: Burnley\'s Ashley Barnes (right) battles to dispossess Middlesbrough\'s Butterfield\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"439\" id=\"i-aafc0e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E58BE00000578-108_634x439.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tight tussle: Burnley\'s Ashley Barnes (right) battles to dispossess Middlesbrough\'s Butterfield</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Spectacular: Ben Mee takes flight for a bicycle attempt while Danny Ings gets primed to head towards goal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"462\" id=\"i-a9390e6a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E9B3200000578-525_634x462.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Spectacular: Ben Mee takes flight for a bicycle attempt while Danny Ings gets primed to head towards goal</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pressing hard: Ings challenges Middlesbrough\'s Dean Whitehead for possession in the box\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"395\" id=\"i-a9e80e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E9F2800000578-312_634x395.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pressing hard: Ings challenges Middlesbrough\'s Dean Whitehead for possession in the box</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Much of the same continued and neat link-up play between Dean Marney and Ings presented the latter with a glorious chance for his 21st league goal of the season.<br/>However, determined defending from Nathaniel Chalobah somehow ensured the striker\'s effort trickled wide.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Shortly after, Albert Adomah surged into the Burnley half and down the right flank and found Danny Graham just yards out - but his first-time volley flashed over the bar.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">After the interval, the hosts came out pressing and should have scored when Kightly weaved into the box and found Ings but Adomah somehow blocked his effort.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But Butterfield sent the away crowd into ecstasy in the 51st minute. Tomlin carried the ball into the Burnley half and released Butterfield, who made no mistake to calmly slot his left-footed strike past Heaton.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"High hopes: Kieran Trippier\'s Clarets will have to wait to celebrate their likely promotion to the Premier League\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"449\" id=\"i-a9a50e75\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E574C00000578-564_634x449.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">High hopes: Kieran Trippier\'s Clarets will have to wait to celebrate their likely promotion to the Premier League</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Denied: Boro keeper Dimi Konstantopoulos saves a shot from Burnley\'s Ashley Barnes\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-a97b0e6a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E9D4200000578-543_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Denied: Boro keeper Dimi Konstantopoulos saves a shot from Burnley\'s Ashley Barnes</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Both ends: Goal stopper and scorer Konstantopoulos (right) and Butterfield embrace after the match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"394\" id=\"i-a89e0e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E9A1100000578-214_634x394.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Both ends: Goal stopper and scorer Konstantopoulos (right) and Butterfield embrace after the match</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It was almost 2-0 four minutes later as Tomlin curled his effort wide but Burnley looked to respond and almost equalised on 72 minutes, Trippier again charging forward and finding Ings - the striker\'s snap-shot going wide to Dyche\'s despair.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The hosts continued to press and came close again in the closing stages but Ings again failed to convert from Trippier\'s teasing cross.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Konstantopoulos remained unflappable in the Boro goal and despite the dismissal of defender Daniel Ayala late on, they were not to be denied another impressive scalp.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603087/Burnley-0-1-Middlesbrough-Butterfield-gives-Clarets-no-chance-promotion-party.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603087/Burnley-0-1-Middlesbrough-Butterfield-gives-Clarets-no-chance-promotion-party.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Burnley 0-1 Middlesbrough: Butterfield gives Clarets no chance of promotion party\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603087/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">7</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603087-1D0E1C0800000578-731_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:45','2014-04-12 19:48:17'),(15,'69eef1b946921502f5f688131db2a5a57f8aea555bc42ca363e5b3a7aa88fd95','dailymail',NULL,'Stoke 1-0 Newcastle: Potters laughing as Pieters\' cross-shot adds to Toon misery','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603081/Stoke-1-0-Newcastle-Potters-laughing-Pieters-cross-shot-adds-Toon-misery.html',' By Craig Hope Follow @@CraigHope01 Published: 10:59 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 12:36 EST, 12 April 2014 7 shares 27 View comments MATCH ZONE Click here for your ultimate stats package for the big game – including how Erik Pieters managed to find the net for Stoke On the evidence of this insipid performance, Newcastle have little left to play for this season - if the club\'s supporters had their way boss Alan Pardew would be fighting for his future. Fight, however, is something his team does not boast at present. As a consequence, for the first time this season the 2,900 travelling fans sounded their dissent in the direction of the manager, who was seated in the stands serving the sixth game of his seven-match touchline ban for headbutting Hull City\'s David Meyler. \'We want Pardew out\' was the audible accompaniment to the banners which read, \'No more excuses. No more lies. Pardew out\' and, quite charmingly, \'Pardew is a muppet\'. Pardew: We lack creative flair and ability in and around the box  Up for it: Erik Pieters celebrates after his cross found the net to give Stoke a 1-0 lead over Newcastle Totally meant it: Pieters is congratulated after his cross went over the head of Newcastle\'s Tim Krul Slow motion: Krul can only watch as the ball bounces off the far post and into the net for Stoke Hughes: I\'m pleased Erik Pieters got the headlines today  Match factsStoke (4-4-1-1): Begovic 6; Cameron 6.5, Shawcross 7, Wilson 6, Pieters 6.5; Ireland 5.5 (Adam 66, 6) Nzonzi 7, Whelan 6, Arnautovic 7.5; Odemwingie 6.5 (Walters 87, 6); Crouch 7Subs not used: Sorensen, Muniesa, Palacios, Guidetti, Wilkinson Goals: Pieters 42Booked: PietersNewcastle (3-5-2): Krul 5; S Taylor 6 (Yanga-Mbiwa 61, 5.5) Williamson 6, Coloccini 6; Anita 5.5, Gosling 6.5 (Ben Arfa 73, 5), Tiote 6, Gouffran 5, Dummett 7; Sh Ameobi 6, Cisse 5.5 (Armstrong 73, 6)Subs not used: Elliot, Haidara, Bigirimana, de Jong Booked: ColocciniRef: Mike Jones (Cheshire) Att: 27, 400MOM: Marko Arnautovic*Player ratings by CRAIG HOPE at the Britannia StadiumClick HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Premier League - plus your stats zone from the match Saturday\'s game was the first since the club\'s new managing director, Lee Charnley, delivered a 1,500-word statement which did nought to rally supporter enthusiasm. \'We will sign one or two players per year\' was the sorry soundbite soon seized upon by disgruntled followers whose club have not made a permanent addition since January of 2013. But the criticism of Pardew and calls for him to go have broken new ground, for until now he had played the role of master mediator between owner Mike Ashley and the Toon Army. \'Of course (I noticed the chants),\' Pardew said afterwards. \'(I\'ve had) Four defeats (in a row) as Newcastle manager. \'I think their frustration has boiled over a little bit and we need to settle it down. \'The best way to do that is to get a win and unfortunately it hasn\'t come. \'The only thing you can do is try to get a performance on the pitch which gives you a chance of winning and I thought we were close today. \'But we lack creative flair and a little bit of ability in and around the box.\' The goal which separated the sides arrived three minutes before the break, the nature of it entirely in keeping with the dearth of quality during the first half.  More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season? Newcastle fans unveil Pardew out banners ahead of kick-off at the Britannia Stadium  Danger man: Man of the match Marko Arnautovic wreaked havoc on the Newcastle defence Out of little: City\'s Dutch defender Pieters just before he unleashes the cross that wins the match Heads up: Newcastle\'s Mike Williamson\'s ducks down to Peter Crouch\'s raised boot Chance: Newcastle\'s Dutch midfielder Vurnon Anita (left) heads over the bar   Early dig: Newcastle fans hold a sign saying \'Pardew is a Muppet\' as the teams come out of the tunnel Good day out: Ryan Shawcross became the first player to play 200 Premier League games for the club Handful: Lanky frontman Crouch puts himself about in the box against Williamson Unleashed: Newcastle\'s Yoan Gouffran shoots as Glenn Whelan tries to shut him down  Erik Pieters sized a cross from the left, skewed his delivery and watched in glee as it sailed above and beyond Dutch compatriot Tim Krul. United had earlier been denied what looked a clear penalty when Geoff Cameron clumsily barged into Papiss Cisse. And Pardew, whose side are without a goal in six hours, went on: \'The goal was a bit of a fluke and the wind caught hold of it, which made it almost impossible for Tim to save. \'But we should have had a penalty and that was a big turning point for us. We need a goal and that would have been a nice opportunity.\' The concession was United\'s 12th since they last scored a league goal of their own and sparked the anti-Pardew chants.  Boost: Returning from injury, Krul saves a diving header from Stoke striker Peter Crouch   Under fire: The pressure is now heaped on Newcastle boss Alan Pardew after the side fourth loss in a row   No uncertain terms: Some travelling Toon fans made their feelings about Pardew clear with banners   Can\'t look up: Newcastle\'s Adam Armstrong (left) and Krul walk off the pitch heads bowed after the loss  Stoke\'s victory, meanwhile, takes them to within three points of their ninth-placed opponents. Austrian wideman Marko Arnautovic terrorised the visitors throughout, twice serving up crosses for Peter Crouch who saw his headers denied a goal - first by a post and then the gloves of Krul. Potters boss Mark Hughes said: \'I thought he (Arnautovic) was excellent. We were able to get him in situations where he can show his talent. \'In terms of his ability to cross the ball on the run he is one of the best I\'ve seen do that, it\'s a real quality not too many players have.\'    More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season? Newcastle fans unveil Pardew out banners ahead of kick-off at the Britannia Stadium  Share or comment on this article 7shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Craig+Hope\" rel=\"nofollow\">Craig Hope</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@CraigHope01\">Follow @@CraigHope01</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 10:59 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:36 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603081/Stoke-1-0-Newcastle-Potters-laughing-Pieters-cross-shot-adds-Toon-misery.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603081/Stoke-1-0-Newcastle-Potters-laughing-Pieters-cross-shot-adds-Toon-misery.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Stoke 1-0 Newcastle: Potters laughing as Pieters\' cross-shot adds to insipid Toon misery and fans call for Pardew to be axed\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 7</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603081/Stoke-1-0-Newcastle-Potters-laughing-Pieters-cross-shot-adds-Toon-misery.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">27</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>MATCH ZONE</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#s2013-c8-m695236\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> for your ultimate stats package for the big game – including how Erik Pieters managed to find the net for Stoke<br/></font></p><div class=\"clear\"> </div> <img alt=\"Fortunate: Erik Pieters received the ball from Marko Arnautovic and his shot went in off the post\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"191\" id=\"i-a8840e6b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E068A00000578-638_296x191.jpg\" width=\"296\"/> </div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">On the evidence of this insipid performance, Newcastle have little left to play for this season - if the club\'s supporters had their way boss Alan Pardew would be fighting for his future.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Fight, however, is something his team does not boast at present. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">As a consequence, for the first time this season the 2,900 travelling fans sounded their dissent in the direction of the manager, who was seated in the stands serving the sixth game of his seven-match touchline ban for headbutting Hull City\'s David Meyler.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'We want Pardew out\' was the audible accompaniment to the banners which read, \'No more excuses. No more lies. Pardew out\' and, quite charmingly, \'Pardew is a muppet\'.</font>  <br/></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3461274877001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Pardew: We lack creative flair and ability in and around the box</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/video-undefined-1D0EC19100000578-154_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Up for it: Erik Pieters celebrates after his cross found the net to give Stoke a 1-0 lead over Newcastle\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"477\" id=\"i-aa830e7e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0DE54F00000578-922_634x477.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Up for it: Erik Pieters celebrates after his cross found the net to give Stoke a 1-0 lead over Newcastle</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Totally meant it: Pieters is congratulated after his cross went over the head of Newcastle\'s Tim Krul\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"388\" id=\"i-aa980e83\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0DE80D00000578-758_634x388.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Totally meant it: Pieters is congratulated after his cross went over the head of Newcastle\'s Tim Krul</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Slow motion: Krul can only watch as the ball bounces off the far post and into the net for Stoke\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"406\" id=\"i-8ff40e10\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0DF7C600000578-5_634x406.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Slow motion: Krul can only watch as the ball bounces off the far post and into the net for Stoke</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3461286738001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Hughes: I\'m pleased Erik Pieters got the headlines today</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/video-undefined-1D0ED2D600000578-317_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Match facts</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Stoke (4-4-1-1):</b> Begovic 6; Cameron 6.5, Shawcross 7, Wilson 6, Pieters 6.5; Ireland 5.5 (Adam 66, 6) Nzonzi 7, Whelan 6, Arnautovic 7.5; Odemwingie 6.5 (Walters 87, 6); Crouch 7<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Subs not used: Sorensen, Muniesa, Palacios, Guidetti, Wilkinson <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Goals: Pieters 42<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Booked: Pieters<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Newcastle (3-5-2):</b> Krul 5; S Taylor 6 (Yanga-Mbiwa 61, 5.5) Williamson 6, Coloccini 6; Anita 5.5, Gosling 6.5 (Ben Arfa 73, 5), Tiote 6, Gouffran 5, Dummett 7; Sh Ameobi 6, Cisse 5.5 (Armstrong 73, 6)<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Subs not used: Elliot, Haidara, Bigirimana, de Jong <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Booked: Coloccini<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Ref: Mike Jones (Cheshire) <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Att: 27, 400<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">MOM: Marko Arnautovic<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">*Player ratings by CRAIG HOPE at the Britannia</span> Stadium<br/></font></p><ul><li><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Premier League - plus your stats zone from the match<br/></a></font></li></ul></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Saturday\'s game was the first since the club\'s new managing director, Lee Charnley, delivered a 1,500-word statement which did nought to rally supporter enthusiasm. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'We will sign one or two players per year\' was the sorry soundbite soon seized upon by disgruntled followers whose club have not made a permanent addition since January of 2013.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But the criticism of Pardew and calls for him to go have broken new ground, for until now he had played the role of master mediator between owner Mike Ashley and the Toon Army.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Of course (I noticed the chants),\' Pardew said afterwards. \'(I\'ve had) Four defeats (in a row) as Newcastle manager.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I think their frustration has boiled over a little bit and we need to settle it down.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'The best way to do that is to get a win and unfortunately it hasn\'t come.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'The only thing you can do is try to get a performance on the pitch which gives you a chance of winning and I thought we were close today.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'But we lack creative flair and a little bit of ability in and around the box.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The goal which separated the sides arrived three minutes before the break, the nature of it entirely in keeping with the dearth of quality during the first half. </font></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2555289/Premier-League-team-news-stats-February-11-12.html\"> All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html\"> Newcastle fans unveil Pardew out banners ahead of kick-off at the Britannia Stadium</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Danger man: Man of the match Marko Arnautovic wreaked havoc on the Newcastle defence\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a9e40e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E5B3E00000578-915_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Danger man: Man of the match Marko Arnautovic wreaked havoc on the Newcastle defence</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Out of little: City\'s Dutch defender Pieters just before he unleashes the cross that wins the match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"434\" id=\"i-a6b30e55\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E060900000578-825_634x434.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Out of little: City\'s Dutch defender Pieters just before he unleashes the cross that wins the match</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Heads up: Newcastle\'s Mike Williamson\'s ducks down to Peter Crouch\'s raised boot\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"485\" id=\"i-ab580e85\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0DF1AE00000578-732_634x485.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Heads up: Newcastle\'s Mike Williamson\'s ducks down to Peter Crouch\'s raised boot</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Chance: Newcastle\'s Dutch midfielder Vurnon Anita (left) heads over the bar\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"399\" id=\"i-aba90e8d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E7ACC00000578-428_634x399.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Chance: Newcastle\'s Dutch midfielder Vurnon Anita (left) heads over the bar</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Early dig: Newcastle fans hold a sign saying \'Pardew is a Muppet\' as the teams come out of the tunnel\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"399\" id=\"i-a8d00e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0DD21900000578-657_634x399.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Early dig: Newcastle fans hold a sign saying \'Pardew is a Muppet\' as the teams come out of the tunnel</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Good day out: Ryan Shawcross became the first player to play 200 Premier League games for the club\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"478\" id=\"i-a9060e73\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E559A00000578-259_634x478.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Good day out: Ryan Shawcross became the first player to play 200 Premier League games for the club</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Handful: Lanky frontman Crouch puts himself about in the box against Williamson\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"403\" id=\"i-a5d50e49\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E050200000578-690_634x403.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Handful: Lanky frontman Crouch puts himself about in the box against Williamson</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Unleashed: Newcastle\'s Yoan Gouffran shoots as Glenn Whelan tries to shut him down\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"432\" id=\"i-a9e80e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E39BB00000578-733_634x432.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Unleashed: Newcastle\'s Yoan Gouffran shoots as Glenn Whelan tries to shut him down</p> </div><p> </p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Erik Pieters sized a cross from the left, skewed his delivery and watched in glee as it sailed above and beyond Dutch compatriot Tim Krul.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">United had earlier been denied what looked a clear penalty when Geoff Cameron clumsily barged into Papiss Cisse.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And Pardew, whose side are without a goal in six hours, went on: \'The goal was a bit of a fluke and the wind caught hold of it, which made it almost impossible for Tim to save.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'But we should have had a penalty and that was a big turning point for us. We need a goal and that would have been a nice opportunity.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The concession was United\'s 12th since they last scored a league goal of their own and sparked the anti-Pardew chants.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Boost: Returning from injury, Krul saves a diving header from Stoke striker Peter Crouch\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"434\" id=\"i-a72a0e56\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E120F00000578-411_634x434.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Boost: Returning from injury, Krul saves a diving header from Stoke striker Peter Crouch</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Under fire: The pressure is now heaped on Newcastle boss Alan Pardew after the side fourth loss in a row\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a8250e5f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E3C4300000578-286_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Under fire: The pressure is now heaped on Newcastle boss Alan Pardew after the side fourth loss in a row</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"No uncertain terms: Some travelling Toon fans made their feelings about Pardew clear with banners\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"409\" id=\"i-9cc90e43\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0DA77D00000578-44_634x409.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">No uncertain terms: Some travelling Toon fans made their feelings about Pardew clear with banners</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Can\'t look up: Newcastle\'s Adam Armstrong (left) and Krul walk off the pitch heads bowed after the loss\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"430\" id=\"i-a94e0e66\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0E6AA600000578-113_634x430.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Can\'t look up: Newcastle\'s Adam Armstrong (left) and Krul walk off the pitch heads bowed after the loss</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Stoke\'s victory, meanwhile, takes them to within three points of their ninth-placed opponents. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Austrian wideman Marko Arnautovic terrorised the visitors throughout, twice serving up crosses for Peter Crouch who saw his headers denied a goal - first by a post and then the gloves of Krul.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Potters boss Mark Hughes said: \'I thought he (Arnautovic) was excellent. We were able to get him in situations where he can show his talent.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'In terms of his ability to cross the ball on the run he is one of the best I\'ve seen do that, it\'s a real quality not too many players have.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"><div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"sport item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"519px\" marginheight=\"0px\" marginwidth=\"0px\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"http://www.eplayer.performgroup.com/DailyMailWidget/pID/1g604t4kq6fyo1wo49pqf3lf8h/chID/2E169DC069D84610A298598B2B00F561/version/Stoke\" style=\"margin-left: 41px\" width=\"225px\"></iframe> </div> </div> <br/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"><div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"sport item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"519px\" marginheight=\"0px\" marginwidth=\"0px\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"http://www.eplayer.performgroup.com/DailyMailWidget/pID/1cetnzphctg3l12jp77bwrt48m/chID/31864B72927B47E5BE1754870584B713/version/Newcastle\" style=\"margin-left: 41px\" width=\"225px\"></iframe> </div> </div> <br/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2555289/Premier-League-team-news-stats-February-11-12.html\"> All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html\"> Newcastle fans unveil Pardew out banners ahead of kick-off at the Britannia Stadium</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603081/Stoke-1-0-Newcastle-Potters-laughing-Pieters-cross-shot-adds-Toon-misery.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603081/Stoke-1-0-Newcastle-Potters-laughing-Pieters-cross-shot-adds-Toon-misery.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Stoke 1-0 Newcastle: Potters laughing as Pieters\' cross-shot adds to insipid Toon misery and fans call for Pardew to be axed\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603081/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">7</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603081-1D0DE80D00000578-950_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:46','2014-04-12 19:36:06'),(16,'6aa5f678d03e5da13d23d257d3be50d717798ecc850436b235d371c219931e1e','dailymail',NULL,'Yeovil 1-1 Bournemouth: Deadlock no good for Glovers\' relegation battle or Cherries\' play-off push as Fraser cancels out Moore','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html','  Published: 11:31 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 12:34 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments  A freak second-half goal from Ryan Fraser spared the Cherries\' blushes, cancelling out Kieffer Moore\'s opener. Hot on the heels of their rivals, the in-form visitors made the 48-mile trip to Huish Park two points outside the Sky Bet Championship top six and came up against a side they had beaten eight times in their last 10 meetings. Cherries winger Matt Ritchie scored twice inside the opening 20 minutes to inspire his side to victory against Reading on Tuesday, and the 24-year-old should have notched another early opener on two minutes but blazed Lewis Grabban\'s cross over the bar. However, it was Yeovil - who came into the match six points from safety - that shaded an open first half and nearly snatched an early lead when Joe Edwards evaded Ian Harte and pulled the back to James Hayter, but the ex-Bournemouth striker fluffed his lines.  Breakthrough: Yeovil\'s Kieffer Moore celebrates opening the scoring against Bournemouth at Huish Park Blast: Moore drives his right-footed shot goalward as the Glovers take the lead Elated: The Yeovil players in raptures after Moore found the net but didn\'t last and they remain second bottom  Match factsYeovil Town: Stech, Ayling, McAllister, Palazuelos, Webster, Duffy, Lawrence, Edwards, Hayter (Hoskins 91\'), Moore, RallsSubs: Dawson, Hoskins, Lanzoni, Davis, Grant, Dunn, Ofori-TwumasiGoal: MooreBooked: McAllisterAFC Bournemouth: Camp, Francis, Harte (Smith 57\'), O\'Kane, Elphick, Cook, Ritchie, Surman, Kermorgant, Grabban (Pitman 68\'), Fraser (Rantie 80\')Subs: Allsop, Pugh, MacDonald, Ward, RantieGoal: FraserBooked: Francis, CookClick HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship The visitors had found the net 14 times in their previous five matches before arriving in Somerset, and their attacking prowess was evident when Fraser, who replaced Marc Pugh in Eddie Howe\'s only change from Tuesday\'s win, called Marek Stech into action with a low shot. With the Yeovil fans and players growing increasingly irate at referee Robert Madley, their anger turned to joy on 25 minutes when former Dorchester striker Moore threatened to derail Bournemouth\'s late promotion charge. A seemingly routine free-kick into the Cherries box by Jamie McAllister was headed clear but fell to Moore at the edge of the box, and the youngster rifled an unstoppable volley into the top corner. Bournemouth responded well and ended the first half strongly with the lively Grabban spurning two good chances before the break, twice firing wide after good work from Ritchie and strike partner Yann Kermorgant.   Got the edge: Cherries\' Ryan Fraser (right) finds the net for the Cherries\' equaliser Saving blushes: Fraser (left) and teammates celebrate his freak goal that made the score 1-1  Shortly after half-time, the visitors thought they should have had a penalty after Byron Webster appeared to handle in the area, but moments later drew level through a freak goal. With the Cherries turning the screw, Webster attempted to clear from inside his own box but the ball cannoned into Fraser and looped over Stech and into the net. With four games now left to decide their fate, Yeovil responded well to the setback as Moore dragged a shot narrowly wide before Bournemouth winger Ritchie threatened to complete a quickfire comeback for the visitors. Eyeing a sixth successive league win, the Cherries poured forward in search for a late winner but almost left themselves open at the back when Manchester United loanee Tom Lawrence weaved his way into the box, but his curling shot crept wide as the match gradually petered out.   More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:31 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:34 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Yeovil 1-1 Bournemouth: Deadlock no good for Glovers\' relegation battle or Cherries\' play-off push as Fraser cancels out Moore\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">A freak second-half goal from Ryan Fraser spared the Cherries\' blushes, cancelling out Kieffer Moore\'s opener.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Hot on the heels of their rivals, the in-form visitors made the 48-mile trip to Huish Park two points outside the Sky Bet Championship top six and came up against a side they had beaten eight times in their last 10 meetings.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Cherries winger Matt Ritchie scored twice inside the opening 20 minutes to inspire his side to victory against Reading on Tuesday, and the 24-year-old should have notched another early opener on two minutes but blazed Lewis Grabban\'s cross over the bar.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">However, it was Yeovil - who came into the match six points from safety - that shaded an open first half and nearly snatched an early lead when Joe Edwards evaded Ian Harte and pulled the back to James Hayter, but the ex-Bournemouth striker fluffed his lines.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Breakthrough: Yeovil\'s Kieffer Moore celebrates opening the scoring against Bournemouth at Huish Park\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"434\" id=\"i-aac10e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603091-1D0DF75B00000578-459_634x434.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Breakthrough: Yeovil\'s Kieffer Moore celebrates opening the scoring against Bournemouth at Huish Park</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Blast: Moore drives his right-footed shot goalward as the Glovers take the lead\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-abbf0e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603091-1D0DF7AF00000578-421_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Blast: Moore drives his right-footed shot goalward as the Glovers take the lead</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Elated: The Yeovil players in raptures after Moore found the net but didn\'t last and they remain second bottom\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-aa740e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603091-1D0EAE8000000578-866_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Elated: The Yeovil players in raptures after Moore found the net but didn\'t last and they remain second bottom</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\">Match facts<br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Yeovil Town:</b> Stech, Ayling, McAllister, Palazuelos, Webster, Duffy, Lawrence, Edwards, Hayter (Hoskins 91\'), Moore, Ralls<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Subs: Dawson, Hoskins, Lanzoni, Davis, Grant, Dunn, Ofori-Twumasi</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Goal: Moore</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Booked: McAllister<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>AFC Bournemouth:</b> Camp, Francis, Harte (Smith 57\'), O\'Kane, Elphick, Cook, Ritchie, Surman, Kermorgant, Grabban (Pitman 68\'), Fraser (Rantie 80\')<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Subs: Allsop, Pugh, MacDonald, Ward, Rantie</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Goal: Fraser</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Booked: Francis, Cook<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The visitors had found the net 14 times in their previous five matches before arriving in Somerset, and their attacking prowess was evident when Fraser, who replaced Marc Pugh in Eddie Howe\'s only change from Tuesday\'s win, called Marek Stech into action with a low shot.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With the Yeovil fans and players growing increasingly irate at referee Robert Madley, their anger turned to joy on 25 minutes when former Dorchester striker Moore threatened to derail Bournemouth\'s late promotion charge.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">A seemingly routine free-kick into the Cherries box by Jamie McAllister was headed clear but fell to Moore at the edge of the box, and the youngster rifled an unstoppable volley into the top corner.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Bournemouth responded well and ended the first half strongly with the lively Grabban spurning two good chances before the break, twice firing wide after good work from Ritchie and strike partner <br/>Yann Kermorgant.</font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Got the edge: Cherries\' Ryan Fraser (right) finds the net for the Cherries\' equaliser\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"455\" id=\"i-a8240e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603091-1D0E1E3200000578-365_634x455.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Got the edge: Cherries\' Ryan Fraser (right) finds the net for the Cherries\' equaliser</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Saving blushes: Fraser (left) and teammates celebrate his freak goal that made the score 1-1\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a6390e4a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603091-1D0E116400000578-713_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Saving blushes: Fraser (left) and teammates celebrate his freak goal that made the score 1-1</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Shortly after half-time, the visitors thought they should have had a penalty after Byron Webster appeared to handle in the area, but moments later drew level through a freak goal.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With the Cherries turning the screw, Webster attempted to clear from inside his own box but the ball cannoned into Fraser and looped over Stech and into the net.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With four games now left to decide their fate, Yeovil responded well to the setback as Moore dragged a shot narrowly wide before Bournemouth winger Ritchie threatened to complete a quickfire comeback for the visitors.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Eyeing a sixth successive league win, the Cherries poured forward in search for a late winner but almost left themselves open at the back when Manchester United loanee Tom Lawrence weaved his way into the box, but his curling shot crept wide as the match gradually petered out.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Yeovil 1-1 Bournemouth: Deadlock no good for Glovers\' relegation battle or Cherries\' play-off push as Fraser cancels out Moore\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603091/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603091-1D0DF75B00000578-96_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:46','2014-04-12 19:34:44'),(17,'b257552642eb6987d34f0875bfff68727f26beab435f5340e4d3bc01cf53ab34','dailymail',NULL,'Newcastle fans unveil Pardew out banners ahead of kick-off at the Britannia Stadium','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html',' By Tom Sheen Follow @@Tom_Sheen Published: 09:56 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 12:23 EST, 12 April 2014 55 shares 48 View comments Newcastle boss Alan Pardew was feeling the heat before his team had even kicked-off after the club\'s fans unveiled banners opposing his management. Pardew, who is still serving a touchline ban for headbutting Hull\'s David Meyler, was greeted with one banner that said: \'No more lies or excuses. Pardew out\' and another that called him a \'muppet\'. Newcastle are sitting safely in mid-table but are enduring a miserable run of performances. Pardew: We lack creative flair and ability in and around the box  Pardew out: Newcastle fans unveiled banners in opposition to Alan Pardew\'s management against Stoke   Muppet: These fans also packed a homemade banner for Pardew  They have won just four of their last 15 matches, failing to score in 11 of those, serving up dross in the absence of star man Loic Remy. Since Newcastle beat Stoke 5-1 on Boxing Day, Newcastle have scored just two goals in eight matches at St James\' Park. They laboured to 1-0 victories against strugglers Aston Villa and Crystal Palace and have been well beaten by Manchester United, Tottenham and Everton in recent weeks. Speaking to the Newcastle Evening Chronicle ahead of the match against Stoke, Pardew said he was \'not enjoying\' the criticism that has come in the last couple of weeks.  Criticised: Alan Pardew - at St James\' Park last week - said he was \'not enjoying\' the criticism he was facing   Struggling: Newcastle have won just four of their last 15 matches going into today\'s game  \'I am not enjoying it – you do not want criticism,\' he said. \'However, you have to accept it, particularly in this job. I think you have to be resilient. It is a word I have been using with the players. \'We have lost a bit of resilience in our play. I cannot lose that otherwise I really am in trouble. I have to accept criticism which comes our way. I take it full on.\'  More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds Never forgotten: Hillsborough\'s 96 victims remembered up and down the country on 25th anniversary of disaster Pardew defiant as Newcastle boss insists he won\'t crumble in the firing line MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders    Share or comment on this article 55shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Tom+Sheen\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tom Sheen</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@Tom_Sheen\">Follow @@Tom_Sheen</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 09:56 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:23 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Newcastle fans unveil Pardew out banners ahead of kick-off at the Britannia Stadium\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 55</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">48</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Newcastle boss Alan Pardew was feeling the heat before his team had even kicked-off after the club\'s fans unveiled banners opposing his management.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pardew, who is still serving a touchline ban for headbutting Hull\'s David Meyler, was greeted with one banner that said: \'No more lies or excuses. Pardew out\' and another that called him a \'muppet\'.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Newcastle are sitting safely in mid-table but are enduring a miserable run of performances. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3461274877001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Pardew: We lack creative flair and ability in and around the box</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/video-undefined-1D0EC19100000578-154_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pardew out: Newcastle fans unveiled banners in opposition to Alan Pardew\'s management against Stoke\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-5da70d38\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DA77D00000578-330_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pardew out: Newcastle fans unveiled banners in opposition to Alan Pardew\'s management against Stoke</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Muppet: These fans also packed a homemade banner for Pardew\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-5db40d3e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0DA4D400000578-494_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Muppet: These fans also packed a homemade banner for Pardew</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They have won just four of their last 15 matches, failing to score in 11 of those, serving up dross in the absence of star man Loic Remy.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Since Newcastle beat Stoke 5-1 on Boxing Day, Newcastle have scored just two goals in eight matches at St James\' Park.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They laboured to 1-0 victories against strugglers Aston Villa and Crystal Palace and have been well beaten by Manchester United, Tottenham and Everton in recent weeks.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Speaking to the Newcastle Evening Chronicle ahead of the match against Stoke, Pardew said he was \'not enjoying\' the criticism that has come in the last couple of weeks.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Criticised: Alan Pardew - at St James\' Park last week - said he was \'not enjoying\' the criticism he was facing\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"459\" id=\"i-a0140e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603188-1CDBED8100000578-38_634x459.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Criticised: Alan Pardew - at St James\' Park last week - said he was \'not enjoying\' the criticism he was facing</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Struggling: Newcastle have won just four of their last 15 matches going into today\'s game\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"466\" id=\"i-ab5c0e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603188-1D0DA97F00000578-203_634x466.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Struggling: Newcastle have won just four of their last 15 matches going into today\'s game</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I am not enjoying it – you do not want criticism,\' he said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'However, you have to accept it, particularly in this job. I think you have to be resilient. It is a word I have been using with the players.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We have lost a bit of resilience in our play. I cannot lose that otherwise I really am in trouble. I have to accept criticism which comes our way. I take it full on.\'</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603141/Never-forgotten-Hillsboroughs-96-victims-remembered-country-25th-anniversary-disaster.html\"> Never forgotten: Hillsborough\'s 96 victims remembered up and down the country on 25th anniversary of disaster</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602461/Pardew-defiant-Newcastle-boss-insists-wont-crumble-firing-line.html\"> Pardew defiant as Newcastle boss insists he won\'t crumble in the firing line</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\"> From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603188/Newcastle-fans-unveil-Pardew-banners-ahead-kick-Britannia-Stadium.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Newcastle fans unveil Pardew out banners ahead of kick-off at the Britannia Stadium\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603188/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">55</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603188-1D0DA77D00000578-35_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:47','2014-04-12 19:23:16'),(18,'053c5575c54b1ec08a75ce37cda5c5d82fb872b815271b27e46ca2849c772dc9','dailymail',NULL,'Kompany limps out of training injured ahead of Man City\'s pivotal title clash with Liverpool after Richards collision','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603173/Kompany-limps-training-ahead-Man-Citys-pivotal-title-clash-Liverpool-Richards-collision.html',' By Dan Willis Follow @@danwillis23 Published: 09:55 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 12:00 EST, 12 April 2014 793 shares 163 View comments Manchester City\'s Vincent Kompany limped out of training on Saturday after a collision with team-mate Micah Richards, making him a serious doubt for the Premier League title showdown with Liverpool on Sunday. The City captain, widely acknowledged to be one of the best defenders in Europe, looked to have injured his knee after landing awkwardly and his absence would be a huge blow for Manuel Pellegrini\'s team. This is especially true given City are coming up against the Premier League\'s top scorers, with 90 goals, not to mention Liverpool\'s prolific strikeforce of Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge.  Crocked: Man City captain Vincent Kompany limps out of training after a collision with Micah Richards   Painful: Both Kompany (left) and Micah Richards lie on the floor after their mid-air collision in training Pellegrini: An excess of anxiety could mean more mistakes  The Uruguayan has already notched 29 Premier League this season, while Sturridge has 20, and they\'ll fancy their chances of adding to that should Kompany miss tomorrow\'s clash. Martin Demichelis would have been expected to line up alongside Kompany at the heart of the City defence. But should Kompany fail to recover, then either Joleon Lescott or Javi Garcia will most likely deputise.   More... LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title Liverpool boss Rodgers demands midfield dominance ahead of Premier League title decider against City Kompany won\'t be fazed by Liverpool as Man City aim to strike killer blow in Premier League title race at Anfield Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield? Liverpool vs Man City is THE match to decide destination of the Premier League title... but will it live up to these classics? Kompany full of confidence after victory over Saints ahead of Reds title clash  Up you come: Yaya Toure (right) helps Kompany up of the floor after the defender is injured in training   The incident on the training ground looked innocuous as Kompany and Richards challenged for a high ball, but the Belgian international looked to land awkwardly and was said to let out a loud cry in pain. His concerned team-mates were quick to rush to his aid as he clutched his left knee, with Yaya Toure helping the City captain up off the ground. Samir Nasri then helped Kompany off the training ground. Third-placed City are four points behind league leaders Liverpool with two games in hand. But were the Reds to win tomorrow, even victory in their two extra matches would still leave City a point behind Brendan Rodgers\' men.  In form: Daniel Sturridge (left) and Luis Suarez have been scoring freely for Liverpool this season Funny music video starring Kompany, Fellaini and Hazard    More... LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title Liverpool boss Rodgers demands midfield dominance ahead of Premier League title decider against City Kompany won\'t be fazed by Liverpool as Man City aim to strike killer blow in Premier League title race at Anfield Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield? Liverpool vs Man City is THE match to decide destination of the Premier League title... but will it live up to these classics? Kompany full of confidence after victory over Saints ahead of Reds title clash     Share or comment on this article 793shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Dan+Willis\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dan Willis</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@danwillis23\">Follow @@danwillis23</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 09:55 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:00 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\