ull of confidence after victory over Saints ahead of Reds title clash</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> <br/></font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603173/Kompany-limps-training-ahead-Man-Citys-pivotal-title-clash-Liverpool-Richards-collision.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603173/Kompany-limps-training-ahead-Man-Citys-pivotal-title-clash-Liverpool-Richards-collision.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Kompany limps out of training injured ahead of Man City\'s pivotal title clash with Liverpool after Richards collision\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603173/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">793</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603173-1D0D573700000578-638_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:47','2014-04-12 19:00:43'),(19,'8a8cfc458fce1a272d908a659e153fdc483be0219e3696cdcc372771da551560','dailymail',NULL,'Sheff Wed 3-3 Blackburn: Stuart Gray\'s men honour Hillsborough with late comeback','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html','  Published: 11:32 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 12:00 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments Sheffield Wednesday and Blackburn shared the points in a six-goal thriller at Hillsborough on a day when English football\'s biggest tragedy was remembered. Jordan Rhodes, Craig Conway and Michael Keane scored for the visitors with Lewis Buxton and Atdhe Nuhiu, with a double, replying for Wednesday in front of 22,792 fans in the Sky Bet Championship. The day marked the 25th anniversary of the deaths of 96 Liverpool fans who had been killed in a crush inside Hillsborough at the FA Cup semi-final with Nottingham Forest on April 15, 1989.  Respect: 96 blue seats at the Leppings Lane end of Hillsborough are replaced by 96 white seats to represent the 96 Liverpool fans who died at the Hillsborough disaster   Honoured: Flowers are laid as a tribute outside the ground before the Championship match at Hillsborough Level: Atdhe Nuhiu races off to celebrate after scoring Sheffield Wednesday\'s 90th minute equaliser  Match factsSheffield Wednesday: Kirkland, Buxton, Onyewu, Llera,Mattock (Helan 60), Maguire, Lee, Palmer (Lavery 59),Hutchinson (Afobe 79), Antonio, Nuhiu.Subs Not Used: Jermaine, Johnson, Coke, Taylor, Martinez.Booked: Llera,Hutchinson,Nuhiu,Afobe.Goals: Buxton 30,Nuhiu 72,90.Blackburn: Robinson, Keane, Kilgallon, Hanley, Spurr, Cairney, Lowe, Williamson, Conway, Rhodes (Varney 90),Gestede.Subs Not Used: Kane, King, Eastwood, Olsson,Taylor, Feeney.Booked: Hanley,Williamson,Gestede,Rhodes.Goals: Rhodes 15,Conway 36,Keane 43.Att: 22,792Ref: Fred GrahamClick HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship That game had been called off after six minutes when the horror that was unfolding had become apparent to the referee, with fans climbing the fences at the Leppings Lane end and crowding on to the pitch. Saturday\'s game kicked off at seven minutes past three, as with all games in the Premier League, Football League and Conference this weekend, after a mintue\'s silence had been impeccably observed. Wednesday coach Stuart Gray and Blackburn manager Gary Bowyer had laid wreaths behind the goal in front of the West Stand and a Liverpool shirt and scarf were also placed there. Wednesday had marked the day by changing 96 blue seats to white and placing a single red rose on each on the lower tier of the stand at the same end of the ground. Blackburn were the first to threaten but Jason Lowe fired wide across the goal from the edge of the area. Wednesday\'s Chris Maguire forced a corner when his shot from distance was deflected wide. Blackburn went ahead after 11 minutes when the Wednesday defence failed to clear a ball into the box and Rhodes had the simple job of rounding Chris Kirkland before slotting the ball into the empty net. Wednesday had their best chance so far when Liam Palmer chased a through ball but was beaten to it by Paul Robinson. They went even closer when Michail Antonio set up Nuhiu but his shot from the edge of the area was beaten away by Robinson. With 28 minutes gone Robinson again kept his side ahead when he brilliantly tipped a header from Antonio over the bar. Wednesday were not to be denied and, from the corner by Maguire, Buxton came in at the far post and forced the ball in.  Thriller: Sheffield Wednesday\'s Atdhe Nuhiu (right) races off to celebrate after scoring his team\'s third goal  Wednesday were enjoying more of the pressure but the visitors went ahead again when the ball fell to Conway and he fired low and hard inside Kirkland\'s right-hand post. Blackburn got a third when Jason Lowe crossed and Keane got up well to head past Kirkland 10 minutes before half-time. Rhodes again had the ball in the net with 53 minutes on the clock but was rightly given offside before he fired high across Kirkland and into the roof of the net as rain lashed down at Hillsborough. Kirkland did well to twice deny Rovers on the hour, first getting down well to his right to stop Rhodes who gathered a chipped ball over the defence.  Aerial battle: Tom Cairney (left) and Sheffield Wednesday\'s Lewis Buxton challenge for a header   Battle: Sheffield Wednesday\'s Michail Antonio (left) is tackled by Blackburn Rovers\' Jordan Rhodes  Rhodes claimed the loose ball and cut it back for Rudy Gestede but again Kirkland kept the effort out. Antonio almost caught Robinson out when his cross hit the far post and Caolan Lavery could not get much power behind his hooked follow-up which he hit into the ground and Robinson gathered. Wednesday got a second and it owed a lot to the persistence of Antonio who powered down the left and went the long way around Keane before firing a low cross. Robinson got his hand to the ball but it bounced up for Nuhiu to force in from close range with 17 minutes remaining.  Heated: Sam Hutchinson (centre) and Lee Williamson go head to head during the Championship clash  Rudy Gestede fired over after Rhodes had beaten Oguchi Onyewu to the loose ball and laid off to his strike partner. Rhodes fired into the side netting after gathering from a poor clearance by the Wednesday defence as Blackburn continued to look the more likely to add to the score. They were made to pay in the dying moments of added time when the visitors failed to clear from a Wednesday attack and Nuhiu hit his second goal high into the roof of the net from 12 yards. Nuhiu almost claimed his third and Wednesday\'s fourth but Robinson beat away his shot and both teams had to settle for a point.   More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:32 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:00 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Sheff Wed 3-3 Blackburn: Gray\'s men honour Hillsborough with late comeback\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Sheffield Wednesday and Blackburn shared the points in a six-goal thriller at Hillsborough on a day when English football\'s biggest tragedy was remembered.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Jordan Rhodes, Craig Conway and Michael Keane scored for the visitors with Lewis Buxton and Atdhe Nuhiu, with a double, replying for Wednesday in front of 22,792 fans in the Sky Bet Championship.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The day marked the 25th anniversary of the deaths of 96 Liverpool fans who had been killed in a crush inside Hillsborough at the FA Cup semi-final with Nottingham Forest on April 15, 1989.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Respect: 96 blue seats at the Leppings Lane end of Hillsborough are replaced by 96 white seats to represent the 96 Liverpool fans who died at the Hillsborough disaster\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"390\" id=\"i-a8330e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0DC71200000578-195_634x390.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Respect: 96 blue seats at the Leppings Lane end of Hillsborough are replaced by 96 white seats to represent the 96 Liverpool fans who died at the Hillsborough disaster</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Honoured: Flowers are laid as a tribute outside the ground before the Championship match at Hillsborough\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"416\" id=\"i-abda0e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0D7FCF00000578-350_634x416.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Honoured: Flowers are laid as a tribute outside the ground before the Championship match at Hillsborough</p> </div><p> </p> <img alt=\"Level: Atdhe Nuhiu races off to celebrate after scoring Sheffield Wednesday\'s 90th minute equaliser\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-a9640e6f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0E5D8600000578-954_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Level: Atdhe Nuhiu races off to celebrate after scoring Sheffield Wednesday\'s 90th minute equaliser</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Match facts</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Sheffield Wednesday:</b> Kirkland, Buxton, Onyewu, Llera,Mattock (Helan 60), Maguire, Lee, Palmer (Lavery 59),Hutchinson (Afobe 79), Antonio, Nuhiu.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used:</b> Jermaine, Johnson, Coke, Taylor, Martinez.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Booked:</b> Llera,Hutchinson,Nuhiu,Afobe.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Buxton 30,Nuhiu 72,90.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Blackburn:</b> Robinson, Keane, Kilgallon, Hanley, Spurr, Cairney, Lowe, Williamson, Conway, Rhodes (Varney 90),Gestede.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used: </b>Kane, King, Eastwood, Olsson,Taylor, Feeney.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Booked:</b> Hanley,Williamson,Gestede,Rhodes.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Rhodes 15,Conway 36,Keane 43.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Att:</b> 22,792</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Ref:</b> Fred Graham</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#results\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a><br/></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">That game had been called off after six minutes when the horror that was unfolding had become apparent to the referee, with fans climbing the fences at the Leppings Lane end and crowding on to the pitch.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Saturday\'s game kicked off at seven minutes past three, as with all games in the Premier League, Football League and Conference this weekend, after a mintue\'s silence had been impeccably observed. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wednesday coach Stuart Gray and Blackburn manager Gary Bowyer had laid wreaths behind the goal in front of the West Stand and a Liverpool shirt and scarf were also placed there. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wednesday had marked the day by changing 96 blue seats to white and placing a single red rose on each on the lower tier of the stand at the same end of the ground.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Blackburn were the first to threaten but Jason Lowe fired wide across the goal from the edge of the area. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wednesday\'s Chris Maguire forced a corner when his shot from distance was deflected wide.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Blackburn went ahead after 11 minutes when the Wednesday defence failed to clear a ball into the box and Rhodes had the simple job of rounding Chris Kirkland before slotting the ball into the empty net.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wednesday had their best chance so far when Liam Palmer chased a through ball but was beaten to it by Paul Robinson.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">They went even closer when Michail Antonio set up Nuhiu but his shot from the edge of the area was beaten away by Robinson.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With 28 minutes gone Robinson again kept his side ahead when he brilliantly tipped a header from Antonio over the bar.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wednesday were not to be denied and, from the corner by Maguire, Buxton came in at the far post and forced the ball in.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Thriller: Sheffield Wednesday\'s Atdhe Nuhiu (right) races off to celebrate after scoring his team\'s third goal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-a9e50e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0E5E0E00000578-392_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Thriller: Sheffield Wednesday\'s Atdhe Nuhiu (right) races off to celebrate after scoring his team\'s third goal</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wednesday were enjoying more of the pressure but the visitors went ahead again when the ball fell to Conway and he fired low and hard inside Kirkland\'s right-hand post.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Blackburn got a third when Jason Lowe crossed and Keane got up well to head past Kirkland 10 minutes before half-time.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rhodes again had the ball in the net with 53 minutes on the clock but was rightly given offside before he fired high across Kirkland and into the roof of the net as rain lashed down at Hillsborough.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Kirkland did well to twice deny Rovers on the hour, first getting down well to his right to stop Rhodes who gathered a chipped ball over the defence.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Aerial battle: Tom Cairney (left) and Sheffield Wednesday\'s Lewis Buxton challenge for a header\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"384\" id=\"i-aba50e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0DFBF000000578-716_634x384.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Aerial battle: Tom Cairney (left) and Sheffield Wednesday\'s Lewis Buxton challenge for a header</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Battle: Sheffield Wednesday\'s Michail Antonio (left) is tackled by Blackburn Rovers\' Jordan Rhodes\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"376\" id=\"i-ab4e0e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0DFD4A00000578-205_634x376.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Battle: Sheffield Wednesday\'s Michail Antonio (left) is tackled by Blackburn Rovers\' Jordan Rhodes</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rhodes claimed the loose ball and cut it back for Rudy Gestede but again Kirkland kept the effort out. Antonio almost caught Robinson out when his cross hit the far post and Caolan Lavery could not get much power behind his hooked follow-up which he hit into the ground and Robinson gathered.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Wednesday got a second and it owed a lot to the persistence of Antonio who powered down the left and went the long way around Keane before firing a low cross.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Robinson got his hand to the ball but it bounced up for Nuhiu to force in from close range with 17 minutes remaining.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Heated: Sam Hutchinson (centre) and Lee Williamson go head to head during the Championship clash\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"391\" id=\"i-a6d90e57\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0E644200000578-437_634x391.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Heated: Sam Hutchinson (centre) and Lee Williamson go head to head during the Championship clash</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rudy Gestede fired over after Rhodes had beaten Oguchi Onyewu to the loose ball and laid off to his strike partner.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rhodes fired into the side netting after gathering from a poor clearance by the Wednesday defence as Blackburn continued to look the more likely to add to the score.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">They were made to pay in the dying moments of added time when the visitors failed to clear from a Wednesday attack and Nuhiu hit his second goal high into the roof of the net from 12 yards.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Nuhiu almost claimed his third and Wednesday\'s fourth but Robinson beat away his shot and both teams had to settle for a point.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Sheff Wed 3-3 Blackburn: Gray\'s men honour Hillsborough with late comeback\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603090/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603090-1D0E5E0E00000578-755_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:48','2014-04-12 19:00:34'),(20,'dd64f73571fddc761bbcc87929455640706b11722b97548261cefd64f77e2b57','dailymail',NULL,'Leeds 2-0 Blackpoo - match reportl: Murphy brace gives Cellino first win as Seasiders continue slide','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603089/Leeds-2-0-Blackpoo-match-reportl-Murphy-brace-gives-Cellino-win-Seasiders-continue-slide.html','  Published: 11:51 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 11:51 EST, 12 April 2014 2 View comments Recalled midfielder Luke Murphy struck in each half as Leeds gained their first win under new owner Massimo Cellino and plunged Blackpool into deeper relegation peril following the 2-0 result. Murphy, a £1million buy from Crewe in the summer, has struggled to live up to his price tag this season but he was outstanding as Leeds ended a run of five defeats. Two teams in desperate need of a win after a dismal run of form elected to play five men across the midfield.  Double: Luke Murphy scored twice as Leeds won their first game under new owner Massimo Cellino Dejection: Blackpool boss Barry Ferguson looks on after the first goal  Match factsLeeds: Butland, Wootton, Lees, Zaliukas (White 81), Pearce, Warnock, Tonge, Brown, Murphy, Smith (Hunt 65), McCormack.Subs Not Used: Pugh, Poleon, Stewart, Cairns, Mowatt.Goals: Murphy 21,73.Blackpool: Gilks, McMahon, MacKenzie, Cathcart, Robinson, Basham (Haroun 67), Ferguson, Perkins, Bishop, Halliday (Keogh 74), Goodwillie.Subs Not Used: Osbourne, Halstead, Barkhuizen, Dobbie, Grandin.Booked: Halliday.Att: 23,416Ref: David Coote (Nottinghamshire).Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship Leeds, without a goal in their previous three matches, threatened to break the spell when Murphy burst into the penalty box in the 14th minute but Craig Cathcart completed an immaculately timed tackle. Murphy, back in the starting line-up after three games on the bench, justified manager Brian McDermott\'s faith by opening the scoring after 21 minutes. Tom Lees\' high ball was nodded down to Ross McCormack by Matt Smith. McCormack played the ball across to goalmouth to Murphy, who switched it onto his left foot on the corner of the six-yard box and steered it past keeper Matt Gilks for his first goal since the opening day of the season. It was Leeds\' first goal in 319 minutes of football and they continued to put Blackpool\'s defence under pressure. Former Crewe midfielder Murphy was again to the fore as he released Scott Wootton down the right and his cross was headed just wide of the far post by McCormack. Blackpool, with just two wins from their previous 25 matches, should have equalised in the 35th minute. Tony McMahon motored down the right and the unmarked Neal Bishop powered a header just over the bar from 15 yards.  Hooked: Jason Pearce clears the ball with Andy Halliday bearing down  David Goodwillie, playing alone up front for the Tangerines, sent an angled shot wide with the defence in disarray but Leeds nearly doubled their lead in the 43rd minute. The lively Murphy was barged to the ground by David Perkins just outside the box and Gilks spilled Michael Tonge\'s driven free-kick before gathering it to his chest in the nick of time. Leeds looked vulnerable at the back and Chris Basham just failed to turn Goodwillie\'s low centre into the net soon after the interval. Noel Hunt was booed by Leeds fans when he left the bench to replace Smith inthe 65th minute and - two minutes later - Blackpool replaced Basham with Belgian Faris Haroun.  Silence: Players and fans at Elland Road mark the anniversary of the Hillsborough Disaster  Murphy\'s second goal arrived in the 73rd minute. Hunt headed on another long ball from Lees and this time Murphy neatly dinked the ball over Gilks with his right foot from eight angled yards. Leeds keeper Jack Butland denied Blackpool a consolation goal by stretching to tip Gary MacKenzie\'s header over the bar with five minutes left.   More... Brighton 3-0 Charlton: Lingard on target again as Seagulls move into play-off zone Sheff Wed 3-3 Blackburn: Gray\'s men honour Hillsborough with late comeback Yeovil 1-1 Bournemouth: Deadlock no good for Glovers\' relegation battle or Cherries\' play-off push as Fraser cancels out Moore Millwall 2-2 Watford: Woolford earns hosts valuable point with dramatic late leveller Bolton 1-0 Barnsley: Beckford leaves rock bottom Tykes staring relegation in the face  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=