headed on another long ball from Lees and this time Murphy neatly dinked the ball over Gilks with his right foot from eight angled yards. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Leeds keeper Jack Butland denied Blackpool a consolation goal by stretching to tip Gary MacKenzie\'s header over the bar with five minutes left.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html\"> Brighton 3-0 Charlton: Lingard on target again as Seagulls move into play-off zone</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html\"> Sheff Wed 3-3 Blackburn: Gray\'s men honour Hillsborough with late comeback</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html\"> Yeovil 1-1 Bournemouth: Deadlock no good for Glovers\' relegation battle or Cherries\' play-off push as Fraser cancels out Moore</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html\"> Millwall 2-2 Watford: Woolford earns hosts valuable point with dramatic late leveller</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html\"> Bolton 1-0 Barnsley: Beckford leaves rock bottom Tykes staring relegation in the face</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603089/Leeds-2-0-Blackpoo-match-reportl-Murphy-brace-gives-Cellino-win-Seasiders-continue-slide.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603089/Leeds-2-0-Blackpoo-match-reportl-Murphy-brace-gives-Cellino-win-Seasiders-continue-slide.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Leeds 2-0 Blackpool: Murphy brace gives Cellino first win as Seasiders continue slide\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603089/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603089-1D0E0E7200000578-307_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:48','2014-04-12 18:51:42'),(21,'b1bf106fca9cdbd3501eff65c20ebe81258a2650a397da0c337b9dfc417db72f','dailymail',NULL,'Millwall 2-2 Watford: Woolford earns hosts valuable point with dramatic late leveller','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html','  Published: 11:31 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 11:50 EST, 12 April 2014 1 View comments Martyn Woolford struck deep into stoppage time to earn relegation-threatened Millwall a 2-2 draw against Watford at The Den. Watford travelled to Millwall in the thick of a fruitful spell in front of goal, and Lewis McGugan put them ahead inside the opening 20 minutes, but Steve Morison - introduced by Lions boss Ian Holloway at half-time - drew the hosts level midway through the second half and appeared to have salvaged a point. Almen Abdi then thought he had had the final say when he restored the Hornets\' lead four minutes from time, but Woolford struck in the fifth added minute to halt Waford\'s play-off push.With both teams needing a win for their respective end-of-season ambitions, the game began at a frantic pace as Carlos Edwards fired over from 20 yards early on. Millwall players celebrate Martyn Woolford\'s dramatic late equaliser  The first big chance fell to Gabriele Angella, but the Watford centre-half could only glance McGugan\'s inviting corner just wide of the far post from six yards.  Match factsMillwall: Forde, Edwards, Dunne, Beevers, Malone, Bailey, Williams, Martin (Jackson 62), Garvan (Morison 46), Woolford, Maierhofer (Easter 74).Subs Not Used: Robinson, Fredericks, Abdou, Bywater.Booked: Martin, Woolford.Goals: Morison 64, Woolford 90.Watford: Almunia, Hoban, Angella, Ekstrand, Faraoni, Abdi, McGugan (Murray 83), Tozser, Riera (Pudil 67), Deeney, Anya (Forestieri 45).Subs Not Used: Belkalem, Merkel, Ranegie, Bond.Booked: Riera,McGugan,Murray.Goals: McGugan 17,Abdi 86.Attendance: 10,851Referee: Keith Stroud (Hampshire).Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championshi Watford\'s in-form duo of McGugan and Troy Deeney were linking up well and the pair combined to give the visitors the lead on 17 minutes. McGugan\'s dummy allowed Deeney to back-heel the ball back into the midfielder\'s path before driving home past David Forde from 20 yards for his 10th goal of the season. Watford could have doubled their lead moments later but Ford was out quickly to block Deeney\'s close-range effort on the angle. That shocked Millwall into life and the hosts should have levelled before the break, but Owen Garvan could only shoot straight at Manuel Almunia from Stefan Maierhofer\'s low cross. The hosts began the second half on top with Maierhofer heading over from six yards on 55 minutes after meeting Lee Martin\'s outswinging free-kick. And Millwall finally got their reward shortly after when second-half substitute Morison volleyed home from the angle following Woolford\'s corner. As the hosts pushed for the winner the game became stretched, and Fernando Forestieri should have reclaimed the lead for the visitors on the break but his low drive struck the legs of Forde. Having brought three strikers on, Holloway was desperate for the three points and Nicky Bailey was inches from a spectacular 25-yard winner but was denied by the fingertips of Almunia. Watford\'s Almen Abdi scores the second goal for his team Millwall\'s John Morison celebrates after scoring the second-half equaliser against Watford Off to a flyer: Lewis McGugan put the visitors 1-0 after 17 minutes And that save proved vital as, just a minute later, Abdi thought he had stolen the points for Watford as his deflected 18-yard effort found the corner of Forde\'s net with just four minutes remaining. But Milwall kept coming and Woolford snatched a dramatic last-minute equaliser, squeezing his left-footed effort through Almunia, to earn his side a much-deserved point. The draw stretched Millwall\'s unbeaten run to four games, and left the Lions still without a home win since January.  Lewis McGugan (centre) celebrates with team-mates after putting the Hornets ahead   Watford\'s Gabriele Angella heads close in the first half   Millwall goalkeeper David Forde punches away a Watford cross as the visitors search for a second goal   On the ball: Lewis McGugan (right) proves too sharp for Millwall defender Carlos Edwards    More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:31 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 11:50 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Millwall 2-2 Watford: Woolford earns hosts valuable point with dramatic late leveller\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">1</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Martyn Woolford struck deep into stoppage time to earn relegation-threatened Millwall a 2-2 draw against Watford at The Den.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Watford travelled to Millwall in the thick of a fruitful spell in front of goal, and Lewis McGugan put them ahead inside the opening 20 minutes, but Steve Morison - introduced by Lions boss Ian Holloway at half-time - drew the hosts level midway through the second half and appeared to have salvaged a point.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Almen Abdi then thought he had had the final say when he restored the Hornets\' lead four minutes from time, but Woolford struck in the fifth added minute to halt Waford\'s play-off push.</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With both teams needing a win for their respective end-of-season ambitions, the game began at a frantic pace as Carlos Edwards fired over from 20 yards early on.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Millwall players celebrate Martyn Woolford\'s dramatic late equaliser\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"466\" id=\"i-a8360e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0E671F00000578-525_634x466.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Millwall players celebrate Martyn Woolford\'s dramatic late equaliser</p> </div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The first big chance fell to Gabriele Angella, but the Watford centre-half could only glance McGugan\'s inviting corner just wide of the far post from six yards.</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Match facts<br/></b></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Millwall</b>: Forde, Edwards, Dunne, Beevers, Malone, Bailey, Williams, Martin (Jackson 62), Garvan (Morison 46), Woolford, Maierhofer (Easter 74).</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used</b>: Robinson, Fredericks, Abdou, Bywater.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Booked</b>: Martin, Woolford.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals</b>: Morison 64, Woolford 90.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Watford</b>: Almunia, Hoban, Angella, Ekstrand, Faraoni, Abdi, McGugan (Murray 83), Tozser, Riera (Pudil 67), Deeney, Anya (Forestieri 45).</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used</b>: Belkalem, Merkel, Ranegie, Bond.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Booked</b>: Riera,McGugan,Murray.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals</b>: McGugan 17,Abdi 86.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Attendance</b>: 10,851</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Referee</b>: Keith Stroud (Hampshire).</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championshi</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Watford\'s in-form duo of McGugan and Troy Deeney were linking up well and the pair combined to give the visitors the lead on 17 minutes.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">McGugan\'s dummy allowed Deeney to back-heel the ball back into the midfielder\'s path before driving home past David Forde from 20 yards for his 10th goal of the season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Watford could have doubled their lead moments later but Ford was out quickly to block Deeney\'s close-range effort on the angle.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That shocked Millwall into life and the hosts should have levelled before the break, but Owen Garvan could only shoot straight at Manuel Almunia from Stefan Maierhofer\'s low cross.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The hosts began the second half on top with Maierhofer heading over from six yards on 55 minutes after meeting Lee Martin\'s outswinging free-kick.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And Millwall finally got their reward shortly after when second-half substitute Morison volleyed home from the angle following Woolford\'s corner.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As the hosts pushed for the winner the game became stretched, and Fernando Forestieri should have reclaimed the lead for the visitors on the break but his low drive struck the legs of Forde.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Having brought three strikers on, Holloway was desperate for the three points and Nicky Bailey was inches from a spectacular 25-yard winner but was denied by the fingertips of Almunia.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Watford\'s Almen Abdi scores the second goal for his team\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-a8b40e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0E4D6900000578-782_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Watford\'s Almen Abdi scores the second goal for his team</p> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Millwall\'s John Morison celebrates after scoring the second-half equaliser against Watford\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"469\" id=\"i-a77a0e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0E27B000000578-805_634x469.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Millwall\'s John Morison celebrates after scoring the second-half equaliser against Watford</p> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Off to a flyer: Lewis McGugan put the visitors 1-0 after 17 minutes\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"425\" id=\"i-aab50e7a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0DB8AE00000578-152_634x425.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Off to a flyer: Lewis McGugan put the visitors 1-0 after 17 minutes</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And that save proved vital as, just a minute later, Abdi thought he had stolen the points for Watford as his deflected 18-yard effort found the corner of Forde\'s net with just four minutes remaining.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But Milwall kept coming and Woolford snatched a dramatic last-minute equaliser, squeezing his left-footed effort through Almunia, to earn his side a much-deserved point.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The draw stretched Millwall\'s unbeaten run to four games, and left the Lions still without a home win since January.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Lewis McGugan (centre) celebrates with team-mates after putting the Hornets ahead\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"428\" id=\"i-aa1f0e7a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0DB98B00000578-682_634x428.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Lewis McGugan (centre) celebrates with team-mates after putting the Hornets ahead</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Watford\'s Gabriele Angella heads close in the first half\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"440\" id=\"i-a8af0e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0DF10A00000578-574_634x440.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Watford\'s Gabriele Angella heads close in the first half</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Millwall goalkeeper David Forde punches away a Watford cross as the visitors search for a second goal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-a53f0e49\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0E002400000578-690_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Millwall goalkeeper David Forde punches away a Watford cross as the visitors search for a second goal</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the ball: Lewis McGugan (right) proves too sharp for Millwall defender Carlos Edwards\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"466\" id=\"i-a8270e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0DF11800000578-890_634x466.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the ball: Lewis McGugan (right) proves too sharp for Millwall defender Carlos Edwards</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Millwall 2-2 Watford: Woolford earns hosts valuable point with dramatic late leveller\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603104/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603104-1D0E671F00000578-674_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:50','2014-04-12 18:50:08'),(22,'32c237a171daa47ddccd1f273306b9a396cee3c0e2eb35c76465a90c7d20abce','dailymail',NULL,'Derby County 3-1 Huddersfield Town: McClaren\'s men continue promotion push as Terriers see red','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603102/Derby-County-3-1-Huddersfield-Town-McClarens-men-continue-promotion-push-Terriers-red.html','  Published: 11:46 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 11:46 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments Derby all but booked their place in the Sky Bet Championship play-offs when they came from a goal down to beat nine-man Huddersfield 3-1 at the iPro Stadium. Nahki Wells put the Terriers in front, but Johnny Russell equalised before Joel Lynch was sent off for two yellow cards. And after goalkeeper Alex Smithies slapped the ball into his own net, skipper Peter Clarke was also dismissed as Chris Martin sealed victory from the penalty spot with his 21st goal of the season.  Cool: Chris Martin celebrates scoring Derby\'s third goal of the afternoon from the penalty spot  Match factsDerby: Grant, Wisdom, Keogh, Buxton, Forsyth (Naylor 70), Bryson, Thorne (Hendrick 70), Hughes, Bamford (Ward 67), Martin, Russell.Subs Not Used: Eustace, Sammon, Legzdins, Whitbread.Goals: Russell 28, Smithies 50 og, Martin 57 pen.Huddersfield: Smithies, Clarke, Gerrard, Lynch, Hammill (Smith 46), Clayton, Norwood (Wallace 59), Hogg, Woods, Wells (Scannell 74), Ward.Subs Not Used: Gobern, Bennett, Holmes, Bunn.Sent Off: Lynch (43),Clarke (56).Booked: Clarke,Lynch,Gerrard.Goals: Wells 14.Att: 25,809Ref: Darren Deadman Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship It puts Derby 11 points clear of seventh place with four games to go, and means Huddersfield still have work to do to pull clear of the drop zone after a third consecutive defeat. Derby had started with the confidence of a team almost guaranteed a top-six finish, and they nearly scored in the third minute when a Russell volley from outside the area was blocked one-handed by Smithies and Richard Keogh scooped the rebound over the bar. Clarke was booked two minutes later for a deliberate trip which halted a Will Hughes run, but the visitors had claims for a penalty waved aside by referee Darren Deadman when Danny Ward went over in the ninth minute. However, Ward was smiling five minutes later when he provided the low cross from the right which travelled all the way to the back post, where Wells had a simple tap-in from two yards. Derby almost conceded again in the 20th minute when a mistake by Keogh allowed Wells to run into the box, but Lee Grant raced out to deny the striker his second goal. It was a big moment because, eight minutes later, Derby were level when a George Thorne pass sliced Huddersfield open and Russell cleverly flicked the ball over Smithies from just inside the box. Huddersfield were reduced to 10 men two minutes before the interval when Lynch, who had already been booked for time wasting, caught Patrick Bamford late on the left touchline and was shown a second yellow card.  Seeing red: Referee Darren Deadman sends off Huddersfield\'s Peter Clarke (5)  Bamford was able to continue after treatment and wasted a great chance when he blazed over from 10 yards, but the advantage was now with Derby and they were literally given a helping hand by Smithies in the 50th minute. A cross from Craig Forsyth was totally misjudged by the keeper, who palmed the ball one-handed into his own net. And it got even worse for Huddersfield, who had Clarke sent off for the foul which also earned Derby a penalty. The defender clearly caught Hughes and, after Clarke had been shown his second yellow, Martin sent Smithies the wrong way with a spot-kick into the bottom left corner.   More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:46 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 11:46 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603102/Derby-County-3-1-Huddersfield-Town-McClarens-men-continue-promotion-push-Terriers-red.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603102/Derby-County-3-1-Huddersfield-Town-McClarens-men-continue-promotion-push-Terriers-red.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Derby 3-1 Huddersfield: McClaren\'s men continue promotion push as Terriers see red\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603102/Derby-County-3-1-Huddersfield-Town-McClarens-men-continue-promotion-push-Terriers-red.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Derby all but booked their place in the Sky Bet Championship play-offs when they came from a goal down to beat nine-man Huddersfield 3-1 at the iPro Stadium.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Nahki Wells put the Terriers in front, but Johnny Russell equalised before Joel Lynch was sent off for two yellow cards.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And after goalkeeper Alex Smithies slapped the ball into his own net, skipper Peter Clarke was also dismissed as Chris Martin sealed victory from the penalty spot with his 21st goal of the season.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Cool: Chris Martin celebrates scoring Derby\'s third goal of the afternoon from the penalty spot\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"381\" id=\"i-ab3f0e88\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603102-1D0E2FFA00000578-689_634x381.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Cool: Chris Martin celebrates scoring Derby\'s third goal of the afternoon from the penalty spot</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Match facts</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Derby:</b> Grant, Wisdom, Keogh, Buxton, Forsyth (Naylor 70), Bryson, Thorne (Hendrick 70), Hughes, Bamford (Ward 67), Martin, Russell.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used:</b> Eustace, Sammon, Legzdins, Whitbread.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Russell 28, Smithies 50 og, Martin 57 pen.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Huddersfield:</b> Smithies, Clarke, Gerrard, Lynch, Hammill (Smith 46), Clayton, Norwood (Wallace 59), Hogg, Woods, Wells (Scannell 74), Ward.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used:</b> Gobern, Bennett, Holmes, Bunn.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Sent Off:</b> Lynch (43),Clarke (56).<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Booked:</b> Clarke,Lynch,Gerrard.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Wells 14.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Att:</b> 25,809<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Ref:</b> Darren Deadman <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It puts Derby 11 points clear of seventh place with four games to go, and means Huddersfield still have work to do to pull clear of the drop zone after a third consecutive defeat.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Derby had started with the confidence of a team almost guaranteed a top-six finish, and they nearly scored in the third minute when a Russell volley from outside the area was blocked one-handed by Smithies and Richard Keogh scooped the rebound over the bar.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Clarke was booked two minutes later for a deliberate trip which halted a Will Hughes run, but the visitors had claims for a penalty waved aside by referee Darren Deadman when Danny Ward went over in the ninth minute.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">However, Ward was smiling five minutes later when he provided the low cross from the right which travelled all the way to the back post, where Wells had a simple tap-in from two yards.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Derby almost conceded again in the 20th minute when a mistake by Keogh allowed Wells to run into the box, but Lee Grant raced out to deny the striker his second goal.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It was a big moment because, eight minutes later, Derby were level when a George Thorne pass sliced Huddersfield open and Russell cleverly flicked the ball over Smithies from just inside the box.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Huddersfield were reduced to 10 men two minutes before the interval when Lynch, who had already been booked for time wasting, caught Patrick Bamford late on the left touchline and was shown a second yellow card.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Seeing red: Referee Darren Deadman sends off Huddersfield\'s Peter Clarke (5)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"387\" id=\"i-a7e10e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603102-1D0E1A2A00000578-305_634x387.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Seeing red: Referee Darren Deadman sends off Huddersfield\'s Peter Clarke (5)</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bamford was able to continue after treatment and wasted a great chance when he blazed over from 10 yards, but the advantage was now with Derby and they were literally given a helping hand by Smithies in the 50th minute.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A cross from Craig Forsyth was totally misjudged by the keeper, who palmed the ball one-handed into his own net.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And it got even worse for Huddersfield, who had Clarke sent off for the foul which also earned Derby a penalty.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The defender clearly caught Hughes and, after Clarke had been shown his second yellow, Martin sent Smithies the wrong way with a spot-kick into the bottom left corner.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603102/Derby-County-3-1-Huddersfield-Town-McClarens-men-continue-promotion-push-Terriers-red.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603102/Derby-County-3-1-Huddersfield-Town-McClarens-men-continue-promotion-push-Terriers-red.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Derby 3-1 Huddersfield: McClaren\'s men continue promotion push as Terriers see red\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603102/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603102-1D0E2FFA00000578-868_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:50','2014-04-12 18:46:54'),(23,'dbfd1704124250fb16f1bd4b3a16091d97c8a2bab355fb8c56467234f688d607','dailymail',NULL,'Ipswich 2-1 Doncaster: Chambers\' late goal keeps McCarthy\'s men in play-off hunt','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603103/Ipswich-2-1-Doncaster-Chambers-late-goal-keeps-McCarthys-men-play-hunt.html','  Published: 11:40 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 11:40 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments Luke Chambers snatched three points to lift Ipswich Town to within the cusp of the Sky Bet Championship play-offs after scoring late on to mark a thrilling end to their 2-1 win over Doncaster Rovers. Daryl Murphy\'s 13th of the season gave Ipswich the lead shortly after the restart but it looked like their top-six hopes would be dented after Chris Brown equalised from an 82nd-minute penalty. But three minutes later, Ipswich skipper Chambers hammered home to move Ipswich into seventh, level with sixth-placed Brighton.  Late winner: Luke Chambers celebrates the goal that keeps Ipswich in touching distance of the play-offs  Match factsIpswich: Gerken, Chambers, Berra, Smith, Mings, Anderson (Ebanks-Blake 46), Skuse, Williams (Richardson 90), Hyam, Hunt (Nouble 46), Murphy.Subs Not Used: Loach, Wordsworth, Green, Tabb.Booked: Berra.Goals: Murphy 47, Chambers 86.Doncaster: Johnstone, Tamas, Quinn, Meite (Robinson 90), Husband (Stevens 80), Coppinger, Furman (Duffy 77), Keegan, Cotterill, Sharp, Brown.Subs Not Used: Middleton, McCullough, Maxted, De Val Fernandez.Booked: Brown, Sharp, Meite.Goals: Brown 83 pen.Att: 19,496Ref: Graham Scott (Oxfordshire).Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship Against a Doncaster side just above the relegation zone, Ipswich did not take long to settle and Paul Anderson\'s flick-on from Stephen Hunt\'s free-kick just evaded four onrushing team-mates. They went even closer in the 14th minute when left-back Tyrone Mings - making only his fifth ever Championship start - tested Sam Johnstone from 25 yards, the Doncaster keeper fortunate to see the rebound cleared from danger. Ipswich should have taken the lead in the 20th minute when Anderson showed great pace to streak away from Abdoulaye Meite, but his first-time cross was slid just wide from Hunt. Doncaster were far from out of it with a grounded Brown bringing a save from Ipswich keeper Dean Gerken before Gabriel Tamas was given far too much room in the Town area and his powerful header was turned around by Gerken. The best chance of the first half fell to the home side in injury time when Hunt\'s wicked inswinging free-kick was headed goalwards by Tommy Smith but Johnstone produced a fantastic diving save as the ball was destined for the far corner. It took Ipswich just one minute and seven seconds to break the deadlock after the restart.  Opener: Daryl Murphy heads home the opener for Ipswich  A patient build-up involving Luke Hyam and Cole Skuse got the ball out to Mings and his cross was headed home by Murphy. The play-off chasing hosts had the momentum and they caused more panic in the Doncaster defence when Tamas\' attempt to clear Murphy\'s cross was almost hacked into his own net. Sylvan Ebanks-Blake, one of two attacking subs by Ipswich boss Mick McCarthy at the interval, then shot wide after good closing down from Hyam. A largely uneventful second half seemed to be heading safely towards a home win when Doncaster received a lifeline out of nothing.  Level: Chris Brown scored a penalty for Rovers just seven minutes before the end  Mings was adjudged to have pushed substitute Mark Duffy just inside the box and Brown made no mistake from 12 yards with 82 minutes on the clock. But Ipswich restored their lead less than three minutes later when Williams\' shot was deflected to Chambers, who rattled the ball past Johnstone. A nervy home side were hanging on and Gerken had to save from Brown\'s close-range header and Duffy\'s low 20-yarder before Frank Nouble wasted a glorious chance to make it three.   More... Brighton 3-0 Charlton: Lingard on target again as Seagulls move into play-off zone Sheff Wed 3-3 Blackburn: Gray\'s men honour Hillsborough with late comeback Yeovil 1-1 Bournemouth: Deadlock no good for Glovers\' relegation battle or Cherries\' play-off push as Fraser cancels out Moore Millwall 2-2 Watford: Woolford earns hosts valuable point with dramatic late leveller Bolton 1-0 Barnsley: Beckford leaves rock bottom Tykes staring relegation in the face  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:40 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 11:40 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603103/Ipswich-2-1-Doncaster-Chambers-late-goal-keeps-McCarthys-men-play-hunt.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603103/Ipswich-2-1-Doncaster-Chambers-late-goal-keeps-McCarthys-men-play-hunt.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Ipswich 2-1 Doncaster: Chambers\' late goal keeps McCarthy\'s men in play-off hunt\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603103/Ipswich-2-1-Doncaster-Chambers-late-goal-keeps-McCarthys-men-play-hunt.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Luke Chambers snatched three points to lift Ipswich Town to within the cusp of the Sky Bet Championship play-offs after scoring late on to mark a thrilling end to their 2-1 win over Doncaster Rovers.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Daryl Murphy\'s 13th of the season gave Ipswich the lead shortly after the restart but it looked like their top-six hopes would be dented after Chris Brown equalised from an 82nd-minute penalty.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But three minutes later, Ipswich skipper Chambers hammered home to move Ipswich into seventh, level with sixth-placed Brighton.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Late winner: Luke Chambers celebrates the goal that keeps Ipswich in touching distance of the play-offs\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a85e0e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603103-1D0E49D600000578-239_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Late winner: Luke Chambers celebrates the goal that keeps Ipswich in touching distance of the play-offs</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Match facts</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Ipswich: </b>Gerken, Chambers, Berra, Smith, Mings, Anderson (Ebanks-Blake 46), Skuse, Williams (Richardson 90), Hyam, Hunt (Nouble 46), Murphy.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used:</b> Loach, Wordsworth, Green, Tabb.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Booked:</b> Berra.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Murphy 47, Chambers 86.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Doncaster:</b> Johnstone, Tamas, Quinn, Meite (Robinson 90), Husband (Stevens 80), Coppinger, Furman (Duffy 77), Keegan, Cotterill, Sharp, Brown.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs Not Used:</b> Middleton, McCullough, Maxted, De Val Fernandez.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Booked:</b> Brown, Sharp, Meite.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Brown 83 pen.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Att: </b>19,496</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Ref:</b> Graham Scott (Oxfordshire).</font></p><p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a></font></b></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Against a Doncaster side just above the relegation zone, Ipswich did not take long to settle and Paul Anderson\'s flick-on from Stephen Hunt\'s free-kick just evaded four onrushing team-mates.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">They went even closer in the 14th minute when left-back Tyrone Mings - making only his fifth ever Championship start - tested Sam Johnstone from 25 yards, the Doncaster keeper fortunate to see the rebound cleared from danger.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ipswich should have taken the lead in the 20th minute when Anderson showed great pace to streak away from Abdoulaye Meite, but his first-time cross was slid just wide from Hunt.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Doncaster were far from out of it with a grounded Brown bringing a save from Ipswich keeper Dean Gerken before Gabriel Tamas was given far too much room in the Town area and his powerful header was turned around by Gerken.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The best chance of the first half fell to the home side in injury time when Hunt\'s wicked inswinging free-kick was headed goalwards by Tommy Smith but Johnstone produced a fantastic diving save as the ball was destined for the far corner.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It took Ipswich just one minute and seven seconds to break the deadlock after the restart.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Opener: Daryl Murphy heads home the opener for Ipswich\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-a7960e5c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603103-1D0E07F200000578-663_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Opener: Daryl Murphy heads home the opener for Ipswich</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A patient build-up involving Luke Hyam and Cole Skuse got the ball out to Mings and his cross was headed home by Murphy.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The play-off chasing hosts had the momentum and they caused more panic in the Doncaster defence when Tamas\' attempt to clear Murphy\'s cross was almost hacked into his own net.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Sylvan Ebanks-Blake, one of two attacking subs by Ipswich boss Mick McCarthy at the interval, then shot wide after good closing down from Hyam.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A largely uneventful second half seemed to be heading safely towards a home win when Doncaster received a lifeline out of nothing.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Level: Chris Brown scored a penalty for Rovers just seven minutes before the end\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-aab90e7e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603103-1D0E3DCB00000578-558_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Level: Chris Brown scored a penalty for Rovers just seven minutes before the end</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mings was adjudged to have pushed substitute Mark Duffy just inside the box and Brown made no mistake from 12 yards with 82 minutes on the clock.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But Ipswich restored their lead less than three minutes later when Williams\' shot was deflected to Chambers, who rattled the ball past Johnstone.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A nervy home side were hanging on and Gerken had to save from Brown\'s close-range header and Duffy\'s low 20-yarder before Frank Nouble wasted a glorious chance to make it three.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html\"> Brighton 3-0 Charlton: Lingard on target again as Seagulls move into play-off zone</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603090/Sheff-Wed-3-3-Blackburn-Stuart-Grays-men-honour-Hillsborough-late-comeback.html\"> Sheff Wed 3-3 Blackburn: Gray\'s men honour Hillsborough with late comeback</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603091/Yeovil-1-1-Bournemouth-Deadlock-no-good-Glovers-relegation-battle-Cherries-play-push-Fraser-cancels-Moore.html\"> Yeovil 1-1 Bournemouth: Deadlock no good for Glovers\' relegation battle or Cherries\' play-off push as Fraser cancels out Moore</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603104/Millwall-2-2-Watford-Woolford-earns-hosts-valuable-point-dramatic-late-leveller.html\"> Millwall 2-2 Watford: Woolford earns hosts valuable point with dramatic late leveller</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html\"> Bolton 1-0 Barnsley: Beckford leaves rock bottom Tykes staring relegation in the face</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603103/Ipswich-2-1-Doncaster-Chambers-late-goal-keeps-McCarthys-men-play-hunt.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603103/Ipswich-2-1-Doncaster-Chambers-late-goal-keeps-McCarthys-men-play-hunt.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Ipswich 2-1 Doncaster: Chambers\' late goal keeps McCarthy\'s men in play-off hunt\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603103/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603103-1D0E49D600000578-444_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:51','2014-04-12 18:40:36'),(24,'1f1e1340747ff5f701ec8cd8ae512332bbc17ff5eaf4262ed24a2f4be7832815','dailymail',NULL,'Bolton 1-0 Barnsley match report: Jermaine Beckford leaves rock bottom Tykes staring relegation in the face','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html','  Published: 11:25 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 11:38 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments  Barnsley\'s relegation fears worsened after Jermaine Beckford\'s first half goal saw them beaten 1-0 at Bolton in the Sky Bet Championship. The Tykes had a golden opportunity to take a point back to South Yorkshire, when Ryan McLaughlin won a penalty with just under 10 minutes left. But Chris O\'Grady\'s spot-kick smashed the frame of the goal to deny them a draw which on the balance of play they would have deserved.  First blood: Jermaine Beckford (R) rounds the keeper to put Bolton in the lead just before half-time All action: Bolton striker Jermaine Beckford (C) has another attempt on Barnsley\'s goal  Match factsBolton: Bogdan, Hutton, Baptiste, Spearing, Mills, Ream, Lee, Trotter, Beckford, Moritz, Hall.Subs: Knight, Danns, Lonergan, Mason, Jutkiewicz, Wheater, Kamara Barnsley: Steele, Etuhu, Kennedy, Dawson, Mvoto, Nyatanga, McLaughlin, Lawrence, O\'Grady, Cywka, JenningsSubs: Hassell, Cranie, Proschwitz, Hunt, Mellis, Turner, McCourtClick HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship Bolton\'s on-loan signing Joe Mason was named among the substitutes in what was the last game of his loan spell before returning to parent club Cardiff. Liam Lawrence returned for the visitors after missing their defeat by Burnley with a slight calf strain and Kelvin Etuhu came back from suspension. Barnsley looked threatening early on and should have taken the lead. Terrific interplay saw McLaughlin feed the ball into Dale Jennings, who somehow blazed it over the bar. Beckford then had a chance to open the scoring. Chung-Yong Lee cut the ball back inside from a cross, but the Jamaican international could not guide the pass to the target in a half that failed to capture the imagination. But, just as the game was approached the break, Wanderers scored a surprising goal. A long ball out of defence from Matt Mills caught the Barnsley defence napping, with Beckford controlling well and then rounding the ball past Luke Steele into an empty net. They then had the opportunity to double the lead early in the second half. Alan Hutton set-up Andre Moritz from close range, but Steele stood tall and chested the ball out for a corner.   More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season? The Tykes had a chance to equalise when O\'Grady volleyed from the edge of the area, though the ball went straight into the hands of Adam Bogdan. A Rob Hall long ball puts Beckford into a similar situation from which he scored. However, this time he could not guide the ball home. Barnsley were now pushing for the draw with chances from Kennedy and Thomasz Cywka and they could have had a penalty when O\'Grady looked to be pushed in the back by Matt Mills.  Man hug: Beckford is congratulated by team-mates after scoring the winning goal that leaves Barnsley bottom  Rear guard action: Bolton\'s Robert Hall (R) battles with Barnsley\'s Tom Kennedy at the Reebok  Getting palmed off: Bolton\'s Andre Moritz keeps Barnsley\'s Dale Jenning at bay    McLaughlin had a great opportunity but his free header from three yards out was not on target. Jennings then hit a shot from 25 yards which smashes against the post, though the referee awarded a corner. Their biggest chance came when McLaughlin won a penalty after being brought down in the box from a clumsy challenge from Alex Baptiste, who was then substituted shortly after. But O\'Grady\'s penalty hit the post and went out for a throw, with Bolton then holding on for the win   More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:25 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 11:38 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Bolton 1-0 Barnsley: Beckford leaves rock bottom Tykes staring relegation in the face\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Barnsley\'s relegation fears worsened after Jermaine Beckford\'s first half goal saw them beaten 1-0 at Bolton in the Sky Bet Championship.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Tykes had a golden opportunity to take a point back to South Yorkshire, when Ryan McLaughlin won a penalty with just under 10 minutes left.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But Chris O\'Grady\'s spot-kick smashed the frame of the goal to deny them a draw which on the balance of play they would have deserved.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"First blood: Jermaine Beckford (R) rounds the keeper to put Bolton in the lead just before half-time\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a7510e59\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603086-1D0E564000000578-409_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">First blood: Jermaine Beckford (R) rounds the keeper to put Bolton in the lead just before half-time</p> </div><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All action: Bolton striker Jermaine Beckford (C) has another attempt on Barnsley\'s goal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-ab500e82\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603086-1D0DD2E900000578-648_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All action: Bolton striker Jermaine Beckford (C) has another attempt on Barnsley\'s goal</p> </div><p> </p></div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\">Match facts<br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Bolton</b>: Bogdan, Hutton, Baptiste, Spearing, Mills, Ream, Lee, Trotter, Beckford, Moritz, Hall.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs</b>: Knight, Danns, Lonergan, Mason, Jutkiewicz, Wheater, Kamara <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Barnsley</b>: Steele, Etuhu, Kennedy, Dawson, Mvoto, Nyatanga, McLaughlin, Lawrence, O\'Grady, Cywka, Jennings</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs</b>: Hassell, Cranie, Proschwitz, Hunt, Mellis, Turner, McCourt<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Bolton\'s on-loan signing Joe Mason was named among the substitutes in what was the last game of his loan spell before returning to parent club Cardiff.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Liam Lawrence returned for the visitors after missing their defeat by Burnley with a slight calf strain and Kelvin Etuhu came back from suspension.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Barnsley looked threatening early on and should have taken the lead. Terrific interplay saw McLaughlin feed the ball into Dale Jennings, who somehow blazed it over the bar.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Beckford then had a chance to open the scoring. Chung-Yong Lee cut the ball back inside from a cross, but the Jamaican international could not guide the pass to the target in a half that failed to capture the imagination.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But, just as the game was approached the break, Wanderers scored a surprising goal. A long ball out of defence from Matt Mills caught the Barnsley defence napping, with Beckford controlling well and then rounding the ball past Luke Steele into an empty net.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They then had the opportunity to double the lead early in the second half. Alan Hutton set-up Andre Moritz from close range, but Steele stood tall and chested the ball out for a corner.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Tykes had a chance to equalise when O\'Grady volleyed from the edge of the area, though the ball went straight into the hands of Adam Bogdan.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">A Rob Hall long ball puts Beckford into a similar situation from which he scored. However, this time he could not guide the ball home.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Barnsley were now pushing for the draw with chances from Kennedy and Thomasz Cywka and they could have had a penalty when O\'Grady looked to be pushed in the back by Matt Mills.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Man hug: Beckford is congratulated by team-mates after scoring the winning goal that leaves Barnsley bottom\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a7c00e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603086-1D0E072700000578-749_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Man hug: Beckford is congratulated by team-mates after scoring the winning goal that leaves Barnsley bottom</p> </div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rear guard action: Bolton\'s Robert Hall (R) battles with Barnsley\'s Tom Kennedy at the Reebok\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-aa290e6f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603086-1D0DCA7500000578-111_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rear guard action: Bolton\'s Robert Hall (R) battles with Barnsley\'s Tom Kennedy at the Reebok</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Getting palmed off: Bolton\'s Andre Moritz keeps Barnsley\'s Dale Jenning at bay\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"469\" id=\"i-ab8d0e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603086-1D0DCAC000000578-732_634x469.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Getting palmed off: Bolton\'s Andre Moritz keeps Barnsley\'s Dale Jenning at bay</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">McLaughlin had a great opportunity but his free header from three yards out was not on target. Jennings then hit a shot from 25 yards which smashes against the post, though the referee awarded a corner.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Their biggest chance came when McLaughlin won a penalty after being brought down in the box from a clumsy challenge from Alex Baptiste, who was then substituted shortly after.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But O\'Grady\'s penalty hit the post and went out for a throw, with Bolton then holding on for the win</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603086/Bolton-1-0-Barnsley-match-report-Jermaine-Beckford-leaves-rock-bottom-Tykes-staring-relegation-face.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Bolton 1-0 Barnsley: Beckford leaves rock bottom Tykes staring relegation in the face\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603086/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603086-1D0DD2E900000578-201_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:52','2014-04-12 18:38:40'),(25,'67a4e1249048c80290c59265dfa7d7f1bd8d1c5ab05157daccf0790b42dd7b7a','dailymail',NULL,'Brighton 3-0 Charlton: Lingard on target again as Seagulls move into play-off zone','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html','  Published: 11:37 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 11:37 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments Goals from Jesse Lingard, Leonardo Ulloa and Jake Forster-Caskey put Brighton into the play-off zone for the second time this season with a deserved 3-0 victory over Charlton at the Amex Stadium.  The Addicks\' fourth defeat under head coach Jose Riga increased their relegation worries, while the Seagulls now boast 19 clean sheets - the most in the Sky Bet Championship.  Brighton, beaten in their previous two home games, had to make a change in goal with former Leeds player Casper Ankergren drafted in for his first league start in a year in place of Tomasz Kuszczak,who was forced to withdraw through illness.  Clinical: Brighton\'s Leonardo Ulloa (third left) scores second goal against Charlton  Match facts Brighton: Ankergren, Saltor, Greer, Upson, Ward, March (Calderon 89), Andrews, Stephens, Lingard (David Rodriguez 90), Ulloa,LuaLua (Forster-Caskey 64).Subs Not Used: Brezovan, Dunk, Mackail-Smith, Lopez.Booked: LuaLua, March.Goals: Lingard 11,Ulloa 43, Forster-Caskey 90.Charlton: Hamer, Wilson, Morrison, Dervite, Wiggins, Poyet, Ghoochannejhad (Solly 65), Cousins, Jackson (Church 81), Ajdarevic (Harriott 46), Sordell.Subs Not Used: Wood, Thuram-Ulien, Pigott, Fox.Booked: Harriott.Att: 28,770Ref: Roger East (Wiltshire).Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship Ankergren\'s opposite number, Ben Hamer, showed good handling early on to claim crosses from Kazenga LuaLua and Solly March, but was beaten in the 11th minute when Lingard notched his first home goal just days after scoring his first club for the club in 4-1 win over Leicester City. Lingard, on loan from Manchester United, skipped past Michael Morrison to score with a cool low shot after good play from LuaLua had put pressure on the Charlton defence. Charlton were indebted to Hamer shortly after when the keeper dashed out positively to claim the ball at the feet of the on-rushing LuaLua. Skipper Gordon Greer came to Brighton\'s rescue with a well-timed challenge on Marvin Sordell on the edge of the area after March gave the ball away. Defender Stephen Ward over-hit a cross for the Seagulls, directed at striker Ulloa, when LuaLua had created space down the left with a surging run. Hamer was able to make a straightforward claim after March got the better of Lawrie Wilson, but his cross was disappointing. Charlton captain Johnnie Jackson displayed composure to clear under pressure from former England defender Matthew Upson, March having delivered a deep corner to the far post. The visitors almost snatched an equaliser when a shot from Reza Ghoochannejhad took a deflection off Greer and came back against the bar.  On the run: Charlton Athletic\'s Diego Poyet (left) and Brighton and Hove Albion\'s Jesse Lingard battle for the ball  Play switched to the other end and, a minute before the break, Ulloa pounced to hit his 15th goal of the season from close range latching onto a short pass from Lingard. Ankergren, seldom troubled in the first half, dived to deflect a dangerous cross from substitute Callum Harriott shortly after the interval, Harriott having been introduced in place of Astrit Ajdarevic. A 50-yard pass from Greer sent LuaLua away on goal for the Seagulls, but Hamer showed alertness to come out and save at the winger\'s feet. Hamer later denied Lingard by turning his goal-bound shot round the post, and Lingard should have done better moments later when he rounded Hamer only to put the ball wastefully over. Charlton, with Sordell up front on his own, threatened when a free-kick from Jackson was headed wide by Morrison with Greer covering him well. Substitute Jake Forster-Caskey put a free-kick into the side-netting for the Seagulls 10 minutes from time after Lingard was pulled down just outside the area. Forster-Caskey put the seal on Brighton\'s comfortable win in the fourth minute of added time by latching onto a pass from Ward and giving Hamer no chance with a low shot into the corner.   More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:37 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 11:37 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Brighton 3-0 Charlton: Lingard on target again as Seagulls move into play-off zone\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Goals from Jesse Lingard, Leonardo Ulloa and Jake Forster-Caskey put Brighton into the play-off zone for the second time this season with a deserved 3-0 victory over Charlton at the Amex Stadium.</font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> The Addicks\' fourth defeat under head coach Jose Riga increased their relegation worries, while the Seagulls now boast 19 clean sheets - the most in the Sky Bet Championship.</font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Brighton, beaten in their previous two home games, had to make a change in goal with former Leeds player Casper Ankergren drafted in for his first league start in a year in place of Tomasz Kuszczak,who was forced to withdraw through illness.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Clinical: Brighton\'s Leonardo Ulloa (third left) scores second goal against Charlton\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"384\" id=\"i-a72c0e5c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603101-1D0E3A5600000578-108_634x384.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Clinical: Brighton\'s Leonardo Ulloa (third left) scores second goal against Charlton</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\">Match facts </h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Brighton:</span> Ankergren, Saltor, Greer, Upson, Ward, March (Calderon 89), Andrews, Stephens, Lingard (David Rodriguez 90), Ulloa,<br/>LuaLua (Forster-Caskey 64).<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Subs Not Used:</span> Brezovan, Dunk, Mackail-Smith, Lopez.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Booked:</span> LuaLua, March.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Goals:</span> Lingard 11,Ulloa 43, Forster-Caskey 90.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Charlton:</span> Hamer, Wilson, Morrison, Dervite, Wiggins, Poyet, Ghoochannejhad (Solly 65), Cousins, Jackson (Church 81), Ajdarevic (Harriott 46), Sordell.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Subs Not Used:</span> Wood, Thuram-Ulien, Pigott, Fox.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Booked:</span> Harriott.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Att:</span> 28,770<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Ref:</span> Roger East (Wiltshire).<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Ankergren\'s opposite number, Ben Hamer, showed good handling early on to claim crosses from Kazenga LuaLua and Solly March, but was beaten in the 11th minute when Lingard notched his first home goal just days after scoring his first club for the club in 4-1 win over Leicester City.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Lingard, on loan from Manchester United, skipped past Michael Morrison to score with a cool low shot after good play from LuaLua had put pressure on the Charlton defence.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Charlton were indebted to Hamer shortly after when the keeper dashed out positively to claim the ball at the feet of the on-rushing LuaLua.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Skipper Gordon Greer came to Brighton\'s rescue with a well-timed challenge on Marvin Sordell on the edge of the area after March gave the ball away.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Defender Stephen Ward over-hit a cross for the Seagulls, directed at striker Ulloa, when LuaLua had created space down the left with a surging run.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> Hamer was able to make a straightforward claim after March got the better of Lawrie Wilson, but his cross was disappointing.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Charlton captain Johnnie Jackson displayed composure to clear under pressure from former England defender Matthew Upson, March having delivered a deep corner to the far post.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> The visitors almost snatched an equaliser when a shot from Reza Ghoochannejhad took a deflection off Greer and came back against the bar.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the run: Charlton Athletic\'s Diego Poyet (left) and Brighton and Hove Albion\'s Jesse Lingard battle for the ball\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-a67a0e4f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603101-1D0E3A3300000578-322_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the run: Charlton Athletic\'s Diego Poyet (left) and Brighton and Hove Albion\'s Jesse Lingard battle for the ball</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Play switched to the other end and, a minute before the break, Ulloa pounced to hit his 15th goal of the season from close range latching onto a short pass from Lingard.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Ankergren, seldom troubled in the first half, dived to deflect a dangerous cross from substitute Callum Harriott shortly after the interval, Harriott having been introduced in place of Astrit Ajdarevic.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> A 50-yard pass from Greer sent LuaLua away on goal for the Seagulls, but Hamer showed alertness to come out and save at the winger\'s feet.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Hamer later denied Lingard by turning his goal-bound shot round the post, and Lingard should have done better moments later when he rounded Hamer only to put the ball wastefully over.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Charlton, with Sordell up front on his own, threatened when a free-kick from Jackson was headed wide by Morrison with Greer covering him well.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Substitute Jake Forster-Caskey put a free-kick into the side-netting for the Seagulls 10 minutes from time after Lingard was pulled down just outside the area.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Forster-Caskey put the seal on Brighton\'s comfortable win in the fourth minute of added time by latching onto a pass from Ward and giving Hamer no chance with a low shot into the corner.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> <br/></div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603101/Brighton-3-0-Charlton-Lingard-target-Seagulls-play-zone.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Brighton 3-0 Charlton: Lingard on target again as Seagulls move into play-off zone\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603101/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603101-1D0E3A3300000578-875_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:53','2014-04-12 18:37:38'),(26,'1aad6a9eb5274f9084c4729ff315a63f9beb25baf0ed03205437bb9e3af7b094','dailymail',NULL,'Louis van Gaal lined up to be next Manchester United boss as David Moyes faces sack','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603094/Louis-van-Gaal-lined-Manchester-United-boss-David-Moyes-faces-sack.html',' By John Edwards Follow @@JEAlty Published: 05:24 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 11:24 EST, 12 April 2014 525 shares 296 View comments  Louis Van Gaal has been lined up as a potential replacement for David Moyes, as pressure mounts on the Manchester United manager after another setback in a calamitous first season in charge. Reports in Dutch newspaper De Telegraaf have claimed an Old Trafford delegation met with Van Gaal earlier this week, in the wake of a Champions’ League defeat against Bayern Munich that ended Moyes’ hopes of having something to show for his debut campaign as United boss. United denied any such meeting took place, but it is clear Van Gaal is figuring prominently in their thoughts as they deliberate over Moyes’ future. VIDEO Scroll down to see Van Gaal on Robin van Persie and admitting to speaking to Spurs  In the frame: Louis van Gaal is being lined up to replace David Moyes at Manchester United this summer, according to reports in Holland   Brazil bound: Van Gaal is stepping down from his position as the Holland coach after the World Cup in Brazil   Heading for the exit? David Moyes is under intense pressure after a disappointing debut season at home and abroad  More... The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit Porto goal machine Martinez monitored by Premier League giants United and Chelsea Sportsmail revealed the policy shift over the former Everton manager in the wake of a last 16 first-leg defeat by Olympiacos that set alarm bells ringing among United bosses. The signals coming out of Old Trafford had always been that Moyes would have every opportunity to stamp his mark on a new era and would be given until next Christmas, at least, to succeed. But such was the sense of dismay at a dismal performance in Athens that, even though the damage was repaired in the return leg, doubts crept in about his suitability and thoughts turned to who might replace him. Van Gaal admits holding Tottenham talks  Replacement: Van Gaal has also been linked with the Tottenham manager\'s position, that will become vacant when Tim Sherwood leaves in the summer   End of the road: Manchester United players look dejected after Bayern Munich knocked them out of the Champions League in midweek   Nightmare: Wayne Rooney reacts in dismay as Thomas Muller scores Bayern Munich\'s second goal in the second leg at the Allianz Arena  VAN GAAL\'S TROPHY CABINET AJAXEredivisie: 1993-1994, 1994-1995, 1995-1996KNVB Cup: 1992-1993Johan Cruyff Shield: 1993, 1994, 1995Champions League: 1994-1995UEFA Cup: 1991-1992UEFA Super Cup: 1995Intercontinental Cup: 1995BARCELONALa Liga: 1997-1998, 1998-1999Copa del Rey: 1997-1998UEFA Super Cup: 1997AZ ALKMAAREredivisie: 2008-2009BAYERN MUNICHBundesliga: 2009-2010DFB-Pokal: 2009-2010DFB-Supercup: 2010 Sportsmail understands United are adamant that, if a change is made, their next choice will be a proven name with a pedigree for winning honours at the highest level. It is also understood Van Gaal, 62, who steps down as Holland coach after this summer’s World Cup and becomes a free agent, has been made aware he is at the top of their list. He has a good relationship with United striker Robin van Persie after working together for the Holland team. Van Gaal has also been sounded out about succeeding Tim Sherwood at White Hart Lane, where Tottenham bosses are becoming increasingly concerned about his reluctance to commit himself. Sources in Holland insist that is because he knows he is in the frame at United, should patience with Moyes run out. United may yet persevere with Moyes, and Van Gaal would then step in at Tottenham, but the former Barcelona boss would prefer Old Trafford as his next destination and will continue to monitor developments there. When asked about the discussions United dismissed any link with Van Gaal and said that meeting had taken place.  Reports: The story appeared in a left-hand column on the back page of Dutch newspaper De Telegraaf on Saturday Van Gaal: Van Persie a big miss for United   Partnership: Van Gaal has worked extensively with Man United striker Robin van Persie during his tenure as Holland manager    Van Gaal agreed to succeed Sir Alex Ferguson when he announced his retirement in 2001, only to be thwarted when the Scot changed his mind a few months later. He wrote in his autobiography: \'It was before the World Cup of 2002, I was in contact with Manchester United through Peter Kenyon (then United chief executive). \'It was said to me that Alex Ferguson was going to retire. \'The moment he\'d go, I\'d succeed him. But in the end Ferguson didn\'t want to quit.\' Louis van Gaal loses his temper on TV sports show  More... The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit Porto goal machine Martinez monitored by Premier League giants United and Chelsea  Share or comment on this article 525shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Edwards\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Edwards</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@JEAlty\">Follow @@JEAlty</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 05:24 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 11:24 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603094/Louis-van-Gaal-lined-Manchester-United-boss-David-Moyes-faces-sack.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603094/Louis-van-Gaal-lined-Manchester-United-boss-David-Moyes-faces-sack.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Van Gaal lined up to be next Man United boss as Moyes faces axe in summer after disastrous first season at Old Trafford\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 525</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603094/Louis-van-Gaal-lined-Manchester-United-boss-David-Moyes-faces-sack.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">296</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Louis Van Gaal has been lined up as a potential replacement for David Moyes, as pressure mounts on the Manchester United manager after another setback in a calamitous first season in charge.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Reports in Dutch newspaper <i>De Telegraaf</i> have claimed an Old Trafford delegation met with Van Gaal earlier this week, in the wake of a Champions’ League defeat against Bayern Munich that ended Moyes’ hopes of having something to show for his debut campaign as United boss.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">United denied any such meeting took place, but it is clear Van Gaal is figuring prominently in their thoughts as they deliberate over Moyes’ future.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO</span></font> Scroll down to see Van Gaal on Robin van Persie and admitting to speaking to Spurs</b><br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"In the frame: Louis van Gaal is being lined up to replace David Moyes at Manchester United this summer, according to reports in Holland\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"427\" id=\"i-a9490e6c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CEC059000000578-438_634x427.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">In the frame: Louis van Gaal is being lined up to replace David Moyes at Manchester United this summer, according to reports in Holland</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Brazil bound: Van Gaal is stepping down from his position as the Holland coach after the World Cup in Brazil\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"517\" id=\"i-ab5f0e7e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CEC04BA00000578-116_634x517.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Brazil bound: Van Gaal is stepping down from his position as the Holland coach after the World Cup in Brazil</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Heading for the exit? David Moyes is under intense pressure after a disappointing debut season at home and abroad\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"785\" id=\"i-add70e9c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CF9EFD300000578-166_634x785.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Heading for the exit? David Moyes is under intense pressure after a disappointing debut season at home and abroad</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\"> The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602434/Welbeck-Cleverley-seen-dancing-street-early-hours-The-day-United-crashed-Champions-League.html\"> Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601877/David-Moyes-faces-uncertain-future-10-Manchester-United-stars-heading-exit.html\"> Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601693/Porto-goal-machine-Jackson-Martinez-monitored-Premier-League-giants-Manchester-United-Chelsea.html\"> Porto goal machine Martinez monitored by Premier League giants United and Chelsea</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><i>Sportsmail </i>revealed the policy shift over the former Everton manager in the wake of a last 16 first-leg defeat by Olympiacos that set alarm bells ringing among United bosses.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The signals coming out of Old Trafford had always been that Moyes would have every opportunity to stamp his mark on a new era and would be given until next Christmas, at least, to succeed.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But such was the sense of dismay at a dismal performance in Athens that, even though the damage was repaired in the return leg, doubts crept in about his suitability and thoughts turned to who might replace him.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3079780909001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Van Gaal admits holding Tottenham talks</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/01/20/video-undefined-1AD3334200000578-364_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Replacement: Van Gaal has also been linked with the Tottenham manager\'s position, that will become vacant when Tim Sherwood leaves in the summer\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-a8c20e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CEB721400000578-134_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Replacement: Van Gaal has also been linked with the Tottenham manager\'s position, that will become vacant when Tim Sherwood leaves in the summer</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"End of the road: Manchester United players look dejected after Bayern Munich knocked them out of the Champions League in midweek\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"394\" id=\"i-ac5e0e8c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CF9B1BA00000578-355_634x394.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">End of the road: Manchester United players look dejected after Bayern Munich knocked them out of the Champions League in midweek</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Nightmare: Wayne Rooney reacts in dismay as Thomas Muller scores Bayern Munich\'s second goal in the second leg at the Allianz Arena\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"471\" id=\"i-aadf0e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CF9B82700000578-858_634x471.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Nightmare: Wayne Rooney reacts in dismay as Thomas Muller scores Bayern Munich\'s second goal in the second leg at the Allianz Arena</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>VAN GAAL\'S TROPHY CABINET</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">AJAX</font></b><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Eredivisie:</b> 1993-1994, 1994-1995, 1995-1996</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>KNVB Cup:</b> 1992-1993</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Johan Cruyff Shield:</b> 1993, 1994, 1995</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Champions League: </b>1994-1995</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>UEFA Cup:</b> 1991-1992</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>UEFA Super Cup:</b> 1995</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Intercontinental Cup:</b> 1995</font></p><p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">BARCELONA</font></b><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>La Liga: </b>1997-1998, 1998-1999</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Copa del Rey: </b>1997-1998</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>UEFA Super Cup:</b> 1997</font><br/><br/><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">AZ ALKMAAR</font><br/></b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Eredivisie:</b> 2008-2009</font><br/><br/><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">BAYERN MUNICH</font></b><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Bundesliga: </b>2009-2010</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>DFB-Pokal: </b>2009-2010</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>DFB-Supercup: </b>2010</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><i>Sportsmail </i>understands United are adamant that, if a change is made, their next choice will be a proven name with a pedigree for winning honours at the highest level.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> It is also understood Van Gaal, 62, who steps down as Holland coach after this summer’s World Cup and becomes a free agent, has been made aware he is at the top of their list.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He has a good relationship with United striker Robin van Persie after working together for the Holland team. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Van Gaal has also been sounded out about succeeding Tim Sherwood at White Hart Lane, where Tottenham bosses are becoming increasingly concerned about his reluctance to commit himself.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sources in Holland insist that is because he knows he is in the frame at United, should patience with Moyes run out.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">United may yet persevere with Moyes, and Van Gaal would then step in at Tottenham, but the former Barcelona boss would prefer Old Trafford as his next destination and will continue to monitor developments there.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">When asked about the discussions United dismissed any link with Van Gaal and said that meeting had taken place.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Reports: The story appeared in a left-hand column on the back page of Dutch newspaper De Telegraaf on Saturday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"871\" id=\"i-a8f90e6f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1D0C14F500000578-449_634x871.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Reports: The story appeared in a left-hand column on the back page of Dutch newspaper De Telegraaf on Saturday</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3079823938001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Van Gaal: Van Persie a big miss for United</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/01/20/video-undefined-1AD34A4900000578-105_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Partnership: Van Gaal has worked extensively with Man United striker Robin van Persie during his tenure as Holland manager\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"738\" id=\"i-ab0e0e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CEC05D600000578-257_634x738.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Partnership: Van Gaal has worked extensively with Man United striker Robin van Persie during his tenure as Holland manager</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Van Gaal agreed to succeed Sir Alex Ferguson when he announced his retirement in 2001, only to be thwarted when the Scot changed his mind a few months later.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He wrote in his autobiography: \'It was before the World Cup of 2002, I was in contact with Manchester United through Peter Kenyon (then United chief executive). </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It was said to me that Alex Ferguson was going to retire.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'The moment he\'d go, I\'d succeed him. But in the end Ferguson didn\'t want to quit.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-2964068592001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Louis van Gaal loses his temper on TV sports show</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2013/12/23/video-undefined-1A44954D00000578-956_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\"> The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602434/Welbeck-Cleverley-seen-dancing-street-early-hours-The-day-United-crashed-Champions-League.html\"> Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601877/David-Moyes-faces-uncertain-future-10-Manchester-United-stars-heading-exit.html\"> Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601693/Porto-goal-machine-Jackson-Martinez-monitored-Premier-League-giants-Manchester-United-Chelsea.html\"> Porto goal machine Martinez monitored by Premier League giants United and Chelsea</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603094/Louis-van-Gaal-lined-Manchester-United-boss-David-Moyes-faces-sack.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603094/Louis-van-Gaal-lined-Manchester-United-boss-David-Moyes-faces-sack.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Van Gaal lined up to be next Man United boss as Moyes faces axe in summer after disastrous first season at Old Trafford\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603094/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">525</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603094-1CEC04BA00000578-282_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:54','2014-04-12 18:24:49'),(27,'cc628e1b78ddf8a8d6ec3cc64a3843ef9e5baac6bb6f39227fffe23890f9f8ef','dailymail',NULL,'QPR 5-2 Nottingham Forest: Onuoha\'s late stunner leaves Reds\' play-off hopes in ruins','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603085/QPR-4-2-Nottingham-Forest-Onuohas-late-stunner-leaves-Reds-play-hopes-ruins.html',' By Andy Sims, Press Association Published: 08:15 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 10:15 EST, 12 April 2014 21 shares 9 View comments QPR got back to winning ways and consolidated their place in the Sky Bet Championship play-offs with a thrilling 5-2 victory over Nottingham Forest. Rangers twice threw away the lead, given to them by Yossi Benayoun - after just 65 seconds - and Junior Hoilett, when they gifted Jamaal Lascelles and Matt Derbyshire equalisers. But just as their inability to defend corners looked set to cost them, late goals from Nedum Onuoha, Ravel Morrison and Bobby Zamora secured a first win in four for the hosts.  Pumped: Nedum Onuoha thundered in QPR\'s third goal as they beat Nottingham Forest 5-2   Decent start! Midfielder Yossi Benayoun gave the hosts an early lead on Saturday afternoon  MATCH FACTSQPR: Green; Simpson, Dunne, Onuoha, Assou-Ekotto, Hoilett (Kranjcar 77), Jenas (Henry 13), Carroll, Benayoun, Morrison, Austin (Zamora 75)Goals: Benayoun 2, Hoilett, 43, Onuoha 84, Morrison 90, Zamora 90Nottingham Forest: Darlow, Halford, Lascelles, Wilson, Fox, Peltier, Jara (Greening 65), Mackie, Cox (Henderson 74), Lansbury (Osborn 65), DerbyshireGoals: Lascelles 37, Derbyshire 75Att: 17,220Referee: Oliver LangfordClick HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship They should now at least be assured of a top-six finish, which is more than can be said for Forest after a 12th game without a win. Incoming manager Stuart Pearce was in the Loftus Road stands to cast his eye over the team he will inherit in the summer, but he will have been less than impressed with their start to the match. Morrison and Hoilett combined to tee up Tom Carroll, whose shot from the edge of the area was palmed away by Karl Darlow. Unfortunately for the Forest keeper the ball bounced straight to the lurking Benayoun who nodded it into an empty net. Rangers\' chances of making it through the play-offs are likely to rest on leading scorer Charlie Austin\'s shoulders - as did their automatic promotion hopes until he dislocated one of them in January. On his first start since returning to fitness the striker should have been celebrating his 16th goal of the season but, lacking match sharpness, he failed to connect with Benoit Assou-Ekotto\'s inviting cross in front of goal.    Wanted it more: The former Chelsea star got ahead of left-back Danny Fox to nod in the opener at Loftus Road   Watching brief: Stuart Pearce was at the game to run the rule over Forest before taking charge in the summer   All smiles! Wigner Junior Hoilett celebrates after scoring QPR\'s second goal just before half-time Slipped in: The Canadian finished off a wonderful move by placing underneath goalkeeper Karl Darlow     More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season? Doyle set for early return to QPR after fears Wolves striker would be out for the season Blackburn 2-0 QPR: Rovers leave Rangers\' hopes of automatic promotion in tatters Pearson calls for focused minds as Foxes chase Championship title after promotion And Rangers, never ones to make life easy for themselves, gave away a sloppy corner in the 37th minute and then left defender Lascelles all alone at the near post to head in Henri Lansbury\'s cross.Forest were only level for five minutes, however, before a slick move involving Benayoun and Carroll ended with Hoilett dinking the ball over Darlow to put Rangers back into the lead.But in the 73rd minute Forest were level again, and Rangers could not say they had not been warned as from another corner, Derbyshire was allowed too much room to power home his header.The match by now could have gone either way but it swung back towards Rangers when Onuoha\'s persistence in keeping the ball in play was rewarded when he tucked in Carroll\'s reverse pass.Then in stoppage time Rangers put a heavy gloss on the scoreline, Morrison slotting past Darlow before teeing up substitute Zamora for the fifth. Nodded: Central defender Jamaal Lascelles celebrates after notching Forest\'s equaliser form a corner Thundered: Matt Derbyshire had looked to secure a point for Forest with a header from a corner Is it over? Forest ower Fawaz Al Hasawi was in the stands, but his side face a struggle to make the play-offs   Pulling the strings: On-loan Ravel Morrison impressed again in the Rangers midfield Redknapp: It\'s time for Ravel to show what he can do   Remember: Both sets of players observed a minute\'s silence in honour of the 96 Hillsborough victims   Drifts on by: Hoilett was put clean through but couldn\'t force a way past Darlow in goal Redknapp: Engage your brain before opening your mouth    More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season? Doyle set for early return to QPR after fears Wolves striker would be out for the season Blackburn 2-0 QPR: Rovers leave Rangers\' hopes of automatic promotion in tatters Pearson calls for focused minds as Foxes chase Championship title after promotion  Share or comment on this article 21shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Andy+Sims,+Press+Association\" rel=\"nofollow\">Andy Sims, Press Association</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 08:15 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 10:15 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603085/QPR-4-2-Nottingham-Forest-Onuohas-late-stunner-leaves-Reds-play-hopes-ruins.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603085/QPR-4-2-Nottingham-Forest-Onuohas-late-stunner-leaves-Reds-play-hopes-ruins.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"QPR 5-2 Nottingham Forest: Reds\' play-off hopes in ruins after battering\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 21</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603085/QPR-4-2-Nottingham-Forest-Onuohas-late-stunner-leaves-Reds-play-hopes-ruins.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">9</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">QPR got back to winning ways and consolidated their place in the Sky Bet Championship play-offs with a thrilling 5-2 victory over Nottingham Forest.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rangers twice threw away the lead, given to them by Yossi Benayoun - after just 65 seconds - and Junior Hoilett, when they gifted Jamaal Lascelles and Matt Derbyshire equalisers.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But just as their inability to defend corners looked set to cost them, late goals from Nedum Onuoha, Ravel Morrison and Bobby Zamora secured a first win in four for the hosts.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pumped: Nedum Onuoha thundered in QPR\'s third goal as they beat Nottingham Forest 5-2\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"388\" id=\"i-a8dd0e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0D753B00000578-712_634x388.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pumped: Nedum Onuoha thundered in QPR\'s third goal as they beat Nottingham Forest 5-2</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Decent start! Midfielder Yossi Benayoun gave the hosts an early lead on Saturday afternoon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"393\" id=\"i-a9850e6f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0C2A4D00000578-340_634x393.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Decent start! Midfielder Yossi Benayoun gave the hosts an early lead on Saturday afternoon</p> </div></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>MATCH FACTS</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>QPR:</b> Green; Simpson, Dunne, Onuoha, Assou-Ekotto, Hoilett (Kranjcar 77), Jenas (Henry 13), Carroll, Benayoun, Morrison, Austin (Zamora 75)<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals: </b>Benayoun 2, Hoilett, 43, Onuoha 84, Morrison 90, Zamora 90<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Nottingham Forest:</b> Darlow, Halford, Lascelles, Wilson, Fox, Peltier, Jara (Greening 65), Mackie, Cox (Henderson 74), Lansbury (Osborn 65), Derbyshire</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Lascelles 37, Derbyshire 75<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Att:</b> 17,220</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Referee:</b> Oliver Langford<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Championship</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">They should now at least be assured of a top-six finish, which is more than can be said for Forest after a 12th game without a win.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Incoming manager Stuart Pearce was in the Loftus Road stands to cast his eye over the team he will inherit in the summer, but he will have been less than impressed with their start to the match.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Morrison and Hoilett combined to tee up Tom Carroll, whose shot from the edge of the area was palmed away by Karl Darlow.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Unfortunately for the Forest keeper the ball bounced straight to the lurking Benayoun who nodded it into an empty net.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rangers\' chances of making it through the play-offs are likely to rest on leading scorer Charlie Austin\'s shoulders - as did their automatic promotion hopes until he dislocated one of them in January.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">On his first start since returning to fitness the striker should have been celebrating his 16th goal of the season but, lacking match sharpness, he failed to connect with Benoit Assou-Ekotto\'s inviting cross in front of goal.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wanted it more: The former Chelsea star got ahead of left-back Danny Fox to nod in the opener at Loftus Road\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"402\" id=\"i-a8220e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0C259800000578-597_634x402.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wanted it more: The former Chelsea star got ahead of left-back Danny Fox to nod in the opener at Loftus Road</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Watching brief: Stuart Pearce was at the game to run the rule over Forest before taking charge in the summer\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"379\" id=\"i-aa7a0e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0C2DC600000578-366_634x379.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Watching brief: Stuart Pearce was at the game to run the rule over Forest before taking charge in the summer</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All smiles! Wigner Junior Hoilett celebrates after scoring QPR\'s second goal just before half-time\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"499\" id=\"i-a7130e5f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0C734000000578-238_634x499.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All smiles! Wigner Junior Hoilett celebrates after scoring QPR\'s second goal just before half-time</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Slipped in: The Canadian finished off a wonderful move by placing underneath goalkeeper Karl Darlow\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"399\" id=\"i-a9dd0e7c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0CF82400000578-696_634x399.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Slipped in: The Canadian finished off a wonderful move by placing underneath goalkeeper Karl Darlow</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602214/Doyle-set-early-return-QPR-fears-hed-season-reveals-Jackett.html\"> Doyle set for early return to QPR after fears Wolves striker would be out for the season</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599855/Blackburn-2-0-QPR-Rovers-leave-Rangers-hopes-automatic-promotion-tatters.html\"> Blackburn 2-0 QPR: Rovers leave Rangers\' hopes of automatic promotion in tatters</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598843/Nigel-Pearson-calls-focused-minds-Foxes-chase-Championship-title-promotion.html\"> Pearson calls for focused minds as Foxes chase Championship title after promotion</a></li> </ul> </div> </div> <p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And Rangers, never ones to make life easy for themselves, gave away a sloppy corner in the 37th minute and then left defender Lascelles all alone at the near post to head in Henri Lansbury\'s cross.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Forest were only level for five minutes, however, before a slick move involving Benayoun and Carroll ended with Hoilett dinking the ball over Darlow to put Rangers back into the lead.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But in the 73rd minute Forest were level again, and Rangers could not say they had not been warned as from another corner, Derbyshire was allowed too much room to power home his header.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The match by now could have gone either way but it swung back towards Rangers when Onuoha\'s persistence in keeping the ball in play was rewarded when he tucked in Carroll\'s reverse pass.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Then in stoppage time Rangers put a heavy gloss on the scoreline, Morrison slotting past Darlow before teeing up substitute Zamora for the fifth.</font></p> <img alt=\"Nodded: Central defender Jamaal Lascelles celebrates after notching Forest\'s equaliser form a corner\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"455\" id=\"i-a89f0e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0D48F100000578-201_634x455.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Nodded: Central defender Jamaal Lascelles celebrates after notching Forest\'s equaliser form a corner</p></div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Thundered: Matt Derbyshire had looked to secure a point for Forest with a header from a corner\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"393\" id=\"i-a99a0e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0D668E00000578-146_634x393.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Thundered: Matt Derbyshire had looked to secure a point for Forest with a header from a corner</p> </div><p> </p> <img alt=\"Is it over? Forest ower Fawaz Al Hasawi was in the stands, but his side face a struggle to make the play-offs\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"398\" id=\"i-aa3d0e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0C2E0B00000578-769_634x398.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Is it over? Forest ower Fawaz Al Hasawi was in the stands, but his side face a struggle to make the play-offs</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pulling the strings: On-loan Ravel Morrison impressed again in the Rangers midfield\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"503\" id=\"i-a91e0e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0D0F5900000578-427_634x503.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pulling the strings: On-loan Ravel Morrison impressed again in the Rangers midfield</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3202063507001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Redknapp: It\'s time for Ravel to show what he can do</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/02/14/video-undefined-1B7CB3CD00000578-226_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Remember: Both sets of players observed a minute\'s silence in honour of the 96 Hillsborough victims\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-a7450e54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0C736500000578-252_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Remember: Both sets of players observed a minute\'s silence in honour of the 96 Hillsborough victims</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Drifts on by: Hoilett was put clean through but couldn\'t force a way past Darlow in goal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a98d0e6b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0D1E4A00000578-224_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Drifts on by: Hoilett was put clean through but couldn\'t force a way past Darlow in goal</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3431036148001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Redknapp: Engage your brain before opening your mouth</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/04/video-undefined-1CD6478C00000578-459_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602214/Doyle-set-early-return-QPR-fears-hed-season-reveals-Jackett.html\"> Doyle set for early return to QPR after fears Wolves striker would be out for the season</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599855/Blackburn-2-0-QPR-Rovers-leave-Rangers-hopes-automatic-promotion-tatters.html\"> Blackburn 2-0 QPR: Rovers leave Rangers\' hopes of automatic promotion in tatters</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598843/Nigel-Pearson-calls-focused-minds-Foxes-chase-Championship-title-promotion.html\"> Pearson calls for focused minds as Foxes chase Championship title after promotion</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603085/QPR-4-2-Nottingham-Forest-Onuohas-late-stunner-leaves-Reds-play-hopes-ruins.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603085/QPR-4-2-Nottingham-Forest-Onuohas-late-stunner-leaves-Reds-play-hopes-ruins.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"QPR 5-2 Nottingham Forest: Reds\' play-off hopes in ruins after battering\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603085/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">21</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603085-1D0C2A4D00000578-991_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:54','2014-04-12 17:15:45'),(28,'b3f7e29deded3a507b53cf100a53ff430297057a569424e075617fe9c344b051','dailymail',NULL,'Liverpool boss Rodgers demands midfield dominance ahead of Premier League title decider against Manchester City','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603124/Vincent-Kompany-confident-Liverpool-battle-ahead-Premier-League-title-decider.html',' By John Drayton Published: 06:26 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 09:55 EST, 12 April 2014 15 shares 31 View comments Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers demands his side should always dominate in midfield and has warned that will be more crucial than ever when title rivals Manchester City visit on Sunday. The Reds’ pressing and passing, with Steven Gerrard playing a holding role, has been a key to their success this season.  Key battle: Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers wants his side to dominate midfield vs Manchester City on Sunday Pellegrini: An excess of anxiety could mean more mistakes   Enthralling encounter: In the reverse fixture in December City won 2-1 against Liverpool in a pulsating clash  But against City they will come up against one of finest midfields in the top flight, and Rodgers knows whoever comes out on top in that area is likely to do so in the game. \'Midfield is always a key battleground, it’s the jungle of the pitch,\' he said. \'They have a world-class player in Yaya Toure. I’ve seen him a lot since he came to this country - he has been a real attacking force for them.  One to stop: Rodgers admits that City midfielder Yaya Toure (left) will be a key attacking threat against Liverpool      \'Before that at Barcelona he played as a holding player and at centre-half in some games. He is a player of immense quality. \'Fernandinho has come in and been a real rock for them and they’ve dropped David Silva into that number 10 role and he is one of the best in the world. \'We will look forward to that battle in there, it is an area where we look to dominate in a lot of our games and I am sure it will be contested competitively.    More... Man City\'s reasons to be fearful... Premier League title chasers must visit three bogey teams in Liverpool, Everton and Palace to lift the trophy MARTIN KEOWN: Suarez, Sturridge and Sterling over Aguero and Co... why Liverpool have the edge in my combined title-chasing XI Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield? From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place \'We will play with no fear because that is the way we know how to play football.\' Speaking ahead of the match, City captain Vincent Kompany is confident they have the players to deal with the attacking threats posed by Rodgers\' side. The Capital One Cup winners\' opponents have climbed to the top of the Barclays Premier League on a run of nine successive wins.  Deadly: Liverpool\'s Luis Suarez (left) and Daniel Sturridge (right) have scored 49 league goals this season  The match could have a huge bearing on the destiny of the title, with City third in the table, four points behind Liverpool but with two games in hand. Kompany said: \'We remember the match against them earlier in the season and for me, Liverpool are still the best Premier League team we\'ve faced at the Etihad.  Ready for war: City captain Vincent Kompany is confident of getting a result at Liverpool on Sunday   Welcome addition: City star striker Sergio Aguero is fit to feature vs Liverpool after a hamstring injury   Champions: City are looking to add the Premier League title to their Capital One Cup success this season  \'They have been on a fantastic run and we know we have to be focused and leave the pitch at the end knowing we\'ve given everything because there is so much at stake in this game. \'But then again, this is a great challenge for us. \'They have a great squad and while we will be wary of that, I think we have quite a few great players of our own.  Still in the hunt: Chelsea are also title contenders, as they currently sitting in second in the Premier League    Share or comment on this article 15shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Drayton\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Drayton</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 06:26 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 09:55 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603124/Vincent-Kompany-confident-Liverpool-battle-ahead-Premier-League-title-decider.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603124/Vincent-Kompany-confident-Liverpool-battle-ahead-Premier-League-title-decider.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Liverpool boss Rodgers demands midfield dominance ahead of Premier League title decider against City\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 15</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603124/Vincent-Kompany-confident-Liverpool-battle-ahead-Premier-League-title-decider.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">31</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers demands his side should always dominate in midfield and has warned that will be more crucial than ever when title rivals Manchester City visit on Sunday.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Reds’ pressing and passing, with Steven Gerrard playing a holding role, has been a key to their success this season.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Key battle: Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers wants his side to dominate midfield vs Manchester City on Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"550\" id=\"i-99420e20\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1D0A559000000578-49_634x550.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Key battle: Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers wants his side to dominate midfield vs Manchester City on Sunday</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3460793165001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Pellegrini: An excess of anxiety could mean more mistakes</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/video-undefined-1D0D86B700000578-849_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Enthralling encounter: In the reverse fixture in December City won 2-1 against Liverpool in a pulsating clash\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-a86b0e5f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1A4C59F400000578-117_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Enthralling encounter: In the reverse fixture in December City won 2-1 against Liverpool in a pulsating clash</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But against City they will come up against one of finest midfields in the top flight, and Rodgers knows whoever comes out on top in that area is likely to do so in the game.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Midfield is always a key battleground, it’s the jungle of the pitch,\' he said.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'They have a world-class player in Yaya Toure. I’ve seen him a lot since he came to this country - he has been a real attacking force for them.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"One to stop: Rodgers admits that City midfielder Yaya Toure (left) will be a key attacking threat against Liverpool\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"456\" id=\"i-a5cf0e4d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-0753EB6100000514-155_634x456.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">One to stop: Rodgers admits that City midfielder Yaya Toure (left) will be a key attacking threat against Liverpool</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Before that at Barcelona he played as a holding player and at centre-half in some games. He is a player of immense quality.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Fernandinho has come in and been a real rock for them and they’ve dropped David Silva into that number 10 role and he is one of the best in the world.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'We will look forward to that battle in there, it is an area where we look to dominate in a lot of our games and I am sure it will be contested competitively.</font><br/></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603068/Manchester-City-beat-bogey-teams-Liverpool-Everton-Crystal-Palace-win-Premier-League.html\"> Man City\'s reasons to be fearful... Premier League title chasers must visit three bogey teams in Liverpool, Everton and Palace to lift the trophy</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602889/Suarez-Sturridge-Sterling-Aguero-Co-Liverpool-edge-combined-title-chasing-XI.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN: Suarez, Sturridge and Sterling over Aguero and Co... why Liverpool have the edge in my combined title-chasing XI</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\"> Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\"> From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\"> Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'We will play with no fear because that is the way we know how to play football.\'</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Speaking ahead of the match, City captain Vincent Kompany is confident they have the players to deal with the attacking threats posed by Rodgers\' side.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Capital One Cup winners\' opponents have climbed to the top of the Barclays Premier League on a run of nine successive wins.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Deadly: Liverpool\'s Luis Suarez (left) and Daniel Sturridge (right) have scored 49 league goals this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"588\" id=\"i-a8670e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1B09B34F00000578-628_634x588.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Deadly: Liverpool\'s Luis Suarez (left) and Daniel Sturridge (right) have scored 49 league goals this season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The match could have a huge bearing on the destiny of the title, with City third in the table, four points behind Liverpool but with two games in hand.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Kompany said: \'We remember the match against them earlier in the season and for me, Liverpool are still the best Premier League team we\'ve faced at the Etihad.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Ready for war: City captain Vincent Kompany is confident of getting a result at Liverpool on Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"550\" id=\"i-a9b00e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1CEDA03400000578-753_634x550.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Ready for war: City captain Vincent Kompany is confident of getting a result at Liverpool on Sunday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Welcome addition: City star striker Sergio Aguero is fit to feature vs Liverpool after a hamstring injury\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"443\" id=\"i-a77e0e59\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1D0A681E00000578-112_634x443.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Welcome addition: City star striker Sergio Aguero is fit to feature vs Liverpool after a hamstring injury</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Champions: City are looking to add the Premier League title to their Capital One Cup success this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-ad790e95\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1BF8AFAB00000578-296_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Champions: City are looking to add the Premier League title to their Capital One Cup success this season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'They have been on a fantastic run and we know we have to be focused and leave the pitch at the end knowing we\'ve given everything because there is so much at stake in this game.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'But then again, this is a great challenge for us.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'They have a great squad and while we will be wary of that, I think we have quite a few great players of our own.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Still in the hunt: Chelsea are also title contenders, as they currently sitting in second in the Premier League\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-a8980e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1CF17E5300000578-138_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Still in the hunt: Chelsea are also title contenders, as they currently sitting in second in the Premier League</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603124/Vincent-Kompany-confident-Liverpool-battle-ahead-Premier-League-title-decider.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603124/Vincent-Kompany-confident-Liverpool-battle-ahead-Premier-League-title-decider.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Liverpool boss Rodgers demands midfield dominance ahead of Premier League title decider against City\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603124/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">15</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603124-1D0A559000000578-918_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:54','2014-04-12 16:55:12'),(29,'c5a946f53f528578c943ca3d523a39d1c0e38abff102c52d7b3e1062200d66b2','dailymail',NULL,'Former Leeds and Liverpool ace Harry Kewell ends injury-ravaged career on a low as Heart seal wooden spoon','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603138/Former-Leeds-Liverpool-ace-Harry-Kewell-ends-injury-ravaged-career-low-Heart-seal-wooden-spoon.html',' By Graeme Yorke Published: 07:29 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 09:17 EST, 12 April 2014 93 shares 10 View comments Harry Kewell was carried aloft on the shoulders of his team-mates despite his final professional match ending in defeat on Saturday. The former Leeds United and Liverpool winger, who was a part of the Champions League winning side in Istanbul in 2005, has brought the curtain down on his 18-year career in football. Appropriately, after an injury-ravaged career, the 35-year-old Socceroos legend was only survived a late fitness test after just recovering from a rib injury.  Hit and miss: Harry Kewell is carried aloft after his enigmatic career ended in Melbourne on Saturday   Farewell, Harry: The Socceroos legend walks down the tunnel with his children after his final match   Outjumped: Kewell is beaten to a header by Iacopo La Rocca of the Wanderers during the match   Remember her? Kewell\'s wife, Sheree Murphy (centre), watches her husband from the stands  More... Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield? Kompany won\'t be fazed by Liverpool as Man City aim to strike killer blow in Premier League title race at Anfield The night Milan fans paid tribute to the 96 victims of Hillsborough with spine-tingling rendition of You\'ll Never Walk Alone CONTINENTAL BREAKFAST: Chelsea and Bayern \'tremble with fear\' over Champions League ties with Real and Atletico Madrid From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000 Kewell, who also had a three-year spell at Galatasaray, exploded into the game as a pacy, skilful winger at Elland Road. He was part of the Leeds youth-team that claimed the 1996–97 FA Youth Cup final, and then made his name as part of the young and impressive side that featured the likes of Jonathan Woodgate, Mark Viduka and Alan Smith. Kewell decided to bring an end to his career in the match on Saturday because the opponenets, Western Sydney Wanderers, are from the suburbs where he was raised. And the Wanderers came from behind to beat Melbourne Heart 3-2 at AAMI Park, denying Kewell a winning send-off. Goals from Nikolai Topor-Stanley, Brendan Santalab and Youssouf Hersi sealed the victory for the away team.  Young gun: Kewell made his name as a skilful winger at Leeds United in the late 1990s   Derby goal: The forward scores for Liverpool against Everton at Goodison Park in 2003   Glory: Kewell (left) and Liverpool celebrate Champions League final victory against Milan in 2005   Golden boys: Kewell celebrates Craig Moore (left) scoring for Australia against Croatia at the 2006 World Cup  Heart, meanwhile, collected the wooden spoon as the competition\'s bottom team. Premier League giants Manchester City, who led the consortium which bought the Heart in January, are soon expected to change the team\'s name to City and the kit from red and white stripes to sky blue to match the parent club. \'He\'s had a fantastic career,\' said Wanderers coach and former Crystal Palace defender Tony Popovic. \'It\'s been a pleasure playing with him and watching him over the years.\' Harry Kewell Worst Penalty Ever - Sydney FC vs Melbourne Heart   More... Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield? Kompany won\'t be fazed by Liverpool as Man City aim to strike killer blow in Premier League title race at Anfield The night Milan fans paid tribute to the 96 victims of Hillsborough with spine-tingling rendition of You\'ll Never Walk Alone CONTINENTAL BREAKFAST: Chelsea and Bayern \'tremble with fear\' over Champions League ties with Real and Atletico Madrid From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000   Share or comment on this article 93shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Graeme+Yorke\" rel=\"nofollow\">Graeme Yorke</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 07:29 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 09:17 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603138/Former-Leeds-Liverpool-ace-Harry-Kewell-ends-injury-ravaged-career-low-Heart-seal-wooden-spoon.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603138/Former-Leeds-Liverpool-ace-Harry-Kewell-ends-injury-ravaged-career-low-Heart-seal-wooden-spoon.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Former Leeds and Liverpool ace Kewell ends injury-ravaged career on a low as Heart seal wooden spoon in Aussie league\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 93</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603138/Former-Leeds-Liverpool-ace-Harry-Kewell-ends-injury-ravaged-career-low-Heart-seal-wooden-spoon.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">10</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Harry Kewell was carried aloft on the shoulders of his team-mates despite his final professional match ending in defeat on Saturday.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The former Leeds United and Liverpool winger, who was a part of the Champions League winning side in Istanbul in 2005, has brought the curtain down on his 18-year career in football.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Appropriately, after an injury-ravaged career, the 35-year-old Socceroos legend was only survived a late fitness test after just recovering from a rib injury.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Hit and miss: Harry Kewell is carried aloft after his enigmatic career ended in Melbourne on Saturday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-acfb0e98\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-1D0BF9DD00000578-588_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Hit and miss: Harry Kewell is carried aloft after his enigmatic career ended in Melbourne on Saturday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Farewell, Harry: The Socceroos legend walks down the tunnel with his children after his final match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"451\" id=\"i-a9d80e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-1D0BE90C00000578-600_634x451.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Farewell, Harry: The Socceroos legend walks down the tunnel with his children after his final match</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Outjumped: Kewell is beaten to a header by Iacopo La Rocca of the Wanderers during the match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"461\" id=\"i-8eb90e01\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-1D0B8E9400000578-0_634x461.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Outjumped: Kewell is beaten to a header by Iacopo La Rocca of the Wanderers during the match</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Remember her? Kewell\'s wife, Sheree Murphy (centre), watches her husband from the stands\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"443\" id=\"i-a82a0e60\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-1D0C0A9400000578-262_634x443.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Remember her? Kewell\'s wife, Sheree Murphy (centre), watches her husband from the stands</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\"> Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603112/Vincent-Kompany-insists-Manchester-City-wont-daunted-Liverpool-Anfield-Premier-League-title-showdown.html\"> Kompany won\'t be fazed by Liverpool as Man City aim to strike killer blow in Premier League title race at Anfield</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603082/Hillsborough-25th-Anniversary-Milan-fans-emotional-tribute-Liverpool-victims-1989-European-Cup-semi-final-video.html\"> The night Milan fans paid tribute to the 96 victims of Hillsborough with spine-tingling rendition of You\'ll Never Walk Alone</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603055/CONTINENTAL-BREAKFAST-Chelsea-Bayern-tremble-fear-Champions-League-ties-Real-Atletico-Madrid.html\"> CONTINENTAL BREAKFAST: Chelsea and Bayern \'tremble with fear\' over Champions League ties with Real and Atletico Madrid</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\"> From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html\"> CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Kewell, who also had a three-year spell at Galatasaray, exploded into the game as a pacy, skilful winger at Elland Road. He was part of the Leeds youth-team that claimed the 1996–97 FA Youth Cup final, and then made his name as part of the young and impressive side that featured the likes of Jonathan Woodgate, Mark Viduka and Alan Smith.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Kewell decided to bring an end to his career in the match on Saturday because the opponenets, Western Sydney Wanderers, are from the suburbs where he was raised.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And the Wanderers came from behind to beat Melbourne Heart 3-2 at AAMI Park, denying Kewell a winning send-off. Goals from Nikolai Topor-Stanley, Brendan Santalab and Youssouf Hersi sealed the victory for the away team.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Young gun: Kewell made his name as a skilful winger at Leeds United in the late 1990s\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"535\" id=\"i-97e30e17\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-00487D1100000258-98_634x535.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Young gun: Kewell made his name as a skilful winger at Leeds United in the late 1990s</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Derby goal: The forward scores for Liverpool against Everton at Goodison Park in 2003\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"492\" id=\"i-a7b70e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-006B67BA00000258-235_634x492.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Derby goal: The forward scores for Liverpool against Everton at Goodison Park in 2003</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Glory: Kewell (left) and Liverpool celebrate Champions League final victory against Milan in 2005\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-9b9b0e36\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-02B7CF250000044D-13_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Glory: Kewell (left) and Liverpool celebrate Champions League final victory against Milan in 2005</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Golden boys: Kewell celebrates Craig Moore (left) scoring for Australia against Croatia at the 2006 World Cup\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"584\" id=\"i-a95b0e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-04D71F0E0000044D-824_634x584.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Golden boys: Kewell celebrates Craig Moore (left) scoring for Australia against Croatia at the 2006 World Cup</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Heart, meanwhile, collected the wooden spoon as the competition\'s bottom team.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Premier League giants Manchester City, who led the consortium which bought the Heart in January, are soon expected to change the team\'s name to City and the kit from red and white stripes to sky blue to match the parent club.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'He\'s had a fantastic career,\' said Wanderers coach and former Crystal Palace defender Tony Popovic.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> \'It\'s been a pleasure playing with him and watching him over the years.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-2937253705001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Harry Kewell Worst Penalty Ever - Sydney FC vs Melbourne Heart</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2013/12/15/video-undefined-1A1F3BD000000578-133_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\"> Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603112/Vincent-Kompany-insists-Manchester-City-wont-daunted-Liverpool-Anfield-Premier-League-title-showdown.html\"> Kompany won\'t be fazed by Liverpool as Man City aim to strike killer blow in Premier League title race at Anfield</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603082/Hillsborough-25th-Anniversary-Milan-fans-emotional-tribute-Liverpool-victims-1989-European-Cup-semi-final-video.html\"> The night Milan fans paid tribute to the 96 victims of Hillsborough with spine-tingling rendition of You\'ll Never Walk Alone</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603055/CONTINENTAL-BREAKFAST-Chelsea-Bayern-tremble-fear-Champions-League-ties-Real-Atletico-Madrid.html\"> CONTINENTAL BREAKFAST: Chelsea and Bayern \'tremble with fear\' over Champions League ties with Real and Atletico Madrid</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\"> From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html\"> CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603138/Former-Leeds-Liverpool-ace-Harry-Kewell-ends-injury-ravaged-career-low-Heart-seal-wooden-spoon.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603138/Former-Leeds-Liverpool-ace-Harry-Kewell-ends-injury-ravaged-career-low-Heart-seal-wooden-spoon.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Former Leeds and Liverpool ace Kewell ends injury-ravaged career on a low as Heart seal wooden spoon in Aussie league\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603138/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">93</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603138-1D0C722C00000578-110_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:55','2014-04-12 16:17:53'),(30,'aad73f9abc074e315ceba917a6c39485528e185f602ab2474769531d719efe3a','dailymail',NULL,'Manny Pacquiao-Tim Bradley bout has the potential to be epic','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602774/Manny-Pacquiao-Tim-Bradley-bout-potential-epic.html',' By Jeff Powell Follow @@jeffpowell_Mail Published: 17:21 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 08:58 EST, 12 April 2014 80 shares 12 View comments  The PacMan has been glued to the screen. Not playing the video game named after him. Watching the tape of his contentious first fight with Tim Bradley which has set up this weekend’s potentially epic re-match. Most of the world believes Manny Pacquiao was robbed here two years ago and the crowd at the weigh-in on Friday night continued to make their allegiance clear as Bradley soaked up the boos. Pacquiao\'s own verdict after reviewing the film: ‘I’ve watched it a few times and I haven’t seen anything yet which can explain how two of the judges made Tim the winner.’ Scroll down for videos  Pound-for-pound: Manny Pacquiao (left) and Timothy Bradley pose for photos following the weigh-in Pick me: Pacquiao is desperate for revenge after losing the first fight Flex: Pacquiao (left) will become only the second boxer to exceed $700 million in terms of PPV revenue    More... PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch Bradley reveals he received death threats after controversial win over Pacquiao Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley Groves fully prepared to leave no doubt of who\'s the better boxer second time around In PacMan speak – since this is a most courteous gentleman – that is as close as he would ever get to complaining or criticising. Rather than snap back at Bradley’s prediction that he is about to finish the boxing career of the Philippines congressman, Pacquiao says:  ‘I don’t care about him disrespecting me. I pray for him.’ That said, by a devout Roman Catholic, there are consolations for Pacquiao in the controversy which has obliged them to do it all over again. Millions of them. Pacquiao is guaranteed a minimum of $20 million for a Saturday night’s work in the MGM Grand Garden Arena lasting a maximum of 36 minutes. How richly he deserves that reward is best explained by another statistic. This is the occasion on which Pacquiao will become only the second boxer to exceed $700 million in terms of pay-per-viewTV revenue generated in their careers The other is Floyd Mayweather and if ever these two do get into a ring together they would burst through the one billion barrier. Manny Pacquiao: I am so motivated for Timothy Bradley fight Rolling in it: Pacquiao is guaranteed a minimum of $20 million for a Saturday night¿s work Confidence: Pacquiao of the Philippines poses with undefeated WBO welterweight champion Bradley Leaving the rest in the shade: Manny Pacquiao is a fusion of supreme fighter and politician  For the moment, Pacquiao is content to leap-frog over Oscar De La Hoya into the 700 club. He goes back in against Bradley on $661 million, while Mayweather will add to his $756 million tally when he fights Marcos Maidana next month. HBO network executives are expecting Pacquiao-Bradley 11 to comfortably surpass one million buys. But even a repeat of the 890,000 who subscribed for the first fight will carry the PacMan above that $700 million mark. The big one: Manny Pacquiao faces Timothy Bradley in Las Vegas on Saturday night Answer to their prayers: The fans\' favourite acknowledges the supporters in Las Vegas Those numbers are all the more remarkable since Pacquiao is the only non-American in a top five, in which Evander Holyfield and Mike Tyson place fourth and fifth behind De La Hoya. They are a testament in part to his charm, modesty and generosity of spirit but mostly to the high-octane excitement he brings to the ring and which he is promising to rev back up to full power here on the Las Vegas Strip Pacquiao has not landed a knock-out since 2009, the year in which that dynamite left hook flattened Ricky Hatton and stopped Miguel Cotto. Bradley, having benefited from the skewed judging against Pacquiao and then seen him brutally knocked out by Juan Manuel Marquez, believes this distinguished challenger for his world welterweight title has lost his killer instinct. But while there have been signs of Pacquiao showing compassion in the later round to opponents he is beating comfortably, he insists there will be no let up from now on. Manny Pacquiao arrives in Vegas ahead of Timothy Bradley bout May the best man win: Pacquiao and Bradley were respectful at their pre-fight press conference He says: ‘Tim will find out that my intensity is there. I will be throwing punches non-stop. Not least because I want to excite the fans and make them happy. I don’t know if the opportunity will come to knock him out but if it does I will take it. ‘I won’t get careless like I did when I was about to stop Marquez but I will take the moment if it comes. I know this is an important fight in my career and I am very positive about everything.’ Pacquiao acknowledges that Bradley has improved since their first meeting, coming through a war against Ruslan Provodnikov and then impressively out-pointing Marquez. The Californian has won all his 31 fights thus far, courtesy in part of that scandalous decision against Pacquiao. He, too, suffered from that miss-judging, even though he was convinced he had won that fight despite suffering from sore feet. He was abused by many of the public, received death threats and became so depressed that at one point he contemplated suicide. Grudge match: Bradley celebrates with the welterweight belt after beating the Filipino almost two years ago Psychologically he has re-grouped with the help of his wife Monica, who is also his manager. And at 27 he is foretelling the end of the ring’s only eight-division world champion, who is eight years his elder. To which Pacquiao says: ‘I’m 35 years young.’ That means that he is ready to chase down – for the full 12 rounds if necessary – an opponent who, although graduated to world class now,  he expects to try to hit and run. Were he to fail in that pursuit it is conceivable that boxing would lose a star attraction and one of its two biggest money generators. But if he shines against Bradley, as he did against another young gun Brandon Rios in November, we might yet see that super-fight with Mayweather. Undefeated: But Floyd Mayweather plans to retire next season Doubts: Pacquiao\'s trainer Freddie Roach Pacquiao does not go in for boastful predictions but he does say:  ‘Rios also said he was going to retire me.  But they have to prove it in the ring and I know everything that is necessary against Bradley. ‘My journey will continue beyond Saturday night.’ Since he assures he has got his KO mojo working again, believe him. Expect the PacMan, whose wife Jinkee expects their fifth child imminently, either to deliver a late stoppage or receive a unanimous decision from a new set of judges in whom, he says, he trusts completely. Pacquiao v Bradley screens live on BoxNation from 2 am on Sunday morning.  More... PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch Bradley reveals he received death threats after controversial win over Pacquiao Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley Groves fully prepared to leave no doubt of who\'s the better boxer second time around    Share or comment on this article 80shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Jeff+Powell\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jeff Powell</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@jeffpowell_Mail\">Follow @@jeffpowell_Mail</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 17:21 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 08:58 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602774/Manny-Pacquiao-Tim-Bradley-bout-potential-epic.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602774/Manny-Pacquiao-Tim-Bradley-bout-potential-epic.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Millions involved and revenge at stake... Pacquiao vs Bradley has the potential to be the most epic contest in years\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 80</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602774/Manny-Pacquiao-Tim-Bradley-bout-potential-epic.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">12</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The PacMan has been glued to the screen. Not playing the video game named after him. Watching the tape of his contentious first fight with Tim Bradley which has set up this weekend’s potentially epic re-match.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Most of the world believes Manny Pacquiao was robbed here two years ago and the crowd at the weigh-in on Friday night continued to make their allegiance clear as Bradley soaked up the boos.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pacquiao\'s own verdict after reviewing the film: ‘I’ve watched it a few times and I haven’t seen anything yet which can explain how two of the judges made Tim the winner.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Scroll down for videos</b></font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pound-for-pound: Manny Pacquiao (left) and Timothy Bradley pose for photos following the weigh-in\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"539\" id=\"i-aa290e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602774-1D0A5C2B00000578-544_634x539.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pound-for-pound: Manny Pacquiao (left) and Timothy Bradley pose for photos following the weigh-in</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pick me: Pacquiao is desperate for revenge after losing the first fight\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"406\" id=\"i-ac3c0e8a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602774-1D0A5CBF00000578-494_634x406.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pick me: Pacquiao is desperate for revenge after losing the first fight</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Flex: Pacquiao (left) will become only the second boxer to exceed $700 million in terms of PPV revenue\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"411\" id=\"i-abf10e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602774-1D0A5CCB00000578-864_634x411.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Flex: Pacquiao (left) will become only the second boxer to exceed $700 million in terms of PPV revenue</p> </div><p> </p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601650/PacMan-people-Mannys-superstar-statesman-entertains-serves-fellow-Filipinos-Jeff-Powell.html\"> PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html\"> Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600995/Tim-Bradley-nearly-committed-suicide-Manny-Pacquiao-decision.html\"> Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600820/Bradley-reveals-received-death-threats-controversial-win-Pacquiao.html\"> Bradley reveals he received death threats after controversial win over Pacquiao</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600192/Pacquiao-sets-sights-Mayweather-Marquez-revenge-against-Bradley.html\"> Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html\"> Groves fully prepared to leave no doubt of who\'s the better boxer second time around</a></li> </ul> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In PacMan speak – since this is a most courteous gentleman – that is as close as he would ever get to complaining or criticising. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Rather than snap back at Bradley’s prediction that he is about to finish the boxing career of the Philippines congressman, Pacquiao says:  ‘I don’t care about him disrespecting me. I pray for him.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That said, by a devout Roman Catholic, there are consolations for Pacquiao in the controversy which has obliged them to do it all over again. Millions of them.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pacquiao is guaranteed a minimum of $20 million for a Saturday night’s work in the MGM Grand Garden Arena lasting a maximum of 36 minutes.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">How richly he deserves that reward is best explained by another statistic.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">This is the occasion on which Pacquiao will become only the second boxer to exceed $700 million in terms of pay-per-viewTV revenue generated in their careers </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The other is Floyd Mayweather and if ever these two do get into a ring together they would burst through the one billion barrier.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3448336945001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Manny Pacquiao: I am so motivated for Timothy Bradley fight</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/video-undefined-1CF6578200000578-217_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rolling in it: Pacquiao is guaranteed a minimum of $20 million for a Saturday night¿s work\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"402\" id=\"i-a8cc0e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602774-1D0A60C800000578-904_634x402.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rolling in it: Pacquiao is guaranteed a minimum of $20 million for a Saturday night¿s work</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Confidence: Pacquiao of the Philippines poses with undefeated WBO welterweight champion Bradley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-abd30e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602774-1D0A5FBC00000578-410_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Confidence: Pacquiao of the Philippines poses with undefeated WBO welterweight champion Bradley</p> </div><p> </p> </div><p> </p> <img alt=\"Leaving the rest in the shade: Manny Pacquiao is a fusion of supreme fighter and politician\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-aa060e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601650-1CF99F4500000578-565_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Leaving the rest in the shade: Manny Pacquiao is a fusion of supreme fighter and politician</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">For the moment, Pacquiao is content to leap-frog over Oscar De La Hoya into the 700 club. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He goes back in against Bradley on $661 million, while Mayweather will add to his $756 million tally when he fights Marcos Maidana next month.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">HBO network executives are expecting Pacquiao-Bradley 11 to comfortably surpass one million buys. But even a repeat of the 890,000 who subscribed for the first fight will carry the PacMan above that $700 million mark.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"The big one: Manny Pacquiao faces Timothy Bradley in Las Vegas on Saturday night\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"386\" id=\"i-abc80e8c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601650-1CF9C7F500000578-757_634x386.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">The big one: Manny Pacquiao faces Timothy Bradley in Las Vegas on Saturday night</p> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Answer to their prayers: The fans\' favourite acknowledges the supporters in Las Vegas\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"286\" id=\"i-a7e20e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601650-1CF22B6000000578-644_634x286.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Answer to their prayers: The fans\' favourite acknowledges the supporters in Las Vegas</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Those numbers are all the more remarkable since Pacquiao is the only non-American in a top five, in which Evander Holyfield and Mike Tyson place fourth and fifth behind De La Hoya.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They are a testament in part to his charm, modesty and generosity of spirit but mostly to the high-octane excitement he brings to the ring and which he is promising to rev back up to full power here on the Las Vegas Strip </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pacquiao has not landed a knock-out since 2009, the year in which that dynamite left hook flattened Ricky Hatton and stopped Miguel Cotto.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Bradley, having benefited from the skewed judging against Pacquiao and then seen him brutally knocked out by Juan Manuel Marquez, believes this distinguished challenger for his world welterweight title has lost his killer instinct.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But while there have been signs of Pacquiao showing compassion in the later round to opponents he is beating comfortably, he insists there will be no let up from now on.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3448334805001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Manny Pacquiao arrives in Vegas ahead of Timothy Bradley bout</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/video-undefined-1CF63E4A00000578-254_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"May the best man win: Pacquiao and Bradley were respectful at their pre-fight press conference\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-a9920e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601650-1CF9B34800000578-477_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">May the best man win: Pacquiao and Bradley were respectful at their pre-fight press conference</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He says: ‘Tim will find out that my intensity is there. I will be throwing punches non-stop. Not least because I want to excite the fans and make them happy. I don’t know if the opportunity will come to knock him out but if it does I will take it.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I won’t get careless like I did when I was about to stop Marquez but I will take the moment if it comes. I know this is an important fight in my career and I am very positive about everything.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pacquiao acknowledges that Bradley has improved since their first meeting, coming through a war against Ruslan Provodnikov and then impressively out-pointing Marquez.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Californian has won all his 31 fights thus far, courtesy in part of that scandalous decision against Pacquiao. He, too, suffered from that miss-judging, even though he was convinced he had won that fight despite suffering from sore feet.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He was abused by many of the public, received death threats and became so depressed that at one point he contemplated suicide. </font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Grudge match: Bradley celebrates with the welterweight belt after beating the Filipino almost two years ago\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"460\" id=\"i-5cd30d41\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/07/article-0-1389299A000005DC-379_634x460.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Grudge match: Bradley celebrates with the welterweight belt after beating the Filipino almost two years ago</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Psychologically he has re-grouped with the help of his wife Monica, who is also his manager. And at 27 he is foretelling the end of the ring’s only eight-division world champion, who is eight years his elder.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">To which Pacquiao says: ‘I’m 35 years young.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That means that he is ready to chase down – for the full 12 rounds if necessary – an opponent who, although graduated to world class now,  he expects to try to hit and run.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Were he to fail in that pursuit it is conceivable that boxing would lose a star attraction and one of its two biggest money generators.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But if he shines against Bradley, as he did against another young gun Brandon Rios in November, we might yet see that super-fight with Mayweather.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Undefeated: But Floyd Mayweather plans to retire next season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"636\" id=\"i-a65f0e51\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601846-03D6D12400000514-508_634x636.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Undefeated: But Floyd Mayweather plans to retire next season</p><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Doubts: Pacquiao\'s trainer Freddie Roach\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"542\" id=\"i-9c830e4b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601846-1303DCD5000005DC-46_634x542.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Doubts: Pacquiao\'s trainer Freddie Roach</p> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pacquiao does not go in for boastful predictions but he does say:  ‘Rios also said he was going to retire me.  But they have to prove it in the ring and I know everything that is necessary against Bradley.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘My journey will continue beyond Saturday night.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Since he assures he has got his KO mojo working again, believe him.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Expect the PacMan, whose wife Jinkee expects their fifth child imminently, either to deliver a late stoppage or receive a unanimous decision from a new set of judges in whom, he says, he trusts completely.</font></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pacquiao v Bradley screens live on BoxNation from 2 am on Sunday morning.</font></span></span></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601650/PacMan-people-Mannys-superstar-statesman-entertains-serves-fellow-Filipinos-Jeff-Powell.html\"> PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html\"> Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600995/Tim-Bradley-nearly-committed-suicide-Manny-Pacquiao-decision.html\"> Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600820/Bradley-reveals-received-death-threats-controversial-win-Pacquiao.html\"> Bradley reveals he received death threats after controversial win over Pacquiao</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600192/Pacquiao-sets-sights-Mayweather-Marquez-revenge-against-Bradley.html\"> Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html\"> Groves fully prepared to leave no doubt of who\'s the better boxer second time around</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602774/Manny-Pacquiao-Tim-Bradley-bout-potential-epic.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602774/Manny-Pacquiao-Tim-Bradley-bout-potential-epic.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Millions involved and revenge at stake... Pacquiao vs Bradley has the potential to be the most epic contest in years\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602774/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">80</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602774-1CF9C7F500000578-5_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:55','2014-04-12 15:58:33'),(31,'02440fd2586a2bff813f59df55e96d407ea694f7634436f33fd17505b9241b24','dailymail',NULL,'Hillsborough 25th Anniversary: Milan fans\' emotional tribute to Liverpool victims in 1989 European Cup semi-final - video','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603082/Hillsborough-25th-Anniversary-Milan-fans-emotional-tribute-Liverpool-victims-1989-European-Cup-semi-final-video.html',' By Adam Shergold Follow @@adamjshergold Published: 05:17 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 08:38 EST, 12 April 2014 147 shares 8 View comments  Football grounds the length and breadth of the country will fall silent on Saturday afternoon to mark the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough Disaster, in which 96 Liverpool supporters lost their lives. All matches in England will kick-off seven minutes late and be preceded by a minutes\' silence to remember those lost while cheering on their team at the FA Cup semi-final with Nottingham Forest on April 15, 1989. But few tributes this weekend will be as spine-tinglingly emotional as the rendition of Liverpool\'s club anthem \'You\'ll Never Walk Alone\' during the European Cup semi-final between AC Milan and Real Madrid just four days after the tragedy. VIDEO Scroll to the bottom for former Anfield stars talking of the Hillsborough tribute game   Respect: Milan and Real Madrid players stopped for a minutes\' silence to remember the 96 victims of the Hillsborough Disaster in their European Cup semi-final in 1989   Tribute: In a pre-arranged step, referee Alexis Ponnet blew his whistle a minute in to the match at the San Siro, the players stopping to pay their respects   Unity: The 73,000 spectators inside the San Siro broke into spontaneous applause   Emotion: The crowd also sang the chorus of Liverpool anthem \'You\'ll Never Walk Alone\'  AC Milan 5-0 Real Madrid EUROPEAN CUP SEMI-FINAL, SECOND LEGApril 19th, 1989 - San Siro, MilanMilan won 6-1 on aggregateMilan: Giovanni Galli, Mauro Tassotti, Paolo Maldini, Angelo Colombo (Filippo Galli 78), Alessandro Costacurta, Franco Baresi (c), Roberto Donadoni, Frank Rijkaard, Marco van Basten, Ruud Gullit (Paolo Pietro Virdis 70), Carlo Ancelotti Scorers: Ancelotti 17; Rijkaard 24; Gullit 45; Van Basten 49; Donadoni 60Real Madrid: Paco Buyo, Chendo, Rafael Gordillo, Michel, Manuel Sanchis, Francisco Llorente, Emilo Butragueno, Bernd Schuster, Hugo Sanchez, Ricardo Gallego (c), Rafael Martin Vazquez In a pre-arranged step, the Belgian referee Alexis Ponnet blew his whistle after just one minute of the match for a moment of reflection. The two teams stopped where they were on the pitch and bowed their heads as the 73,000 San Siro crowd broke out into spontaneous applause. Milan supporters\' groups had distributed leaflets with the words of the song printed on them in the days leading up to the match and urged their fans to learn them off by heart. The result was a remarkable rendition from all sides of the ground that makes the hairs on the back of your neck stand on end. It was a brilliant night for Milan, whose team included such legends as Franco Baresi, Paolo Maldini, Frank Rijkaard, Marco van Basten, Ruud Gullit and Carlo Ancelotti. They crushed Real 5-0, thanks to goals from Ancelotti, Rijkaard, Gullit, van Basten and Roberto Donadoni, and went on to lift the trophy by beating Steaua Bucharest 4-0 in the final.  Kings of Europe: The Milan team celebrate their European Cup triumph after beating Steaua Bucharest 4-0 in the final at the Nou Camp   Pre-match: Real Madrid captain Ricardo Gallego (left) shakes hands with Milan counterpart Franco Baresi as referee Alexis Ponnet looks on   Last four clash: Milan\'s Marco van Basten wins the ball ahead of Real Madrid\'s Chendo   On the ball: Van Basten takes the ball ahead of Chendo Dalglish: We laugh at same stories every time we\'re back together  Whelan: I will drive Kenny home to make sure he starts me Evans: It\'s nice to have a Premier League which is competitive Kennedy: It\'s a fantastic opportunity to pay a tribute to the 96  More... JAMIE CARRAGHER: Hillsborough - every child must be told why games kick off seven minutes late this weekend Roar us to title! We\'ll unleash power of Anfield against City, says Liverpool boss Rodgers Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield? MARTIN KEOWN: Suarez, Sturridge and Sterling over Aguero and Co... why Liverpool have the edge in my combined title-chasing XI SOMETHING FOR THE WEEKEND: Liverpool and Man City\'s title showdown and FA Cup semis take centre stage as Hillsborough is remembered 25 years on Sheffield Wednesday dedicate programme front page to 96 Liverpool fans who died at Hillsborough   Share or comment on this article 147shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Adam+Shergold\" rel=\"nofollow\">Adam Shergold</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@adamjshergold\">Follow @@adamjshergold</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 05:17 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 08:38 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603082/Hillsborough-25th-Anniversary-Milan-fans-emotional-tribute-Liverpool-victims-1989-European-Cup-semi-final-video.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603082/Hillsborough-25th-Anniversary-Milan-fans-emotional-tribute-Liverpool-victims-1989-European-Cup-semi-final-video.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"The night Milan fans paid tribute to the 96 victims of Hillsborough with spine-tingling rendition of You\'ll Never Walk Alone\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 147</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603082/Hillsborough-25th-Anniversary-Milan-fans-emotional-tribute-Liverpool-victims-1989-European-Cup-semi-final-video.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">8</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Football grounds the length and breadth of the country will fall silent on Saturday afternoon to mark the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough Disaster, in which 96 Liverpool supporters lost their lives.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">All matches in England will kick-off seven minutes late and be preceded by a minutes\' silence to remember those lost while cheering on their team at the FA Cup semi-final with Nottingham Forest on April 15, 1989. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But few tributes this weekend will be as spine-tinglingly emotional as the rendition of Liverpool\'s club anthem \'You\'ll Never Walk Alone\' during the European Cup semi-final between AC Milan and Real Madrid just four days after the tragedy.</font><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\"><br/></span></font></font></b></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO</span></font> Scroll to the bottom for former Anfield stars talking of the Hillsborough tribute game</font></b></p>\n<p><br/><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"480\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/mFX07w2-4ls\" width=\"640\"></iframe></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Respect: Milan and Real Madrid players stopped for a minutes\' silence to remember the 96 victims of the Hillsborough Disaster in their European Cup semi-final in 1989\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"513\" id=\"i-a8a10e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-1D0BD65500000578-193_634x513.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Respect: Milan and Real Madrid players stopped for a minutes\' silence to remember the 96 victims of the Hillsborough Disaster in their European Cup semi-final in 1989</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tribute: In a pre-arranged step, referee Alexis Ponnet blew his whistle a minute in to the match at the San Siro, the players stopping to pay their respects\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"520\" id=\"i-aa790e7b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-1D0BD63C00000578-899_634x520.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tribute: In a pre-arranged step, referee Alexis Ponnet blew his whistle a minute in to the match at the San Siro, the players stopping to pay their respects</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Unity: The 73,000 spectators inside the San Siro broke into spontaneous applause\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"517\" id=\"i-a8ba0e6a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-1D0BD64400000578-476_634x517.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Unity: The 73,000 spectators inside the San Siro broke into spontaneous applause</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Emotion: The crowd also sang the chorus of Liverpool anthem \'You\'ll Never Walk Alone\'\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"513\" id=\"i-aa200e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-1D0BD64D00000578-915_634x513.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Emotion: The crowd also sang the chorus of Liverpool anthem \'You\'ll Never Walk Alone\'</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>AC Milan 5-0 Real Madrid</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">EUROPEAN CUP SEMI-FINAL, SECOND LEG</font></b><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">April 19th, 1989 - San Siro, Milan</font><i><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Milan won 6-1 on aggregate</font></i></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Milan: </b>Giovanni Galli, Mauro Tassotti, Paolo Maldini, Angelo Colombo (Filippo Galli 78), Alessandro Costacurta, Franco Baresi (c), Roberto Donadoni, Frank Rijkaard, Marco van Basten, Ruud Gullit (Paolo Pietro Virdis 70), Carlo Ancelotti <br/><b>Scorers:</b> Ancelotti 17; Rijkaard 24; Gullit 45; Van Basten 49; Donadoni 60<br/><br/><b>Real Madrid: </b>Paco Buyo, Chendo, Rafael Gordillo, Michel, Manuel Sanchis, Francisco Llorente, Emilo Butragueno, Bernd Schuster, Hugo Sanchez, Ricardo Gallego (c), Rafael Martin Vazquez</font><i><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></i><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In a pre-arranged step, the Belgian referee Alexis Ponnet blew his whistle after just one minute of the match for a moment of reflection.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The two teams stopped where they were on the pitch and bowed their heads as the 73,000 San Siro crowd broke out into spontaneous applause. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Milan supporters\' groups had distributed leaflets with the words of the song printed on them in the days leading up to the match and urged their fans to learn them off by heart.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The result was a remarkable rendition from all sides of the ground that makes the hairs on the back of your neck stand on end. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It was a brilliant night for Milan, whose team included such legends as Franco Baresi, Paolo Maldini, Frank Rijkaard, Marco van Basten, Ruud Gullit and Carlo Ancelotti. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They crushed Real 5-0, thanks to goals from Ancelotti, Rijkaard, Gullit, van Basten and Roberto Donadoni, and went on to lift the trophy by beating Steaua Bucharest 4-0 in the final. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Kings of Europe: The Milan team celebrate their European Cup triumph after beating Steaua Bucharest 4-0 in the final at the Nou Camp\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"439\" id=\"i-a9950e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-052F12DC000005DC-922_634x439.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Kings of Europe: The Milan team celebrate their European Cup triumph after beating Steaua Bucharest 4-0 in the final at the Nou Camp</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pre-match: Real Madrid captain Ricardo Gallego (left) shakes hands with Milan counterpart Franco Baresi as referee Alexis Ponnet looks on\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a8030e59\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-1D0BE45300000578-422_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pre-match: Real Madrid captain Ricardo Gallego (left) shakes hands with Milan counterpart Franco Baresi as referee Alexis Ponnet looks on</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Last four clash: Milan\'s Marco van Basten wins the ball ahead of Real Madrid\'s Chendo\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"458\" id=\"i-a91c0e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-1D0BE46400000578-983_634x458.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Last four clash: Milan\'s Marco van Basten wins the ball ahead of Real Madrid\'s Chendo</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the ball: Van Basten takes the ball ahead of Chendo\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a8600e60\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603082-1D0BE47000000578-862_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the ball: Van Basten takes the ball ahead of Chendo</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3452153365001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Dalglish: We laugh at same stories every time we\'re back together</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/video-undefined-1CFF33C200000578-767_636x364.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\