y aware of the challenge that awaits.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I don\'t buy we could catch them cold after midweek,\' he added.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'The players they have through the squad are top-class players. I am sure they will make changes, but whoever comes in is top-class.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'They are not pushing for the title for no reason. They have experience and class all over the pitch. It\'s an extremely tough game, but a challenge we are looking forward to and have to relish.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Vital: Monk has described Williams as an \'important player\' for Swansea and wants him to stay for many years\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"685\" id=\"i-abd90e89\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603148-1BC3CCD000000578-634_634x685.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Vital: Monk has described Williams as an \'important player\' for Swansea and wants him to stay for many years</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'The journey this club (Swansea) has been on and fighting for is to be on this level, to compete against these sort of teams, and we have to make sure we continue that.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Swansea will go into the Chelsea clash following a 1-0 defeat Hull last weekend, which came as a jolt, given that Monk had seen his team draw with Arsenal and beat Norwich in their previous two games.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Swansea are currently six points above the relegation zone. After Chelsea, their remaining fixtures are against Newcastle, Aston Villa, Southampton and Sunderland.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"History: As captain, Williams (centre) led Swansea to the Capital One Cup trophy last season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"413\" id=\"i-a6810e58\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603148-18404889000005DC-404_634x413.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">History: As captain, Williams (centre) led Swansea to the Capital One Cup trophy last season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I was very annoyed with the (Hull) performance. The training was very good, the sessions very competitive,\' Monk said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'As a manager all you can do is get it to that level and understand fully what is expected that they do it on a Saturday. That\'s the disappointment - the work they put in and we end up with a performance like that.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'If you had to say mathematically, we need two more wins. I want it, and we\'re aware of it. But we want more, we want consistency. We have been too inconsistent this season.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Moving on: Monk wants his side to bounce back against Chelsea after losing 1-0 at Hull last weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a97a0e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603148-1CDB547600000578-333_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Moving on: Monk wants his side to bounce back against Chelsea after losing 1-0 at Hull last weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It is not as if it is small inconsistencies. We have performed brilliantly, then against Hull we were very, very poor.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It is too big a gap. The best teams stay at a level, and that is what I want for the rest of the season.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603148/Gary-Monk-wants-Swansea-City-skipper-Ashley-Williams-prolong-stay-amidst-Napoli-interest.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603148/Gary-Monk-wants-Swansea-City-skipper-Ashley-Williams-prolong-stay-amidst-Napoli-interest.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Monk wants Swansea skipper Williams to prolong stay amidst Napoli interest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603148/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">7</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603148-1A4BD27700000578-625_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:58','2014-04-12 14:57:28'),(35,'21d61c0013a4efe28aac62e0bba1cc7a5bab5865bb697e4a0a560321763a16ae','dailymail',NULL,'MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: Rory McIlroy will tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html',' By Phil Casey Published: 05:03 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 07:54 EST, 12 April 2014 7 shares 6 View comments  Pre-tournament favourite Rory McIlroy will tee off on his own to begin the third round of the Masters at the Augusta National on Saturday. The 24-year-old looked to be in contention for his first green jacket after carding an opening round of one under par 71.  Lone ranger: Rory McIlroy will play the third round of the Masters on his own after just making the cut on Friday McIlroy\'s funny gaffe suggesting Ian Woosnam can\'t win Masters Day to forget: McIlroy had a disappointing second round of 77 at Augusta National on Friday   MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES1515 Rory McIlroy (NIrl)1525 Jason Day (Aus), Joost Luiten (Ned)1535 Jose Maria Olazabal (Spa), Darren Clarke (NIrl)1545 Miguel Angel Jimenez (Spa), Sandy Lyle (Sco)1555 Billy Horschel (USA), Gary Woodland (USA)1605 Chris Kirk (USA), Martin Kaymer (Ger)1615 Oliver Goss (Aus - amateur), Francesco Molinari (Ita)1625 Nick Watney (USA), Thongchai Jaidee (Tha)1635 Bill Haas (USA), Thorbjorn Olesen (Den)1655 Ian Poulter (Eng), Rickie Fowler (USA)1705 Steven Bowditch (Aus), Brendon de Jonge (Zim)1715 Hunter Mahan (USA), Justin Rose (Eng)1725 Vijay Singh (Fij), Bernhard Langer (Ger) MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES1735 Steve Stricker (USA), Larry Mize (USA)1745 Mike Weir (Can), KJ Choi (Kor)1755 Henrik Stenson (Swe), Stewart Cink (USA)1805 Lee Westwood (Eng), Brandt Snedeker (USA)1815 Louis Oosthuizen (Rsa), Gonzalo Fernandez-Castano (Spa)1835 Lucas Glover (USA), Matt Kuchar (USA)1845 Kevin Stadler (USA), Jamie Donaldson (Wal)1855 Stephen Gallacher (Sco), Russell Henley (USA)1905 Jim Furyk (USA), Kevin Streelman (USA)1915 Fred Couples (USA), Jimmy Walker (USA)1925 Adam Scott (Aus), Jordan Spieth (USA)1935 Thomas Bjorn (Den), Jonas Blixt (Swe)1945 Bubba Watson (USA), John Senden (Aus) However, the world number nine had a day to forget on Friday as he made the weekend\'s play with his final shot. The Northern Ireland golfer did not realise he had to par the last to make the halfway cut on the mark of four over par, but held his nerve from four feet to complete a disappointing - and admittedly unfortunate - 77.  That meant a total of 51 players - 50 professionals and Australian amateur Oliver Goss - qualified for the last two rounds and ensured McIlroy would be the first man out at 1515, most likely playing with club member Jeff Knox as his marker.   More... It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic Scotsman Gallacher delighted to make cut on Masters debut... but is staying grounded Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike \'I just want to go out there and try to get off to a fast start,\' said McIlroy, who visited some seldom-seen parts of the course on the 10th and 13th, the latter after his ball hit a sprinkler and bounded into the azaleas which give the hole its name. \'Eleven shots back (of leader Bubba Watson) with two rounds to play is going to be nearly impossible to make up so I\'m trying to shoot two really low rounds and see where that puts me at the end of the week. \'It will take something phenomenal to shoot something in the mid-60s and get myself back under par going into the last day. But I\'m going to need to be two, three or four under par going into the last day to have any sort of chance.\'  Winners and losers: 2012 champion Bubba Watson (left) is the overnight leader, while three-time champion Phil Mickelson (right) failed to make the weekend cut at Augusta National for the first time in 17 years  McIlroy at least had an outside chance to cling onto, which is more than could be said for three-time winner Phil Mickelson, who missed the cut by a shot to make an early exit for the first time since 1997. \'I just had one bad hole there at 12,\' said Mickelson, who found a greenside bunker on the 155-yard par three, thinned his second shot into another bunker and then did exactly the same again. \'I keep making these triple bogeys, they\'re tough to overcome. I\'ve actually played reasonably well for a majority of the holes and then the ones that I let slide I end up making a big number.\'  Early exit: South African duo Charl Schwartzel (left) and Ernie Els (right) both failed to make the weekend cut  Asked if he would watch the final two rounds on television, Mickelson added: \'It\'s an exciting tournament, so I probably will. It will kind of be my punishment.\' Luke Donald, Sergio Garcia, Ernie Els and 2011 champion Charl Schwartzel also missed out by a shot, Donald shooting a second round of 70 but paying the price for an opening 79 which included a two-shot penalty for touching the sand in a bunker on the ninth after failing to escape at the first attempt. Rory is 10/1 favourite to lift the Masters  Share or comment on this article 7shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Phil+Casey\" rel=\"nofollow\">Phil Casey</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 05:03 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 07:54 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy will tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut by skin of his teeth\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 7</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">6</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pre-tournament favourite Rory McIlroy will tee off on his own to begin the third round of the Masters at the Augusta National on Saturday.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 24-year-old looked to be in contention for his first green jacket after carding an opening round of one under par 71.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Lone ranger: Rory McIlroy will play the third round of the Masters on his own after just making the cut on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-5e5b0d49\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A8DC300000578-899_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Lone ranger: Rory McIlroy will play the third round of the Masters on his own after just making the cut on Friday</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3448381114001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">McIlroy\'s funny gaffe suggesting Ian Woosnam can\'t win Masters</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/video-undefined-1CF6522600000578-506_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Day to forget: McIlroy had a disappointing second round of 77 at Augusta National on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"486\" id=\"i-5b3f0d2c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A845900000578-309_634x486.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Day to forget: McIlroy had a disappointing second round of 77 at Augusta National on Friday</p> </div><p> </p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> </span></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter art-ins sport\"><div class=\"splitLeft\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES</span><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">1515</span> Rory McIlroy (NIrl)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">1525</span> Jason Day (Aus), Joost Luiten (Ned)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">1535</span> Jose Maria Olazabal (Spa), Darren Clarke (NIrl)</font><br/