last two rounds and ensured McIlroy would be the first man out at 1515, most likely playing with club member Jeff Knox as his marker.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html\"> It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\"> Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602890/Stepen-Gallacher-continues-early-Masters-magic-Ian-Poulter-Justin-Rose-enjoy-good-second-day-cut-sight.html\"> McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602801/Stephen-Gallacher-delighted-make-cut-Masters-debut.html\"> Scotsman Gallacher delighted to make cut on Masters debut... but is staying grounded</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html\"> Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html\"> He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I just want to go out there and try to get off to a fast start,\' said McIlroy, who visited some seldom-seen parts of the course on the 10th and 13th, the latter after his ball hit a sprinkler and bounded into the azaleas which give the hole its name.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Eleven shots back (of leader Bubba Watson) with two rounds to play is going to be nearly impossible to make up so I\'m trying to shoot two really low rounds and see where that puts me at the end of the week.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It will take something phenomenal to shoot something in the mid-60s and get myself back under par going into the last day. But I\'m going to need to be two, three or four under par going into the last day to have any sort of chance.\'</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"One to beat: 2012 champion Bubba Watson is the current Masters overnight leader on seven under par\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-aa6b0e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603077-1D0ACF3800000578-407_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Out: Three-time Masters winner Phil Mickelson failed to make the 36-hole cut for the first time in 17 years\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a81d0e5b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603077-1D09E65700000578-442_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Winners and losers: 2012 champion Bubba Watson (left) is the overnight leader, while three-time champion Phil Mickelson (right) failed to make the weekend cut at Augusta National for the first time in 17 years<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">McIlroy at least had an outside chance to cling onto, which is more than could be said for three-time winner Phil Mickelson, who missed the cut by a shot to make an early exit for the first time since 1997.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I just had one bad hole there at 12,\' said Mickelson, who found a greenside bunker on the 155-yard par three, thinned his second shot into another bunker and then did exactly the same again.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I keep making these triple bogeys, they\'re tough to overcome. I\'ve actually played reasonably well for a majority of the holes and then the ones that I let slide I end up making a big number.\'</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Early exit: 2011 winner Charl Schwartzel also failed to make the cut after finishing five over par overall\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a8640e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603077-1D0A920A00000578-598_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Eyes on the prize: Ernie Els\' wait for his first Masters win will continue after also not making the cut on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-9acb0e2a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603077-1D0960AA00000578-26_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Early exit: South African duo Charl Schwartzel (left) and Ernie Els (right) both failed to make the weekend cut<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Asked if he would watch the final two rounds on television, Mickelson added: \'It\'s an exciting tournament, so I probably will. It will kind of be my punishment.\'<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Luke Donald, Sergio Garcia, Ernie Els and 2011 champion Charl Schwartzel also missed out by a shot, Donald shooting a second round of 70 but paying the price for an opening 79 which included a two-shot penalty for touching the sand in a bunker on the ninth after failing to escape at the first attempt.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3451933249001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Rory is 10/1 favourite to lift the Masters</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/video-undefined-1CFD5E6200000578-699_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy will tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut by skin of his teeth\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603077/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">7</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603077-1D0A8DC300000578-947_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:57:58','2014-04-12 14:54:20'),(36,'a2547c00524f8a54e250b5f5e181e80b3d9f4b5188b427cedd98e905661b9a75','dailymail',NULL,'Barcelona players and WAGS attend Cesc Fabregas\' daughter\'s birthday','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602734/Barcelona-players-WAGS-attend-Cesc-Fabregas-daughters-birthday.html',' By John Drayton Published: 14:13 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 07:47 EST, 12 April 2014 34 shares 28 View comments  Things may not be going well for Barcelona on the pitch, but at least they got to let their hair down off it. Many of the La Liga stars were at Cesc Fabregas\' house for his daughter Lia\'s first birthday. Gerard Pique was joined by wife and pop singer Shakira, while Lionel Messi rocked up with girlfriend Anotella Roccuzzo.  Occasion: Pique (right) and his girlfriend Shakira (left) are all smiles just hours after Barcelona\'s defeat Shakira\'s man Pique tells reporters about his nerves at the birth   Down time: Lionel Messi and his girlfriend Antonella Roccuzzo arrive at the party on Friday Brilliant Barcelona TV advert with Messi and team-mates   Hair down: Fabregas (right) and Sergio Busquets (left) fish something out of the water  Barcelona were dumped out of the Champions League on Wednesday night after a 1-0 loss to Atletico Madrid (2-1 on agg). It is now time to focus on their domestic efforts, with a league fixture away at Granada on Saturday. Carles Puyol and Xavi were also at the party ahead of the game, and Tata Martino is sure to have put them through their paces following the midweek defeat.  Arrival: Sergio Busquets turns up with his partner to the Fabregas bash   Celebrate: Midfielder Xavi with his partner at Fabregas\' daughter\'s first birthday party BARCELONA WEDDING Xavi gets married   Down and out: Barcelona were eliminated from the Champions League by Atletico Madrid in the week Neymar gets nutmegged by freestyler Séan Garnier at Castol shoot   More... Schalke 0-1 Barcelona: Top scorer Munir nets late winner as Catalans set up UEFA Youth League final against Benfica Bale, Modric and Co lather up in new ad as Real stars prepare for another close shave Mourinho is a specialist in winning while Arsenal are just laughable... it\'s the reader comments of the week The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack Real Madrid 0-4 Benfica: Zidane\'s son taken off as Spanish side are smashed in UEFA Youth League semi-final in Switzerland EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow    Share or comment on this article 34shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Drayton\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Drayton</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 14:13 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 07:47 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602734/Barcelona-players-WAGS-attend-Cesc-Fabregas-daughters-birthday.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602734/Barcelona-players-WAGS-attend-Cesc-Fabregas-daughters-birthday.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Barca players forget their troubles on the pitch with party for Fabregas\' daughter\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 34</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602734/Barcelona-players-WAGS-attend-Cesc-Fabregas-daughters-birthday.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">28</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Things may not be going well for Barcelona on the pitch, but at least they got to let their hair down off it. Many of the La Liga stars were at Cesc Fabregas\' house for his daughter Lia\'s first birthday.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Gerard Pique was joined by wife and pop singer Shakira, while Lionel Messi rocked up with girlfriend Anotella Roccuzzo.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Occasion: Pique (right) and his girlfriend Shakira (left) are all smiles just hours after Barcelona\'s defeat\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"382\" id=\"i-ab960e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602734-1D09ABBE00000578-172_634x382.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Occasion: Pique (right) and his girlfriend Shakira (left) are all smiles just hours after Barcelona\'s defeat</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-2114315757001\" style=\"width:63