. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Since the implementation of the Equality Act in 2010, and legislation dating back to 1995, it has been illegal for service providers, including football clubs, to treat disabled people less favourably than other customers.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mr Penning said he has also written to the Football Association chairman, former BBC director-general Greg Dyke, and described the situation.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Crackdown: MP Mike Penning said he would look to prosecute clubs that failed to meet criteria\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"470\" id=\"i-a4540e41\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603127-0122D83400000514-849_634x470.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Crackdown: MP Mike Penning said he would look to prosecute clubs that failed to meet criteria</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The MP said: \'It\'s not just about wheelchair access. You can get wheelchair access in but if you just plant them around the edge of the game, they don\'t feel part of the game, they don\'t feel part of the atmosphere.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I want to build on the legacy from the Paralympics and football clubs need to use a piece of their loose change.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">In a statement, the Premier League said: \'All Premier League clubs have arrangements in place to provide access and facilities for disabled fans. The highest standards of access are generally at clubs with new grounds but all clubs, even those working within the constraints of older stadia, work hard to make sure that disabled fans can attend matches and enjoy their football.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'The Accessible Stadia Guide sets out agreed standards to be achieved when new grounds are designed or existing grounds rebuilt, however all clubs use those standards to assess existing provisions and guide them on how to make improvements.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Particular attention is given to achieving stadium management solutions that make the best of the constraints and opportunities inherent in each stadium. This includes working with the fans to arrive at solutions that work for them, and providing special training for stewards and staff to ensure that appropriate assistance is given.\'<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602712/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Every-child-told-games-kick-seven-minutes-late-weekend.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Hillsborough - every child must be told why games kick off seven minutes late this weekend</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603094/Louis-van-Gaal-lined-Manchester-United-boss-David-Moyes-faces-sack.html\"> Van Gaal lined up to be next Man United boss as Moyes faces axe in summer after disastrous first season at Old Trafford</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602729/FA-Cup-win-trophies-Arsenal-says-Alex-Oxlade-Chamberlain.html\"> FA Cup win can bring back glory days for barren Arsenal, says Oxlade-Chamberlain</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602902/Thibaut-Courtois-face-Chelsea-UEFA-tell-Blues-stop-Atletico-Madrid-keeper-playing.html\"> Chelsea to face Courtois as UEFA tell Blues they can\'t stop Atletico keeper playing</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602777/Liverpool-boss-Brendan-Rodgers-Well-unleash-power-Anfield-against-City.html\"> Roar us to title! We\'ll unleash power of Anfield against City, says Liverpool boss Rodgers</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html\"> CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603127/Only-THREE-Premier-League-clubs-adequate-wheelchair-facilities.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603127/Only-THREE-Premier-League-clubs-adequate-wheelchair-facilities.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Only THREE Premier League clubs have adequate wheelchair facilities\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603127/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">11</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603127-1CAC1B6900000578-574_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:00','2014-04-12 13:40:12'),(39,'091cd73e08ac2b4887a6bef14edac81a3347b04598cb911e9af543d0acdd4082','dailymail',NULL,'MARTIN KEOWN BOOT ROOM: Timing was wrong for Chris Hughton sacking from Norwich','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html',' By Martin Keown - Boot Room Follow @@martinkeown5 Published: 16:00 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 06:16 EST, 12 April 2014 16 shares 8 View comments  The relegation roadshow rolls on this week with a massive fixture at Craven Cottage. Fulham are  desperate for points and Norwich enter the game with a new manager. I was shocked to see Chris Hughton sacked last weekend but only because of the timing. In terms of results, it’s been coming. Hughton helped establish Norwich in the Premier League last season, finishing a respectable 11th. The club took that as a sign of progress and backed their manager to the tune of £25m in the summer.    Shown the door: Hughton was sacked by Norwich, currently 17th in the table, after a dismal run of results Down the bottom: Norwich and Fulham face up in a huge relegation six-pointer at Craven Cottage More... Norwich\'s Premier League survival will not be decided by Fulham clash, insists Adams EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final FA charge Crawley defender Connolly with violent conduct for slapping Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park Carson hoping for Cup chance as Wigan look to repeat Wembley heroics The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack For any club that is a healthy investment but for a club of Norwich’s size it is a huge sum. Eight players came in, including striker Ricky van Wolfswinkel for a club-record £8.6m. He has scored one goal. They showed enormous faith in Hughton and would have expected to see improvements. Instead they were sucked into a  relegation battle. Losing to West Brom last weekend was the final straw and the club lost patience. Norwich chief executive David McNally has clearly had his finger hovering over the trigger for some time. In February he revealed he had a list of replacements ready to take over from Hughton, so the question is, why leave it until the last five games? Norwich have won just three of their last 18 league fixtures and conceded 17 goals in their last six away games. In their minds, Norwich have made this a 34-game season because their final four matches, against Liverpool, Manchester United, Chelsea and Arsenal are so tough. Making his point: David McNally (left) says the club were faced with no option then to sack Hughton That has created a panic and desperation in their play. That desperation has gripped everyone at the club and culminated in Hughton getting sacked. Have recent performances suggested they are going to get anything at Craven Cottage? Probably not. With the following four games a write-off, the board have gambled and tried to make one last change to secure their survival. If it works, it could be an inspired decision but I can’t help feeling it would have been better to keep Hughton on. Vital victory: Hugo Rodallega and Lewis Holtby (right) celebrate Fulham\'s 2-1 win over Aston Villa   Former Under 18s boss Neil Adams has been promoted and even if he manages for another 50 years, he will not face a bigger task. Norwich have not lacked willingness or quality, but Adams needs to change the mood, calm his players and  spread some belief. With the upheaval at Norwich, Fulham will feel this is their chance. They have been in the top flight since 2001 and will not go down without a fight. Roy Hodgson led their great escape in 2008 and a win on Saturday will give them the belief they can overhaul Norwich. That is some turnaround, given how far adrift they were.  Waste: Ricky van Wolfswinkel (left) was brought in by Chris Hughton and has scored just one league goal  I was relegated with Aston Villa and there is no worse feeling. Playing in the top flight gives you an enormous sense of pride and trying to get promoted the following season was the hardest of my career. There is more than money and glamour at stake. The whole world knows about the Premier League and people don’t realise just how much that status means to a player. It is a part of who you are and, make no mistake, the players will have to fight for it on Saturday.  Praying: Sunderland are also fighting for their lives at the bottom of the Premier League  PS Sunday is the cut-off date for a two-match ban for 10 yellow cards. Steven Gerrard, Ramires, Gareth Barry, and Cheick Tiote are all on nine. All are vital for their clubs and nobody will want to sit out crucial games. Time to tread carefully.  Thin ice: Both Steven Gerrard (left) and Ramires (right) are one booking away from a two-match ban   Spotlight on: Lewis Grabban, Bournemouth, Age 26 Bournemouth are on the march and are now within touching distance of the play-offs. They are on a good run of form, winning their last five matches, and Lewis Grabban has been a big part of that with five goals in those games. He is an  eye-catching striker who is quick, confident in front of goal and causes problems for every defender he faces. There was talk of him leaving in January but he signed a new deal and that is testament to the good job manager Eddie Howe is doing at the club in his second spell there. Howe got them promoted from League One last season and they are having another good year. The positive environment he creates is a major reason why Grabban is still there and why he is in such good form.  Hit man: Grabban has scored five goals in five games, with Bournemouth on fine form   More... Norwich\'s Premier League survival will not be decided by Fulham clash, insists Adams EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final FA charge Crawley defender Connolly with violent conduct for slapping Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park Carson hoping for Cup chance as Wigan look to repeat Wembley heroics The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack    Share or comment on this article 16shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1081237/Martin-Keown---Boot-Room.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Martin Keown - Boot Room</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@martinkeown5\">Follow @@martinkeown5</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:00 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 06:16 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 16</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">8</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The relegation roadshow rolls on this week with a massive fixture at Craven Cottage. Fulham are  desperate for points and Norwich enter the game with a new manager.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">I was shocked to see Chris Hughton sacked last weekend but only because of the timing. In terms of results, it’s been coming.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Hughton helped establish Norwich in the Premier League last season, finishing a respectable 11th. The club took that as a sign of progress and backed their manager to the tune of £25m in the summer.</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<img alt=\"Shown the door: Hughton was sacked by Norwich, currently 17th in the table, after a dismal run of results\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"457\" id=\"i-5ade0d26\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-0-1CF8145200000578-372_634x457.jpg\" width=\"634\"/>\n<p class=\"imageCaption\">Shown the door: Hughton was sacked by Norwich, currently 17th in the table, after a dismal run of results</p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Down the bottom: Norwich and Fulham face up in a huge relegation six-pointer at Craven Cottage\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"452\" id=\"i-a8910e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-1D0694C900000578-674_634x452.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Down the bottom: Norwich and Fulham face up in a huge relegation six-pointer at Craven Cottage</p> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602677/Norwichs-Premier-League-survival-not-decided-Fulham-clash-insists-Neil-Adams.html\"> Norwich\'s Premier League survival will not be decided by Fulham clash, insists Adams</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602588/Hull-City-boss-Steve-Bruce-admits-wall-team-defeat-old-club-Sheffield-United-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\"> FA charge Crawley defender Connolly with violent conduct for slapping Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602720/Scott-Carson-hoping-FA-Cup-chance-Wigan-Athletic-look-repeat-Wembley-heroics.html\"> Carson hoping for Cup chance as Wigan look to repeat Wembley heroics</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\"> The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack</a></li> </ul> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">For any club that is a healthy investment but for a club of Norwich’s size it is a huge sum. Eight players came in, including striker Ricky van Wolfswinkel for a club-record £8.6m. He has scored one goal.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They showed enormous faith in Hughton and would have expected to see improvements. Instead they were sucked into a  relegation battle. Losing to West Brom last weekend was the final straw and the club lost patience.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Norwich chief executive David McNally has clearly had his finger hovering over the trigger for some time. In February he revealed he had a list of replacements ready to take over from Hughton, so the question is, why leave it until the last five games?</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Norwich have won just three of their last 18 league fixtures and conceded 17 goals in their last six away games. In their minds, Norwich have made this a 34-game season because their final four matches, against Liverpool, Manchester United, Chelsea and Arsenal are so tough. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Making his point: David McNally (left) says the club were faced with no option then to sack Hughton\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"340\" id=\"i-ab960e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/07/article-2598921-1CE830E200000578-372_634x340.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Making his point: David McNally (left) says the club were faced with no option then to sack Hughton</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That has created a panic and desperation in their play. That desperation has gripped everyone at the club and culminated in Hughton getting sacked.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Have recent performances suggested they are going to get anything at Craven Cottage? Probably not. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With the following four games a write-off, the board have gambled and tried to make one last change to secure their survival. If it works, it could be an inspired decision but I can’t help feeling it would have been better to keep Hughton on.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Vital victory: Hugo Rodallega and Lewis Holtby (right) celebrate Fulham\'s 2-1 win over Aston Villa\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"544\" id=\"i-aa610e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602001-1CDC05EC00000578-772_634x544.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Vital victory: Hugo Rodallega and Lewis Holtby (right) celebrate Fulham\'s 2-1 win over Aston Villa</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Former Under 18s boss Neil Adams has been promoted and even if he manages for another 50 years, he will not face a bigger task. Norwich have not lacked willingness or quality, but Adams needs to change the mood, calm his players and  spread some belief. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With the upheaval at Norwich, Fulham will feel this is their chance. They have been in the top flight since 2001 and will not go down without a fight.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Roy Hodgson led their great escape in 2008 and a win on Saturday will give them the belief they can overhaul Norwich. That is some turnaround, given how far adrift they were.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Waste: Ricky van Wolfswinkel (left) was brought in by Chris Hughton and has scored just one league goal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"437\" id=\"i-a8420e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-1A3D41D100000578-343_634x437.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Waste: Ricky van Wolfswinkel (left) was brought in by Chris Hughton and has scored just one league goal</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">I was relegated with Aston Villa and there is no worse feeling. Playing in the top flight gives you an enormous sense of pride and trying to get promoted the following season was the hardest of my career. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There is more than money and glamour at stake. The whole world knows about the Premier League and people don’t realise just how much that status means to a player. It is a part of who you are and, make no mistake, the players will have to fight for it on Saturday.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Praying: Sunderland are also fighting for their lives at the bottom of the Premier League\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"495\" id=\"i-a7c70e66\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-1C97783100000578-867_634x495.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Praying: Sunderland are also fighting for their lives at the bottom of the Premier League</p><div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.6em;\">PS </font></span><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sunday is the cut-off date for a two-match ban for 10 yellow cards. Steven Gerrard, Ramires, Gareth Barry, and Cheick Tiote are all on nine. All are vital for their clubs and nobody will want to sit out crucial games. Time to tread carefully.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Needed: Steven Gerrard is one booking away from a ban\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"430\" id=\"i-a72d0e50\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-079904CF00000514-630_306x430.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Risky: Ramires is also on thin ice, but the bookings reload after this weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"430\" id=\"i-a6900e47\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-054EB60900000514-250_306x430.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Thin ice: Both Steven Gerrard (left) and Ramires (right) are one booking away from a two-match ban</p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Spotlight on: Lewis Grabban, Bournemouth, Age 26</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Bournemouth are on the march and are now within touching distance of the play-offs. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They are on a good run of form, winning their last five matches, and Lewis Grabban has been a big part of that with five goals in those games. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He is an  eye-catching striker who is quick, confident in front of goal and causes problems for every defender he faces. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There was talk of him leaving in January but he signed a new deal and that is testament to the good job manager Eddie Howe is doing at the club in his second spell there. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Howe got them promoted from League One last season and they are having another good year. The positive environment he creates is a major reason why Grabban is still there and why he is in such good form.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Hit man: Grabban has scored five goals in five games, with Bournemouth on fine form\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"401\" id=\"i-9d060e40\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-1D08F89D00000578-56_634x401.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Hit man: Grabban has scored five goals in five games, with Bournemouth on fine form</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"What\'s the score: Brendan Foster\" class=\"img-no-border img-share\" height=\"669\" id=\"i-a6f70e5f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-1D09666300000578-438_634x669.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602677/Norwichs-Premier-League-survival-not-decided-Fulham-clash-insists-Neil-Adams.html\"> Norwich\'s Premier League survival will not be decided by Fulham clash, insists Adams</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602588/Hull-City-boss-Steve-Bruce-admits-wall-team-defeat-old-club-Sheffield-United-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\"> FA charge Crawley defender Connolly with violent conduct for slapping Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602720/Scott-Carson-hoping-FA-Cup-chance-Wigan-Athletic-look-repeat-Wembley-heroics.html\"> Carson hoping for Cup chance as Wigan look to repeat Wembley heroics</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\"> The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602719/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">16</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602719-1D099BDD00000578-649_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:01','2014-04-12 13:16:23'),(40,'cbbe740e4d5445511d5b34eec377e55ad463284e836eb1a67c536f5fd6df38d0','dailymail',NULL,'MASTERS 2014: Bubba Watson: I didn\'t know how to handle being Masters champion... but I\'m ready to win','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html',' By Phil Casey, Press Association Published: 06:04 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 06:04 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments Bubba Watson will have to improve on an unimpressive record to claim a second Masters title, despite holding a three-shot lead going into Saturday\'s third round. Watson has held or shared the lead after 36 holes eight times on the PGA Tour, but only converted one of those into a victory at the Zurich Classic of New Orleans in 2011. And the left-hander\'s task would not be made easier by the presence of defending champion Adam Scott on the leaderboard, the Australian recovering from three bogeys in the first five holes of his second round to lie just four off the pace.  Leader: Bubba Watson reacts after making a huge birdie putt on the 14th green on Friday   Another birdie: Watson hits his superb tee shot on the 16th hole during his second-round 68   Experience: The Florida native is bidding for a second Masters title after his victory two years ago  Watson, who adopted a month-old son with his wife Angie shortly before his Masters win in 2012, withdrew from his last event after blaming an opening 83 at the Arnold Palmer Invitational on his head being \'all discombobulated\' due to severe allergies. More... MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy to tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta But the 35-year-old from Bagdad, Florida, did claim his first PGA Tour title since the Masters in February, shooting back-to-back bogey-free rounds of 64 to win the Northern Trust Open. \'This year I\'m trying to get the (green) jacket back,\' said Watson, who had five birdies in a row from the 12th to card a 68 and finish seven under par. \'Media attention is on the defending champion. You\'re asked all these questions, can you defend, how are you going to play, how are you going to do this? You have to give up the green jacket. \'For me I didn\'t know how to handle it the best way and so I didn\'t play my best golf last year. But this year I came in here with no media attention, somehow I was lost in the crowd a little so I could go about my practice rounds without much attention.\' Australian John Senden matched Watson\'s 68 to claim second place on four under, with Thomas Bjorn also returning a 68 to lie a shot further back alongside Scott, 20-year-old American Jordan Spieth and Sweden\'s Jonas Blixt.  Lurking: Australian John Senden is Watson\'s nearest challenger, trailing by three shots   Dangerman: Defending champion Adam Scott is four shots behind Watson at the halfway stage   Looking good: Welshman Jamie Donaldson is leading the British charge on one under par  \'I was a little frail but patience came into it on the back nine and I just tried to remember all the good shots I hit on Thursday,\' said Scott, who is aiming to join Jack Nicklaus, Nick Faldo and Tiger Woods in winning back-to-back titles. \'It\'s good to be within shouting distance but Saturday is a big day for everyone. I would like to close the gap to feel in with a chance on Sunday.\' Twenty two years after winning a green jacket, 54-year-old Fred Couples was five off the pace on two under, with Scotland\'s Stephen Gallacher and Welshman Jamie Donaldson a shot further back.   More... MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy to tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Phil+Casey,+Press+Association\" rel=\"nofollow\">Phil Casey, Press Association</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 06:04 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 06:04 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Bubba: I didn\'t know how to handle being Masters champion last year... but now I\'m ready to win back the green jacket\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bubba Watson will have to improve on an unimpressive record to claim a second Masters title, despite holding a three-shot lead going into Saturday\'s third round.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Watson has held or shared the lead after 36 holes eight times on the PGA Tour, but only converted one of those into a victory at the Zurich Classic of New Orleans in 2011.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And the left-hander\'s task would not be made easier by the presence of defending champion Adam Scott on the leaderboard, the Australian recovering from three bogeys in the first five holes of his second round to lie just four off the pace.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Leader: Bubba Watson reacts after making a huge birdie putt on the 14th green on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"412\" id=\"i-a98e0e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603123-1D09B5DA00000578-475_634x412.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Leader: Bubba Watson reacts after making a huge birdie putt on the 14th green on Friday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Another birdie: Watson hits his superb tee shot on the 16th hole during his second-round 68\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-a83d0e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603123-1D09CE0800000578-226_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Another birdie: Watson hits his superb tee shot on the 16th hole during his second-round 68</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Experience: The Florida native is bidding for a second Masters title after his victory two years ago\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"382\" id=\"i-a8570e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603123-1D09E6B400000578-532_634x382.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Experience: The Florida native is bidding for a second Masters title after his victory two years ago</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Watson, who adopted a month-old son with his wife Angie shortly before his Masters win in 2012, withdrew from his last event after blaming an opening 83 at the Arnold Palmer Invitational on his head being \'all discombobulated\' due to severe allergies.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\"> MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy to tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html\"> It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602945/Masters-2014-Second-round-leaderboard-Bubba-Watson-holds-halfway-lead-Augusta.html\"> Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\"> Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602890/Stepen-Gallacher-continues-early-Masters-magic-Ian-Poulter-Justin-Rose-enjoy-good-second-day-cut-sight.html\"> McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html\"> Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But the 35-year-old from Bagdad, Florida, did claim his first PGA Tour title since the Masters in February, shooting back-to-back bogey-free rounds of 64 to win the Northern Trust Open.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'This year I\'m trying to get the (green) jacket back,\' said Watson, who had five birdies in a row from the 12th to card a 68 and finish seven under par.</font></p>\n<p>\'<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Media attention is on the defending champion. You\'re asked all these questions, can you defend, how are you going to play, how are you going to do this? You have to give up the green jacket.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'For me I didn\'t know how to handle it the best way and so I didn\'t play my best golf last year. But this year I came in here with no media attention, somehow I was lost in the crowd a little so I could go about my practice rounds without much attention.\'</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Australian John Senden matched Watson\'s 68 to claim second place on four under, with Thomas Bjorn also returning a 68 to lie a shot further back alongside Scott, 20-year-old American Jordan Spieth and Sweden\'s Jonas Blixt.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Lurking: Australian John Senden is Watson\'s nearest challenger, trailing by three shots\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-a7550e5b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603123-1D0A436A00000578-745_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Lurking: Australian John Senden is Watson\'s nearest challenger, trailing by three shots</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dangerman: Defending champion Adam Scott is four shots behind Watson at the halfway stage\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"426\" id=\"i-a5d80e4f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603123-1D0A610800000578-177_634x426.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dangerman: Defending champion Adam Scott is four shots behind Watson at the halfway stage</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Looking good: Welshman Jamie Donaldson is leading the British charge on one under par\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a8b70e69\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603123-1D0A489E00000578-497_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Looking good: Welshman Jamie Donaldson is leading the British charge on one under par</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p>\'<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I was a little frail but patience came into it on the back nine and I just tried to remember all the good shots I hit on Thursday,\' said Scott, who is aiming to join Jack Nicklaus, Nick Faldo and Tiger Woods in winning back-to-back titles.</font></p>\n<p>\'<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It\'s good to be within shouting distance but Saturday is a big day for everyone. I would like to close the gap to feel in with a chance on Sunday.\'</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Twenty two years after winning a green jacket, 54-year-old Fred Couples was five off the pace on two under, with Scotland\'s Stephen Gallacher and Welshman Jamie Donaldson a shot further back. </font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2603077/Rory-McIlroy-tee-Masters-round-just-making-halfway-cut.html\"> MASTERS THIRD ROUND TEE TIMES: McIlroy to tee off on his own after surviving halfway cut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html\"> It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602945/Masters-2014-Second-round-leaderboard-Bubba-Watson-holds-halfway-lead-Augusta.html\"> Masters 2014: Second round leaderboard - Watson holds halfway lead at Augusta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\"> Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602890/Stepen-Gallacher-continues-early-Masters-magic-Ian-Poulter-Justin-Rose-enjoy-good-second-day-cut-sight.html\"> McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html\"> Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603123/MASTERS-2014-Bubba-Watson-I-didnt-know-handle-Masters-champion-Im-ready-win.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Bubba: I didn\'t know how to handle being Masters champion last year... but now I\'m ready to win back the green jacket\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2603123/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603123-1D09CE0800000578-589_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:01','2014-04-12 13:04:36'),(41,'f02d5367077601c56cdc8e56c2d6e76a467e78f8041407aed945a2db24bc1407','dailymail',NULL,'Jose Mourinho demands cure to Chelsea travel sickness to sustain Premier League title push at Swansea City','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603108/Jose-Mourinho-demands-cure-Chelsea-travel-sickness-sustain-Premier-League-title-push-Swansea-City.html',' By Matt Mcgeehan, Press Association Published: 05:55 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 05:55 EST, 12 April 2014 30 shares 9 View comments  Jose Mourinho has called on Chelsea to end their three-match losing streak on the road by demonstrating more of the togetherness that saw them to a famous win over Paris St Germain in midweek. The Blues travel to Swansea on Sunday on the back of defeats to Aston Villa, Crystal Palace and PSG in successive games on their travels, and need to stop the rot to keep their Barclays Premier League title hopes from receding further. Chelsea looked much improved from those three defeats as they beat PSG 2-0 at Stamford Bridge on Tuesday to secure an away-goals win that tees up a Champions League semi-final with Atletico Madrid.  Improvement needed: Jose Mourinho wants Chelsea to arrest their recent away day slump when they travel to Swansea City in the Premier League on Sunday   Own goal: John Terry put through his own net to gift Crystal Palace a 1-0 victory in the Premier League at the end of March   Stunned: Mourinho looks out in amazement as Chelsea lost 3-1 to Paris Saint-Germain in the first leg of their Champions League tie   In the hunt: Chelsea have a chance of winning the Premier League but are third favourites behind Liverpool and Manchester City  More... Everton boss Martinez keen to sign on-loan Lukaku on a permanent deal from Chelsea Chelsea to face Courtois as UEFA tell Blues they can\'t stop Atletico keeper playing Chelsea No 2 Courtois can become world No 1, claims Blues coach Lollichon SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race Looking ahead to the match with Swansea at the Liberty Stadium, Mourinho said: \'They are a good team, they play good football. \'Especially at Swansea it is never easy and Chelsea knows that better than other teams. \'They still need the three points, they are not in big danger like other teams but they still need a couple of points to stay in the Premier League and of course they will try to get points out of this game.\' Eden Hazard is out with a calf injury, but Nemanja Matic and Mohamed Salah are available after being ineligible in Europe and Ramires is back from a three-match ban. Striker Demba Ba could be given a first Premier League start since October at Norwich after his midweek heroics against PSG.  Back again: Mohamed Salah, who scored against Stoke City last weekend, is available for selection against Swansea   Hero: Demba Ba could be handed a first Premier League start since October following his midweek winner against PSG  CHELSEA\'S TITLE RUN-IN April 13 Swansea City (A)April 19 Sunderland (H)April 27 Liverpool (A)May 4 Norwich (H)May 11 Cardiff City (A) \'People are working well and hard,\' Mourinho added. \'The ones that are not playing so regular, all of them are being good professionals to try to be ready. \'You could see Demba as an example as a player who doesn\'t play a lot and was ready to try to respond. \'All of them, they were ready. They are a good group, they are good friends, they have a good relationship. \'I think when one of them goes onto the pitch he goes to help the other players.\' Chelsea play at the Liberty Stadium after the weekend\'s crunch game at Anfield, although Mourinho does not plan to watch Liverpool versus Manchester City. \'Maybe it is a historical day for football and they both win,\' he said.  More... Everton boss Martinez keen to sign on-loan Lukaku on a permanent deal from Chelsea Chelsea to face Courtois as UEFA tell Blues they can\'t stop Atletico keeper playing Chelsea No 2 Courtois can become world No 1, claims Blues coach Lollichon SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race  Share or comment on this article 30shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Matt+Mcgeehan,+Press+Association\" rel=\"nofollow\">Matt Mcgeehan, Press Association</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 05:55 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=