> Chelsea No 2 Courtois can become world No 1, claims Blues coach Lollichon</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601501/SWANSEA-vs-CHELSEA-All-latest-team-news-stats-visitors-aim-regain-ground-title-race.html\"> SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603108/Jose-Mourinho-demands-cure-Chelsea-travel-sickness-sustain-Premier-League-title-push-Swansea-City.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603108/Jose-Mourinho-demands-cure-Chelsea-travel-sickness-sustain-Premier-League-title-push-Swansea-City.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Mourinho demands cure to Chelsea travel sickness to keep Premier League title hopes alive at Swansea\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603108/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">30</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603108-1CC5B85500000578-842_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:02','2014-04-12 12:55:18'),(42,'ce62cd9cb18e89b80b8ad9f8395a6141af567c3b564d7ed982dc140cd65c2515','dailymail',NULL,'Everton boss Roberto Martinez keen to sign on-loan Roberto Lukaku on a permanent deal from Chelsea','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603070/Everton-boss-Roberto-Martinez-keen-sign-loan-Roberto-Lukaku-permanent-deal-Chelsea.html',' By John Drayton Published: 04:01 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 05:51 EST, 12 April 2014 18 shares 64 View comments Everton boss Roberto Martinez has admitted he is keen on signing on-loan forward Romelu Lukaku on a permanent basis in the summer. Lukaku has been a revelation at Goodison Park since joining the Toffees on a season-long deal in September, having scored 14 goals in all competitions so far.  Wanted: Everton boss Roberto Martinez has admitted he wants to sign Romelu Lukaku on a permanent deal     Stellar campaign: Martinez\'s Everton are in the hunt for UEFA Champions League for the first time in nine years  Martinez recently revealed that the Merseyside outfit has more than £20million to spend for the next campaign even if the club don\'t qualify for next season\'s UEFA Champions League - with the Spaniard prepared to spend a large amount of that on the 20-year-old.   Speaking about Lukaku\'s future, Martinez is clear that he should stay with Everton where he is playing regularly. He said: \'I think if there is something we can give that he can’t get elsewhere it’s enjoying his football.    Joy: Lukaku (right) celebrates with Martinez (left) after scoring in Everton\'s 3-0 win vs Arsenal last weekend  \'In football, as a player, you can take football happiness for granted very quickly. As a young man to be important in a football club and being happy is vital. \'Nobody can guarantee you that unless you’ve experienced it, or know who you are going to work with. It’s as simple as that really.\'   More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place SUNDERLAND vs EVERTON: All the latest team news and stats as visitors maintain charge for the Champions League Mourinho is a specialist in winning while Arsenal are just laughable... it\'s the reader comments of the week Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Martinez blasts loan criticism as \'ridiculous\' and \'lazy\' as Everton march towards Europe Everton currently sit fifth in the Barclays Premier League but victory at relegation-threatened Sunderland on Saturday would see the side move above Arsenal with five games to go. At present Lukaku\'s future is unclear, with his parent club Chelsea unsure whether or not to keep the striker next season.  Blue is the colour: Lukaku joined parent club Chelsea from Belgian side Anderlecht for £18million in 2011     The Belgian international joined the Blues from Anderlecht for £18 million in 2011 but he could be used by Chelsea boss Jose Mourinho as part of a deal to bring Atletico Madrid talisman Diego Costa to Stamford Bridge. Another reason why Martinez is keen to keep hold of the Belgian international is because it will save Everton having to find a ready-made replacement that suits their style of play.  Bargaining tool? Chelsea may use Lukaku as part of a deal to sign Atletico Madrid star Diego Costa    The Spaniard added: \'You are not gambling on him doing things well, because you know what he can bring and it’s a perfect fit in that respect. \'I think if you look at the way he has developed this season he’s aware of that. \'If we can extend his stay then fantastic, if not we will have great memories.\' Everton will also sit down with Lukaku’s compatriot Kevin Mirallas in the summer to discuss a new contract for the forward with his current deal set to expire in 2016.  New deal: Everton will open talks with Kevin Mirallas (second left) over a extending his contract beyond 2016     Share or comment on this article 18shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Drayton\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Drayton</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 04:01 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 05:51 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603070/Everton-boss-Roberto-Martinez-keen-sign-loan-Roberto-Lukaku-permanent-deal-Chelsea.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603070/Everton-boss-Roberto-Martinez-keen-sign-loan-Roberto-Lukaku-permanent-deal-Chelsea.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Everton boss Martinez keen to sign on-loan Lukaku on a permanent deal from Chelsea\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 18</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603070/Everton-boss-Roberto-Martinez-keen-sign-loan-Roberto-Lukaku-permanent-deal-Chelsea.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">64</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Everton boss Roberto Martinez has admitted he is keen on signing on-loan forward Romelu Lukaku on a permanent basis in the summer.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Lukaku has been a revelation at Goodison Park since joining the Toffees on a season-long deal in September, having scored 14 goals in all competitions so far.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wanted: Everton boss Roberto Martinez has admitted he wants to sign Romelu Lukaku on a permanent deal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-a6cd0e54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603070-1CF1390400000578-629_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wanted: Everton boss Roberto Martinez has admitted he wants to sign Romelu Lukaku on a permanent deal</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Stellar campaign: Martinez\'s Everton are in the hunt for UEFA Champions League for the first time in nine years\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"491\" id=\"i-a6b50e54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603070-1CE2476100000578-117_634x491.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Stellar campaign: Martinez\'s Everton are in the hunt for UEFA Champions League for the first time in nine years</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Martinez recently revealed that the Merseyside outfit has more than £20million to spend for the next campaign even if the club don\'t qualify for next season\'s UEFA Champions League - with the Spaniard prepared to spend a large amount of that on the 20-year-old.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Speaking about Lukaku\'s future, Martinez is clear that he should stay with Everton where he is playing regularly. He said:</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I think if there is something we can give that he can’t get elsewhere it’s enjoying his football.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Joy: Lukaku (right) celebrates with Martinez (left) after scoring in Everton\'s 3-0 win vs Arsenal last weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-9cd90e3f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603070-1CE1FF2400000578-83_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Joy: Lukaku (right) celebrates with Martinez (left) after scoring in Everton\'s 3-0 win vs Arsenal last weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'In football, as a player, you can take football happiness for granted very quickly. As a young man to be important in a football club and being happy is vital.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Nobody can guarantee you that unless you’ve experienced it, or know who you are going to work with. It’s as simple as that really.\'<br/></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600813/SUNDERLAND-vs-EVERTON-All-latest-team-news-stats-visitors-maintain-charge-Champions-League.html\"> SUNDERLAND vs EVERTON: All the latest team news and stats as visitors maintain charge for the Champions League</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602626/Jose-Mourinho-specialist-winning-Arsenal-laughable-reader-comments-week.html\"> Mourinho is a specialist in winning while Arsenal are just laughable... it\'s the reader comments of the week</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601623/Roberto-Martinez-defends-Evertons-loan-tactics-slamming-ridiculous-critics.html\"> Martinez blasts loan criticism as \'ridiculous\' and \'lazy\' as Everton march towards Europe</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Everton currently sit fifth in the Barclays Premier League but victory at relegation-threatened Sunderland on Saturday would see the side move above Arsenal with five games to go.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">At present Lukaku\'s future is unclear, with his parent club Chelsea unsure whether or not to keep the striker next season.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Blue is the colour: Lukaku joined parent club Chelsea from Belgian side Anderlecht for £18million in 2011\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-ac270e89\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603070-1ADC70AD000005DC-213_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Blue is the colour: Lukaku joined parent club Chelsea from Belgian side Anderlecht for £18million in 2011</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Belgian international joined the Blues from Anderlecht for £18 million in 2011 but he could be used by Chelsea boss Jose Mourinho as part of a deal to bring Atletico Madrid talisman Diego Costa to Stamford Bridge.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Another reason why Martinez is keen to keep hold of the Belgian international is because it will save Everton having to find a ready-made replacement that suits their style of play.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bargaining tool? Chelsea may use Lukaku as part of a deal to sign Atletico Madrid star Diego Costa\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"451\" id=\"i-a8120e5e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603070-1CF05A2900000578-261_634x451.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bargaining tool? Chelsea may use Lukaku as part of a deal to sign Atletico Madrid star Diego Costa</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Spaniard added: \'You are not gambling on him doing things well, because you know what he can bring and it’s a perfect fit in that respect.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I think if you look at the way he has developed this season he’s aware of that.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'If we can extend his stay then fantastic, if not we will have great memories.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Everton will also sit down with Lukaku’s compatriot Kevin Mirallas in the summer to discuss a new contract for the forward with his current deal set to expire in 2016.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"New deal: Everton will open talks with Kevin Mirallas (second left) over a extending his contract beyond 2016\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a58e0e45\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603070-1CE2203300000578-450_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">New deal: Everton will open talks with Kevin Mirallas (second left) over a extending his contract beyond 2016</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603070/Everton-boss-Roberto-Martinez-keen-sign-loan-Roberto-Lukaku-permanent-deal-Chelsea.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603070/Everton-boss-Roberto-Martinez-keen-sign-loan-Roberto-Lukaku-permanent-deal-Chelsea.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Everton boss Martinez keen to sign on-loan Lukaku on a permanent deal from Chelsea\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603070/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">18</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603070-1CF1390400000578-230_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:02','2014-04-12 12:51:34'),(43,'b20ae35fec324536ae6f2b84dce2fcdd7cac7b37c878ae1eeb8df944fb06161f','dailymail',NULL,'Manchester City must beat bogey teams in Liverpool, Everton and Crystal Palace to win Premier League','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603068/Manchester-City-beat-bogey-teams-Liverpool-Everton-Crystal-Palace-win-Premier-League.html',' By Nick Harris Published: 04:01 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 04:24 EST, 12 April 2014 14 shares 7 View comments  With seven matches remaining to Liverpool\'s five, and just four points to make up, the destiny of the Premier League title is still in Manchester City\'s hands. Four of those seven are at home and coming against Sunderland, West Bromwich, Aston Villa and West Ham, should yield a maximum 12 points from 12. But the three outstanding away fixtures - at Liverpool, Crystal Palace and Everton - will be a real source of trepidation for City fans.  Apprehensive: Manuel Pellegrini\'s Manchester City still have their title destiny in their hands but face three away games in the run-in at teams they traditionally perform badly against - Liverpool, Everton and Crystal Palace   Tough: City have seven games remaining to overhaul Liverpool\'s four-point advantage, starting with a trip to Anfield this weekend   On course: City beat Southampton 4-1 last weekend to continue their title charge   Home stretch: City enjoy two games in hand on Liverpool but can\'t afford any slip-ups  TRAVEL SICKNESS CITY\'S AWAY RECORD VS LIVERPOOLPlayed 16 Won 1 Drawn 5 Lost 10Average points gained 0.5CITY\'S AWAY RECORD VS EVERTONPlayed 16 Won 2 Drawn 4 Lost 10Average points gained 0.63CITY\'S AWAY RECORD VS PALACEPlayed 3 Won 1 Drawn 1 Lost 1 Average points gained 1.33 They have rarely performed well on Merseyside during the Premier League era, and have only won once at Palace in three attempts. City travel to Anfield for Sunday\'s title showdown having only won there once in 16 attempts since 1992. They have managed five draws and lost on 10 occasions, with that sole victory coming way back in May 2003 when a late Nicolas Anelka goal handed them a 2-1 win. City have played 44 different opponents during the Premier League era and they have worse away records against only Arsenal (17 matches, 1 win) and Cardiff (1 match, 0 wins). Their record at Everton, where they visit on May 3, is almost as bad. With just two victories from 16 attempts, it\'s City\'s sixth worst opponent on the road.  Repeat performance? Man City lifted the Premier League title in 2012   Rare success: Nicolas Anelka scored twice the last time City won at Anfield - a 2-1 scoreline back in May 2003   Him again: Anelka also scored twice when Manchester City recorded their only win at Crystal Palace back in September 2004   Enlarge   On the road: Manchester City\'s away record against the 44 opponents they have faced in the Premier League era  CITY\'S TITLE RUN-IN April 13 Liverpool (A)April 16 Sunderland (H)April 21 West Bromwich (H)April 27 Crystal Palace (A)May 3 Everton (A)May 7 Aston Villa (H)May 11 West Ham (H) City must also go to Crystal Palace on April 27 and have won just one of their three encounters at Selhurst Park. That win came in September 2004 and, funnily enough, it was Nicolas Anelka who again scored the winner. With the margins so thin in this most gripping of Premier League title races, and any dropped points potentially fatal, City must re-write history to make history. You can read more on the Sporting Intelligence website here   More... Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield? From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders MARTIN KEOWN: Suarez, Sturridge and Sterling over Aguero and Co... why Liverpool have the edge in my combined title-chasing XI Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure   Share or comment on this article 14shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Nick+Harris\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nick Harris</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 04:01 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 04:24 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603068/Manchester-City-beat-bogey-teams-Liverpool-Everton-Crystal-Palace-win-Premier-League.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603068/Manchester-City-beat-bogey-teams-Liverpool-Everton-Crystal-Palace-win-Premier-League.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Man City\'s reasons to be fearful... Premier League title chasers must visit three bogey teams in Liverpool, Everton and Palace to lift the trophy\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 14</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603068/Manchester-City-beat-bogey-teams-Liverpool-Everton-Crystal-Palace-win-Premier-League.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">7</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With seven matches remaining to Liverpool\'s five, and just four points to make up, the destiny of the Premier League title is still in Manchester City\'s hands. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Four of those seven are at home and coming against Sunderland, West Bromwich, Aston Villa and West Ham, should yield a maximum 12 points from 12.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But the three outstanding away fixtures - at Liverpool, Crystal Palace and Everton - will be a real source of trepidation for City fans. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Apprehensive: Manuel Pellegrini\'s Manchester City still have their title destiny in their hands but face three away games in the run-in at teams they traditionally perform badly against - Liverpool, Everton and Crystal Palace\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"411\" id=\"i-9c360e39\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-1D07BD7500000578-95_634x411.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Apprehensive: Manuel Pellegrini\'s Manchester City still have their title destiny in their hands but face three away games in the run-in at teams they traditionally perform badly against - Liverpool, Everton and Crystal Palace</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tough: City have seven games remaining to overhaul Liverpool\'s four-point advantage, starting with a trip to Anfield this weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"428\" id=\"i-ac100e8a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-1B9E89BA00000578-637_634x428.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tough: City have seven games remaining to overhaul Liverpool\'s four-point advantage, starting with a trip to Anfield this weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On course: City beat Southampton 4-1 last weekend to continue their title charge\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"411\" id=\"i-ac810e8a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-1CDB06EB00000578-679_634x411.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On course: City beat Southampton 4-1 last weekend to continue their title charge</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Home stretch: City enjoy two games in hand on Liverpool but can\'t afford any slip-ups\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"403\" id=\"i-a0200e5e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-1CEC5DF800000578-94_634x403.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Home stretch: City enjoy two games in hand on Liverpool but can\'t afford any slip-ups</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>TRAVEL SICKNESS</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">CITY\'S AWAY RECORD VS LIVERPOOL</font></b><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Played </b>16 <b>Won </b>1 <b>Drawn </b>5 <b>Lost </b>10</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Average points gained</b> 0.5</font><br/><br/><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">CITY\'S AWAY RECORD VS EVERTON</font></b><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Played </b>16 <b>Won </b>2 <b>Drawn </b>4 <b>Lost </b>10</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Average points gained</b> 0.63</font><br/><br/><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">CITY\'S AWAY RECORD VS PALACE</font></b><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Played </b>3 <b>Won </b>1 <b>Drawn </b>1 <b>Lost </b>1 </font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Average points gained</b> 1.33</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They have rarely performed well on Merseyside during the Premier League era, and have only won once at Palace in three attempts.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">City travel to Anfield for Sunday\'s title showdown having only won there once in 16 attempts since 1992. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They have managed five draws and lost on 10 occasions, with that sole victory coming way back in May 2003 when a late Nicolas Anelka goal handed them a 2-1 win. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">City have played 44 different opponents during the Premier League era and they have worse away records against only Arsenal (17 matches, 1 win) and Cardiff (1 match, 0 wins). </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Their record at Everton, where they visit on May 3, is almost as bad. With just two victories from 16 attempts, it\'s City\'s sixth worst opponent on the road. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Repeat performance? Man City lifted the Premier League title in 2012\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"449\" id=\"i-abad0e94\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-16AAC0A0000005DC-779_634x449.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Repeat performance? Man City lifted the Premier League title in 2012</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rare success: Nicolas Anelka scored twice the last time City won at Anfield - a 2-1 scoreline back in May 2003\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"665\" id=\"i-a5190e4d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-00640F4300000258-793_634x665.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rare success: Nicolas Anelka scored twice the last time City won at Anfield - a 2-1 scoreline back in May 2003</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Him again: Anelka also scored twice when Manchester City recorded their only win at Crystal Palace back in September 2004\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"397\" id=\"i-a5c70e58\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-0193217B0000044D-508_634x397.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Him again: Anelka also scored twice when Manchester City recorded their only win at Crystal Palace back in September 2004</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <a class=\"lightboxPopupLink\" href=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-1D0BA3CA00000578-967_634x871_popup.jpg\" onclick=\"return false;\" rel=\"\"> <span class=\"clickToEnlargeTop\">Enlarge</span> <span class=\"clickToEnlarge\"></span> <span class=\"clickToEnlargeButton\"> </span> <img alt=\"On the road: Manchester City\'s away record against the 44 opponents they have faced in the Premier League era\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"871\" id=\"i-abcb0e8c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-1D0BA3CA00000578-967_634x871.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </a> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the road: Manchester City\'s away record against the 44 opponents they have faced in the Premier League era</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>CITY\'S TITLE RUN-IN</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 13</b> Liverpool (A)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 16</b> Sunderland (H)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 21</b> West Bromwich (H)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 27</b> Crystal Palace (A)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>May 3</b> Everton (A)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>May 7</b> Aston Villa (H)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>May 11</b> West Ham (H)</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">City must also go to Crystal Palace on April 27 and have won just one of their three encounters at Selhurst Park.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That win came in September 2004 and, funnily enough, it was Nicolas Anelka who again scored the winner. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With the margins so thin in this most gripping of Premier League title races, and any dropped points potentially fatal, City must re-write history to make history. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><i><a href=\"http://www.sportingintelligence.com/2014/04/11/four-wins-in-35-man-citys-pl-record-at-liverpool-palace-and-everton-combined-110401/\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">You can read more on the Sporting Intelligence website here</a></i><br/></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\"> Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\"> From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602889/Suarez-Sturridge-Sterling-Aguero-Co-Liverpool-edge-combined-title-chasing-XI.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN: Suarez, Sturridge and Sterling over Aguero and Co... why Liverpool have the edge in my combined title-chasing XI</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\"> Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602389/Aguero-fit-Liverpool-clash-City-striker-recovers-hamstring-injury.html\"> Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603068/Manchester-City-beat-bogey-teams-Liverpool-Everton-Crystal-Palace-win-Premier-League.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603068/Manchester-City-beat-bogey-teams-Liverpool-Everton-Crystal-Palace-win-Premier-League.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Man City\'s reasons to be fearful... Premier League title chasers must visit three bogey teams in Liverpool, Everton and Palace to lift the trophy\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603068/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">14</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603068-1D0BB59C00000578-15_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:02','2014-04-12 11:24:51'),(44,'af2dfb02cf5e891966ea034e3e9781b3e0182026fab403170fbdeb59a4c4b724','dailymail',NULL,'Roy Nelson may have broken his hand in first-round win over Antonio Rodrigo Nogueira','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602835/Roy-Nelson-broken-hand-round-win-Antonio-Rodrigo-Nogueira.html',' By Martin Domin Follow @@martin_domin Published: 15:52 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 03:55 EST, 12 April 2014 6 shares 6 View comments  Roy Nelson feared he had broken his hand after a brutal one-punch knockout stopped Antonio Rodrigo Nogueira in his tracks on Friday night. The first-round stoppage ensured Nelson snapped a two-fight losing streak in Abu Dhabi. And the heavyweight then demanded a title shot against champion Cain Velasquez.  Winner: Roy Nelson celebrates his knockout victory against Antonio Rodrigo Nogueira   One-punch: Nelson connects with a right and knocks out Nogueira in the first round  More... Munoz and Mousasi gear up for Berlin clash as middleweights bid to bounce back UFC 171: Hendricks crowned welterweight champion after absorbing battle with Lawler Gustafsson delivers stunning KO to stop Manuwa and set up potential Jones rematch Arsenal trio Gibbs, Oxlade-Chamberlain and Bendtner celebrate FA Cup win with night out at UFC... and Haye was there too Fighting on: Griffin coming to terms with retirement after calling time on career GUNNAR NELSON: Had we gone a metre more, not everyone would have survived ‘I was expecting a five round battle but things ended a little early,’ he said. ‘Nog has an incredibly hard head, I think I broke my hand. My game plan was to throw more lefts and mix in some takedowns and eventually try to win each round. ‘I didn’t think I was going to be the hometown favorite but Abu Dhabi really was behind me tonight. For my next opponent I want Cain Velazquez because I prefer to move backwards in calling out my opponents.’ For Nogueira, this was his second defeat in succession following a second-round submission defeat to Fabricio Werdum last June.  Arm aloft: Nelson fears he may have broken his hand with the punch in Abu Dhabi   Off we go: UFC Octagon Girl Carly Baker poses before the fight   More... Munoz and Mousasi gear up for Berlin clash as middleweights bid to bounce back UFC 171: Hendricks crowned welterweight champion after absorbing battle with Lawler Gustafsson delivers stunning KO to stop Manuwa and set up potential Jones rematch Arsenal trio Gibbs, Oxlade-Chamberlain and Bendtner celebrate FA Cup win with night out at UFC... and Haye was there too Fighting on: Griffin coming to terms with retirement after calling time on career GUNNAR NELSON: Had we gone a metre more, not everyone would have survived    Share or comment on this article 6shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Martin+Domin\" rel=\"nofollow\">Martin Domin</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@martin_domin\">Follow @@martin_domin</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 15:52 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 03:55 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602835/Roy-Nelson-broken-hand-round-win-Antonio-Rodrigo-Nogueira.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602835/Roy-Nelson-broken-hand-round-win-Antonio-Rodrigo-Nogueira.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Nelson stuns Nogueira with brutal KO in first round as heavyweights thrill Abu Dhabi\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 6</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2602835/Roy-Nelson-broken-hand-round-win-Antonio-Rodrigo-Nogueira.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">6</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Roy Nelson feared he had broken his hand after a brutal one-punch knockout stopped Antonio Rodrigo Nogueira in his tracks on Friday night.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The first-round stoppage ensured Nelson snapped a two-fight losing streak in Abu Dhabi.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And the heavyweight then demanded a title shot against champion Cain Velasquez.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Winner: Roy Nelson celebrates his knockout victory against Antonio Rodrigo Nogueira\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"418\" id=\"i-ab700e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602835-1D09EBC500000578-894_634x418.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Winner: Roy Nelson celebrates his knockout victory against Antonio Rodrigo Nogueira</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"One-punch: Nelson connects with a right and knocks out Nogueira in the first round\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"405\" id=\"i-aa390e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602835-1D09EB0A00000578-842_634x405.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">One-punch: Nelson connects with a right and knocks out Nogueira in the first round</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2595955/Munoz-Mousasi-gear-Berlin-clash-middleweights-bid-bounce-back.html\"> Munoz and Mousasi gear up for Berlin clash as middleweights bid to bounce back</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2581978/UFC-171-Hendricks-crowned-welterweight-champion-absorbing-battle-Lawler.html\"> UFC 171: Hendricks crowned welterweight champion after absorbing battle with Lawler</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2576506/Gustafsson-delivers-stunning-KO-stop-Manuwa-set-potential-Jones-rematch.html\"> Gustafsson delivers stunning KO to stop Manuwa and set up potential Jones rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2576515/Alex-Oxlade-Chamberlain-Kieran-Gibbs-David-Haye-Nicklas-Bendtner-attend-UFC-Fight-Night-O2-Arena.html\"> Arsenal trio Gibbs, Oxlade-Chamberlain and Bendtner celebrate FA Cup win with night out at UFC... and Haye was there too</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2574272/Fighting-Griffin-coming-terms-retirement-calling-time-career.html\"> Fighting on: Griffin coming to terms with retirement after calling time on career</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2574347/GUNNAR-NELSON-Had-gone-metre-not-survived.html\"> GUNNAR NELSON: Had we gone a metre more, not everyone would have survived</a></li> </ul> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I was expecting a five round battle but things ended a little early,’ he said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘Nog has an incredibly hard head, I think I broke my hand.  <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">My game plan was to throw more lefts and mix in some takedowns and eventually try to win each round.  </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I didn’t think I was going to be the hometown favorite but Abu Dhabi really was behind me tonight.  <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">For my next opponent I want Cain Velazquez because I prefer to move backwards in calling out my opponents.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">For Nogueira, this was his second defeat in succession following a second-round submission defeat to Fabricio Werdum last June. <div class=\"iframely-widget-container\" style=\"left: 0px; width: 100%; height: 0px; position: relative; padding-bottom: 56%;\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"true\" class=\"iframely-widget iframely-iframe\" frameborder=\"0\" mozallowfullscreen=\"true\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/AoPcZozVU_Y?rel=0\" style=\"top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div><br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Arm aloft: Nelson fears he may have broken his hand with the punch in Abu Dhabi\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"418\" id=\"i-aa3a0e78\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602835-1D09EA0A00000578-546_634x418.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Arm aloft: Nelson fears he may have broken his hand with the punch in Abu Dhabi</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Off we go: UFC Octagon Girl Carly Baker poses before the fight\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"453\" id=\"i-a9ad0e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602835-1D09D67B00000578-904_634x453.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Off we go: UFC Octagon Girl Carly Baker poses before the fight</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2595955/Munoz-Mousasi-gear-Berlin-clash-middleweights-bid-bounce-back.html\"> Munoz and Mousasi gear up for Berlin clash as middleweights bid to bounce back</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2581978/UFC-171-Hendricks-crowned-welterweight-champion-absorbing-battle-Lawler.html\"> UFC 171: Hendricks crowned welterweight champion after absorbing battle with Lawler</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2576506/Gustafsson-delivers-stunning-KO-stop-Manuwa-set-potential-Jones-rematch.html\"> Gustafsson delivers stunning KO to stop Manuwa and set up potential Jones rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2576515/Alex-Oxlade-Chamberlain-Kieran-Gibbs-David-Haye-Nicklas-Bendtner-attend-UFC-Fight-Night-O2-Arena.html\"> Arsenal trio Gibbs, Oxlade-Chamberlain and Bendtner celebrate FA Cup win with night out at UFC... and Haye was there too</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2574272/Fighting-Griffin-coming-terms-retirement-calling-time-career.html\"> Fighting on: Griffin coming to terms with retirement after calling time on career</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2574347/GUNNAR-NELSON-Had-gone-metre-not-survived.html\"> GUNNAR NELSON: Had we gone a metre more, not everyone would have survived</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602835/Roy-Nelson-broken-hand-round-win-Antonio-Rodrigo-Nogueira.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602835/Roy-Nelson-broken-hand-round-win-Antonio-Rodrigo-Nogueira.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Nelson stuns Nogueira with brutal KO in first round as heavyweights thrill Abu Dhabi\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602835/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">6</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602835-1D09EBC500000578-121_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:03','2014-04-12 10:55:08'),(45,'08d49db51192e7d098cc23470a4b9490f26985f566df88d8f758a548fb5f1895','dailymail',NULL,'JOHNNY NELSON: Pacquiao is on the slide, I\'m backing Bradley to repeat his victory','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602975/JOHNNY-NELSON-Pacquiao-slide-Im-backing-Bradley-repeat-victory.html',' By Johnny Nelson Published: 03:13 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 03:13 EST, 12 April 2014 0 View comments  Manny Pacquiao is still brilliant but he is on the slide and is not the man he once was. But his average is everybody else\'s outstanding so Timothy Bradley has to be on top form if he is to beat him for a second time in Las Vegas on Saturday night.  The first fight was very tight to call and this will decide it all. Both fighters are at different stages in their careers and a lot has changed since the first fight and that’s why I think Bradley will edge it.  Looking good: Timothy Bradley plans to stun Manny Pacquiao for a second time in their rematch in Las Vegas   Can\'t hear you: Bradley remains underrated, particularly compared to the ever-popular Pacquiao   I was at that fight two years ago and the after party was not set up for Bradley to win. It wasn’t expected to be done but he shut the shop. It was mad to suggest he would get the win, never mind the decision.  I saw him first hand, he had a great game plan, he was an excellent physical specimen and a good boxing brain. Timothy Bradley is a rising star and he’s getting better and better with every performance but he’s not getting the credit he’s due. That must be incredibly frustrating for him. He has gone up a notch since the first fight, beating Ruslan Provodnikov and Juan Manuel Marquez. He has been hurt and he feels as though he\'s got something to prove. He\'s in a very strong position and is just on the brow of that hill.   Shock: Pacquiao was the overwhelming favourite to beat Bradley in 2012 but lost on points   Tough: Bradley has never received the recognition he deserves for his victories in recent years   Pacquiao has to use speed, movement and consistent, unpredictable pressure if he is to win the fight. What I mean by that is he needs to use a tormenting pressure like he did against Oscar De La Hoya. He was in, he was out; he was in, he was out. He wouldn’t give De La Hoya breathing space and that\'s what he\'s got to do with Bradley. The problem is, Bradley can also do that but his work is not as tidy as an on-form Pacquiao but we’re talking about of Pacquiao of old – he wouldn’t have been knocked sparked out by Marquez so we know he\'s slipping and he\'s making mistakes.  That\'s why I see Bradley winning on points in a close decision.   Rolling back the years: Pacquiao must pressure Bradley in the same way he did to Oscar De La Hoya   Still got it? Many have questioned if Pacquiao is still capable of re-producing the performances of yesteryear    More... Millions involved and revenge at stake... Pacquiao vs Bradley has the potential to be the most epic contest in years PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley Is Pacquiao all talk? Unbeaten Bradley thinks so as he seeks public redemption in grudge Vegas rematch Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach Pacquiao dismisses Bradley\'s claim he has lost killer instinct ahead of rematch Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch      Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1092731/Johnny-Nelson.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Johnny Nelson</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 03:13 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 03:13 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602975/JOHNNY-NELSON-Pacquiao-slide-Im-backing-Bradley-repeat-victory.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602975/JOHNNY-NELSON-Pacquiao-slide-Im-backing-Bradley-repeat-victory.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"JOHNNY NELSON: Pacquiao has to roll back the years... but I\'m backing Bradley\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602975/JOHNNY-NELSON-Pacquiao-slide-Im-backing-Bradley-repeat-victory.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Manny Pacquiao is still brilliant but he is on the slide and is not the man he once was.<br/></font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But his average is everybody else\'s outstanding so Timothy Bradley has to be on top form if he is to beat him for a second time in Las Vegas on Saturday night.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\"></span></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The first fight was very tight to call and this will decide it all. Both fighters are at different stages in their careers and a lot has changed since the first fight and that’s why I think Bradley will edge it. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Looking good: Timothy Bradley plans to stun Manny Pacquiao for a second time in their rematch in Las Vegas\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5d0e0d3a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A8F6600000578-475_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Looking good: Timothy Bradley plans to stun Manny Pacquiao for a second time in their rematch in Las Vegas</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Timothy Bradley stands on a scale during weigh-in at the MGM Grand Arena in Las Vegas\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-5dba0d3d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A7A9B00000578-845_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Manny Pacquiao and Timothy Bradley stand toe to toe\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-5beb0d2a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A862D00000578-346_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Can\'t hear you: Bradley remains underrated, particularly compared to the ever-popular Pacquiao<br/></p></div> <p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">I was at that fight two years ago and the after party was not set up for Bradley to win. It wasn’t expected to be done but he shut the shop. It was mad to suggest he would get the win, never mind the decision.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">I saw him first hand, he had a great game plan, he was an excellent physical specimen and a good boxing brain. </font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Timothy Bradley is a rising star and he’s getting better and better with every performance but he’s not getting the credit he’s due. That must be incredibly frustrating for him.<br/></font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He has gone up a notch since the first fight, beating Ruslan Provodnikov and Juan Manuel Marquez. He has been hurt and he feels as though he\'s got something to prove. He\'s in a very strong position and is just on the brow of that hill.  </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Shock: Pacquiao was the overwhelming favourite to beat Bradley in 2012 but lost on points\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"459\" id=\"i-5c890d40\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-138918AF000005DC-210_634x459.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Shock: Pacquiao was the overwhelming favourite to beat Bradley in 2012 but lost on points</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tough: Bradley has never received the recognition he deserves for his victories in recent years\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"460\" id=\"i-5b850d31\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1389299A000005DC-340_634x460.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tough: Bradley has never received the recognition he deserves for his victories in recent years</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pacquiao has to use speed, movement and consistent, unpredictable pressure if he is to win the fight. What I mean by that is he needs to use a tormenting pressure like he did against Oscar De La Hoya. He was in, he was out; he was in, he was out. He wouldn’t give De La Hoya breathing space and that\'s what he\'s got to do with Bradley.</font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The problem is, Bradley can also do that but his work is not as tidy as an on-form Pacquiao but we’re talking about of Pacquiao of old – he wouldn’t have been knocked sparked out by Marquez so we know he\'s slipping and he\'s making mistakes. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That\'s why I see Bradley winning on points in a close decision.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rolling back the years: Pacquiao must pressure Bradley in the same way he did to Oscar De La Hoya\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"403\" id=\"i-aa4c0e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602975-1D0B926F00000578-952_634x403.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rolling back the years: Pacquiao must pressure Bradley in the same way he did to Oscar De La Hoya</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Still got it? Many have questioned if Pacquiao is still capable of re-producing the performances of yesteryear\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"399\" id=\"i-a8f10e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602975-1D0B926700000578-292_634x399.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Still got it? Many have questioned if Pacquiao is still capable of re-producing the performances of yesteryear</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602774/Manny-Pacquiao-Tim-Bradley-bout-potential-epic.html\"> Millions involved and revenge at stake... Pacquiao vs Bradley has the potential to be the most epic contest in years</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601650/PacMan-people-Mannys-superstar-statesman-entertains-serves-fellow-Filipinos-Jeff-Powell.html\"> PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2599238/Is-Pacquiao-talk-Unbeaten-Bradley-thinks-seeks-public-redemption-grudge-Vegas-rematch.html\"> Is Pacquiao all talk? Unbeaten Bradley thinks so as he seeks public redemption in grudge Vegas rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html\"> Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2599973/Pacquiao-dismisses-Bradleys-claim-lost-killer-instinct-ahead-rematch.html\"> Pacquiao dismisses Bradley\'s claim he has lost killer instinct ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600995/Tim-Bradley-nearly-committed-suicide-Manny-Pacquiao-decision.html\"> Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602975/JOHNNY-NELSON-Pacquiao-slide-Im-backing-Bradley-repeat-victory.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602975/JOHNNY-NELSON-Pacquiao-slide-Im-backing-Bradley-repeat-victory.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"JOHNNY NELSON: Pacquiao has to roll back the years... but I\'m backing Bradley\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602975/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602975-1D0A862D00000578-703_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:03','2014-04-12 10:13:46'),(46,'a12a77c687687f0f659794e1848e252c16b39cd57792b28a1e5efb2e2037676a','dailymail',NULL,'Max Mosley takes \'blame\' for F1\'s new noise... and is James Hunt\'s son set to follow in his father\'s footsteps?','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/Max-Mosley-takes-blame-F1s-new-noise-James-Hunts-son-set-follow-fathers-footsteps.html',' Max Mosley says he should be blamed for move to V6 turbos this yearThe former FIA chief believes it is important for Formula One to \'evolve\'Mosley\'s memoirs, expected in the autumn, will tell of his F1 experiencesFreddie Hunt is back in Britain in an attempt to restart his racing career By Jonathan McEvoy Published: 17:18 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 02:29 EST, 12 April 2014 28 shares 10 View comments Lunch appointment with Max Mosley. Table for 12.30pm. Usual sort of spot: Sloane Square area of Chelsea. The old FIA president\'s conversation topics were as catholic as usual: judges, whose ranks he half-wished he had joined rather than been lured by motor racing from an early career at the bar; newspaper editors and proprietors, whose journals he has waged war upon; Bernie Ecclestone, his old mucker who finds himself in a spot of bother with the German constabulary. But it was on the subject of Formula One\'s engine development that he made his most pertinent contribution.  In the thick of the action: Lewis Hamilton leads the field on the run down to Turn 1 at the Bahrain Grand Prix  Opinions: Max Mosley met with Jonathan McEvoy  He clearly felt that the sport\'s current governors might have articulated the need for energy recovery era more forcefully. \'If anybody should be \"blamed\" it\'s me,\' he said wryly of the move to V6 turbos this seasons. \'We were the ones who looked at bringing in the new technology. It was 10 years in the making, and I actually like the noise. \'I wear these things in both my ears (hearing aids) because the noise of the engines went right through me for 40 years or more. It\'s too late to save my hearing but not for the next generation. The quieter engines are better for families. You can take children to races without fear of their being deafened. \'It is important for Formula One to evolve. Safety was the big challenge of the 20th Century and the environment is the big challenge of the 21st. If that that fact is not understood and embraced, the sport runs the risk of becoming irrelevant. \'Corporate social responsibility is important for car manufacturers, so there is a need to move in this direction so the sport does not lose sponsors and manufacturers. They see how important this technology is in the development of road cars.  Over the line: Hamilton celebrates his victory in Bahrain after holding off Mercedes team-mate Nico Rosberg  More from Jonathan McEvoy...   JONATHAN McEVOY: Mosley takes \'blame\' for F1\'s new noise... and is James Hunt\'s son set to follow in his father\'s footsteps? 11/04/14   JONATHAN MCEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: Grand prix and Crown Prince Salman must be the catalysts for peace in Bahrain 04/04/14   JONATHAN McEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: I\'ve changed my mind... Rosberg NOT Hamilton will win the title this season 29/03/14   JONATHAN MCEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: Bring on the noise! Controversy is F1\'s currency, and Ecclestone knows that 21/03/14   JONATHAN McEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: Hamilton for the title... if he keeps his cool 14/03/14   VIEW FULL ARCHIVE \'If there is one thing I feel could have been done better it is how the new regulations, and the reasons behind them, have been explained to the public. An opportunity has been missed.\' A few points to consider. First, he turned upside down Ecclestone\'s argument that louder engines are obviously desirable, saying that quieter power trains are not only a necessary by-product of less energy being expelled through the exhaust but that the tranquillity is desirable in itself. He cited watching the sheer violence of a car going round the swimming pool at Monaco, rather than the high-decibel screech, as the truly jaw-dropping spectacle. I agree that watching from the pit wall at Monaco is one of the greatest sights in all sport, and I stop there every year to take it in. Secondly, he argued that Formula One is not shying away from being the most innovative and startling brand in motor racing by moving to a greener world but actually defining the new frontiers by doing so.  Complaint: Luca di Montezemolo has been very outspoken in his criticism of the new Formula One era  More... US team set for Formula One bow in 2015 as FIA accept entrant from NASCAR ace Haas Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle Thirdly, he underlined the fact there would only be one or possibly two engine manufacturers left had the move to energy-saving technology not been brought in. Mercedes, for one, said this week they probably would have quit had the move not come about. Renault would have wobbled, too. Despite these and other worthy points to be made for the new regulations, the agenda through the opening months of the season was set by the antis, notably Ferrari\'s Luca di Montezemolo, Red Bull\'s world champion Sebastian Vettel and, of couse, Ecclestone. Where was the case for the defence from the sport\'s governors, as opposed to Mercedes\' Niki Lauda and, to an extent, McLaren\'s Ron Dennis? Their argument was barely presented, certainly not with the force or coherence it could have been. Instead, the telling rebuttal was delivered, by proxy, through the splendid racing at Bahrain last weekend. But even that evidence, by its nature, failed to make the intellectual case for the revolutionary changes. Another chance to articulate this vision was, I fear, missed this week when the FIA launched its carbon reduction programme. The project was a long time in the planning but was launched with little more than a murmur. The opportunity to join the dots with what is happening in Formula One was wastefully scorned. As for Mosley\'s views on Ecclestone\'s longevity, he believes his old friend will survive the bribery charges in Germany. Or was that just loyalty talking?  Centre of attention: Bernie Ecclestone will be tried on bribery charges in Munich later this year  Back on the pit wall: McLaren chief Ron Dennis pictured at the Bahrain Grand Prix  Mosley memoirs could dent knighthood dreams for Dennis The Piranha Club – the name given to Formula One\'s school of sharp-toothed bosses – should be warned that Mosley has finished his memoirs. I am told that about 10 per cent of the book, which has yet to be given a title, will address his upbringing as the son of Sir Oswald Mosley and Diana Mitford; 25 per cent his campaign to curtail the Press following the News of the World expose into his private life; 65 per cent his experience in and around Formula One. A particularly intrigued piranha will be Ron Dennis, whose designs on a knighthood are unlikely to be helped by another rehearsal of the Spygate scandal, concerning how McLaren came into illicit possession of Ferrari technical data in 2007. Other big fish who could also be wounded by Mosley\'s scabrous pen are Ferrari president Luca di Montezemolo and triple world champion Sir Jackie Stewart. The author, during his period as FIA president, derided them respectively as a \'bella figura\' and a \'certificated halfwit, dressed up as a 1930s\' Music Hall man.\' Watch out. Hunt\'s son rekindles motor racing career If I were a modern-day Lord Hesketh – that is to say richer than I am – I would put some money towards the motor racing career of James Hunt\'s son, Freddie. With his collar-length blond hair, Freddie looks every inch his world champion father\'s boy. He also possesses something of the late James\'s debonair style. So it was one of the pleasures of the week to meet up with Freddie in a London hotel after his return from a spell in Argentina, close to the animals he loves.  Up for the cup: James Hunt celebrating victory at the 1977 British Grand Prix   Like father, like son: Freddie Hunt at the Goodwood Festival of Speed last year and, right, during a photo shoot  He told me how he spent New Year crossing the Andes, 15,000 feet up, sometimes holding on to rock faces for dear life, at other times pausing to breathe in the thin air every 10 steps. He managed just over 50 miles in fractionally fewer hours but had to turn back when there were no horses to take him across the water. The cowboys were on a day off. It was New Year, after all. But, his head cleared and straight, he is back in Britain in an attempt to restart his racing career seven years after he began out in Formula Ford. Aged 26, he admits his original aim of Formula One is beyond him, so is now hell-bent on a crack at Le Mans. The road to Le Mans, through lower categories, will likely take five years at best, and plenty of money. So if anyone fancies helping Freddie on his journey, he can be contacted on Twitter, @FreddieHunt76. PS I am willing to publicise other drivers seeking sponsorship, on only two conditions: first, that they are the son of a Formula One world champion and, secondly, they represent some of the panache missing in modern British sport.   More... US team set for Formula One bow in 2015 as FIA accept entrant from NASCAR ace Haas Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle    Share or comment on this article 28shares','\n<ul class=\"article-summary sport\"><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">Max Mosley says he should be blamed for move to V6 turbos this year</font></span></li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">The former FIA chief believes it is important for Formula One to \'evolve\'</font></span></li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">Mosley\'s memoirs, expected in the autumn, will tell of his F1 experiences<br/></font></span></li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">Freddie Hunt is back in Britain in an attempt to restart his racing career</font></span></li></ul>\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1093163/Jonathan-McEvoy.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jonathan McEvoy</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 17:18 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 02:29 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/Max-Mosley-takes-blame-F1s-new-noise-James-Hunts-son-set-follow-fathers-footsteps.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/Max-Mosley-takes-blame-F1s-new-noise-James-Hunts-son-set-follow-fathers-footsteps.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"JONATHAN McEVOY: Mosley takes \'blame\' for F1\'s new noise... and is James Hunt\'s son set to follow in his father\'s footsteps?\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 28</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/Max-Mosley-takes-blame-F1s-new-noise-James-Hunts-son-set-follow-fathers-footsteps.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">10</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Lunch appointment with Max Mosley. Table for 12.30pm. Usual sort of spot: Sloane Square area of Chelsea.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> The old FIA president\'s conversation topics were as catholic as usual: judges, whose ranks he half-wished he had joined rather than been lured by motor racing from an early career at the bar; newspaper editors and proprietors, whose journals he has waged war upon; Bernie Ecclestone, his old mucker who finds himself in a spot of bother with the German constabulary.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> But it was on the subject of Formula One\'s engine development that he made his most pertinent contribution. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"In the thick of the action: Lewis Hamilton leads the field on the run down to Turn 1 at the Bahrain Grand Prix\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"342\" id=\"i-5a290d1a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CE2721200000578-238_634x342.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">In the thick of the action: Lewis Hamilton leads the field on the run down to Turn 1 at the Bahrain Grand Prix</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS\"> <img alt=\"Opinions: Max Mosley met with Jonathan McEvoy\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"443\" id=\"i-a8c10e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-0567A838000005DC-363_306x443.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Opinions: Max Mosley met with Jonathan McEvoy</p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He clearly felt that the sport\'s current governors might have articulated the need for energy recovery era more forcefully. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'If anybody should be \"blamed\" it\'s me,\' he said wryly of the move to V6 turbos this seasons. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'We were the ones who looked at bringing in the new technology. It was 10 years in the making, and I actually like the noise. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I wear these things in both my ears (hearing aids) because the noise of the engines went right through me for 40 years or more. It\'s too late to save my hearing but not for the next generation. The quieter engines are better for families. You can take children to races without fear of their being deafened. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'It is important for Formula One to evolve. Safety was the big challenge of the 20th Century and the environment is the big challenge of the 21st. If that that fact is not understood and embraced, the sport runs the risk of becoming irrelevant. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Corporate social responsibility is important for car manufacturers, so there is a need to move in this direction so the sport does not lose sponsors and manufacturers. They see how important this technology is in the development of road cars. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Over the line: Hamilton celebrates his victory in Bahrain after holding off Mercedes team-mate Nico Rosberg\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"409\" id=\"i-abfd0e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1CE2EC3600000578-395_634x409.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Over the line: Hamilton celebrates his victory in Bahrain after holding off Mercedes team-mate Nico Rosberg</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"item\"> <div class=\"columnist-archive-narrow bogr1\"> <span class=\"tl\"> </span> <span class=\"tr\"> </span> <h3>More from Jonathan McEvoy...</h3> <ul> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/Max-Mosley-takes-blame-F1s-new-noise-James-Hunts-son-set-follow-fathers-footsteps.html\">JONATHAN McEVOY: Mosley takes \'blame\' for F1\'s new noise... and is James Hunt\'s son set to follow in his father\'s footsteps?</a> <span class=\"date\">11/04/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2597403/JONATHAN-MCEVOY-ON-FORMULA-ONE-Grand-prix-Crown-Prince-Salman-catalysts-peace-Bahrain.html\">JONATHAN MCEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: Grand prix and Crown Prince Salman must be the catalysts for peace in Bahrain</a> <span class=\"date\">04/04/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2592081/Ive-changed-mind-Nico-Rosberg-NOT-Lewis-Hamilton-win-title-season.html\">JONATHAN McEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: I\'ve changed my mind... Rosberg NOT Hamilton will win the title this season</a> <span class=\"date\">29/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2586584/JONATHAN-MCEVOY-Controversy-F1s-currency-Bernie-Ecclestone-knows-it.html\">JONATHAN MCEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: Bring on the noise! Controversy is F1\'s currency, and Ecclestone knows that</a> <span class=\"date\">21/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2581179/JONATHAN-McEVOY-ON-FORMULA-ONE-Lewis-Hamilton-title-keeps-cool.html\">JONATHAN McEVOY ON FORMULA ONE: Hamilton for the title... if he keeps his cool</a> <span class=\"date\">14/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"columnist-1093163/Jonathan-McEvoy.html\">VIEW FULL ARCHIVE</a> </li> </ul> </div> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'If there is one thing I feel could have been done better it is how the new regulations, and the reasons behind them, have been explained to the public. An opportunity has been missed.\' <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A few points to consider. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">First, he turned upside down Ecclestone\'s argument that louder engines are obviously desirable, saying that quieter power trains are not only a necessary by-product of less energy being expelled through the exhaust but that the tranquillity is desirable in itself. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He cited watching the sheer violence of a car going round the swimming pool at Monaco, rather than the high-decibel screech, as the truly jaw-dropping spectacle. I agree that watching from the pit wall at Monaco is one of the greatest sights in all sport, and I stop there every year to take it in. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Secondly, he argued that Formula One is not shying away from being the most innovative and startling brand in motor racing by moving to a greener world but actually defining the new frontiers by doing so. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Complaint: Luca di Montezemolo has been very outspoken in his criticism of the new Formula One era\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-ab1d0e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1CE1F92400000578-999_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Complaint: Luca di Montezemolo has been very outspoken in his criticism of the new Formula One era</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html\"> US team set for Formula One bow in 2015 as FIA accept entrant from NASCAR ace Haas</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2601725/Christian-Horner-claims-Daniel-Ricciardo-best-youngster-enjoys-fine-start-Red-Bull.html\"> Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\"> Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602373/Lewis-Hamilton-shies-away-cameras-meal-Nicole-Scherzinger.html\"> Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598780/Nico-Rosberg-promise-win-Chinese-Grand-Prix-losing-Lewis-Hamilton-brilliant-Bahrain-battle.html\"> I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Thirdly, he underlined the fact there would only be one or possibly two engine manufacturers left had the move to energy-saving technology not been brought in. Mercedes, for one, said this week they probably would have quit had the move not come about. Renault would have wobbled, too. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Despite these and other worthy points to be made for the new regulations, the agenda through the opening months of the season was set by the antis, notably Ferrari\'s Luca di Montezemolo, Red Bull\'s world champion Sebastian Vettel and, of couse, Ecclestone. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Where was the case for the defence from the sport\'s governors, as opposed to Mercedes\' Niki Lauda and, to an extent, McLaren\'s Ron Dennis? Their argument was barely presented, certainly not with the force or coherence it could have been. Instead, the telling rebuttal was delivered, by proxy, through the splendid racing at Bahrain last weekend. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But even that evidence, by its nature, failed to make the intellectual case for the revolutionary changes.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> Another chance to articulate this vision was, I fear, missed this week when the FIA launched its carbon reduction programme. The project was a long time in the planning but was launched with little more than a murmur. The opportunity to join the dots with what is happening in Formula One was wastefully scorned. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">As for Mosley\'s views on Ecclestone\'s longevity, he believes his old friend will survive the bribery charges in Germany. Or was that just loyalty talking?</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Centre of attention: Bernie Ecclestone will be tried on bribery charges in Munich later this year\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"447\" id=\"i-ab500e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1CE1F76900000578-376_634x447.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Centre of attention: Bernie Ecclestone will be tried on bribery charges in Munich later this year</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS\"> <img alt=\"Back on the pit wall: McLaren chief Ron Dennis pictured at the Bahrain Grand Prix\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"488\" id=\"i-90b70e18\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1CDE01E700000578-2_306x488.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Back on the pit wall: McLaren chief Ron Dennis pictured at the Bahrain Grand Prix</p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mosley memoirs could dent knighthood dreams for Dennis<br/></font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> The Piranha Club – the name given to Formula One\'s school of sharp-toothed bosses – should be warned that Mosley has finished his memoirs. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I am told that about 10 per cent of the book, which has yet to be given a title, will address his upbringing as the son of Sir Oswald Mosley and Diana Mitford; 25 per cent his campaign to curtail the Press following the News of the World expose into his private life; 65 per cent his experience in and around Formula One. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A particularly intrigued piranha will be Ron Dennis, whose designs on a knighthood are unlikely to be helped by another rehearsal of the Spygate scandal, concerning how McLaren came into illicit possession of Ferrari technical data in 2007. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Other big fish who could also be wounded by Mosley\'s scabrous pen are Ferrari president Luca di Montezemolo and triple world champion Sir Jackie Stewart. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The author, during his period as FIA president, derided them respectively as a \'bella figura\' and a \'certificated halfwit, dressed up as a 1930s\' Music Hall man.\' Watch out.</font></p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> Hunt\'s son rekindles motor racing career  <br/></font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">If I were a modern-day Lord Hesketh – that is to say richer than I am – I would put some money towards the motor racing career of James Hunt\'s son, Freddie. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With his collar-length blond hair, Freddie looks every inch his world champion father\'s boy. He also possesses something of the late James\'s debonair style. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">So it was one of the pleasures of the week to meet up with Freddie in a London hotel after his return from a spell in Argentina, close to the animals he loves. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Up for the cup: James Hunt celebrating victory at the 1977 British Grand Prix\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"416\" id=\"i-abd30e8d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1B1A32AE000005DC-761_634x416.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Up for the cup: James Hunt celebrating victory at the 1977 British Grand Prix</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Like father like son: Hunt Jnr at Goodwood\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-9a4a0e20\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1D0A278400000578-40_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Freddie Hunt during a photoshoot\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a7120e50\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1D0A284000000578-380_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Like father, like son: Freddie Hunt at the Goodwood Festival of Speed last year and, right, during a photo shoot <br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He told me how he spent New Year crossing the Andes, 15,000 feet up, sometimes holding on to rock faces for dear life, at other times pausing to breathe in the thin air every 10 steps. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He managed just over 50 miles in fractionally fewer hours but had to turn back when there were no horses to take him across the water. The cowboys were on a day off. It was New Year, after all. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But, his head cleared and straight, he is back in Britain in an attempt to restart his racing career seven years after he began out in Formula Ford. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Aged 26, he admits his original aim of Formula One is beyond him, so is now hell-bent on a crack at Le Mans. The road to Le Mans, through lower categories, will likely take five years at best, and plenty of money. So if anyone fancies helping Freddie on his journey, he can be contacted on Twitter, <a href=\"http://twitter.com/FreddieHunt76\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">@FreddieHunt76</a>. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">PS I am willing to publicise other drivers seeking sponsorship, on only two conditions: first, that they are the son of a Formula One world champion and, secondly, they represent some of the panache missing in modern British sport. </font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html\"> US team set for Formula One bow in 2015 as FIA accept entrant from NASCAR ace Haas</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2601725/Christian-Horner-claims-Daniel-Ricciardo-best-youngster-enjoys-fine-start-Red-Bull.html\"> Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\"> Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602373/Lewis-Hamilton-shies-away-cameras-meal-Nicole-Scherzinger.html\"> Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598780/Nico-Rosberg-promise-win-Chinese-Grand-Prix-losing-Lewis-Hamilton-brilliant-Bahrain-battle.html\"> I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/Max-Mosley-takes-blame-F1s-new-noise-James-Hunts-son-set-follow-fathers-footsteps.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/Max-Mosley-takes-blame-F1s-new-noise-James-Hunts-son-set-follow-fathers-footsteps.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"JONATHAN McEVOY: Mosley takes \'blame\' for F1\'s new noise... and is James Hunt\'s son set to follow in his father\'s footsteps?\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602858/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">28</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602858-1D0A284000000578-455_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:04','2014-04-12 09:29:09');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (47,'d1e0e6cf4f92e14a91669818a93ded07f903131180c85ba9f403a6b5c2539512','dailymail',NULL,'It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html',' By Derek Lawrenson Published: 19:03 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 19:15 EST, 11 April 2014 11 shares 8 View comments From an 83 in his last competitive round before Augusta to the runaway halfway lead at the 78th Masters. From a performance blamed on chronic allergies to the sweet perfume of perfection. Welcome to the never dull, box office world of Bubba Watson. Who knows what might happen next as the 35 year old from Bagdad, Florida takes a three stroke advantage over Australian John Senden into the weekend after a second round 68 featuring no fewer than five successive birdies on the back nine. Perhaps it will be a couple of 68s to win by a street. Or it\'s just as likely to be a pair of 78s to become a footnote in the chronicle of this 80th anniversary edition.  Box office: Bubba Watson plays his third shot on the 18th hole  Mind you, Rory McIlroy\'s fate is in danger of being that already following an afternoon filled with an extraordinary collection of mishaps. The favourite coming into the event flew the green at the par three fourth and finished in the bushes against a perimeter wall, with the consequence being he had to go back to the tee. In the end, following his provisional, he played a good bunker shot simply to limit the damage to a double bogey five. At the par four 10th he suffered another double bogey following another poorly executed approach. All that, however, was just a prelude to the unlucky par five 13th, where his second shot was tugged a fraction, landed on a sprinker head by the side of the green and bounded into the azaleas behind the target. Another bogey six there and McIlroy was putting together one of those horror sequences we have seen all too often from him at Augusta and turn his favourite event into a perennial nightmare. Luck continued to be against him right to the end, as his second shot to the 18th failed to come down a ridge in the green and finish next to the hole. \'What is holding that up, a grain of sand?\' asked Sir Nick Faldo, on American television. Now McIlroy had to get down in two putts from above the hole simply to make the halfway cut, and he finished 5ft away with his first effort. Thankfully for the sake of the event, he knocked it in to complete a tough day at the office. But at least he is around for the weekend – albeit 11 off the lead – which is more than can be said for the likes of Open Champion Phil Mickelson, Ernie Els and Sergio Garcia.   Tense: Watson takes a three stroke advantage into the weekend  More... AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain \'It was just a really frustrating day,\' said McIlroy. \'There was a massive wind switch at the 4th and then at the 13th I hit the sprinkler head. I thought I played well after that but just couldn\'t make any putts. But I\'m still here, and hope to go low in the third round.\' Defending champion Adam Scott\'s defence was also in danger of fading away when he bogeyed three holes early on. But he showed the mettle of a champion on the back nine, coming home in 33 shots for a 72 that leaves him tied for third place. And so the UK challenge this weekend will be spearheaded by the unlikely duo who are threatening to take their unsung but impressive skills all the way to the Ryder Cup. Scotland\'s Stephen Gallacher, playing in his first Masters, added a 72 to his first round 71 to be six off the lead, alongside Jamie Donaldson from Wales, who shot 70.   Unlucky: Rory McIlroy hits out of the azaleas to the 13th green The leading Europeans on three under are American-based Swede Jonas Blixt and Thomas Bjorn, a 200-1 shot highlighted by Mail Online earlier in the week as an outstanding each-way bet. Bjorn shot 68. The other player on three under going into the weekend is America\'s remarkable rookie, Jordan Spieth. Just 20, who seems to be in contention practically every week. Watson won the green jacket two years ago with a shot at the first play-off hole that showcased his wonderful natural ability, as he moved the ball 30 yards from left to right through the air with a wedge. Last year, though, he fell off the charts. Any reason? Watson gave a wonderful response. \'Think about it for a moment and where I came from,\' he said. \'My mum took on two jobs to give me a chance at golf. I\'ve never had a lesson. Wouldn\'t it take you a bit of time to get over it if you were called Bubba and you\'d come so far that you won the green jacket?  That was such an accomplishment for me there had to a hangover. In fact, I think I am still celebrating.\'   Rough times: Caddie Jean-Paul Fitzgerald looks for McIlroy\'s ball on the fourth hole  Bjorn\'s renaissance has seen him tip-toe to the brink of Europe\'s Ryder Cup team and continued with a round illustrating his wonderful short game. \'It was right up there with the best rounds I have played at Augusta,\' said the 43 year old Dane, who had so many opportunities to win a major during his thirties. \'I felt comfortable on the course all day and that\'s always a good sign you\'re swinging well.\' Gallacher was similarly content. \'I\'m delighted with that,\' he said. \'It feels great to be in red numbers when you know if you\'re in the wrong places even a bogey is a good score.\'  Impressive: Scotland\'s Stephen Gallacher added a 72 to his first round 71  This is a huge event in itself for Gallacher, who is experiencing the aura of Augusta for the first time at 40. But it\'s a massive tournament in the bigger picture as well, as the quiet man from Linlithgow looks to close in on his primary goal for the season of a place in Europe\'s team at a Ryder Cup taking place just 30 minutes from his home. Right now, he\'s clinging to the 9th and last automatic slot. A good tournament here would certainly impress Europe\'s captain Paul McGinley, who is present and keeping a hawk\'s eye on proceedings. There was much to enjoy as Gallacher displayed his art and craft on another peachy morning in the Deep South. At the third, he left himself in a tricky spot just off the green but \'bladed\' an exquisite wedge shot to within inches of the hole. What was most impressive was the manner in which Gallacher kept bouncing back from bogeys. It happened on four occasions in all and has earned him his lofty spot.   Composed: Gallacher talks with his caddie Damian Moore on the second hole  As for Donaldson, there\'s seemingly no stopping him these days, as the late developing Welshman played the front nine in 33 shots to clamber on to the leaderboard. At his first Masters last year he had a hole in one at the 6th, and this trip is turning into another memorable one. It\'s an indication of his growing belief at this level that he didn\'t feel like he played that well but still shot two under. \'It was a real struggle for me off the tee, so I\'m pleased to finish with such a good score,\' he said. As for the gilded English quartet, they all rebounded from their opening day calamities. Lee Westwood has a superb recent record here and has an opportunity to extend it after a 71 left him inside the top 15, seven shots off the lead.  Confident: Jamie Donaldson, of Wales, watches his putt on the 18th green  US Open Champion Justin Rose bounced back well from an opening 76 with a 70 to be two further shots adrift, as did Ian Poulter, on the same mark after two identical scores. Luke Donald, however, was a shade unfortunate to miss out by a stroke despite improving nine shots on his first round 79. Two more to miss the cut were the English amateurs, Matt Fitzpatrick and Garrick Porteous. The latter missed by a large margin but 19 year old Fitzpatrick from Sheffield recovered so well from his wretched double bogey on the first hole on Thursday that he actually stood over a 12ft birdie putt on the last to make it to the weekend. Alas for him, it slipped by and the disappointment was obvious. Still, he must have learned so much from one playing partner, Scott, and actually beat the other, USPGA Champion Jason Dufner, by three shots. He will be back.  Up for it: Thomas Bjorn\'s renaissance has seen him tip-toe to the brink of Europe\'s Ryder Cup team    More... AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain   Share or comment on this article 11shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Derek+Lawrenson\" rel=\"nofollow\">Derek Lawrenson</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 19:03 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 19:15 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(