.html\"> Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2601950/AUGUSTA-TEE-ROOM-Gareth-Bale-cheering-Dustin-Johnson-Spain.html\"> AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain</a></li> </ul> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'It was just a really frustrating day,\' said McIlroy. \'There was a massive wind switch at the 4th and then at the 13th I hit the sprinkler head. I thought I played well after that but just couldn\'t make any putts. But I\'m still here, and hope to go low in the third round.\'</font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Defending champion Adam Scott\'s defence was also in danger of fading away when he bogeyed three holes early on. But he showed the mettle of a champion on the back nine, coming home in 33 shots for a 72 that leaves him tied for third place. </font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And so the UK challenge this weekend will be spearheaded by the unlikely duo who are threatening to take their unsung but impressive skills all the way to the Ryder Cup. Scotland\'s Stephen Gallacher, playing in his first Masters, added a 72 to his first round 71 to be six off the lead, alongside Jamie Donaldson from Wales, who shot 70. </font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Unlucky: Rory McIlroy hits out of the azaleas to the 13th green\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"474\" id=\"i-5c3b0d33\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A55B800000578-822_634x474.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Unlucky: Rory McIlroy hits out of the azaleas to the 13th green</p></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The leading Europeans on three under are American-based Swede Jonas Blixt and Thomas Bjorn, a 200-1 shot highlighted by Mail Online earlier in the week as an outstanding each-way bet. Bjorn shot 68. The other player on three under going into the weekend is America\'s remarkable rookie, Jordan Spieth. Just 20, who seems to be in contention practically every week.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Watson won the green jacket two years ago with a shot at the first play-off hole that showcased his wonderful natural ability, as he moved the ball 30 yards from left to right through the air with a wedge. Last year, though, he fell off the charts.</font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Any reason? Watson gave a wonderful response. \'Think about it for a moment and where I came from,\' he said. \'My mum took on two jobs to give me a chance at golf. I\'ve never had a lesson. Wouldn\'t it take you a bit of time to get over it if you were called Bubba and you\'d come so far that you won the green jacket?  That was such an accomplishment for me there had to a hangover. In fact, I think I am still celebrating.\'</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rough times: Caddie Jean-Paul Fitzgerald looks for McIlroy\'s ball on the fourth hole\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"485\" id=\"i-5a540d1f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A288200000578-510_634x485.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rough times: Caddie Jean-Paul Fitzgerald looks for McIlroy\'s ball on the fourth hole</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bjorn\'s renaissance has seen him tip-toe to the brink of Europe\'s Ryder Cup team and continued with a round illustrating his wonderful short game.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> \'It was right up there with the best rounds I have played at Augusta,\' said the 43 year old Dane, who had so many opportunities to win a major during his thirties. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I felt comfortable on the course all day and that\'s always a good sign you\'re swinging well.\'</font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Gallacher was similarly content. \'I\'m delighted with that,\' he said. \'It feels great to be in red numbers when you know if you\'re in the wrong places even a bogey is a good score.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Impressive: Scotland\'s Stephen Gallacher added a 72 to his first round 71\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"451\" id=\"i-5d540d3c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D07AE1A00000578-457_634x451.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Impressive: Scotland\'s Stephen Gallacher added a 72 to his first round 71</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">This is a huge event in itself for Gallacher, who is experiencing the aura of Augusta for the first time at 40. But it\'s a massive tournament in the bigger picture as well, as the quiet man from Linlithgow looks to close in on his primary goal for the season of a place in Europe\'s team at a Ryder Cup taking place just 30 minutes from his home. </font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Right now, he\'s clinging to the 9th and last automatic slot. A good tournament here would certainly impress Europe\'s captain Paul McGinley, who is present and keeping a hawk\'s eye on proceedings.</font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">There was much to enjoy as Gallacher displayed his art and craft on another peachy morning in the Deep South. At the third, he left himself in a tricky spot just off the green but \'bladed\' an exquisite wedge shot to within inches of the hole. What was most impressive was the manner in which Gallacher kept bouncing back from bogeys. It happened on four occasions in all and has earned him his lofty spot.</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Composed: Gallacher talks with his caddie Damian Moore on the second hole\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-5c760d35\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D07DC5400000578-821_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Composed: Gallacher talks with his caddie Damian Moore on the second hole</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">As for Donaldson, there\'s seemingly no stopping him these days, as the late developing Welshman played the front nine in 33 shots to clamber on to the leaderboard. At his first Masters last year he had a hole in one at the 6th, and this trip is turning into another memorable one.</font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It\'s an indication of his growing belief at this level that he didn\'t feel like he played that well but still shot two under. \'It was a real struggle for me off the tee, so I\'m pleased to finish with such a good score,\' he said. </font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">As for the gilded English quartet, they all rebounded from their opening day calamities. Lee Westwood has a superb recent record here and has an opportunity to extend it after a 71 left him inside the top 15, seven shots off the lead. </font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Confident: Jamie Donaldson, of Wales, watches his putt on the 18th green\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"475\" id=\"i-5cfe0d3d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0A69B900000578-168_634x475.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Confident: Jamie Donaldson, of Wales, watches his putt on the 18th green</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">US Open Champion Justin Rose bounced back well from an opening 76 with a 70 to be two further shots adrift, as did Ian Poulter, on the same mark after two identical scores. Luke Donald, however, was a shade unfortunate to miss out by a stroke despite improving nine shots on his first round 79. </font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Two more to miss the cut were the English amateurs, Matt Fitzpatrick and Garrick Porteous. The latter missed by a large margin but 19 year old Fitzpatrick from Sheffield recovered so well from his wretched double bogey on the first hole on Thursday that he actually stood over a 12ft birdie putt on the last to make it to the weekend.</font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Alas for him, it slipped by and the disappointment was obvious. Still, he must have learned so much from one playing partner, Scott, and actually beat the other, USPGA Champion Jason Dufner, by three shots.</font></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He will be back.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Up for it: Thomas Bjorn\'s renaissance has seen him tip-toe to the brink of Europe\'s Ryder Cup team\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"462\" id=\"i-5aaa0d20\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0971A800000578-160_634x462.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Up for it: Thomas Bjorn\'s renaissance has seen him tip-toe to the brink of Europe\'s Ryder Cup team</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\"> AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html\"> He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\"> Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602529/MASTERS-2014-Luke-Donald-admits-pretty-dumb-bunker-gaffe-puts-risk-cut.html\"> Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2601950/AUGUSTA-TEE-ROOM-Gareth-Bale-cheering-Dustin-Johnson-Spain.html\"> AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602916/Its-hullabaloo-Bubba-masterful-Watson-mood-Thomas-looks-Bjorn-too.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"It\'s hullabaloo for Bubba as masterful Watson in mood while Thomas looks Bjorn again too\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602916/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">11</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602916-1D09BC7B00000578-81_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:05','2014-04-12 02:15:55'),(48,'206389bfdd89c096f59b95a398b760c126a551ac5b5c7b86c89607253d410b17','dailymail',NULL,'John Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Sergio Garcia and Bubba Watson are pretty in pink','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html',' By Brian Lee Follow @@brianwlee1 Published: 17:59 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 18:47 EST, 11 April 2014 4 View comments John Daly hasn\'t competed at Augusta since 2006 but he\'s a regular at the Hooters car park on Washington Road just a short walk away and turned up again to sell golf gear from his truck. The Wild Thing, who gathered an army of fans after his fairytale 1991 US PGA triumph, is still a big draw, with people stopping to spend a few dollars or snap a photo.     Wild thing: John Daly (left) joins in the fun by selling golf memorabilia in Hooters car park (below)     True colours The colours on show make the Masters one of the most spectacular tournaments on TV and it\'s not just the azaleas catching the eye. Pink was a popular choice for the players - Bubba Watson\'s driver, Sergio Garcia\'s trousers and Henrik Stenson\'s shirt would have looked good together on the girls in Grease.  Dazzling: Sergio Garcia\'s trousers, Henrik Stenson\'s shirt and Bubba Watson\'s driver     Crenshaw crunch As a two-time winner, Ben Crenshaw is granted his annual lap of honour at the Cathedral of Pines but one young woman will be wishing he hadn\'t bothered. The patron was next to the eighth fairway and Crenshaw was on a different hole when a shot from not-so Gentle Ben whacked her on the head and left her grounded with a towel wrapped round her injury.  Floored: A female fan was injured when she was hit by Ben Crenshaw (below)     Fran loves Irons Inter Milan fan Francesco Molinari adopted West Ham as his English team when he moved to London as he is mates with former boss Gianfranco Zola and his coach Denis Pugh is a fan. The grateful Hammers made it a mutual relationship and told Molinari on Twitter: \'We\'re backing you to climb the leaderboard\' before his second round. He safely made the cut.  Hammer time: West Ham are riight behind Francesco Molinari  No brother bother Brothers going their separate ways can be risky - just ask Liam and Noel Gallagher. But when Bill Haas sacked sibling Jay as his caddie at last month\'s Valspar Championship, the axed bagman not only took it in his stride but was also gracious enough to line up Scotty Gneiser to help his brother. With Gneiser by his side, Bill led after round one.  Split: Bill Haas axed his brother for caddie Scott Gneiser  Trouble: Warring brothers Noel Gallagher and Liam Gallagher  No Bubba bogeys Bubba Watson withdrew from the Arnold Palmer Invitational last month claiming his allergies had taken over but it was only bogeys he was sensitive to in his flying start to the year\'s first major. Watson was the one player to go bogey-free on Thursday and the first blot on the copybook didn\'t arrive until the ninth hole of his second round.   More... AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happens at Augusta National   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Brian+Lee\" rel=\"nofollow\">Brian Lee</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@brianwlee1\">Follow @@brianwlee1</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 17:59 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 18:47 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">4</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">John Daly hasn\'t competed at Augusta since 2006 but he\'s a regular at the Hooters car park on Washington Road just a short walk away and turned up again to sell golf gear from his truck. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Wild Thing, who gathered an army of fans after his fairytale 1991 US PGA triumph, is still a big draw, with people stopping to spend a few dollars or snap a photo.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Wild thing: John Daly joins in the fun by selling golf memorabilia in Hooters car park\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a8e20e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602892-1D0A713E00000578-643_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Wild thing: John Daly joins in the fun by selling golf memorabilia in Hooters car park\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-5d5e0d38\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D0A3C9F00000578-245_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wild thing: John Daly (left) joins in the fun by selling golf memorabilia in Hooters car park (below)<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wild thing: John Daly joins in the fun by selling golf memorabilia in Hooters car park\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"427\" id=\"i-a9020e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D0A5B2900000578-405_634x427.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.6em;\">True colours</font></span></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The colours on show make the Masters one of the most spectacular tournaments on TV and it\'s not just the azaleas catching the eye. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Pink was a popular choice for the players - Bubba Watson\'s driver, Sergio Garcia\'s trousers and Henrik Stenson\'s shirt would have looked good together on the girls in Grease.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dazzling: Sergio Garcia\'s trousers, Henrik Stenson\'s shirt and Bubba Watson\'s driver\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-aa660e7b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D09C6F500000578-618_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dazzling: Sergio Garcia\'s trousers, Henrik Stenson\'s shirt and Bubba Watson\'s driver<br/></p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Dazzling: Sergio Garcia\'s trousers, Henrik Stenson\'s shirt and Bubba Watson\'s driver\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a9870e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D08EB2900000578-307_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Dazzling: Sergio Garcia\'s trousers, Henrik Stenson\'s shirt and Bubba Watson\'s driver\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a7590e57\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D09402E00000578-645_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.6em;\">Crenshaw crunch</font></span></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">As a two-time winner, Ben Crenshaw is granted his annual lap of honour at the Cathedral of Pines but one young woman will be wishing he hadn\'t bothered. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The patron was next to the eighth fairway and Crenshaw was on a different hole when a shot from not-so Gentle Ben whacked her on the head and left her grounded with a towel wrapped round her injury.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Down: A woman holds a towel after being hit by a ball played by Ben Crenshaw on the eighth fairway\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"464\" id=\"i-a77b0e5d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D09127A00000578-633_634x464.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Floored: A female fan was injured when she was hit by Ben Crenshaw (below)<br/></p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Floored: A female fan was injured when she was hit by Ben Crenshaw (below)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"508\" id=\"i-aa0f0e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D098AF700000578-403_634x508.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.6em;\">Fran loves Irons</font></span></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Inter Milan fan Francesco Molinari adopted West Ham as his English team when he moved to London as he is mates with former boss Gianfranco Zola and his coach Denis Pugh is a fan. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The grateful Hammers made it a mutual relationship and told Molinari on Twitter: \'We\'re backing you to climb the leaderboard\' before his second round. He safely made the cut.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Hammer time: West Ham are riight behind Francesco Molinari\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-a74a0e59\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D09448600000578-928_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Hammer time: West Ham are riight behind Francesco Molinari</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.6em;\">No brother bother</font></span></p>\n<p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Brothers going their separate ways can be risky - just ask Liam and Noel Gallagher. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But when Bill Haas sacked sibling Jay as his caddie at last month\'s Valspar Championship, the axed bagman not only took it in his stride but was also gracious enough to line up Scotty Gneiser to help his brother. With Gneiser by his side, Bill led after round one.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Split: Bill Haas axed his brother for caddie Scott Gneiser\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"493\" id=\"i-aa090e7b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-1D0A45F500000578-986_634x493.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Split: Bill Haas axed his brother for caddie Scott Gneiser</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Trouble: Warring brothers Noel Gallagher and Liam Gallagher\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-a8a80e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602892-03B85496000005DC-138_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Trouble: Warring brothers Noel Gallagher and Liam Gallagher</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.6em;\">No Bubba bogeys</font></span></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bubba Watson withdrew from the Arnold Palmer Invitational last month claiming his allergies had taken over but it was only bogeys he was sensitive to in his flying start to the year\'s first major. Watson was the one player to go bogey-free on Thursday and the first blot on the copybook didn\'t arrive until the ninth hole of his second round.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2601950/AUGUSTA-TEE-ROOM-Gareth-Bale-cheering-Dustin-Johnson-Spain.html\"> AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\"> Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602529/MASTERS-2014-Luke-Donald-admits-pretty-dumb-bunker-gaffe-puts-risk-cut.html\"> Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602063/MASTERS-LIVE-All-second-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\"> MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happens at Augusta National</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602892/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602892-1D0A73DF00000578-969_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:05','2014-04-12 01:47:15'),(49,'6fe0d48227365fa62f84bef97856569a2c47a4176ef21378ed1c4f8d7e89259e','dailymail',NULL,'Suarez, Sturridge and Sterling over Aguero and Co... Liverpool have the edge in my combined title-chasing XI','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602889/Suarez-Sturridge-Sterling-Aguero-Co-Liverpool-edge-combined-title-chasing-XI.html',' By Martin Keown Follow @@martinkeown5 Published: 18:03 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 18:36 EST, 11 April 2014 52 shares 20 View comments  Sportsmail expert MARTIN KEOWN mulls over the big talking points ahead of Sunday\'s potential Premier League title decider at Anfield. It\'s a tough task picking a side from these squads. Liverpool have the edge in my team (right) with six players to City’s five, but that shows you just how far they have come this season. I think Mignolet has been more consistent than Hart and the same goes for my back four — all are reliable performers. Gerrard and Toure would be some midfield engine room while Liverpool’s attacking trio would be supported by Silva’s creative brilliance.  Dynamic duo: Lethal partnership Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge make it in over City\'s strikers   The midfield battle could decide this match. Brendan Rodgers knows about the threat of Yaya Toure and David Silva, so he may make some tweaks. He has not been afraid to tinker this season and I wouldn’t be surprised if he brings in Lucas or Joe Allen to support Steven Gerrard in combatting City’s power.  Key man: The midfield presence of Yaya Toure could go a long way into deciding the match   Martin Demichelis has played better in recent weeks, but he is still a weak link. Liverpool will attack him whenever they can and Luis Suarez will be licking his lips.   More... From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000 JAMIE CARRAGHER: Every child must be told why games kick off seven minutes late this weekend  174 The combined number of league goals scored by Liverpool (90) and City (84) this season. Everybody talks about the spirit at Anfield this season, but City are just as strong. I watched the Under 21 Premier League cup final this week and all of City’s top stars were there to support the youth team. Lots of the foreign stars have been there for a while now and they feel 100 per cent that this is their club.  Bend it like Becks? Aleksandar Kolarov\'s crossing is an underrated threat in City\'s arsenal Remember me? Kolarov\'s precision is every bit as good as United and England hero David Beckham  Kolarov delivers just like Beckham Not enough is made of Aleksandar Kolarov’s crossing ability. He whips balls into the area that are just begging to be put in the net. When he gets space down the left, he is just as good as David Beckham at putting in dangerous deliveries. City must get behind Gerrard If Liverpool win the league, this will be Steven Gerrard’s greatest ever season. But City will look to isolate him. If he plays alone in that deeper role, City can have success if they flood players in behind him. If Samir Nasri and David Silva can get themselves in behind Gerrard, they can use Edin Dzeko to draw out the centre halves and create space. The City midfielders can then exploit that with clever movement and work the ball in to create chances.  On target: The rejuvenated Steven Gerrard has been key to Liverpool\'s surprise title challenge Tactics: City will want to get behind the Liverpool midfield to create opportunities    More... From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000 JAMIE CARRAGHER: Every child must be told why games kick off seven minutes late this weekend   Share or comment on this article 52shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1047409/Martin-Keown.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Martin Keown</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@martinkeown5\">Follow @@martinkeown5</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 18:03 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timest