OWN mulls over the big talking points ahead of Sunday\'s potential Premier League title decider at Anfield.</i></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It\'s a tough task picking a side from these squads. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Liverpool have the edge in my team (right) with six players to City’s five, but that shows you just how far they have come this season. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">I think Mignolet has been more consistent than Hart and the same goes for my back four — all are reliable performers. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Gerrard and Toure would be some midfield engine room while Liverpool’s attacking trio would be supported by Silva’s creative brilliance.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dynamic duo: Lethal partnership Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge make it in over City\'s strikers\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"460\" id=\"i-ae150e97\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602889-1C7E6BCC00000578-861_634x460.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dynamic duo: Lethal partnership Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge make it in over City\'s strikers</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The midfield battle could decide this match. Brendan Rodgers knows about the threat of Yaya Toure and David Silva, so he may make some tweaks. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He has not been afraid to tinker this season and I wouldn’t be surprised if he brings in Lucas or Joe Allen to support Steven Gerrard in combatting City’s power.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Key man: The midfield presence of Yaya Toure could go a long way into deciding the match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"446\" id=\"i-a1a50e6c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602889-1CDAFC5B00000578-41_634x446.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Key man: The midfield presence of Yaya Toure could go a long way into deciding the match</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Martin Demichelis has played better in recent weeks, but he is still a weak link. Liverpool will attack him whenever they can and Luis Suarez will be licking his lips.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\"> From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\"> Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html\"> CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602712/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Every-child-told-games-kick-seven-minutes-late-weekend.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Every child must be told why games kick off seven minutes late this weekend</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">174 </font></b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b></b>The combined number of league goals scored by Liverpool (90) and City (84) this season. </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Everybody talks about the spirit at Anfield this season, but City are just as strong. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">I watched the Under 21 Premier League cup final this week and all of City’s top stars were there to support the youth team. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Lots of the foreign stars have been there for a while now and they feel 100 per cent that this is their club.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bend it like Becks? Aleksandar Kolarov\'s crossing is an underrated threat in City\'s arsenal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"458\" id=\"i-ae090e9f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602889-1CDB0B6E00000578-896_634x458.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bend it like Becks? Aleksandar Kolarov\'s crossing is an underrated threat in City\'s arsenal</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Remember me? Kolarov\'s precision is every bit as good as United and England hero David Beckham\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"446\" id=\"i-aae20e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602889-00A7DC9100000578-799_634x446.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Remember me? Kolarov\'s precision is every bit as good as United and England hero David Beckham</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Kolarov delivers just like Beckham<br/></font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Not enough is made of Aleksandar Kolarov’s crossing ability. He whips balls into the area that are just begging to be put in the net. When he gets space down the left, he is just as good as David Beckham at putting in dangerous deliveries.</font></p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">City must get behind Gerrard<br/></font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">If Liverpool win the league, this will be Steven Gerrard’s greatest ever season. But City will look to isolate him. If he plays alone in that deeper role, City can have success if they flood players in behind him. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">If Samir Nasri and David Silva can get themselves in behind Gerrard, they can use Edin Dzeko to draw out the centre halves and create space. The City midfielders can then exploit that with clever movement and work the ball in to create chances.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On target: The rejuvenated Steven Gerrard has been key to Liverpool\'s surprise title challenge\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"375\" id=\"i-9f2b0e58\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602889-1CE2CD2600000578-77_634x375.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On target: The rejuvenated Steven Gerrard has been key to Liverpool\'s surprise title challenge</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tactics: City will want to get behind the Liverpool midfield to create opportunities\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"462\" id=\"i-aaf40e76\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602889-1D0A53DC00000578-301_634x462.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tactics: City will want to get behind the Liverpool midfield to create opportunities</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\"> From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\"> Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html\"> CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602712/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Every-child-told-games-kick-seven-minutes-late-weekend.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Every child must be told why games kick off seven minutes late this weekend</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602889/Suarez-Sturridge-Sterling-Aguero-Co-Liverpool-edge-combined-title-chasing-XI.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602889/Suarez-Sturridge-Sterling-Aguero-Co-Liverpool-edge-combined-title-chasing-XI.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"MARTIN KEOWN: Suarez, Sturridge and Sterling over Aguero and Co... why Liverpool have the edge in my combined title-chasing XI\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602889/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">52</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602889-1D0A6F7700000578-507_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:06','2014-04-12 01:36:15'),(50,'6c76875995fa25c35d3da03af010b5a788c746cb365c154c5d88fe7a880886cb','dailymail',NULL,'Thomas Bjorn puts in masterful second round performance at Augusta','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html',' By Phil Casey, Press Association Published: 16:18 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 18:16 EST, 11 April 2014 0 View comments  Arriving at Augusta National this week, Thomas Bjorn was not high on the list of contenders for a first European winner of the Masters since 1999. After all, the 43-year-old Dane had never finished higher than 18th and was a total of 51 over par for his previous 10 Masters appearances, while an opening 73 soon made that 52 over.  On form: Thomas Bjorn of Denmark put in a superb second-round performance, finishing three under Serene: Bjorn will hope to keep his calm throughout the week after comfortably making the cut   But a second round of 68 in testing conditions on Friday gave the world number 29 a halfway total of three under par, four shots behind clubhouse leader and 2012 champion Bubba Watson. \'It was a good day,\' Bjorn said after a round containing four bogeys and eight birdies, four of them coming in the last five holes. \'I played well all the way through. \'I hit two great shots on 13 and walked away with a five. I felt like I had to be a little bit more aggressive in my golf and I took on the shots on 14 and 16 and they paid off. And then it was good to get on the 18th and tap it in for a birdie and sign for 68. A good day\'s work.\' Bjorn\'s best finish in the Masters was back in 2002 and he revealed it was playing badly last year for a share of 46th that was the secret behind only a fifth sub-70 score in 34 rounds. \'I always felt like when I came in here I had to play so well to do any good,\' Bjorn added. \'And I came in here last year and played very poor and I think I finished just outside the top 40 or whatever. \'I felt like I\'ve learned so much from that week last year that I could, even without playing great, find the way around the golf course, put myself in positions.  In touch: Bjorn finished the day four shots off Bubba Watson in the lead at Augusta    \'It was probably the first time I really understood the golf course completely and when I came in this week I just felt like that\'s what you have to do. \'If you play well then you\'ve got a chance of putting good numbers together, but if you don\'t play very well you\'ve still got to try to position yourself and do the right things on the golf course and I certainly did that today. \'There\'s so many holes where you get yourself in a little bit of trouble and if you hit it here you\'ve got a pretty easy chip, but sometimes we get a little bit too cute with our golf, you take on too much and then it will bite you.\' Old and new champion? Bjorn walks with Australian Adam Scott, the winner of last year\'s Masters     More... He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike Scotsman Gallacher delighted to make cut on Masters debut... but is staying grounded Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut Koch named captain for Europe\'s bid to win a third consecutive Solheim Cup Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happens at Augusta National    Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Phil+Casey,+Press+Association\" rel=\"nofollow\">Phil Casey, Press Association</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:18 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 18:16 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Arriving at Augusta National this week, Thomas Bjorn was not high on the list of contenders for a first European winner of the Masters since 1999.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">After all, the 43-year-old Dane had never finished higher than 18th and was a total of 51 over par for his previous 10 Masters appearances, while an opening 73 soon made that 52 over.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On form: Thomas Bjorn of Denmark put in a superb second-round performance, finishing three under\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-a7e20e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602870-1D094B2900000578-349_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On form: Thomas Bjorn of Denmark put in a superb second-round performance, finishing three under</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Serene: Bjorn will hope to keep his calm throughout the week after comfortably making the cut\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"438\" id=\"i-a6090e50\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602870-1D09074700000578-632_634x438.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Serene: Bjorn will hope to keep his calm throughout the week after comfortably making the cut</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"home item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"346\" scrolling=\"no\" seamless=\"\" src=\"http://opta.mc.cloud.opta.net/configurable/index.html?mc=dmgolf1\" width=\"318\"></iframe> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But a second round of 68 in testing conditions on Friday gave the world number 29 a halfway total of three under par, four shots behind clubhouse leader and 2012 champion Bubba Watson.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It was a good day,\' Bjorn said after a round containing four bogeys and eight birdies, four of them coming in the last five holes. \'I played well all the way through.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I hit two great shots on 13 and walked away with a five. I felt like I had to be a little bit more aggressive in my golf and I took on the shots on 14 and 16 and they paid off. And then it was good to get on the 18th and tap it in for a birdie and sign for 68. A good day\'s work.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Bjorn\'s best finish in the Masters was back in 2002 and he revealed it was playing badly last year for a share of 46th that was the secret behind only a fifth sub-70 score in 34 rounds.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I always felt like when I came in here I had to play so well to do any good,\' Bjorn added. \'And I came in here last year and played very poor and I think I finished just outside the top 40 or whatever.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I felt like I\'ve learned so much from that week last year that I could, even without playing great, find the way around the golf course, put myself in positions.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"In touch: Bjorn finished the day four shots off Bubba Watson in the lead at Augusta\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"499\" id=\"i-a7f10e6c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602870-1D01D58500000578-659_634x499.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">In touch: Bjorn finished the day four shots off Bubba Watson in the lead at Augusta</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It was probably the first time I really understood the golf course completely and when I came in this week I just felt like that\'s what you have to do.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'If you play well then you\'ve got a chance of putting good numbers together, but if you don\'t play very well you\'ve still got to try to position yourself and do the right things on the golf course and I certainly did that today.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'There\'s so many holes where you get yourself in a little bit of trouble and if you hit it here you\'ve got a pretty easy chip, but sometimes we get a little bit too cute with our golf, you take on too much and then it will bite you.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Old and new champion? Bjorn walks with Australian Adam Scott, the winner of last year\'s Masters\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"444\" id=\"i-ab250e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602870-1CF8C41D00000578-454_634x444.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Old and new champion? Bjorn walks with Australian Adam Scott, the winner of last year\'s Masters</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html\"> He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602801/Stephen-Gallacher-delighted-make-cut-Masters-debut.html\"> Scotsman Gallacher delighted to make cut on Masters debut... but is staying grounded</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602529/MASTERS-2014-Luke-Donald-admits-pretty-dumb-bunker-gaffe-puts-risk-cut.html\"> Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602315/Koch-named-captain-Europes-bid-win-consecutive-Solheim-Cup.html\"> Koch named captain for Europe\'s bid to win a third consecutive Solheim Cup</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\"> Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602063/MASTERS-LIVE-All-second-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\"> MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happens at Augusta National</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602870/Thomas-Bjorn-puts-masterful-second-round-performance-Augusta.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Bjorn puts in masterful performance having barely been an afterthought before Augusta\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602870/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602870-1D094B2900000578-97_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:07','2014-04-12 01:16:50'),(51,'2c7c7fcefb31919e0dcf2d4fac6692d4277a7c53345cfbd0b6b41e6af87a3ce3','dailymail',NULL,'Thibaut Courtois to face Chelsea as UEFA tell Blues they can\'t stop Atletico Madrid keeper playing','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602902/Thibaut-Courtois-face-Chelsea-UEFA-tell-Blues-stop-Atletico-Madrid-keeper-playing.html',' By Sami Mokbel Follow @@SamiMokbel81_DM Published: 16:56 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 18:09 EST, 11 April 2014 95 shares 143 View comments UEFA have told Chelsea they cannot stop their own goalkeeper Thibaut Courtois playing against them in the Champions League semi-finals. The 21-year-old Belgian, in the third season of a loan from Stamford Bridge to Atletico Madrid, found himself in the middle of a huge contract row after the two clubs were pitted against each other by Friday morning’s draw. Atletico say there is a clause in his loan agreement stipulating they would have to pay a total of £5million to field him in both legs. But a strongly worded UEFA statement on Friday insisted the clause contravenes their regulations and so cannot be applied. VIDEO: Scroll down to watch Thibaut Courtois in action for former club Genk  Decision: UEFA have warned Chelsea they can\'t stop Thibaut Courtois playing against them for Atleico Madrid  Champions League draw Real Madrid vs Bayern Munich Atletico Madrid vs Chelsea Ties to be played on 22-23 and 29-30 of April The statement read: ‘The integrity of sporting competition is a fundamental principle for UEFA. Both the UEFA Champions League and the UEFA disciplinary regulations contain clear provisions which strictly forbid any club to exert, or attempt to exert, any influence whatsoever over the players that another club may (or may not) field in a match. ‘It follows that any provision in a private contract between clubs which might function in such a way as to influence who a club fields in a match is null, void and unenforceable so far as UEFA is concerned. ‘Furthermore, any attempt to enforce such a provision would be a clear violation of both the UEFA Champions League and the UEFA disciplinary regulations and would be sanctioned accordingly.’ It is understood Atletico’s decision to go public with the clause has angered Chelsea. The London club have maintained their stance to not discuss the finer details of the Courtois loan  contract, insisting on Friday such matters should stay confidential. But while they insist Courtois has always been eligible to face them, whether or not they would look to invoke the clause privately remains unclear.  Held to ransom: A clause in Courtois\' loan agreement stated Atletico would have to pay £5m to play the loanee   In form: Courtois kept Neymar and Barcelona at bay to help Atletico reach the last four  More... Courtois can play, but we want £5m OFF Costa price! Chelsea want to strike Atletico deal after UEFA block blues\' demands Chelsea\'s clash with Sunderland moved to help Blues prepare for Atletico trip Chelsea No 2 Courtois can become world No 1, claims Blues coach Lollichon SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race Chelsea want £5m from Atletico for Courtois to play against them... here\'s why the young keeper is rated among the world\'s best Champions League semi-final draw Nevertheless, there is a feeling at Chelsea that Atletico purposefully leaked the details of the penalty clause to ensure the stipulation is publicly scrutinised.Given Friday’s ruling, the clause could be seen to influence Atletico manager Diego Simeone’s decision over Courtois’s selection.Atletico’s tight finances mean they would struggle to pay the £5m, of which Simeone is aware.Both clubs are keen to resolve the issue, knowing their relationship will be key to their transfer dealing this summer. Atletico want to secure another season-long loan deal for the Belgium international next season, while Chelsea want to sign Diego Costa from the Vicente Calderon Stadium and are said to be watching midfielder Arda Turan.One way of resolving the issue could see Atletico reducing Costa’s £32million release clause this summer to help Chelsea sign the star.That would mean Atletico would not be required to directly pay Chelsea any money, though such a move would be open to scrutiny. Watch Thibaut Courtois in action for former club Genk  Donning the gloves: Courtois has been tipped to succeed Petr Cech between the sticks at Stamford Bridge  Meanwhile, Sportsmail understands despite the potentially awkward situation of facing his parent club, Courtois is desperate to play in the semi-final. This is the player’s third loan spell at Atletico and he feels loyal to the club. Chelsea chief executive Ron Gourlay said on Friday: ‘The loan was arranged at the start of the season. He could play against Chelsea - that was never in doubt. ‘Regarding the (UEFA) statement that came out, we’ll evaluate it over the next 24 to 48 hours. As far as we’re concerned we complied with loan rules. He can play against Chelsea - if selected.’ Atletico director Clemente Villa-verde added: ‘Courtois can play, whatever happens. There is a UEFA regulation which prohibits any agreement between clubs that prevents a player from participating freely in the competition. The regulation would have been breached if the player had not been allowed the freedom to participate.’ Real Madrid face Bayern Munich in the other semi-final tie.  Desperate to play: Sportsmail understands Courtois is keen to star for Atletico in the semi-final     More... Courtois can play, but we want £5m OFF Costa price! Chelsea want to strike Atletico deal after UEFA block blues\' demands Chelsea\'s clash with Sunderland moved to help Blues prepare for Atletico trip Chelsea No 2 Courtois can become world No 1, claims Blues coach Lollichon SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race Chelsea want £5m from Atletico for Courtois to play against them... here\'s why the young keeper is rated among the world\'s best  Share or comment on this article 95shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Sami+Mokbel\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sami Mokbel</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@SamiMokbel81_DM\">Follow @@SamiMokbel81_DM</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:56 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 18:09 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602902/Thibaut-Courtois-face-Chelsea-UEFA-tell-Blues-stop-Atletico-Madrid-keeper-playing.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602902/Thibaut-Courtois-face-Chelsea-UEFA-tell-Blues-stop-Atletico-Madrid-keeper-playing.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Chelsea to face Courtois as UEFA tell Blues they can\'t stop Atletico keeper playing\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 95</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602902/Thibaut-Courtois-face-Chelsea-UEFA-tell-Blues-stop-Atletico-Madrid-keeper-playing.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">143</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">UEFA have told Chelsea they cannot stop their own goalkeeper Thibaut Courtois playing against them in the Champions League semi-finals.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The 21-year-old Belgian, in the third season of a loan from Stamford Bridge to Atletico Madrid, found himself in the middle of a huge contract row after the two clubs were pitted against each other by Friday morning’s draw.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Atletico say there is a clause in his loan agreement stipulating they would have to pay a total of £5million to field him in both legs. But a strongly worded UEFA statement on Friday insisted the clause contravenes their regulations and so cannot be applied.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO:</span></font> Scroll down to watch Thibaut Courtois in action for former club Genk</b></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Decision: UEFA have warned Chelsea they can\'t stop Thibaut Courtois playing against them for Atleico Madrid\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"397\" id=\"i-ac530e92\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2602010-1CFDACD400000578-770_634x397.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Decision: UEFA have warned Chelsea they can\'t stop Thibaut Courtois playing against them for Atleico Madrid</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Champions League draw</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Real Madrid vs Bayern Munich </font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Atletico Madrid vs Chelsea <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><i>Ties to be played on 22-23 and 29-30 of April</i><br/></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The statement read: ‘The integrity of sporting competition is a fundamental principle for UEFA. Both the UEFA Champions League and the UEFA disciplinary regulations contain clear provisions which strictly forbid any club to exert, or attempt to exert, any influence whatsoever over the players that another club may (or may not) field in a match.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It follows that any provision in a private contract between clubs which might function in such a way as to influence who a club fields in a match is null, void and unenforceable so far as UEFA is concerned.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Furthermore, any attempt to enforce such a provision would be a clear violation of both the UEFA Champions League and the UEFA disciplinary regulations and would be sanctioned accordingly.’</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It is understood Atletico’s decision to go public with the clause has angered Chelsea. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The London club have maintained their stance to not discuss the finer details of the Courtois loan  contract, insisting on Friday such matters should stay confidential. But while they insist Courtois has always been eligible to face them, whether or not they would look to invoke the clause privately remains unclear.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Held to ransom: A clause in Courtois\' loan agreement stated Atletico would have to pay £5m to play the loanee\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"405\" id=\"i-a7300e59\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602010-1CF9981500000578-860_634x405.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Held to ransom: A clause in Courtois\' loan agreement stated Atletico would have to pay £5m to play the loanee</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"In form: Courtois kept Neymar and Barcelona at bay to help Atletico reach the last four\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"446\" id=\"i-a89a0e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602010-1CF9559A00000578-466_634x446.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">In form: Courtois kept Neymar and Barcelona at bay to help Atletico reach the last four</p><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/foot