 style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I think as players you always want to play in big games,\' Bony said.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'For me, being a big player means playing in the big games. I have 12 league goals and just five more (league) games left. Getting 20 league goals would be nice. I want to score more.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'If you play bad people criticise you, if you score a hat-trick people sing your name, but the main thing is to stay yourself, do what you know and let other people talk.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'We have five more games and I will try to do my best and we\'ll see what will happen.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I have three years left on my contract at Swansea, we have five games left and then the World Cup and we will see what happens. What is more important is the final (league) position we have, and Sunday especially.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bony is hoping to upset the likes of John Terry and the solid Chelsea reaguard\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-9da40e50\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602923-1CF51CF100000578-89_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bony is hoping to upset the likes of John Terry and the solid Chelsea reaguard</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601501/SWANSEA-vs-CHELSEA-All-latest-team-news-stats-visitors-aim-regain-ground-title-race.html\"> SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599742/Michel-Vorm-Keeping-Swansea-Premier-League-No-1-aim-season.html\"> MICHEL VORM EXCLUSIVE: I can\'t wait to go to the World Cup with Holland... but my only target at the moment is keeping Swansea in the Premier League</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602923/Bony-aiming-shoot-Chelsea-little-help-friend-Drogba.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602923/Bony-aiming-shoot-Chelsea-little-help-friend-Drogba.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Bony aiming to shoot down Chelsea, with a little help from his friend Drogba\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602923/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602923-1CD21C2200000578-287_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:08','2014-04-12 00:52:07'),(53,'de708726b24316b2ba03a485a6f7aecb9dcbadb9054440bbb64eabf7e182f345','dailymail',NULL,'It feels just like the 1980s! But are the glory days finally about to return to Anfield?','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html',' By Ian Ladyman Follow @@Ian_Ladyman_DM Published: 17:41 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 17:46 EST, 11 April 2014 73 shares 22 View comments  Early afternoon outside Liverpool\'s training ground on Friday and it was the same as it used to be when the club was last winning league titles. A kid in a full home strip was juggling a football among the throng of autograph hunters while, along the road, another had climbed a ladder to see over the wall. Inside Melwood, it was throwback time, too, as Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers outlined his vision of Blitzkrieg football ahead of Sunday\'s titanic Anfield meeting with Barclays Premier League title rivals Manchester City.  Making his point: Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers is hoping to bring the glory days back to Anfield Getting used to it: Alan Hansen, Kenny Dalglish and Graeme Souness (left-right) lift the Milk Cup in 1984 Flying the flag: A grinning Peter Beardsley celebrates Liverpool winning the league in 1988  More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars \'When we play at Anfield we expect to win,\' said Rodgers. \'This is what we work for, the joy of going and playing. We\'ve an army of supporters behind us who are incredible. We\'ve got a team high in confidence and belief, knowing we can beat anyone. \'At Anfield we\'ve taken a huge amount of points this year and that\'s not going to stop. \'Our confidence to play and to pass and to move and to press and to work will be even higher this weekend and that is something that will be great for us.\' Rodgers, still a young manager in modern terms, was 16-years-old when Liverpool last won the title in 1990. He was a trainee midfielder at Reading, fresh over from Northern Ireland. Few back then thought Liverpool would wait so long for another league triumph. Even fewer perhaps thought the spell would be broken this season. Liverpool, we should remind ourselves here, finished seventh last term.  On target: The rejuvenated Steven Gerrard has been key to Liverpool\'s surprise title challenge   Dynamic duo: Lethal partnership Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge will be major threats to the City defence  LOOK AWAY CITY! Liverpool have won all four home meetings with fellow members of the top seven so far this season, scoring 14 and conceding just once.Man City have only won one of their previous 16 Barclays Premier League matches at Anfield (D5 L10), with that win coming back in May 2003. Nicolas Anelka scored twice that day for the visitors. The scale of progress under Rodgers at Anfield has been immense and now Liverpool stand on the cusp of the most unexpected and fantastic glory. Victory over Manuel Pellegrini\'s City team tomorrow and Liverpool will lead them by seven at the top. Earlier this week, Kenny Dalglish, that most revered Anfield icon, commented that the current Liverpool reminded him of the old Liverpool. \'Everybody is in it together,\' he said. Prompted on this yesterday, Rodgers shoulders eased proud shoulders back just a fraction further. \'Kenny knows the club better than anyone and we are hugely privileged to receive that,\' he said. \'But we\'ve got to keep on working because we haven\'t achieved anything yet. I think what we\'ve shown is we are on the right road.\' Few would dispute that. Liverpool\'s football — so full of energy and forward thrust — has arguably been the best of this season, followed closely by that of Sunday\'s opponents.  Cheering them on: Rodgers vowed to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on City in Sunday\'s clash  In some ways Rodgers and his team have already fulfilled their primary aim. They will play  Champions League football again next season and that, in relative terms, constitutes a successful year already. Pellegrini\'s attempts to place a little pressure on his opponent\'s shoulders yesterday seemed, therefore, a little clumsy. Rodgers, after all, isn\'t the manager who has been told by his chief executive to deliver five trophies in as many years. \'I can\'t believe that at such an important team as Liverpool, the manager has no pressure to win the title,\' said the City manager. \'I think everyone who manages Liverpool has that pressure.\' Rodgers and Pellegrini have a little crossover. City wanted Rodgers to work as assistant to Roberto Mancini a few years ago while Pellegrini was interviewed at Anfield before the appointment of Roy Hodgson. Certainly both are fine coaches and both have some issues to contend with tomorrow.  Presence: Can Liverpool match the physicality of City star Yaya Toure int the midfield battle?  The City manager will know that the pace and directness of players like Daniel Sturridge and Raheem Sterling can seriously worry central defenders Vincent Kompany and Martin Demichelis if they are allowed to break on them. Rodgers, for his part, is aware that he cannot match Yaya Toure and Fernandinho for sheer physical power in midfield. Ultimately, the result may depend on who plays the occasion the better. Rodgers believes his team will be inspired — rather than awed — by the pre-match Hillsborough commemorations, but we must wait for proof of that. Pellegrini\'s players, meanwhile, must hope that European visits to Bayern Munich and Barcelona will help prepare them for what Liverpool believe will be a unique atmosphere.  Tribute: The backdrop to the match will be commemorating the 25th anniversary of Hillsbrorough  \'We will unleash our supporters,\' said Rodgers. \'I\'ve even sensed it myself recently, the roar is  different. Anfield is a different place from the drive up now.\' \'For us the supporters are really the ones that will push us over the line and they\'re the best supporters in the world.\' Occasionally, Rodgers has been accused of talking too much. Certainly he loves his football theory. On Friday, though, he struck the right tone. \'We score a lot of goals because we are relentless in our work to score,\' said Rodgers. \'I think City will probably know that.\' Back in the day, many visiting reams understood it well.\'  More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars   Share or comment on this article 73shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Ian+Ladyman\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ian Ladyman</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@Ian_Ladyman_DM\">Follow @@Ian_Ladyman_DM</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 17:41 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 17:46 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield?\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 73</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">22</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Early afternoon outside Liverpool\'s training ground on Friday and it was the same as it used to be when the club was last winning league titles. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">A kid in a full home strip was juggling a football among the throng of autograph hunters while, along the road, another had climbed a ladder to see over the wall.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Inside Melwood, it was throwback time, too, as Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers outlined his vision of Blitzkrieg football ahead of Sunday\'s titanic Anfield meeting with Barclays Premier League title rivals Manchester City.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Making his point: Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers is hoping to bring the glory days back to Anfield\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"405\" id=\"i-ad990e8e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-1CFF37ED00000578-250_634x405.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Making his point: Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers is hoping to bring the glory days back to Anfield</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Getting used to it: Alan Hansen, Kenny Dalglish and Graeme Souness (left-right) lift the Milk Cup in 1984\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"480\" id=\"i-9c9d0e45\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-0C9D4253000005DC-62_634x480.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Getting used to it: Alan Hansen, Kenny Dalglish and Graeme Souness (left-right) lift the Milk Cup in 1984</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Flying the flag: A grinning Peter Beardsley celebrates Liverpool winning the league in 1988\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-aa5d0e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-0B86EC7100000578-772_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Flying the flag: A grinning Peter Beardsley celebrates Liverpool winning the league in 1988</p> </div><p> </p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602389/Aguero-fit-Liverpool-clash-City-striker-recovers-hamstring-injury.html\"> Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\"> Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'When we play at Anfield we expect to win,\' said Rodgers. \'This is what we work for, the joy of going and playing. We\'ve an army of supporters behind us who are incredible. We\'ve got a team high in confidence and belief, knowing we can beat anyone.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'At Anfield we\'ve taken a huge amount of points this year and that\'s not going to stop.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Our confidence to play and to pass and to move and to press and to work will be even higher this weekend and that is something that will be great for us.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Rodgers, still a young manager in modern terms, was 16-years-old when Liverpool last won the title in 1990. He was a trainee midfielder at Reading, fresh over from Northern Ireland.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Few back then thought Liverpool would wait so long for another league triumph. Even fewer perhaps thought the spell would be broken this season. Liverpool, we should remind ourselves here, finished seventh last term.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On target: The rejuvenated Steven Gerrard has been key to Liverpool\'s surprise title challenge\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"406\" id=\"i-ab1d0e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-1CE2CD2600000578-260_634x406.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On target: The rejuvenated Steven Gerrard has been key to Liverpool\'s surprise title challenge</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dynamic duo: Lethal partnership Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge will be major threats to the City defence\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"454\" id=\"i-ad3e0e91\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-1C7E6BCC00000578-722_634x454.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dynamic duo: Lethal partnership Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge will be major threats to the City defence</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>LOOK AWAY CITY!<br/></b></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> Liverpool have won all four home meetings with fellow members of the top seven so far this season, scoring 14 and conceding just once.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Man City have only won one of their previous 16 Barclays Premier League matches at Anfield (D5 L10), with that win coming back in May 2003. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Nicolas Anelka scored twice that day for the visitors.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The scale of progress under Rodgers at Anfield has been immense and now Liverpool stand on the cusp of the most unexpected and fantastic glory. Victory over Manuel Pellegrini\'s City team tomorrow and Liverpool will lead them by seven at the top.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Earlier this week, Kenny Dalglish, that most revered Anfield icon, commented that the current Liverpool reminded him of the old Liverpool.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Everybody is in it together,\' he said. Prompted on this yesterday, Rodgers shoulders eased proud shoulders back just a fraction further.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Kenny knows the club better than anyone and we are hugely privileged to receive that,\' he said. \'But we\'ve got to keep on working because we haven\'t achieved anything yet. I think what we\'ve shown is we are on the right road.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Few would dispute that. Liverpool\'s football — so full of energy and forward thrust — has arguably been the best of this season, followed closely by that of Sunday\'s opponents.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Cheering them on: Rodgers vowed to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on City in Sunday\'s clash\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"379\" id=\"i-ad440e95\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-1CE2E7EA00000578-352_634x379.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Cheering them on: Rodgers vowed to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on City in Sunday\'s clash</p> </div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In some ways Rodgers and his team have already fulfilled their primary aim. They will play  Champions League football again next season and that, in relative terms, constitutes a successful year already.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pellegrini\'s attempts to place a little pressure on his opponent\'s shoulders yesterday seemed, therefore, a little clumsy. Rodgers, after all, isn\'t the manager who has been told by his chief executive to deliver five trophies in as many years.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I can\'t believe that at such an important team as Liverpool, the manager has no pressure to win the title,\' said the City manager. \'I think everyone who manages Liverpool has that pressure.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Rodgers and Pellegrini have a little crossover. City wanted Rodgers to work as assistant to Roberto Mancini a few years ago while Pellegrini was interviewed at Anfield before the appointment of Roy Hodgson. Certainly both are fine coaches and both have some issues to contend with tomorrow.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Presence: Can Liverpool match the physicality of City star Yaya Toure int the midfield battle?\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"396\" id=\"i-ad0b0e95\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-1CDAA90A00000578-983_634x396.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Presence: Can Liverpool match the physicality of City star Yaya Toure int the midfield battle?</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The City manager will know that the pace and directness of players like Daniel Sturridge and Raheem Sterling can seriously worry central defenders Vincent Kompany and Martin Demichelis if they are allowed to break on them. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Rodgers, for his part, is aware that he cannot match Yaya Toure and Fernandinho for sheer physical power in midfield. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Ultimately, the result may depend on who plays the occasion the better.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Rodgers believes his team will be inspired — rather than awed — by the pre-match Hillsborough commemorations, but we must wait for proof of that. Pellegrini\'s players, meanwhile, must hope that European visits to Bayern Munich and Barcelona will help prepare them for what Liverpool believe will be a unique atmosphere.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tribute: The backdrop to the match will be commemorating the 25th anniversary of Hillsbrorough\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"381\" id=\"i-aaa10e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-18D6C447000005DC-237_634x381.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tribute: The backdrop to the match will be commemorating the 25th anniversary of Hillsbrorough</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We will unleash our supporters,\' said Rodgers. \'I\'ve even sensed it myself recently, the roar is  different. Anfield is a different place from the drive up now.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'For us the supporters are really the ones that will push us over the line and they\'re the best supporters in the world.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Occasionally, Rodgers has been accused of talking too much. Certainly he loves his football theory. On Friday, though, he struck the right tone.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We score a lot of goals because we are relentless in our work to score,\' said Rodgers. \'I think City will probably know that.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Back in the day, many visiting reams understood it well.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602389/Aguero-fit-Liverpool-clash-City-striker-recovers-hamstring-injury.html\"> Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\"> Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602794/It-feels-just-like-1980s-But-glory-days-finally-return-Anfield.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Rodgers\' rampant Liverpool feel just like the legendary 1980s sides... but will the glory days finally return to Anfield?\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602794/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">73</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602794-1D0A5B0D00000578-548_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:08','2014-04-12 00:46:43'),(54,'4e92f164a6af906034c6582fe16b8177ed0f25c9ce1b9040b2bc791ae4d685a6','dailymail',NULL,'JAMIE CARRAGHER: Raheem Sterling, Ross Barkley and Adnan Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html',' By Jamie Carragher Published: 16:00 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 17:45 EST, 11 April 2014 51 shares 28 View comments Luis Suarez is odds-on to win PFA Player of the Year but less clear-cut is who will receive the Young Player’s award. Eden Hazard and Daniel Sturridge are the favourites but these five young stars also deserve to be high up in people’s thinking.  Clear favourite: Liverpool frontman Luis Suarez is odds-on to win the PFA Player of the Year award   Boy in Blue: Chelsea wideman Eden Hazard has been one of the standout performers for the Blues this season   Natural goalscorer: Liverpool striker Daniel Sturridge has been lethal in front of the goal for the Reds   1. Raheem Sterling There was always a buzz around Raheem when I was at Liverpool but this season he has shown there is substance to the hype. He has been brilliant since getting back into the team, adding goals to his speed on the flanks, and he looks set to go to the World Cup.  Living up to the hype: Liverpool frontman Raheem Sterling has added goals to his game this season   2. Ross Barkley Back in August, when I wrote my second column for Sportsmail, I highlighted the Everton midfielder as one to watch and he has done nothing but improve. An explosive talent, with energy and two great feet, he is another who Roy Hodgson will come calling for in June.  One to watch: Ross Barkley has constantly improved this season as Everton challenge for fourth   More... EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Suarez, Gerrard AND Rodgers clean up as Liverpool trio take Premier League manager and player of the month awards Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Real Madrid 0-4 Benfica: Zidane\'s son taken off as Spanish side are smashed in UEFA Youth League semi-final in Switzerland   3. Luke Shaw Scouts have been flocking to St Mary’s to see Shaw in action and it is no wonder the top clubs want to prise the left back away from Southampton. If he moves this summer, Shaw will command a huge fee but it will be warranted as he has consistently impressed.  Top talent: Southampton\'s Luke Shaw has attracted attention from a host of rival Premier League clubs   4. Adnan Januzaj Manchester United have endured a disappointing campaign but the one bright spot has been the emergence of Januzaj. He’s played 32 games, which is a lot for a  19-year-old, but he has a big future. I liked what I saw of him in pre-season and he has built on that impression.  Bright spot: Adnan Januzaj has shined in an otherwise disappointing campaign for Manchester United   5. John Stones Roberto Martinez is not afraid to give young players opportunities if they are good enough and Stones has impressed since being given his Everton chance. I like the way he uses the ball and it was interesting to see he completed 39 of the 40 passes he attempted against Arsenal last week.  Taking his chances: Everton defender John Stones (left) is equally adept at passing as he his tackling    More... EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Suarez, Gerrard AND Rodgers clean up as Liverpool trio take Premier League manager and player of the month awards Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Real Madrid 0-4 Benfica: Zidane\'s son taken off as Spanish side are smashed in UEFA Youth League semi-final in Switzerland   Share or comment on this article 51shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1076287/Jamie-Carragher.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jamie Carragher</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:00 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 17:45 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 51</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">28</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Luis Suarez is odds-on to win PFA Player of the Year but less clear-cut is who will receive the Young Player’s award. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Eden Hazard and Daniel Sturridge are the favourites but these five young stars also deserve to be high up in people’s thinking.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Clear favourite: Liverpool frontman Luis Suarez is odds-on to win the PFA Player of the Year award\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"406\" id=\"i-a8ea0e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-1CB20B2C00000578-901_634x406.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Clear favourite: Liverpool frontman Luis Suarez is odds-on to win the PFA Player of the Year award</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Boy in Blue: Chelsea wideman Eden Hazard has been one of the standout performers for the Blues this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"413\" id=\"i-a9de0e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-06DCB76A00000514-482_634x413.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Boy in Blue: Chelsea wideman Eden Hazard has been one of the standout performers for the Blues this season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Natural goalscorer: Liverpool striker Daniel Sturridge has been lethal in front of the goal for the Reds\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"418\" id=\"i-a9900e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-1B099BE900000578-462_634x418.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Natural goalscorer: Liverpool striker Daniel Sturridge has been lethal in front of the goal for the Reds</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">1. Raheem Sterling </font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">There was always a buzz around Raheem when I was at Liverpool but this season he has shown there is substance to the hype. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He has been brilliant since getting back into the team, adding goals to his speed on the flanks, and he looks set to go to the World Cup.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Living up to the hype: Liverpool frontman Raheem Sterling has added goals to his game this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"486\" id=\"i-aa9b0e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-1B4BB6D600000578-473_634x486.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Living up to the hype: Liverpool frontman Raheem Sterling has added goals to his game this season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">2. Ross Barkley </font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Back in August, when I wrote my second column for <i>Sportsmail</i>, I highlighted the Everton midfielder as one to watch and he has done nothing but improve. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">An explosive talent, with energy and two great feet, he is another who Roy Hodgson will come calling for in June.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"One to watch: Ross Barkley has constantly improved this season as Everton challenge for fourth\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"478\" id=\"i-a8fb0e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-1CE2417E00000578-931_634x478.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">One to watch: Ross Barkley has constantly improved this season as Everton challenge for fourth</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601760/Brendan-Rodgers-Luis-Suarez-amd-Steven-Gerrard-Premier-League-manager-player-month-awards.html\"> Suarez, Gerrard AND Rodgers clean up as Liverpool trio take Premier League manager and player of the month awards</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601458/LIVERPOOL-vs-MANCHESTER-CITY-All-latest-team-news-stats-crunch-battle-race-Premier-League-title.html\"> LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602488/Real-Madrid-0-4-Benfica-UEFA-Youth-League-semi-final.html\"> Real Madrid 0-4 Benfica: Zidane\'s son taken off as Spanish side are smashed in UEFA Youth League semi-final in Switzerland</a></li> </ul> </div> <br/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"><br/><br/> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">3. Luke Shaw </font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Scouts have been flocking to St Mary’s to see Shaw in action and it is no wonder the top clubs want to prise the left back away from Southampton. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">If he moves this summer, Shaw will command a huge fee but it will be warranted as he has consistently impressed.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Top talent: Southampton\'s Luke Shaw has attracted attention from a host of rival Premier League clubs\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"469\" id=\"i-a5520e4b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-0668A55300000514-552_634x469.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Top talent: Southampton\'s Luke Shaw has attracted attention from a host of rival Premier League clubs</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">4. Adnan Januzaj </font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Manchester United have endured a disappointing campaign but the one bright spot has been the emergence of Januzaj. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He’s played 32 games, which is a lot for a  19-year-old, but he has a big future. I liked what I saw of him in pre-season and he has built on that impression.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bright spot: Adnan Januzaj has shined in an otherwise disappointing campaign for Manchester United\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"487\" id=\"i-aba10e8a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-1CDE782C00000578-675_634x487.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bright spot: Adnan Januzaj has shined in an otherwise disappointing campaign for Manchester United</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">5. John Stones </font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Roberto Martinez is not afraid to give young players opportunities if they are good enough and Stones has impressed since being given his Everton chance. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I like the way he uses the ball and it was interesting to see he completed 39 of the 40 passes he attempted against Arsenal last week.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Taking his chances: Everton defender John Stones (left) is equally adept at passing as he his tackling\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-99890e1b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-1CE2384100000578-13_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Taking his chances: Everton defender John Stones (left) is equally adept at passing as he his tackling</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601760/Brendan-Rodgers-Luis-Suarez-amd-Steven-Gerrard-Premier-League-manager-player-month-awards.html\"> Suarez, Gerrard AND Rodgers clean up as Liverpool trio take Premier League manager and player of the month awards</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601458/LIVERPOOL-vs-MANCHESTER-CITY-All-latest-team-news-stats-crunch-battle-race-Premier-League-title.html\"> LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602488/Real-Madrid-0-4-Benfica-UEFA-Youth-League-semi-final.html\"> Real Madrid 0-4 Benfica: Zidane\'s son taken off as Spanish side are smashed in UEFA Youth League semi-final in Switzerland</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602715/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">51</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602715-1D0A252700000578-794_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:09','2014-04-12 00:45:49'),(55,'30d440ff2b1874b09757b31824dd61552169aadb04a65fd10c30115f2567a231','dailymail',NULL,'Leeds United owner Massimo Cellino calls police after secret cameras found','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602519/EXCLUSIVE-Police-Leeds-theft-probe-new-owner-Massimo-Cellino-calls-cops-secret-spy-cameras-Elland-Road-boardroom-toilets.html',' Leeds managing director David Haigh resigned on FridayHaigh claims he was left with \'no alternative\'Spokesman says it has nothing to do with police investigation By Nick Harris Published: 09:59 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 17:42 EST, 11 April 2014 91 shares  Police have been called in by the new owner of Leeds United, Massimo Cellino, after secret spy cameras were discovered at Elland Road. In a sensational twist to the convoluted takeover saga at Leeds, West Yorkshire Police have launched a theft investigation, which sources say relates to club funds used to install the cameras. Sportsmail understands that when controversial new owner Cellino arrived in Leeds on Wednesday to start taking charge of the club, a security sweep found the cameras in the boardroom and the toilets. New owner: Massimo Cellino, pictured right with Leeds boss Brian McDermott, took over the club this week  Old regime: David Haigh, formerly of GFH, in the stands at Elland Road Cellino called in the police, who spent Wednesday evening and much of Thursday trying to ascertain how the cameras got there, what money was used to pay for them and why anyone would want them installed.‘He’s clearly not thrilled that these cameras were there and the police are taking those concerns seriously,’ a source told Sportsmail.Italian Cellino, 57, officially became a board member of Leeds on Tuesday after his £35million deal to buy 75 per cent of the club from Bahrain bankers GFH was effectively given the green light last Saturday. The Football League gave him the all-clear after deeming that a tax-evasion offence in Italy was not due to dishonesty. It is not known who paid for the cameras to be fitted or where the money came from. A spokesman for GFH said: ‘We have no comment.’West Yorkshire Police would provide no detailed information about their investigation. Head of crime for Leeds, Dep Supt Pat Twiggs, said: ‘We can confirm that police are investigating an allegation of theft relating to Leeds United Football Club following a report made by the club on April 9. Rockstar: Cellino plays guitar with his band Maurilios and used AC/DC\'s \'Highway to Hell\' to describe Leeds Thumbs up: Cellino has made it his \'first priority\' to buy back the Championship club\'s Elland Road stadium ‘Enquiries are at an early stage and we are not in a position to give any further information.’Cellino has made clear he intends to run Leeds, who host Blackpool today, and that GFH - who retain 25 per cent of the club - and their personnel will be marginalised. In another twist last night, former GFH employee David Haigh, who had been contracted to become CEO in the Cellino regime, quit as managing director. Haigh said: ‘Owing to various statements made by and on behalf of the new majority owners of Leeds United, I am left with no alternative than to resign. ‘This is a matter of particular regret to me since I was the person who introduced Eleonora Sport (Cellino’s company) to the club’s owners. I also gave them my full and constant support in the Football League’s lengthy approval process.’   Colourful character: Cellino is the guitar-playing, chain-smoking charmer who kept Leeds from administration    Making a point: Leeds striker Ross McCormack (second right) celebrates after scoring earlier this season    More... Elland Road is my Highway to Hell! Guitar player, dishwasher and convicted fraudster... Sportsmail meets Cellino, the man who wants to save Leeds Football League give Cellino green light to take over Leeds and become club director MARTIN SAMUEL - THE DEBATE: I\'m not anti-Everton, I\'m just against the loan system - but the foolish paranoia of football fans never ceases to amaze me Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit   Share or comment on this article 91shares','\n<ul class=\"article-summary sport\"><li><b><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">Leeds managing director David Haigh resigned on Friday</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">Haigh claims he was left with \'no alternative\'<br/></font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">Spokesman says it has nothing to do with police investigation</font></b></li></ul>\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Nick+Harris\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nick Harris</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 09:59 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 17:42 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602519/EXCLUSIVE-Police-Leeds-theft-probe-new-owner-Massimo-Cellino-calls-cops-secret-spy-cameras-Elland-Road-boardroom-toilets.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602519/EXCLUSIVE-Police-Leeds-theft-probe-new-owner-Massimo-Cellino-calls-cops-secret-spy-cameras-Elland-Road-boardroom-toilets.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"EXCLUSIVE: Police in Leeds theft probe - new owner Cellino calls in cops after secret spy cameras found in Elland Road boardroom... and toilets!\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 91</b> <span>shares</span> </div> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Police have been called in by the new owner of Leeds United, Massimo Cellino, after secret spy cameras were discovered at Elland Road.  <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In a sensational twist to the convoluted takeover saga at Leeds, West Yorkshire Police have launched a theft investigation, which sources say relates to club funds used to install the cameras.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sportsmail understands that when controversial new owner Cellino arrived in Leeds on Wednesday to start taking charge of the club, a security sweep found the cameras in the boardroom and the toilets.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"New owner: Massimo Cellino, pictured right with Leeds boss Brian McDermott, took over the club this week\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"472\" id=\"i-aba60e89\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1D00D6ED00000578-787_634x472.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">New owner: Massimo Cellino, pictured right with Leeds boss Brian McDermott, took over the club this week</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"floatRHS\"> <img alt=\"Old regime: David Haigh, formerly of GFH, in the stands at Elland Road\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a6080e5a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602519-1631221A000005DC-697_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Old regime: David Haigh, formerly of GFH, in the stands at Elland Road</p></div> <p> </p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Cellino called in the police, who spent Wednesday evening and much of Thursday trying to ascertain how the cameras got there, what money was used to pay for them and why anyone would want them installed.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘He’s clearly not thrilled that these cameras were there and the police are taking those concerns seriously,’ a source told Sportsmail.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Italian Cellino, 57, officially became a board member of Leeds on Tuesday after his £35million deal to buy 75 per cent of the club from Bahrain bankers GFH was effectively given the green light last Saturday. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Football League gave him the all-clear after deeming that a tax-evasion offence in Italy was not due to dishonesty. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It is not known who paid for the cameras to be fitted or where the money came from. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">A spokesman for GFH said: ‘We have no comment.’</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">West Yorkshire Police would provide no detailed information about their investigation. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Head of crime for Leeds, Dep Supt Pat Twiggs, said: ‘We can confirm that police are investigating an allegation of theft relating to Leeds United Football Club following a report made by the club on April 9.</font></p></div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rockstar: Cellino plays guitar with his band Maurilios and used AC/DC\'s \'Highway to Hell\' to describe Leeds\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"429\" id=\"i-aabc0e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1CFE434400000578-842_634x429.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rockstar: Cellino plays guitar with his band Maurilios and used AC/DC\'s \'Highway to Hell\' to describe Leeds</p> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Thumbs up: Cellino has made it his \'first priority\' to buy back the Championship club\'s Elland Road stadium\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-a8e70e69\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1D00D71D00000578-402_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Thumbs up: Cellino has made it his \'first priority\' to buy back the Championship club\'s Elland Road stadium</p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘Enquiries are at an early stage and we are not in a position to give any further information.’<br/>Cellino has made clear he intends to run Leeds, who host Blackpool today, and that GFH - who retain 25 per cent of the club - and their personnel will be marginalised. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In another twist last night, former GFH employee David Haigh, who had been contracted to become CEO in the Cellino regime, quit as managing director.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Haigh said: ‘Owing to various statements made by and on behalf of the new majority owners of Leeds United, I am left with no alternative than to resign.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘This is a matter of particular regret to me since I was the person who introduced Eleonora Sport (Cellino’s company) to the club’s owners. I also gave them my full and constant support in the Football League’s lengthy approval process.’</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Colourful character: Cellino is the guitar-playing, chain-smoking charmer who kept Leeds from administration\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"438\" id=\"i-a9be0e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602519-1CCC620A00000578-152_634x438.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Colourful character: Cellino is the guitar-playing, chain-smoking charmer who kept Leeds from administration</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Making a point: Leeds striker Ross McCormack (second right) celebrates after scoring earlier this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-ac1d0e85\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-18DD0AE700000578-853_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Making a point: Leeds striker Ross McCormack (second right) celebrates after scoring earlier this season</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601889/Elland-Road-Highway-Hell-Guitar-player-dishwasher-convicted-fraudster-Sportsmail-meets-Cellino-man-wants-save-Leeds.html\"> Elland Road is my Highway to Hell! Guitar player, dishwasher and convicted fraudster... Sportsmail meets Cellino, the man who wants to save Leeds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601787/Football-League-Cellino-green-light-Leeds-club-director.html\"> Football League give Cellino green light to take over Leeds and become club director</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601297/MARTIN-SAMUEL-THE-DEBATE-Im-not-anti-Everton-Im-just-against-loan-foolish-paranoia-football-fans-never-ceases-amaze-me.html\"> MARTIN SAMUEL - THE DEBATE: I\'m not anti-Everton, I\'m just against the loan system - but the foolish paranoia of football fans never ceases to amaze me</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602434/Welbeck-Cleverley-seen-dancing-street-early-hours-The-day-United-crashed-Champions-League.html\"> Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602519/EXCLUSIVE-Police-Leeds-theft-probe-new-owner-Massimo-Cellino-calls-cops-secret-spy-cameras-Elland-Road-boardroom-toilets.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602519/EXCLUSIVE-Police-Leeds-theft-probe-new-owner-Massimo-Cellino-calls-cops-secret-spy-cameras-Elland-Road-boardroom-toilets.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"EXCLUSIVE: Police in Leeds theft probe - new owner Cellino calls in cops after secret spy cameras found in Elland Road boardroom... and toilets!\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602519/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">91</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602519-1CF0DCC800000578-971_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:09','2014-04-12 00:42:55'),(56,'73cfb429fe30950f8259544a126f0d7914debb6498dfc5db143c26be9af73c9a','dailymail',NULL,'Marathon win would be Mo Farah\'s finest feat as Olympic champ steps into the unknown','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602824/Marathon-win-Mo-Farahs-finest-feat-Olympic-champ-steps-unknown.html',' By Laura Williamson Follow @@laura_mail Published: 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 17:24 EST, 11 April 2014 6 shares 10 View comments Mo Farah’s London Marathon full debut on Sunday is a great leap into the unknown; an exciting, challenging and potentially dramatic test of what this magnificent athlete is capable. Farah does not know how he will feel after 20 miles on the streets of the capital, if his ability on the track will convert to the gruelling demands of the road or how he will fare against one of the most competitive fields ever assembled over 26.2 miles. But the reigning Olympic champion at 10,000 metres and 5,000m knows one thing for certain: victory on The Mall would be the greatest feat of his career.  Home turf: Mo Farah runs along the riverside in front of London\'s famous Tower Bridge   National treasure: Mo Farah won two Olympic gold medals at London 2012 in the men\'s 5,000m and 10,000m  More... Bekele throws down the gauntlet as Farah\'s big rival sends out message with Paris win Farah gunning for British record at London marathon after collapse in New York Farah\'s Commonwealth plans depend on how he fares in Glasgow dress rehearsal Farah taken away in wheelchair after collapsing at the end of the New York half marathon Farah set for Glasgow... but for Diamond League (not Commonwealth Games) ‘It would be incredible — the greatest thing I’ve ever achieved, not just in terms of the London Marathon but in terms of the field and the people in it,’ he said. ‘At the London Olympics, I’m sure most believed that if I had a bad day I would finish third or fourth but here we don’t know what’s going to happen. ‘The public doesn’t quite understand because they’re so used to me winning. They just want me to win, but I’m as  clueless as everyone else. Yes, I have  covered 20 miles and a little bit but I haven’t covered the full distance at that pace. The only way to find out is to race.’ For any athlete, let alone a double Olympic and three-time world champion, this could be a terrifying thought. Farah ran half the distance last year to familiarise himself with the demands of marathon race day, but this will still be a new experience for a man so used to the routines, training and tactics of a 400m track. The Briton insists he is excited about taking on a new challenge after those hard months away from his family running up to 150 miles a week on the dirt tracks of Kenya’s Rift Valley, but he is still not the bookmakers’ favourite, despite home advantage. Wilson Kipsang, the world record holder, claimed Farah was ‘not a big threat’ this week but he, too, conceded we do not really know his capabilities. Farah’s coach, Alberto Salazar, has advised the 31-year-old not to follow the near world-record pace expected to be set by Haile Gebrselassie, who will take the leading pack to the halfway mark in around 58 minutes. Ready and willing: Mo Farah insists he is not risking his reputation by taking on the London Marathon   Seeing stars: The long distance runner collapsed at the end of the New York half marathon in March    Up for it: Double Olympic champion Farah poses in front of Tower Bridge to promote the London marathon Instead, Farah will run about 30 seconds slower, ready to attack in the second half of the race. Patience will be crucial. If he goes off too quickly his race could be over before it has begun. More realistic success for Farah on his debut would be to break Steve Jones’s 1985 British record of 2hr 7min 13sec to add to the national marks he already holds at 1500m, 5,000m, 10,000m and the half-marathon. To be Britain’s best over so many distances  would be a phenomenal achievement, after all. Jones, now 58, expressed sadness that his record looks set to go but was surprised it had stood for nearly 29 years. His mark belongs to a different era  — Jones drank 10 pints of cider at a wedding the night before setting a new world half- marathon best in Birmingham in 1984. ‘Mo and I are miles apart, but I ran with no fear and I can’t see why Mo would have any fear,’ he said. ‘I’m just a journeyman compared with him. ‘It wouldn’t be a surprise if he shattered the British record. It wouldn’t surprise me if he won the race. He’s going to go down as one of the great British runners of all time.’ Farah’s place in such prestigious company is assured, but there should be no sense of disappointment or failure if he does not become the first British male winner since Eamonn Martin in 1993. Should he break Jones’s British record, that accolade can wait for another year. On the run: Farah will be the star attraction at the London marathon later this month Stepping up: Farah, pictured during the New York half marathon, will be doubling his distance in London   Defiant: Farah insists his collapse in New York has not affected his preparations for the London marathon   More... Bekele throws down the gauntlet as Farah\'s big rival sends out message with Paris win Farah gunning for British record at London marathon after collapse in New York Farah\'s Commonwealth plans depend on how he fares in Glasgow dress rehearsal Farah taken away in wheelchair after collapsing at the end of the New York half marathon Farah set for Glasgow... but for Diamond League (not Commonwealth Games)   Share or comment on this article 6shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Laura+Williamson\" rel=\"nofollow\">Laura Williamson</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@laura_mail\">Follow @@laura_mail</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 17:24 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602824/Marathon-win-Mo-Farahs-finest-feat-Olympic-champ-steps-unknown.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602824/Marathon-win-Mo-Farahs-finest-feat-Olympic-champ-steps-unknown.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Marathon win would be Farah\'s finest feat as Olympic champ steps into the unknown\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 