nt style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">For any athlete, let alone a double Olympic and three-time world champion, this could be a terrifying thought. Farah ran half the distance last year to familiarise himself with the demands of marathon race day, but this will still be a new experience for a man so used to the routines, training and tactics of a 400m track.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Briton insists he is excited about taking on a new challenge after those hard months away from his family running up to 150 miles a week on the dirt tracks of Kenya’s Rift Valley, but he is still not the bookmakers’ favourite, despite home advantage. Wilson Kipsang, the world record holder, claimed Farah was ‘not a big threat’ this week but he, too, conceded we do not really know his capabilities.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Farah’s coach, Alberto Salazar, has advised the 31-year-old not to follow the near world-record pace expected to be set by Haile Gebrselassie, who will take the leading pack to the halfway mark in around 58 minutes. </font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Ready and willing: Mo Farah insists he is not risking his reputation by taking on the London Marathon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"437\" id=\"i-aed50e98\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599813-1CEFE82200000578-468_634x437.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Ready and willing: Mo Farah insists he is not risking his reputation by taking on the London Marathon</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Seeing stars: The long distance runner collapsed at the end of the New York half marathon in March\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"432\" id=\"i-ad8e0e8c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599813-1C591BAE00000578-763_634x432.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Seeing stars: The long distance runner collapsed at the end of the New York half marathon in March</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Up for it: Double Olympic champion Farah poses in front of Tower Bridge to promote the London marathon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"454\" id=\"i-b0f30ea7\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599813-1CEFAAE400000578-620_634x454.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Up for it: Double Olympic champion Farah poses in front of Tower Bridge to promote the London marathon</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Instead, Farah will run about 30 seconds slower, ready to attack in the second half of the race. Patience will be crucial. If he goes off too quickly his race could be over before it has begun.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">More realistic success for Farah on his debut would be to break Steve Jones’s 1985 British record of 2hr 7min 13sec to add to the national marks he already holds at 1500m, 5,000m, 10,000m and the half-marathon. To be Britain’s best over so many distances  would be a phenomenal achievement, after all.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Jones, now 58, expressed sadness that his record looks set to go but was surprised it had stood for nearly 29 years. His mark belongs to a different era  — Jones drank 10 pints of cider at a wedding the night before setting a new world half- marathon best in Birmingham in 1984.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Mo and I are miles apart, but I ran with no fear and I can’t see why Mo would have any fear,’ he said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’m just a journeyman compared with him.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It wouldn’t be a surprise if he shattered the British record. It wouldn’t surprise me if he won the race. He’s going to go down as one of the great British runners of all time.’ </font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Farah’s place in such prestigious company is assured, but there should be no sense of disappointment or failure if he does not become the first British male winner since Eamonn Martin in 1993. Should he break Jones’s British record, that accolade can wait for another year.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the run: Farah will be the star attraction at the London marathon later this month\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"445\" id=\"i-aecd0e91\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599813-1CEFC84900000578-320_634x445.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the run: Farah will be the star attraction at the London marathon later this month</p> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Stepping up: Farah, pictured during the New York half marathon, will be doubling his distance in London\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"491\" id=\"i-aa5a0e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599813-1C57406F00000578-232_634x491.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Stepping up: Farah, pictured during the New York half marathon, will be doubling his distance in London</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Defiant: Farah insists his collapse in New York has not affected his preparations for the London marathon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"367\" id=\"i-ac3f0e88\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599813-1CF002F400000578-899_634x367.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Defiant: Farah insists his collapse in New York has not affected his preparations for the London marathon</p> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2599074/Bekele-throws-gauntlet-Farahs-big-rival-sends-message-Paris-win.html\"> Bekele throws down the gauntlet as Farah\'s big rival sends out message with Paris win</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2599813/Mo-Farah-gunning-British-record-London-marathon-collapse-New-York.html\"> Farah gunning for British record at London marathon after collapse in New York</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2580489/Mo-Farahs-Commonwealth-plans-depend-fares-Glasgow-dress-rehearsal.html\"> Farah\'s Commonwealth plans depend on how he fares in Glasgow dress rehearsal</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2582066/Farah-collapses-end-New-York-half-marathon.html\"> Farah taken away in wheelchair after collapsing at the end of the New York half marathon</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2573314/Mo-Farah-race-Glasgow-Diamond-League-meeting.html\"> Farah set for Glasgow... but for Diamond League (not Commonwealth Games)</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602824/Marathon-win-Mo-Farahs-finest-feat-Olympic-champ-steps-unknown.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602824/Marathon-win-Mo-Farahs-finest-feat-Olympic-champ-steps-unknown.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Marathon win would be Farah\'s finest feat as Olympic champ steps into the unknown\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602824/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">6</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602824-1D0A506E00000578-119_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:10','2014-04-12 00:24:37'),(57,'bcab26989b7d327b64abd25d3a51c635adb31d9b0e36b4154e7b188276b7f60e','dailymail',NULL,'From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html',' By Isaac Williams Published: 17:16 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 17:16 EST, 11 April 2014 17 shares 9 View comments  As Manchester City travel to league leaders Liverpool in the biggest game of the season, Sportsmail looks back at some of the epic title-deciding clashes from down the years.  1924 Huddersfield v N Forest The 1923-24 season was won by the closest margin in the history of the Football League. With goal average taking precedence over goal difference, Huddersfield Town secured a 1-1 draw against Forest to pip Cardiff City to the post by 0.024 goals. 1962 Ipswich v Aston Villa In 1957, Ipswich Town were in the Third Division South of the Football League. Just five years later, a miraculous period under Alf Ramsey left them one result away from the League title. A 2-0 victory completed arguably the greatest rise in the history of the game.  Jubilation: Ipswich fans and players celebrate Ray Crawford\'s opening goal to set them on the way to the title  1968 Man City v Newcastle Forty-four years before City’s 2012 heroics, exactly the same happened. Manchester United went to Sunderland, knowing a win would grant them the championship. Their 2-1 defeat, though, ensured City’s 4-3 win at Newcastle was enough to turn Manchester sky-blue for a season at least.  Raise a toast: City players celebrate the 1968 title win - top row (L-R) Glyn Pardoe, George Heslop, Alan Oakes, Colin Bell, Francis Lee - bottom row (L-R) Tony Book, Mike Doyle, Ken Mulhearn  1972 Leeds v Wolves With the top four separated by a single point, Leeds travelled to Molineux on the final day needing just a draw to be crowned champions. However, in a game now infamous for an attempted case of match-fixing, Wolves beat them 2-1, gifting the title to Brian Clough’s Derby County.   More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds  Letting it slip: Leeds keeper David Harvey (right) and Paul Reaney after Wolves go 1-0 up  1989 Liverpool v Arsenal On the last day, Arsenal needed a two-goal win, while Liverpool just had to prevent such a result. The Gunners led 1-0 until the final minute, when Michael Thomas broke free and, with virtually the last kick, dinked the ball over Bruce Grobbelaar to secure a first title in 18 years.  Iconic: Michael Thomas hits home past Bruce Grobbelaar to hand Arsenal the title at Anfield in 1989  2002 Man Utd v Arsenal As the Ferguson/Wenger rivalry reached its peak, Arsenal strode into enemy territory to secure a League and FA Cup Double. Sylvain Wiltord marked his 100th Arsenal appearance with a first-time finish for the title.  Wide open: Sylvain Wiltord\'s goal for Arsenal at Old Trafford in 2002 went down in Gunners folklore  2012 Man City v QPR Sergio Aguero\'s 94th-minute winner — after Edin Dzeko’s injury-time goal — saw them come back to beat QPR 3-2, and secure a first title in 44 years, made all the sweeter for being nicked from their fiercest and nearest rivals.  Best ever? Sergio Aguero wheels away after clinching City the title in the dying seconds of the 2012 season    More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds   Share or comment on this article 17shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Isaac+Williams\" rel=\"nofollow\">Isaac Williams</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 17:16 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 17:16 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 17</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">9</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As Manchester City travel to league leaders Liverpool in the biggest game of the season, Sportsmail looks back at some of the epic title-deciding clashes from down the years.</font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">1924 Huddersfield v N Forest</font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 1923-24 season was won by the closest margin in the history of the Football League. With goal average taking precedence over goal difference, Huddersfield Town secured a 1-1 draw against Forest to pip Cardiff City to the post by 0.024 goals. </font></p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">1962 Ipswich v Aston Villa</font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In 1957, Ipswich Town were in the Third Division South of the Football League. Just five years later, a miraculous period under Alf Ramsey left them one result away from the League title. A 2-0 victory completed arguably the greatest rise in the history of the game.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Jubilation: Ipswich fans and players celebrate Ray Crawford\'s opening goal to set them on the way to the title\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"476\" id=\"i-a5bc0e4c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602760-007F948500000258-302_634x476.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Jubilation: Ipswich fans and players celebrate Ray Crawford\'s opening goal to set them on the way to the title</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">1968 Man City v Newcastle</font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Forty-four years before City’s 2012 heroics, exactly the same happened. Manchester United went to Sunderland, knowing a win would grant them the championship. Their 2-1 defeat, though, ensured City’s 4-3 win at Newcastle was enough to turn Manchester sky-blue for a season at least. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Raise a toast: City players celebrate the 1968 title win - top row (L-R) Glyn Pardoe, George Heslop, Alan Oakes, Colin Bell, Francis Lee - bottom row (L-R) Tony Book, Mike Doyle, Ken Mulhearn\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"405\" id=\"i-a7840e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602760-003E14CB00000258-888_634x405.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Raise a toast: City players celebrate the 1968 title win - top row (L-R) Glyn Pardoe, George Heslop, Alan Oakes, Colin Bell, Francis Lee - bottom row (L-R) Tony Book, Mike Doyle, Ken Mulhearn</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">1972 Leeds v Wolves</font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With the top four separated by a single point, Leeds travelled to Molineux on the final day needing just a draw to be crowned champions. However, in a game now infamous for an attempted case of match-fixing, Wolves beat them 2-1, gifting the title to Brian Clough’s Derby County. <br/></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602389/Aguero-fit-Liverpool-clash-City-striker-recovers-hamstring-injury.html\"> Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\"> Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Letting it slip: Leeds keeper David Harvey (right) and Paul Reaney after Wolves go 1-0 up\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"393\" id=\"i-a9560e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602760-1D09AE9700000578-240_634x393.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Letting it slip: Leeds keeper David Harvey (right) and Paul Reaney after Wolves go 1-0 up</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">1989 Liverpool v Arsenal</font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">On the last day, Arsenal needed a two-goal win, while Liverpool just had to prevent such a result. The Gunners led 1-0 until the final minute, when Michael Thomas broke free and, with virtually the last kick, dinked the ball over Bruce Grobbelaar to secure a first title in 18 years.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Iconic: Michael Thomas hits home past Bruce Grobbelaar to hand Arsenal the title at Anfield in 1989\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"324\" id=\"i-a8e30e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602760-12CC4690000005DC-772_634x324.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Iconic: Michael Thomas hits home past Bruce Grobbelaar to hand Arsenal the title at Anfield in 1989</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">2002 Man Utd v Arsenal</font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As the Ferguson/Wenger rivalry reached its peak, Arsenal strode into enemy territory to secure a League and FA Cup Double. Sylvain Wiltord marked his 100th Arsenal appearance with a first-time finish for the title. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wide open: Sylvain Wiltord\'s goal for Arsenal at Old Trafford in 2002 went down in Gunners folklore\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"403\" id=\"i-a1920e21\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602760-0050403500000258-406_634x403.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wide open: Sylvain Wiltord\'s goal for Arsenal at Old Trafford in 2002 went down in Gunners folklore</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">2012 Man City v QPR</font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sergio Aguero\'s 94th-minute winner — after Edin Dzeko’s injury-time goal — saw them come back to beat QPR 3-2, and secure a first title in 44 years, made all the sweeter for being nicked from their fiercest and nearest rivals.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Best ever? Sergio Aguero wheels away after clinching City the title in the dying seconds of the 2012 season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"407\" id=\"i-a57a0e50\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602760-131243F2000005DC-102_634x407.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Best ever? Sergio Aguero wheels away after clinching City the title in the dying seconds of the 2012 season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602389/Aguero-fit-Liverpool-clash-City-striker-recovers-hamstring-injury.html\"> Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\"> Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602760/From-Agueros-gasp-heroics-Michael-Thomas-clinching-league-Arsenal-heres-Sportsmails-best-title-deciders.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"From Aguero\'s last-gasp heroics to Michael Thomas clinching the league for Arsenal, here\'s Sportsmail\'s best-ever title deciders\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602760/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">17</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602760-1D09EE1D00000578-467_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:10','2014-04-12 00:16:45'),(58,'4317f941510ab3dfe84bdc385c304fb905a9951d4832bb9f718f5a4597dd5702','dailymail',NULL,'CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts - Luis Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html',' By Charles Sale Follow @@charliesale Published: 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 16:57 EST, 11 April 2014 21 shares 18 View comments  Liverpool, chasing their first top-flight  league title for 24 years, are also ramping up their commercial operation in anticipation. They have become the first club in the Premier League to sell, on a regular basis, signed shirts worn by the players this season in their official online store — advertised as a chance for fans to ‘own a piece of LFC History’... at a price. Shirts, autographed after the game, cost £1,000 and players with kit on sale include Lucas, Jordan Henderson, Simon Mignolet, Raheem Sterling, Joe Allen, Aly Cissokho and Jon Flanagan.  Sold out! Luis Suarez\'s signed shirt comes at the price of £3,000 - the most expensive in the squad  Jerseys worn by Luis Suarez, priced at £3,000, captain Steven Gerrard, £2,000, and Daniel  Sturridge, £1,000, are already sold out. A club spokesman said Liverpool do not sell shirts for commercial gain when there’s a charity connection on the strip like the 25th anniversary of Hillsborough being worn for tomorrow’s crucial game against Manchester City.  Premier League basement clubs are still upset over Sunderland escaping with a fine rather than a points deduction for fielding the ineligible Ji Dong-won in four games.  Controversy: Sunderland were fined after Ji Dong-won features in four games as an ineligible player  Their anger  now extends to them wanting to know the role, if any, of the Premier League director of governance Jane Purdon. Solicitor Purdon is a lifelong Sunderland fan and was their club secretary for four years until she joined the PL in 2005. The PL, annoyed about any questioning of Purdon’s undoubted integrity, say the issue was dealt with by general secretary Nic Coward and the PL board.  Hull City owner Assem Allam will take his top-table place in the VIP Wembley Suite tomorrow before the FA Cup semi-final against Sheffield United, despite the FA blocking his name change. The Hull hierarchy are planning to forget the FA council rejecting the switch to the Tigers at their meeting last Wednesday, at least for the duration of their Wembley trip.  More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend  Awkward: Assem Allam with sit with FA bigwigs at Wembley, after they rejected his bid to change Hull\'s name  More from Charles Sale...   CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000 11/04/14   Dithering Dyke is ready to reveal all before England head to Brazil 10/04/14   Jacko a thriller for football museum after Jol\'s £20,000 statue offer falls through 07/04/14   Do the BBC really need 272 staff in Brazil? Corporation to send more than DOUBLE ITV\'s World Cup personnel 02/04/14   Another blow for Cleverley as United midfielder\'s agency go into administration 27/03/14   After Manchester derby, United and City go to war again... over academies and FFP 27/03/14   CHARLES SALE: Belo base gives Roy a reminder of worst moment in England\'s World Cup history 20/03/14   CHARLES SALE: Plot thickens over FIFA member Warner\'s 2022 World Cup vote 18/03/14   Government sell racing short as Betfred buy Tote for £32m less than expected 13/03/14   VIEW FULL ARCHIVE Allam, who had threatened to walk out of the club if he couldn’t have his way, will be seated alongside FA chairman Greg Dyke and Darren Eales, the chairman of the FA Cup committee. It is not known which way Spurs’ director of administration Eales voted or whether he abstained. But many of the professional game representatives on the FA were sympathetic to the wishes of Allam, who has invested as much as £74m in his football team. Chelsea’s board refused to sit with the FA in 2012 in protest at the late Cup semi-final kick-off three days before their Champions League semi-final. ......................................................................... Radio 5 Live rugby correspondent Ian Robertson was questioned about an armed robbery in London. The number plate from Robertson’s 500cc midnight blue Piaggio motor bike was caught on CCTV cameras at the scene of a crime.   However, Robertson had a cast-iron alibi as he was commentating on the Newcastle v Worcester Premiership game, having parked his heavily padlocked bike at King’s Cross railway station. Thieves left the bike itself but stole the plates. Robertson said: ‘The police quickly ruled me out of their list of suspects.’  League check on Price The Football League might have failed to keep Italian Massimo Cellino out of Leeds following his successful appeal after failing their owners and directors test.  Fit and proper? The Football League failed to keep Massimo Cellino (R) taking over Leeds  But the FL are continuing their vigilance against the last high-profile fit-and-proper failure, Jim Price, agent of axed  Nottingham Forest manager Billy Davies. The FL have written to Forest wanting confirmation Price is no longer involved at the City Ground.  Manager Roy Hodgson has described the interest in the England team’s wives and girlfriends as a ‘media obsession’ ever since the circus that surrounded their 2006 antics in Baden-Baden.  Circus: England football WAGs became notorious after their antics in Baden-Baden at the 2006 World Cup   However, Hodgson, in a well received address to the FA council this week about his preparations for Brazil, devoted a chunk of his talk about what he’s doing with the WAGs.  The brain drain from Times Sport into the headhunters business continues with former Olympic correspondent Ashling O’Connor  joining former rugby correspondent Mark Souster at Inzito, set up by another former Times correspondent, Carol Leonard.   More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend  Share or comment on this article 21shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-345/Charles-Sale.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Charles Sale</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@charliesale\">Follow @@charliesale</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:57 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"CHARLES SALE: Liverpool lead the way in selling signed shirts... Suarez\'s is yours for just £3,000\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 21</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602803/CHARLES-SALE-Liverpool-lead-way-selling-signed-shirts-Luis-Suarezs-just-3-000.html#comments\"> <span>