/a> <span class=\"date\">13/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"columnist-345/Charles-Sale.html\">VIEW FULL ARCHIVE</a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Allam, who had threatened to walk out of the club if he couldn’t have his way, will be seated alongside FA chairman Greg Dyke and Darren Eales, the chairman of the FA Cup committee.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It is not known which way Spurs’ director of administration Eales voted or whether he abstained. But many of the professional game representatives on the FA were sympathetic to the wishes of Allam, who has invested as much as £74m in his football team. Chelsea’s board refused to sit with the FA in 2012 in protest at the late Cup semi-final kick-off three days before their Champions League semi-final.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>.........................................................................</b><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Radio 5 Live rugby correspondent Ian Robertson was questioned about an armed robbery in London. The number plate from Robertson’s 500cc midnight blue Piaggio motor bike was caught on CCTV cameras at the scene of a crime. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">However, Robertson had a cast-iron alibi as he was commentating on the Newcastle v Worcester Premiership game, having parked his heavily padlocked bike at King’s Cross railway station. Thieves left the bike itself but stole the plates. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Robertson said: ‘The police quickly ruled me out of their list of suspects.’</font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<h2><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">League check on Price </font></h2>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Football League might have failed to keep Italian Massimo Cellino out of Leeds following his successful appeal after failing their owners and directors test. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fit and proper? The Football League failed to keep Massimo Cellino (R) taking over Leeds\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5d6b0d40\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D00D6ED00000578-708_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fit and proper? The Football League failed to keep Massimo Cellino (R) taking over Leeds</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But the FL are continuing their vigilance against the last high-profile fit-and-proper failure, Jim Price, agent of axed  Nottingham Forest manager Billy Davies. The FL have written to Forest wanting confirmation Price is no longer involved at the City Ground.</font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Manager Roy Hodgson has described the interest in the England team’s wives and girlfriends as a ‘media obsession’ ever since the circus that surrounded their 2006 antics in Baden-Baden.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Circus: England football WAGs became notorious after their antics in Baden-Baden at the 2006 World Cup\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5c780d37\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-04D7C5C00000044D-354_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Circus: England football WAGs became notorious after their antics in Baden-Baden at the 2006 World Cup</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">However, Hodgson, in a well received address to the FA council this week about his preparations for Brazil, devoted a chunk of his talk about what he’s doing with the WAGs.</font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The brain drain from Times Sport into the headhunters business continues with former Olympic correspondent Ashling O’Connor  joining former rugby correspondent Mark Souster at Inzito, set up by another former Times correspondent, Carol Leonard.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\"> Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602355/All-Premier-League-FA-Cup-team-news-stats-ahead-weekend.html\"> All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span cla