achine-Marathon-experts-explain-Olympic-champion-Farah-perfect-body-London-storm.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"The Mo Machine! Marathon experts explain why Olympic champion Farah has the perfect body to take London by storm\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602880/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">36</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"social-stats\" id=\"sharedLinkTopComment\"> <div> <p>if he doesn\'t fain that is</p> <span>by <a class=\"js-usr\" href=\"/registration/1351335678839122/kyhan/profile.html\">kyhan</a></span> <span class=\"shared-rating-negative\"></span> <span class=\"shared-rating-negative-text\">-2</span> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602880-1D0A2E9000000578-872_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:12','2014-04-11 23:55:03'),(60,'a8ff16de81bd9c8eb03a944b9fc3a4735b674d319b0062bb532703362b04b0bb','dailymail',NULL,'Quigg set for title defence against Munyai after visa issues rule Cermeno out','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602831/Quigg-set-title-defence-against-Munyai-visa-issues-rule-Cermeno-bout.html',' By Martin Domin Follow @@martin_domin Published: 16:00 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 16:46 EST, 11 April 2014 0 View comments  Scott Quigg will defend his world super-bantamweight title against Tshifhiwa Munyai next Saturday after Nehomar Cermeno was forced out of the bout with visa issues. Munyai is ranked in the top 10 with the WBA and steps in at short notice for the fight at the Manchester Arena. The 28-year-old from South Africa has enjoyed success in England before, having won the Commonwealth bantamweight crown in London against Martin Power in 2006, defending it four months later against Lee Haskins and then defeating Power again in a rematch for the title the following year.  The Bury-born WBA super-bantamweight champion has won 27 of his 29 fights  The former IBO world and WBA Inter-Continental champion boasts 24 wins from his 27 contests with half of them inside the distance, and promoter Eddie Hearn expects him to pose a real threat to the unbeaten Bury star. ‘It’s a great fight for Scott and in my opinion a much tougher test than Cermeno,’ he said. ‘Munyai is no stranger to these shores and is impressive form coming into the fight. Scott is in fantastic shape and ready to make a big statement as we eye unification fights this summer.’ Defence: Scott Quigg won the super-bantamweight world title at the beginning of October Points: Despite a slow start against Yoandris Salinas, Quigg did enough to win the title Quigg’s title defence tops an exciting night of boxing in Manchester, with chief-support in the shape of a lightweight derby between Anthony Crolla and John Murray. Josh Warrington defends his Commonwealth featherweight title against former world title challenger Rendall Munroe, Tyrone Nurse meets Tyler Goodjohn for the vacant English light welterweight title and red hot super-middleweight prospect Callum Smith returns to the ring following injury.  Promoter: Eddie Hearn thinks Quigg faces a tough test in Manchester next weekend     More... DeGale in line for potential Groves rematch after signing with Hearn\'s Matchroom PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley Pacquiao dismisses Bradley\'s claim he has lost killer instinct ahead of rematch British referee Keane forced out of huge Pacquiao-Bradley rematch with sickness   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Martin+Domin\" rel=\"nofollow\">Martin Domin</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@martin_domin\">Follow @@martin_domin</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:00 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:46 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602831/Quigg-set-title-defence-against-Munyai-visa-issues-rule-Cermeno-bout.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602831/Quigg-set-title-defence-against-Munyai-visa-issues-rule-Cermeno-bout.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Quigg set for title defence against Munyai after visa issues rule Cermeno out\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602831/Quigg-set-title-defence-against-Munyai-visa-issues-rule-Cermeno-bout.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Scott Quigg will defend his world super-bantamweight title against Tshifhiwa Munyai next Saturday after Nehomar Cermeno was forced out of the bout with visa issues.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Munyai is ranked in the top 10 with the WBA and steps in at short notice for the fight at the Manchester Arena.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 28-year-old from South Africa has enjoyed success in England before, having won the Commonwealth bantamweight crown in London against Martin Power in 2006, defending it four months later against Lee Haskins and then defeating Power again in a rematch for the title the following year.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"The Bury-born WBA super-bantamweight champion has won 27 of his 29 fights\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"489\" id=\"i-aa860e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602831-199AEF8700000578-117_634x489.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">The Bury-born WBA super-bantamweight champion has won 27 of his 29 fights</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The former IBO world and WBA Inter-Continental champion boasts 24 wins from his 27 contests with half of them inside the distance, and promoter Eddie Hearn expects him to pose a real threat to the unbeaten Bury star.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘It’s a great fight for Scott and in my opinion a much tougher test than Cermeno,’ he said. ‘Munyai is no stranger to these shores and is impressive form coming into the fight. Scott is in fantastic shape and ready to make a big statement as we eye unification fights this summer.’ <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Defence: Scott Quigg won the super-bantamweight world title in October\" class=\"blkBorder\" height=\"402\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2013/10/11/article-0-188C61C800000578-959_634x402.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Defence: Scott Quigg won the super-bantamweight world title at the beginning of October</p> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Points: Despite a slow start against Yoandris Salinas, Quigg did enough to win the title\" class=\"blkBorder\" height=\"412\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2013/10/11/article-0-188D55B100000578-937_634x412.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Points: Despite a slow start against Yoandris Salinas, Quigg did enough to win the title</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Quigg’s title defence tops an exciting night of boxing in Manchester, with chief-support in the shape of a lightweight derby between Anthony Crolla and John Murray.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Josh Warrington defends his Commonwealth featherweight title against former world title challenger Rendall Munroe, Tyrone Nurse meets Tyler Goodjohn for the vacant English light welterweight title and red hot super-middleweight prospect Callum Smith returns to the ring following injury.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Promoter: Eddie Hearn thinks Quigg faces a tough test in Manchester next weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-abcd0e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602831-1CFF5D7900000578-134_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Promoter: Eddie Hearn thinks Quigg faces a tough test in Manchester next weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html\"> DeGale in line for potential Groves rematch after signing with Hearn\'s Matchroom</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601650/PacMan-people-Mannys-superstar-statesman-entertains-serves-fellow-Filipinos-Jeff-Powell.html\"> PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2599973/Pacquiao-dismisses-Bradleys-claim-lost-killer-instinct-ahead-rematch.html\"> Pacquiao dismisses Bradley\'s claim he has lost killer instinct ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600177/British-boxing-referee-John-Keane-forced-Manny-Pacquiaos-rematch-Tim-Bradley-illness.html\"> British referee Keane forced out of huge Pacquiao-Bradley rematch with sickness</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602831/Quigg-set-title-defence-against-Munyai-visa-issues-rule-Cermeno-bout.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602831/Quigg-set-title-defence-against-Munyai-visa-issues-rule-Cermeno-bout.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Quigg set for title defence against Munyai after visa issues rule Cermeno out\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602831/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602831-199AEF8700000578-532_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:13','2014-04-11 23:46:24'),(61,'4d97c7870a46ae27184c7047e13004e878a6d1fabb11e8b6d1d85c87bce8ac83','dailymail',NULL,'Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html',' By Simon Jones Published: 16:35 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 16:35 EST, 11 April 2014 13 shares 42 View comments Manuel Pellegrini has warned his Manchester City players of the need to control their emotions at a supercharged Anfield on Sunday. City take on Premier League leaders Liverpool intent on tilting the title race back in their favour but will face an impassioned cauldron of a stadium as both clubs commemorate the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough disaster. Respectful of the occasion but mindful of the game’s importance, Pellegrini said: ‘It will be a very emotional day but the team that has the cold mind will win the game. VIDEO Scroll down to watch Manuel Pellegrini and Brendan Rodgers talk ahead of the clash  All set: Sergio Aguero trains on Friday at Carrington ahead of Sunday\'s title showdown with Liverpool Chat: Manchester City manager Manuel Pellegrini has a few words with striker Aguero during training Pellegrini: Liverpool game is no more important than any other  LIVERPOOL WIN THE TREBLE!Rodgers, Gerrard and Suarez scoop awards ‘It is easy in these big games to have the motivation but it is very important to manage the anxiety. \'That is very important for all the players. With an excess of anxiety you can make more mistakes. It will be decided by one or two goals. So it’s very important to have control of your minds in these moments.’ Liverpool are chasing their first league title in 24 years while City are still seen as favourites yet Pellegrini does not buy into the mantra that counterpart Brendan Rodgers is under less pressure to deliver. ‘I can’t imagine that the Liverpool manager does not have pressure to win the title,’ he said. ‘I think every manager or every team that has big players and that spends money to win the title has the same pressure every year. \'I can’t believe such an important team as Liverpool, the manager has no pressure to win the title. I think everyone who manages Liverpool has that pressure. Liverpool are favourites because they are top of the table.’ Tickets are changing hands for more than £3,000 apiece on the black market such is the demand, yet Pellegrini, who welcomes back fit-again striker Sergio Aguero, insists the game will not decide the Premier League winners. ‘This is a very important game but it is not a title decider. Of course, the team that wins this game has more chance because they have three points more but if you think that with this you finish the Premier League, it is a mistake. Going to ground: Aguero makes a slide tackle as he gets ready to return in Sunday\'s match Warming up: City players jog around the pitch as they get the training session underway on Friday Rodgers: We will unleash the Liverpool supporters on Man City   ‘Really, we have two games in hand but we do not have six points. We have to play those two games. \'That is why I say it is very important to win at Liverpool but if we think by winning at Liverpool we win the Premier League, I don’t think so because after Sunday we have to play on Wednesday against Sunderland who are in a relegation position and those teams are as difficult as Liverpool. ‘Just one point will decide the title. The pressure is the same for both teams, and for Chelsea also. Three teams will fight for it until the last day.’ Pellegrini insists he has no regrets about not becoming Liverpool manager despite holding talks prior to their appointment of Roy Hodgson in 2010. ‘After I finished with Real Madrid I had a conversation with Liverpool,’ he confirmed. ‘It’s in the past not the future. \'I have no regrets about not taking Liverpool job because it gave me the chance to work at Manchester City. No regrets about that.’ .     Focused: Joleon Lescott (left) and Vincent Kompany have their eye on the ball as a cross is swung in   This way to the title: Aguero and Edin Dzeko (right) have a discussion during training on Friday  Manchester City have sacked head of academy coaching Scott Sellars as the Barclays Premier League club continue revamping their youth-set up. The former Blackburn and Newcastle player joined the club in 2009 under then football administrator Brian Marwood. But in a difference of footballing opinion with the current regime, led by sporting director Txiki Begiristain, Sellars has had his employment terminated.  Breather: Aguero takes the opportunity for a rest as he prepares for the Liverpool match   Come here: Manchester City goalkeeper sticks his arms out as his boss Pellegrini walks towards him     Share or comment on this article 13shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Simon+Jones\" rel=\"nofollow\">Simon Jones</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:35 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:35 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 13</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">42</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Manuel Pellegrini has warned his Manchester City players of the need to control their emotions at a supercharged Anfield on Sunday.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">City take on Premier League leaders Liverpool intent on tilting the title race back in their favour but will face an impassioned cauldron of a stadium as both clubs commemorate the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough disaster.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Respectful of the occasion but mindful of the game’s importance, Pellegrini said: ‘It will be a very emotional day but the team that has the cold mind will win the game.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO</span></font> Scroll down to watch Manuel Pellegrini and Brendan Rodgers talk ahead of the clash</b><br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All set: Sergio Aguero trains on Friday at Carrington ahead of Sunday\'s title showdown with Liverpool\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"484\" id=\"i-8e640e03\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D0714EB00000578-0_634x484.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All set: Sergio Aguero trains on Friday at Carrington ahead of Sunday\'s title showdown with Liverpool</p><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Chat: Manchester City manager Manuel Pellegrini has a few words with striker Aguero during training\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"507\" id=\"i-a7db0e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D07148A00000578-557_634x507.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Chat: Manchester City manager Manuel Pellegrini has a few words with striker Aguero during training</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3457997620001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Pellegrini: Liverpool game is no more important than any other</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D09C95F00000578-574_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>LIVERPOOL WIN THE TREBLE!</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601760/Brendan-Rodgers-Luis-Suarez-amd-Steven-Gerrard-Premier-League-manager-player-month-awards.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">Rodgers, Gerrard and Suarez scoop awards</a></font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It is easy in these big games to have the motivation but it is very important to manage the anxiety. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'That is very important for all the players. With an excess of anxiety you can make more mistakes. It will be decided by one or two goals. So it’s very important to have control of your minds in these moments.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Liverpool are chasing their first league title in 24 years while City are still seen as favourites yet Pellegrini does not buy into the mantra that counterpart Brendan Rodgers is under less pressure to deliver.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I can’t imagine that the Liverpool manager does not have pressure to win the title,’ he said.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I think every manager or every team that has big players and that spends money to win the title has the same pressure every year. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I can’t believe such an important team as Liverpool, the manager has no pressure to win the title. I think everyone who manages Liverpool has that pressure. Liverpool are favourites because they are top of the table.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Tickets are changing hands for more than £3,000 apiece on the black market such is the demand, yet Pellegrini, who welcomes back fit-again striker Sergio Aguero, insists the game will not decide the Premier League winners.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘This is a very important game but it is not a title decider. Of course, the team that wins this game has more chance because they have three points more but if you think that with this you finish the Premier League, it is a mistake. <br/></font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font> <img alt=\"Going to ground: Aguero makes a slide tackle as he gets ready to return in Sunday\'s match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-a8190e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D07158A00000578-478_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"><p class=\"imageCaption\">Going to ground: Aguero makes a slide tackle as he gets ready to return in Sunday\'s match</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Warming up: City players jog around the pitch as they get the training session underway on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"455\" id=\"i-a7c30e63\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D0713D300000578-658_634x455.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Warming up: City players jog around the pitch as they get the training session underway on Friday</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3457929869001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Rodgers: We will unleash the Liverpool supporters on Man City</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D09B6B100000578-585_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div><p> </p> </div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\">  </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Really, we have two games in hand but we do not have six points. We have to play those two games. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'That is why I say it is very important to win at Liverpool but if we think by winning at Liverpool we win the Premier League, I don’t think so because after Sunday we have to play on Wednesday against Sunderland who are in a relegation position and those teams are as difficult as Liverpool.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Just one point will decide the title. The pressure is the same for both teams, and for Chelsea also. Three teams will fight for it until the last day.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Pellegrini insists he has no regrets about not becoming Liverpool manager despite holding talks prior to their appointment of Roy Hodgson in 2010.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘After I finished with Real Madrid I had a conversation with Liverpool,’ he confirmed. ‘It’s in the past not the future. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I have no regrets about not taking Liverpool job because it gave me the chance to work at Manchester City. No regrets about that.’ .<br/></font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Focused: Joleon Lescott (left) and Vincent Kompany have their eye on the ball as a cross is swung in\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"522\" id=\"i-a5b70e4c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D07141000000578-787_634x522.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Focused: Joleon Lescott (left) and Vincent Kompany have their eye on the ball as a cross is swung in</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"This way to the title: Aguero and Edin Dzeko (right) have a discussion during training on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"574\" id=\"i-9bc90e3e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D0715AB00000578-86_634x574.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">This way to the title: Aguero and Edin Dzeko (right) have a discussion during training on Friday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Manchester City have sacked head of academy coaching Scott Sellars as the Barclays Premier League club continue revamping their youth-set up.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The former Blackburn and Newcastle player joined the club in 2009 under then football administrator Brian Marwood.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But in a difference of footballing opinion with the current regime, led by sporting director Txiki Begiristain, Sellars has had his employment terminated.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Breather: Aguero takes the opportunity for a rest as he prepares for the Liverpool match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"482\" id=\"i-a8850e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D078E0700000578-356_634x482.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Breather: Aguero takes the opportunity for a rest as he prepares for the Liverpool match</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Come here: Manchester City goalkeeper sticks his arms out as his boss Pellegrini walks towards him\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"516\" id=\"i-a8cc0e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D078E6600000578-137_634x516.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Come here: Manchester City goalkeeper sticks his arms out as his boss Pellegrini walks towards him</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602818/Pellegrini-warns-players-control-minds-against-Liverpool-City-boss-believes-team-cool-heads-win.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Pellegrini warns his players to \'control\' their minds against Liverpool as City boss believes team with cool heads will win\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602818/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">13</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602389-1D07148A00000578-731_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:13','2014-04-11 23:35:00'),(62,'7f574a0ccb89b90ad892992033616e5cb60af01293825e4c8ce11b8819e2ca2e','dailymail',NULL,'Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers: \'We\'ll unleash power of Anfield against City\'','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602777/Liverpool-boss-Brendan-Rodgers-Well-unleash-power-Anfield-against-City.html',' By Dominic King Follow @@DominicKing_DM Published: 16:34 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 16:34 EST, 11 April 2014 70 shares 235 View comments  Brendan Rodgers has warned Manchester City to expect the \'power of Anfield\' as he backed Liverpool’s players to handle their emotionally-charged title showdown. The impending 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough disaster provides a tragic backdrop to Sunday’s clash, meaning the atmosphere inside Anfield will take on a different intensity; both clubs will pay tribute to the 96 Liverpool fans who died on April 15, 1989. It will not, however, be a purely sombre occasion. Liverpool’s chance of winning the title will be significantly enhanced if they record a first win over City in the Premier League since April 11, 2011 and Rodgers wants to use every possible avenue to help his side. VIDEO Scroll down to watch Rodgers discuss Liverpool vs Manchester City  Looking ahead: Brendan Rodgers admits Sunday\'s match against Manchester City is \'significant\'   Catch us: Liverpool are top of the Premier League table with 15 points still up for grabs this season Team man: Liverpool striker Luis Suarez is on track to win the Golden Boot Hard yards: Suarez takes on Aly Cissokho as Liverpool prepare for their encounter with Manchester City  More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds That, in his view, means \'unleashing our supporters again\' and creating an environment that will prove inspirational for his own players and intimidating for City, the side Rodgers feels are under the most pressure as they are expected to finish first. Rodgers, who was named Manager of the Month for March, said: ‘I think our players will feed off it. We will pay our commemoration before the game; the (Memorial) Service on Tuesday is going to be where the raw emotion comes out. ‘Our job is to provide a lift to the supporters, families and victims in terms of our performance. We embrace that. It (expectation) is not something that’s going to sabotage our work. It will help us grow and help our responsibility. We know what that is. Hopefully we can use that to good effect.’ At the end of Liverpool’s last home game, the 4-0 dismantling of Tottenham, the Kop let out a spontaneous roar that struck a chord with Rodgers and his squad and he is adamant the hoem crowd are capable of influencing results. ‘I’ve sensed it myself, the roar is different,’ said Rodgers. ‘Anfield is a different place from the drive up now. Growing up as a kid and I remember watching on the TV and seeing the bloom of Anfield, there’s a touch of that now. The supporters are really the ones that will push us over the line.  Form: Rodgers (left), Steven Gerrard and Suarez win the Manager and Players of the Month Awards for March     No holding back: Suarez may be closing in on goal records but Lucas Leiva gives him no quarter at Melwood Listen in: Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers gives instruction to a concentrated Suarez on Friday‘I felt it when I was with Chelsea (during the Champions League semi-final in 2005). I remember going back and the players and manager (Jose Mourinho) even said the supporters won the game. \'That’s the beauty of Anfield. It’s an iconic ground and for us it’s so important in our destiny.’ There is no sense from the way Liverpool have been training that they are feeling the strain of trying to win a first title since 1990 and midfielder Philippe Coutinho feels the pressure is squarely on the shoulders of City. Home: Liverpool players will be hope they have a result to celebrate at Anfield on Sunday   Plotting: Brendan Rodgers and Steven Gerrard worked for 30 minutes on free-kicks at Melwood   Burst a valve: The manager and his captain are particular about how the ball is placed before it\'s struck ‘We are not thinking about pressure or external factors in these last five matches,’ he said. ‘We know that City are considered one of the favourites from the start but Brendan tells us to forget the excitement, the expectations and not to worry about anything that\'s happening around us.’ Luis Suarez added: ‘Our target was to finish in the top four and we\'ve won our last few games. \'We also know Chelsea and City dropped some points, so we\'re at the top of the league now and that\'s amazing for us. Now we can\'t stop because we have a really good chance.’ Rodgers: We will unleash the Liverpool supporters on Man City Ready to roll: Suarez and Rodgers watch on as Gerrard hits a stationary ball      More... Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds  Share or comment on this article 70shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Dominic+King\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dominic King</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@DominicKing_DM\">Follow @@DominicKing_DM</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:34 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:34 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602777/Liverpool-boss-Brendan-Rodgers-Well-unleash-power-Anfield-against-City.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602777/Liverpool-boss-Brendan-Rodgers-Well-unleash-power-Anfield-against-City.html\" data-cookiepoli