style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">At the end of Liverpool’s last home game, the 4-0 dismantling of Tottenham, the Kop let out a spontaneous roar that struck a chord with Rodgers and his squad and he is adamant the hoem crowd are capable of influencing results.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I’ve sensed it myself, the roar is different,’ said Rodgers. ‘Anfield is a different place from the drive up now. Growing up as a kid and I remember watching on the TV and seeing the bloom of Anfield, there’s a touch of that now. The supporters are really the ones that will push us over the line.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Form: Rodgers (left), Steven Gerrard and Suarez win the Manager and Players of the Month Awards for March\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"352\" id=\"i-9d160e45\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602777-1D0669FC00000578-39_634x352.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Form: Rodgers (left), Steven Gerrard and Suarez win the Manager and Players of the Month Awards for March</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"No holding back: Suarez may be closing in on goal records but Lucas Leiva gives him no quarter at Melwood\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"389\" id=\"i-5f360d4f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CFF56D800000578-610_634x389.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">No holding back: Suarez may be closing in on goal records but Lucas Leiva gives him no quarter at Melwood</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Listen in: Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers gives instruction to a concentrated Suarez on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"507\" id=\"i-5d5e0d39\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CFF382800000578-119_634x507.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Listen in: Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers gives instruction to a concentrated Suarez on Friday</p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I felt it when I was with Chelsea (during the Champions League semi-final in 2005). I remember going back and the players and manager (Jose Mourinho) even said the supporters won the game. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'That’s the beauty of Anfield. It’s an iconic ground and for us it’s so important in our destiny.’ <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There is no sense from the way Liverpool have been training that they are feeling the strain of trying to win a first title since 1990 and midfielder Philippe Coutinho feels the pressure is squarely on the shoulders of City.</font></p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Home: Liverpool players will be hope they have a result to celebrate at Anfield on Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"370\" id=\"i-a8430e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602777-078358DB00000514-719_634x370.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Home: Liverpool players will be hope they have a result to celebrate at Anfield on Sunday</p> </div><p> </p></div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"One-on-one: Rodgers and Gerrard spent 30 minutes practising free-kicks\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a4dd0e42\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602409-1D07105500000578-981_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Pinpoint: Gerrard takes a closer look at the ball as he works on his set pieces\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a4c40e3f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602409-1D07103900000578-823_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Plotting: Brendan Rodgers and Steven Gerrard worked for 30 minutes on free-kicks at Melwood <br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Placement: Liverpool are preparing to take on City in a match many say could decide the champions\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a4d50e40\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602409-1D07090300000578-861_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Hands on: Rodgers directs Gerrard at Liverpool\'s Melwood training ground\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a8a90e66\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602409-1D0708FE00000578-761_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Burst a valve: The manager and his captain are particular about how the ball is placed before it\'s struck <br/></p></div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘We are not thinking about pressure or external factors in these last five matches,’ he said. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘We know that City are considered one of the favourites from the start but Brendan tells us to forget the excitement, the expectations and not to worry about anything that\'s happening around us.’ <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Luis Suarez added: ‘Our target was to finish in the top four and we\'ve won our last few games. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We also know Chelsea and City dropped some points, so we\'re at the top of the league now and that\'s amazing for us. Now we can\'t stop because we have a really good chance.’</font></p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3457929869001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Rodgers: We will unleash the Liverpool supporters on Man City</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D09B6B100000578-585_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <img alt=\"Ready to roll: Suarez and Rodgers watch on as Gerrard hits a stationary ball\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"399\" id=\"i-a6bc0e5f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602409-1D0731F100000578-177_634x399.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Ready to roll: Suarez and Rodgers watch on as Gerrard hits a stationary ball</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602666/Stop-Toure-stop-City-Neville-delivers-verdict-title-decider.html\"> Stop Toure and you stop City! Neville delivers his verdict on title decider</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\"> Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602389/Aguero-fit-Liverpool-clash-City-striker-recovers-hamstring-injury.html\"> Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\"> Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602777/Liverpool-boss-Brendan-Rodgers-Well-unleash-power-Anfield-against-City.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602777/Liverpool-boss-Brendan-Rodgers-Well-unleash-power-Anfield-against-City.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Roar us to title! We\'ll unleash power of Anfield against City, says Liverpool boss Rodgers\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602777/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">70</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D070C3C00000578-34_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:14','2014-04-11 23:34:48'),(63,'6d1fa727e1f3a80583cdac6742e64e0e5a9d0effaf9c1b2dc9520bc431858993','dailymail',NULL,'Nigel Clough: Stay-away Hull fans may be saving themselves for FA Cup final, but we\'re not','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602759/Nigel-Clough-Stay-away-Hull-fans-saving-FA-Cup-final-not.html',' By John Edwards Follow @@JEAlty Published: 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 17 View comments Nigel Clough accused Hull supporters of taking victory for granted in tomorrow’s FA Cup semi-final after it emerged there were still 6,000 unsold tickets at the KC Stadium. ‘We’ve heard a few stories that a lot of Hull fans are saving their money for the final, but they may just be taking a risk,’ said the manager of League One Sheffield United. ‘I’ve made sure our players are well aware of it. Any little thing we can use as extra motivation, we will. We need everything going for us if we are to get through.’ VIDEO: Scroll down to watch Clough and Bruce ahead of the Wembley showdown  At your peril! Clough has warned Hull fans not to take their FA Cup semi-final against for granted   Clough: Hull fans may be saving themselves for the final, we...  Defender Neill Collins will also have the motivation of United’s last Wembley visit two years ago, when an epic play-off final against Huddersfield was decided after a marathon penalty shootout that ended with both goalkeepers trying their luck from 12 yards.   More... Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final Clough favours the Scottish factor as Nigel follows his dad\'s recipe for success HULL vs SHEFFIELD UNITED: Latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final SOMETHING FOR THE WEEKEND: Liverpool and Man City\'s title showdown and FA Cup semis take centre stage as Hillsborough is remembered 25 years on Steve Simonsen had the misfortune to blaze his over the bar, and Collins can vividly remember his own reaction as the hapless keeper slumped to the ground while Huddersfield’s players celebrated. Steve Bruce: Wembley trip will be fantastic for the Hull...  Stay away: There were still 6,000 tickets for Hull fans unsold ahead of the Wembley semi-final  ‘I was thumping the turf in frustration,’ said the former Scotland Under 21 centre back. ‘It was a horrible, horrible feeling, probably the worst of my career, and I couldn’t help myself. I just fell to my knees and started punching the ground. ‘We didn’t have a lot of goals in that team, but we were solid and we gave ourselves a great opportunity by keeping it scoreless and taking it to penalties. In fact, we had it in the palm of our hands after Huddersfield missed their third penalty. I had just scored, we were one in front with a pen in hand and I really thought it was going to be our day. ‘But it all went wrong and it turned into an experience none of us will want to go through again. We all had families there and they were emotional, too, so we basically got on the bus and headed back to Sheffield, drained and desperately disappointed.  Down: Blades keeper Steve Simonsen (R) is consoled after missing a penalty in the 2012 League One play-off final  ‘After that, we went our separate ways and headed home. Then we started thinking about another season in League One. ‘Honestly, I couldn’t get it out of my head. We went away on holiday, but I just kept reliving it over and over again. It wasn’t the best summer I’ve ever had. ‘The play-offs basically boil your entire season down to one game. We will have butterflies in our stomachs this time, but the  pressure will be very different. Let’s be honest, nobody thought we would be in the semi-final of the FA Cup, but here we are.  Showdown: Clough will come up against old adversary Steve Bruce (R) when the two sides meet at Wembley  ‘It could help us, having been to Wembley before and gone through that experience. You know the smells, the size of the dressing room, what the tunnel is like. All little things, but it means you can concentrate on your job. ‘I am sure there are even international players who go there and are a bit in awe first time. ‘Wembley is the sort of place where you can’t have an “OK” memory. It is either elation or despair. There’s nothing in between because of what’s at stake. Please let it be elation this time.’   More... Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final Clough favours the Scottish factor as Nigel follows his dad\'s recipe for success HULL vs SHEFFIELD UNITED: Latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final SOMETHING FOR THE WEEKEND: Liverpool and Man City\'s title showdown and FA Cup semis take centre stage as Hillsborough is remembered 25 years on   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Edwards\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Edwards</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@JEAlty\">Follow @@JEAlty</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602759/Nigel-Clough-Stay-away-Hull-fans-saving-FA-Cup-final-not.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602759/Nigel-Clough-Stay-away-Hull-fans-saving-FA-Cup-final-not.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Clough: Stay-away Hull fans may be saving themselves for FA Cup final... we\'re not!\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602759/Nigel-Clough-Stay-away-Hull-fans-saving-FA-Cup-final-not.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">17</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Nigel Clough accused Hull supporters of taking victory for granted in tomorrow’s FA Cup semi-final after it emerged there were still 6,000 unsold tickets at the KC Stadium.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘We’ve heard a few stories that a lot of Hull fans are saving their money for the final, but they may just be taking a risk,’ said the manager of League One Sheffield United. </font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’ve made sure our players are well aware of it. Any little thing we can use as extra motivation, we will. We need everything going for us if we are to get through.’</font></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(51, 153, 102);\">VIDEO:</span></font> Scroll down to watch Clough and Bruce ahead of the Wembley showdown<br/></font></b></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"At your peril! Clough has warned Hull fans not to take their FA Cup semi-final against for granted\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-54770d2a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CFF4CD500000578-98_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">At your peril! Clough has warned Hull fans not to take their FA Cup semi-final against for granted</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3457306414001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Clough: Hull fans may be saving themselves for the final, we...</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D08E85C00000578-655_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Defender Neill Collins will also have the motivation of United’s last Wembley visit two years ago, when an epic play-off final against Huddersfield was decided after a marathon penalty shootout that ended with both goalkeepers trying their luck from 12 yards.</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602456/Hull-write-new-chapter-clubs-history-reaching-FA-Cup-final-says-Chester.html\"> Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602019/Nigel-Clough-does-battle-Steve-Bruce-Wembley.html\"> Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601901/Clough-favours-Scottish-factor-Nigel-follows-dads-recipe-success.html\"> Clough favours the Scottish factor as Nigel follows his dad\'s recipe for success</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601451/HULL-vs-SHEFFIELD-UNITED-Latest-team-news-stats-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> HULL vs SHEFFIELD UNITED: Latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html\"> SOMETHING FOR THE WEEKEND: Liverpool and Man City\'s title showdown and FA Cup semis take centre stage as Hillsborough is remembered 25 years on</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Steve Simonsen had the misfortune to blaze his over the bar, and Collins can vividly remember his own reaction as the hapless keeper slumped to the ground while Huddersfield’s players celebrated.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3318947212001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Steve Bruce: Wembley trip will be fantastic for the Hull...</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/03/09/video-undefined-1C273EE600000578-998_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Stay away: There were still 6,000 tickets for Hull fans unsold ahead of the Wembley semi-final\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5da40d46\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1B8C431E000005DC-262_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Stay away: There were still 6,000 tickets for Hull fans unsold ahead of the Wembley semi-final</p> </div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I was thumping the turf in frustration,’ said the former Scotland Under 21 centre back. ‘It was a horrible, horrible feeling, probably the worst of my career, and I couldn’t help myself. I just fell to my knees and started punching the ground.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘We didn’t have a lot of goals in that team, but we were solid and we gave ourselves a great opportunity by keeping it scoreless and taking it to penalties. In fact, we had it in the palm of our hands after Huddersfield missed their third penalty. I had just scored, we were one in front with a pen in hand and I really thought it was going to be our day.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘But it all went wrong and it turned into an experience none of us will want to go through again. We all had families there and they were emotional, too, so we basically got on the bus and headed back to Sheffield, drained and desperately disappointed.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Down: Blades keeper Steve Simonsen (R) is consoled after missing a penalty in the 2012 League One play-off final\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5df60d4b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-134F5FF1000005DC-118_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Down: Blades keeper Steve Simonsen (R) is consoled after missing a penalty in the 2012 League One play-off final</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘After that, we went our separate ways and headed home. Then we started thinking about another season in League One.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Honestly, I couldn’t get it out of my head. We went away on holiday, but I just kept reliving it over and over again. It wasn’t the best summer I’ve ever had.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘The play-offs basically boil your entire season down to one game. We will have butterflies in our stomachs this time, but the  pressure will be very different. Let’s be honest, nobody thought we would be in the semi-final of the FA Cup, but here we are.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Showdown: Clough will come up against old adversary Steve Bruce (R) when the two sides meet at Wembley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5fcd0d53\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CF5FE9700000578-619_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Showdown: Clough will come up against old adversary Steve Bruce (R) when the two sides meet at Wembley</p> </div></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It could help us, having been to Wembley before and gone through that experience. You know the smells, the size of the dressing room, what the tunnel is like. All little things, but it means you can concentrate on your job.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I am sure there are even international players who go there and are a bit in awe first time.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Wembley is the sort of place where you can’t have an “OK” memory. It is either elation or despair. There’s nothing in between because of what’s at stake. Please let it be elation this time.’</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602456/Hull-write-new-chapter-clubs-history-reaching-FA-Cup-final-says-Chester.html\"> Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602019/Nigel-Clough-does-battle-Steve-Bruce-Wembley.html\"> Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601901/Clough-favours-Scottish-factor-Nigel-follows-dads-recipe-success.html\"> Clough favours the Scottish factor as Nigel follows his dad\'s recipe for success</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601451/HULL-vs-SHEFFIELD-UNITED-Latest-team-news-stats-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> HULL vs SHEFFIELD UNITED: Latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html\"> SOMETHING FOR THE WEEKEND: Liverpool and Man City\'s title showdown and FA Cup semis take centre stage as Hillsborough is remembered 25 years on</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602759/Nigel-Clough-Stay-away-Hull-fans-saving-FA-Cup-final-not.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602759/Nigel-Clough-Stay-away-Hull-fans-saving-FA-Cup-final-not.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Clough: Stay-away Hull fans may be saving themselves for FA Cup final... we\'re not!\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602759/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602759-1CF5FE9700000578-813_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:14','2014-04-11 23:30:21'),(64,'d8532bb312dfaa014b541c5d6066153b4aca537d31360528175128661ca59b35','dailymail',NULL,'Curtis Davies captures the imagination in Hull\'s FA Cup semi-final - as far as Sierra Leone','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602756/Curtis-Davies-captures-imagination-Hulls-FA-Cup-semi-final-far-Sierra-Leone.html',' By John Edwards Follow @@JEAlty Published: 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 5 shares 1 View comments The FA Cup final is always assured of a worldwide audience, but at least one of this weekend’s semi-finals has captured the imagination abroad. After Curtis Davies leads Hull City out at Wembley tomorrow afternoon, his every header and tackle will be monitored in a quiet corner of West Africa. Davies is of Sierra Leonean descent, and if Sheffield United are kept at bay by his resolute defending, they will be cheering thousands of miles away. VIDEO: Scroll down to watch the Hull and Blades managers ahead of the game  Out of Africa: Hull captain will be cheered on from Sierra Leone during Sunday\'s FA Cup semi-final at Wembley  Steve Bruce: Wembley trip will be fantastic for the Hull... London-born of a Sierra Leonean father, the  29-year-old hopes England manager Roy Hodgson may also tune in but is beginning to lose hope of making Brazil this summer. With a Republic of Ireland call-up looking unlikely, due to tenuous links and a broadside from Roy Keane, his relatives on Africa’s Atlantic coast could even soon be celebrating him playing for Sierra Leone.   More... Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester I was a nightmare, I let people down and I was threatened with arrest for Cup protest, admits Hull boss Bruce Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final Martinez tips former club Wigan to shock Arsenal in FA Cup semi-final at Wembley The former Luton, West Bromwich Albion, Aston Villa and Birmingham centre back said: ‘I’ve got family over there — my granddad, great uncle and people like that — and they will all be glued to the telly. The game is being shown over there; they’ll all be keeping their fingers crossed for me. Brilliant, really, isn’t it?  Blades run: Only League One underdogs Sheffield United stand between Hull and the final  Clough: Hull fans may be saving themselves for the final, we... ‘Only the Cup could do that. There could be quite a crowd watching over there; Liam Rosenior’s family are from Sierra Leone. ‘You wonder whether Wembley could be a stage for pressing England claims, but, then again, Roy Hodgson said if you haven’t been in one of the squads by now, there is only a slim chance you’ll make the World Cup. It looks like the only way I’ll get close is if there are massive injury problems. ‘As for Ireland, I had a  pint of Guinness once! What can I say? My nan was born in Ireland, but she’s not Irish. She’s English. Her father was in the army and he was in Ireland when she was born. So I qualify, but there’s no heritage.  Ship has sailed: Davies accepts he is unlikely to feature in England boss Roy Hodgson\'s World Cup squad  ‘Anyway, Roy Keane made it clear he didn’t think I was good enough, when he was asked recently, and it has been well documented that Martin O’Neill and I had problems at Villa. So that would be a great managerial duo for me! ‘I’d never shut the door on anything, but I’m striving my heart out to try to get in the England squad and, after that, Sierra Leone is my next country. It’d be difficult with commitments like the Africa Cup of Nations. I can just imagine how that would go down with the gaffer (Steve Bruce) if I disappeared for a few weeks in January, but that would be the next option for me.’  Not fans! Neither Martin O\'Neill (L) or Roy Keane are likely to give the Hull defender a call-up for Ireland  Davies should have been involved in the first ever game at the rebuilt Wembley but was injured. ‘It was an England Under 21 game. I was told I would partner Anton Ferdinand in the centre of defence. I was really excited, but a week before the game, I got a painful knock on the foot. I had a scan and it was a broken metatarsal. I was devastated, so upset I couldn’t bring myself to go and watch the game. I just hope there are different emotions this time…’   More... Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester I was a nightmare, I let people down and I was threatened with arrest for Cup protest, admits Hull boss Bruce Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final Martinez tips former club Wigan to shock Arsenal in FA Cup semi-final at Wembley  Share or comment on this article 5shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Edwards\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Edwards</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@JEAlty\">Follow @@JEAlty</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:30 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602756/Curtis-Davies-captures-imagination-Hulls-FA-Cup-semi-final-far-Sierra-Leone.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602756/Curtis-Davies-captures-imagination-Hulls-FA-Cup-semi-final-far-Sierra-Leone.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Davies captures the imagination in Hull\'s FA Cup semi-final... all the way to Sierra Leone\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 5</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602756/Curtis-Davies-captures-imagination-Hulls-FA-Cup-semi-final-far-Sierra-Leone.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">1</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The FA Cup final is always assured of a worldwide audience, but at least one of this weekend’s semi-finals has captured the imagination abroad.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">After Curtis Davies leads Hull City out at Wembley tomorrow afternoon, his every header and tackle will be monitored in a quiet corner of West Africa.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Davies is of Sierra Leonean descent, and if Sheffield United are kept at bay by his resolute defending, they will be cheering thousands of miles away.</font></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(51, 153, 102);\">VIDEO:</span> </font>Scroll down to watch the Hull and Blades managers ahead of the game</font></b></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Out of Africa: Hull captain will be cheered on from Sierra Leone during Sunday\'s FA Cup semi-final at Wembley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5fae0d51\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CDB6DB300000578-753_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Out of Africa: Hull captain will be cheered on from Sierra Leone during Sunday\'s FA Cup semi-final at Wembley</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3318947212001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Steve Bruce: Wembley trip will be fantastic for the Hull...</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/03/09/video-undefined-1C273EE600000578-998_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">London-born of a Sierra Leonean father, the  29-year-old hopes England manager Roy Hodgson may also tune in but is beginning to lose hope of making Brazil this summer.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With a Republic of Ireland call-up looking unlikely, due to tenuous links and a broadside from Roy Keane, his relatives on Africa’s Atlantic coast could even soon be celebrating him playing for Sierra Leone. </font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602588/Hull-City-boss-Steve-Bruce-admits-wall-team-defeat-old-club-Sheffield-United-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602456/Hull-write-new-chapter-clubs-history-reaching-FA-Cup-final-says-Chester.html\"> Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html\"> I was a nightmare, I let people down and I was threatened with arrest for Cup protest, admits Hull boss Bruce</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602019/Nigel-Clough-does-battle-Steve-Bruce-Wembley.html\"> Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602006/Roberto-Martinez-tips-former-club-Wigan-shock-Arsenal-FA-Cup-semi-final-Wembley.html\"> Martinez tips former club Wigan to shock Arsenal in FA Cup semi-final at Wembley</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The former Luton, West Bromwich Albion, Aston Villa and Birmingham centre back said: ‘I’ve got family over there — my granddad, great uncle and people like that — and they will all be glued to the telly. The game is being shown over there; they’ll all be keeping their fingers crossed for me. Brilliant, really, isn’t it?</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Blades run: Only League One underdogs Sheffield United stand between Hull and the final\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-59690d1a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1C26094600000578-576_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Blades run: Only League One underdogs Sheffield United stand between Hull and the final</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3457306414001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Clough: Hull fans may be saving themselves for the final, we...</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D08E85C00000578-655_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Only the Cup could do that. There could be quite a crowd watching over there; Liam Rosenior’s family are from Sierra Leone.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘You wonder whether Wembley could be a stage for pressing England claims, but, then again, Roy Hodgson said if you haven’t been in one of the squads by now, there is only a slim chance you’ll make the World Cup. It looks like the only way I’ll get close is if there are massive injury problems.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘As for Ireland, I had a  pint of Guinness once! What can I say? My nan was born in Ireland, but she’s not Irish. She’s English. Her father was in the army and he was in Ireland when she was born. So I qualify, but there’s no heritage.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Ship has sailed: Davies accepts he is unlikely to feature in England boss Roy Hodgson\'s World Cup squad\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-5b000d27\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-197E06C100000578-815_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Ship has sailed: Davies accepts he is unlikely to feature in England boss Roy Hodgson\'s World Cup squad</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Anyway, Roy Keane made it clear he didn’t think I was good enough, when he was asked recently, and it has been well documented that Martin O’Neill and I had problems at Villa. So that would be a great managerial duo for me!</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’d never shut the door on anything, but I’m striving my heart out to try to get in the England squad and, after that, Sierra Leone is my next country. It’d be difficult with commitments like the Africa Cup of Nations. I can just imagine how that would go down with the gaffer (Steve Bruce) if I disappeared for a few weeks in January, but that would be the next option for me.’ </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Not fans! Neither Martin O\'Neill (L) or Roy Keane are likely to give the Hull defender a call-up for Ireland\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-59150d17\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-193633C300000578-393_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Not fans! Neither Martin O\'Neill (L) or Roy Keane are likely to give the Hull defender a call-up for Ireland</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Davies should have been involved in the first ever game at the rebuilt Wembley but was injured.</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It was an England Under 21 game. I was told I would partner Anton Ferdinand in the centre of defence. I was really excited, but a week before the game, I got a painful knock on the foot. I had a scan and it was a broken metatarsal. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I was devastated, so upset I couldn’t bring myself to go and watch the game. I just hope there are different emotions this time…’</font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602588/Hull-City-boss-Steve-Bruce-admits-wall-team-defeat-old-club-Sheffield-United-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> Hull boss Bruce admits he will go \'off the wall\' if his team defeat old club Sheffield United in FA Cup semi-final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602456/Hull-write-new-chapter-clubs-history-reaching-FA-Cup-final-says-Chester.html\"> Hull can write new chapter in club\'s history by reaching FA Cup final, says Chester</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html\"> I was a nightmare, I let people down and I was threatened with arrest for Cup protest, admits Hull boss Bruce</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602019/Nigel-Clough-does-battle-Steve-Bruce-Wembley.html\"> Clough goes to battle with Bruce again at Wembley for a place in the FA Cup final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602006/Roberto-Martinez-tips-former-club-Wigan-shock-Arsenal-FA-Cup-semi-final-Wembley.html\"> Martinez tips former club Wigan to shock Arsenal in FA Cup semi-final at Wembley</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602756/Curtis-Davies-captures-imagination-Hulls-FA-Cup-semi-final-far-Sierra-Leone.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602756/Curtis-Davies-captures-imagination-Hulls-FA-Cup-semi-final-far-Sierra-Leone.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Davies captures the imagination in Hull\'s FA Cup semi-final... all the way to Sierra Leone\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602756/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">5</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CDB6DB300000578-854_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:15','2014-04-11 23:30:17'),(65,'04766e91ed96749b2023a30b155f61efa86d3669d1fab99419ccee2416566984','dailymail',NULL,'He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike McCoy','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html',' By Derek Lawrenson Published: 16:08 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 16:08 EST, 11 April 2014 0 View comments Every decent club golfer in Britain has surely tuned into the Masters and wondered how they would score if playing off the same tees - and to the same flags - as the 97 competitors in the 78th Masters. It\'s an impossible question to answer, of course. But perhaps the fate of America\'s Mid-Amateur champion Mike McCoy offers a clue. Now McCoy is no decent club golfer. He\'s a brilliant club golfer.  Hard yards: Michael McCoy followed up an 78 with an 83 in the second round  In fact, the 51-year-old insurance executive from Des Moines is the greatest amateur golfer the state of Iowa has ever produced. McCoy is an 11-time Iowa amateur player of the year and five-time Iowa amateur champion. To get here, McCoy prevailed from an original entry of 4,238 players for the Mid-Amateur Championship to claim the Bob Jones Memorial Trophy, named after the greatest amateur of all and the founder of the Masters. Make no mistake, our friend from Iowa is very much the real McCoy. So how did he shape up against such daunting yardage and flag positions so precarious they look like they might fall off the ledges they\'re perched upon?  Dream ticket: Amateur McCoy had resolved to enjoy every moment of Masters experience  Poor McCoy had resolved to enjoy every minute of his once-in-a-lifetime experience. But how can a man so accustomed to shooting in the sixties enjoy what happened on Friday? After opening with a 78, he had the satisfaction at least of seeing a couple of former champions - albeit now in their 60s - in Ben Crenshaw and Craig Stadler below him on the leaderboard, not to mention a current star in Luke Donald. What happened on day two?  Experience: British Amateur champion Garrick Porteous carded an eight over par 80  McCoy shot 44 for the front nine, notionally what a 16-handicapper is supposed to shoot. He finished with an 83. \'My body just wouldn\'t respond to what my brain was telling it to do,\' he sighed. He was not alone. Garrick Porteous, the 24-year-old British Amateur champion at the other end of the age scale, will turn pro on Saturday having signed off with an 80. What would a decent club golfer shoot? Watching McCoy, a good four-handicapper would do well to break 100.    More... Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut Gallacher enjoys dream start and McIlroy shines but Brits find it rough going at Augusta MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happened at Augusta National   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Derek+Lawrenson\" rel=\"nofollow\">Derek Lawrenson</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 16:08 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:08 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Every decent club golfer in Britain has surely tuned into the Masters and wondered how they would score if playing off the same tees - and to the same flags - as the 97 competitors in the 78th Masters.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> It\'s an impossible question to answer, of course. But perhaps the fate of America\'s Mid-Amateur champion Mike McCoy offers a clue.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Now McCoy is no decent club golfer. He\'s a brilliant club golfer. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Hard yards: Michael McCoy followed up an 78 with an 83 in the second round\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"601\" id=\"i-5bbd0d26\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D08FA4200000578-143_634x601.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Hard yards: Michael McCoy followed up an 78 with an 83 in the second round</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> In fact, the 51-year-old insurance executive from Des Moines is the greatest amateur golfer the state of Iowa has ever produced. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> McCoy is an 11-time Iowa amateur player of the year and five-time Iowa amateur champion.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> To get here, McCoy prevailed from an original entry of 4,238 players for the Mid-Amateur Championship to claim the Bob Jones Memorial Trophy, named after the greatest amateur of all and the founder of the Masters.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Make no mistake, our friend from Iowa is very much the real McCoy.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> So how did he shape up against such daunting yardage and flag positions so precarious they look like they might fall off the ledges they\'re perched upon? <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dream ticket: Amateur McCoy had resolved to enjoy every moment of Masters experience\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"443\" id=\"i-5c0b0d30\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D07C26D00000578-391_634x443.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dream ticket: Amateur McCoy had resolved to enjoy every moment of Masters experience</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Poor McCoy had resolved to enjoy every minute of his once-in-a-lifetime experience. But how can a man so accustomed to shooting in the sixties enjoy what happened on Friday? </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> After opening with a 78, he had the satisfaction at least of seeing a couple of former champions - albeit now in their 60s - in Ben Crenshaw and Craig Stadler below him on the leaderboard, not to mention a current star in Luke Donald.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> What happened on day two? <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Experience: British Amateur champion Garrick Porteous carded an eight over par 80\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-5d9d0d43\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D07B3BC00000578-688_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Experience: British Amateur champion Garrick Porteous carded an eight over par 80</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> McCoy shot 44 for the front nine, notionally what a 16-handicapper is supposed to shoot. He finished with an 83. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'My body just wouldn\'t respond to what my brain was telling it to do,\' he sighed.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> He was not alone. Garrick Porteous, the 24-year-old British Amateur champion at the other end of the age scale, will turn pro on Saturday having signed off with an 80.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> What would a decent club golfer shoot? </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Watching McCoy, a good four-handicapper would do well to break 100.</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\"> Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602529/MASTERS-2014-Luke-Donald-admits-pretty-dumb-bunker-gaffe-puts-risk-cut.html\"> Donald admits he was \'pretty dumb\' after bunker gaffe puts him at risk of Masters cut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602081/Gallacher-enjoys-dream-start-McIlroy-shines-Brits-rough-going-Augusta.html\"> Gallacher enjoys dream start and McIlroy shines but Brits find it rough going at Augusta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602063/MASTERS-LIVE-All-second-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\"> MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happened at Augusta National</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602866/Hes-real-McCoy-angry-Augusta-eats-17-par-Mike-McCoy.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"He\'s the real McCoy but angry Augusta eats up 17-over-par Mike\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602866/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D08FA4200000578-983_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:16','2014-04-11 23:08:35'),(66,'06a53c20e949eb8c4fef25678883b70de984444c3e7cd17b0e6e4adbd4a41835','dailymail',NULL,'Cardiff City believe they have \'concrete evidence\' that at least three members of staff were involved in Crystal Palace spying scandal','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html',' Crystal Palace director of football Iain Moody allegedly tried to find out team information ahead of match with his old club CardiffA member of staff at Cardiff is set to leaveTwo more employees are under investigationCardiff have reported their claims to the Premier LeagueMoody and Palace deny they tried to obtain team information By Riath Al-Samarrai Follow @@riathalsam Published: 10:37 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 15:33 EST, 11 April 2014 10 shares 23 View comments One Cardiff City employee is set to leave the club and another two are being investigated over the spying scandal  surrounding their game against Crystal Palace. The Welsh club’s former head of recruitment, Iain Moody, now director of football at Palace, is accused of obtaining team information ahead of Palace’s 3-0 win in Wales last Saturday. VIDEO: Scroll down to watch Ole Gunnar Solskjaer admit Cardiff need a miracle  Living on a prayer: Vincent Tan has accused former director Iain Moody of trying to find out Cardiff team news   Six-pointer: Crystal Palace beat Cardiff 3-0 to move seven points clear of the relegation zone  More... Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man? Caulker urges internal inquiry into leak after concerns over early release of team news Palace accused of SPYING on Cardiff before 3-0 win as Premier League investigate Tan claims Cardiff have reported their suspicions to the Premier League and Sportsmail can reveal that the allegations also include an assertion that Moody contacted at least three individuals at the club between Wednesday and Friday of last week, asking for information about the team. A prominent Cardiff source has told us that manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer was made aware of what was going on when a message sent from Moody’s phone, listing the starting 11 against Palace, was received by a Cardiff employee. The employee tipped off Solskjaer, who reported the matter to the club hierarchy, but the Norwegian did not change his team. Moody and Palace have strenuously denied they attempted to obtain team information from anyone at Cardiff. Cardiff have not complained formally to the  Premier League, but chairman Mehmet Dalman has handed over a dossier and requested the incident be reviewed. The dossier has been built around what the source calls ‘real evidence’, including the phone records of staff who would have had access to the information that was leaked, and text messages from Moody, who was sacked by owner Vincent Tan last year. Solskjaer: We now need a miracle but I\'m full of fight   Solskjaer referred all matters relating to the incident to Dalman, but he did not wish to comment.Solskjaer raised eyebrows after the Palace defeat by indicating there was a lack of ‘loyalty’ among some elements of the dressing room, though he said it related to players following his instructions. On Saturday he said: ‘I have no reason to doubt any of my players’ professionality (sic), honesty, integrity or loyalty. I have said what I have said and the rest will come from Mehmet. I have just answered the question and how many times have I got to tell you?’ Responding to the allegations on Thursday, Moody said: ‘I don’t think I have done anything wrong. That is incredibly, extraordinarily untrue. That is untrue, completely untrue.’ While he strongly denied  contacting anyone at Cardiff to try to elicit information, he did admit to using wider contacts in the game, as is standard practice.  Clear conscience: Iain Moody (centre) and Crystal Palace have denied all allegations made by Tan ‘That is the whole point of what we do as scouts,’ he added Cardiff captain Steve Caulker said yesterday: ‘To be honest with you, there have been problems like that all season, where certain things have been leaked. ‘It is frustrating. We need to focus on getting things right on the pitch, not what’s going on off the pitch. I will be telling the boys that we need to get performances in and get results, not concern  ourselves with off-the-field issues. ‘It has obviously come from somewhere. That’s down to the gaffer (Solskjaer) and the staff above him to sort out, and we can just focus on playing football. ‘A lot of stuff has been going on off the pitch all season, and that has been highlighted in the press. It is important we all ignore all that stuff. Our performances have not been up to scratch of late.’   More... Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man? Caulker urges internal inquiry into leak after concerns over early release of team news Palace accused of SPYING on Cardiff before 3-0 win as Premier League investigate Tan claims  Share or comment on this article 10shares','\n<ul class=\"article-summary sport\"><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Crystal Palace director of football Iain Moody allegedly tried to find out team information ahead of match with his old club Cardiff</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">A member of staff at Cardiff is set to leave</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Two more employees are under investigation</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Cardiff have reported their claims to the Premier League</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Moody and Palace deny they tried to obtain team information<br/></font></b></li></ul>\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Riath+Al-Samarrai\" rel=\"nofollow\">Riath Al-Samarrai</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@riathalsam\">Follow @@riathalsam</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 10:37 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:33 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Cardiff believe they have \'concrete evidence\' that at least three members of staff were involved in Palace spying scandal\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 10</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">23</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">One Cardiff City employee is set to leave the club and another two are being investigated over the spying scandal  surrounding their game against Crystal Palace.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Welsh club’s former head of recruitment, Iain Moody, now director of football at Palace, is accused of obtaining team information ahead of Palace’s 3-0 win in Wales last Saturday.</font></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO:</span> </font>Scroll down to watch Ole Gunnar Solskjaer admit Cardiff need a miracle</font></b></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Living on a prayer: Vincent Tan has accused former director Iain Moody of trying to find out Cardiff team news\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-ab280e83\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601934-1CDB2F2500000578-898_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Living on a prayer: Vincent Tan has accused former director Iain Moody of trying to find out Cardiff team news</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Six-pointer: Crystal Palace beat Cardiff 3-0 to move seven points clear of the relegation zone\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a95b0e6f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601934-1CDC175300000578-829_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Six-pointer: Crystal Palace beat Cardiff 3-0 to move seven points clear of the relegation zone</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602487/Cardiff-sack-member-staff-Palace-spying-scandal-check-phone-records.html\"> Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602355/All-Premier-League-FA-Cup-team-news-stats-ahead-weekend.html\"> All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602212/Nine-ten-players-Premier-League-distance-covered-table-English-West-Hams-Noble-leading-running-NINE-London-Marathons-season.html\"> Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602399/Steven-Caulker-urges-internal-inquiry-leak-concerns-early-release-team-news.html\"> Caulker urges internal inquiry into leak after concerns over early release of team news</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601934/Vincent-Tan-demands-probe-accusing-Crystal-Palace-director-Iain-Moody-trying-Cardiff-team-unethical-means.html\"> Palace accused of SPYING on Cardiff before 3-0 win as Premier League investigate Tan claims</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cardiff have reported their suspicions to the Premier League and Sportsmail can reveal that the allegations also include an assertion that Moody contacted at least three individuals at the club between Wednesday and Friday of last week, asking for information about the team.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A prominent Cardiff source has told us that manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer was made aware of what was going on when a message sent from Moody’s phone, listing the starting 11 against Palace, was received by a Cardiff employee. The employee tipped off Solskjaer, who reported the matter to the club hierarchy, but the Norwegian did not change his team.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Moody and Palace have strenuously denied they attempted to obtain team information from anyone at Cardiff.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cardiff have not complained formally to the  Premier League, but chairman Mehmet Dalman has handed over a dossier and requested the incident be reviewed.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The dossier has been built around what the source calls ‘real evidence’, including the phone records of staff who would have had access to the information that was leaked, and text messages from Moody, who was sacked by owner Vincent Tan last year.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3435025353001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Solskjaer: We now need a miracle but I\'m full of fight</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/05/video-undefined-1CDCA55A00000578-237_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Solskjaer referred all matters relating to the incident to Dalman, but he did not wish to comment.<br/>Solskjaer raised eyebrows after the Palace defeat by indicating there was a lack of ‘loyalty’ among some elements of the dressing room, though he said it related to players following his instructions.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">On Saturday he said: ‘I have no reason to doubt any of my players’ professionality (sic), honesty, integrity or loyalty. I have said what I have said and the rest will come from Mehmet. I have just answered the question and how many times have I got to tell you?’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Responding to the allegations on Thursday, Moody said: ‘I don’t think I have done anything wrong. That is incredibly, extraordinarily untrue. That is untrue, completely untrue.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">While he strongly denied  contacting anyone at Cardiff to try to elicit information, he did admit to using wider contacts in the game, as is standard practice.  <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Clear conscience: Iain Moody (centre) and Crystal Palace have denied all allegations made by Tan\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a9670e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601934-1D01D1ED00000578-461_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Clear conscience: Iain Moody (centre) and Crystal Palace have denied all allegations made by Tan</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘That is the whole point of what we do as scouts,’ he added</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cardiff captain Steve Caulker said yesterday: ‘To be honest with you, there have been problems like that all season, where certain things have been leaked.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It is frustrating. We need to focus on getting things right on the pitch, not what’s going on off the pitch. I will be telling the boys that we need to get performances in and get results, not concern  ourselves with off-the-field issues.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It has obviously come from somewhere. That’s down to the gaffer (Solskjaer) and the staff above him to sort out, and we can just focus on playing football.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘A lot of stuff has been going on off the pitch all season, and that has been highlighted in the press. It is important we all ignore all that stuff. Our performances have not been up to scratch of late.’</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602487/Cardiff-sack-member-staff-Palace-spying-scandal-check-phone-records.html\"> Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602355/All-Premier-League-FA-Cup-team-news-stats-ahead-weekend.html\"> All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602212/Nine-ten-players-Premier-League-distance-covered-table-English-West-Hams-Noble-leading-running-NINE-London-Marathons-season.html\"> Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602399/Steven-Caulker-urges-internal-inquiry-leak-concerns-early-release-team-news.html\"> Caulker urges internal inquiry into leak after concerns over early release of team news</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601934/Vincent-Tan-demands-probe-accusing-Crystal-Palace-director-Iain-Moody-trying-Cardiff-team-unethical-means.html\"> Palace accused of SPYING on Cardiff before 3-0 win as Premier League investigate Tan claims</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Cardiff believe they have \'concrete evidence\' that at least three members of staff were involved in Palace spying scandal\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602600/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">10</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601934-1CDB2F2500000578-374_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:16','2014-04-11 22:33:56'),(67,'97d17a682eae47711cd77f7ea8eb509492bf5153ca37a13de37055b8918542ab','dailymail',NULL,'The view from Manchester: Shinji Kagawa must stay! Manchester United can thrive with Japan star','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html',' By Red Mancunian Published: 10:58 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 15:28 EST, 11 April 2014 180 shares 83 View comments Sportsmail asked Manchester United blog RedMancunian about the potential clearout of 10 players at Old Trafford by boss David Moyes following Manchester United\'s disappointing season. Shinji Kagawa is one player understood to be fighting for his future at the club.  There have been very few genuine high points in what has been a disastrous first season at Manchester United for David Moyes, but one common denominator in almost every performance of note has been the involvement of Shinji Kagawa. The Japanese playmaker has been widely tipped to be part of the expected summer exodus from Old Trafford, and to a certain extent that\'s understandable - there\'s no denying that the 25 year-old has yet to reproduce the sort of form that lit up the Bundesliga during his time with Borussia Dortmund, and under Moyes he has started just 19 of the club\'s 50 matches thus far this term. VIDEO Scroll down to watch funny videos of Shinji Kagawa  On the ball: Shinji Kagawa (right) in action against Bayern Munich in the Champions League on Wednesday   Rare sighting: The Japan playmaker has found his chances limited at Old Trafford this season  Mitigating factors abound, however. Sir Alex Ferguson\'s opportunistic signing of Robin van Persie and Moyes\' general unwillingness to look beyond partnering the Dutchman with Wayne Rooney have seen Kagawa largely utilised out of position on the left wing. Perhaps even more crucially, the laboured, plodding football United have played this season has been the very antithesis of the fluid, creative, high-tempo setup on which he thrived at Dortmund. Starved of possession and ignored when taking up clever positions, it can be little surprise that Kagawa has often struggled to influence. Until recent weeks, that is. With Van Persie sidelined and Rooney pushed forward into the centre-forward role most consider to be his best, United have produced some of their best football all season. Kagawa has still nominally been deployed in a left-sided role, but now alongside a genuine, inventive No 10 in Juan Mata, on whom he can rely to get him the ball in the parts of the pitch where he can really do damage. Shinji Kagawa takes on samurais and wins  Promising: Kagawa and Juan Mata (right, also with Javier Hernandez) linked well in the win at Newcastle   Why does it always rain on me? 10 United players are facing the exit in a summer clearout, including Kagawa    More... Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man? All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend Glum United arrive home after Munich failure as Fletcher warns they still have plenty to play for with futures on the line Kagawa\'s late introduction at The Hawthorns saw a marked change in United\'s style of play, and he was integral to the Reds\' comeback against Aston Villa, with two sublime first-half passes leading directly to goals. The interplay between Kagawa, Mata and Adnan Januzaj against Newcastle was an absolute joy, and if allowed to continue, it\'s only a matter of time before the Japanese follows the latter pair onto the scoresheet with regularity - his goal return in the Bundesliga is ample proof of that. Recent big games have seen Moyes revert somewhat to the more one-dimensional norm for this season, and if that is continues to be the case we may never see the best of Kagawa in a United shirt. Kagawa stars with dog and dolphins in new advert   Tough choices: United manager David Moyes (second left) must make some big decisions over his squad  Shift: Wayne Rooney\'s move into the centre-forward position could make room for Kagawa in the side  If, however, the manager has learnt anything from the quality of football produced in the lesser games of late, it is absolutely imperative that the Japanese is not just kept on but made integral to the club\'s plans moving forward.  Read more on RedMancunian and follow them on Twitter @RedMancunian   More... Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man? All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend Glum United arrive home after Munich failure as Fletcher warns they still have plenty to play for with futures on the line   Share or comment on this article 180shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Red+Mancunian\" rel=\"nofollow\">Red Mancunian</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 10:58 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:28 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 180</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">83</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Sportsmail asked Manchester United blog <a href=\"http://redmancunian.com/\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">RedMancunian </a>about the potential clearout of 10 players at Old Trafford by boss David Moyes following Manchester United\'s disappointing season. Shinji Kagawa is one player understood to be fighting for his future at the club.<br/></font></span></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">There have been very few genuine high points in what has been a disastrous first season at Manchester United for David Moyes, but one common denominator in almost every performance of note has been the involvement of Shinji Kagawa.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Japanese playmaker has been widely tipped to be part of the expected summer exodus from Old Trafford, and to a certain extent that\'s understandable - there\'s no denying that the 25 year-old has yet to reproduce the sort of form that lit up the Bundesliga during his time with Borussia Dortmund, and under Moyes he has started just 19 of the club\'s 50 matches thus far this term.</font></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO</span></font> Scroll down to watch funny videos of Shinji Kagawa</font></b><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the ball: Shinji Kagawa (right) in action against Bayern Munich in the Champions League on Wednesday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-aa660e6f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602589-1CF91F0700000578-242_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the ball: Shinji Kagawa (right) in action against Bayern Munich in the Champions League on Wednesday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rare sighting: The Japan playmaker has found his chances limited at Old Trafford this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"457\" id=\"i-aaee0e7e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602589-1CDE136800000578-954_634x457.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rare sighting: The Japan playmaker has found his chances limited at Old Trafford this season</p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Mitigating factors abound, however. Sir Alex Ferguson\'s opportunistic signing of Robin van Persie and Moyes\' general unwillingness to look beyond partnering the Dutchman with Wayne Rooney have seen Kagawa largely utilised out of position on the left wing. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Perhaps even more crucially, the laboured, plodding football United have played this season has been the very antithesis of the fluid, creative, high-tempo setup on which he thrived at Dortmund. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Starved of possession and ignored when taking up clever positions, it can be little surprise that Kagawa has often struggled to influence. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Until recent weeks, that is. With Van Persie sidelined and Rooney pushed forward into the centre-forward role most consider to be his best, United have produced some of their best football all season. Kagawa has still nominally been deployed in a left-sided role, but now alongside a genuine, inventive No 10 in Juan Mata, on whom he can rely to get him the ball in the parts of the pitch where he can really do damage.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3269550176001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Shinji Kagawa takes on samurais and wins</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/02/28/video-undefined-1BE88D4D00000578-632_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Promising: Kagawa and Juan Mata (right, also with Javier Hernandez) linked well in the win at Newcastle\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"437\" id=\"i-afa80ea9\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602589-1CDBA9EF00000578-933_634x437.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Promising: Kagawa and Juan Mata (right, also with Javier Hernandez) linked well in the win at Newcastle</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Why does it always rain on me? 10 United players are facing the exit in a summer clearout, including Kagawa\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-aa940e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602589-1CB6B48700000578-274_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Why does it always rain on me? 10 United players are facing the exit in a summer clearout, including Kagawa</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602434/Welbeck-Cleverley-seen-dancing-street-early-hours-The-day-United-crashed-Champions-League.html\"> Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601877/David-Moyes-faces-uncertain-future-10-Manchester-United-stars-heading-exit.html\"> Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602212/Nine-ten-players-Premier-League-distance-covered-table-English-West-Hams-Noble-leading-running-NINE-London-Marathons-season.html\"> Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602355/All-Premier-League-FA-Cup-team-news-stats-ahead-weekend.html\"> All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601654/Manchester-United-arrive-home-Munich-failure-Fletcher-warns-plenty-play-futures-line.html\"> Glum United arrive home after Munich failure as Fletcher warns they still have plenty to play for with futures on the line</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Kagawa\'s late introduction at The Hawthorns saw a marked change in United\'s style of play, and he was integral to the Reds\' comeback against Aston Villa, with two sublime first-half passes leading directly to goals. <br/></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The interplay between Kagawa, Mata and Adnan Januzaj against Newcastle was an absolute joy, and if allowed to continue, it\'s only a matter of time before the Japanese follows the latter pair onto the scoresheet with regularity - his goal return in the Bundesliga is ample proof of that.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Recent big games have seen Moyes revert somewhat to the more one-dimensional norm for this season, and if that is continues to be the case we may never see the best of Kagawa in a United shirt. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-2317476653001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Kagawa stars with dog and dolphins in new advert</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2013/04/22/video-undefined-196D4F80000005DC-723_290x163.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tough choices: United manager David Moyes (second left) must make some big decisions over his squad\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-ac370e82\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602589-1CF90AE900000578-901_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tough choices: United manager David Moyes (second left) must make some big decisions over his squad</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Shift: Wayne Rooney\'s move into the centre-forward position could make room for Kagawa in the side\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"393\" id=\"i-acf00e8b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602589-1CF9F3D900000578-312_634x393.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Shift: Wayne Rooney\'s move into the centre-forward position could make room for Kagawa in the side</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">If, however, the manager has learnt anything from the quality of football produced in the lesser games of late, it is absolutely imperative that the Japanese is not just kept on but made integral to the club\'s plans moving forward. </font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\"></span><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Read more on <a href=\"http://redmancunian.com/\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">RedMancunian</a> and follow them on Twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/RedMancunian\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">@RedMancunian</a></span></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602434/Welbeck-Cleverley-seen-dancing-street-early-hours-The-day-United-crashed-Champions-League.html\"> Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601877/David-Moyes-faces-uncertain-future-10-Manchester-United-stars-heading-exit.html\"> Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602212/Nine-ten-players-Premier-League-distance-covered-table-English-West-Hams-Noble-leading-running-NINE-London-Marathons-season.html\"> Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602355/All-Premier-League-FA-Cup-team-news-stats-ahead-weekend.html\"> All the Premier League and FA Cup team news and stats ahead of the weekend</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601654/Manchester-United-arrive-home-Munich-failure-Fletcher-warns-plenty-play-futures-line.html\"> Glum United arrive home after Munich failure as Fletcher warns they still have plenty to play for with futures on the line</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602589/The-view-Manchester-Shinji-Kagawa-stay-Manchester-United-thrive-Japan-star.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"The view from Manchester: Kagawa must stay! United can thrive with Japan star and Mata at heart of their attack\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602589/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">180</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602589-1CDE136800000578-803_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:17','2014-04-11 22:28:51'),(68,'66195a38fa76714f4ad785c85c38283f54925c8c4c5289e988abea6efcef1f70','dailymail',NULL,'Brailsford quits as head of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky duties','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602195/Brailsford-quits-head-British-Cycling-focus-Team-Sky-duties.html',' By Matt Lawton Follow @@Matt_Lawton_DM Published: 01:39 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 15:25 EST, 11 April 2014 14 shares 10 View comments For Sir Dave Brailsford it really had become the impossible job. With British Cycling based in Manchester and Team Sky’s main training headquarters now in Nice, it was like asking Jose Mourinho to take on Chelsea without relinquishing control of Real Madrid. So on Friday, after a 10-year reign that had brought eight gold medals at both the London and Beijing Olympics in 2008, Brailsford stood down as performance director of British Cycling to focus on running the Team Sky road team.  Quit: Sir Dave Brailsford has resigned as performance director of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky  Brailsford made it clear before the recent Track World Championships that it was becoming too much — that he was being spread too thin and that both teams could suffer as a consequence. For a man who sets the highest of standards, whose mantra is ‘marginal gains’, and has an acute attention to detail, a  situation that meant he might be giving less than his best was unacceptable.He hopes the British Cycling team he has put in place will continue to achieve success, not least at the Rio Games in 2016. ‘It just feels like it’s a natural transition,’ Brailsford said yesterday. ‘We’ve thought for a long time as to how we can get British Cycling in the best possible shape and give the riders the best possible support going into Rio, because that’s the most important thing. Chat: Brailsford speaks to Chris Froome as the Brit rides to victory at the 2013 Tour de France   ‘It’s been well documented that my time is more stretched across Team Sky and British Cycling. Team Sky have grown with the success of the Tour de France and I felt that the back-up that now exists at British Cycling — with Ian Drake as CEO, with Shane Sutton knowing all the riders — it’s the right team to move that team on.’ For some of the riders, Brailsford’s departure might be as unsettling as it was for Manchester United’s players when Sir Alex Ferguson retired. To add to their woes is the departure of Dr Steve Peters, the acclaimed psychiatrist to whom  Sir Chris Hoy, Sir Bradley Wiggins and Victoria Pendleton have said they owe much of their success. Those who remain can only hope a healthy degree of continuity will ensure there is further success.A major reshuffle sees Sutton promoted to British Cycling’s technical director with responsibility for rider performance. Andy Harrison will continue as programmes director. Both report to Drake but a new role — head of performance support — has also been created. Having left Team Sky as sporting director to join the Premier League youth department as head of elite performance, it is thought Dan Hunt could return to cycling from football. Peters, recruited by England manager Roy Hodgson after his success with Liverpool, will step down but will remain with Brailsford at Team Sky. Before he departs he will assist in setting up a new support system for riders. Mastermind: Brailsford celebrates Victoria Pendleton\'s gold medal in the keirin at London 2012 ‘I want to thank Sir Dave Brailsford for his enormous contribution to British Cycling,’ said Drake. ‘The organisation he leaves behind is transformed from the one we both joined in 1998. ‘I’m confident we have the right management team to take us into Rio and beyond. Cycling in this country has travelled a long way but the best is yet to come.’ Brailsford insisted he will remain close to British Cycling. Success: Brailsford poses with 2012 Tour de France winner Sir Bradley Wiggins (left), and receives his knighthood from Queen Elizabeth II at Buckingham Palace in February 2013    ‘I’ll still be available to Ian, Shane and Andy for support and my role at Team Sky will mean we’ll still work closely and support the aims of British Cycling,’ he said. ‘I’ve spent the past week sitting down with every rider who is going to Rio. We have a fantastically  talented group of very young,  brilliantly enthusiastic riders. The talent is there, the support network is there and sometimes you just need to freshen things up. ‘This will help that group going forward. I’ve got no concerns at all that they’ll move on to bigger things and Rio will be fantastic for them.’ FIVE OF BRAILSFORD\'S BESTSir Dave Brailsford on Friday stood down as British Cycling performance director after a decade of unprecedented success.BEIJING BOUNTYIt began with Nicole Cooke in torrential rain, storming to gold in the women\'s road race by the Great Wall of China. There followed a display of dominance in the velodrome few thought could ever be repeated. In 10 events, Britain won seven, including three gold medals for Sir Chris Hoy. The remarkable thing is Britain\'s cyclists matched the feat in London four years later.TEAM PURSUIT TYROSThe four-man, four-kilometre team pursuit, perhaps more than any other discipline, occupied Brailsford\'s attention and provided the greatest demonstration of Britain\'s dominance at the Laoshan Velodrome in Beijing. Ed Clancy, Paul Manning, Geraint Thomas and Bradley Wiggins won in scintillating fashion, nearly seven seconds ahead of their nearest rivals, in posting a world record which stood for four years.UNION FLAGS AT THE TOUR DE FRANCEIt was not all glory and gold for Brailsford. Team Sky\'s first Tour de France in 2010 was a failure, with Wiggins underperforming from the start in Rotterdam. But the roadside support of British riders in a British team galvanised Brailsford, ever the enthusiast, and encouraged him that the Team Sky project was the right one to pursue. Three years later, two British Team Sky riders had won the sport\'s greatest race.WIGGINS SEIZING YELLOWFor Brailsford, the seventh stage of the 2012 Tour de France to La Planche des Belles Filles, won by Chris Froome as Sir Bradley Wiggins took the race lead, \"couldn\'t have been more perfect\". He said: \"There was a brow (of a hill), beautiful blue sky behind it, and all you could see was Froomie\'s helmet coming up like a helicopter. That was one of the highlights of my career. That stage will stay with me forever.\"HOY\'S FINAL STANDHoy, winner of gold in Athens and three more in Beijing, had seen it all in the velodrome and bowed out after winning the Keirin at London 2012. He won his sixth gold and Britain\'s eighth of London 2012 on the final day of the track programme. Laura Trott, Jason Kenny and others showed the next generation had arrived, but Hoy\'s final flourish proved to be a glorious Olympic hurrah for Brailsford.    More... Team Sky rider Henao withdrawn from racing after \'questions\' emerge from tests Their coaches said they were on a \'path to failure\', so how did Britain\'s women cyclists become best team in world sport? Brailsford set to review British cycling role after world track championships in Cali   Share or comment on this article 14shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Matt+Lawton\" rel=\"nofollow\">Matt Lawton</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@Matt_Lawton_DM\">Follow @@Matt_Lawton_DM</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 01:39 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:25 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602195/Brailsford-quits-head-British-Cycling-focus-Team-Sky-duties.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602195/Brailsford-quits-head-British-Cycling-focus-Team-Sky-duties.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Brailsford quits as head of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky duties\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 14</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2602195/Brailsford-quits-head-British-Cycling-focus-Team-Sky-duties.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">10</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">For Sir Dave Brailsford it really had become the impossible job. With British Cycling based in Manchester and Team Sky’s main training headquarters now in Nice, it was like asking Jose Mourinho to take on Chelsea without relinquishing control of Real Madrid.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">So on Friday, after a 10-year reign that had brought eight gold medals at both the London and Beijing Olympics in 2008, Brailsford stood down as performance director of British Cycling to focus on running the Team Sky road team.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Quit: Sir Dave Brailsford has resigned as performance director of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"453\" id=\"i-9ac70e30\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-1D021DB600000578-73_634x453.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Quit: Sir Dave Brailsford has resigned as performance director of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Brailsford made it clear before the recent Track World Championships that it was becoming too much — that he was being spread too thin and that both teams could suffer as a consequence.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">For a man who sets the highest of standards, whose mantra is ‘marginal gains’, and has an acute attention to detail, a  situation that meant he might be giving less than his best was unacceptable.<br/>He hopes the British Cycling team he has put in place will continue to achieve success, not least at the Rio Games in 2016.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It just feels like it’s a natural transition,’ Brailsford said yesterday. ‘We’ve thought for a long time as to how we can get British Cycling in the best possible shape and give the riders the best possible support going into Rio, because that’s the most important thing.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Chat: Brailsford speaks to Chris Froome as the Brit rides to victory at the 2013 Tour de France\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"430\" id=\"i-a9c00e6a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-071DFCA700000514-631_634x430.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Chat: Brailsford speaks to Chris Froome as the Brit rides to victory at the 2013 Tour de France</p> </div>\n<div class=\"floatRHS\"> <img alt=\"sir dave brailsford\'s haul\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"626\" id=\"i-a9130e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-1D09F4B100000578-288_306x626.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It’s been well documented that my time is more stretched across Team Sky and British Cycling. Team Sky have grown with the success of the Tour de France and I felt that the back-up that now exists at British Cycling — with Ian Drake as CEO, with Shane Sutton knowing all the riders — it’s the right team to move that team on.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">For some of the riders, Brailsford’s departure might be as unsettling as it was for Manchester United’s players when Sir Alex Ferguson retired. To add to their woes is the departure of Dr Steve Peters, the acclaimed psychiatrist to whom  Sir Chris Hoy, Sir Bradley Wiggins and Victoria Pendleton have said they owe much of their success.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Those who remain can only hope a healthy degree of continuity will ensure there is further success.<br/>A major reshuffle sees Sutton promoted to British Cycling’s technical director with responsibility for rider performance. Andy Harrison will continue as programmes director. Both report to Drake but a new role — head of performance support — has also been created. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Having left Team Sky as sporting director to join the Premier League youth department as head of elite performance, it is thought Dan Hunt could return to cycling from football.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Peters, recruited by England manager Roy Hodgson after his success with Liverpool, will step down but will remain with Brailsford at Team Sky. Before he departs he will assist in setting up a new support system for riders.</font><br/><br/> <img alt=\"Mastermind: Brailsford celebrates Victoria Pendleton\'s gold medal in the keirin at London 2012\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-a76a0e5c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-1D021E3A00000578-520_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </p>\n<p class=\"imageCaption\">Mastermind: Brailsford celebrates Victoria Pendleton\'s gold medal in the keirin at London 2012</p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I want to thank Sir Dave Brailsford for his enormous contribution to British Cycling,’ said Drake. ‘The organisation he leaves behind is transformed from the one we both joined in 1998.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’m confident we have the right management team to take us into Rio and beyond. Cycling in this country has travelled a long way but the best is yet to come.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Brailsford insisted he will remain close to British Cycling.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Success: Brailsford poses with 2012 Tour de France winner Sir Bradley Wiggins\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"442\" id=\"i-a95a0e75\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-078C419C000005DC-509_306x442.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Success: Brailsford receives his knighthood from Queen Elizabeth II at Buckingham Palace in February 2013\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"442\" id=\"i-a23e0e26\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-0335270200000514-761_306x442.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Success: Brailsford poses with 2012 Tour de France winner Sir Bradley Wiggins (left), and receives his knighthood from Queen Elizabeth II at Buckingham Palace in February 2013<br/></p></div> <p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’ll still be available to Ian, Shane and Andy for support and my role at Team Sky will mean we’ll still work closely and support the aims of British Cycling,’ he said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I’ve spent the past week sitting down with every rider who is going to Rio. We have a fantastically  talented group of very young,  brilliantly enthusiastic riders. The talent is there, the support network is there and sometimes you just need to freshen things up. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘This will help that group going forward. I’ve got no concerns at all that they’ll move on to bigger things and Rio will be fantastic for them.’</font></p>\n<div class=\"cleared art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>FIVE OF BRAILSFORD\'S BEST<br/></b></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sir Dave Brailsford on Friday stood down as British Cycling performance director after a decade of unprecedented success.<br/></font></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">BEIJING BOUNTY</font></span><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It began with Nicole Cooke in torrential rain, storming to gold in the women\'s road race by the Great Wall of China. There followed a display of dominance in the velodrome few thought could ever be repeated. In 10 events, Britain won seven, including three gold medals for Sir Chris Hoy. The remarkable thing is Britain\'s cyclists matched the feat in London four years later.</font></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">TEAM PURSUIT TYROS</font></span><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The four-man, four-kilometre team pursuit, perhaps more than any other discipline, occupied Brailsford\'s attention and provided the greatest demonstration of Britain\'s dominance at the Laoshan Velodrome in Beijing. Ed Clancy, Paul Manning, Geraint Thomas and Bradley Wiggins won in scintillating fashion, nearly seven seconds ahead of their nearest rivals, in posting a world record which stood for four years.</font></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">UNION FLAGS AT THE TOUR DE FRANCE</font></span></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It was not all glory and gold for Brailsford. Team Sky\'s first Tour de France in 2010 was a failure, with Wiggins underperforming from the start in Rotterdam. But the roadside support of British riders in a British team galvanised Brailsford, ever the enthusiast, and encouraged him that the Team Sky project was the right one to pursue. Three years later, two British Team Sky riders had won the sport\'s greatest race.</font></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">WIGGINS SEIZING YELLOW</font></span></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">For Brailsford, the seventh stage of the 2012 Tour de France to La Planche des Belles Filles, won by Chris Froome as Sir Bradley Wiggins took the race lead, \"couldn\'t have been more perfect\". He said: \"There was a brow (of a hill), beautiful blue sky behind it, and all you could see was Froomie\'s helmet coming up like a helicopter. That was one of the highlights of my career. That stage will stay with me forever.\"</font></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">HOY\'S FINAL STAND</font></span></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Hoy, winner of gold in Athens and three more in Beijing, had seen it all in the velodrome and bowed out after winning the Keirin at London 2012. He won his sixth gold and Britain\'s eighth of London 2012 on the final day of the track programme. Laura Trott, Jason Kenny and others showed the next generation had arrived, but Hoy\'s final flourish proved to be a glorious Olympic hurrah for Brailsford.</font></p></div></div>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2584349/Team-Sky-rider-Sergio-Henao-withdrawn-racing-questions-emerge-tests.html\"> Team Sky rider Henao withdrawn from racing after \'questions\' emerge from tests</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2581899/Their-coaches-said-path-failure-did-Britains-women-cyclists-best-team-world-sport.html\"> Their coaches said they were on a \'path to failure\', so how did Britain\'s women cyclists become best team in world sport?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2560866/Brailsford-set-review-British-cycling-role-world-track-championships-Cali.html\"> Brailsford set to review British cycling role after world track championships in Cali</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602195/Brailsford-quits-head-British-Cycling-focus-Team-Sky-duties.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602195/Brailsford-quits-head-British-Cycling-focus-Team-Sky-duties.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Brailsford quits as head of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky duties\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602195/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">14</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-1D021DB600000578-652_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:18','2014-04-11 22:25:07'),(69,'176c62f8a67d758e9e2f99bf39f3c521be3876648104293fdfa80ebb40e7a7f0','dailymail',NULL,'Conquest needs to be at his best in Commonwealth defence against McKenzie','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602786/Conquest-needs-best-Commonwealth-defence-against-McKenzie.html',' By Martin Domin Follow @@martin_domin Published: 15:19 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 15:19 EST, 11 April 2014 0 View comments Tony Conquest knows he will have to be on the ball if he is going to keep hold of his Commonwealth title in the first defence against hard-hitting Ovill McKenzie. Cruiserweight Conquest, who won the belt in a brutal battle against Daniel Ammann in February, takes on McKenzie at the Copper Box Arena on Saturday. The Romford ace knows he’ll have to be at his best against the two-time Commonwealth champion at light-heavyweight who gave Enzo Maccarinelli a tough fight last time before being stopped in the 11th round.  Contender: Ovil McKenzie (left) will be a stern test to Tony Conquest\'s title defence    ‘If you’re a champion you can’t pick and choose who you’re gonna fight. Eventually you’re going to have to fight good men,’ said Conquest. ‘I’d rather fight someone who gives me that little bit of fear in my belly because I know I have to fight and it makes be better. ‘When I boxed Wadi Camacho I knew he was a terrific puncher and a big old lump. That gave me the added little bit of incentive and the adrenalin was pumping. ‘If you look at his body, Ovill’s legs aren’t that big but his upper body is like a cruiserweight. He is the complete polar opposite of me.  Conquest defeated Wadi Camacho at the O2 Arena in October   Take that: Conquest lands a punch on Camacho in an epic battle  ‘There is a big jump from light-heavyweight to cruiserweight but he’s beaten big lumps like Buster Keaton and Terry Dunstan. Ovill got his tactics right against them and showed he isn’t just a big puncher, but also has a bit of a brain. ‘I will have to be right on the ball. ‘He is dangerous all the time, and I will have to be on my guard especially early on when he has won before. ‘Ovill does get a little bit tired, but when you look how much muscle there is on him he’s gonna get a little bit tire.‘The first six rounds is when he’ll be at his most dangerous and I’m expecting to come in stronger than ever because he hasn’t got any weight troubles.’ Frank Buglioni, Bradley Skeete and Lewis Pettitt are also in action at the Olympic venue in London.Tony Conquest vs Ovill McKenzie is live on Box Nation on Saturday.     Victorious: Conquest beat Camacho by a unanimous decision    More... PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley Is Pacquiao all talk? Unbeaten Bradley thinks so as he seeks public redemption in grudge Vegas rematch Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach Love him or loathe him, Amir Khan has skill, courage and ambition... he deserves respect  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Martin+Domin\" rel=\"nofollow\">Martin Domin</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@martin_domin\">Follow @@martin_domin</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 15:19 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:19 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602786/Conquest-needs-best-Commonwealth-defence-against-McKenzie.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602786/Conquest-needs-best-Commonwealth-defence-against-McKenzie.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Conquest needs to be at his best in Commonwealth defence against McKenzie\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602786/Conquest-needs-best-Commonwealth-defence-against-McKenzie.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Tony Conquest knows he will have to be on the ball if he is going to keep hold of his Commonwealth title in the first defence against hard-hitting Ovill McKenzie.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Cruiserweight Conquest, who won the belt in a brutal battle against Daniel Ammann in February, takes on McKenzie at the Copper Box Arena on Saturday.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Romford ace knows he’ll have to be at his best against the two-time Commonwealth champion at light-heavyweight who gave Enzo Maccarinelli a tough fight last time before being stopped in the 11th round.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Contender: Ovil McKenzie (left) will be a stern test to Tony Conquest\'s title defence\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"440\" id=\"i-a86b0e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602786-1D0946A600000578-752_634x440.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Contender: Ovil McKenzie (left) will be a stern test to Tony Conquest\'s title defence</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘If you’re a champion you can’t pick and choose who you’re gonna fight. Eventually you’re going to have to fight good men,’ said Conquest.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I’d rather fight someone who gives me that little bit of fear in my belly because I know I have to fight and it makes be better.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘When I boxed Wadi Camacho I knew he was a terrific puncher and a big old lump. That gave me the added little bit of incentive and the adrenalin was pumping.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘If you look at his body, Ovill’s legs aren’t that big but his upper body is like a cruiserweight. He is the complete polar opposite of me.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Conquest defeated Wadi Camacho at the O2 Arena in October\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"427\" id=\"i-ac500e8a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602786-1D09CCF900000578-572_634x427.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Conquest defeated Wadi Camacho at the O2 Arena in October</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Take that: Conquest lands a punch on Camacho in an epic battle\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-ab1f0e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602786-1D09CD5A00000578-531_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Take that: Conquest lands a punch on Camacho in an epic battle</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘There is a big jump from light-heavyweight to cruiserweight but he’s beaten big lumps like Buster Keaton and Terry Dunstan. Ovill got his tactics right against them and showed he isn’t just a big puncher, but also has a bit of a brain.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I will have to be right on the ball.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘He is dangerous all the time, and I will have to be on my guard especially early on when he has won before.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘Ovill does get a little bit tired, but when you look how much muscle there is on him he’s gonna get a little bit tire.‘The first six rounds is when he’ll be at his most dangerous and I’m expecting to come in stronger than ever because he hasn’t got any weight troubles.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Frank Buglioni, Bradley Skeete and Lewis Pettitt are also in action at the Olympic venue in London.<br/>Tony Conquest vs Ovill McKenzie is live on Box Nation on Saturday.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"xx\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"432\" id=\"i-aa220e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602786-1D09CD4500000578-590_634x432.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Victorious: Conquest beat Camacho by a unanimous decision\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"401\" id=\"i-a9c80e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602786-1D09CD5600000578-213_634x401.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Victorious: Conquest beat Camacho by a unanimous decision</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601650/PacMan-people-Mannys-superstar-statesman-entertains-serves-fellow-Filipinos-Jeff-Powell.html\"> PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2599238/Is-Pacquiao-talk-Unbeaten-Bradley-thinks-seeks-public-redemption-grudge-Vegas-rematch.html\"> Is Pacquiao all talk? Unbeaten Bradley thinks so as he seeks public redemption in grudge Vegas rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html\"> Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2593624/Love-loathe-Amir-Khan-skill-courage-ambition-deserves-respect.html\"> Love him or loathe him, Amir Khan has skill, courage and ambition... he deserves respect</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602786/Conquest-needs-best-Commonwealth-defence-against-McKenzie.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602786/Conquest-needs-best-Commonwealth-defence-against-McKenzie.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Conquest needs to be at his best in Commonwealth defence against McKenzie\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602786/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602786-1D09D24B00000578-233_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:19','2014-04-11 22:19:38'),(70,'be3cb2cda50ea27831226fa21bb7590132a3554defcddbbd1a1baa223ec4d46a','dailymail',NULL,'Sir Clive Woodward: Sir Dave Brailsford was tough, bullish and terrific','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602807/Sir-Clive-Woodward-Brailsford-tough-bullish-terrific.html','  Published: 15:16 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 15:19 EST, 11 April 2014 0 View comments Sir Dave Brailsford was fantastically abrupt and to the point during Olympic testing one day at the Velodrome. ‘You see that door… it must not be opened during any time a British cyclist is riding.’ ‘What door? Are you winding me up?’  Quit: Sir Dave Brailsford has resigned as performance director of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky  ‘That door… ’ It wasn’t as if it was that close to the track; it was a door for spectators. ‘I am serious. It could be the difference between winning and losing,’ he continued. He was being his usual bullish self. Challenging, forcing the boundaries — Brailsford is a man after my own heart. He loves attention to detail and will always seek to use home advantage. ‘Close it. Keep it closed. It will impact on times… but get it opened when the opposition are cycling!’ That is what happened. I thought he was terrific. I was the director of sport for the British Olympic Association and my first call on the first day in the job was from the cycling performance director. I didn’t know very much about him, but he invited me to join him. While others were unwelcoming, he was like a sponge. Chat: Brailsford speaks to Chris Froome as the Brit rides to victory at the 2013 Tour de France  Wow factor: Sir Clive Woodward classed Brailsford as an outstanding coach  He would be all over you, asking questions, demanding more. If the answer was ‘no’, he wouldn’t accept it. He knew what I had achieved in sport and wanted to see if he could tap into it. You see the gold medals, the lycra and the glamour of cycling, but he created a tough regime, taking no prisoners. In fact, he created the toughest environment I’ve witnessed outside the England rugby set-up — for men and women. He called it marginal gains. He thought it was all so obvious, but he would break it down to this simple message: ‘Do everything better than anyone else.’ You can’t do that without leadership — and success starts at the top. His biggest success has been the performance of Team Sky in the Tour de France. His Olympic golds were amazing, but the Tour success made me say ‘wow’. People said he couldn’t do it, but he is not a man to accept failure. Success in professional sport is about outstanding athletes, but also about outstanding coaching. Sir Dave Brailsford is outstanding.     More... Brailsford quits as head of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky duties Wiggins hints at British Cycling unrest after Brailsford quits to focus on Team Sky role   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\"></p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 15:16 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:19 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602807/Sir-Clive-Woodward-Brailsford-tough-bullish-terrific.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602807/Sir-Clive-Woodward-Brailsford-tough-bullish-terrific.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Sir Clive Woodward: Brailsford was tough, bullish and terrific\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2602807/Sir-Clive-Woodward-Brailsford-tough-bullish-terrific.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Sir Dave Brailsford was fantastically abrupt and to the point during Olympic testing one day at the Velodrome.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘You see that door… it must not be opened during any time a British cyclist is riding.’</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘What door? Are you winding me up?’</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Quit: Sir Dave Brailsford has resigned as performance director of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"453\" id=\"i-9ac70e30\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-1D021DB600000578-73_634x453.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Quit: Sir Dave Brailsford has resigned as performance director of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘That door… ’ It wasn’t as if it was that close to the track; it was a door for spectators.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I am serious. It could be the difference between winning and losing,’ he continued. He was being his usual bullish self.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Challenging, forcing the boundaries — Brailsford is a man after my own heart. He loves attention to detail and will always seek to use home advantage.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Close it. Keep it closed. It will impact on times… but get it opened when the opposition are cycling!’ That is what happened. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">I thought he was terrific. I was the director of sport for the British Olympic Association and my first call on the first day in the job was from the cycling performance director. I didn’t know very much about him, but he invited me to join him. While others were unwelcoming, he was like a sponge. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Chat: Brailsford speaks to Chris Froome as the Brit rides to victory at the 2013 Tour de France\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"430\" id=\"i-a9c00e6a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602195-071DFCA700000514-631_634x430.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Chat: Brailsford speaks to Chris Froome as the Brit rides to victory at the 2013 Tour de France</p></div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wow factor: Sir Clive Woodward classed Brailsford as an outstanding coach\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a9930e6a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602807-0C92FC9400000578-520_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wow factor: Sir Clive Woodward classed Brailsford as an outstanding coach</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He would be all over you, asking questions, demanding more. If the answer was ‘no’, he wouldn’t accept it. He knew what I had achieved in sport and wanted to see if he could tap into it.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">You see the gold medals, the lycra and the glamour of cycling, but he created a tough regime, taking no prisoners. In fact, he created the toughest environment I’ve witnessed outside the England rugby set-up — for men and women.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He called it marginal gains. He thought it was all so obvious, but he would break it down to this simple message: ‘Do everything better than anyone else.’</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">You can’t do that without leadership — and success starts at the top.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">His biggest success has been the performance of Team Sky in the Tour de France. His Olympic golds were amazing, but the Tour success made me say ‘wow’. People said he couldn’t do it, but he is not a man to accept failure.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Success in professional sport is about outstanding athletes, but also about outstanding coaching. Sir Dave Brailsford is outstanding.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2602195/Brailsford-quits-head-British-Cycling-focus-Team-Sky-duties.html\"> Brailsford quits as head of British Cycling to focus on Team Sky duties</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/othersports/article-2602726/Sir-Bradley-Wiggins-hints-British-Cycling-unrest-Sir-David-Brailsford-quits-focus-Team-Sky-role.html\"> Wiggins hints at British Cycling unrest after Brailsford quits to focus on Team Sky role</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602807/Sir-Clive-Woodward-Brailsford-tough-bullish-terrific.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602807/Sir-Clive-Woodward-Brailsford-tough-bullish-terrific.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Sir Clive Woodward: Brailsford was tough, bullish and terrific\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/othersports/article-2602807/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602807-0C92FC9400000578-818_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:20','2014-04-11 22:19:28'),(71,'f4704453ecd5cf027f22e000912feaa283c3eb3a75b519d966df651ae4a24534','dailymail',NULL,'US team set for Formula One bow in 2015 as FIA accept entrant from NASCAR ace Haas','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html',' By Ian Parkes, Press Association Published: 15:04 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 15:08 EST, 11 April 2014 10 shares 6 View comments The United States is to finally have a team on the Formula One grid from 2015 after the FIA accepted the entry of NASCAR guru Gene Haas. Four months after motor sport\'s world governing body called for new entrants to compete in the sport, Haas has been accepted following a period of due diligence. Haas said in a statement: \'Obviously, we\'re extremely pleased to have been granted a Formula One licence by the FIA.  New owner: The FIA have accepted an entrant from American Gene Haas (left)  Across the pond: Lewis Hamilton celebrates winning the inaugural United States Grand Prix in Austin in 2012 More... Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull Ecclestone says F1 will accept two new teams in 2015 with Haas leading chase \'It\'s an exciting time for me, Haas Automation and anyone who wanted to see an American team return to Formula One. \'Now, the really hard work begins. It\'s a challenge we embrace as we work to put cars on the grid. \'I want to thank the FIA for this opportunity and the diligence everyone put forth to see our licence application come to fruition.\' Haas at least has motor sport running through his veins as he forms one half of the successful Stewart-Haas Racing team based in Kannapolis, North Carolina.  Champagne moment: Lewis Hamilton celebrates winning the Bahrain Grand Prix last Sunday  F1 Grid: The teams in 2014 Red Bull RacingMercedesFerrariLotusMcLarenForce India Toro Rosso SauberWilliams Martini Racing Catheram Marussia Haas certainly has the credentials and capability to get a new team up and running as he owns factory facilities in Brussels which would likely be key for a European base. Haas also runs the full-scale Windshear rolling-road wind tunnel in North Carolina that has previously been used by a number of Formula One teams, although that facility is understood to be banned at present. Former Red Bull and Jaguar technical director Guenther Steiner is working with Haas on the project. America last tried to get a team on the grid in 2010 at a time when F1 was seeking significant expansion, only for US F1\'s plans to fail to come to fruition. Haas still has numerous hurdles to overcome, notably with regard to cost as F1 supremo Bernie Ecclestone has warned one billion dollars (£600million) would likely last him four years. Haas is entering at a time when the major marques have put a block on FIA president Jean Todt\'s plans for a cost cap to be introduced from next year. Financial control will instead supposedly come through a tightening of the technical and sporting regulations. Haas will also certainly be all too aware that since the last three new teams were accepted from 2010, Hispania Racing no longer exists, whilst Marussia and Caterham have failed to score a point in 80 races to date despite the fact the top 10 cars now score points.  More... Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull Ecclestone says F1 will accept two new teams in 2015 with Haas leading chase     Share or comment on this article 10shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Ian+Parkes,+Press+Association\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ian Parkes, Press Association</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 15:04 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:08 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"US team set for Formula One bow in 2015 as FIA accept entrant from NASCAR ace Haas\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 10</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">6</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The United States is to finally have a team on the Formula One grid from 2015 after the FIA accepted the entry of NASCAR guru Gene Haas. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Four months after motor sport\'s world governing body called for new entrants to compete in the sport, Haas has been accepted following a period of due diligence. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Haas said in a statement: \'Obviously, we\'re extremely pleased to have been granted a Formula One licence by the FIA. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"New owner: The FIA have accepted an entrant from American Gene Haas (left)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"369\" id=\"i-5ff00d58\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CCC6E4C00000578-742_634x369.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">New owner: The FIA have accepted an entrant from American Gene Haas (left)</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Across the pond: Lewis Hamilton celebrates winning the inaugural United States Grand Prix in Austin in 2012\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-a73b0e51\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/03/article-2595918-02551D6900000514-167_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Across the pond: Lewis Hamilton celebrates winning the inaugural United States Grand Prix in Austin in 2012</p> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602373/Lewis-Hamilton-shies-away-cameras-meal-Nicole-Scherzinger.html\"> Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\"> Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2601725/Christian-Horner-claims-Daniel-Ricciardo-best-youngster-enjoys-fine-start-Red-Bull.html\"> Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598099/Ecclestone-says-F1-accept-two-new-teams-2015-Haas-leading-chase.html\"> Ecclestone says F1 will accept two new teams in 2015 with Haas leading chase</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'It\'s an exciting time for me, Haas Automation and anyone who wanted to see an American team return to Formula One. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Now, the really hard work begins. It\'s a challenge we embrace as we work to put cars on the grid. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'I want to thank the FIA for this opportunity and the diligence everyone put forth to see our licence application come to fruition.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> Haas at least has motor sport running through his veins as he forms one half of the successful Stewart-Haas Racing team based in Kannapolis, North Carolina. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Champagne moment: Lewis Hamilton celebrates winning the Bahrain Grand Prix last Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"409\" id=\"i-a95b0e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602806-1CE377A300000578-770_634x409.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Champagne moment: Lewis Hamilton celebrates winning the Bahrain Grand Prix last Sunday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"art-insert sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">F1 Grid: The teams in 2014 </span></span><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Red Bull Racing</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Merc</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">edes</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ferrari</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Lotus</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">McLaren</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Force</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> India </font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Toro Rosso </font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Sauber</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Williams Martini Racing </font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cathera</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">m </font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Marussia </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Haas certainly has the credentials and capability to get a new team up and running as he owns factory facilities in Brussels which would likely be key for a European base. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Haas also runs the full-scale Windshear rolling-road wind tunnel in North Carolina that has previously been used by a number of Formula One teams, although that facility is understood to be banned at present. Former Red Bull and Jaguar technical director Guenther Steiner is working with Haas on the project. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">America last tried to get a team on the grid in 2010 at a time when F1 was seeking significant expansion, only for US F1\'s plans to fail to come to fruition. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Haas still has numerous hurdles to overcome, notably with regard to cost as F1 supremo Bernie Ecclestone has warned one billion dollars (£600million) would likely last him four years. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Haas is entering at a time when the major marques have put a block on FIA president Jean Todt\'s plans for a cost cap to be introduced from next year. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Financial control will instead supposedly come through a tightening of the technical and sporting regulations. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Haas will also certainly be all too aware that since the last three new teams were accepted from 2010, Hispania Racing no longer exists, whilst Marussia and Caterham have failed to score a point in 80 races to date despite the fact the top 10 cars now score points. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2602373/Lewis-Hamilton-shies-away-cameras-meal-Nicole-Scherzinger.html\"> Hamilton shies away from the cameras after meal with girlfriend Nicole in London</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\"> Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2601725/Christian-Horner-claims-Daniel-Ricciardo-best-youngster-enjoys-fine-start-Red-Bull.html\"> Horner claims Ricciardo is among the best after youngster enjoys fine start at Red Bull</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598099/Ecclestone-says-F1-accept-two-new-teams-2015-Haas-leading-chase.html\"> Ecclestone says F1 will accept two new teams in 2015 with Haas leading chase</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/US-team-set-Formula-One-bow-2015-FIA-accept-entrant-NASCAR-ace-Haas.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"US team set for Formula One bow in 2015 as FIA accept entrant from NASCAR ace Haas\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2602806/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">10</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CCC6E4C00000578-423_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:21','2014-04-11 22:08:23'),(72,'2cb289064bd9a2712c201d95a9c562d835757a0a4b03519864214b25b1642b06','dailymail',NULL,'King declares war on Rangers board as he urges fans to withhold season-ticket money','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602649/King-declares-war-Rangers-board-urges-fans-withhold-season-ticket-money.html',' By Mark Wilson Published: 14:30 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 14:31 EST, 11 April 2014 24 shares 29 View comments  Dave King declared all-out war on the Rangers board on Friday night after accusing them of broken promises. The South Africa-based businessman has urged fans to follow through on a plan to withhold season ticket money – and also starve the club hierarchy of other commercial income. His searing attack follows the launch earlier this week of season ticket renewals, despite chief executive Graham Wallace’s 120-day business review not yet being released. The 59-year-old believes there has been a breach of an agreement reached last month when, following talks between the two sides, King agreed to delay his plans until the board had produced a plan for the club’s future.  Man with a plan: Dave King wants supporters\' cash to be held in a separate trust  More... Scotland on the up as Strachan\'s side rise 15 places to 22nd in the FIFA world rankings... with England up to 11th Dundee United boss backs starlet Moore in his battle with skin cancer McNamara\'s appeal against three-match ban is big risk for Scottish Cup final McCoist: We felt the same pain as fans after Raith defeat... we\'ll bounce back in Cup semi More explosively, he claimed chairman David Somers had intimated the board always wanted to delay publication of the crucial review until after season ticket money was collected. The Rangers board responded by strongly refuting all of King’s accusations – branding them ‘disgraceful’ – and said they could consider legal action. The Ibrox directors insisted King had misrepresented their position, stating the review would appear before the season ticket renewal deadline on May 6. While the war of words rages on anew, King will now press ahead with his fan-led revolution. And he has gained the backing of nine-in-a-row captain Richard Gough, who will act as a custodian of the trust account being activated to keep supporter cash out of the board’s reach until specific conditions are met. Speaking of his talks last month, King said: ‘The board recommitted to issue the business review within the original 120 day deadline and, importantly, committed that the fans will have access to this review prior to advancing funds by way of season ticket renewals.  Rangers Chairman David Somers (front, left) is accused of reneging on a promise to supporters‘Despite strong reservations from fan groups I asked the fans to give the board time to honour this commitment. ‘Part of my motivation was that any public company board is bound to act in good faith and that breach of such a share price sensitive commitment would be an ethical, moral, and probably criminal breach.  ‘I followed up on this commitment with the board after the recent announcement on season ticket renewals. The Chairman has advised me that the board will now only issue the review at the end of the season ticket renewal period and it will consequently not be timeously made available to fans. Disturbingly, the Chairman has advised me that the true intention of the board had always been to delay issuing the review until funds had been largely collected. ‘I apologise to all fans for wasting time by lending credibility to the board’s false representations. I was wrong to give them the benefit of the doubt.’ The timing of King’s statement is controversial, given that it came on the eve of Saturday\'s crucial Scottish Cup semi-final against Dundee United. It’s understood he felt he had no option but to break cover again after the formal launch of season ticket renewals on Wednesday. King has stated his intention to provide at least £30 million of the £50 million he feels it will take to restore Rangers over the next four years, but wants to do so via a new share issue that would dilute the current power base.If enough fans rally behind his plan, it could force the board to either agree to his wish or risk the club suffer another insolvency event.‘It is common cause that the club is not a going concern without access to the season ticket loan from the fans,’ said King. ‘It is also common cause that the season ticket money will only provide partial relief in advance of a more permanent recapitalisation. ‘I have hitherto urged restraint in dealing with the board, however due to this extreme act of bad faith I believe that it is vital that fans now withhold season ticket money from this board and similarly refuse to support the club by way of the purchase of replica kit or any other retail product.  ‘An announcement will shortly be made providing details of a bank account that season ticket money can be paid into as an interim measure.   Dejected: Rangers players after their cup final defeat against Raith Rovers  The specific terms and conditions of this account will be made available to fans, including the basis on which funds will be advanced to the club and the basis on which funds will be returned to fans. As a minimum, the board must provide the club property as security against the season ticket money. ‘I recognise that fans will have anxiety about “betraying” the club and the risk of loss of a cherished seat at Ibrox.  However, the time has come when the trade-off is a potential loss of a seat against the loss of the club. That would be the real betrayal. This board has lost its right to be dealt with on a good faith basis.’ King’s words provoked an equally stern response from within the Ibrox boardroom. ‘The Chairman and the Board refute all such allegations in the strongest terms and have referred Mr King’s statement to the Club’s legal advisors,’ said their statement. ‘Mr King clearly has elected to ignore the Board’s previous public statement following the Board’s meeting with him. In this statement, which was reviewed with him prior to issue, the Board stated that it will issue the results of the business review prior to the season ticket renewal window ending. ‘This position remains unchanged and Mr King is well aware of this having sought personal confirmation on this matter from the Chairman as recently as yesterday.’ They added: ‘When the Board met Mr King a few weeks ago, he made it clear that he did not want to put another penny into the Club and would prefer to see the Club using other investors’ money.  The Board was therefore surprised, but gave him the benefit of the doubt when, a few days later, Mr King made media comments about a willingness to invest his money into the Club.  This is an easy statement to make to the media but is contrary to what he told the whole Board. ‘It is extremely disappointing that Mr King should consider it appropriate to issue this latest statement, clearly designed to unsettle and mislead Rangers fans, on the eve of an important Scottish Cup semi-final match. \'For someone who claims to have the interests of Rangers at heart and as an ex-director, King’s untrue comments are nothing short of disgraceful.’   More... Scotland on the up as Strachan\'s side rise 15 places to 22nd in the FIFA world rankings... with England up to 11th Dundee United boss backs starlet Moore in his battle with skin cancer McNamara\'s appeal against three-match ban is big risk for Scottish Cup final McCoist: We felt the same pain as fans after Raith defeat... we\'ll bounce back in Cup semi    Share or comment on this article 24shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Mark+Wilson\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mark Wilson</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 14:30 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 14:31 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602649/King-declares-war-Rangers-board-urges-fans-withhold-season-ticket-money.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602649/King-declares-war-Rangers-board-urges-fans-withhold-season-ticket-money.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"King declares war on Rangers board as he urges fans to withhold season-ticket money\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 24</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602649/King-declares-war-Rangers-board-urges-fans-withhold-season-ticket-money.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">29</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><span style=\'font-size:9.0pt; font-family:\"Arial\",\"sans-serif\";color:black\'></span><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt; font-family:\"Arial\",\"sans-serif\";color:black\'></span><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Dave King declared all-out war on the Rangers board on Friday night after accusing them of broken promises.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The South Africa-based businessman has urged fans to follow through on a plan to withhold season ticket money – and also starve the club hierarchy of other commercial income.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">His searing attack follows the launch earlier this week of season ticket renewals, despite chief executive Graham Wallace’s 120-day business review not yet being released.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 59-year-old believes there has been a breach of an agreement reached last month when, following talks between the two sides, King agreed to delay his plans until the board had produced a plan for the club’s future.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Man with a plan: Dave King wants supporters\' cash to be held in a separate trust\" class=\"