ution. And he has gained the backing of nine-in-a-row captain Richard Gough, who will act as a custodian of the trust account being activated to keep supporter cash out of the board’s reach until specific conditions are met.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Speaking of his talks last month, King said: ‘The board recommitted to issue the business review within the original 120 day deadline and, importantly, committed that the fans will have access to this review prior to advancing funds by way of season ticket renewals.  <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rangers Chairman David Somers (front, left) is accused of reneging on a promise to supporters\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"395\" id=\"i-ab5c0e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602649-1CE272CE00000578-283_634x395.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rangers Chairman David Somers (front, left) is accused of reneging on a promise to supporters</p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘Despite strong reservations from fan groups I asked the fans to give the board time to honour this commitment. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘Part of my motivation was that any public company board is bound to act in good faith and that breach of such a share price sensitive commitment would be an ethical, moral, and probably criminal breach.  <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I followed up on this commitment with the board after the recent announcement on season ticket renewals. The Chairman has advised me that the board will now only issue the review at the end of the season ticket renewal period and it will consequently not be timeously made available to fans. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Disturbingly, the Chairman has advised me that the true intention of the board had always been to delay issuing the review until funds had been largely collected. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I apologise to all fans for wasting time by lending credibility to the board’s false representations. I was wrong to give them the benefit of the doubt.’ <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The timing of King’s statement is controversial, given that it came on the eve of Saturday\'s crucial Scottish Cup semi-final against Dundee United. It’s understood he felt he had no option but to break cover again after the formal launch of season ticket renewals on Wednesday. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">King has stated his intention to provide at least £30 million of the £50 million he feels it will take to restore Rangers over the next four years, but wants to do so via a new share issue that would dilute the current power base.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">If enough fans rally behind his plan, it could force the board to either agree to his wish or risk the club suffer another insolvency event.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘It is common cause that the club is not a going concern without access to the season ticket loan from the fans,’ said King. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘It is also common cause that the season ticket money will only provide partial relief in advance of a more permanent recapitalisation. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I have hitherto urged restraint in dealing with the board, however due to this extreme act of bad faith I believe that it is vital that fans now withhold season ticket money from this board and similarly refuse to support the club by way of the purchase of replica kit or any other retail product.  <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘An announcement will shortly be made providing details of a bank account that season ticket money can be paid into as an interim measure. <br/></font></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dejected: Rangers players after their cup final defeat against Raith Rovers\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"392\" id=\"i-aa710e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602649-1CE34F4900000578-264_634x392.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dejected: Rangers players after their cup final defeat against Raith Rovers</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The specific terms and conditions of this account will be made available to fans, including the basis on which funds will be advanced to the club and the basis on which funds will be returned to fans. As a minimum, the board must provide the club property as security against the season ticket money. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I recognise that fans will have anxiety about “betraying” the club and the risk of loss of a cherished seat at Ibrox.  However, the time has come when the trade-off is a potential loss of a seat against the loss of the club. That would be the real betrayal. This board has lost its right to be dealt with on a good faith basis.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">King’s words provoked an equally stern response from within the Ibrox boardroom.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘The Chairman and the Board refute all such allegations in the strongest terms and have referred Mr King’s statement to the Club’s legal advisors,’ said their statement.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘Mr King clearly has elected to ignore the Board’s previous public statement following the Board’s meeting with him. In this statement, which was reviewed with him prior to issue, the Board stated that it will issue the results of the business review prior to the season ticket renewal window ending. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘This position remains unchanged and Mr King is well aware of this having sought personal confirmation on this matter from the Chairman as recently as yesterday.’ <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They added: ‘When the Board met Mr King a few weeks ago, he made it clear that he did not want to put another penny into the Club and would prefer to see the Club using other investors’ money.  The <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Board was therefore surprised, but gave him the benefit of the doubt when, a few days later, Mr King made media comments about a willingness to invest his money into the Club.  This is an easy statement to make to the media but is contrary to what he told the whole Board.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘It is extremely disappointing that Mr King should consider it appropriate to issue this latest statement, clearly designed to unsettle and mislead Rangers fans, on the eve of an important Scottish Cup semi-final match. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'For someone who claims to have the interests of Rangers at heart and as an ex-director, King’s untrue comments are nothing short of disgraceful.’ </font> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602058/Scotland-22nd-FIFA-world-rankings-England-11th.html\"> Scotland on the up as Strachan\'s side rise 15 places to 22nd in the FIFA world rankings... with England up to 11th</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601900/Dundee-United-boss-backs-starlet-Moore-battle-skin-cancer.html\"> Dundee United boss backs starlet Moore in his battle with skin cancer</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601878/Jackie-McNamaras-appeal-against-three-match-ban-big-risk-Scottish-Cup-final.html\"> McNamara\'s appeal against three-match ban is big risk for Scottish Cup final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601853/Ally-McCoist-insists-felt-pain-fans-Ramsdens-Cup-defeat.html\"> McCoist: We felt the same pain as fans after Raith defeat... we\'ll bounce back in Cup semi</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602649/King-declares-war-Rangers-board-urges-fans-withhold-season-ticket-money.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602649/King-declares-war-Rangers-board-urges-fans-withhold-season-ticket-money.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"King declares war on Rangers board as he urges fans to withhold season-ticket money\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602649/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">24</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602649-1D0939DE00000578-574_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:22','2014-04-11 21:31:43'),(73,'08573e0c91382cd8154a25916b45b579f7ebc27203b31a3e5af8d291545919e6','dailymail',NULL,'Tim Sherwood admits he couldn\'t cope without management as Tottenham boss prepares to leave at the end of the season','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602446/Tim-Sherwood-admits-cope-without-management-Tottenham-boss-prepares-leave-end-season.html',' Tim Sherwood admits he has caught the management bug at TottenhamKyle Walker is still injured - a doubt for the World CupSherwood blasts managers for talking about his jobTottenham face West Brom this weekend By David Kent Published: 09:00 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 13:17 EST, 11 April 2014 8 shares 5 View comments  Despite experiencing a \'baptism of fire\' in charge of Tottenham, Tim Sherwood says he only has his mind on managing again after this season. The 38-year-old will leave the club at the end of the season having failed to impress Daniel Levy after Andre Villas Boas\' sacking in December. And Sherwood admits he \'couldn\'t do without\' management, playing down reports of a future as an assistant. VIDEO Scroll down to watch Tim Sherwood talk ahead of Saturday\'s West Brom clash Sherwood: It\'s been an honour to manage this club, I\'ve loved it  Caught the bug: Tim Sherwood says he has loved his experience at Tottenham and only wants more   You\'re the man: Sherwood salutes Emmanuel Adebayor after the striker scored against Sunderland on Monday  More... WEST BROM vs TOTTENHAM: All the latest team news and stats as hosts look for boost in relegation battle Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Holtby targets Tottenham return and backs Van Gaal to replace Sherwood Newcastle in talks over Perez, Man Utd line up Milinkovic-Savic trial and Kaboul is wanted by Fiorentina Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public \'I have,\' said Sherwood after being asked whether he had enjoyed his time at the club. \'It\'s been an honour to manage this great football club.It\'s been different, it\'s an an experience like no other.\' \'Unless you\'ve ever stood in that technical area and had the expectation of the whole football club then you don\'t really know what it\'s like to be a manager. \'I\'ve enjoyed it and perversely I\'ve enjoyed the pressure. I\'m not sure I could do without it now.\' As well as denying he had talks over a No 2 role, he also rejected claims he would be interested in the Norwich job, calling it disrespectful. Tottenham travel to play West Brom this weekend, and despite the hosts needing points to secure their Premier League survival, Sherwood insists the match is just as important for his side. \'Any other club\'s need can\'t be greater than ours. We need to win. We\'ve got five Cup finals left and I think we can take maximum points from those games.\'  Playmaker: The victory against the Black Cats, inspired by Christian Eriksen, helped Spurs regain some form   Sherwood: If we play as well as we can we\'ll beat West Brom Big game: They face West Brom at the weekend, a team who are fighting for their lives at the bottom  One worry for Tottenham, and possibly England, is the fitness of Kyle Walker. The right-back has been out of action in recent weeks with a pelvic problem, and his manager says that although the injury is worrying, he is sure he will still make the plane to Brazil to play in the World Cup this summer. \'We\'re concerned immediately because he\'s not fit and it would be very doubtful if he were fit for next week. \'He\'s still got  a lot of time before the World Cup and Kyle is one of the best right backs - I\'m sure he\'ll be on the plane even if he doesn\'t make an appearance for Tottenham before the end of the season.\'  Fight against time: Kyle Walker is no nearer to making a comeback with his World Cup dream now in doubt  Sherwood blasts other managers for talking about his job Louis Van Gaal is the favourite to be made the next permanent manager at White Hart Lane, but Sherwood has been consistent in refusing to talk about the future of the club. \'It\'s just about me concentrating on the game and today I\'m concentrating on the game tomorrow. I think those questions are not for me to answer. Its just for me to worry about football matches and hopefully trying to win the next five games for Tottenham. \'That will iron itself out in due course. For me to worry about preparing the team, like I\'ve done this week. We had a good week\'s training and we\'re really going to West Brom on the front foot and trying to entertain those great Tottenham fans and get three points. \'The speculation has never eased since I came in. I\'ve always fended off the questions. I don\'t see a difference from the first hour to now.\'  Summer switch? Sherwood refused to comment on speculation about Louis van Gaal     Share or comment on this article 8shares','\n<ul class=\"article-summary sport\"><li><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\"><b>Tim Sherwood admits he has caught the management bug at Tottenham</b></font></li><li><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\"><b>Kyle Walker is still injured - a doubt for the World Cup</b></font></li><li><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\"><b>Sherwood blasts managers for talking about his job</b></font></li><li><font style=\"font-size:1.4em;\"><b>Tottenham face West Brom this weekend</b></font></li></ul>\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=David+Kent\" rel=\"nofollow\">David Kent</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 09:00 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 13:17 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602446/Tim-Sherwood-admits-cope-without-management-Tottenham-boss-prepares-leave-end-season.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602446/Tim-Sherwood-admits-cope-without-management-Tottenham-boss-prepares-leave-end-season.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Sherwood admits he couldn\'t cope without management as Spurs boss prepares to leave at the end of the season\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 8</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602446/Tim-Sherwood-admits-cope-without-management-Tottenham-boss-prepares-leave-end-season.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">5</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Despite experiencing a \'baptism of fire\' in charge of Tottenham, Tim Sherwood says he only has his mind on managing again after this season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 38-year-old will leave the club at the end of the season having failed to impress Daniel Levy after Andre Villas Boas\' sacking in December.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And Sherwood admits he \'couldn\'t do without\' management, playing down reports of a future as an assistant.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO</span></font> Scroll down to watch Tim Sherwood talk ahead of Saturday\'s West Brom clash</b><br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3457783704001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Sherwood: It\'s been an honour to manage this club, I\'ve loved it</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D097FED00000578-230_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Caught the bug: Tim Sherwood says he has loved his experience at Tottenham and only wants more\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"500\" id=\"i-ae030e93\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602446-1CEA7ECD00000578-921_634x500.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Caught the bug: Tim Sherwood says he has loved his experience at Tottenham and only wants more</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"You\'re the man: Sherwood salutes Emmanuel Adebayor after the striker scored against Sunderland on Monday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-ad960e8f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602446-1CEABD8B00000578-403_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">You\'re the man: Sherwood salutes Emmanuel Adebayor after the striker scored against Sunderland on Monday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600838/WEST-BROM-vs-TOTTENHAM-All-latest-team-news-stats-hosts-look-boost-relegation-battle.html\"> WEST BROM vs TOTTENHAM: All the latest team news and stats as hosts look for boost in relegation battle</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602250/Lewis-Holtby-targets-Tottenham-return-backs-Louis-van-Gaal-replace-Tim-Sherwood.html\"> Holtby targets Tottenham return and backs Van Gaal to replace Sherwood</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601580/Newcastle-talks-Perez-Man-Utd-line-Milinkovic-Savic-trial-Kaboul-wanted-Fiorentina-THE-TRANSFER-COLUMN.html\"> Newcastle in talks over Perez, Man Utd line up Milinkovic-Savic trial and Kaboul is wanted by Fiorentina</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html\"> Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I have,\' said Sherwood after being asked whether he had enjoyed his time at the club. \'It\'s been an honour to manage this great football club.It\'s been different, it\'s an an experience like no other.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Unless you\'ve ever stood in that technical area and had the expectation of the whole football club then you don\'t really know what it\'s like to be a manager. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I\'ve enjoyed it and perversely I\'ve enjoyed the pressure. I\'m not sure I could do without it now.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As well as denying he had talks over a No 2 role, he also rejected claims he would be interested in the Norwich job, calling it disrespectful.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Tottenham travel to play West Brom this weekend, and despite the hosts needing points to secure their Premier League survival, Sherwood insists the match is just as important for his side.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Any other club\'s need can\'t be greater than ours. We need to win. We\'ve got five Cup finals left and I think we can take maximum points from those games.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Playmaker: The victory against the Black Cats, inspired by Christian Eriksen, helped Spurs regain some form\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"404\" id=\"i-ad4d0e91\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602446-1CEADE8500000578-668_634x404.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Playmaker: The victory against the Black Cats, inspired by Christian Eriksen, helped Spurs regain some form</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"moduleFull\">  <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3456962816001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Sherwood: If we play as well as we can we\'ll beat West Brom</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D07940100000578-188_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <img alt=\"Big game: They face West Brom at the weekend, a team who are fighting for their lives at the bottom\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"452\" id=\"i-aba40e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602446-1CDBE59700000578-147_634x452.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Big game: They face West Brom at the weekend, a team who are fighting for their lives at the bottom</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">One worry for Tottenham, and possibly England, is the fitness of Kyle Walker.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The right-back has been out of action in recent weeks with a pelvic problem, and his manager says that although the injury is worrying, he is sure he will still make the plane to Brazil to play in the World Cup this summer.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We\'re concerned immediately because he\'s not fit and it would be very doubtful if he were fit for next week. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'He\'s still got  a lot of time before the World Cup and Kyle is one of the best right backs - I\'m sure he\'ll be on the plane even if he doesn\'t make an appearance for Tottenham before the end of the season.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fight against time: Kyle Walker is no nearer to making a comeback with his World Cup dream now in doubt\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"549\" id=\"i-a8090e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602446-05AD42E800000514-142_634x549.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fight against time: Kyle Walker is no nearer to making a comeback with his World Cup dream now in doubt</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3456992745001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Sherwood blasts other managers for talking about his job</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D07A32200000578-743_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Louis Van Gaal is the favourite to be made the next permanent manager at White Hart Lane, but Sherwood has been consistent in refusing to talk about the future of the club.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It\'s just about me concentrating on the game and today I\'m concentrating on the game tomorrow. I think those questions are not for me to answer. Its just for me to worry about football matches and hopefully trying to win the next five games for Tottenham.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'That will iron itself out in due course. For me to worry about preparing the team, like I\'ve done this week. We had a good week\'s training and we\'re really going to West Brom on the front foot and trying to entertain those great Tottenham fans and get three points.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'The speculation has never eased since I came in. I\'ve always fended off the questions. I don\'t see a difference from the first hour to now.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Summer switch? Sherwood refused to comment on speculation about Louis van Gaal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"491\" id=\"i-a7670e5f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602446-1CF0451400000578-758_634x491.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Summer switch? Sherwood refused to comment on speculation about Louis van Gaal</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<br/>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602446/Tim-Sherwood-admits-cope-without-management-Tottenham-boss-prepares-leave-end-season.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602446/Tim-Sherwood-admits-cope-without-management-Tottenham-boss-prepares-leave-end-season.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Sherwood admits he couldn\'t cope without management as Spurs boss prepares to leave at the end of the season\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602446/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">8</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602446-1CEA7ECD00000578-990_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:23','2014-04-11 20:17:29'),(74,'008b1c8387018f5bff42d4b49323d203730d9a0ba8944aca07f93abf00015f60','dailymail',NULL,'Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit launch','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html',' By Graeme Yorke Published: 07:15 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 13:09 EST, 11 April 2014 4,330 shares 29 View comments Kolo Toure seems to be a fan of his song, at least if Liverpool\'s new kit launch was anything to go by. The Ivorian defender was all smiles as he led a chorus of the Kolo Toure song on stage in Liverpool city centre. Toure joined Philippe Coutinho, Jordan Henderson and Simon Mignolet in Liverpool One to help launch the new red home strip that the Premier League leaders will wear next season. Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit release Click here to check out more Liverpool-related content from The Redmen TV  Chorus: Kolo Toure sang his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit launch on Thursday    The 33-year-old arrived at Liverpool on a free transfer from Manchester City in the summer. After a number of mistakes, Toure was dropped from the first team, but he returned to the squad and came on as a substitute in Liverpool\'s 2-1 win at West Ham on Sunday. Toure may face his former team this weekend when Liverpool face Manchester City in a huge showdown at Anfield. Unveiling: Toure joined Philippe Coutinho, Jordan Henderson, Simon Mignolet at the launch event In action: Toure returned to the team as a substitute during Liverpool\'s win over West Ham on Sunday    More... Liverpool launch new kit for next season... but will Suarez and Co be wearing it as Premier League champions? Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS than Etihad stars Sturridge: I would be on City bench had I stayed there... all their players are big buys Rodgers: Mind guru Peters is here to stay after key role in Liverpool\'s title charge All the latest Liverpool news, features and opinion  Read more: The Redmen TV Share or comment on this article 4.3kshares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Graeme+Yorke\" rel=\"nofollow\">Graeme Yorke</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 07:15 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 13:09 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 4,330</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">29</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Kolo Toure seems to be a fan of his song, at least if Liverpool\'s new kit launch was anything to go by.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Ivorian defender was all smiles as he led a chorus of the Kolo Toure song on stage in Liverpool city centre.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Toure joined Philippe Coutinho, Jordan Henderson and Simon Mignolet in Liverpool One to help launch the new red home strip that the Premier League leaders will wear next season.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3456018271001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit release</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D06D45200000578-315_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Click <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/WeAreTheRedmen\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> to check out more Liverpool-related content from The Redmen TV</b><br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Chorus: Kolo Toure sang his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit launch on Thursday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"320\" id=\"i-a46c0e3f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602412-1D07328000000578-658_634x320.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Chorus: Kolo Toure sang his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit launch on Thursday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 33-year-old arrived at Liverpool on a free transfer from Manchester City in the summer.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">After a number of mistakes, Toure was dropped from the first team, but he returned to the squad and came on as a substitute in Liverpool\'s 2-1 win at West Ham on Sunday.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Toure may face his former team this weekend when Liverpool face Manchester City in a huge showdown at Anfield.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Unveiling: Toure joined Philippe Coutinho, Jordan Henderson, Simon Mignolet at the launch event\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"472\" id=\"i-a5bc0e53\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602412-1D01159A00000578-657_634x472.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Unveiling: Toure joined Philippe Coutinho, Jordan Henderson, Simon Mignolet at the launch event</p> </div><p> </p> <img alt=\"In action: Toure returned to the team as a substitute during Liverpool\'s win over West Ham on Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"565\" id=\"i-a9070e6b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602412-1CE2DD0300000578-223_634x565.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">In action: Toure returned to the team as a substitute during Liverpool\'s win over West Ham on Sunday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601586/Liverpool-launch-new-kit-season-Luis-Suarez-Steven-wearing-Premier-League-champions.html\"> Liverpool launch new kit for next season... but will Suarez and Co be wearing it as Premier League champions?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\"> Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS than Etihad stars</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602237/Daniel-Sturridge-I-Manchester-City-bench-I-stayed-players-big-buys.html\"> Sturridge: I would be on City bench had I stayed there... all their players are big buys</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602011/Rodgers-Mind-guru-Peters-stay-key-role-Liverpools-title-charge.html\"> Rodgers: Mind guru Peters is here to stay after key role in Liverpool\'s title charge</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/liverpool.html\"> All the latest Liverpool news, features and opinion</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"item\" data-track-module=\"am-external-links^external-links\" id=\"external-source-links\"> <span>Read more:</span> <ul> <li><a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/WeAreTheRedmen\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">The Redmen TV</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602412/Kolo-Toure-sings-song-Liverpools-new-kit-launch.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new Warrior kit launch\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602412/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">4.3k</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602412-1D07328000000578-167_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:24','2014-04-11 20:09:41'),(75,'dbd1edbb4a600fb937f0e913d2c694f16ce523c2b0b168edbd2788d28e6caa38','dailymail',NULL,'FA charge Crawley defender Paul Connolly with violent conduct for slapping Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html',' By James Andrew Follow @@JamesAndrew_ Published: 10:58 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 12:49 EST, 11 April 2014 19 shares 0 View comments  Crawley defender Paul Connolly faces a lengthy ban after being charged with violent conduct by The FA. The charge relates to an incident during his side’s 1-0 defeat to Brentford on Tuesday where the defender appeared to hit a fan. The incident happened late in the game when the ball went out for a throw in into the crowd.   Aggravation: Crawley\'s Paul Connolly (29) is clearly angered by something shouted from the crowd   Cheap shot: Connelly takes a swing at a fan during Brentford\'s 1-0 League One win   Shock: Fans look outraged as stewards split up the altercation and Connelly walks away   Flashpoint: Connolly walks away from the crowd after an altercation with a fan  Connolly appeared to lose his cool and squared up to a fan, who threw the ball back forcefully, before appearing to swing his right arm at the supporter. Stewards were quickly on the scene and diffused the situation but referee Steve Martin nor any of his officials took any action but the incident was caught on video. Connolly said on Twitter on Friday afternoon: ‘Everyone\'s had there say. I did NOT slap/punch the fan. I reacted wrongly but was hugely provoked all game. I\'ll wait for the FA decision. ‘No more to be said at the moment.’ The FA believe Connolly should receive more than the standard three game ban due to the severity of the incident.   More... Crawley defender Connolly faces a ban after SLAPPING Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park Crawley defender Connolly SLAPS Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park Cardiff believe they have \'concrete evidence\' that at least three members of staff were involved in Palace spying scandal EXCLUSIVE: Police in Leeds theft probe - new owner Cellino calls in cops after secret spy cameras found in Elland Road boardroom... and toilets! Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records Official line: Connolly is spoken to by the match referee as stewards step in   Investigation: The Crawley man could find himself in trouble after the incident  Last-gasp: Sheffield United celebrate Ben Davies\' last minute winner against Rotherham  In a statement, The FA said: ‘The FA has submitted that the standard punishment of a three-match suspension would be clearly insufficient given the nature of the offence.’ After the match Connolly tried to play down the incident by taking to Twitter to say: ‘A total blown up incident at the game last night! Handbags! We move on.’ Connolly has until 6pm on April 11 to respond to the charge.     More... Crawley defender Connolly faces a ban after SLAPPING Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park Crawley defender Connolly SLAPS Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park Cardiff believe they have \'concrete evidence\' that at least three members of staff were involved in Palace spying scandal EXCLUSIVE: Police in Leeds theft probe - new owner Cellino calls in cops after secret spy cameras found in Elland Road boardroom... and toilets! Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records  Share or comment on this article 19shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=James+Andrew\" rel=\"nofollow\">James Andrew</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@JamesAndrew_\">Follow @@JamesAndrew_</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 10:58 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:49 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"FA charge Crawley defender Connolly with violent conduct for slapping Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 19</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Crawley defender Paul Connolly faces a lengthy ban after being charged with violent conduct by The FA.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The charge relates to an incident during his side’s 1-0 defeat to Brentford on Tuesday where the defender appeared to hit a fan.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The incident happened late in the game when the ball went out for a throw in into the crowd.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\"></span></font></span></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Aggravation: Crawley\'s Paul Connolly (29) is clearly angered by something shouted from the crowd\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"372\" id=\"i-a9b10e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600128-1CF50B2700000578-772_634x372.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Aggravation: Crawley\'s Paul Connolly (29) is clearly angered by something shouted from the crowd</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Cheap shot: Connelly takes a swing at a fan during Brentford\'s 1-0 League One win\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"379\" id=\"i-aba40e89\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600128-1CF50AF200000578-986_634x379.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Cheap shot: Connelly takes a swing at a fan during Brentford\'s 1-0 League One win</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Shock: Fans look outraged as stewards split up the altercation and Connelly walks away\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"365\" id=\"i-91700e1e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600128-1CF50BBA00000578-5_634x365.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Shock: Fans look outraged as stewards split up the altercation and Connelly walks away</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Flashpoint: Connolly walks away from the crowd after an altercation with a fan\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"412\" id=\"i-ab3c0e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2600128-1CF1D57A00000578-862_634x412.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Flashpoint: Connolly walks away from the crowd after an altercation with a fan</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Connolly appeared to lose his cool and squared up to a fan, who threw the ball back forcefully, before appearing to swing his right arm at the supporter.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Stewards were quickly on the scene and diffused the situation but referee Steve Martin nor any of his officials took any action but the incident was caught on video.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Connolly said on Twitter on Friday afternoon: ‘Everyone\'s had there say. I did NOT slap/punch the fan. I reacted wrongly but was hugely provoked all game. I\'ll wait for the FA decision. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘No more to be said at the moment.’<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The FA believe Connolly should receive more than the standard three game ban due to the severity of the incident. </font><br/></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600577/Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-faces-ban-SLAPPING-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\"> Crawley defender Connolly faces a ban after SLAPPING Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600128/Crawley-defender-Connolly-SLAPS-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\"> Crawley defender Connolly SLAPS Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html\"> Cardiff believe they have \'concrete evidence\' that at least three members of staff were involved in Palace spying scandal</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602519/EXCLUSIVE-Police-Leeds-theft-probe-new-owner-Cellino-calls-cops-secret-spy-cameras-Elland-Road-boardroom-toilets.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Police in Leeds theft probe - new owner Cellino calls in cops after secret spy cameras found in Elland Road boardroom... and toilets!</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602487/Cardiff-sack-member-staff-Palace-spying-scandal-check-phone-records.html\"> Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Official line: Connolly is spoken to by the match referee as stewards step in\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"432\" id=\"i-aae30e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2600128-1CF1D5A200000578-791_634x432.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Official line: Connolly is spoken to by the match referee as stewards step in</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Investigation: The Crawley man could find himself in trouble after the incident\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"377\" id=\"i-aac80e7c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2600128-1CF1D59900000578-375_634x377.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Investigation: The Crawley man could find himself in trouble after the incident</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Last-gasp: Sheffield United celebrate Ben Davies\' last minute winner against Rotherham\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"434\" id=\"i-a9410e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2600128-1CF204B200000578-799_634x434.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Last-gasp: Sheffield United celebrate Ben Davies\' last minute winner against Rotherham</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In a statement, The FA said: ‘The FA has submitted that the standard punishment of a three-match suspension would be clearly insufficient given the nature of the offence.’<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">After the match Connolly tried to play down the incident by taking to Twitter to say: ‘A total blown up incident at the game last night! Handbags! We move on.’<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Connolly has until 6pm on April 11 to respond to the charge.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600577/Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-faces-ban-SLAPPING-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\"> Crawley defender Connolly faces a ban after SLAPPING Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600128/Crawley-defender-Connolly-SLAPS-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\"> Crawley defender Connolly SLAPS Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602600/Cardiff-City-believe-concrete-evidence-three-members-staff-involved-Palace-spying-scandal.html\"> Cardiff believe they have \'concrete evidence\' that at least three members of staff were involved in Palace spying scandal</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602519/EXCLUSIVE-Police-Leeds-theft-probe-new-owner-Cellino-calls-cops-secret-spy-cameras-Elland-Road-boardroom-toilets.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Police in Leeds theft probe - new owner Cellino calls in cops after secret spy cameras found in Elland Road boardroom... and toilets!</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602487/Cardiff-sack-member-staff-Palace-spying-scandal-check-phone-records.html\"> Cardiff sack member of staff over Palace spying scandal after check of phone records</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602608/FA-charge-Crawley-defender-Paul-Connolly-violent-conduct-slapping-Brentford-fan-defeat-Griffin-Park.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"FA charge Crawley defender Connolly with violent conduct for slapping Brentford fan during defeat at Griffin Park\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602608/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">19</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2600128-1CF206EC00000578-925_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:25','2014-04-11 19:49:53'),(76,'a24913e8926068da9c155e7f1f1880a333ba40c535abfbb51e1c7fd208e8faa3','dailymail',NULL,'EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html',' By Sami Mokbel Follow @@SamiMokbel81_DM Published: 11:42 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 12:00 EST, 11 April 2014 49 shares 79 View comments  Manchester City have sacked head of academy coaching Scott Sellars as the Barclays Premier League club continue revamping their youth-set up. The former Blackburn and Newcastle player joined the club in 2009 under then football administrator Brian Marwood. But in a difference of footballing opinion with the current regime, led by sporting director Txiki Begiristain, Sellars has had his employment terminated.  Axed: Manchester City have got rid of Scott Sellars (right), with Paul Power, for a lack of emerging English talent   Homegrown: City have fears over a lack of homegrown talent like Micah Richards, in training    More... Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Mangala struggles for Porto as Man City target is given a going over by Sevilla His sacking comes in light of the club\'s fears they could struggle to fill their homegrown players quota next season - news revealed by Sportsmail last week. The club will now begin the search for a new man to fill the role vacated by Sellars ahead of next season. City are pumping significant funds into their academy set-up to ensure they can produce their own talent in years to come. Work has started on a new state-of-the-art academy set-up, which will include a 7,000 seater stadium for youth games and 16 pitches.  Foreign legion: Much of City\'s top talent, like Edin Dzeko (left) and David Silva, is from overseas   More... Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? Mangala struggles for Porto as Man City target is given a going over by Sevilla    Share or comment on this article 49shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Sami+Mokbel\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sami Mokbel</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@SamiMokbel81_DM\">Follow @@SamiMokbel81_DM</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:42 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 12:00 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"EXCLUSIVE: Sellars axed from Man City academy role as fears over homegrown quota grow\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 49</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602639/EXCLUSIVE-City-axe-academy-chief-Sellars-fears-homegrown-quota-grow.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">79</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Manchester City have sacked head of academy coaching Scott Sellars as the Barclays Premier League club continue revamping their youth-set up.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The former Blackburn and Newcastle player joined the club in 2009 under then football administrator Brian Marwood.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But in a difference of footballing opinion with the current regime, led by sporting director Txiki Begiristain, Sellars has had his employment terminated.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Axed: Manchester City have got rid of Scott Sellars (right), with Paul Power, for a lack of emerging English talent\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"412\" id=\"i-a6440e4e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602639-1D09306700000578-268_634x412.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Axed: Manchester City have got rid of Scott Sellars (right), with Paul Power, for a lack of emerging English talent</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Homegrown: City have fears over a lack of homegrown talent like Micah Richards, in training\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-ac330e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602639-1CBE2DA700000578-302_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Homegrown: City have fears over a lack of homegrown talent like Micah Richards, in training</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to \'unleash\' Liverpool fans on Manchester City in crunch title clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601458/LIVERPOOL-vs-MANCHESTER-CITY-All-latest-team-news-stats-crunch-battle-race-Premier-League-title.html\"> LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602389/Aguero-fit-Liverpool-clash-City-striker-recovers-hamstring-injury.html\"> Pellegrini turns tables on Rodgers as he insists Liverpool boss is under pressure</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602353/Porto-sword-Sevilla-Manchester-City-target-Eliaquim-Mangala-endures-testing-evening.html\"> Mangala struggles for Porto as Man City target is given a going over by Sevilla</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">His sacking comes in light of the club\'s fears they could struggle to fill their homegrown players quota next season - news revealed by<i> Sportsmail </i>last week.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The club will now begin the search for a new man to fill the role vacated by Sellars ahead of next season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">City are pumping significant funds into their academy set-up to ensure they can produce their own talent in years to come.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Work has started on a new state-of-the-art academy set-up, which will include a 7,000 seater stadium for youth games and 16 pitches.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Foreign legion: Much of City\'s top talent, like Edin Dzeko (left) and David Silva, is from overseas\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"506\" id=\"i-abf50e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602639-1CACAC1800000578-312_634x506.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Foreign legion: Much of City\'s top talent, like Edin Dzeko (left) and David Silva, is from overseas</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602549/Rodgers-vows-unleash-Liverpool-fans-Manchester-City-crunch-title-clash.html\"> Rodgers vows to