.</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601877/David-Moyes-faces-uncertain-future-10-Manchester-United-stars-heading-exit.html\"> Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html\"> We went for Fergie! Newcastle tried to sign United great after Keegan, admits Shepherd</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602249/Chelsea-play-Atletico-Madrid-Champions-League-semi-finals.html\"> Chelsea land Atletico Madrid in semi-finals of the Champions League</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598043/Liverpool-vs-Man-City-THE-match-decide-destination-Premier-League-title.html\"> Liverpool vs Man City is THE match to decide destination of the Premier League title... but will it live up to these classics?</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#s2013-c5-m749266\"> MATCH ZONE: Bayern Munich 3-1 (Agg: 4-2) Manchester United</a></li> </ul> </div> <br/></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The England pair were joined by winger Ashley Young, according to the Manchester Evening News, for the night which started at a popular nightspot called Neighbourhood before moving on to Sakura at the city\'s Deansgate Locks.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Welbeck was replaced after 81 minutes by Adnan Januzaj at the Allianz Arena. Young was an unused substitute but Cleverley was not part of the quarter-final, second leg squad. United lost 3-1 on the night despite Patrice Evra\'s thunderbolt opener.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Eyewitnesses report Young getting into a taxi before Welbeck emerged from the rear entrance of Sakura</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3308528869001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">David Moyes makes a passionate defence of Tom Cleverley</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/03/07/video-undefined-1C1CEE5E00000578-480_636x365.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Taxi! United midfielder Cleverley jigs around a mini-cab as a girl looks to leave the Deansgate Locks area\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"551\" id=\"i-a8570e6a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602434-1D0732FB00000578-749_634x551.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Taxi! United midfielder Cleverley jigs around a mini-cab as a girl looks to leave the Deansgate Locks area</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Good night: Cleverley bids the girl farewell after his night out with Welbeck and Ashley Young. Young had left the club earlier in a taxi\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"546\" id=\"i-a7340e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602434-1D0732B900000578-966_634x546.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Good night: Cleverley bids the girl farewell after his night out with Welbeck and Ashley Young. Young had left the club earlier in a taxi</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Street party: Welbeck (hidden, back right) and his friends were in boisterous mood despite United\'s Euro exit\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"463\" id=\"i-a5600e4b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602434-1D07357300000578-446_634x463.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Street party: Welbeck (hidden, back right) and his friends were in boisterous mood despite United\'s Euro exit</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Tom Cleverley\'s fiance Georgina Dorsett\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a62e0e4e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602434-1D0902C500000578-915_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Georgina Dorsett out in Cheshire on Friday afternoon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-b1a70e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602434-1D09017900000578-1000_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Other half: Tom Cleverley\'s fiance Georgina Dorsett photographed out in Cheshire on Friday afternoon<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He was then joined by Cleverley and the pair were both seen dancing in front of friends.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">One onlooker told the MEN: \'It is amazing. They were laughing and dancing and looked to be having a real good night.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'It is surprising after their defeat on Wednesday but it looked like they had fun.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">There is no suggestion that the players had broken any club curfew</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> as there is no first-team match for more than a week.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Manchester United declined to comment on the situation.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Getting stuck in: Welbeck challenges Bayern Munich\'s Thomas Muller (right) during Wednesday\'s clash\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"858\" id=\"i-aa6c0e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602434-1CF90A1F00000578-275_634x858.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Getting stuck in: Welbeck challenges Bayern Munich\'s Thomas Muller (right) during Wednesday\'s clash</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601877/David-Moyes-faces-uncertain-future-10-Manchester-United-stars-heading-exit.html\"> Moyes faces uncertain future... with up to 10 United stars heading for Old Trafford exit</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html\"> We went for Fergie! Newcastle tried to sign United great after Keegan, admits Shepherd</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602249/Chelsea-play-Atletico-Madrid-Champions-League-semi-finals.html\"> Chelsea land Atletico Madrid in semi-finals of the Champions League</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598043/Liverpool-vs-Man-City-THE-match-decide-destination-Premier-League-title.html\"> Liverpool vs Man City is THE match to decide destination of the Premier League title... but will it live up to these classics?</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#s2013-c5-m749266\"> MATCH ZONE: Bayern Munich 3-1 (Agg: 4-2) Manchester United</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602434/Welbeck-Cleverley-seen-dancing-street-early-hours-The-day-United-crashed-Champions-League.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602434/Welbeck-Cleverley-seen-dancing-street-early-hours-The-day-United-crashed-Champions-League.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Welbeck and Cleverley pictured dancing in the street... hours after returning from United\'s Champions League exit\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602434/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">1.4k</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D07330D00000578-791_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:26','2014-04-11 18:25:54'),(78,'44855d1c8917489a23f3e8daf23b96e3e51b4b0e33682aaaaf2ea8cc1555f175','dailymail',NULL,'IN THE SPOTLIGHT: Paco Alcacer, the Valencia hat-trick hero who could solve Arsenal\'s goalscoring problems','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602445/IN-THE-SPOTLIGHT-Paco-Alcacer-Valencia-hat-trick-hero-solve-Arsenals-goalscoring-problems.html',' By In the Spotlight Published: 07:58 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 11:08 EST, 11 April 2014 14 shares 18 View comments Sportsmail gives you the lowdown on the best emerging talent breaking through at football clubs throughout Europe. Here, PETE JENSON take a look at Paco Alcacer, the youngster who scored a crucial hat-trick for Valencia on Thursday night.  So, who is this guy I’m hearing whispers about? Name: Paco Alcacer Club: Valencia Age: 20 Position: Striker How long has he been on Arsenal’s radar? Top European clubs started looking at Alcacer in 2010 when he top scored in the U17 Euros with six goals for Spain. He was free-scoring 16 year-old in Valencia’s youth academy at the time. He got 14 goals in total in that tournament including qualifying. VIDEO: Scroll down to watch Alcacer score one of his hat-trick goals against Basle  Potential: Paco Alcacer is a target for Arsenal after his fine recent displays for Valencia   Delight: The Spanish striker scored a hat-trick for Valencia against Basle in the Europa League on Thursday   More... Europa League round-up: Valencia complete stunning comeback, while Juventus, Sevilla and Benfica seal semi-final berths Arsenal keep tabs on Valencia striker Alcacer as Wenger plans summer spending Drmic to be scouted by Allardyce this weekend as Hammers boss eyes Arsenal target in quest for more firepower Arsenal players ready to stick together for FA Cup battle against Wigan as the pressure mounts on Wenger WIGAN vs ARSENAL: All the latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final What happened next? His international career continued to go from strength to strength. He got three goals for the U19s as they won the Euros in Romania in 2011, scoring twice in the final against the Czech Republic and a year later he repeated the feat scoring this time in the semi-final against France. And his club form? He was farmed out to Getafe on loan in 2012 but with it written into his contract that he had to play 20 games. It was tough going at their tumbleweed stadium, watched by just two or three thousand supporters in a flat mid-table season he scored just four goals, but still showed enough promise to be recalled and pushed up to the first team this season. He has repaid that faith with 14 goals and that hat-trick to put Valencia in the Europa League semis. What are his key strengths? He is a finisher first and foremost. Quick, strong and clever enough to get in front defenders and get on the end of crosses in the six-yard box. Likes to finish with a first touch as he did to get the winner against Barcelona at the Camp Nou earlier in this year but also has the quick feet to make room for himself in the penalty area.  Composed: Alcacer is a finisher first and foremost, and may be an improvement on Olivier Giroud (below)     So he’s a No 9? He’s technically good with the touch to play with his back to goal and hold the ball up for midfielders to join so he can play in deeper areas but he is at his best when he is getting away from defenders inside the penalty area. Does he create as well as score? Loves to peel off to the right and cross for a team-mate. Not a selfish player despite his goals return – has linked brilliantly with Gerard Deulofeu (now at Everton on loan) and Real Madrid’s Jese, at Spanish youth level. And his character? Has leadership quality. Led the U17s. Takes responsibility be that with the armband or by being the player who takes penalties.  All-round game: He possesses fine technique, and has the ability to set up others as well     But he’s not the biggest… too small for the Premier League? At just under 5ft 9in he won’t be climbing above Vicent Kompany. But he does leap very well and like a lot of good smaller strikers he hangs in the air for that extra half-second to make good contact with the ball. What will it cost to get him out of Valencia? More than it would have done in last transfer window. Goals against Barcelona and Basle have seen to that. Valencia like to fatten the calf before they slaughter it so they will want him to stay next season before selling him for a big price. But his current contract runs out in 2016 and his buy out clause is set at £15m, so a bid this summer which comes close to that might see him leave the Mestalla and head for London. VIDEO: Watch Alcacer score one of his hat-trick goals against Basle   Character: He has captained Spain at youth level, and is a fine example for others    More... Europa League round-up: Valencia complete stunning comeback, while Juventus, Sevilla and Benfica seal semi-final berths Arsenal keep tabs on Valencia striker Alcacer as Wenger plans summer spending Drmic to be scouted by Allardyce this weekend as Hammers boss eyes Arsenal target in quest for more firepower Arsenal players ready to stick together for FA Cup battle against Wigan as the pressure mounts on Wenger WIGAN vs ARSENAL: All the latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final   Share or comment on this article 14shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1090736/In-the-Spotlight.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">In the Spotlight</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 07:58 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 11:08 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602445/IN-THE-SPOTLIGHT-Paco-Alcacer-Valencia-hat-trick-hero-solve-Arsenals-goalscoring-problems.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602445/IN-THE-SPOTLIGHT-Paco-Alcacer-Valencia-hat-trick-hero-solve-Arsenals-goalscoring-problems.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"IN THE SPOTLIGHT: Paco Alcacer, the Valencia hat-trick hero who could solve Arsenal\'s goalscoring problems\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 14</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602445/IN-THE-SPOTLIGHT-Paco-Alcacer-Valencia-hat-trick-hero-solve-Arsenals-goalscoring-problems.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">18</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Sportsmail gives you the lowdown on the best emerging talent breaking through at football clubs throughout Europe. Here, <i><b>PETE JENSON</b></i> take a look at Paco Alcacer, the youngster who scored a crucial hat-trick for Valencia on Thursday night.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>So, who is this guy I’m hearing whispers about?</b><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Name: Paco Alcacer<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Club: Valencia<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Age: 20<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Position: Striker<br/></font></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">How long has he been on Arsenal’s radar?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Top European clubs started looking at Alcacer in 2010 when he top scored in the U17 Euros with six goals for Spain. He was free-scoring 16 year-old in Valencia’s youth academy at the time. He got 14 goals in total in that tournament including qualifying.</font></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">VIDEO:</span></span> Scroll down to watch Alcacer score one of his hat-trick goals against Basle</font></span></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Potential: Paco Alcacer is a target for Arsenal after his fine recent displays for Valencia\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-59cf0d1a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D020D6500000578-248_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Potential: Paco Alcacer is a target for Arsenal after his fine recent displays for Valencia</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Delight: The Spanish striker scored a hat-trick for Valencia against Basle in the Europa League on Thursday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"473\" id=\"i-5cc30d3b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D01F69F00000578-177_634x473.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Delight: The Spanish striker scored a hat-trick for Valencia against Basle in the Europa League on Thursday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601995/Europa-League-round-Valencia-complete-stunning-comeback-Juventus-Sevilla-Benfica-seal-semi-final-berths.html\"> Europa League round-up: Valencia complete stunning comeback, while Juventus, Sevilla and Benfica seal semi-final berths</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2580068/Arsenal-tabs-Valencia-striker-Francisco-Alcacer-Arsene-Wenger-plans-summer-spending.html\"> Arsenal keep tabs on Valencia striker Alcacer as Wenger plans summer spending</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602357/Sam-Allardyce-fly-Germany-weekend-watch-Arsenal-target-Drmic-West-Ham-boss-seeks-added-firepower.html\"> Drmic to be scouted by Allardyce this weekend as Hammers boss eyes Arsenal target in quest for more firepower</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602422/Arsenal-prepare-FA-Cup-battle-against-Wigan-pressure-firmly-Arsene-Wenger.html\"> Arsenal players ready to stick together for FA Cup battle against Wigan as the pressure mounts on Wenger</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601446/WIGAN-vs-ARSENAL-All-latest-team-news-stats-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> WIGAN vs ARSENAL: All the latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">What happened next?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">His international career continued to go from strength to strength. He got three goals for the U19s as they won the Euros in Romania in 2011, scoring twice in the final against the Czech Republic and a year later he repeated the feat scoring this time in the semi-final against France.</font><br/></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And his club form?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He was farmed out to Getafe on loan in 2012 but with it written into his contract that he had to play 20 games. It was tough going at their tumbleweed stadium, watched by just two or three thousand supporters in a flat mid-table season he scored just four goals, but still showed enough promise to be recalled and pushed up to the first team this season. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He has repaid that faith with 14 goals and that hat-trick to put Valencia in the Europa League semis.</font><br/></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">What are his key strengths?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He is a finisher first and foremost. Quick, strong and clever enough to get in front defenders and get on the end of crosses in the six-yard box. Likes to finish with a first touch as he did to get the winner against Barcelona at the Camp Nou earlier in this year but also has the quick feet to make room for himself in the penalty area. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Composed: Alcacer is a finisher first and foremost, and may be an improvement on Olivier Giroud (below)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a7a30e5e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602445-1D01CB0500000578-548_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Composed: Alcacer is a finisher first and foremost, and may be an improvement on Olivier Giroud (below)</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Composed: Alcacer is a finisher first and foremost, and may be an improvement on Olivier Giroud (below)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"474\" id=\"i-a7370e5f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602445-1D070F9000000578-368_634x474.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">So he’s a No 9?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He’s technically good with the touch to play with his back to goal and hold the ball up for midfielders to join so he can play in deeper areas but he is at his best when he is getting away from defenders inside the penalty area.</font><br/></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Does he create as well as score?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Loves to peel off to the right and cross for a team-mate. Not a selfish player despite his goals return – has linked brilliantly with Gerard Deulofeu (now at Everton on loan) and Real Madrid’s Jese, at Spanish youth level.</font><br/></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And his character?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Has leadership quality. Led the U17s. Takes responsibility be that with the armband or by being the player who takes penalties.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All-round game: He possesses fine technique, and has the ability to set up others as well\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"514\" id=\"i-a6430e4e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602445-1D018F1200000578-414_634x514.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All-round game: He possesses fine technique, and has the ability to set up others as well</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All-round game: He possesses fine technique, and has the ability to set up others as well\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-a6440e54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602445-1D07758300000578-843_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But he’s not the biggest… too small for the Premier League?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">At just under 5ft 9in he won’t be climbing above Vicent Kompany. But he does leap very well and like a lot of good smaller strikers he hangs in the air for that extra half-second to make good contact with the ball. </font><br/></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">What will it cost to get him out of Valencia?</font></b><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">More than it would have done in last transfer window. Goals against Barcelona and Basle have seen to that. Valencia like to fatten the calf before they slaughter it so they will want him to stay next season before selling him for a big price. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But his current contract runs out in 2016 and his buy out clause is set at £15m, so a bid this summer which comes close to that might see him leave the Mestalla and head for London.</font></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">VIDEO:</span></span> Watch Alcacer score one of his hat-trick goals against Basle</font></span></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Rbv9yPv7qx0\" width=\"640\"></iframe><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Character: He has captained Spain at youth level, and is a fine example for others\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"380\" id=\"i-acb20e89\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602445-1CF5FFC400000578-305_634x380.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Character: He has captained Spain at youth level, and is a fine example for others</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601995/Europa-League-round-Valencia-complete-stunning-comeback-Juventus-Sevilla-Benfica-seal-semi-final-berths.html\"> Europa League round-up: Valencia complete stunning comeback, while Juventus, Sevilla and Benfica seal semi-final berths</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2580068/Arsenal-tabs-Valencia-striker-Francisco-Alcacer-Arsene-Wenger-plans-summer-spending.html\"> Arsenal keep tabs on Valencia striker Alcacer as Wenger plans summer spending</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602357/Sam-Allardyce-fly-Germany-weekend-watch-Arsenal-target-Drmic-West-Ham-boss-seeks-added-firepower.html\"> Drmic to be scouted by Allardyce this weekend as Hammers boss eyes Arsenal target in quest for more firepower</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602422/Arsenal-prepare-FA-Cup-battle-against-Wigan-pressure-firmly-Arsene-Wenger.html\"> Arsenal players ready to stick together for FA Cup battle against Wigan as the pressure mounts on Wenger</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601446/WIGAN-vs-ARSENAL-All-latest-team-news-stats-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> WIGAN vs ARSENAL: All the latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602445/IN-THE-SPOTLIGHT-Paco-Alcacer-Valencia-hat-trick-hero-solve-Arsenals-goalscoring-problems.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602445/IN-THE-SPOTLIGHT-Paco-Alcacer-Valencia-hat-trick-hero-solve-Arsenals-goalscoring-problems.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"IN THE SPOTLIGHT: Paco Alcacer, the Valencia hat-trick hero who could solve Arsenal\'s goalscoring problems\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602445/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">14</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602445-1D020D6500000578-767_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:26','2014-04-11 18:08:54'),(79,'0f558dcd501cf297f7c862f979fc39e9cf6bd7af7e853d069c8092b1e9df6523','dailymail',NULL,'Chelsea vs Sunderland Premier League game moved to Saturday 19 April','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602512/Chelsea-V-Sunderland-Premier-League-game-moved-Saturday-19-April.html',' Chelsea v Sunderland moved from Sunday 20 April to Saturday 19 AprilGame will kick off at 5.30pm and remain on Sky SportsHull v Arsenal shifted from Saturday 19 April to Sunday 20 AprilMove allows Chelsea more time to prepare for Champions League semiChelsea travel to Atletico Madrid for first leg on Tuesday 22 AprilSecond leg of tie at Stamford Bridge on Wednesday 30 AprilLiverpool v Chelsea on Sunday 27 April unaffected By Craig Hope Follow @@CraigHope01 Published: 09:32 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 10:17 EST, 11 April 2014 95 shares 64 View comments Chelsea\'s Premier League game against Sunderland has been moved forward by one day to help Jose Mourinho\'s quest for Champions League glory. The Blues were drawn to play Atletico Madrid in the semi-final of the competition with the first leg scheduled for Tuesday, April 22 in the Spanish capital. That match was scheduled to take place just 48 hours after Chelsea\'s home game with Sunderland.  Euro march: Chelsea will be given more time to prepare for their Champions League tie at Atletico   Swap: Chelsea will now face Sunderland on Saturday April 19, a day earlier than scheduled But the Premier League has now confirmed that the fixture has been brought forward to Saturday tea-time and a 5.30pm kick-off and will be shown live on Sky Sports.Hull City versus Arsenal will now take place on Sunday, April 20 with kick-off at 2.05pm and will also be shown live on Sky Sports.The move affords Chelsea an extra day to prepare for their trip to Spain. The return leg at Stamford Bridge on Wednesday, April 30 comes three days after Chelsea\'s away fixture at Liverpool. On the road: Arsenal\'s visit to Hull has been pushed back a day to Sunday 20 April Still standing: Chelsea drew Atletico Madrid in the last four of the Champions League    More... Courtois can play, but we want £5m OFF Costa price! Chelsea want to strike Atletico deal after UEFA block blues\' demands Chelsea land Atletico Madrid in semi-finals of the Champions League Courtois set to face Chelsea despite loan restrictions... will he knock out parent club just like Morientes did to Real 10 years ago? Chelsea chief Gourlay believes Chelsea can go on and win the double this season Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table? All the latest Chelsea news, features and opinion  Share or comment on this article 95shares','\n<ul class=\"article-summary sport\"><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Chelsea v Sunderland moved from Sunday 20 April to Saturday 19 April</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Game will kick off at 5.30pm and remain on Sky Sports<br/></font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Hull v Arsenal shifted from Saturday 19 April to Sunday 20 April</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Move allows Chelsea more time to prepare for Champions League semi</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Chelsea travel to Atletico Madrid for first leg on Tuesday 22 April</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Second leg of tie at Stamford Bridge on Wednesday 30 April</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Liverpool v Chelsea on Sunday 27 April unaffected<br/></font></b></li></ul>\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Craig+Hope\" rel=\"nofollow\">Craig Hope</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@CraigHope01\">Follow @@CraigHope01</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 09:32 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 10:17 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602512/Chelsea-V-Sunderland-Premier-League-game-moved-Saturday-19-April.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602512/Chelsea-V-Sunderland-Premier-League-game-moved-Saturday-19-April.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Chelsea\'s clash with Sunderland moved to help Blues prepare for Atletico trip\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 95</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602512/Chelsea-V-Sunderland-Premier-League-game-moved-Saturday-19-April.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">64</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Chelsea\'s Premier League game against Sunderland has been moved forward by one day to help Jose Mourinho\'s quest for Champions League glory.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Blues were drawn to play Atletico Madrid in the semi-final of the competition with the first leg scheduled for Tuesday, April 22 in the Spanish capital.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">That match was scheduled to take place just 48 hours after Chelsea\'s home game with Sunderland.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Euro march: Chelsea will be given more time to prepare for their Champions League tie at Atletico\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-a9eb0e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602512-1CF18C0E00000578-584_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Euro march: Chelsea will be given more time to prepare for their Champions League tie at Atletico</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Swap: Chelsea will now face Sunderland on Saturday April 19, a day earlier than scheduled\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"429\" id=\"i-aae90e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602512-1CDCBB0100000578-657_634x429.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Swap: Chelsea will now face Sunderland on Saturday April 19, a day earlier than scheduled</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But the Premier League has now confirmed that the fixture has been brought forward to Saturday tea-time and a 5.30pm kick-off and will be shown live on Sky Sports.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Hull City versus Arsenal will now take place on Sunday, April 20 with kick-off at 2.05pm and will also be shown live on Sky Sports.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The move affords Chelsea an extra day to prepare for their trip to Spain. </font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The return leg at Stamford Bridge on Wednesday, April 30 comes three days after Chelsea\'s away fixture at Liverpool.</font></p> <img alt=\"On the road: Arsenal\'s visit to Hull has been pushed back a day to Sunday 20 April\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"388\" id=\"i-a8920e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602512-1CE1F81300000578-159_634x388.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the road: Arsenal\'s visit to Hull has been pushed back a day to Sunday 20 April</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Still standing: Chelsea drew Atletico Madrid in the last four of the Champions League\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-a9d90e76\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602512-1D06FFB000000578-687_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Still standing: Chelsea drew Atletico Madrid in the last four of the Champions League</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602333/Courtois-CLEARED-play-against-Chelsea-UEFA-warns-Blues-5m-Atletico-demand-violate-rules.html\"> Courtois can play, but we want £5m OFF Costa price! Chelsea want to strike Atletico deal after UEFA block blues\' demands</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602249/Chelsea-play-Atletico-Madrid-Champions-League-semi-finals.html\"> Chelsea land Atletico Madrid in semi-finals of the Champions League</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602377/Thibaut-Courtois-gets-set-face-Chelsea-despite-loan-restrictions-knock-parent-club-just-like-Fernando-Morientes-did-10-years-ago.html\"> Courtois set to face Chelsea despite loan restrictions... will he knock out parent club just like Morientes did to Real 10 years ago?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602438/Chelsea-Champions-League-reaction.html\"> Chelsea chief Gourlay believes Chelsea can go on and win the double this season</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602289/Everton-near-Champions-League-without-loan-signings-table-proves.html\"> Everton would be nowhere near Champions League without loan stars like Lukaku... but where would your side be in the table?</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/chelsea.html\"> All the latest Chelsea news, features and opinion</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602512/Chelsea-V-Sunderland-Premier-League-game-moved-Saturday-19-April.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602512/Chelsea-V-Sunderland-Premier-League-game-moved-Saturday-19-April.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Chelsea\'s clash with Sunderland moved to help Blues prepare for Atletico trip\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602512/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">95</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602512-1CDCBB0100000578-60_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:26','2014-04-11 17:17:32'),(80,'2f2014c8696edf706d7d9c8f43b7b91b99b669d876db08e1fb9147a6756ebd21','dailymail',NULL,'Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html',' By Carl Markham Published: 06:53 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 10:08 EST, 11 April 2014 30 shares 58 View comments Luis Suarez may be chasing the Premier League\'s goalscoring record but he would happily sacrifice a Golden Boot for Champions League football with the Reds. The Uruguay striker, jointly named the top flight\'s player of the month for March with captain Steven Gerrard, has 29 goals in 28 matches - having been suspended for five league games at the start of the season. Andy Cole, in 1993-94, and Alan Shearer, in the following season, scored 34 in 40 and 42 games respectively, while the record for a 38-game Premier League campaign is 31 - achieved by Cristiano Ronaldo in 2008-09 and Shearer in 1995-96.  Team man: Liverpool striker Luis Suarez is on track to win the Golden Boot   Hard yards: Suarez takes on Aly Cissokho as Liverpool prepare for their encounter with Manchester City   No holding back: Suarez may be closing in on goal records but Lucas Leiva gives him no quarter at Melwood Listen in: Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers gives instruction to a concentrated Suarez on Friday Steve McManaman weighs in on Sturridge and Suarez  More... Luis \'the Hulk\' Suarez! Liverpool striker reveals daughter\'s love of superhero has inspired new celebration EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS than Etihad stars Sturridge: I would be on City bench had I stayed there... all their players are big buys Suarez has \'God\' on his side! Liverpool legend Fowler insists lethal striker deserves to win everything this season Suarez, Gerrard AND Rodgers clean up as Liverpool trio take Premier League manager and player of the month awards EXCLUSIVE: When Jamie met Yaya - \'Liverpool have been amazing. This game WILL decide the title\' With five matches remaining, both targets remain within his grasp but Suarez insists team success is more important than personal milestones - and that is the reason why he has not asked to take over spot-kick duty from Gerrard. \'If I wanted to do that I could ask Stevie if I could take a penalty, but I don\'t like that,\' he said. \'For myself it is more important that Liverpool finish in a good position. I try in every game to score because I am a striker. \'I love to make goals but for me if I could swap being top scorer or winning the Golden Boot for the team finishing in the top four that would be more important. \'Of course it would be special (to break the record). In the last few years I have tried to do my job as well as I can to help the team and the Liverpool supporters. \'To finish the season as top scorer or with a new record would be nice for me, for my family and for the Liverpool supporters because it\'s important for them to have a player who holds the record. \'But if I think back a few games, I didn\'t score (he was goalless for five games in February) but I kept trying my best on the pitch.\'  Goal machine: Suarez has scored 29 in 28 matches after missing five matches at the start of the season   Chasing legends: The Uruguay striker is on track to overtake records held by Alan Shearer and Cristiano Ronaldo   On the spot: Suarez\'s goal tally could be even greater if Steven Gerrard handed over penalty taking duties   Liverpool head into the weekend as Premier League leaders but face a crunch clash at home to title rivals Manchester City on Sunday as they look to extend their winning run to 10 successive matches. \'For some people, it\'s a surprise because in the Premier League it is difficult to win nine games in a row,\' Suarez told liverpoolfc.com.  \'But if we continue at this level, we\'ll play very well. \'The team know we\'ve had some really good performances in the last few weeks and we\'ll try to continue in this way.\' \'Our target was to finish in the top four and we\'ve won our last few games. \'We also know Chelsea and City dropped some points, so we\'re at the top of the league now and that\'s amazing for us. \'Now we can\'t stop because we have a really good chance.\'  Plotting: Brendan Rodgers and Steven Gerrard spent 30 minutes working on free-kicks at Melwood   Burst a valve: The manager and his captain are particular about how the ball is placed before it\'s struck   Ready to roll: Suarez and Rodgers watch on as Gerrard hits a stationary ball      More... Luis \'the Hulk\' Suarez! Liverpool striker reveals daughter\'s love of superhero has inspired new celebration EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS than Etihad stars Sturridge: I would be on City bench had I stayed there... all their players are big buys Suarez has \'God\' on his side! Liverpool legend Fowler insists lethal striker deserves to win everything this season Suarez, Gerrard AND Rodgers clean up as Liverpool trio take Premier League manager and player of the month awards EXCLUSIVE: When Jamie met Yaya - \'Liverpool have been amazing. This game WILL decide the title\' Seeing double: meet Luis Suarez\'s doppelganger Luis Suarez spoofs his bad rep in new advert  Share or comment on this article 30shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Carl+Markham\" rel=\"nofollow\">Carl Markham</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 06:53 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 10:08 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Suarez would give up Golden Boot for shot at Champions League glory with the Reds\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 30</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602409/Suarez-Golden-Boot-shot-Champions-League-glory-Reds.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">58</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Luis Suarez may be chasing the Premier League\'s goalscoring record but he would happily sacrifice a Golden Boot for Champions League football with the Reds.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Uruguay striker, jointly named the top flight\'s player of the month for March with captain Steven Gerrard, has 29 goals in 28 matches - having been suspended for five league games at the start of the season.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Andy Cole, in 1993-94, and Alan Shearer, in the following season, scored 34 in 40 and 42 games respectively, while the record for a 38-game Premier League campaign is 31 - achieved by Cristiano Ronaldo in 2008-09 and Shearer in 1995-96.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Team man: Liverpool striker Luis Suarez is on track to win the Golden Boot\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-5d3a0d3a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CFF508400000578-169_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Team man: Liverpool striker Luis Suarez is on track to win the Golden Boot</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Hard yards: Suarez takes on Aly Cissokho as Liverpool prepare for their encounter with Manchester City\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"381\"