f they need help I must be there.’</font></p></div></div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All smiles: Cellino, pictured with his band, believes Leeds can get to the Premier League in two years\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"402\" id=\"i-aa7e0e6f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1CFE438000000578-625_634x402.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All smiles: Cellino, pictured with his band, believes Leeds can get to the Premier League in two years</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rant: Cellino was recorded complaining about Leeds striker Noel Hunt\'s wages when a stranger called him up\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"506\" id=\"i-aa020e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1D0199DB00000578-409_634x506.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rant: Cellino was recorded complaining about Leeds striker Noel Hunt\'s wages when a stranger called him up</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Colourful character: Cellino is the guitar-playing, chain-smoking charmer who kept Leeds from administration\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"438\" id=\"i-ab7f0e85\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1CCC620A00000578-696_634x438.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Colourful character: Cellino is the guitar-playing, chain-smoking charmer who kept Leeds from administration</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">In football terms, he has proved his commitment to a club, but in 22 years at Cagliari, which is he now trying to sell, he has sacked 36 managers. He also sacked Leeds boss Brian McDermott in January before the club reinstated him because Cellino’s takeover had not actually gone through.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">All in all, it’s why the Football League were disappointed that he won an appeal against their decision to keep him out. Now he has arrived, one of the most controversial and bombastic figures in the British game. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Over the course of more than an hour, he delivers on the funny stuff but skirts around the gritty particulars. He talks about his first forays into this country, back in 1975, the year Leeds made it to the European Cup final.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I was a waiter in London, I did washing up. I came here when I was 18 years old and didn’t have any money. I came here, rock and roll, I was playing guitar but it wasn’t going to earn enough money so I had to wash plates and glasses. I worked in the Regent Palace Hotel in 1975 for eight months.’ </font></p>\n<div class=\"cleared art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Cellino on sacking McDermott in January... </b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'When I fired the coach at the beginning, not because it was his fault but because I was told so, I was worrying for Leeds to stay in the Championship. I still now, if you ask me what happened that night, I don’t know.\' </font><br/></p></div></div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Making a point: Leeds striker Ross McCormack (second right) celebrates after scoring earlier this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-ac1d0e85\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-18DD0AE700000578-853_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Making a point: Leeds striker Ross McCormack (second right) celebrates after scoring earlier this season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">In time he became the ‘King of Corn’, inheriting his father’s  successful agricultural company. How much is he worth? </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I have never been able to find out how much money I have. I can keep an engagement.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He is adamant he is not a criminal. ‘I’m not dishonest. I didn’t make any contraband, the boat belongs to an American company and I paid the tax in America. I’ve got nothing to hide. Today in Italy there is a big mess.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">There is also a fairly big one to clean up at Leeds, where they do not own the training ground or Elland Road, and whose 2012-13 losses were revealed this week to be £9.5m. The club are currently losing £1m a month, with staff and players deferring 35 per cent of their wages last month.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cellino has promised to settle the salaries this week. But buying back Elland Road, which is rented for more than £1m a year, is described as ‘a first priority’.</font></p>\n<div class=\"cleared art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Cellino on McDermott...</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘He is a good guy. Have you seen Brian in a match? What is he doing with the water? He drinks it every 10 seconds and he throws it to the floor, 420 times a match. Bang, he throws it down. When I see him I say, “Here is a bottle of water for the next game”.’</font><br/></p></div></div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Thumbs up: Cellino has made it his \'first priority\' to buy back the Championship club\'s Elland Road stadium\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-a8e70e69\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1D00D71D00000578-402_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Thumbs up: Cellino has made it his \'first priority\' to buy back the Championship club\'s Elland Road stadium</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">On the club’s worrying Football League financial fair play position, one of his associates says vaguely: ‘I think the losses this year will be substantial. We have reviewed it (FFP), but because of the way the (takeover) deal is structured, some of the expenses that create the losses are getting written off as part of the deal, so we should qualify for the FFP in 2014.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">For his part, Cellino had not read Leeds’ financial results for 2012-13, which were released the day we met. ‘Please, I am too weak,’ he said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He is more forthcoming on his plans. Gulf Finance House, from whom he bought a 75 per cent stake, retain 25 per cent but will likely be marginalised, as will Haigh. ‘They have not done a good job running Leeds,’ he says. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘The people who lose money at clubs don’t do it on purpose. But they don’t know that when you take a club you take fans, you take emotions - they are not just numbers. I’ve seen people crying after games - kids, mothers.’  </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"cleared art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Cellino on divisions of labour...</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'There is a big misunderstanding in my point of view between manager and coach. For me, the coach runs the team, the players. The coach has to look after the players and we have to make the team together. \"I like that player. Can we afford him?\" \"OK, let’s do it\".\' </font></p></div></div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Not just numbers: Cellino admits that actions by the owners can have an effect on supporter\'s emotions\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-9c7f0e39\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1D00D2AD00000578-42_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Not just numbers: Cellino admits that actions by the owners can have an effect on supporter\'s emotions\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a6b60e4c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1D00D26000000578-161_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Not just numbers: Cellino admits that actions by a club\'s owners can have an effect on supporters\' emotions<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He adds: ‘They were running the bus, now the bus is ours. The other driver is not my problem, he can sit on the bench, he can go fishing, it is not my problem. We run the bus.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Then there is McDermott. He’s lost eight of the past nine games. ‘A nice guy,’ Cellino says. But in Italy they call Cellino a mangiallenatori - a manager-eater. By his own admission he is hands-on.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I like to give Brian the chance to find out if it is good or not,’ he says. ‘If it is not good I have to change. I hope not.’ All being well, he says: ‘Season 2015-16, if we don’t go (to the Premier League) I failed.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With that, he’s off. His band - he is friends with members of KISS - will soon be playing in front of 25,000 in Sardinia. Before then he has to ‘get to work’ cleaning up Leeds and ‘involving the fans again’.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Whatever the outcome of all this, it will be some bus ride.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601787/Football-League-Cellino-green-light-Leeds-club-director.html\"> Football League give Cellino green light to take over Leeds and become club director</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600924/Zola-NOT-replace-McDermott-Leeds-Cellino-takes-charge-Elland-Road.html\"> Zola will NOT replace McDermott at Leeds as Cellino takes charge at Elland Road</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599997/Is-Cellino-predicting-score-New-Leeds-owner-joins-McDermott-dugout-Watford-clash.html\"> Is Cellino predicting the score? New Leeds owner joins McDermott in dugout before Watford clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599816/Italian-Cellino-given-ahead-35m-takeover-Leeds.html\"> Italian Cellino completes takeover at Leeds and promises to pay all unpaid wages</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598466/Massimo-Cellino-sacks-Diego-Lopez-Cagliari-coach-just-hours-sealing-Leeds-takeover.html\"> Cellino sacks Lopez as Cagliari coach just hours after sealing Leeds takeover</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2597913/Crooks-charter-Football-fears-worst-fraudster-Cellino-given-ahead-35m-takeover-Leeds.html\"> Crooks charter: Football fears the worst after fraudster Cellino is given go-ahead for £35m takeover at Leeds</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601889/Elland-Road-Highway-Hell-Guitar-player-dishwasher-convicted-fraudster-Sportsmail-meets-Cellino-man-wants-save-Leeds.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601889/Elland-Road-Highway-Hell-Guitar-player-dishwasher-convicted-fraudster-Sportsmail-meets-Cellino-man-wants-save-Leeds.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Elland Road is my Highway to Hell! Guitar player, dishwasher and convicted fraudster... Sportsmail meets Cellino, the man who wants to save Leeds\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601889/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">129</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601889-1D01B10500000578-279_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:28','2014-04-11 17:03:55'),(82,'b46601db0cd2c4c22246cc75434a87d48761747ce39f8aa25baea463e3cb545e','dailymail',NULL,'EXCLUSIVE: There may be little to separate Liverpool and City on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS than Etihad stars','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html',' By Craig Hope Follow @@CraigHope01 Published: 06:16 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 09:37 EST, 11 April 2014 103 shares 143 View comments Liverpool and Manchester City are the free-scoring rivals set to do battle in the race for the Premier League title. On the pitch there is little to separate the two teams and the victor from Sunday\'s showdown at Anfield will, in all likelihood, go on to be crowned champions. Off the pitch, however, we can exclusively reveal that Liverpool\'s title-chasing stars are being paid, on average, £2million per year LESS than what their City adversaries.  Gulf: Liverpool players such as Kolo Toure (right) are earning, on average, £2m per year less than their City rivals, including Yaya Toure (left)  More... Sturridge: I would be on City bench had I stayed there... all their players are big buys He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training Rodgers: Mind guru Peters is here to stay after key role in Liverpool\'s title charge Suarez has \'God\' on his side! Liverpool legend Fowler insists lethal striker deserves to win everything this season Richards to leave Manchester City at the end of the season... with Liverpool, West Ham and Newcastle keen Sheik Mansour has bankrolled City\'s emergence over the past six years, an unprecedented investment which has transformed the financial landscape of the English game. In turn, players such as Yaya Toure were rewarded with contracts worth £200,000 a week when they signed up for the Etihad revolution and City have continued to shell out more than any other club for the services of their players. Indeed, their average annual wage is a massive £5,337,944, equating to £102,653 per week. Such outlay means they pay their stars more than any other sporting club in the world, with Major League Baseball\'s New York Yankees a close second.  Investment: Sheik Mansour\'s money has taken Manchester City to a whole new level  But it is the contrast with Liverpool which is most striking. They pay their players an average of £3,403,783 per annum, that is £65,457 each week. A sizeable investment, yes, but when drawn in comparison to City it is proof that shrewd recruitment can pay dividends without breaking the bank. Liverpool, under the canny guidance of Brendan Rodgers and thanks to master marksmen Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge, have the destiny of the title in their own hands. Clean sweep: Brendan Rodgers (left) won Manager of the Month for March, while Steven Gerrard (centre) and Luis Suarez were named joint Player of the Month  Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit release Victory in each of their five remaining matches – first up, of course, is City – would see them regain their English crown some 23 years on from being dethroned. In turn, they would become the first side in the Premier League to come from a finish as low as seventh to lift the trophy. It is a common footballing adage that the higher the wage bill the higher the standing in the division; were that the case then City would be champions and Liverpool would be scrapping it out for the Europa League in fifth.  Glory days: Manchester City are looking to reclaim the Premier League crown they won in 2012  The Merseysiders, however, have turned the accounts on their head this season. For the £2m pay disparity ultimately matters not, the only number which counts is the points tally come May 11. To that end, three against their title rivals on Sunday is priceless. The full salary comparison tables will appear on www.sportingintelligence.com on Monday GOAL RUSHLiverpool and Manchester City are in a race to reach a century of goals this season.The Reds have plundered 90 already this term while City, with two games to spare on their rivals, have 84.One of the two clubs – if not both - are almost certain to break Chelsea\'s Premier League record of the 103 they scored in 2009-10.Below is our breakdown of Liverpool and City\'s goalscoring exploits... Enlarge  All statistics courtesy of WhoScored.com, where you can find yet more stats, including live in-game data and unique player and team ratings.   More... Sturridge: I would be on City bench had I stayed there... all their players are big buys He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training Rodgers: Mind guru Peters is here to stay after key role in Liverpool\'s title charge Suarez has \'God\' on his side! Liverpool legend Fowler insists lethal striker deserves to win everything this season Richards to leave Manchester City at the end of the season... with Liverpool, West Ham and Newcastle keen   Read more: Football Statistics | Football Live Scores | WhoScored.com Share or comment on this article 103shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Craig+Hope\" rel=\"nofollow\">Craig Hope</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@CraigHope01\">Follow @@CraigHope01</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 06:16 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 09:37 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"EXCLUSIVE: Liverpool and City are well-matched on the pitch... but Anfield players earn £2m LESS per man than Etihad stars\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 103</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602299/EXCLUSIVE-There-little-separate-Liverpool-City-pitch-Anfield-players-earn-2m-LESS-Etihad-stars.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">143</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Liverpool and Manchester City are the free-scoring rivals set to do battle in the race for the Premier League title.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">On the pitch there is little to separate the two teams and the victor from Sunday\'s showdown at Anfield will, in all likelihood, go on to be crowned champions.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Off the pitch, however, we can exclusively reveal that Liverpool\'s title-chasing stars are being paid, on average, £2million per year LESS than what their City adversaries.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Gulf: Liverpool players are earning, on average, £2m per year less than their City rivals\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"466\" id=\"i-a7690e5c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602299-1D0194C200000578-544_306x466.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Gulf: Liverpool players are earning, on average, £2m per year less than their City rivals\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"466\" id=\"i-ac340e87\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602299-05C6BEBF00000514-463_306x466.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Gulf: Liverpool players such as Kolo Toure (right) are earning, on average, £2m per year less than their City rivals, including Yaya Toure (left)<br/></p></div> <p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602237/Daniel-Sturridge-I-Manchester-City-bench-I-stayed-players-big-buys.html\"> Sturridge: I would be on City bench had I stayed there... all their players are big buys</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601553/Hes-Sergio-Aguero-ready-Liverpool-star-steps-injury-recovery-training.html\"> He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602011/Rodgers-Mind-guru-Peters-stay-key-role-Liverpools-title-charge.html\"> Rodgers: Mind guru Peters is here to stay after key role in Liverpool\'s title charge</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601837/Liverpool-legend-Robbie-Fowler-insists-Luis-Suarez-deserves-win-season.html\"> Suarez has \'God\' on his side! Liverpool legend Fowler insists lethal striker deserves to win everything this season</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599838/Micah-Richards-leave-Manchester-City-end-season.html\"> Richards to leave Manchester City at the end of the season... with Liverpool, West Ham and Newcastle keen</a></li> </ul> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Sheik Mansour has bankrolled City\'s emergence over the past six years, an unprecedented investment which has transformed the financial landscape of the English game.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">In turn, players such as Yaya Toure were rewarded with contracts worth £200,000 a week when they signed up for the Etihad revolution and City have continued to shell out more than any other club for the services of their players.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Indeed, their average annual wage is a massive £5,337,944, equating to £102,653 per week.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Such outlay means they pay their stars more than any other sporting club in the world, with Major League Baseball\'s New York Yankees a close second.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Investment: Sheik Mansour\'s money has taken Manchester City to a whole new level\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"357\" id=\"i-ac930e94\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602299-0AE47E2A000005DC-108_634x357.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Investment: Sheik Mansour\'s money has taken Manchester City to a whole new level</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But it is the contrast with Liverpool which is most striking. They pay their players an average of £3,403,783 per annum, that is £65,457 each week.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">A sizeable investment, yes, but when drawn in comparison to City it is proof that shrewd recruitment can pay dividends without breaking the bank.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Liverpool, under the canny guidance of Brendan Rodgers and thanks to master marksmen Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge, have the destiny of the title in their own hands.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Clean sweep: Brendan Rodgers (left) won Manager of the Month for March, while Steven Gerrard (centre) and Luis Suarez were named joint Player of the Month\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"540\" id=\"i-9a9d0e2c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602299-1D00B59400000578-78_634x540.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Clean sweep: Brendan Rodgers (left) won Manager of the Month for March, while Steven Gerrard (centre) and Luis Suarez were named joint Player of the Month</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3456018271001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit release</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D06D45200000578-315_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Victory in each of their five remaining matches – first up, of course, is City – would see them regain their English crown some 23 years on from being dethroned.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">In turn, they would become the first side in the Premier League to come from a finish as low as seventh to lift the trophy.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It is a common footballing adage that the higher the wage bill the higher the standing in the division; were that the case then City would be champions and Liverpool would be scrapping it out for the Europa League in fifth.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Glory days: Manchester City are looking to reclaim the Premier League crown they won in 2012\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"363\" id=\"i-a8810e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602299-1312AE27000005DC-207_634x363.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Glory days: Manchester City are looking to reclaim the Premier League crown they won in 2012</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Merseysiders, however, have turned the accounts on their head this season.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">For the £2m pay disparity ultimately matters not, the only number which counts is the points tally come May 11.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">To that end, three against their title rivals on Sunday is priceless.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><i>The full salary comparison tables will appear on <a href=\"http://www.sportingintelligence.com\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">www.sportingintelligence.com</a> on Monday</i></font></p>\n<div class=\"cleared art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>GOAL RUSH<br/></b></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Liverpool and Manchester City are in a race to reach a century of goals this season.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Reds have plundered 90 already this term while City, with two games to spare on their rivals, have 84.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">One of the two clubs – if not both - are almost certain to break Chelsea\'s Premier League record of the 103 they scored in 2009-10.</font><br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Below is our breakdown of Liverpool and City\'s goalscoring exploits...</font></p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <a class=\"lightboxPopupLink\" href=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602299-1D0788B100000578-785_625x478_popup.jpg\" onclick=\"return false;\" rel=\"\"> <span class=\"clickToEnlargeTop\">Enlarge</span> <span class=\"clickToEnlarge\"></span> <span class=\"clickToEnlargeButton\"> </span> <img alt=\"Liverpool City\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"478\" id=\"i-a8d30e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602299-1D0788B100000578-785_625x478.jpg\" width=\"625\"/> </a> </div><p> </p><p></p></div></div>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p 