filltext=\"Nine of the top ten players in the Premier League distance covered table are English... but which star is the top-flight\'s marathon man?\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602212/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">1.5k</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602212-1D071AF500000578-854_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:28','2014-04-11 16:34:58'),(84,'9a38941ad9470b5c1eb79a722264e1973ef497e61cf14b264c64cd4af115615f','dailymail',NULL,'George Groves fully prepared to leave no doubt of who\'s the better boxer second time around','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html',' By Mike Dawes Published: 08:36 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 09:27 EST, 11 April 2014 3 View comments  George Groves has claimed he will leave nothing to chance when he faces Carl Froch as he bids to claim the the world super middleweight title at a second time of asking. The 26-year-old controversially lost out to his Welsh counterpart last November and he believes he will show who the better fighter is at the much awaited rematch at a sold-out Wembley Stadium. Neither boxer has seen eye to eye with the other and Groves has continued with his verbal tirade against Froch claiming that he would have easily won the bout had he not been illegally stopped.  Fighting talk: George Groves at the launch of Call of Duty: Ghosts Devastation on Friday    Shoving match: Froch looks to get an early start on the much anticipated rematch against Groves   No backing down: Groves looks unimpressed with Carl Froch during a photocall at Wembley  \'With this fight with Carl Froch there is not one thing that will be left to chance. If I decide to do something it will be for a reason,\' he said speaking at the launch of Call of Duty: Ghosts Devastation. \'If I decide to say something or decide to throw a particular punch, absolutely every little detail is perfection.\' Groves believes he\'s got the psychological edge and that even his opponent know that he can\'t beat him. With no love lost between the two it is expected to be one of the closest fought matches in front a record breaking crowd.  Controversy: Groves looks devastated after he was stopped during the first match in November in Manchester No stopping him: Groves believes he\'s a far better boxer than Froch and will be looking show that at Wembley   ‘I know I would have beaten him the first time if it hadn’t been improperly stopped. Now there’s no way Carl can beat me,\' he said when speaking at the Sports Journalists\' Association launch. \'He says he can’t even stand to hear my name spoken and he can’t look at me for the stare-down photographs which are part of being a professional and selling a fight. ‘He’s seeking help from a sports psychologist because he’s in a bad place.’   More... Groves to manage himself after securing seven-figure pay day for Froch rematch DeGale in line for potential Groves rematch after signing with Hearn\'s Matchroom PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch Bradley reveals he received death threats after controversial win over Pacquiao   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Mike+Dawes\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mike Dawes</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 08:36 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 09:27 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Groves fully prepared to leave no doubt of who\'s the better boxer second time around\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">3</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">George Groves has claimed he will leave nothing to chance when he faces Carl Froch as he bids to claim the the world super middleweight title at a second time of asking.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 26-year-old controversially lost out to his Welsh counterpart last November and he believes he will show who the better fighter is at the much awaited </font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">rematch at a sold-out Wembley Stadium.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Neither boxer has seen eye to eye with the other and Groves has continued with his verbal tirade against Froch claiming that he would have easily won the bout had he not been illegally stopped.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fighting talk: George Groves at the launch of Call of Duty: Ghosts Devastation on Friday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-5a3e0d1f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D07422D00000578-946_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fighting talk: George Groves at the launch of Call of Duty: Ghosts Devastation on Friday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<img alt=\"Shoving match: Froch looks to get an early start on the much anticipated rematch against Groves\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"653\" id=\"i-a8720e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/03/article-2596108-1C2B534800000578-416_634x653.jpg\" width=\"634\"/>\n<p class=\"imageCaption\">Shoving match: Froch looks to get an early start on the much anticipated rematch against Groves</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"No backing down: Groves looks unimpressed with Carl Froch during a photocall at Wembley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"464\" id=\"i-5c6d0d37\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1C2B627E00000578-943_634x464.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">No backing down: Groves looks unimpressed with Carl Froch during a photocall at Wembley</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'With this fight with Carl Froch there is not one thing that will be left to chance. If I decide to do something it will be for a reason,\' he said speaking at the launch of Call of Duty: Ghosts Devastation.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'If I decide to say something or decide to throw a particular punch, absolutely every little detail is perfection.\'  <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Groves believes he\'s got the psychological edge and that even his opponent know that he can\'t beat him.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With no love lost between the two it is expected to be one of the closest fought matches in front a record breaking crowd.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/woTgPYoc4v4\" width=\"640\"></iframe> <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Controversy: Groves looks devastated after he was stopped during the first match in November in Manchester\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"429\" id=\"i-a6e10e55\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/03/article-2596108-06132E2E00000514-434_634x429.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Controversy: Groves looks devastated after he was stopped during the first match in November in Manchester</p> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"No stopping him: Groves believes he\'s a far better boxer than Froch and will be looking show that at Wembley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"607\" id=\"i-a9100e6c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/03/article-2596108-1C077C8100000578-947_634x607.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">No stopping him: Groves believes he\'s a far better boxer than Froch and will be looking show that at Wembley</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I know I would have beaten him the first time if it hadn’t been improperly stopped. Now there’s no way Carl can beat me,\' he said when speaking at the Sports Journalists\' Association launch.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'He says he can’t even stand to hear my name spoken and he can’t look at me for the stare-down photographs which are part of being a professional and selling a fight. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘He’s seeking help from a sports psychologist because he’s in a bad place.’</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2596108/Groves-manage-securing-seven-figure-pay-day-Froch-rematch.html\"> Groves to manage himself after securing seven-figure pay day for Froch rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html\"> DeGale in line for potential Groves rematch after signing with Hearn\'s Matchroom</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601650/PacMan-people-Mannys-superstar-statesman-entertains-serves-fellow-Filipinos-Jeff-Powell.html\"> PacMan of the people: Manny\'s the superstar statesman who entertains and serves his fellow Filipinos - and he\'s out for revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html\"> Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600995/Tim-Bradley-nearly-committed-suicide-Manny-Pacquiao-decision.html\"> Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600820/Bradley-reveals-received-death-threats-controversial-win-Pacquiao.html\"> Bradley reveals he received death threats after controversial win over Pacquiao</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602500/George-Groves-fully-prepared-leave-no-doubt-whos-better-boxer-second-time-around.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Groves fully prepared to leave no doubt of who\'s the better boxer second time around\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2602500/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1D07422D00000578-769_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:29','2014-04-11 16:27:36'),(85,'98d3e4aa98e9b1bda1ee09162463a8ddd956d6f17187cb6201a662a94bcda4c3','dailymail',NULL,'I was a nightmare, I let people down and I was threatened with arrest for Cup protest, admits Hull boss Steve Bruce','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html',' By John Edwards Follow @@JEAlty Published: 18:08 EST, 10 April 2014 | Updated: 08:56 EST, 11 April 2014 6 View comments Steve Bruce has bluntly admitted he was \'a nightmare\' as a rookie boss and revealed he was threatened with arrest just six months into his first managerial post.   Newly appointed as Sheffield United manager, Bruce found himself in the midst of uproar after Arsenal failed to return possession to his team, after they kicked the ball out to allow an injured player to be treated, and scored one of the most controversial goals of recent times through Marc Overmars.  Cup ties: Wembley-bound Hull City manager Steve Bruce can see the funny side    Video: Arsenal v Sheffield United controversy  \'To say there were difficult times off the pitch at Sheffield United would be an understatement, but that day at Arsenal was something else,\' he said. \'I had only been in charge six months, and suddenly I was confronted by this. I took the players off and was almost arrested for it.   \'A police officer walked in and told us that if we didn\'t get them back on pretty sharpish, I would end up in the nick. The whole thing was weird.   \'When I look back to those days, and how I was as a young manager, I was a nightmare. I let people down. Simon Jordan comes rushing back to me (after he left Crystal Palace three months into his first season to take over at Birmingham City). I was young and headstrong, and I wanted to take on the world.  Row: Sheffield United manager Steve Bruce leads the protests against Arsenal goal   Flashpoint: Sheffield United players confront Arsenal\'s Marc Overmars (right) and Nwankwo Kanu     Headstrong: Bruce wanted to \'take on the world\' after his move into management  \'I resigned from Sheffield, because things were promised that were not forthcoming. I was told, when I arrived there, I had £5million to spend, but when I went to see the chief executive soon after, he said if I didn\'t raise £350,000 by August, no-one was getting paid.  \'The good thing about management is you are tested every day, and you learn from experience, but that was certainly a steep learning curve.\' If Bruce looks round, when he leads Hull City out against Sheffield United in Sunday\'s FA Cup semi-final at Wembley, he will be confronted by a familiar sight. Face masks depicting the Hull manager have been a popular sale item in recent weeks and are expected to figure prominently at the Hull end.  \'Dear, oh dear, oh dear,\' he said, shaking his head. \'I just hope any kids who are going, especially really young ones, aren\'t frightened by that. If we\'d had those made at my previous club (Sunderland), they\'d have been throwing darts at them. The fickle world of football, eh?\'   More... HULL vs SHEFFIELD UNITED: Latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final Allam willing to go to court in his bid to get Hull\'s name changed to Tigers Tan accuses former director Moody of using contacts to find out Cardiff team ahead of crucial clash with Crystal Palace Wenger: Finishing in top-four is vital... but I fight every day to win trophies for Arsenal Bruce: It\'ll come down to which team handles the occasion better   Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Edwards\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Edwards</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@JEAlty\">Follow @@JEAlty</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 18:08 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 08:56 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"I was a nightmare, I let people down and I was threatened with arrest for Cup protest, admits Hull boss Bruce\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">6</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Steve Bruce has bluntly admitted he was \'a nightmare\' as a rookie boss and revealed he was threatened with arrest just six months into his first managerial post.</font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Newly appointed as Sheffield United manager, Bruce found himself in the midst of uproar after Arsenal failed to return possession to his team, after they kicked the ball out to allow an injured player to be treated, and scored one of the most controversial goals of recent times through Marc Overmars.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Cup ties: Wembley-bound Hull City manager Steve Bruce can see the funny side\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"359\" id=\"i-a8970e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2602021-1CF697C100000578-297_634x359.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Cup ties: Wembley-bound Hull City manager Steve Bruce can see the funny side</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Video: Arsenal v Sheffield United controversy</font></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"477\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/whO5GAFBp30\" width=\"636\"></iframe><br/></font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'To say there were difficult times off the pitch at Sheffield United would be an understatement, but that day at Arsenal was something else,\' he said. \'I had only been in charge six months, and suddenly I was confronted by this. I took the players off and was almost arrested for it.</font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'A police officer walked in and told us that if we didn\'t get them back on pretty sharpish, I would end up in the nick. The whole thing was weird.</font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'When I look back to those days, and how I was as a young manager, I was a nightmare. I let people down. Simon Jordan comes rushing back to me (after he left Crystal Palace three months into his first season to take over at Birmingham City). I was young and headstrong, and I wanted to take on the world.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Row: Sheffield United manager Steve Bruce leads the protests against Arsenal goal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"456\" id=\"i-a5920e53\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602021-1D02284F00000578-483_634x456.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Row: Sheffield United manager Steve Bruce leads the protests against Arsenal goal</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Flashpoint: Sheffield United players confront Arsenal\'s Marc Overmars (right) and Nwankwo Kanu\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"488\" id=\"i-8a560de5\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602021-1D02289400000578-9_634x488.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Flashpoint: Sheffield United players confront Arsenal\'s Marc Overmars (right) and Nwankwo Kanu</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Headstrong: Bruce wanted to \'take on the world\' after his move into management\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"549\" id=\"i-a5bc0e59\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602021-00468AE700000258-937_634x549.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Headstrong: Bruce wanted to \'take on the world\' after his move into management</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I resigned from Sheffield, because things were promised that were not forthcoming. I was told, when I arrived there, I had £5million to spend, but when I went to see the chief executive soon after, he said if I didn\'t raise £350,000 by August, no-one was getting paid.</font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'The good thing about management is you are tested every day, and you learn from experience, but that was certainly a steep learning curve.\' </font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">If Bruce looks round, when he leads Hull City out against Sheffield United in Sunday\'s FA Cup semi-final at Wembley, he will be confronted by a familiar sight. Face masks depicting the Hull manager have been a popular sale item in recent weeks and are expected to figure prominently at the Hull end.</font></p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Dear, oh dear, oh dear,\' he said, shaking his head. \'I just hope any kids who are going, especially really young ones, aren\'t frightened by that. If we\'d had those made at my previous club (Sunderland), they\'d have been throwing darts at them. The fickle world of football, eh?\'</font></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601451/HULL-vs-SHEFFIELD-UNITED-Latest-team-news-stats-FA-Cup-semi-final.html\"> HULL vs SHEFFIELD UNITED: Latest team news and stats for the FA Cup semi-final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600870/Hull-owner-Allam-fight-bid-clubs-changed.html\"> Allam willing to go to court in his bid to get Hull\'s name changed to Tigers</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601934/Vincent-Tan-demands-probe-accusing-Crystal-Palace-director-Iain-Moody-trying-Cardiff-team-unethical-means.html\"> Tan accuses former director Moody of using contacts to find out Cardiff team ahead of crucial clash with Crystal Palace</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601836/Arsene-Wenger-Champions-League-vital-I-fight-day-win-trophies-Arsenal.html\"> Wenger: Finishing in top-four is vital... but I fight every day to win trophies for Arsenal</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3449789287001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Bruce: It\'ll come down to which team handles the occasion better</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/video-undefined-1CF87BB800000578-168_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602021/I-nightmare-I-let-people-I-threatened-arrest-Cup-protest-admits-Hull-boss-Steve-Bruce.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"I was a nightmare, I let people down and I was threatened with arrest for Cup protest, admits Hull boss Bruce\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602021/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602021-1D022F2600000578-387_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:29','2014-04-11 15:56:55'),(86,'522eccc0c3f6431ace1d70affd4de2a3ccc1a2c04247f630ee499030528d1699','dailymail',NULL,'France scrum-half (and scourge of England) Dimitri Yachvili reveals he will hang up his boots','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html',' By Mike Dawes Published: 08:48 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 08:48 EST, 11 April 2014 1 View comments Former France scrum-half Dimitri Yachvili has announced he will retire at the end of the season. Yachvili, 33, played for France in the 2011 World Cup final defeat to New Zealand and enjoyed success at club level with Biarritz after launching his top-flight career with a brief stint at Gloucester in 2001/02. Early in his 61-cap international career he played a key role in France winning the Six Nations grand slam in 2004 - including a starring role in a dramatic final game victory against England - and clinching the trophy again two years later, before having peripheral roles in Les Bleus\' 2007 and 2010 triumphs.  Pass master: Dimitri Yachvili is calling time on his rugby career after success with France and Biarritz   Try time: Yachvili scores during the Six Nations-deciding victory against England in 2004  He made his final appearances for France in the 2012 RBS 6 Nations campaign. Biarritz confirmed Yachvili\'s retirement on their website, stating: \'Dimitri Yachvili told (Biarritz president) Serge Blanco on Thursday evening of his decision to bring his career to an end. \'It\'s with great emotion that Biarritz sees a great champion, who has given so much to the Red and White, retire from the rugby field. \'After his titles as champion of France in 2005 and 2006, his two Heineken Cup finals in 2006 and 2010, an Amlin Cup in 2012 but equally a title as vice-champion of the world in New Zealand, we wish Dimitri much success in his new life as a businessman.\'  Trusty boot: The scrum-half often took kicking duties for France, and here lands a penalty at Twickenham   I\'ll drink to that: Yachvili celebrates Biarritz\'s Heineken Cup semi-final win over Bath in 2006  With Biarritz relegated from the Top 14 for next season, Yachvili decided it was time to bow out. He told L\'Equipe: \'It\'s the right moment for me to put an end to my career. I feel that my body needs to stop.\'   More... Leicester close to signing Barbieri as Tigers CEO Cohen reveals Italian transfer targets Sale to move home games to Saturdays after Friday night crowds dwindle Roberts ready to take over Wales captaincy as Gatland\'s squad prepare for South Africa European Champions Cup finally confirmed as rugby heavyweights end bitter dispute Exeter snap up Lees as Aussie back-row forward switches Welsh for Chiefs Wasps coach backs in-form Haskell to make England\'s summer tour of New Zealand  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Mike+Dawes\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mike Dawes</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 08:48 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 08:48 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"France scrum-half (and scourge of England) Yachvili reveals he will hang up his boots\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">1</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Former France scrum-half Dimitri Yachvili has announced he will retire at the end of the season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Yachvili, 33, played for France in the 2011 World Cup final defeat to New Zealand and enjoyed success at club level with Biarritz after launching his top-flight career with a brief stint at Gloucester in 2001/02.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Early in his 61-cap international career he played a key role in France winning the Six Nations grand slam in 2004 - including a starring role in a dramatic final game victory against England - and clinching the trophy again two years later, before having peripheral roles in Les Bleus\' 2007 and 2010 triumphs.</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pass master: Dimitri Yachvili is calling time on his rugby career after success with France and Biarritz\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"432\" id=\"i-a7880e60\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602503-1D0751BC00000578-737_634x432.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pass master: Dimitri Yachvili is calling time on his rugby career after success with France and Biarritz</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Try time: Yachvili scores during the Six Nations-deciding victory against England in 2004\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-a6100e52\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602503-0216E9B10000044D-502_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Try time: Yachvili scores during the Six Nations-deciding victory against England in 2004</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He made his final appearances for France in the 2012 RBS 6 Nations campaign.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Biarritz confirmed Yachvili\'s retirement on their website, stating: \'Dimitri Yachvili told (Biarritz president) Serge Blanco on Thursday evening of his decision to bring his career to an end.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'It\'s with great emotion that Biarritz sees a great champion, who has given so much to the Red and White, retire from the rugby field.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'After his titles as champion of France in 2005 and 2006, his two Heineken Cup finals in 2006 and 2010, an Amlin Cup in 2012 but equally a title as vice-champion of the world in New Zealand, we wish Dimitri much success in his new life as a businessman.\'</font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Trusty boot: The scrum-half often took kicking duties for France, and here lands a penalty at Twickenham\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"431\" id=\"i-a6e10e5b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602503-0226DA980000044D-219_634x431.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Trusty boot: The scrum-half often took kicking duties for France, and here lands a penalty at Twickenham</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"I\'ll drink to that: Yachvili celebrates Biarritz\'s Heineken Cup semi-final win over Bath in 2006\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-a7500e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602503-0492FD520000044D-556_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">I\'ll drink to that: Yachvili celebrates Biarritz\'s Heineken Cup semi-final win over Bath in 2006</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With Biarritz relegated from the Top 14 for next season, Yachvili decided it was time to bow out.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He told L\'Equipe: \'It\'s the right moment for me to put an end to my career. I feel that my body needs to stop.\'</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602065/Leicester-close-signing-Italy-international-Robert-Barbieri-Simon-Cohen-reveals-transfer-targets.html\"> Leicester close to signing Barbieri as Tigers CEO Cohen reveals Italian transfer targets</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602372/Sale-home-games-Saturdays-Friday-night-crowds-dwindle.html\"> Sale to move home games to Saturdays after Friday night crowds dwindle</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2601816/Jamie-Roberts-ready-Wales-captaincy-Warren-Gatlands-squad-prepare-South-Africa.html\"> Roberts ready to take over Wales captaincy as Gatland\'s squad prepare for South Africa</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2601788/European-Champions-Cup-confirmed-rugby-heavyweights-finally-reach-agreement.html\"> European Champions Cup finally confirmed as rugby heavyweights end bitter dispute</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2601362/Exeter-snap-Lees-Aussie-row-forward-switches-Welsh-Chiefs.html\"> Exeter snap up Lees as Aussie back-row forward switches Welsh for Chiefs</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/rugbyunion/article-2601173/Wasps-coach-backs-form-Haskell-make-Englands-summer-tour-New-Zealand.html\"> Wasps coach backs in-form Haskell to make England\'s summer tour of New Zealand</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/France-scrum-half-scourge-England-Dimitri-Yachvili-reveals-hang-boots.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"France scrum-half (and scourge of England) Yachvili reveals he will hang up his boots\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/article-2602503/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602503-0216E9B10000044D-965_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:30','2014-04-11 15:48:46'),(87,'362d3227ba74f33cb373965ad02b39d19218408067f0a467b23cbb7d3bdd299e','dailymail',NULL,'Spurs ace Eriksen set for £40,000 bonus if former club Ajax win Dutch league','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602492/Spurs-ace-Eriksen-set-40-000-bonus-former-club-Ajax-win-Dutch-league.html',' By Craig Hope Follow @@CraigHope01 Published: 08:43 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 08:43 EST, 11 April 2014 7 shares 11 View comments Christian Eriksen is set for a £40,000 bonus from former club Ajax should they win the Dutch league this season. The Danish international played four games in the Eredivisie at the start of this campaign before his £11million move to Spurs. And according to reports in Holland that makes Eriksen – as well as Atletico Madrid’s Toby Alderweireld - eligible for a share of the bonus payments made to Ajax’s squad.  Something to celebrate: Christian Eriksen could receive a bonus of £40,000 if Ajax win the league  The full amount of £250,000 is paid to players who appear in at least 25 league matches. Ajax can clinch a fourth successive title this weekend if they beat ADO Den Haag and Feyenoord, in second, fail to win at PSV Eindhoven. Eriksen won three league championships during his time with the club, scoring 10 times during last year’s triumph.  Playing his part: Eriksen started the season at Ajax   Fondly thought of: Eriksen received a warm reception when he went back to Ajax for the game against Heerenveen  He returned to the Amsterdam ArenA earlier this season where he was afforded a spectacular send-off complete with fireworks and his name illuminated in sparklers. The popular midfielder has been one of the few summer signings to impress at White Hart Lane, scoring nine times from 31 outings.   More... WEST BROM vs TOTTENHAM: All the latest team news and stats as hosts look for boost in relegation battle Holtby targets Tottenham return and backs Van Gaal to replace Sherwood Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public Eriksen says his future is at Spurs after starring in win over Sunderland Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer ADRIAN DURHAM: Kane must not be allowed to follow McEachran and Wickham in falling down the English talent drain  Share or comment on this article 7shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Craig+Hope\" rel=\"nofollow\">Craig Hope</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@CraigHope01\">Follow @@CraigHope01</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 08:43 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 08:43 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602492/Spurs-ace-Eriksen-set-40-000-bonus-former-club-Ajax-win-Dutch-league.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602492/Spurs-ace-Eriksen-set-40-000-bonus-former-club-Ajax-win-Dutch-league.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Spurs ace Eriksen set for £40,000 bonus if former club Ajax win Dutch league\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 7</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602492/Spurs-ace-Eriksen-set-40-000-bonus-former-club-Ajax-win-Dutch-league.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">11</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Christian Eriksen is set for a £40,000 bonus from former club Ajax should they win the Dutch league this season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Danish international played four games in the Eredivisie at the start of this campaign before his £11million move to Spurs.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And according to reports in Holland that makes Eriksen – as well as Atletico Madrid’s Toby Alderweireld - eligible for a share of the bonus payments made to Ajax’s squad.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Something to celebrate: Christian Eriksen could receive a bonus of £40,000 if Ajax win the league\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"402\" id=\"i-605e0d52\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-0-1CEADE8500000578-582_634x402.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Something to celebrate: Christian Eriksen could receive a bonus of £40,000 if Ajax win the league</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The full amount of £250,000 is paid to players who appear in at least 25 league matches. Ajax can clinch a fourth successive title this weekend if they beat ADO Den Haag and Feyenoord, in second, fail to win at PSV Eindhoven.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Eriksen won three league championships during his time with the club, scoring 10 times during last year’s triumph.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Playing his part: Eriksen started the season at Ajax\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a9320e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602492-1D07A3DA00000578-201_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Playing his part: Eriksen started the season at Ajax</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fondly thought of: Eriksen received a warm reception when he went back to Ajax for the game against Heerenveen\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-a93d0e6b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602492-1D07A3CA00000578-102_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fondly thought of: Eriksen received a warm reception when he went back to Ajax for the game against Heerenveen</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He returned to the Amsterdam ArenA earlier this season where he was afforded a spectacular send-off complete with fireworks and his name illuminated in sparklers.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The popular midfielder has been one of the few summer signings to impress at White Hart Lane, scoring nine times from 31 outings.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600838/WEST-BROM-vs-TOTTENHAM-All-latest-team-news-stats-hosts-look-boost-relegation-battle.html\"> WEST BROM vs TOTTENHAM: All the latest team news and stats as hosts look for boost in relegation battle</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602250/Lewis-Holtby-targets-Tottenham-return-backs-Louis-van-Gaal-replace-Tim-Sherwood.html\"> Holtby targets Tottenham return and backs Van Gaal to replace Sherwood</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html\"> Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599623/Eriksen-says-future-Spurs-starring-win-Sunderland.html\"> Eriksen says his future is at Spurs after starring in win over Sunderland</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599731/Louis-Van-Gaal-reveals-hes-totally-sick-national-team-coach-Holland-boss-opens-door-Spurs-summer.html\"> Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599453/Adrian-Durham-column-We-allow-Premier-League-clubs-graveyards-young-English-talents.html\"> ADRIAN DURHAM: Kane must not be allowed to follow McEachran and Wickham in falling down the English talent drain</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602492/Spurs-ace-Eriksen-set-40-000-bonus-former-club-Ajax-win-Dutch-league.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602492/Spurs-ace-Eriksen-set-40-000-bonus-former-club-Ajax-win-Dutch-league.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Spurs ace Eriksen set for £40,000 bonus if former club Ajax win Dutch league\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602492/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">7</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602492-1CEADE8500000578-834_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:33','2014-04-11 15:43:37'),(88,'c91ebb9121a0fc05a6ce82b335b279b9839e63cf5c86b597d1f15669052b0fe6','dailymail',NULL,'Lewis Holtby targets Tottenham return and backs Louis van Gaal to replace Tim Sherwood','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602250/Lewis-Holtby-targets-Tottenham-return-backs-Louis-van-Gaal-replace-Tim-Sherwood.html',' By John Drayton Published: 03:19 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 08:41 EST, 11 April 2014 40 shares 16 View comments  Lewis Holtby hopes to resurrect his Tottenham career and would be happy to see Louis van Gaal become the club\'s next manager. Holtby was farmed out on loan to Spurs\' west London neighbours Fulham earlier this season where he has been stuck in a relegation battle. Van Gaal has been installed as favourite to replace Tim Sherwood who is expected to leave his post at the end of the season - a move that would please the Germany international. VIDEO Scroll down to watch Tim Sherwood blast other managers for talking about his job  Lew-king for a return: Holtby has expressed his desire to return to White hart Lane Party time: Holtby celebrates with match-winner Hugo Rodallega after the decisive goal against Aston Villa    More... Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public Eriksen says his future is at Spurs after starring in win over Sunderland I won\'t be No 2 at Spurs, says Sherwood as Tottenham line up Holland boss Van Gaal Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer \'There is little sense in talking about other clubs since I have a long-term contract at Tottenham,\' he told Goal. \'The status quo is that I will go back to Spurs after the summer holidays. I can\'t tell you what is going to happen until then. My agent takes care of everything and as far as I know his mobile is always turned on.   \'I loved playing for Tottenham and I would like to fulfil my contract there. But at first it is important to avoid relegation with Fulham. \'There is always lots of talk. Louis van Gaal is an exceptional coach, you can\'t deny that. \'He led big teams to big success. I don\'t know whether he will be the new coach and of course it is not for me to decide. I don\'t want to think about it now.\' Sherwood blasts other managers for talking about his job    Leap of faith: Holtby hopes he can kick0-start his career under a new boss at Tottenham On target: Holtby scored a cracker against Fulham for Tottenham earlier this season     More... Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public Eriksen says his future is at Spurs after starring in win over Sunderland I won\'t be No 2 at Spurs, says Sherwood as Tottenham line up Holland boss Van Gaal Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer   Share or comment on this article 40shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=John+Drayton\" rel=\"nofollow\">John Drayton</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 03:19 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 08:41 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602250/Lewis-Holtby-targets-Tottenham-return-backs-Louis-van-Gaal-replace-Tim-Sherwood.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602250/Lewis-Holtby-targets-Tottenham-return-backs-Louis-van-Gaal-replace-Tim-Sherwood.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Holtby targets Tottenham return and backs Van Gaal to replace Sherwood\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 40</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602250/Lewis-Holtby-targets-Tottenham-return-backs-Louis-van-Gaal-replace-Tim-Sherwood.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">1