o doubt about it, the game will be very important. We know how difficult it will be against teams fighting relegation but the important thing is going to Liverpool and trying to get a good result. After that we have to continue to perform because if we want to win the league we have to win all games.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>When you won the title in 2012 it was all about competing with Manchester United but this year it has been Chelsea and now Liverpool. Have Liverpool impressed you?</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All smiles: Jamie Redknapp (left) and Yaya Toure share a joke at Manchester City\'s training base\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-ab840e85\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEB52A00000578-634_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All smiles: Jamie Redknapp (left) and Yaya Toure share a joke at Manchester City\'s training base</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Versatile: Toure tells Jamie how he reinvented his game to become a fearsome midfield player\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-ac260e85\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEB8E200000578-382_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Versatile: Toure tells Jamie how he reinvented his game to become a fearsome midfield player</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Strike a pose: Redknapp and Toure smile for Sportsmail\'s Andy Hooper in Carrington\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-ae770e9e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEAFF800000578-486_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Strike a pose: Redknapp and Toure smile for Sportsmail\'s Andy Hooper in Carrington</p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>They have been amazing. They have had the advantage of playing one game a week and so they have been fresh. With players of their calibre, it helps to train all week and prepare for one game. It’s going to be very, very tough until the end.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>Who has impressed you?</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya:</b> Defensively they have been good but in midfield they are so strong. Steven Gerrard is fantastic and has so much experience. And Luis Suarez and Daniel Sturridge have been unbelievable. They score goals like a machine. Things are going to be tough for our defence and if we make a mistake, or we are not concentrating 100 per cent, we are going to pay.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>I’ve been watching you in the Champions League for years and you used to be the perfect defensive midfielder. Now you’ve turned into a goalscoring midfielder. What’s changed?</font></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Man on man: Toure and Jamie appear to be enjoying one another\'s company\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"484\" id=\"i-ab500e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEB51E00000578-103_634x484.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Man on man: Toure and Jamie appear to be enjoying one another\'s company</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Under the spotlight: Toure and Redknapp were talking ahead of Manchester City\'s clash with Liverpool\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-ac1f0e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEB6F200000578-258_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Under the spotlight: Toure and Redknapp were talking ahead of Manchester City\'s clash with Liverpool</p><div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601395/Rip-touts-sell-tickets-Liverpools-crunch-clash-City-5-000-pair.html\"> Rip-off touts sell tickets for Liverpool\'s crunch clash with City at up to £5,000 a pair</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601553/Hes-Sergio-Aguero-ready-Liverpool-star-steps-injury-recovery-training.html\"> He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601529/Rodgers-raring-title-showdown-City-Suarez-Co-paces.html\"> Bumming around! Liverpool in good spirits ahead of title showdown as Suarez and Co are put through their paces</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/manchester-city.html\"> Read the latest Manchester City news and views here</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/liverpool.html\"> Read the latest Liverpool news and views here</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div> <p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>It started when I was in Belgium and I went to Arsenal to do some training. I remember the first chat I had with Arsene Wenger. He asked me: ‘Yaya, which position do you want to play?’ I told him I wanted to be a midfielder. He said: ‘Why? When I saw you training, for me you look more like a striker.’ I said: ‘Ah, that’s why you keep playing me up front! Move me, I want to play in midfield like Patrick Vieira. I can play like Patrick and I can be better than Patrick.’ He said: ‘No, no. That’s impossible. No one is better than Patrick.’</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>Are you better than him now?</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>(laughing) No, Patrick is unbelievable, with the trophies he has. Arsene liked me further  forward because when I was training close to the goal I would take five shots and score with four of them. That was not too bad, but for me I wanted to definitely play in midfield. Then when I went back to Belgium the manager moved me further forward. It was nice and I enjoyed it but after that I moved back into midfield. </font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>Take me back to your early career. Is it true that when you first came to Europe you arrived as a young man with no boots?</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>(laughing) Yeah! When I was 16 in Ivory Coast I played for ASEC Mimosas in Abidjan. It was a great club in my country and after that I started to think about what would be the next level for me. In my mind all the big players are supposed to play in Europe. That was my target — to be there and compare myself to them. That’s when I came to Belgium and started to play in the first team in Beveren.</font></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Big task: Toure will hope to dominate the game at Anfield and hand City a title boost\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"446\" id=\"i-ac5b0e8e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEB6E200000578-649_634x446.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Big task: Toure will hope to dominate the game at Anfield and hand City a title boost</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Words of wisdom: Toure is targeting his second Premier League title with Manchester City\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-aa830e75\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEB38500000578-147_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Words of wisdom: Toure is targeting his second Premier League title with Manchester City</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>Then you went and played in Ukraine. That must have been quite a contrast from growing up in Africa?</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>Yes, I played for Metalurh Donetsk and it was an amazing experience. Coming from Africa, I started to learn how to eat properly, how to get rest and concentrate and I started to understand the high level of sport. You need to be careful with when you go out. You have to get more rest, and you have to be very, very focused. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>Then another move, this time to Greece?</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya:</b> I spent one year at Olympiacos and won two trophies, so it was a good year! I got to play with Rivaldo, too, and he taught me so much. He gave me a lot of confidence for when I went to Barcelona. We won the Greek league and cup. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>And after success in Greece you spent a season in Monaco before the big move to Barcelona. Then you got to play with Lionel Messi, Xavi, Andres Iniesta. It must have been incredible to work with players like that?</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>It was unbelievable. In my second year I won six trophies, which was an amazing achievement for an African player coming from Monaco. I was the only player who came from a small club but I learned so much about preparing for games and being professional. After that I always came to training an hour or two early because, for me, that’s very important.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Goal threat: Toure, pictured celebrating against United, has netted 18 Premier League goals this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"439\" id=\"i-9a060e2c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1C90B46700000578-28_634x439.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Goal threat: Toure, pictured celebrating against United, has netted 18 Premier League goals this season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Well travelled: Toure slides in on Wayne Rooney during Barcelona\'s victorious Champions League final against Manchester United in 2009\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"491\" id=\"i-a67c0e5a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1C0F027000000578-878_634x491.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Well travelled: Toure slides in on Wayne Rooney during Barcelona\'s victorious Champions League final against Manchester United in 2009</p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie:</b> I read a few weeks ago that Barcelona said the one player they would like to sign again was you...</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>(laughing) I know they loved me there and it was difficult to get out of Barcelona. Pep Guardiola said he wanted me to stay, but I knew it was the right time for me to go. I was 27 and it was time to move on and try to continue to play. I wanted to come to England with a big club and win trophies.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>You lost to Barcelona in the last 16 of the Champions League last month. How do you think City can make the strides needed to become European champions?</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>We already are. We have a fantastic manager and we are playing good football, which the players are enjoying a lot. We have a few things to do better and there are always some difficult clubs that will cause us a lot of problems.  <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Barcelona game was a good example. We went out because of our first game, at home, where we respected them a lot. By the second game we showed different things but by then it was too late. It’s good for next year.</font></p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3455793961001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Kolo Toure: We\'re fighting for the title, definitely</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D05D5D100000578-786_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"One that got away: Toure pictured in an Arsenal kit\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a6130e5c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1301626F000005DC-983_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Kolo Toure also played for Arsenal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a8a50e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-0291C9DA000004B0-968_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Family affair: Yaya trained with Arsenal where his older brother Kolo (right) became a key part of the squad<br/></p><div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3456018271001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Kolo Toure sings his own song at Liverpool\'s new kit release</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D06D45200000578-315_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Brothers in arms: Yaya and Kolo played together at Manchester City\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a8560e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1B2121AD000005DC-863_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Staying on: Toure fired City to Capital One Cup glory earlier this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a89e0e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1BF7766600000578-968_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Staying put: The Toure brothers played together at City but Yaya remained at the Etihad after Kolo moved on<br/></p></div> <p> </p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>It sounds bright for the future, but what about this year? In 2012 you won the title with  Roberto Mancini and now you have Manuel Pellegrini in charge. Is there much difference between the two managers?</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya:</b> It’s difficult to criticise the managers because they both work us very hard. Mancini had a different style, it was more about defensive skill, and with Pellegrini we are more attacking. All the players are enjoying it and we are improving. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Samir Nasri and David Silva are doing fantastically well and Sergio Aguero is fantastic. We got new signings who have helped a lot. Jesus Navas and Alvaro Negredo have been great this season and I hope, with all this hard work we have done, at the end we will lift this trophy.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>I’ve not seen many players come into the league and settle as quickly as Fernandinho. He is the perfect foil for you, he sits and protects the back four while you work your magic. Is he easy to play with?</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"The opposition: Luis Suarez and Steven Gerrard in training at Melwood\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-aa910e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CFF396800000578-897_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Machine: Toure is impressed with how Daniel Sturridge has been playing this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-aaa70e73\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CFF56C500000578-207_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Mean machine: Toure has been impressed with Luis Suarez (left) and Daniel Sturridge this season <br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Clash of the titans: Toure will square off against another first-class midfielder in Steven Gerrard on Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"391\" id=\"i-ab550e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CE2CCC200000578-192_634x391.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Clash of the titans: Toure will square off against another first-class midfielder in Steven Gerrard on Sunday</p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya:</b> He’s very clever. Brazilians play pretty, fantastic football and Fernandinho is clever — he anticipates well, he presses well. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">His movement is so good but he can play with the ball as well. Before he came to City, he was at Shakhtar playing in my position, more as an offensive midfielder. Sometimes we have some difficulties because when he attacks I have to stay more to protect the defence, but we are doing well and he helps me a lot. The manager demands a lot from us because he wants us to have more of the ball and he wants us to attack. He doesn’t want to just score and defend.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>You have scored 22 goals this season, including some spectacular free-kicks. When I watched you at Barcelona you never took a free-kick and now you’re bending them in the top corner every time! What’s changed? Do you practise them a lot?</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>Of course. In my first year with Mancini, I took them in training. But in a game it was difficult because Carlos Tevez would just take the ball and hit it.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie:</b> Was he a bit greedy?</font></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dynamic duo: Fernandinho (right) and Toure have struck up some partnership in the City midfield\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-abad0e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CDAAC7100000578-478_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dynamic duo: Fernandinho (right) and Toure have struck up some partnership in the City midfield</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>Yes! And Mario Balotelli. But afterwards it was easier. Because I’m an experienced player, I’m calmer than the rest. When I want to shoot, first of all I only take a few steps back. For me it’s not just about the power, it’s about the technique as well. When you hit the ball, it has to be with precision. In England, you get a lot of tall players in the wall and it can be difficult to get the ball up and down quickly.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>What about penalties? Did you learn any techniques from playing with Messi and Drogba?</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>Penalties are all about being calm. Joe Hart is very good  with penalties: he’s quick in his  movement, goes down very fast and he waits until the last minute. It makes it difficult in training for us but it’s good for me because in a match you can come up against a good goalkeeper who can stop your penalty, but we have had practice.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie:</b> When you won the title in 2012, it came down to that last-gasp winner from Sergio Aguero. Do you think the same thing could happen this year?</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya:</b> I hope so! I remember in 2012, it was so difficult until the last minute. I hope Aguero will be fit because we need him. Edin Dzeko and Negredo have been fantastic this season, but especially Aguero. He makes such a difference.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie:</b> Are there any individuals at Liverpool you will be watching out for? Do you have any special plans for Luis Suarez?</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"High praise: Toure believes City can become European champions under the guidance of Manuel Pellegrini\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"456\" id=\"i-ab200e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1C7EAC4600000578-869_634x456.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">High praise: Toure believes City can become European champions under the guidance of Manuel Pellegrini</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya:</b> This year they have been playing as a team. Brendan Rodgers is a great manager and everybody has been happy with him. Even my brother Kolo has had low game time but he is very happy with him. He always keeps his team 100 per cent fit and concentrating so it’s going to be tough. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Against Liverpool, everything is going to come from everywhere. Gerrard can score penalties and free-kicks and Suarez is a danger man. But football is all about winning, about technique, about being clever and sharper. We are playing very well and we have a fantastic side. My target is to win a lot of trophies with this club.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Jamie: </b>Yaya, it’s been a pleasure. I’d love to wish you good luck against my old team but I don’t think I can!</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Yaya: </b>Thank you. It will be a very difficult match but when you love your job and you love this sport, you can do anything.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Greedy? Toure and Carlos Tevez\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a8740e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-183F49E1000005DC-201_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Toure and Balotelli (right)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a7dc0e5d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-0EA4687700000578-763_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Greedy! Toure is glad he can take more free-kicks now that Carlos Tevez and Mario Balotelli (right) have gone<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Happy: Yaya spoke of his brother Kolo\'s admiration for Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"476\" id=\"i-a90f0e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCD347300000578-944_634x476.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Happy: Yaya spoke of his brother Kolo\'s admiration for Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601395/Rip-touts-sell-tickets-Liverpools-crunch-clash-City-5-000-pair.html\"> Rip-off touts sell tickets for Liverpool\'s crunch clash with City at up to £5,000 a pair</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601553/Hes-Sergio-Aguero-ready-Liverpool-star-steps-injury-recovery-training.html\"> He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601529/Rodgers-raring-title-showdown-City-Suarez-Co-paces.html\"> Bumming around! Liverpool in good spirits ahead of title showdown as Suarez and Co are put through their paces</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/manchester-city.html\"> Read the latest Manchester City news and views here</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/liverpool.html\"> Read the latest Liverpool news and views here</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3450190965001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Michael Owen: Great to see Liverpool back in the big time</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/video-undefined-1CF904DF00000578-150_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3455825791001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Fowler: I can see Liverpool winning but it won\'t guarantee title</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D05FD4200000578-664_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601625/EXCLUSIVE-When-Jamie-met-Yaya-Liverpool-amazing-This-game-WILL-decide-title.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601625/EXCLUSIVE-When-Jamie-met-Yaya-Liverpool-amazing-This-game-WILL-decide-title.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"EXCLUSIVE: When Jamie met Yaya - \'Liverpool have been amazing. This game WILL decide the title\'\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601625/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">422</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601625-1CCEB51E00000578-955_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:37','2014-04-11 13:03:59'),(94,'29cdd87aaac1043f65095d63918af1858bcab11f2d883a1a9b83c7ec2fe72e8b','dailymail',NULL,'MASTERS 2014: Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Caroline Wozniacki in watching Rory McIlroy','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html',' By Shane Mcgrath Published: 05:13 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 05:14 EST, 11 April 2014 6 View comments Rory McIlroy is predicting a \'grinding\' battle for the Masters after a punishing first day in Augusta - but he sits just three shots off the lead. McIlroy finished one under par, a shot ahead of Graeme McDowell and three behind first-round leader Bill Haas. He could have been a shot closer but for a dropped shot at the 18th, but McIlroy was pleased with surviving 18 holes notable for the speed of the greens. ‘They are getting firm and fast already. There are putts you hit, look like they’re going in, then they shave the edge and you’re four or five feet by.  Fairway to go: Rory McIlroy is well placed after a promising first round at the Masters   Now watch this drive: The Northern Irishman tees off on the famous final hole at Augusta on Thursday   Challenge: McIlroy reckons the greens will become harder under the sun as the week goes on  ‘To score anything around 70 today, people would take it,’ he said. However, with the ground expected to get even harder under a baking Georgian sun, McIlroy admitted he will have to adapt as his powerful long game will not count for as much. ‘It brings the guys that don’t hit it as far, into the mix a little bit more, because it’s not just about power. It’s about precision and making sure you’re going to the right place and it becomes more of a mental challenge than anything else. ‘It hasn’t been my forte in the past, but I’ll learn to love it this week.’ Pink hair and Geordie light-entertainment mavens were but two features of the McIlroy caravan during the first round. He was a favourite for this tournament even before the withdrawal of Tiger Woods, but the fiendishness of Augusta National has crumbled big fancies to dust in the past. Short odds, then, did not explain the large crowds following him.  Well played, darling: McIlroy chats with fiance Caroline Wozniacki after the first round in Georgia   Takeaway: Ant and Dec have jetted from Britain to Georgia to watch McIlroy at the Masters   Lady in red: The Danish tennis star is sporting a dramatic hair colour at the Masters this week  Fame did. He is talented and his personality and charisma are repeatedly praised, but the entire package can be filed under fame. His girlfriend, Caroline Wozniacki, was the owner of the coloured hair. She moved unobtrusively following the fortunes of her fiance, generally unnoticed but occasionally getting snagged on the attentions of spectators who knew the face below the shocking hair. Ant and Dec were part of the snaking support that followed McIlroy, Jordan Spieth and Patrick Reed, too. The two TV hosts have not worn America down with their insubstantial Saturday evening fare the way Britain and Ireland have submitted to their cheeky charms, so they were here merely another pair of golf fans hitched on to the most interesting battle of the day.   More... Great Scott in charge: Defending champ off to a flying start in Augusta as Haas leads the way... but Watson and McIlroy are in sight Fitzpatrick shows his mettle after first hole to forget on Masters debut MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happens at Augusta National AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain Gallacher enjoys dream start and McIlroy shines but Brits find it rough going at Augusta Masters 2014: First round leaderboard - Haas leads the way at Augusta  Share or comment on this article','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Shane+Mcgrath\" rel=\"nofollow\">Shane Mcgrath</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 05:13 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 05:14 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">6</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rory McIlroy is predicting a \'grinding\' battle for the Masters after a punishing first day in Augusta - but he sits just three shots off the lead. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">McIlroy finished one under par, a shot ahead of Graeme McDowell and three behind first-round leader Bill Haas. He could have been a shot closer but for a dropped shot at the 18th, but McIlroy was pleased with surviving 18 holes notable for the speed of the greens. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘They are getting firm and fast already. There are putts you hit, look like they’re going in, then they shave the edge and you’re four or five feet by. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fairway to go: Rory McIlroy is well placed after a promising first round at the Masters\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"424\" id=\"i-a56d0e47\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602331-1D005A8600000578-402_634x424.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fairway to go: Rory McIlroy is well placed after a promising first round at the Masters</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Now watch this drive: The Northern Irishman tees off on the famous final hole at Augusta on Thursday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a60c0e4d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602331-1D01D17900000578-815_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Now watch this drive: The Northern Irishman tees off on the famous final hole at Augusta on Thursday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Challenge: McIlroy reckons the greens will become harder under the sun as the week goes on\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"414\" id=\"i-a6ca0e55\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602331-1D01E33D00000578-135_634x414.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Challenge: McIlroy reckons the greens will become harder under the sun as the week goes on</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘To score anything around 70 today, people would take it,’ he said.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">However, with the ground expected to get even harder under a baking Georgian sun, McIlroy admitted he will have to adapt as his powerful long game will not count for as much. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It brings the guys that don’t hit it as far, into the mix a little bit more, because it’s not just about power. It’s about precision and making sure you’re going to the right place and it becomes more of a mental challenge than anything else.</font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘It hasn’t been my forte in the past, but I’ll learn to love it this week.’  <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Pink hair and Geordie light-entertainment mavens were but two features of the McIlroy caravan during the first round. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He was a favourite for this tournament even before the withdrawal of Tiger Woods, but the fiendishness of Augusta National has crumbled big fancies to dust in the past. Short odds, then, did not explain the large crowds following him. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Well played, darling: McIlroy chats with fiance Caroline Wozniacki after the first round in Georgia\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"431\" id=\"i-a6fd0e5d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602331-1D01C04B00000578-897_634x431.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">