hed on to the most interesting battle of the day.<br/></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2601985/Masters-2014-Adam-Scott-flying-start-Bill-Haas-leads-way-Rory-McIlroy-right-tail.html\"> Great Scott in charge: Defending champ off to a flying start in Augusta as Haas leads the way... but Watson and McIlroy are in sight</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602008/Matt-Fitzpatrick-shows-mettle-hole-forget-Masters-debut.html\"> Fitzpatrick shows his mettle after first hole to forget on Masters debut</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602063/MASTERS-LIVE-All-second-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\"> MASTERS LIVE: All the second-round action as it happens at Augusta National</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2601950/AUGUSTA-TEE-ROOM-Gareth-Bale-cheering-Dustin-Johnson-Spain.html\"> AUGUSTA TEE ROOM: Johnson doesn\'t just have Gretzky behind him... Real superstar Bale is also cheering American on in Spain</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602081/Gallacher-enjoys-dream-start-McIlroy-shines-Brits-rough-going-Augusta.html\"> Gallacher enjoys dream start and McIlroy shines but Brits find it rough going at Augusta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2601989/Masters-2014-First-round-leaderboard-Haas-leads-way-Augusta.html\"> Masters 2014: First round leaderboard - Haas leads the way at Augusta</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602331/MASTERS-2014-Augustas-Got-Talent-Ant-Dec-join-Caroline-Wozniacki-watching-Rory-McIlroy.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Augusta\'s Got Talent: Ant and Dec join Wozniacki in watching McIlroy\'s slog in the sun at the Masters\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602331/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602331-1D01C04B00000578-895_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:38','2014-04-11 12:14:58'),(95,'99825cef83ce0018d399fb9bb2f98100e6d861155cfa5d02ab1494e4e961a753','dailymail',NULL,'DeGale in line for potential Groves rematch after signing with Hearn\'s Matchroom','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html',' By Martin Domin Follow @@martin_domin Published: 06:47 EST, 10 April 2014 | Updated: 03:50 EST, 11 April 2014 15 shares 32 View comments  At his lowest ebb, James DeGale considering giving up boxing; now he’s on the verge of a world title fight – and revenge. The super middleweight will fight Brandon Gonzalez on the undercard of George Groves’ rematch with Carl Froch at Wembley on May 31. The two winners will meet later in the year, possibly giving DeGale the chance to avenge his defeat to bitter rival Groves in 2011.  Deal sealed: James DeGale has signed with Eddie Hearn\'s Matchroom and will fight at Wembley on May 31 Big bout: DeGale will fight on the Carl Froch-George Groves undercard against Brandon Gonzales James DeGale joins Matchroom The 28-year-old was speaking as he confirmed his switch to Eddie Hearn’s Matchroom stable after leaving Mick Hennessy last week. ‘If I\'m brutally honest, I was unhappy, depressed if anything,’ he admitted. I wasn’t sleeping at night, constantly thinking about my next move. ‘I didn’t want to train, there was a time I wanted to give it the elbow and give up. ‘But I’ve got a good family and team around me and they were like, “James, stop being stupid”. ‘They got me back on track and I feel re-energized now and I’ve got a new lease of life. ‘If I were you lot, I’d fasten your seat belt and enjoy the ride.’  Defeat: DeGale suffered the first loss of his professional career to George Groves in May 2011 On board: Hearn has snapped up DeGale after he split with promoter Mick Hennessy last week When pressed on which of his British rivals he wanted to fight, DeGale added: \'Groves. But I\'m not too sure if he\'s going to win. It\'s a 50/50 fight and I can\'t pick who\'s going to win but i want my revenge on \"ugly boy\". \'But I can\'t overlook this guy. He\'s unbeaten and trained with Andre Ward and Amir Khan so that must give him an extra push.\' DeGale, who is bidding to become the first British Olympic gold medallist to win a professional world title, has endured a frustrating time since his contentious defeat to Groves. Despite beating Piotr Wilczewski to win the European title just five months later, a shot at the ultimate prize has thus far remained elusive. DeGale signed with Hennessy after leaving Frank Warren in 2012 but it has taken six fights to manoeuvre him into a mandatory position with the WBC.  Aiming high: DeGale is bidding to become the first British Olympic gold medallist to win a world title   Addressing the media: Hearn and DeGale announce the new deal at a press conference in London  Gold: DeGale won the middleweight competition at the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing He has instead opted to fight a final eliminator to challenge for the IBF belt held by Froch - at least for the time being. But while his bitter west London rival Groves has seen his profile rocket following his controversial defeat to Froch last November, DeGale\'s has plummeted in equal measure. From the O2 Arena to a shopping centre in Kent, DeGale has slipped off British boxing’s radar. He will hope that is all about to change.   More... Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley British referee Keane forced out of huge Pacquiao-Bradley rematch with sickness Which sports star showed off his jewellery collection on Instagram? Burns splits with trainer Nelson as Scot looks towards reclaiming world title   Share or comment on this article 15shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Martin+Domin\" rel=\"nofollow\">Martin Domin</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@martin_domin\">Follow @@martin_domin</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 06:47 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 03:50 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"DeGale in line for potential Groves rematch after signing with Hearn\'s Matchroom\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 15</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">32</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">At his lowest ebb, James DeGale considering giving up boxing; now he’s on the verge of a world title fight – and revenge.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The super middleweight will fight Brandon Gonzalez on the undercard of George Groves’ rematch with Carl Froch at Wembley on May 31.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The two winners will meet later in the year, possibly giving DeGale the chance to avenge his defeat to bitter rival Groves in 2011.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Deal sealed: James DeGale has signed with Eddie Hearn\'s Matchroom and will fight at Wembley on May 31\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"511\" id=\"i-ad6e0e94\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-1CFE1F6C00000578-869_634x511.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Deal sealed: James DeGale has signed with Eddie Hearn\'s Matchroom and will fight at Wembley on May 31</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Big bout: DeGale will fight on the Carl Froch-George Groves undercard against Brandon Gonzales\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"498\" id=\"i-aa300e7b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-1CFF345500000578-347_634x498.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Big bout: DeGale will fight on the Carl Froch-George Groves undercard against Brandon Gonzales</p> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3455804906001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">James DeGale joins Matchroom</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D057C6800000578-139_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The 28-year-old was speaking as he confirmed his switch to Eddie Hearn’s Matchroom stable after leaving Mick Hennessy last week.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘If I\'m brutally honest, I was unhappy, depressed if anything,’ he admitted. I wasn’t sleeping at night, constantly thinking about my next move.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘I didn’t want to train, there was a time I wanted to give it the elbow and give up.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘But I’ve got a good family and team around me and they were like, “James, stop being stupid”.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘They got me back on track and I feel re-energized now and I’ve got a new lease of life.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘If I were you lot, I’d fasten your seat belt and enjoy the ride.’</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Defeat: DeGale suffered the first loss of his professional career to George Groves in May 2011\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"428\" id=\"i-9a2f0e2a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-0F4382D200000578-71_634x428.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Defeat: DeGale suffered the first loss of his professional career to George Groves in May 2011</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On board: Hearn has snapped up DeGale after he split with promoter Mick Hennessy last week\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"535\" id=\"i-ad330e92\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-1CFE5AD700000578-239_634x535.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On board: Hearn has snapped up DeGale after he split with promoter Mick Hennessy last week</p> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">When pressed on which of his British rivals he wanted to fight, DeGale added: \'Groves. But I\'m not too sure if he\'s going to win. It\'s a 50/50 fight and I can\'t pick who\'s going to win but i want my revenge on \"ugly boy\".</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'But I can\'t overlook this guy. He\'s unbeaten and trained with Andre Ward and Amir Khan so that must give him an extra push.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">DeGale, who is bidding to become the first British Olympic gold medallist to win a professional world title, has endured a frustrating time since his contentious defeat to Groves.<br/> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Despite beating Piotr Wilczewski to win the European title just five months later, a shot at the ultimate prize has thus far remained elusive.<br/> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">DeGale signed with Hennessy after leaving Frank Warren in 2012 but it has taken six fights to manoeuvre him into a mandatory position with the WBC.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Aiming high: DeGale is bidding to become the first British Olympic gold medallist to win a world title\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-ad5e0e94\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-1CFF5D8A00000578-382_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Aiming high: DeGale is bidding to become the first British Olympic gold medallist to win a world title</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Addressing the media: Hearn and DeGale announce the new deal at a press conference in London\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-ab5e0e78\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-1CFF5D8000000578-217_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Addressing the media: Hearn and DeGale announce the new deal at a press conference in London</p> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Gold: DeGale won the middleweight competition at the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-a8500e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-0264D2DE00000578-234_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Gold: DeGale won the middleweight competition at the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He has instead opted to fight a final eliminator to challenge for the IBF belt held by Froch - at least for the time being.<br/> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But while his bitter west London rival Groves has seen his profile rocket following his controversial defeat to Froch last November, DeGale\'s has plummeted in equal measure.<br/> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">From the O2 Arena to a shopping centre in Kent, DeGale has slipped off British boxing’s radar.<br/> </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He will hope that is all about to change.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600995/Tim-Bradley-nearly-committed-suicide-Manny-Pacquiao-decision.html\"> Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600192/Pacquiao-sets-sights-Mayweather-Marquez-revenge-against-Bradley.html\"> Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600177/British-boxing-referee-John-Keane-forced-Manny-Pacquiaos-rematch-Tim-Bradley-illness.html\"> British referee Keane forced out of huge Pacquiao-Bradley rematch with sickness</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2598769/Floyd-Mayweather-shows-jewellery-Instagram.html\"> Which sports star showed off his jewellery collection on Instagram?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2599103/Ricky-Burns-splits-trainer-Nelson-Scot-looks-reclaiming-world-title.html\"> Burns splits with trainer Nelson as Scot looks towards reclaiming world title</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601486/DeGale-fight-Froch-Groves-undercard-signing-Hearns-Matchroom.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"DeGale in line for potential Groves rematch after signing with Hearn\'s Matchroom\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601486/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">15</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601486-1CFE1F6C00000578-240_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:40','2014-04-11 10:50:09'),(96,'1475e6e36d4463f55fe8c64aa94853b6be3a821805095059c7960cb7d6bb5e8f','dailymail',NULL,'Joe Hart says winning the Premier League in 2012 makes him hungry to do it again','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602173/Joe-Hart-says-winning-Premier-League-2012-makes-hungry-again.html',' By Ben Baker Published: 01:02 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 03:06 EST, 11 April 2014 14 shares 20 View comments England goalkeeper Joe Hart has rubbished suggestions having been there and done it in a tight Premier League title race gives Manchester City the edge second time around. With just a month left in this season’s title race, it looks like being one of the closest finishes yet with Man City, Liverpool and Chelsea all eyeing up the prize come May. While Chelsea has been accustomed to fighting for domestic dominance since the arrival of Roman Abramovich, Liverpool are relatively new to the experience having finished seventh last season. VIDEO: Watch Joe Hart talk about the title race and England\'s chances at the World Cup  Safe hands: Joe Hart has rediscovered his best form for City this season   Title aim: Hart believes City are capable of winning their second Premier League title  Joe Hart is reunited with his first coach More... EXCLUSIVE: When Jamie met Yaya - \'Liverpool have been amazing. This game WILL decide the title\' Aguero can inject some title-winning flair just like Tevez did, claims City star Zabaleta Watch City star Negredo score screamer in training ahead of Liverpool title showdown He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training Olympiacos target Boyata as City defender looks set to leave Etihad this summer LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title As for City, they can harp back to memories of two seasons ago when they snatched the title out of arch rivals Manchester United’s hands on goal difference thanks to a last-gasp Sergio Aguero strike against QPR on the final day. But with this campaign fast becoming a three-horse race with an extra team thrown into the mix, England goalkeeper Hart is adamant City’s maiden Premier League success and the pressures it put them through will have no bearing on the destination of the title this season. \'I have been lucky that a lot of my career so far has been pretty exciting,\' said Hart, speaking on behalf of the Gillette Great Start programme. \'There has always been stuff coming up or things on the horizon and right now we are in the thick of a title race. \'I don’t know if having been there and done it before helps. It has not been a hindrance but things have changed and times changed and everything is different.  Leaving it late: Sergio Aguero scores against QPR in the dying seconds of the season to win the title in 2012   We\'ve done it! Hart celebrates the dramatic end to the 2012 season   Winning the big one: City players celebrate with the Premier League title  \'It is not a bad thing that a few of us have got a winner’s medal already but we are all just as hungry for another one and while everything is different we are ready for it. \'It is going to be an exciting day on Sunday against Liverpool first and foremost and that is what we are concentrating on. There has been a lot of build up but we remain focused. \'We had a big game at the weekend against Southampton and got a good result out of that so we go into Liverpool confident.\' Hart also has a World Cup in football’s spiritual home of Brazil to occupy his thoughts, although earlier this season it didn’t look too promising. After a momentary loss of form Hart was dropped for Costel Pantilimon in November with the Romanian holding the fort for two months.  Brazil bound: Hart is hoping to help England do well at the World Cup this summer  But Hart was thrown back into the thick of the action just before Christmas against Fulham and he hasn’t looked back since, producing a string of commanding performances to cement his place as No 1 at Manchester City and also for England. \'We [Man City] have put ourselves in the position with a lot of hard work and hopefully that will finish the way we want to with that even bigger carrot of the summer tournament for me,\' he added. \'It is easy to get carried away and look forward to that but right now it is hard because there is so much going on in my football life right now. \'I am focused on things with Man City and I believe that if that all goes well I can take it on into the summer.  Flying save: Hart believes City can go on and win the title - but says it won\'t be easy  \'We all want to finish our season well for our clubs and see where we go from there.\' Meanwhile, Hart’s first goalkeeping coach Dave Timmins believes Joe Hart’s loyalty to Shrewsbury has been crucial in propelling the England shot stopper to the cusp of a World Cup debut. Timmins first encountered Hart when the young goalkeeper was just eight, the coach and his apprentice joining forces at Shrewsbury Town and with Shropshire Schools Football. The relationship lasted a decade before Hart, who is a brand ambassador for Gillette and is helping to launch this year’s Great Start programme, was picked up by Man City in 2006, the 26-year-old being able to boast Premier League and FA Cup-winning campaigns on his CV.  Starting out: Hart began his career at Shrewsbury   Reunited: Hart attends a training session with Dave Timmins - his first goalkeeping coach  But the two were reunited on Monday at the AJ Bell Stadium to help launch the 2014 Gillette Great Start Programme, which supports and celebrates great coaches who inspire the next generation at every level by awarding coaching grants through the scheme. \'I first came across Joe most probably when he was eight years of age with Shrewsbury Town, Timmins said. \'We used to train on a second hand light off the Astroturf on the grass and he just loved diving around. \'And quite quickly after about six weeks we moved him up into the under-11s and 12s group because he wasn’t afraid. \'When he was about 13 or 14 was when I really started to see that there was something special about Joe. \'It was quite funny really because he was trialing at other clubs but for whatever reason they never sorted it out with him. \'It was good really because it was good for me, good for Shrewsbury Town and I believe good for himself too as he got to experience first team football rather than potentially just sit on a bench somewhere. \'He is a loyal lad too, loyal to Shrewsbury Town and at that age he just stuck with it and look where he is now.\'  Gillette’s Great Start programme celebrates the role of coaching and encourages people to get into coaching by offering grants. To apply for a coaching grant visit www.facebook.com/GilletteUK open from the 8th April 2014. Fowler: I can see Liverpool winning but it won\'t guarantee title Kolo Toure: We\'re fighting for the title, definitely   More... EXCLUSIVE: When Jamie met Yaya - \'Liverpool have been amazing. This game WILL decide the title\' Aguero can inject some title-winning flair just like Tevez did, claims City star Zabaleta Watch City star Negredo score screamer in training ahead of Liverpool title showdown He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training Olympiacos target Boyata as City defender looks set to leave Etihad this summer LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title   Share or comment on this article 14shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Ben+Baker\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ben Baker</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 01:02 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 03:06 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602173/Joe-Hart-says-winning-Premier-League-2012-makes-hungry-again.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602173/Joe-Hart-says-winning-Premier-League-2012-makes-hungry-again.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Winning the title in 2012 makes me hungry to do it again, claims City keeper Hart\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 14</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2602173/Joe-Hart-says-winning-Premier-League-2012-makes-hungry-again.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">20</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">England goalkeeper Joe Hart has rubbished suggestions having been there and done it in a tight Premier League title race gives Manchester City the edge second time around.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With just a month left in this season’s title race, it looks like being one of the closest finishes yet with Man City, Liverpool and Chelsea all eyeing up the prize come May.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">While Chelsea has been accustomed to fighting for domestic dominance since the arrival of Roman Abramovich, Liverpool are relatively new to the experience having finished seventh last season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO:</span></font> Watch Joe Hart talk about the title race and England\'s chances at the World Cup</b><br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Safe hands: Joe Hart has rediscovered his best form for City this season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"352\" id=\"i-a9aa0e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-1CDB1D0200000578-866_634x352.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Safe hands: Joe Hart has rediscovered his best form for City this season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Title aim: Hart believes City are capable of winning their second Premier League title\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"403\" id=\"i-aa9f0e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-1CDCB24800000578-973_634x403.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Title aim: Hart believes City are capable of winning their second Premier League title</p> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3455621660001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Joe Hart is reunited with his first coach</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D04FC7900000578-797_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"floatRHS\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601625/EXCLUSIVE-When-Jamie-met-Yaya-Liverpool-amazing-This-game-WILL-decide-title.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: When Jamie met Yaya - \'Liverpool have been amazing. This game WILL decide the title\'</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602041/Sergio-Aguero-inject-title-winning-flair-just-like-Carlos-Tevez-did-claims-City-star-Pablo-Zabaleta.html\"> Aguero can inject some title-winning flair just like Tevez did, claims City star Zabaleta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601801/Watch-City-star-Negredo-score-screamer-training-ahead-Liverpool-title-showdown.html\"> Watch City star Negredo score screamer in training ahead of Liverpool title showdown</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601553/Hes-Sergio-Aguero-ready-Liverpool-star-steps-injury-recovery-training.html\"> He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601643/Olympiacos-target-Boyata-City-defender-looks-set-leave-Etihad-summer.html\"> Olympiacos target Boyata as City defender looks set to leave Etihad this summer</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601458/LIVERPOOL-vs-MANCHESTER-CITY-All-latest-team-news-stats-crunch-battle-race-Premier-League-title.html\"> LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title</a></li> </ul> </div> <br/> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As for City, they can harp back to memories of two seasons ago when they snatched the title out of arch rivals Manchester United’s hands on goal difference thanks to a last-gasp Sergio Aguero strike against QPR on the final day.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But with this campaign fast becoming a three-horse race with an extra team thrown into the mix, England goalkeeper Hart is adamant City’s maiden Premier League success and the pressures it put them through will have no bearing on the destination of the title this season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I have been lucky that a lot of my career so far has been pretty exciting,\' said Hart, speaking on behalf of the Gillette Great Start programme.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'There has always been stuff coming up or things on the horizon and right now we are in the thick of a title race.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I don’t know if having been there and done it before helps. It has not been a hindrance but things have changed and times changed and everything is different.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Leaving it late: Sergio Aguero scores against QPR in the dying seconds of the season to win the title in 2012\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"363\" id=\"i-a5eb0e52\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-07922F6700000514-968_634x363.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Leaving it late: Sergio Aguero scores against QPR in the dying seconds of the season to win the title in 2012</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"We\'ve done it! Hart celebrates the dramatic end to the 2012 season\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"413\" id=\"i-9c4a0e44\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-15FD6629000005DC-74_634x413.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">We\'ve done it! Hart celebrates the dramatic end to the 2012 season</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Winning the big one: City players celebrate with the Premier League title\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"448\" id=\"i-aa440e82\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-16AAC0A0000005DC-236_634x448.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Winning the big one: City players celebrate with the Premier League title</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It is not a bad thing that a few of us have got a winner’s medal already but we are all just as hungry for another one and while everything is different we are ready for it.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It is going to be an exciting day on Sunday against Liverpool first and foremost and that is what we are concentrating on. There has been a lot of build up but we remain focused.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We had a big game at the weekend against Southampton and got a good result out of that so we go into Liverpool confident.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Hart also has a World Cup in football’s spiritual home of Brazil to occupy his thoughts, although earlier this season it didn’t look too promising.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">After a momentary loss of form Hart was dropped for Costel Pantilimon in November with the Romanian holding the fort for two months.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Brazil bound: Hart is hoping to help England do well at the World Cup this summer\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"367\" id=\"i-ab0e0e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-1CB83F5F00000578-178_634x367.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Brazil bound: Hart is hoping to help England do well at the World Cup this summer</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But Hart was thrown back into the thick of the action just before Christmas against Fulham and he hasn’t looked back since, producing a string of commanding performances to cement his place as No 1 at Manchester City and also for England. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We [Man City] have put ourselves in the position with a lot of hard work and hopefully that will finish the way we want to with that even bigger carrot of the summer tournament for me,\' he added.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It is easy to get carried away and look forward to that but right now it is hard because there is so much going on in my football life right now.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I am focused on things with Man City and I believe that if that all goes well I can take it on into the summer.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Flying save: Hart believes City can go on and win the title - but says it won\'t be easy\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"456\" id=\"i-ab9c0e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-1CDAD53C00000578-254_634x456.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Flying save: Hart believes City can go on and win the title - but says it won\'t be easy</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We all want to finish our season well for our clubs and see where we go from there.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Meanwhile, Hart’s first goalkeeping coach Dave Timmins believes Joe Hart’s loyalty to Shrewsbury has been crucial in propelling the England shot stopper to the cusp of a World Cup debut.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Timmins first encountered Hart when the young goalkeeper was just eight, the coach and his apprentice joining forces at Shrewsbury Town and with Shropshire Schools Football.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The relationship lasted a decade before Hart, who is a brand ambassador for Gillette and is helping to launch this year’s Great Start programme, was picked up by Man City in 2006, the 26-year-old being able to boast Premier League and FA Cup-winning campaigns on his CV.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Starting out: Hart began his career at Shrewsbury\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a85e0e65\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-1D04FE5000000578-476_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Starting out: Hart began his career at Shrewsbury</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Reunited: Hart attends a training session with Dave Timmins - his first goalkeeping coach\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"516\" id=\"i-a6b40e54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-1D04D56500000578-540_634x516.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Reunited: Hart attends a training session with Dave Timmins - his first goalkeeping coach</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But the two were reunited on Monday at the AJ Bell Stadium to help launch the 2014 Gillette Great Start Programme, which supports and celebrates great coaches who inspire the next generation at every level by awarding coaching grants through the scheme. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I first came across Joe most probably when he was eight years of age with Shrewsbury Town, Timmins said. \'We used to train on a second hand light off the Astroturf on the grass and he just loved diving around.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'And quite quickly after about six weeks we moved him up into the under-11s and 12s group because he wasn’t afraid. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'When he was about 13 or 14 was when I really started to see that there was something special about Joe.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It was quite funny really because he was trialing at other clubs but for whatever reason they never sorted it out with him.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It was good really because it was good for me, good for Shrewsbury Town and I believe good for himself too as he got to experience first team football rather than potentially just sit on a bench somewhere.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'He is a loyal lad too, loyal to Shrewsbury Town and at that age he just stuck with it and look where he is now.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><i><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Gillette’s Great Start programme celebrates the role of coaching and encourages people to get into coaching by offering grants. To apply for a coaching grant visit <a href=\"www.facebook.com/GilletteUK\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">www.facebook.com/GilletteUK</a> open from the 8th April 2014.</font></i>  </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3455825791001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Fowler: I can see Liverpool winning but it won\'t guarantee title</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D05FD4200000578-664_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3455793961001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Kolo Toure: We\'re fighting for the title, definitely</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/video-undefined-1D05D5D100000578-786_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601625/EXCLUSIVE-When-Jamie-met-Yaya-Liverpool-amazing-This-game-WILL-decide-title.html\"> EXCLUSIVE: When Jamie met Yaya - \'Liverpool have been amazing. This game WILL decide the title\'</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602041/Sergio-Aguero-inject-title-winning-flair-just-like-Carlos-Tevez-did-claims-City-star-Pablo-Zabaleta.html\"> Aguero can inject some title-winning flair just like Tevez did, claims City star Zabaleta</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601801/Watch-City-star-Negredo-score-screamer-training-ahead-Liverpool-title-showdown.html\"> Watch City star Negredo score screamer in training ahead of Liverpool title showdown</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601553/Hes-Sergio-Aguero-ready-Liverpool-star-steps-injury-recovery-training.html\"> He\'s behind you! Aguero ready for Liverpool as star steps up injury recovery in training</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601643/Olympiacos-target-Boyata-City-defender-looks-set-leave-Etihad-summer.html\"> Olympiacos target Boyata as City defender looks set to leave Etihad this summer</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601458/LIVERPOOL-vs-MANCHESTER-CITY-All-latest-team-news-stats-crunch-battle-race-Premier-League-title.html\"> LIVERPOOL vs MANCHESTER CITY: All the latest team news and stats for the crunch battle in race for Premier League title</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602173/Joe-Hart-says-winning-Premier-League-2012-makes-hungry-again.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602173/Joe-Hart-says-winning-Premier-League-2012-makes-hungry-again.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Winning the title in 2012 makes me hungry to do it again, claims City keeper Hart\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2602173/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">14</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602173-1CDB1D0200000578-837_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:41','2014-04-11 10:06:17'),(97,'ed7d918614c00195fad5b36c1f074aa2e38e3346303a6ec9328b75e4f44f552c','dailymail',NULL,'Something for the Weekend: Liverpool vs Manchester City, Arsenal vs Wigan Athletic and Hull City vs Sheffield United centre stage in football preview','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html',' By Adam Shergold Follow @@adamjshergold Published: 19:05 EST, 10 April 2014 | Updated: 03:02 EST, 11 April 2014 23 shares 12 View comments  A poignant weekend awaits as football joins together to remember the 96 victims of the Hillsborough Disaster 25 years on. The events of April 15, 1989 changed football profoundly and, while the crusade for justice continues in the courts, we will this weekend take a moment to reflect and remember those who died supporting the team they loved. Across the English football schedule, matches will kick off seven minutes later than usual, preceded by a minutes\' silence in memory of the victims.  25th anniversary: Steven Gerrard holds up a commemorative patch to be worn on Liverpool\'s shirts during Sunday\'s match with Manchester City, as football marks the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough Disaster   Never forgotten: Kick-offs have been pushed back seven minutes and there will be a minute\'s silence before every game in England this weekend, while Liverpool will honour the 96 victims with this shirt tribute   Eternal flame: Floral tributes left at the Hillsborough memorial outside Anfield on last year\'s anniversary  It will be particularly emotional at Anfield, where Liverpool take on Manchester City in a season-defining game on Sunday afternoon. That\'s the weekend\'s highlight but we also have the pick of the action from the FA Cup semi-finals, Football League and beyond.  Liverpool vs Manchester City, Barclays Premier League, Sunday 1.37pm, Sky Sports 1  There will be no louder roar in an English football stadium this season than when Mark Clattenburg blows his whistle to signal the end of the minutes\' silence at Anfield on Sunday afternoon. For Liverpool fans, the occasion will be emotional enough as they mark the passing of 25 years since the Hillsborough tragedy took 96 of their brothers. That combined with the very real chance they are going to win their first league championship in 24 years will almost be enough to lift the roof off.  Written in the stars: With the team sat top of the Premier League, Liverpool fans are dreaming of a first title triumph in 24 years   Pointing the way to the title? Manager Brendan Rodgers during Liverpool\'s training session on Thursday ahead of their important clash with Manchester City   Sitting pretty: Liverpool currently enjoy a two-point lead over Chelsea and four over Manchester City  Sunday\'s season-defining match between the two title favourites is the hottest ticket on Merseyside in years, with £5,000 needed to buy a pair from certain online vendors this week. There are many who see a Liverpool triumph as a breath of fresh air for the league, smashing the hegemony of the Manchester clubs and Chelsea at long last. Manager Brendan Rodgers wants his team to cross the finish line first to honour the memories of the \'96 fans in the sky\' and he will be encouraged ahead of this big game by the statistics. Liverpool have faced four of the top seven at Anfield this season and won them all, scoring 14 goals and conceding just once.  Unplayable: Luis Suarez has scored 29 league goals this season to propel Liverpool\'s title push   In hot pursuit: Stevan Jovetic rounds off Manchester City\'s 4-1 win over Southampton last weekend   Outstanding: Yaya Toure has scored 18 league goals from midfield - the third-highest tally in the top scorers\' chart  More... Bumming around! Liverpool in good spirits ahead of title showdown as Suarez and Co are put through their paces Ronaldo injury rocks Real! Star could be out of the Copa del Rey final with muscle tear Messi can\'t be bothered, Xavi\'s too weak and they\'re a shambles at the back. What the hell is going on at Barcelona? MARTIN SAMUEL - THE DEBATE: I\'m not anti-Everton, I\'m just against the loan system - but the foolish paranoia of football fans never ceases to amaze me TACKLE KEOWN: Why Azpilicueta could be just the man to stop rampant Robben... and who was the fittest star I ever played with? They also have a very good home record against Manchester City, who have won just one of the last 16 Anfield meetings - and that was 11 years ago. In terms of the engrossing title race, a Liverpool win would take them seven points clear of City, who retain two matches in hand. Three points for City and the pendulum swings towards them, while a draw brings Chelsea back into contention. They play at Swansea later on Sunday afternoon. Hopefully the match will live up to expectations - on the face of it, we should see goals galore. Liverpool have scored 90 league goals this season, just three shy of City\'s overall total from their title-winning 2011-2012 campaign. City have 84 themselves this term. There\'s really no excuse for the strikers!  Wigan Athletic vs Arsenal, FA Cup semi-final, Wembley, Saturday 5.07pm, ITV With such important fixtures in the Premier League, it\'s quite easy to forget it\'s FA Cup semi-final weekend as well. Arsenal will be the clear bookmakers\' favourites to end their nine-year trophy drought by winning the competition but an upset cannot be ruled out against Wigan. While league status, squad strength and Cup pedigree all point to a Gunners victory on Saturday teatime, there is a nagging feeling of foreboding after the Latics\' dual wins over Manchester City in last season\'s final and this season\'s sixth round.  Repeat performance: Wigan won the FA Cup last season, stunning Manchester City in the final, and will aim to do the same against Arsenal   Deja-vu: James Perch celebrates scoring what proved to be Wigan\'s winning goal against Manchester City in the sixth round   Long wait: Arsenal last lifted the FA Cup in 2005 but are favourites to end their trophy drought this time  ARSENAL\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY 3rd Round Tottenham (H) 2-04th Round Coventry City (H) 4-05th Round Liverpool (H) 2-16th Round Everton (H) 4-1 The two sides have never met in the FA Cup but Arsenal dominate the overall head-to-head record with 15 wins out of 20. They were also responsible for sending Wigan back down into the Championship last season, just three days after they had stunned Manchester City in the final. \'We are the massive underdogs,\' said Wigan manager Uwe Rosler. \'We are going to Wembley, we can\'t lose. We only can win. \'Arsenal really have to go for the FA Cup, their own players said it this week. That puts extra pressure on Arsenal.\'  Underdog: Uwe Rosler is confident that Wigan can spring another surprise at Arsenal on Saturday   Match winner: Wigan\'s Martyn Waghorn celebrates his goal against Leeds United last weekend but the Latics lost to Millwall in midweek  WIGAN\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY 3rd Round MK Dons (H) 3-3Replay MK Dons (A) 3-14th Round Crystal Palace (H) 2-15th Round Cardiff City (A) 2-16th Round Manchester City (A) 2-1 As does a backlog of injuries that has not exactly helped as Arsenal\'s title challenge fell apart and their grip on the fourth Champions League has floundered. Arsene Wenger will be without Mathieu Flamini, who must serve a two-match suspension after collecting a 10th yellow card of the season at Everton. Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain, Tomas Rosicky, Laurent Koscielny, Mesut Ozil and Jack Wilshere are all on the treatment table, giving the manager a bit of a selection headache. Could it all be set for another glorious giant-killing from Wigan?  Off the boil: Arsenal\'s hopes of qualifying for the Champions League took a hit with a 3-0 defeat at Everton last weekend   Missing: Mathieu Flamini (centre) is suspended and one of a number of players Arsene Wenger will have to do without at Wembley   Hull City vs Sheffield United, FA Cup semi-final, Wembley, Sunday 4.07pm, BT Sport 1 Expect a sizeable migration south from Yorkshire on Sunday as Hull City and Sheffield United aim to book a return Wembley ticket for the end of next month. Both teams have embarked on remarkable runs to reach this stage and though it\'s first tier against third, you would imagine the occasion will provide a leveller. It\'s been an eventful week on Humberside as owner Assem Allam\'s attempts to change the club\'s name to Hull Tigers was thrown out by the FA Council.  Rejected: The FA Council this week turned down an application by Hull City owner Assem Allam to change to club\'s name to Hull Tigers   Dyed in the wool: Hull fans have staged protests at the KC Stadium against the proposed name change  HULL CITY\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY 3rd Round Middlesbrough (A) 2-04th Round Southend United (A) 2-05th Round Brighton (H) 2-16th Round Sunderland (H) 3-0 It had looked like the vocal fan protests inside the ground had fallen on deaf ears when a rather suspicious and undemocratic ballot of less than half of season ticket holders found that a \'majority\' were in favour of a change. But just as Allam thought he finally had a mandate, the authorities sensibly stopped the plans dead. It now remains to be seen whether the Egyptian takes the matter further but it\'s good to see the powers that be taking a stand against careless owners who think a century of history and heritage can be tossed away on a whim.  Staying out of it: Hull manager Steve Bruce has kept his counsel on the name change   Close knit: Hull\'s players celebrate George Boyd\'s winner in last weekend\'s 1-0 home win over Swansea, a result that should secure their Premier League survival  In the meantime, manager Steve Bruce has kept his counsel and concentrated on this historic occasion, admitting he has a series of \'horrible\' selection dilemmas to address. \'I\'ve got 25 players and I can pick 11, so I\'m going to have more people disappointed than happy,\' Bruce told the Hull Daily Mail. Should they do what is expected and beat the Blades, they will reach a first ever Cup final. The Sheffield club, meanwhile, have not reached the showpiece since 1936, when they lost to Arsenal.  Up for the Cup: Progression to the final would continue an extraordinary season for Nigel Clough and his Sheffield United side   Local bragging rights: Ben Davies converted a late penalty as Sheffield United beat Rotherham at Bramall Lane in midweek  SHEFF UNITED\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY 3rd Round Aston Villa (A) 2-14th Round Fulham (H) 1-1Replay Fulham (A) 1-05th Round Nottingham Forest (H) 3-16th Round Charlton Athletic (H) 2-0 Their season has been extraordinary - from the depths of League One and the very real prospect of dropping into the fourth tier, to a top-half finish and a Cup semi-final. With one eye on Sunday, manager Nigel Clough changed eight players for Tuesday night\'s derby with Rotherham United and they still had enough to end the Millers\' 16-game unbeaten run. As the underdogs, they have little to lose here and a win would extend a quite remarkable season.  Burnley vs Middlesbrough, Sky Bet Championship, Saturday 3.07pm They\'ve watched as Leicester City secured their return to the Premier League last weekend and now Burnley can follow suit if things go their way. Tuesday\'s 1-0 win at Barnsley, earned thanks to an Ashley Barnes goal early on, took them to the brink and a win at home to Middlesbrough on Saturday coupled with a Derby defeat by Huddersfield will see them home and hosed. \'The next game for us is a big one,\' manager Sean Dyche said after the match at Oakwell.\'We\'ve been focusing on it all season and that won\'t change.\'  Almost there: Sean Dyche and his Burnley team can secure promotion to the Premier League this weekend   Big winner: Ashley Barnes scored the decisive goal as Burnley beat Barnsley 1-0 in midweek to edge themselves to the brink of promotion   Going up: The top six in the Championship ahead of the weekend\'s matches  PROMOTION PERMUTATION Burnley will secure promotion this weekend if they beat Middlesbrough and Derby lose to Huddersfield. Two factors have taken Burnley into this strong position. A 10-game unbeaten run on the road - which included five wins - has proved their stamina on the final push for home. And their miserly defence has also helped - the tally of 34 goals conceded is the lowest in the Championship. The champagne is on ice but nothing is guaranteed against a Middlesbrough side who have won their last three. Their boss, Aitor Karanka, certainly doesn\'t want his players rolling over so the Lancashire side can enjoy their promotion party. \'It\'s a great game for us against Burnley who can be promoted this weekend but we will go there to win the game and not to celebrate their promotion,\' he said. \'We are there to play; we don\'t go to celebrate anything.\'  Party pooper: Middlesbrough manager Aitor Karanka is determined to spoil Burnley\'s afternoon   League One promotion race, Saturday 3.07pm This was the week in which, finally, we can safely assume that Wolves and Brentford will be the two sides going up automatically from League One. It\'s been a classic tussle, with Leyton Orient surging ahead and then being dragged back down, Brentford steadily building and Wolves coming from behind to storm clear. There was a brief late challenge from Rotherham but their loss at Sheffield United combined with Brentford\'s win over Crawley means a healthy gap of nine points has once again opened between second and third.  So close: Brentford took a big step towards reaching the Championship with a 1-0 midweek win over Crawley   Golden boys: Sam Ricketts celebrates with the Wolves fans after David Edwards put them two-up against Peterborough last time out   Two\'s company: Wolves and Brentford are odds-on favourites to go up automatically  Wolves have lost just twice since the turn of the year and last Saturday\'s 2-0 success over play-off chasing Peterborough took them to 90 points. Should they win at Crewe on Saturday they will practically be up, as will Brentford if they gain three points at Swindon. I watched Brentford\'s slender 1-0 win over Crawley on Tuesday night, one of those at the end of the season when the result is far more important than the performance. \'These are the hard games and we knew they were going to be a tough opponent,\' said Bees manager Mark Warburton afterwards. \'They slowed the game down and we had to respond to it and not get impatient.\'  Patience: As manager Mark Warburton acknowledged, Brentford had to play the waiting game before getting their winner against Crawley   Bad memories: Brentford suffered last minute heart-break last season when Doncaster pipped them to automatic promotion  It was telling, however, that despite the importance of the win, there were fairly muted celebrations in the stands at the end. Brentford\'s faithful are clearly still chastened by the horrendous experience of the final afternoon last year. But for them and Wolves, the party is most definitely coming soon.   Bristol Rovers vs Torquay United, Sky Bet League Two, Saturday 3.07pm While some can assure themselves of promotion this weekend, others are in the last chance saloon. Take Torquay United, in the League Two relegation zone for the last 19 games and yet, incredibly, still confident of avoiding the drop into non-league. After last Saturday\'s 1-0 defeat to title-chasing Scunthorpe United left them 10 points adrift with five matches to play, manager Chris Hargreaves insisted the great escape was still on.  Optimism: Torquay manager Chris Hargreaves still believes they can avoid relegation from the Football League   Tough ask: The Gulls find themselves 10 points adrift of safety at the foot of League Two with five games left  TORQUAY\'S GREAT ESCAPE? April 12 Bristol Rovers (A)April 18 Dagenham (H)April 21 Exeter City (A)April 26 Mansfield (A)May 3 Wycombe (H) He told BBC Radio Devon: \'Of course we can get out of this - five wins. I\'ll keep fighting, the players will keep fighting and we know that the fans are behind us.\' You have to admire his optimism and to be fair, he wouldn\'t be much of a manager if he threw in the towel. One encouraging thing for the Gulls is that three of their remaining five games come against sides in the bottom five of the table. On the other hand, they could be relegated by defeat at Bristol Rovers on Saturday if results elsewhere go against them.  Luton Town vs Braintree Town, Skrill Premier, Saturday 12.52pm, BT Sport 1 And should Torquay go down, we could know their replacement by Saturday evening. There will be a cracking atmosphere in front of the TV cameras at Kenilworth Road when Luton Town welcome Braintree Town on Saturday lunchtime knowing three points will secure their return to the Football League after four years away. The Skrill Premier is a notoriously tough division, packed with former League sides, but the Hatters have absolutely dominated and enjoy a 16-point lead.  On the up: Pelly Ruddock-Mpanzu scores for Luton against Dartford last week. They could secure promotion back to the Football League this weekend   All smiles: John Still has guided Luton back into the League after four seasons away  Manager John Still, who guided Maidstone United up from this division in 1989 and Dagenham into the League in 2007, is poised to make it a hat-trick. Luton also look good to reach both a century of goals (currently on 93) and points (92) in their four remaining games.  Scottish Cup Semi-final weekend It\'s semi-final time north of the border as well, with one tie on Saturday and the other on Sunday. Both will be staged at Ibrox, since Hampden Park is currently being revamped for the Commonwealth Games, and that has been a source of controversy ever since Rangers squeezed past Albion Rovers to reach the final four. Dundee United, who have been drawn against the Gers (Saturday, 12.45pm, Sky Sports 2), demanded an equal share of tickets to counter-balance their opponent\'s home advantage.  All to play for: It\'s the Scottish Cup semi-finals this weekend with Rangers playing Dundee United and Aberdeen playing St Johnstone, both at Ibrox   Blow: Rangers were shell-shocked after Raith Rovers beat them in the final of the Ramsdens Cup last Sunday  Rangers have sold 20,000 tickets so far, and the Tangerines half that, but former Dundee United man Jon Daly insists his Rangers team will enjoy no benefits. \'It\'s a one off game, so I don\'t think the venue really matters. It\'s a grass pitch and there are going to be 22 players, so that\'s all that\'s important,\' he said. Besides, Rangers aren\'t in the best frame of mind after a surprise defeat by Raith Rovers in the Ramsdens Cup final last weekend.  Neutral: Rangers striker Jon Daly insists playing at Ibrox will not necessarily benefit the Gers when they take on Dundee United   Confident: St Johnstone boss Tommy Wright is sure his team can upset Aberdeen and reach the final  On Sunday, Aberdeen are favourites against St Johnstone in the other semi-final (12.45pm, BBC Two Scotland and Sky Sports 2). The Dons have won three out of the four SPFL encounters this season but Saints boss Tommy Wright remains confident of a Cupset. \'If we look at the games we\'ve played against them, we know we can do better,\' he said. \'Hopefully we can do that on Sunday.\'  La Liga title race They\'ve locked horns in Europe this week, with Atletico Madrid getting the better of Barcelona in the quarter-finals of the Champions League. And now they resume their slow-burning La Liga title battle alongside Real Madrid, with all three contenders having favourable fixtures this weekend.  Changing of the guard: Koke and David Villa celebrate what proved to be the winning goal for Atletico Madrid against Barcelona in the quarter-finals of the Champions League in the week   Stunned: Lionel Messi was left dumbstruck after Barcelona failed to get through to the semi-finals  Barcelona, chastened from their European exit but nonetheless just one point off the summit, travel to Granada (Saturday, 7pm, Sky Sports 2). Straight afterwards, Real are in Bernabeu action against Almeria as they bid to close their three-point gap to their city rivals (9pm, Sky Sports 2). With both likely to win, the onus is then on Atletico, at Getafe on Sunday night (6pm, Sky Sports 1).  Bread and butter: It\'s back to the La Liga title push for Cristiano Ronaldo and Gareth Bale after successfully negotiating the challenge of Borussia Dortmund in the Champions League    Bayern Munich vs Borussia Dortmund, Bundesliga, Saturday 5.30pm, BT Sport 1 The Bundesliga title may already have been concluded - a whopping 20 points separate these two rivals - but Borussia Dortmund can maybe whack a few dents in Bayern\'s mighty armour as the season reaches the fag end. Pep Guardiola paid the price for resting key players ahead of the Champions League clash with Manchester United when they lost to Augsburg, snapping their 53-game unbeaten league run.  We\'re through: Bayern Munich suffered a scare but ultimately prevailed against Manchester United to reach the final four of the Champions League   Not enough: Robert Lewandowski and Borussia Dortmund came up just short against Real Madrid  But they recovered their poise with a clinical performance against United and all talk of a crisis was dispelled. Dortmund were impressive in beating Real Madrid 2-0 but were unable to grab the additional goals to overturn their first leg deficit. With plenty of talent on show, this game never fails to disappoint.   More... Bumming around! Liverpool in good spirits ahead of title showdown as Suarez and Co are put through their paces Ronaldo injury rocks Real! Star could be out of the Copa del Rey final with muscle tear Messi can\'t be bothered, Xavi\'s too weak and they\'re a shambles at the back. What the hell is going on at Barcelona? MARTIN SAMUEL - THE DEBATE: I\'m not anti-Everton, I\'m just against the loan system - but the foolish paranoia of football fans never ceases to amaze me TACKLE KEOWN: Why Azpilicueta could be just the man to stop rampant Robben... and who was the fittest star I ever played with?   Share or comment on this article 23shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Adam+Shergold\" rel=\"nofollow\">Adam Shergold</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@adamjshergold\">Follow @@adamjshergold</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 19:05 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 03:02 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"SOMETHING FOR THE WEEKEND: Liverpool and Man City\'s title showdown and FA Cup semis take centre stage as Hillsborough is remembered 25 years on\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 23</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">12</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">A poignant weekend awaits as football joins together to remember the 96 victims of the Hillsborough Disaster 25 years on. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The events of April 15, 1989 changed football profoundly and, while the crusade for justice continues in the courts, we will this weekend take a moment to reflect and remember those who died supporting the team they loved. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Across the English football schedule, matches will kick off seven minutes later than usual, preceded by a minutes\' silence in memory of the victims. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"25th anniversary: Steven Gerrard holds up a commemorative patch to be worn on Liverpool\'s shirts during Sunday\'s match with Manchester City, as football marks the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough Disaster\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"491\" id=\"i-a8950e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF05C5600000578-613_634x491.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">25th anniversary: Steven Gerrard holds up a commemorative patch to be worn on Liverpool\'s shirts during Sunday\'s match with Manchester City, as football marks the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough Disaster</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Never forgotten: Kick-offs have been pushed back seven minutes and there will be a minute\'s silence before every game in England this weekend, while Liverpool will honour the 96 victims with this shirt tribute\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"431\" id=\"i-9bab0e33\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF05D7900000578-33_634x431.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Never forgotten: Kick-offs have been pushed back seven minutes and there will be a minute\'s silence before every game in England this weekend, while Liverpool will honour the 96 victims with this shirt tribute</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Eternal flame: Floral tributes left at the Hillsborough memorial outside Anfield on last year\'s anniversary\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"401\" id=\"i-9c090e41\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-18D6C447000005DC-85_634x401.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Eternal flame: Floral tributes left at the Hillsborough memorial outside Anfield on last year\'s anniversary</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It will be particularly emotional at Anfield, where Liverpool take on Manchester City in a season-defining game on Sunday afternoon.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That\'s the weekend\'s highlight but we also have the pick of the action from the FA Cup semi-finals, Football League and beyond. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Liverpool vs Manchester City, Barclays Premier League, Sunday 1.37pm, Sky Sports 1</font></b>\n<font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><br/><br/></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There will be no louder roar in an English football stadium this season than when Mark Clattenburg blows his whistle to signal the end of the minutes\' silence at Anfield on Sunday afternoon.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">For Liverpool fans, the occasion will be emotional enough as they mark the passing of 25 years since the Hillsborough tragedy took 96 of their brothers. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That combined with the very real chance they are going to win their first league championship in 24 years will almost be enough to lift the roof off. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Written in the stars: With the team sat top of the Premier League, Liverpool fans are dreaming of a first title triumph in 24 years\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"397\" id=\"i-a5ea0e53\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CB2073000000578-336_634x397.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Written in the stars: With the team sat top of the Premier League, Liverpool fans are dreaming of a first title triumph in 24 years</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Pointing the way to the title? Manager Brendan Rodgers during Liverpool\'s training session on Thursday ahead of their important clash with Manchester City\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"411\" id=\"i-ac7c0e87\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CFF37ED00000578-264_634x411.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Pointing the way to the title? Manager Brendan Rodgers during Liverpool\'s training session on Thursday ahead of their important clash with Manchester City</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Sitting pretty: Liverpool currently enjoy a two-point lead over Chelsea and four over Manchester City\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"409\" id=\"i-ace80e92\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CEC5DF800000578-727_634x409.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Sitting pretty: Liverpool currently enjoy a two-point lead over Chelsea and four over Manchester City</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sunday\'s season-defining match between the two title favourites is the hottest ticket on Merseyside in years, with £5,000 needed to buy a pair from certain online vendors this week.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There are many who see a Liverpool triumph as a breath of fresh air for the league, smashing the hegemony of the Manchester clubs and Chelsea at long last.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Manager Brendan Rodgers wants his team to cross the finish line first to honour the memories of the \'96 fans in the sky\' and he will be encouraged ahead of this big game by the statistics.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Liverpool have faced four of the top seven at Anfield this season and won them all, scoring 14 goals and conceding just once.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Unplayable: Luis Suarez has scored 29 league goals this season to propel Liverpool\'s title push\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"470\" id=\"i-aa000e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CB3C84C00000578-228_634x470.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Unplayable: Luis Suarez has scored 29 league goals this season to propel Liverpool\'s title push</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"In hot pursuit: Stevan Jovetic rounds off Manchester City\'s 4-1 win over Southampton last weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"407\" id=\"i-ab1a0e7a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDAFA4000000578-801_634x407.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">In hot pursuit: Stevan Jovetic rounds off Manchester City\'s 4-1 win over Southampton last weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Outstanding: Yaya Toure has scored 18 league goals from midfield - the third-highest tally in the top scorers\' chart\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"493\" id=\"i-ab060e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDAC68700000578-283_634x493.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Outstanding: Yaya Toure has scored 18 league goals from midfield - the third-highest tally in the top scorers\' chart</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601529/Rodgers-raring-title-showdown-City-Suarez-Co-paces.html\"> Bumming around! Liverpool in good spirits ahead of title showdown as Suarez and Co are put through their paces</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601489/Ronaldo-injury-rocks-Real-Cristiano-15-days-muscle-tear.html\"> Ronaldo injury rocks Real! Star could be out of the Copa del Rey final with muscle tear</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601440/Messi-bothered-Xavis-weak-theyre-shambles-What-hell-going-Barcelona.html\"> Messi can\'t be bothered, Xavi\'s too weak and they\'re a shambles at the back. What the hell is going on at Barcelona?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601297/MARTIN-SAMUEL-THE-DEBATE-Im-not-anti-Everton-Im-just-against-loan-foolish-paranoia-football-fans-never-ceases-amaze-me.html\"> MARTIN SAMUEL - THE DEBATE: I\'m not anti-Everton, I\'m just against the loan system - but the foolish paranoia of football fans never ceases to amaze me</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601394/TACKLE-KEOWN-LIVE-English-teams-cope-Arjen-Robben.html\"> TACKLE KEOWN: Why Azpilicueta could be just the man to stop rampant Robben... and who was the fittest star I ever played with?</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They also have a very good home record against Manchester City, who have won just one of the last 16 Anfield meetings - and that was 11 years ago. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In terms of the engrossing title race, a Liverpool win would take them seven points clear of City, who retain two matches in hand. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Three points for City and the pendulum swings towards them, while a draw brings Chelsea back into contention. They play at Swansea later on Sunday afternoon. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Hopefully the match will live up to expectations - on the face of it, we should see goals galore. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Liverpool have scored 90 league goals this season, just three shy of City\'s overall total from their title-winning 2011-2012 campaign. City have 84 themselves this term. There\'s really no excuse for the strikers! <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Wigan Athletic vs Arsenal, FA Cup semi-final, Wembley, Saturday 5.07pm, ITV</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With such important fixtures in the Premier League, it\'s quite easy to forget it\'s FA Cup semi-final weekend as well. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Arsenal will be the clear bookmakers\' favourites to end their nine-year trophy drought by winning the competition but an upset cannot be ruled out against Wigan. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">While league status, squad strength and Cup pedigree all point to a Gunners victory on Saturday teatime, there is a nagging feeling of foreboding after the Latics\' dual wins over Manchester City in last season\'s final and this season\'s sixth round. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Repeat performance: Wigan won the FA Cup last season, stunning Manchester City in the final, and will aim to do the same against Arsenal\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"444\" id=\"i-9d6a0e51\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-19BD36E7000005DC-42_634x444.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Repeat performance: Wigan won the FA Cup last season, stunning Manchester City in the final, and will aim to do the same against Arsenal</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Deja-vu: James Perch celebrates scoring what proved to be Wigan\'s winning goal against Manchester City in the sixth round\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"483\" id=\"i-a6ec0e5d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1C2811F700000578-906_634x483.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Deja-vu: James Perch celebrates scoring what proved to be Wigan\'s winning goal against Manchester City in the sixth round</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Long wait: Arsenal last lifted the FA Cup in 2005 but are favourites to end their trophy drought this time\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"381\" id=\"i-a99f0e7a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-029FFA060000044D-967_634x381.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Long wait: Arsenal last lifted the FA Cup in 2005 but are favourites to end their trophy drought this time</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>ARSENAL\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>3rd Round</b> Tottenham (H) 2-0</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>4th Round</b> Coventry City (H) 4-0</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>5th Round</b> Liverpool (H) 2-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>6th Round</b> Everton (H) 4-1</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The two sides have never met in the FA Cup but Arsenal dominate the overall head-to-head record with 15 wins out of 20.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They were also responsible for sending Wigan back down into the Championship last season, just three days after they had stunned Manchester City in the final. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We are the massive underdogs,\' said Wigan manager Uwe Rosler. \'We are going to Wembley, we can\'t lose. We only can win. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Arsenal really have to go for the FA Cup, their own players said it this week. That puts extra pressure on Arsenal.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Underdog: Uwe Rosler is confident that Wigan can spring another surprise at Arsenal on Saturday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-a91b0e69\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF8E13300000578-666_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Underdog: Uwe Rosler is confident that Wigan can spring another surprise at Arsenal on Saturday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Match winner: Wigan\'s Martyn Waghorn celebrates his goal against Leeds United last weekend but the Latics lost to Millwall in midweek\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"429\" id=\"i-ac950e93\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDAB7D600000578-688_634x429.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Match winner: Wigan\'s Martyn Waghorn celebrates his goal against Leeds United last weekend but the Latics lost to Millwall in midweek</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>WIGAN\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>3rd Round</b> MK Dons (H) 3-3</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Replay </b>MK Dons (A) 3-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>4th Round </b>Crystal Palace (H) 2-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>5th Round </b>Cardiff City (A) 2-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>6th Round</b> Manchester City (A) 2-1</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As does a backlog of injuries that has not exactly helped as Arsenal\'s title challenge fell apart and their grip on the fourth Champions League has floundered. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Arsene Wenger will be without Mathieu Flamini, who must serve a two-match suspension after collecting a 10th yellow card of the season at Everton. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain, Tomas Rosicky, Laurent Koscielny, Mesut Ozil and Jack Wilshere are all on the treatment table, giving the manager a bit of a selection headache. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Could it all be set for another glorious giant-killing from Wigan? <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Off the boil: Arsenal\'s hopes of qualifying for the Champions League took a hit with a 3-0 defeat at Everton last weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"450\" id=\"i-a7100e55\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CE2100F00000578-224_634x450.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Off the boil: Arsenal\'s hopes of qualifying for the Champions League took a hit with a 3-0 defeat at Everton last weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Missing: Mathieu Flamini (centre) is suspended and one of a number of players Arsene Wenger will have to do without at Wembley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-a9ac0e73\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CE22A4B00000578-948_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Missing: Mathieu Flamini (centre) is suspended and one of a number of players Arsene Wenger will have to do without at Wembley</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Hull City vs Sheffield United, FA Cup semi-final, Wembley, Sunday 4.07pm, BT Sport 1</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Expect a sizeable migration south from Yorkshire on Sunday as Hull City and Sheffield United aim to book a return Wembley ticket for the end of next month. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Both teams have embarked on remarkable runs to reach this stage and though it\'s first tier against third, you would imagine the occasion will provide a leveller. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It\'s been an eventful week on Humberside as owner Assem Allam\'s attempts to change the club\'s name to Hull Tigers was thrown out by the FA Council. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Rejected: The FA Council this week turned down an application by Hull City owner Assem Allam to change to club\'s name to Hull Tigers\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-a6f70e53\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF6842000000578-711_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rejected: The FA Council this week turned down an application by Hull City owner Assem Allam to change to club\'s name to Hull Tigers</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Dyed in the wool: Hull fans have staged protests at the KC Stadium against the proposed name change\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"390\" id=\"i-ad3d0e97\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDAF7E700000578-869_634x390.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Dyed in the wool: Hull fans have staged protests at the KC Stadium against the proposed name change</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>HULL CITY\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>3rd Round</b> Middlesbrough (A) 2-0</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>4th Round</b> Southend United (A) 2-0</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>5th Round</b> Brighton (H) 2-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>6th Round</b> Sunderland (H) 3-0</font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It had looked like the vocal fan protests inside the ground had fallen on deaf ears when a rather suspicious and undemocratic ballot of less than half of season ticket holders found that a \'majority\' were in favour of a change. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But just as Allam thought he finally had a mandate, the authorities sensibly stopped the plans dead. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It now remains to be seen whether the Egyptian takes the matter further but it\'s good to see the powers that be taking a stand against careless owners who think a century of history and heritage can be tossed away on a whim.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Staying out of it: Hull manager Steve Bruce has kept his counsel on the name change\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"924\" id=\"i-a8a40e6b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDB603500000578-729_634x924.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Staying out of it: Hull manager Steve Bruce has kept his counsel on the name change</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Close knit: Hull\'s players celebrate George Boyd\'s winner in last weekend\'s 1-0 home win over Swansea, a result that should secure their Premier League survival\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-a7970e56\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDB711000000578-246_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Close knit: Hull\'s players celebrate George Boyd\'s winner in last weekend\'s 1-0 home win over Swansea, a result that should secure their Premier League survival</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In the meantime, manager Steve Bruce has kept his counsel and concentrated on this historic occasion, admitting he has a series of \'horrible\' selection dilemmas to address.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I\'ve got 25 players and I can pick 11, so I\'m going to have more people disappointed than happy,\' Bruce told the Hull Daily Mail.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Should they do what is expected and beat the Blades, they will reach a first ever Cup final. The Sheffield club, meanwhile, have not reached the showpiece since 1936, when they lost to Arsenal. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Up for the Cup: Progression to the final would continue an extraordinary season for Nigel Clough and his Sheffield United side\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-acc80e8c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CFF4CD500000578-795_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Up for the Cup: Progression to the final would continue an extraordinary season for Nigel Clough and his Sheffield United side</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Local bragging rights: Ben Davies converted a late penalty as Sheffield United beat Rotherham at Bramall Lane in midweek\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-ac230e88\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF17DBF00000578-567_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Local bragging rights: Ben Davies converted a late penalty as Sheffield United beat Rotherham at Bramall Lane in midweek</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>SHEFF UNITED\'S ROAD TO WEMBLEY</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>3rd Round </b>Aston Villa (A) 2-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>4th Round</b> Fulham (H) 1-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Replay </b>Fulham (A) 1-0</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>5th Round </b>Nottingham Forest (H) 3-1</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>6th Round</b> Charlton Athletic (H) 2-0 </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Their season has been extraordinary - from the depths of League One and the very real prospect of dropping into the fourth tier, to a top-half finish and a Cup semi-final. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With one eye on Sunday, manager Nigel Clough changed eight players for Tuesday night\'s derby with Rotherham United and they still had enough to end the Millers\' 16-game unbeaten run. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As the underdogs, they have little to lose here and a win would extend a quite remarkable season. </font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Burnley vs Middlesbrough, Sky Bet Championship, Saturday 3.07pm</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They\'ve watched as Leicester City secured their return to the Premier League last weekend and now Burnley can follow suit if things go their way.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Tuesday\'s 1-0 win at Barnsley, earned thanks to an Ashley Barnes goal early on, took them to the brink and a win at home to Middlesbrough on Saturday coupled with a Derby defeat by Huddersfield will see them home and hosed.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'The next game for us is a big one,\' manager Sean Dyche said after the match at Oakwell.\'We\'ve been focusing on it all season and that won\'t change.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Almost there: Sean Dyche and his Burnley team can secure promotion to the Premier League this weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"685\" id=\"i-a9a60e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF1963B00000578-898_634x685.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Almost there: Sean Dyche and his Burnley team can secure promotion to the Premier League this weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Big winner: Ashley Barnes scored the decisive goal as Burnley beat Barnsley 1-0 in midweek to edge themselves to the brink of promotion\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-a7520e5e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF1075700000578-639_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Big winner: Ashley Barnes scored the decisive goal as Burnley beat Barnsley 1-0 in midweek to edge themselves to the brink of promotion</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Going up: The top six in the Championship ahead of the weekend\'s matches\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-9b280e37\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1D008E7E00000578-38_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Going up: The top six in the Championship ahead of the weekend\'s matches</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>PROMOTION PERMUTATION</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Burnley will secure promotion this weekend if they beat Middlesbrough and Derby lose to Huddersfield. </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Two factors have taken Burnley into this strong position. A 10-game unbeaten run on the road - which included five wins - has proved their stamina on the final push for home. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And their miserly defence has also helped - the tally of 34 goals conceded is the lowest in the Championship. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The champagne is on ice but nothing is guaranteed against a Middlesbrough side who have won their last three. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Their boss, Aitor Karanka, certainly doesn\'t want his players rolling over so the Lancashire side can enjoy their promotion party. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It\'s a great game for us against Burnley who can be promoted this weekend but we will go there to win the game and not to celebrate their promotion,\' he said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We are there to play; we don\'t go to celebrate anything.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Party pooper: Middlesbrough manager Aitor Karanka is determined to spoil Burnley\'s afternoon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"483\" id=\"i-a8ef0e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF1990A00000578-663_634x483.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Party pooper: Middlesbrough manager Aitor Karanka is determined to spoil Burnley\'s afternoon</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">League One promotion race, Saturday 3.07pm</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">This was the week in which, finally, we can safely assume that Wolves and Brentford will be the two sides going up automatically from League One.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It\'s been a classic tussle, with Leyton Orient surging ahead and then being dragged back down, Brentford steadily building and Wolves coming from behind to storm clear.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There was a brief late challenge from Rotherham but their loss at Sheffield United combined with Brentford\'s win over Crawley means a healthy gap of nine points has once again opened between second and third.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"So close: Brentford took a big step towards reaching the Championship with a 1-0 midweek win over Crawley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-abee0e8a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF1A7DF00000578-328_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">So close: Brentford took a big step towards reaching the Championship with a 1-0 midweek win over Crawley</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Golden boys: Sam Ricketts celebrates with the Wolves fans after David Edwards put them two-up against Peterborough last time out\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-9d240e40\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDB97E200000578-40_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Golden boys: Sam Ricketts celebrates with the Wolves fans after David Edwards put them two-up against Peterborough last time out</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Two\'s company: Wolves and Brentford are odds-on favourites to go up automatically\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-a4ac0e3e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1D00936400000578-606_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Two\'s company: Wolves and Brentford are odds-on favourites to go up automatically</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Wolves have lost just twice since the turn of the year and last Saturday\'s 2-0 success over play-off chasing Peterborough took them to 90 points. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Should they win at Crewe on Saturday they will practically be up, as will Brentford if they gain three points at Swindon. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">I watched Brentford\'s slender 1-0 win over Crawley on Tuesday night, one of those at the end of the season when the result is far more important than the performance. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'These are the hard games and we knew they were going to be a tough opponent,\' said Bees manager Mark Warburton afterwards. \'They slowed the game down and we had to respond to it and not get impatient.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Patience: As manager Mark Warburton acknowledged, Brentford had to play the waiting game before getting their winner against Crawley\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-a93d0e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF1575E00000578-567_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Patience: As manager Mark Warburton acknowledged, Brentford had to play the waiting game before getting their winner against Crawley</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bad memories: Brentford suffered last minute heart-break last season when Doncaster pipped them to automatic promotion\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"360\" id=\"i-a5d10e4a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-03C414E900000514-372_634x360.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bad memories: Brentford suffered last minute heart-break last season when Doncaster pipped them to automatic promotion</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It was telling, however, that despite the importance of the win, there were fairly muted celebrations in the stands at the end. Brentford\'s faithful are clearly still chastened by the horrendous experience of the final afternoon last year. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But for them and Wolves, the party is most definitely coming soon. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<b></b>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Bristol Rovers vs Torquay United, Sky Bet League Two, Saturday 3.07pm</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">While some can assure themselves of promotion this weekend, others are in the last chance saloon. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Take Torquay United, in the League Two relegation zone for the last 19 games and yet, incredibly, still confident of avoiding the drop into non-league.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">After last Saturday\'s 1-0 defeat to title-chasing Scunthorpe United left them 10 points adrift with five matches to play, manager Chris Hargreaves insisted the great escape was still on.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Optimism: Torquay manager Chris Hargreaves still believes they can avoid relegation from the Football League\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"455\" id=\"i-ac900e93\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CDB5E7A00000578-887_634x455.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Optimism: Torquay manager Chris Hargreaves still believes they can avoid relegation from the Football League</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tough ask: The Gulls find themselves 10 points adrift of safety at the foot of League Two with five games left\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"338\" id=\"i-a5f70e50\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1D009A7100000578-405_634x338.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tough ask: The Gulls find themselves 10 points adrift of safety at the foot of League Two with five games left</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>TORQUAY\'S GREAT ESCAPE? </b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 12 </b>Bristol Rovers (A)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 18</b> Dagenham (H)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 21</b> Exeter City (A)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>April 26</b> Mansfield (A)</font><br/><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>May 3</b> Wycombe (H)</font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He told BBC Radio Devon: \'Of course we can get out of this - five wins. I\'ll keep fighting, the players will keep fighting and we know that the fans are behind us.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">You have to admire his optimism and to be fair, he wouldn\'t be much of a manager if he threw in the towel. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">One encouraging thing for the Gulls is that three of their remaining five games come against sides in the bottom five of the table. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">On the other hand, they could be relegated by defeat at Bristol Rovers on Saturday if results elsewhere go against them.</font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Luton Town vs Braintree Town, Skrill Premier, Saturday 12.52pm, BT Sport 1</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And should Torquay go down, we could know their replacement by Saturday evening. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There will be a cracking atmosphere in front of the TV cameras at Kenilworth Road when Luton Town welcome Braintree Town on Saturday lunchtime knowing three points will secure their return to the Football League after four years away. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Skrill Premier is a notoriously tough division, packed with former League sides, but the Hatters have absolutely dominated and enjoy a 16-point lead. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"On the up: Pelly Ruddock-Mpanzu scores for Luton against Dartford last week. They could secure promotion back to the Football League this weekend\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"376\" id=\"i-9c8d0e43\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CC0F39A00000578-25_634x376.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On the up: Pelly Ruddock-Mpanzu scores for Luton against Dartford last week. They could secure promotion back to the Football League this weekend</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All smiles: John Still has guided Luton back into the League after four seasons away\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"426\" id=\"i-9c1c0e3a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CBF682800000578-53_634x426.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All smiles: John Still has guided Luton back into the League after four seasons away</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Manager John Still, who guided Maidstone United up from this division in 1989 and Dagenham into the League in 2007, is poised to make it a hat-trick. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Luton also look good to reach both a century of goals (currently on 93) and points (92) in their four remaining games. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Scottish Cup Semi-final weekend</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It\'s semi-final time north of the border as well, with one tie on Saturday and the other on Sunday.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Both will be staged at Ibrox, since Hampden Park is currently being revamped for the Commonwealth Games, and that has been a source of controversy ever since Rangers squeezed past Albion Rovers to reach the final four. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Dundee United, who have been drawn against the Gers (Saturday, 12.45pm, Sky Sports 2), demanded an equal share of tickets to counter-balance their opponent\'s home advantage. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All to play for: It\'s the Scottish Cup semi-finals this weekend with Rangers playing Dundee United and Aberdeen playing St Johnstone, both at Ibrox\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"396\" id=\"i-ad030e95\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CFF59FB00000578-227_634x396.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All to play for: It\'s the Scottish Cup semi-finals this weekend with Rangers playing Dundee United and Aberdeen playing St Johnstone, both at Ibrox</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Blow: Rangers were shell-shocked after Raith Rovers beat them in the final of the Ramsdens Cup last Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"463\" id=\"i-a9db0e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CE30E4B00000578-278_634x463.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Blow: Rangers were shell-shocked after Raith Rovers beat them in the final of the Ramsdens Cup last Sunday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Rangers have sold 20,000 tickets so far, and the Tangerines half that, but former Dundee United man Jon Daly insists his Rangers team will enjoy no benefits.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'It\'s a one off game, so I don\'t think the venue really matters. It\'s a grass pitch and there are going to be 22 players, so that\'s all that\'s important,\' he said. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Besides, Rangers aren\'t in the best frame of mind after a surprise defeat by Raith Rovers in the Ramsdens Cup final last weekend. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Neutral: Rangers striker Jon Daly insists playing at Ibrox will not necessarily benefit the Gers when they take on Dundee United\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-aa8d0e73\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CAFF44500000578-347_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Neutral: Rangers striker Jon Daly insists playing at Ibrox will not necessarily benefit the Gers when they take on Dundee United</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Confident: St Johnstone boss Tommy Wright is sure his team can upset Aberdeen and reach the final\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"376\" id=\"i-aae40e85\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF5B4A500000578-978_634x376.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Confident: St Johnstone boss Tommy Wright is sure his team can upset Aberdeen and reach the final</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">On Sunday, Aberdeen are favourites against St Johnstone in the other semi-final (12.45pm, BBC Two Scotland and Sky Sports 2). </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Dons have won three out of the four SPFL encounters this season but Saints boss Tommy Wright remains confident of a Cupset. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'If we look at the games we\'ve played against them, we know we can do better,\' he said. \'Hopefully we can do that on Sunday.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"> </div>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">La Liga title race</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They\'ve locked horns in Europe this week, with Atletico Madrid getting the better of Barcelona in the quarter-finals of the Champions League.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">And now they resume their slow-burning La Liga title battle alongside Real Madrid, with all three contenders having favourable fixtures this weekend.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Changing of the guard: Koke and David Villa celebrate what proved to be the winning goal for Atletico Madrid against Barcelona in the quarter-finals of the Champions League in the week\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-a7ce0e5e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF9159200000578-473_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Changing of the guard: Koke and David Villa celebrate what proved to be the winning goal for Atletico Madrid against Barcelona in the quarter-finals of the Champions League in the week</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Stunned: Lionel Messi was left dumbstruck after Barcelona failed to get through to the semi-finals\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-aa000e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF9A22C00000578-470_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Stunned: Lionel Messi was left dumbstruck after Barcelona failed to get through to the semi-finals</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Barcelona, chastened from their European exit but nonetheless just one point off the summit, travel to Granada (Saturday, 7pm, Sky Sports 2).</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Straight afterwards, Real are in Bernabeu action against Almeria as they bid to close their three-point gap to their city rivals (9pm, Sky Sports 2). </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">With both likely to win, the onus is then on Atletico, at Getafe on Sunday night (6pm, Sky Sports 1).</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Bread and butter: It\'s back to the La Liga title push for Cristiano Ronaldo and Gareth Bale after successfully negotiating the challenge of Borussia Dortmund in the Champions League\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"652\" id=\"i-a9b60e73\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF21FC000000578-464_634x652.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Bread and butter: It\'s back to the La Liga title push for Cristiano Ronaldo and Gareth Bale after successfully negotiating the challenge of Borussia Dortmund in the Champions League</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"pageBreak\"><b> </b></div>\n<b> </b>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bayern Munich vs Borussia Dortmund, Bundesliga, Saturday 5.30pm, BT Sport 1</font></b></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Bundesliga title may already have been concluded - a whopping 20 points separate these two rivals - but Borussia Dortmund can maybe whack a few dents in Bayern\'s mighty armour as the season reaches the fag end. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Pep Guardiola paid the price for resting key players ahead of the Champions League clash with Manchester United when they lost to Augsburg, snapping their 53-game unbeaten league run. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"We\'re through: Bayern Munich suffered a scare but ultimately prevailed against Manchester United to reach the final four of the Champions League\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-a9740e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF994B200000578-670_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">We\'re through: Bayern Munich suffered a scare but ultimately prevailed against Manchester United to reach the final four of the Champions League</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Not enough: Robert Lewandowski and Borussia Dortmund came up just short against Real Madrid\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"418\" id=\"i-a7600e5a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601436-1CF20E0100000578-612_634x418.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Not enough: Robert Lewandowski and Borussia Dortmund came up just short against Real Madrid</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But they recovered their poise with a clinical performance against United and all talk of a crisis was dispelled.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Dortmund were impressive in beating Real Madrid 2-0 but were unable to grab the additional goals to overturn their first leg deficit. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With plenty of talent on show, this game never fails to disappoint.</font></p>\n<p><br/></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601529/Rodgers-raring-title-showdown-City-Suarez-Co-paces.html\"> Bumming around! Liverpool in good spirits ahead of title showdown as Suarez and Co are put through their paces</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601489/Ronaldo-injury-rocks-Real-Cristiano-15-days-muscle-tear.html\"> Ronaldo injury rocks Real! Star could be out of the Copa del Rey final with muscle tear</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601440/Messi-bothered-Xavis-weak-theyre-shambles-What-hell-going-Barcelona.html\"> Messi can\'t be bothered, Xavi\'s too weak and they\'re a shambles at the back. What the hell is going on at Barcelona?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601297/MARTIN-SAMUEL-THE-DEBATE-Im-not-anti-Everton-Im-just-against-loan-foolish-paranoia-football-fans-never-ceases-amaze-me.html\"> MARTIN SAMUEL - THE DEBATE: I\'m not anti-Everton, I\'m just against the loan system - but the foolish paranoia of football fans never ceases to amaze me</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601394/TACKLE-KEOWN-LIVE-English-teams-cope-Arjen-Robben.html\"> TACKLE KEOWN: Why Azpilicueta could be just the man to stop rampant Robben... and who was the fittest star I ever played with?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601436/Something-Weekend-Liverpool-vs-Manchester-City-Arsenal-vs-Wigan-Athletic-Hull-City-vs-Sheffield-United-centre-stage-football-preview.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"SOMETHING FOR THE WEEKEND: Liverpool and Man City\'s title showdown and FA Cup semis take centre stage as Hillsborough is remembered 25 years on\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601436/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">23</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2601436-1D01CCB500000578-121_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:41','2014-04-11 10:02:10');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (98,'a88c9abe7e26e258e208a3c6975450317f781753302b6ef51e69ec18ff058701','dailymail',NULL,'Pietersen opens the door to England return... and thinks he could hit 10,000 runs!','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2601732/Pietersen-opens-door-England-return-thinks-hit-10-000-runs.html',' By Isaac Williams Published: 11:19 EST, 10 April 2014 | Updated: 02:02 EST, 11 April 2014 12 shares 22 View comments Kevin Pietersen has hinted that he would be interested in resurrecting his international career - and wants to hit 10,000 runs for England. The 33-year-old was axed earlier this year after several months of simmering dressing room tension, culminating in an alleged spat with former coach, Andy Flower. After being asked about his England run-rate, Pietersen told the Indian Express. \'Yes, maybe I’ll still get to 10,000\', before claiming that ex-skipper \'Andrew Strauss is a good friend\' following the pair’s fallout during the ‘textgate’ affair of 2012.  All over? Kevin Pietersen was left out of England\'s squad for the West Indies and the Twenty20 World Cup   Parting of the ways: Skipper Alastair Cook has run out of patience with Pietersen\'s attitude   New face: The ECB\'s new Managing Director Paul Downton (right) was heavily involved in the decision  Angling for a way back: Pietersen, however, still harbours hope of scoring 10,000 Test runs for England   More... All a-BROAD the breakfast express! England star does the rounds on milk float Bairstow a doubt for start of England\'s Test summer after sustaining broken finger Pietersen claims he was the first person to notice Trott\'s trouble during the Ashes Trott manages just eight runs for Warwickshire as struggles after return from stress-related illness continue Sri Lanka legends Sangakkara and Jayawardene bow out in style with World Twenty20 triumph The former England talisman has 8,181 runs from 104 Tests, placing him fourth on the all-time list. He appeared contrite over the 2012 scandal, when he reportedly sent South African players critical text messages that targeted Strauss and his team-mates. \'Andrew Strauss is a great friend. I was just in a bad space. We were not having a great relationship at that time. It should never have come out, all that nonsense. That wasn\'t a special time at all,\" Pietersen said. Pietersen, who will captain the Delhi Daredevils in the Indian Premier League Twenty20 tournament, said he did not care what the media in England say about him. \'I don\'t read the media, especially in England. No interest,\' he said. \'I\'ll have a look at it and stuff. I will obviously see it through Twitter. You sort of gauge what\'s going on. But I have got no interest in what those … gentlemen … have got to say.\'  Wanted to stay: Pietersen, pictured with Surrey chairman Richard Thompson, hasn\'t closed the door on a return to the international fold    More... All a-BROAD the breakfast express! England star does the rounds on milk float Bairstow a doubt for start of England\'s Test summer after sustaining broken finger Pietersen claims he was the first person to notice Trott\'s trouble during the Ashes Trott manages just eight runs for Warwickshire as struggles after return from stress-related illness continue Sri Lanka legends Sangakkara and Jayawardene bow out in style with World Twenty20 triumph  Share or comment on this article 12shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Isaac+Williams\" rel=\"nofollow\">Isaac Williams</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:19 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 02:02 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2601732/Pietersen-opens-door-England-return-thinks-hit-10-000-runs.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2601732/Pietersen-opens-door-England-return-thinks-hit-10-000-runs.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Pietersen opens the door to England return... and thinks he could hit 10,000 runs!\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 12</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2601732/Pietersen-opens-door-England-return-thinks-hit-10-000-runs.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">22</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Kevin Pietersen has hinted that he would be interested in resurrecting his international career - and wants to hit 10,000 runs for England. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The 33-year-old was axed earlier this year after several months of simmering dressing room tension, culminating in an alleged spat with former coach, Andy Flower.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">After being asked about his England run-rate, Pietersen told the Indian Express. \'Yes, maybe I’ll still get to 10,000\', before claiming that ex-skipper \'Andrew Strauss is a good friend\' following the pair’s fallout during the ‘textgate’ affair of 2012. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All over: Kevin Pietersen has been left out of England\'s squad for the West Indies and the Twenty20 World Cup\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"357\" id=\"i-a9a20e76\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/02/04/article-2551857-1B3304FC00000578-568_634x357.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All over? Kevin Pietersen was left out of England\'s squad for the West Indies and the Twenty20 World Cup</p> </div></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Parting of the ways: Skipper Alastair Cook has run out of patience with Pietersen\'s attitude\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-a6fe0e58\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/02/04/article-2551857-0222B5B600000514-757_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Parting of the ways: Skipper Alastair Cook has run out of patience with Pietersen\'s attitude</p> </div></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"New face: The ECB\'s new Managing Director Paul Downton (right) was heavily involved in the decision\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"368\" id=\"i-ad250e95\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/02/04/article-2551857-1A64CBBF00000578-373_634x368.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">New face: The ECB\'s new Managing Director Paul Downton (right) was heavily involved in the decision</p> </div></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Distracted: Pietersen and Cook carrying the drinks off during a practise game in Australia this winter\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"415\" id=\"i-ac430e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/02/04/article-2551857-19BAFB1700000578-818_634x415.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Angling for a way back: Pietersen, however, still harbours hope of scoring 10,000 Test runs for England<br/></p> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2600748/Stuart-Broad-rides-milk-float.html\"> All a-BROAD the breakfast express! England star does the rounds on milk float</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2601047/Jonny-Bairstow-suffers-broken-finger.html\"> Bairstow a doubt for start of England\'s Test summer after sustaining broken finger</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2600173/Kevin-Pietersen-claims-person-notice-Jonathan-Trotts-trouble-Ashes.html\"> Pietersen claims he was the first person to notice Trott\'s trouble during the Ashes</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2599837/Jonathan-Trott-manages-just-eight-runs-Warwickshire-struggles-return-stress-related-illness-continue.html\"> Trott manages just eight runs for Warwickshire as struggles after return from stress-related illness continue</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2598206/Sri-Lanka-win-major-trophy-1996-defeat-India-World-T20.html\"> Sri Lanka legends Sangakkara and Jayawardene bow out in style with World Twenty20 triumph</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The former England talisman has 8,181 runs from 104 Tests, placing him fourth on the all-time list. He appeared contrite over the 2012 scandal, when he reportedly sent South African players critical text messages that targeted Strauss and his team-mates.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Andrew Strauss is a great friend. I was just in a bad space. We were not having a great relationship at that time. It should never have come out, all that nonsense. That wasn\'t a special time at all,\" Pietersen said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pietersen, who will captain the Delhi Daredevils in the Indian Premier League Twenty20 tournament, said he did not care what the media in England say about him. \'I don\'t read the media, especially in England. No interest,\' he said. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I\'ll have a look at it and stuff. I will obviously see it through Twitter. You sort of gauge what\'s going on. But I have got no interest in what those … gentlemen … have got to say.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wanted to stay: Pietersen, pictured with Surrey chairman Richard Thompson, hasn\'t closed the door on a return to the international fold\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-ac020e88\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601732-1CE1FDB700000578-842_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wanted to stay: Pietersen, pictured with Surrey chairman Richard Thompson, hasn\'t closed the door on a return to the international fold</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2600748/Stuart-Broad-rides-milk-float.html\"> All a-BROAD the breakfast express! England star does the rounds on milk float</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2601047/Jonny-Bairstow-suffers-broken-finger.html\"> Bairstow a doubt for start of England\'s Test summer after sustaining broken finger</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2600173/Kevin-Pietersen-claims-person-notice-Jonathan-Trotts-trouble-Ashes.html\"> Pietersen claims he was the first person to notice Trott\'s trouble during the Ashes</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2599837/Jonathan-Trott-manages-just-eight-runs-Warwickshire-struggles-return-stress-related-illness-continue.html\"> Trott manages just eight runs for Warwickshire as struggles after return from stress-related illness continue</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/cricket/article-2598206/Sri-Lanka-win-major-trophy-1996-defeat-India-World-T20.html\"> Sri Lanka legends Sangakkara and Jayawardene bow out in style with World Twenty20 triumph</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2601732/Pietersen-opens-door-England-return-thinks-hit-10-000-runs.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2601732/Pietersen-opens-door-England-return-thinks-hit-10-000-runs.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Pietersen opens the door to England return... and thinks he could hit 10,000 runs!\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2601732/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">12</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601732-1CE1FDB700000578-273_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:43','2014-04-11 09:02:25'),(99,'6d63e641c6ebb5aa7b17077e8c2a665ffb4606ff549cc7c7d971a51cbbd847d2','dailymail',NULL,'Floyd Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Manny Pacquiao, says trainer Freddie Roach','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html',' By Jeff Powell Follow @@jeffpowell_Mail Published: 14:29 EST, 10 April 2014 | Updated: 00:39 EST, 11 April 2014 134 shares 81 View comments Freddie Roach, fabled trainer of Manny Pacquiao, fears that the chance has been lost of Floyd Mayweather ever taking on his man in the richest fight in boxing history. As he put the final touches to Pacquaio\'s preparations for Saturday\'s rematch with Tim Bradley, Roach said: \'It looked close two years ago but I don\'t think Floyd will take the chance now.\'  Re-match: Manny Pacquiao faces undefeated WBO welterweight champion Tim Bradley on Saturday  More... Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch Pacquiao dismisses Bradley\'s claim he has lost killer instinct ahead of rematch British referee Keane forced out of huge Pacquiao-Bradley rematch with sickness The PacMan versus the Money Man is still the fight the whole world wants to see but Roach doubts it will happen now Mayweather is so close to ending his career undefeated. He says: \'Floyd\'s main concern has become keeping that 0 (for zero losses) on his record. I don\'t see him taking any real risk of losing that before the end of next year, when he says he\'s retiring. \'It\'s not that he\'s afraid of Manny. No fighters are scared of anybody in the world. It\'s just that he believes if he goes out undefeated he will be seen as better than greats like Sugar Ray Robinson, who had losses on their records. Floyd Mayweather core strengthening ahead of Maidana bout  Undefeated: But Floyd Mayweather plans to retire next season  \'Manny and Floyd should have happened a couple of years ago when both were in their prime. I think Mayweather wanted the fight then. Later when we put them on the phone together Floyd said he wanted blood testing and 60 per cent of the money. \'Manny said yes to both but then we never heard back from Floyd again.\' The failure to make the super-fight happen has been blamed by some on the long-running feud between rival promoters Bob Arum (Pacquiao) and Golden Boy (Mayweather). But Roach said: \'Down the years, no matter what the issues, if two fighters really want to fight each other they maks it happen. Manny will fight anyone but Floyd is two years older and thinking about that record of his.  Doubts: Pacquiao\'s trainer Freddie Roach  \'Also we all get older and the first sign of aging in a fighter is that his legs go a little. After he got hit a lot by Miguel Cotto he said that he decided to stand and trade because he wanted to give more excitement to his fans. I don\'t think so.  He got caught because he can no longer move around the ring as quickly as before.\' Mayweather follows Pacquiao into the MGM Grand Arena in Las Vegas next month, for the third bout in his $300 million six-fight contract with the Showtime cable TV network. Roach is unsurprised that he opted at the last moment to box Marcos Maidana rather than the young, fast Amir Khan and he expects Mayweather to make sensible choices for his final three fights, one in September and two next year. The last, outside chance for the prize-ring\'s most climactic night of all hangs on Mayweather\'s finale, when he hopes to equal Rocky Marciano\'s record of retiring unbeaten after 49 fights. Roach says: \'It would be great if Floyd and Manny met in what could be the last fight for both of them.\' But he\'s not holding his breath and says: \'Down the years all the great fights which were supposed to happen did happen. Sometimes sooner, sometimes, usually because the fighters demanded it. \'Those are the fights for which they are best remembered.  But it looks like in the future people will look back and ask why these two never fought each other.\' Manny Pacquiao trains in L.A. ahead of rematch with Bradley    More... Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch Pacquiao dismisses Bradley\'s claim he has lost killer instinct ahead of rematch British referee Keane forced out of huge Pacquiao-Bradley rematch with sickness   Share or comment on this article 134shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Jeff+Powell\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jeff Powell</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@jeffpowell_Mail\">Follow @@jeffpowell_Mail</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 14:29 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 00:39 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoact