"i-9c830e4b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601846-1303DCD5000005DC-46_634x542.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Doubts: Pacquiao\'s trainer Freddie Roach</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> \'Also we all get older and the first sign of aging in a fighter is that his legs go a little. After he got hit a lot by Miguel Cotto he said that he decided to stand and trade because he wanted to give more excitement to his fans. I don\'t think so.  He got caught because he can no longer move around the ring as quickly as before.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Mayweather follows Pacquiao into the MGM Grand Arena in Las Vegas next month, for the third bout in his $300 million six-fight contract with the Showtime cable TV network.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Roach is unsurprised that he opted at the last moment to box Marcos Maidana rather than the young, fast Amir Khan and he expects Mayweather to make sensible choices for his final three fights, one in September and two next year. The last, outside chance for the prize-ring\'s most climactic night of all hangs on Mayweather\'s finale, when he hopes to equal Rocky Marciano\'s record of retiring unbeaten after 49 fights.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Roach says: \'It would be great if Floyd and Manny met in what could be the last fight for both of them.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> But he\'s not holding his breath and says: \'Down the years all the great fights which were supposed to happen did happen. Sometimes sooner, sometimes, usually because the fighters demanded it.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> \'Those are the fights for which they are best remembered.  But it looks like in the future people will look back and ask why these two never fought each other.\'</font>  </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3426825017001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Manny Pacquiao trains in L.A. ahead of rematch with Bradley</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/03/video-undefined-1CCDEEFB00000578-488_638x362.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600192/Pacquiao-sets-sights-Mayweather-Marquez-revenge-against-Bradley.html\"> Pacquiao sets sights on Mayweather and Marquez after revenge against Bradley</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600995/Tim-Bradley-nearly-committed-suicide-Manny-Pacquiao-decision.html\"> Abuse after Pacquiao fight nearly drove me to suicide, says Bradley ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2599973/Pacquiao-dismisses-Bradleys-claim-lost-killer-instinct-ahead-rematch.html\"> Pacquiao dismisses Bradley\'s claim he has lost killer instinct ahead of rematch</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/boxing/article-2600177/British-boxing-referee-John-Keane-forced-Manny-Pacquiaos-rematch-Tim-Bradley-illness.html\"> British referee Keane forced out of huge Pacquiao-Bradley rematch with sickness</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601846/Floyd-Mayweather-not-risk-unbeaten-record-fighting-Manny-Pacquiao-says-trainer-Freddie-Roach.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Mayweather will not risk his unbeaten record by fighting Pacquiao, claims Manny\'s trainer Roach\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/boxing/article-2601846/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">134</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601846-1CF9C7F500000578-968_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:44','2014-04-11 07:39:58'),(100,'3c569be2decc571d2e0b9218ecf55d8bb60292bd45346274e7dd5ca7b853708b','dailymail',NULL,'Sir Alex Ferguson was hunted by Newcastle United after Kevin Keegan left','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html',' By Graeme Yorke Published: 15:32 EST, 10 April 2014 | Updated: 17:43 EST, 10 April 2014 50 shares 69 View comments  Former Newcastle United chairman Freddy Shepherd has admitted the Magpies tried to bring Sir Alex Ferguson to the club after Kevin Keegan had left in 1997. After Keegan\'s walk-out, which shocked the club and fans and sent shockwaves through Tyneside, Shepherd made an approach for Ferguson, but soon realised the Scot was \'using\' Shepherd\'s club.  back then: Ferguson was a wanted man by Newcastle in 1997, but went on to have even more success   Stunned: Kevin Keegan left the club in 1997, sending shock waves through Tyneside  More... Newcastle in talks over Perez, Man Utd line up Milinkovic-Savic trial and Kaboul is wanted by Fiorentina Remy injury frustration grows for Newcastle with star striker to miss Stoke clash Newcastle forced to refund Southampton fans £12,000 after overcharging for tickets REVEALED: How Manchester United were told to cough up £25m for Shearer... before Newcastle bought him for just £15m! Newcastle confirm Charnley as new managing director as he reveals club will sign \'one or two\' players each year All the latest Manchester United news and headlines Newcastle did talk with Ferguson\'s advisers, but Shepherd believes he was just trying to get a new, more expensive deal at Old Trafford. \'When Keegan left we tried to get Ferguson to Newcastle as his replacement\' Shepherd told the Newcastle Evening Chronicle. \'We had talks with his advisors at the time. We soon realised there was no way he was going to come to Newcastle. \'He was just trying to get an increase in salary. We knew we were just being used. \'We were ambitious, we tried to get him – at least we tried.\' On January 8, 1997, Keegan announced his resignation as manager, despite the club attempting to change his mind. Manchester United went on to win the title with Ferguson that year, his fourth with the club, and continued to win another nine at Old Trafford, along with five FA Cup and two Champions League trophies. Newcastle eventually appointed Kenny Dalglish as manager, with the club runners-up for a second straight season.  Wanted man: Newcastle and Manchester United also battled over Alan Shearer in 1996   Ploy: Shepherd admitted Ferguson\'s advisers spoke to Newcastle, but that the club were \'used\'  Shepherd left the club in 2007 after selling his shares to Mike Ashley, and the club have not won a trophy since 1955. Shepherd also revealed this week how he fought off competition from Manchester United to land the word-record signing of Alan Shearer. It was the summer of 1996 when the Premier League’s top two clubs did battle over the England striker. But it was the Magpies who won the race with both Shearer and Blackburn favouring their offer, Rovers owner Jack Walker even telling Shepherd that the asking price was £10million lower for his club.  Staying put: United went on to win the league that season, and won nine more under Ferguson Every success: Fergie lifts the Premier League trophy in 2013, his 13th and final as United boss   More... Newcastle in talks over Perez, Man Utd line up Milinkovic-Savic trial and Kaboul is wanted by Fiorentina Remy injury frustration grows for Newcastle with star striker to miss Stoke clash Newcastle forced to refund Southampton fans £12,000 after overcharging for tickets REVEALED: How Manchester United were told to cough up £25m for Shearer... before Newcastle bought him for just £15m! Newcastle confirm Charnley as new managing director as he reveals club will sign \'one or two\' players each year All the latest Manchester United news and headlines    Share or comment on this article 50shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Graeme+Yorke\" rel=\"nofollow\">Graeme Yorke</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 15:32 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 17:43 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"We went for Fergie! Newcastle tried to sign United great after Keegan, admits Shepherd\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 50</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">69</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Former Newcastle United chairman Freddy Shepherd has admitted the Magpies tried to bring Sir Alex Ferguson to the club after Kevin Keegan had left in 1997.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">After Keegan\'s walk-out, which shocked the club and fans and sent shockwaves through Tyneside, Shepherd made an approach for Ferguson, but soon realised the Scot was \'using\' Shepherd\'s club.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"back then: Ferguson was a wanted man by Newcastle in 1997, but went on to have even more success\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"476\" id=\"i-a9ba0e7b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601894-0000CFDF00000258-549_634x476.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">back then: Ferguson was a wanted man by Newcastle in 1997, but went on to have even more success</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Stunned: Kevin Keegan left the club in 1997, sending shock waves through Tyneside\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"510\" id=\"i-acd30e8b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601894-00EECE8E00000191-588_634x510.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Stunned: Kevin Keegan left the club in 1997, sending shock waves through Tyneside</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601580/Newcastle-talks-Perez-Man-Utd-line-Milinkovic-Savic-trial-Kaboul-wanted-Fiorentina-THE-TRANSFER-COLUMN.html\"> Newcastle in talks over Perez, Man Utd line up Milinkovic-Savic trial and Kaboul is wanted by Fiorentina</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601678/Loic-Remy-injury-frustration-grows-Newcastle-star-striker-miss-Stoke-clash.html\"> Remy injury frustration grows for Newcastle with star striker to miss Stoke clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600987/Newcastle-refund-Southampton-fans-12-000-overcharging-tickets.html\"> Newcastle forced to refund Southampton fans £12,000 after overcharging for tickets</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599716/Former-Newcastle-chief-Shepherd-reveals-tussle-United-Shearer-Blackburn-quoted-10m-less.html\"> REVEALED: How Manchester United were told to cough up £25m for Shearer... before Newcastle bought him for just £15m!</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598947/Newcastle-confirm-Charnley-new-managing-director-reveals-club-sign-one-two-players-year.html\"> Newcastle confirm Charnley as new managing director as he reveals club will sign \'one or two\' players each year</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/newcastle-united.html\"> All the latest Manchester United news and headlines</a></li> </ul> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Newcastle did talk with Ferguson\'s advisers, but Shepherd believes he was just trying to get a new, more expensive deal at Old Trafford.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'When Keegan left we tried to get Ferguson to Newcastle as his replacement\' Shepherd told the <i>Newcastle Evening Chronicle.</i></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We had talks with his advisors at the time. We soon realised there was no way he was going to come to Newcastle.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'He was just trying to get an increase in salary. We knew we were just being used.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'We were ambitious, we tried to get him – at least we tried.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">On January 8, 1997, Keegan announced his resignation as manager, despite the club attempting to change his mind.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Manchester United went on to win the title with Ferguson that year, his fourth with the club, and continued to win another nine at Old Trafford, along with five FA Cup and two Champions League trophies.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Newcastle eventually appointed Kenny Dalglish as manager, with the club runners-up for a second straight season.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wanted man: Newcastle and Manchester United also battled over Alan Shearer in 1996\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"328\" id=\"i-a59d0e57\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601894-0000A21600000C1D-873_634x328.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wanted man: Newcastle and Manchester United also battled over Alan Shearer in 1996</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Ploy: Shepherd admitted Ferguson\'s advisers spoke to Newcastle, but that the club were \'used\'\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"461\" id=\"i-a6520e53\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601894-0286B22800000578-646_634x461.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Ploy: Shepherd admitted Ferguson\'s advisers spoke to Newcastle, but that the club were \'used\'</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Shepherd left the club in 2007 after selling his shares to Mike Ashley, and the club have not won a trophy since 1955. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Shepherd also revealed this week how he fought off competition from Manchester United to land the word-record signing of Alan Shearer.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It was the summer of 1996 when the Premier League’s top two clubs did battle over the England striker.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But it was the Magpies who won the race with both Shearer and Blackburn favouring their offer, Rovers owner Jack Walker even telling Shepherd that the asking price was £10million lower for his club.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Staying put: United went on to win the league that season, and won nine more under Ferguson\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"387\" id=\"i-a58d0e52\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601894-0008C35600000258-288_634x387.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Staying put: United went on to win the league that season, and won nine more under Ferguson</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Every success: Fergie lifts the Premier League trophy in 2013, his 13th and final as United boss\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-ac2c0e8e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601894-19BEC456000005DC-457_634x423.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Every success: Fergie lifts the Premier League trophy in 2013, his 13th and final as United boss</p><p> </p></div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601580/Newcastle-talks-Perez-Man-Utd-line-Milinkovic-Savic-trial-Kaboul-wanted-Fiorentina-THE-TRANSFER-COLUMN.html\"> Newcastle in talks over Perez, Man Utd line up Milinkovic-Savic trial and Kaboul is wanted by Fiorentina</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601678/Loic-Remy-injury-frustration-grows-Newcastle-star-striker-miss-Stoke-clash.html\"> Remy injury frustration grows for Newcastle with star striker to miss Stoke clash</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600987/Newcastle-refund-Southampton-fans-12-000-overcharging-tickets.html\"> Newcastle forced to refund Southampton fans £12,000 after overcharging for tickets</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599716/Former-Newcastle-chief-Shepherd-reveals-tussle-United-Shearer-Blackburn-quoted-10m-less.html\"> REVEALED: How Manchester United were told to cough up £25m for Shearer... before Newcastle bought him for just £15m!</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598947/Newcastle-confirm-Charnley-new-managing-director-reveals-club-sign-one-two-players-year.html\"> Newcastle confirm Charnley as new managing director as he reveals club will sign \'one or two\' players each year</a></li> <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/teampages/newcastle-united.html\"> All the latest Manchester United news and headlines</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601894/Sir-Alex-Ferguson-hunted-Newcastle-United-Kevin-Keegan-left.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"We went for Fergie! Newcastle tried to sign United great after Keegan, admits Shepherd\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601894/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">50</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/article-2601894-1D01DDBD00000578-659_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:45','2014-04-11 00:43:28'),(101,'03608dec0bb1bb566afe34f7681a38548eeb55d1d9fd57456e8aca31d03cdfe5','dailymail',NULL,'Blues fans club together to pay Mourinho\'s £8,000 FA fine after Aston Villa sending off','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601783/Blues-fans-club-pay-Mourinhos-8-000-FA-fine-Aston-Villa-sending-off.html',' By Matt Barlow Follow @@Matt_Barlow_DM Published: 12:28 EST, 10 April 2014 | Updated: 16:50 EST, 10 April 2014 588 shares 269 View comments Chelsea fans will launch a collection to pay Jose Mourinho’s £8,000 fine imposed by the Football Association for improper conduct after he was sent to the stands against Aston Villa. They will start collecting on Sunday among supporters travelling to Swansea and will donate the 8,000 £1 coins to charity if the manager, who earns £8million a year, doesn’t want to accept the donation . Mourinho denied the FA charge but his case was rejected by an independent commission at a hearing this week and the fine was confirmed on Thursday. VIDEO: Scroll down to see Mourinho\'s views on Chelsea\'s win against PSG    Fined and warned: Jose Mourinho has been fined £8,000 for the sending off at Villa Park Support: Chelsea fans have vowed to chip in to pay Jose Mourinho\'s fine   Breach: The Chelsea boss breached FA Rule E3 for improper conduct, by re-entering the field of play to speak to the referee  More... Mourinho fined £8,000 and warned for sending off at the end of Aston Villa defeat Mourinho keen to focus on Chelsea\'s league form despite Champions League draw Porto goal machine Martinez monitored by Premier League giants United and Chelsea TACKLE KEOWN: Why Azpilicueta could be just the man to stop rampant Robben... and who was the fittest star I ever played with? SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race Mourinho will NOT face action after running on to pitch to celebrate Chelsea win over PSG   He was also warned of his future conduct, in relation to the incident at Villa Park last month when he twice went onto the pitch to remonstrate to referee Chris Foy, who sent off Ramires and Willian during a Chelsea defeat.Dave Johnstone, a spokesman for the Chelsea fanzine cfcuk, said: \'He’s not hard up but we support Jose Mourinho and we don’t think he should’ve been fined.\'We also wanted to make the point that we think Chris Foy is a terrible referee. So we’ll be holding a collections on the club special train to Swansea and around Stamford Bridge before the Sunderland game.\'If he doesn’t need the money, hopefully there’s a charity that will benefit.\'  Chelsea manager Jose Mourinho - PSG post game press conference To the stands: Mourinho is given a pat on the back by Paul Lambert after being dismissed for his protests  Spark: Ramires\' horror tackle on Karim el Ahmadi caused the row at the end of the game    More... Mourinho fined £8,000 and warned for sending off at the end of Aston Villa defeat Mourinho keen to focus on Chelsea\'s league form despite Champions League draw Porto goal machine Martinez monitored by Premier League giants United and Chelsea TACKLE KEOWN: Why Azpilicueta could be just the man to stop rampant Robben... and who was the fittest star I ever played with? SWANSEA vs CHELSEA: All the latest team news and stats as visitors aim to regain ground in the title race Mourinho will NOT face action after running on to pitch to celebrate Chelsea win over PSG   Share or comment on this article 588shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Matt+Barlow\" rel=\"nofollow\">Matt Barlow</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@Matt_Barlow_DM\">Follow @@Matt_Barlow_DM</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 12:28 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:50 EST, 10 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601783/Blues-fans-club-pay-Mourinhos-8-000-FA-fine-Aston-Villa-sending-off.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2601783/Blues-fans-club-pay-Mourinhos-8-000-FA-fine-Aston-Villa-sending-off.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Blues fans club together to pay Mourinho\'s £8,000 FA fine after Aston Villa sending off\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 588</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2601783/Blues-fans-club-pay-Mourinhos-8-000-FA-fine-Aston-Villa-sending-off.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">269</p> <p class=\"count-tex