bus-park-mile-away-West-Ham-did-upset-Liverpool.html\"> Gerrard: A hot dressing room, dry pitch and the bus had to park a mile away... West Ham did everything they could to upset Liverpool</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598800/Luis-Suarez-stay-Liverpool-according-Liverpool-chief-executive.html\"> Suarez and Rodgers are going nowhere: Liverpool chief gives sponsors assurances pair will be at Anfield next season</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599115/Steven-Gerrard-scored-10-penalties-given-Graham-Poll.html\"> Gerrard has scored 10 penalties for Liverpool this season... but how many should have been given?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598773/Do-Sturridge-Liverpool-star-surprises-young-fans-teaches-THAT-dance.html\"> Do the Sturridge! Liverpool star surprises young fans and teaches them THAT dance</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">His leadership has been exemplary. The young players have a star to look up to and learn from, the senior professionals are full of admiration for one of the finest players this country has ever produced. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Luis Suarez has been disciplined all season: it’s stretching plausible thinking to believe the Liverpool captain has said nothing to and had no influence on the Uruguayan star. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Even if Liverpool don’t win the title, the remarkable improvement from last season is enough for Gerrard to win it.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">What seals it for me though is what Gerrard has done as England captain. It’s this that sets him apart from the rest this season.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Leading by example: Gerrard celebrates the goal against Poland that made absolutely sure of England\'s progress to the World Cup finals in Brazil\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"380\" id=\"i-ab3b0e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599443-059D3B5D00000514-532_634x380.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Leading by example: Gerrard celebrates the goal against Poland that made absolutely sure of England\'s progress to the World Cup finals in Brazil</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Leading by example: Gerrard celebrates the goal against Poland that made absolutely sure of England\'s progress to the World Cup finals in Brazil\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"400\" id=\"i-aa480e66\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599443-18C2A18800000578-164_634x400.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As undisputed skipper for the first time, with no chance of the manager inexplicably giving the armband to John Terry or Rio Ferdinand, Gerrard has flourished. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There will be those who claim they don’t care about international football, club comes first. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Steven Gerrard is sensible enough to realise you can actually have commitment to both club and country. And we all know that once England get to a World Cup everyone in this country gets interested.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Last October, England faced two must-win qualifiers in the space of four days. The mood of the football nation depended on the results of these games. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"The dream: Can Gerrard emulate the great Bobby Moore in 1966 and lift the World Cup in Brazil this summer?\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"452\" id=\"i-acb20e8d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599443-0A2E53A2000005DC-349_634x452.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">The dream: Can Gerrard emulate the great Bobby Moore in 1966 and lift the World Cup in Brazil this summer?</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Gerrard led his country to a 4-1 victory over Montenegro. And then, late in the game, with England holding a precarious 1-0 lead over Poland, he strode through on goal, showing strength and riding challenges, before poking the ball into the back of the net.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">At that moment we all breathed a huge sigh of relief. The captain had delivered. He now has an opportunity to be the best captain England have had since Bobby Moore. I hope he takes it.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">For club and country, Steven Gerrard is my number one this season. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As player, captain, and leader – for club and country - nobody comes close.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599453/Adrian-Durham-column-We-allow-Premier-League-clubs-graveyards-young-English-talents.html\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">CLICK HERE TO READ ADRIAN DURHAM ON THE SHAMEFUL WASTE OF ENGLISH TALENT</a></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599453/Adrian-Durham-column-We-allow-Premier-League-clubs-graveyards-young-English-talents.html\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599499/Adrian-Durham-Roy-Hodgson-John-Stones-Jon-Flanagan-World-Cup.html\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">CLICK HERE TO READ ADRIAN DURHAM ON HODGSON\'S WORLD CUP SQUAD</a><br/></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598824/Gerrard-A-hot-dressing-room-dry-pitch-bus-park-mile-away-West-Ham-did-upset-Liverpool.html\"> Gerrard: A hot dressing room, dry pitch and the bus had to park a mile away... West Ham did everything they could to upset Liverpool</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598800/Luis-Suarez-stay-Liverpool-according-Liverpool-chief-executive.html\"> Suarez and Rodgers are going nowhere: Liverpool chief gives sponsors assurances pair will be at Anfield next season</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599115/Steven-Gerrard-scored-10-penalties-given-Graham-Poll.html\"> Gerrard has scored 10 penalties for Liverpool this season... but how many should have been given?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2598773/Do-Sturridge-Liverpool-star-surprises-young-fans-teaches-THAT-dance.html\"> Do the Sturridge! Liverpool star surprises young fans and teaches them THAT dance</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599443/Adrian-Durham-column-Liverpools-Steven-Gerrard-deserves-win-player-year-ahead-Luis-Suarez.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599443/Adrian-Durham-column-Liverpools-Steven-Gerrard-deserves-win-player-year-ahead-Luis-Suarez.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"ADRIAN DURHAM: Why Gerrard deserves to beat Suarez to Player of the Season award\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599443/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count_small\">232</div><div class=\"shares_text_small\">shares</div> </div> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599443-1CE2B26100000578-459_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:53','2014-04-09 18:11:48'),(109,'6bf81f2a20554bad8610db7d15ec2d31ecea8ef9540582ea6121e30042d806ae','dailymail',NULL,'Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html',' By Phil Duncan Follow @@PhilDuncanF1 Published: 06:48 EST, 9 April 2014 | Updated: 08:11 EST, 9 April 2014 11 shares 58 View comments Nico Rosberg completed more than two race distances at the Bahrain International Circuit on Tuesday in his bid to wrestle the tittle initiative back from Lewis Hamilton. Less than 48 hours after their fascinating battle in Sunday’s Bahrain Grand Prix, Rosberg was back in his Mercedes cockpit for the first in-season test of the campaign. Rosberg, who has already vowed to beat Hamilton to the chequered flag at the Chinese Grand Prix next Sunday, turned in 121 laps - the equivalent of 413 miles. Rosberg: Fair play to Lewis but I\'ll be back in two weeks to win  Testing, testing: Mercedes driver Nico Rosberg took full advantage of the session in Bahrain on Tuesday Let battle commence: Rosberg (left) and Lewis Hamilton look set for a lengthy and thrilling battle Duel: Hamilton (left) held off the challenge of his team-mate to win the Bahrain Grand Prix on Sunday  The German also topped the lap charts with a time of 1:35.697, which was four tenths quicker than Nico Hulkenberg in his Force India. ‘I completed 121 laps today in testing here in Bahrain - that’s like London to Paris and nearly all the way back flat out all the time,’ said Rosberg afterwards. ‘I learned a lot, I am starting to smile again, too and I am getting back into full attack mode for Shanghai.  Second best: Force India driver Nico Hulkenberg was four-tenths of a second behind Rosberg in testing  ‘Part of me is happy we apparently put on a great show in Bahrain which is the best way to shut down all the premature criticism that Formula One was getting. ‘I can assure you there is going to be more of that with a different ending obviously.’ Hamilton, who trails his team-mate in the drivers’ standings by 11 points despite back-to-back wins in Malaysia and Bahrain will take over testing duties from Rosberg on Wednesday. Nico Rosberg donuts his Mercedes F1 car in Kuala Lumpur  Sealed with a kiss: Hamilton celebrates winning the Bahrain Grand Prix and closing the gap on rival Rosberg     More... Hamilton to study Rosberg data as he bids to beat Mercedes team-mate in title battle I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle F1 is boring? No chance! Brilliant Hamilton holds off Rosberg in race of the century Ferrari must work day and night to fix this, says Alonso as he demands improvement after drab display in Bahrain F1 ace Vergne hospitalised after Australian Grand Prix due to weight loss Gutierrez taken to hospital after crash, and credit to Mercedes for allowing Lewis and Rosberg to race... but how long can it last?     Share or comment on this article 11shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Phil+Duncan\" rel=\"nofollow\">Phil Duncan</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@PhilDuncanF1\">Follow @@PhilDuncanF1</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 06:48 EST, 9 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 08:11 EST, 9 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 11</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">58</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Nico Rosberg completed more than two race distances at the Bahrain International Circuit on Tuesday in his bid to wrestle the tittle initiative back from Lewis Hamilton. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Less than 48 hours after their fascinating battle in Sunday’s Bahrain Grand Prix, Rosberg was back in his Mercedes cockpit for the first in-season test of the campaign. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rosberg, who has already vowed to beat Hamilton to the chequered flag at the Chinese Grand Prix next Sunday, turned in 121 laps - the equivalent of 413 miles.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3439924282001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Rosberg: Fair play to Lewis but I\'ll be back in two weeks to win</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/07/video-undefined-1CE6003E00000578-309_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Testing, testing: Mercedes driver Nico Rosberg took full advantage of the session in Bahrain on Tuesday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"360\" id=\"i-ab870e7a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600543-1CF075DF00000578-513_634x360.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Testing, testing: Mercedes driver Nico Rosberg took full advantage of the session in Bahrain on Tuesday</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Let battle commence: Rosberg (left) and Lewis Hamilton look set for a lengthy and thrilling battle\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-ab510e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600543-1CE33CE200000578-647_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Let battle commence: Rosberg (left) and Lewis Hamilton look set for a lengthy and thrilling battle</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Duel: Hamilton (left) held off the challenge of his team-mate to win the Bahrain Grand Prix on Sunday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"369\" id=\"i-a9420e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600543-1CE3E41200000578-410_634x369.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Duel: Hamilton (left) held off the challenge of his team-mate to win the Bahrain Grand Prix on Sunday</p> </div><p> </p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The German also topped the lap charts with a time of 1:35.697, which was four tenths quicker than Nico Hulkenberg in his Force India. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I completed 121 laps today in testing here in Bahrain - that’s like London to Paris and nearly all the way back flat out all the time,’ said Rosberg afterwards.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I learned a lot, I am starting to smile again, too and I am getting back into full attack mode for Shanghai. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Second best: Force India driver Nico Hulkenberg was four-tenths of a second behind Rosberg in testing\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"362\" id=\"i-ab240e79\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600543-1CF079F900000578-391_634x362.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Second best: Force India driver Nico Hulkenberg was four-tenths of a second behind Rosberg in testing</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Part of me is happy we apparently put on a great show in Bahrain which is the best way to shut down all the premature criticism that Formula One was getting.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘I can assure you there is going to be more of that with a different ending obviously.’</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Hamilton, who trails his team-mate in the drivers’ standings by 11 points despite back-to-back wins in Malaysia and Bahrain will take over testing duties from Rosberg on Wednesday.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3393454626001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Nico Rosberg donuts his Mercedes F1 car in Kuala Lumpur</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/03/26/video-undefined-1C93680900000578-375_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Sealed with a kiss: Hamilton celebrates winning the Bahrain Grand Prix and closing the gap on rival Rosberg\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"419\" id=\"i-ab8a0e82\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600543-1CE326EB00000578-746_634x419.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Sealed with a kiss: Hamilton celebrates winning the Bahrain Grand Prix and closing the gap on rival Rosberg</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2599029/Lewis-Hamilton-study-Nico-Rosberg-data-bids-beat-Mercedes-team-mate-title-battle.html\"> Hamilton to study Rosberg data as he bids to beat Mercedes team-mate in title battle</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598780/Nico-Rosberg-promise-win-Chinese-Grand-Prix-losing-Lewis-Hamilton-brilliant-Bahrain-battle.html\"> I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598204/Hamilton-holds-Rosberg-win-Bahrain-Grand-Prix-epic-Mercedes-battle.html\"> F1 is boring? No chance! Brilliant Hamilton holds off Rosberg in race of the century</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/Ferrari-work-day-night-fix-says-Fernando-Alonso-demands-improvement-drab-Bahrain-display.html\"> Ferrari must work day and night to fix this, says Alonso as he demands improvement after drab display in Bahrain</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598138/F1-ace-Jean-Eric-Vergne-hospitalised-Australian-Grand-Prix-weight-loss.html\"> F1 ace Vergne hospitalised after Australian Grand Prix due to weight loss</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598302/Esteban-Gutierrez-taken-hospital-crash-credit-Mercedes-allowing-Lewis-Hamilton-Nico-Rosberg-race-long-last.html\"> Gutierrez taken to hospital after crash, and credit to Mercedes for allowing Lewis and Rosberg to race... but how long can it last?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><br/></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/Rosberg-drives-London-Paris-bid-stop-Hamilton-winning-title.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Rosberg drives \'from London to Paris and back\' in bid to stop Hamilton winning title\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2600543/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">11</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/09/article-2600543-1CF608E700000578-823_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:55','2014-04-09 15:11:43'),(110,'ffa70db39f7f68e12d2b8c4232997f780012c9eaf9e7a865f51a5b692268e87d','dailymail',NULL,'Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders... no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html',' Jurgen Klinsmann is favoured by the Spurs board to be the next manager because he hasn\'t agitated for the jobThe German was offered post after Andre Villas-Boas was sackedLouis van Gaal has been waiting for the Manchester United jobCarlo Ancelotti is an option if he is fired by Real MadridFrank De Boer is also keen to be Tottenham managerSouthampton boss Mauricio Pochettino could be deemed not ready By Neil Ashton Follow @@neilashton_ Published: 18:01 EST, 8 April 2014 | Updated: 04:57 EST, 9 April 2014 24 shares 70 View comments  When Tim Sherwood met Tottenham chairman Daniel Levy last week, he gave him three specific transfer targets. West Ham defender Winston Reid, Manchester City midfielder Gareth Barry and Chelsea striker Romelu Lukaku were the men he wanted at White Hart Lane next season. Sherwood’s recommendations had been taken so seriously during a transfer meeting the previous month that director of football Franco Baldini went to watch Fulham play Everton on March 30, instead of travelling to Anfield to watch Tottenham. Given the 4-0 scoreline at Liverpool, it was a wise decision. VIDEO: Scroll down to watch Sherwood defiant over Spurs future after 5-1 win  All over bar the shouting: Tim Sherwood will be replaced as Tottenham manager in the summer   Character: Sherwood has been outspoken as Spurs boss and at times it might have been too much Attention! Sherwood (right) salutes Emmanuel Adebayor after the Spurs striker\'s second against Sunderland Don\'t get too comfortable: Sherwood (centre) sits in the dug-out before Tottenham\'s 5-1 win over Sunderland   Sherwood defiant over Spurs future after 5-1 win  More from Neil Ashton...   Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public 08/04/14   Arsenal are not the tight-knit family unit they were... Wenger can\'t do it all on his own 01/04/14   As Hillsborough anniversary approaches, football must not forget all those who have been loved and lost in stadium tragedies 25/03/14   Why do some Tottenham fans want Levy out of White Hart Lane when Spurs are consistently punching above their weight? 18/03/14   Sturridge may never be a Kop idol like Suarez or Gerrard - he\'s destined to be brilliant but unloved at Liverpool, like Owen 11/03/14   Shaw, Lallana, Lambert and Rodriguez are Saints success stories... Arsenal, Chelsea, Spurs and the rest should follow Southampton\'s lead and go for full English 04/03/14   ASH WEDNESDAY: Leave Januzaj alone! Only United kid must decide if he wants to play for England... and so what if he does? 18/02/14   United used to be kings of the last-minute winner... but under their new manager, the players just don\'t fancy it any more 11/02/14   Another big-game snub means Cole\'s time at Chelsea is over... but don\'t rule out a shock move back to Arsenal 04/02/14   VIEW FULL ARCHIVE This break from the norm for Baldini, who usually sits close to Levy in the directors\' box at Tottenham matches, was significant. Lukaku and Barry both played the full 90 minutes for Everton in their 3-1 victory and they were wanted men. Sherwood was desperate to get them to Spurs. At the time he was in with a chance of keeping the job, despite the interest from Louis van Gaal, Frank de Boer, Carlo Ancelotti and Mauricio Pochettino. Of the names under consideration at White Hart Lane, former Tottenham striker Jurgen Klinsmann is the only candidate who has not been agitating for the job behind the scenes. Big tick there from the boardroom. More on them in a moment. Sherwood knows he has made mistakes since he replaced Andre Villas-Boas as Tottenham’s manager and it probably wasn’t a good idea to ask for the ear of the chairman after another leathering, this time at Anfield. Goodness knows Levy has had a gutful of that this season and anybody who knows him will tell you that no-one gets away with humiliating Tottenham’s chairman in public. This season alone he has been on the end of some hidings: 6-0 and 5-1 against Manchester City, 5-0 and and 4-0 against Liverpool, 4-0 at Chelsea, 3-0 at home to West Ham and three defeats against Arsenal. In Levy’s world, someone will always pay the price for that. Sherwood has certainly provided some entertainment in his 23 games in charge of Spurs, but Levy believes he lacks maturity and stature for such a prestigious position.  Tim\'s targets: Romelu Lukaku, Gareth Barry (below left) and Winston Reid (below right) were wanted by Sherwood when he thought he still had a future as Tottenham manager     It probably wasn’t wise, even in jest, for Sherwood to say that he would be returning to the technical area for the Sunderland game and ‘might knock a few people out’. He knows that. He is highly-emotional, passionate about his work and his team. There is something to be said for that, even if it is a bit much at times. Sherwood spoke of the ‘shackles coming off’ after the team ran out 5-1 winners against Sunderland on Monday, shining a torch on his pre-match team talk with Tottenham’s players. They have been made aware that their manager is leaving at the end of the season and will be replaced someone with vast experience in the game.  Waiting game: Louis van Gaal (right) has kept Spurs hanging on as he watches the situation at Manchester United Big tick: Jurgen Klinsmann (left) is favoured by the Spurs board, while Frank De Boer also wants the job Under pressure: Carlo Ancelotti (left) remains an option for Tottenham if he is fired by Real Madrid Not the answer: Southampton boss Mauricio Pochettino isn\'t ready to manage Tottenham  More... Everton fairytale has us hooked, shame it\'s built on £50m loan sham of Lukaku, Barry and Deulofeu (so Wenger\'s right to moan) I won\'t be No 2 at Spurs, says Sherwood as Tottenham line up Holland boss Van Gaal Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer The mad world of King Louis van Gaal: Tottenham\'s next boss in waiting? Lukaku transfer hinders on World Cup as Chelsea hope strong display from Belgium star will increase asking price That is Levy’s wish, something he has already articulated to his board as he begins to plan for next season. Presumably this means Southampton manager Pochettino, who has lost twice against Tottenham in the league this season, is not ready for the 14th biggest job in European football, according to the 2014 Deloitte Money League. At 42, a man who refuses to speak English despite a near perfect command of the language, is not the answer for Tottenham at this moment in time. Klinsmann, who is preparing for the World Cup with the USA, had been offered the position until the end of the season when Villas-Boas was fired. Levy had tried to tempt him with the bait that he could keep a closer eye on the Americans playing in Europe if he could help Spurs out in the short term. Klinsmann said no. Sherwood\'s journey from happy-go-lucky rookie to troubled manager   Rebuilding job: Daniel Levy (front) will have to appoint yet another manager  After Real Madrid’s stunning 4-3 defeat at home by Barcelona on March 23, Ancelotti was under so much pressure at the Bernabeu he believed he could be fired at the end of the season. His team are now third in La Liga, three points off Atletico, although they are in Friday’s draw for the Champions League semi-final after beating Borussia Dortmund. Ancelotti has not been ruled out. The Italian remains an option if he is fired. Then there is Van Gaal, the man who has kept Tottenham waiting after hanging out for the possibility that Manchester United could replace David Moyes. The relative upturn in recent results, with the exception of the 3-0 defeat at home by Manchester City, has closed the door on Van Gaal’s hopes of heading to Old Trafford. Moyes is staying for the time being. Sherwood will not remain and he will walk away from Spurs after their final game of the season at home to Aston Villa on May 11. Beyond that, Levy will have to start rebuilding this club. Again.   More... Everton fairytale has us hooked, shame it\'s built on £50m loan sham of Lukaku, Barry and Deulofeu (so Wenger\'s right to moan) I won\'t be No 2 at Spurs, says Sherwood as Tottenham line up Holland boss Van Gaal Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer The mad world of King Louis van Gaal: Tottenham\'s next boss in waiting? Lukaku transfer hinders on World Cup as Chelsea hope strong display from Belgium star will increase asking price    Share or comment on this article 24shares','\n<ul class=\"article-summary sport\"><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Jurgen Klinsmann is favoured by the Spurs board to be the next manager because he hasn\'t agitated for the job</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">The German was offered post after Andre Villas-Boas was sacked</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Louis van Gaal has been waiting for the Manchester United job</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Carlo Ancelotti is an option if he is fired by Real Madrid</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Frank De Boer is also keen to be Tottenham manager</font></b></li><li><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.4em;\">Southampton boss Mauricio Pochettino could be deemed not ready<br/></font></b></li></ul>\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1000161/Neil-Ashton.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Neil Ashton</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@neilashton_\">Follow @@neilashton_</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 18:01 EST, 8 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 04:57 EST, 9 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 24</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">70</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">When Tim Sherwood met Tottenham chairman Daniel Levy last week, he gave him three specific transfer targets.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">West Ham defender Winston Reid, Manchester City midfielder Gareth Barry and Chelsea striker Romelu Lukaku were the men he wanted at White Hart Lane next season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sherwood’s recommendations had been taken so seriously during a transfer meeting the previous month that director of football Franco Baldini went to watch Fulham play Everton on March 30, instead of travelling to Anfield to watch Tottenham.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Given the 4-0 scoreline at Liverpool, it was a wise decision.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">VIDEO:</span></span> Scroll down to watch Sherwood defiant over Spurs future after 5-1 win</span><br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"All over bar the shouting: Tim Sherwood will be replaced as Tottenham manager in the summer\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-ae7f0e8e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CEAC1C100000578-555_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">All over bar the shouting: Tim Sherwood will be replaced as Tottenham manager in the summer</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Character: Sherwood has been outspoken as Spurs boss and at times it might have been too much\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"561\" id=\"i-ad110e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CEAC13300000578-139_634x561.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Character: Sherwood has been outspoken as Spurs boss and at times it might have been too much</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Attention! Sherwood (right) salutes Emmanuel Adebayor after the Spurs striker\'s second against Sunderland\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"411\" id=\"i-b10c0ea8\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CEABD8B00000578-917_634x411.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Attention! Sherwood (right) salutes Emmanuel Adebayor after the Spurs striker\'s second against Sunderland</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Don\'t get too comfortable: Sherwood (centre) sits in the dug-out before Tottenham\'s 5-1 win over Sunderland\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"331\" id=\"i-ad610e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CEA7C3000000578-807_634x331.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Don\'t get too comfortable: Sherwood (centre) sits in the dug-out before Tottenham\'s 5-1 win over Sunderland</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"moduleFull\">  <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3443071424001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Sherwood defiant over Spurs future after 5-1 win</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/video-undefined-1CEB4F0F00000578-877_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"item\"> <div class=\"columnist-archive-narrow bogr1\"> <span class=\"tl\"> </span> <span class=\"tr\"> </span> <h3>More from Neil Ashton...</h3> <ul> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html\">Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public</a> <span class=\"date\">08/04/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2594332/Arsenal-not-tight-knit-family-unit-Wenger-own.html\">Arsenal are not the tight-knit family unit they were... Wenger can\'t do it all on his own</a> <span class=\"date\">01/04/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2588939/As-Hillsborough-anniversary-approaches-football-not-forget-loved-lost.html\">As Hillsborough anniversary approaches, football must not forget all those who have been loved and lost in stadium tragedies</a> <span class=\"date\">25/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2583575/Ash-Wednesday-Why-Tottenham-fans-want-Levy-Spurs-punching-weight.html\">Why do some Tottenham fans want Levy out of White Hart Lane when Spurs are consistently punching above their weight?</a> <span class=\"date\">18/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2578345/Sturridge-never-Kop-idol-like-Suarez-Gerrard-hes-destined-brilliant-unloved-Liverpool-like-Owen.html\">Sturridge may never be a Kop idol like Suarez or Gerrard - he\'s destined to be brilliant but unloved at Liverpool, like Owen</a> <span class=\"date\">11/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2572962/Shaw-Lallana-Lambert-Rodriguez-Saints-success-stories-Arsenal-rest-follow-Southamptons-lead.html\">Shaw, Lallana, Lambert and Rodriguez are Saints success stories... Arsenal, Chelsea, Spurs and the rest should follow Southampton\'s lead and go for full English</a> <span class=\"date\">04/03/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2562116/Leave-Adnan-Januzaj-Only-United-kid-decide-wants-play-England-ASH-WEDNESDAY.html\">ASH WEDNESDAY: Leave Januzaj alone! Only United kid must decide if he wants to play for England... and so what if he does?</a> <span class=\"date\">18/02/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2556814/NEIL-ASHTON-United-used-kings-minute-winner-new-manager-players-just-dont-fancy-it.html\">United used to be kings of the last-minute winner... but under their new manager, the players just don\'t fancy it any more</a> <span class=\"date\">11/02/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"/sport/football/article-2551560/Another-big-game-snub-means-Coles-time-Chelsea-dont-rule-shock-Arsenal.html\">Another big-game snub means Cole\'s time at Chelsea is over... but don\'t rule out a shock move back to Arsenal</a> <span class=\"date\">04/02/14</span> </li> <li class=\"cleared\"> <span class=\"arrow-small-r\"> </span> <a href=\"columnist-1000161/Neil-Ashton.html\">VIEW FULL ARCHIVE</a> </li> </ul> </div> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">This break from the norm for Baldini, who usually sits close to Levy in the directors\' box at Tottenham matches, was significant.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Lukaku and Barry both played the full 90 minutes for Everton in their 3-1 victory and they were wanted men. Sherwood was desperate to get them to Spurs.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">At the time he was in with a chance of keeping the job, despite the interest from Louis van Gaal, Frank de Boer, Carlo Ancelotti and Mauricio Pochettino.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Of the names under consideration at White Hart Lane, former Tottenham striker Jurgen Klinsmann is the only candidate who has not been agitating for the job behind the scenes. Big tick there from the boardroom. More on them in a moment.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sherwood knows he has made mistakes since he replaced Andre Villas-Boas as Tottenham’s manager and it probably wasn’t a good idea to ask for the ear of the chairman after another leathering, this time at Anfield.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Goodness knows Levy has had a gutful of that this season and anybody who knows him will tell you that no-one gets away with humiliating Tottenham’s chairman in public.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">This season alone he has been on the end of some hidings: 6-0 and 5-1 against Manchester City, 5-0 and and 4-0 against Liverpool, 4-0 at Chelsea, 3-0 at home to West Ham and three defeats against Arsenal.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">In Levy’s world, someone will always pay the price for that.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sherwood has certainly provided some entertainment in his 23 games in charge of Spurs, but Levy believes he lacks maturity and stature for such a prestigious position.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tim\'s targets: Romelu Lukaku, Gareth Barry (below left) and Winston Reid (below right) were wanted by Sherwood when he thought he still had a future as Tottenham manager\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"366\" id=\"i-adc90e92\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CE1FC0400000578-696_634x366.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tim\'s targets: Romelu Lukaku, Gareth Barry (below left) and Winston Reid (below right) were wanted by Sherwood when he thought he still had a future as Tottenham manager</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Wanted: Barry was on Sherwood\'s radar\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-acc00e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CE22EC200000578-415_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"On the list: Reid was another player wanted by Sherwood\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-add60e89\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CE2E66C00000578-770_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It probably wasn’t wise, even in jest, for Sherwood to say that he would be returning to the technical area for the Sunderland game and ‘might knock a few people out’. He knows that.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">He is highly-emotional, passionate about his work and his team. There is something to be said for that, even if it is a bit much at times.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sherwood spoke of the ‘shackles coming off’ after the team ran out 5-1 winners against Sunderland on Monday, shining a torch on his pre-match team talk with Tottenham’s players.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">They have been made aware that their manager is leaving at the end of the season and will be replaced someone with vast experience in the game. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Waiting game: Louis van Gaal (right) has kept Spurs hanging on as he watches the situation at Manchester United\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"463\" id=\"i-a9ef0e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CF0451400000578-471_634x463.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Waiting game: Louis van Gaal (right) has kept Spurs hanging on as he watches the situation at Manchester United</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Favourite: Jurgen Klinsmann is liked by the Spurs board as he has not agitated for the job\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-abc50e7a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CF0451D00000578-967_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Interest: Frank De Boer also wants the Tottenham job\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-9cd80e32\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CF0451900000578-81_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Big tick: Jurgen Klinsmann (left) is favoured by the Spurs board, while Frank De Boer also wants the job<br/></p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Under pressure: Carlo Ancelotti (left) remains an option for Tottenham if he is fired by Real Madrid\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"431\" id=\"i-af890e9b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CEA6DA600000578-863_634x431.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Under pressure: Carlo Ancelotti (left) remains an option for Tottenham if he is fired by Real Madrid</p> </div><p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Not the answer: Southampton boss Mauricio Pochettino isn\'t ready to manage Tottenham\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"477\" id=\"i-ac160e80\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CDB094300000578-643_634x477.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Not the answer: Southampton boss Mauricio Pochettino isn\'t ready to manage Tottenham</p> </div><p> </p></div> <p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\"><div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599917/Everton-fairytale-hooked-shame-built-50m-loan-sham-Lukaku-Barry-Deulofeu-Wengers-right-moan.html\"> Everton fairytale has us hooked, shame it\'s built on £50m loan sham of Lukaku, Barry and Deulofeu (so Wenger\'s right to moan)</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600039/Tim-Sherwood-not-assistant-manager-Tottenham.html\"> I won\'t be No 2 at Spurs, says Sherwood as Tottenham line up Holland boss Van Gaal</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599731/Louis-Van-Gaal-reveals-hes-totally-sick-national-team-coach-Holland-boss-opens-door-Spurs-summer.html\"> Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599636/The-mad-world-King-Louis-van-Gaal-Tottenhams-boss-waiting.html\"> The mad world of King Louis van Gaal: Tottenham\'s next boss in waiting?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599706/Romelu-Lukaku-transfer-hinders-World-Cup-Chelsea-hope-strong-display-Belgium-star-increase-asking-price.html\"> Lukaku transfer hinders on World Cup as Chelsea hope strong display from Belgium star will increase asking price</a></li> </ul> </div>   </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That is Levy’s wish, something he has already articulated to his board as he begins to plan for next season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Presumably this means Southampton manager Pochettino, who has lost twice against Tottenham in the league this season, is not ready for the 14th biggest job in European football, according to the 2014 Deloitte Money League.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">At 42, a man who refuses to speak English despite a near perfect command of the language, is not the answer for Tottenham at this moment in time.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Klinsmann, who is preparing for the World Cup with the USA, had been offered the position until the end of the season when Villas-Boas was fired.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Levy had tried to tempt him with the bait that he could keep a closer eye on the Americans playing in Europe if he could help Spurs out in the short term. Klinsmann said no.</font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3427041464001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Sherwood\'s journey from happy-go-lucky rookie to troubled manager</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/03/video-undefined-1CCE869700000578-6_636x360.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS\"> <img alt=\"Rebuilding job: Daniel Levy (front) will have to appoint yet another manager\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-add10e8b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CE7C1A600000578-875_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Rebuilding job: Daniel Levy (front) will have to appoint yet another manager</p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">After Real Madrid’s stunning 4-3 defeat at home by Barcelona on March 23, Ancelotti was under so much pressure at the Bernabeu he believed he could be fired at the end of the season.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">His team are now third in La Liga, three points off Atletico, although they are in Friday’s draw for the Champions League semi-final after beating Borussia Dortmund. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Ancelotti has not been ruled out. The Italian remains an option if he is fired.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Then there is Van Gaal, the man who has kept Tottenham waiting after hanging out for the possibility that Manchester United could replace David Moyes. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The relative upturn in recent results, with the exception of the 3-0 defeat at home by Manchester City, has closed the door on Van Gaal’s hopes of heading to Old Trafford. Moyes is staying for the time being.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Sherwood will not remain and he will walk away from Spurs after their final game of the season at home to Aston Villa on May 11.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Beyond that, Levy will have to start rebuilding this club. Again.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599917/Everton-fairytale-hooked-shame-built-50m-loan-sham-Lukaku-Barry-Deulofeu-Wengers-right-moan.html\"> Everton fairytale has us hooked, shame it\'s built on £50m loan sham of Lukaku, Barry and Deulofeu (so Wenger\'s right to moan)</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2600039/Tim-Sherwood-not-assistant-manager-Tottenham.html\"> I won\'t be No 2 at Spurs, says Sherwood as Tottenham line up Holland boss Van Gaal</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599731/Louis-Van-Gaal-reveals-hes-totally-sick-national-team-coach-Holland-boss-opens-door-Spurs-summer.html\"> Van Gaal reveals he\'s \'totally sick\' of being a national team coach as Holland boss opens door for Spurs move in the summer</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599636/The-mad-world-King-Louis-van-Gaal-Tottenhams-boss-waiting.html\"> The mad world of King Louis van Gaal: Tottenham\'s next boss in waiting?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2599706/Romelu-Lukaku-transfer-hinders-World-Cup-Chelsea-hope-strong-display-Belgium-star-increase-asking-price.html\"> Lukaku transfer hinders on World Cup as Chelsea hope strong display from Belgium star will increase asking price</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599812/Tottenham-boss-Sherwood-wanted-Lukaku-Barry-Reid-instead-got-marching-orders-no-one-gets-away-humiliating-Levy-public.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Tottenham boss Sherwood wanted Lukaku, Barry and Reid, instead he got his marching orders… no-one gets away with humiliating Levy in public\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2599812/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">24</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599812-1CF0BDF600000578-918_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:56','2014-04-09 11:57:00'),(111,'62aa063b6625ddcedf3d92ba6038b0e4dd9a61356074c7708e90780bd59d9cd6','dailymail',NULL,'Ferrari must work day and night to fix this, says Fernando Alonso as he demands improvement after drab Bahrain display','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/Ferrari-work-day-night-fix-says-Fernando-Alonso-demands-improvement-drab-Bahrain-display.html',' By Ian Parkes, Press Association Published: 04:32 EST, 8 April 2014 | Updated: 07:57 EST, 8 April 2014 21 shares 20 View comments Fernando Alonso has called on Ferrari to work \'day and night\' in an attempt to fire the ailing marque back to the front of the grid. Ferrari\'s failings this season were laid bare under the glare of the spotlights at the Bahrain International Circuit on Sunday. On a track where power is critical, Ferrari found themselves lacking in that area, resulting in Alonso finishing ninth and team-mate Kimi Raikkonen 10th, both just over 30 seconds adrift of race-winner Lewis Hamilton.  Up in smoke: Fernando Alonso could manage only 9th on Sunday and has demanded improvement from Ferrari   Out of sorts: The Spaniard has demanded improvement from Ferrari after struggling in Bahrain  With Mercedes the benchmark following their dominant start to the season, Alonso is again facing another catch-up campaign and a potential fifth year at Ferrari without a world title. \'Sunday\'s race was complicated for us, even if we knew what to expect, because with its long straights the track showed up our weak points,\' said Alonso. \'Although we did all we could, we can\'t be happy with our level of performance and now our sole focus must be on working day and night. \'The season is in its early stages and we can stage a recovery. We have the resources and the potential to do it and it\'s all down to us.\'  Battle: The Ferrari pair of Alonso (left) and Raikkonen were off the pace of the leaders during Sunday\'s race  Taking a stroll: Alonso is already 35 points behind Nico Rosberg in the drivers\' standings  The teams return to the circuit on Tuesday for the first of four two-day tests this year as in-season testing returns to Formula One. Whilst Ferrari know they cannot now alter anything to do with the new power unit as they have been homologated, they can focus on improving their aero package to find time. \'The test is very important,\' added Alonso. \'We have a very aggressive programme, which we need as our rivals will not just be sitting back and watching.\' Team principal Stefano Domenicali claimed the weekend overall was \'as difficult as we had thought it would be\', with the grand prix one \'we must forget\'. President Luca Di Montezemolo attended his first race this year, and he would have been far from happy with what he witnessed as Ferrari struggled to make any inroads. Domenicali has also emphasised the critical importance of the next two days in Bahrain, saying: \'I expect to see an initial step up in terms of quality. \'The team must not get downhearted, even if things have not turned out the way they should so far. \'They must continue to work in order to step up a gear as quickly as possible.\'   More... Hamilton to study Rosberg data as he bids to beat Mercedes team-mate in title battle I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle Gutierrez taken to hospital after crash, and credit to Mercedes for allowing Lewis and Rosberg to race... but how long can it last? F1 is boring? No chance! Brilliant Hamilton holds off Rosberg in race of the century   Share or comment on this article 21shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Ian+Parkes,+Press+Association\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ian Parkes, Press Association</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 04:32 EST, 8 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 07:57 EST, 8 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/Ferrari-work-day-night-fix-says-Fernando-Alonso-demands-improvement-drab-Bahrain-display.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/Ferrari-work-day-night-fix-says-Fernando-Alonso-demands-improvement-drab-Bahrain-display.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Ferrari must work day and night to fix this, says Alonso as he demands improvement after drab display in Bahrain\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 21</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/Ferrari-work-day-night-fix-says-Fernando-Alonso-demands-improvement-drab-Bahrain-display.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">20</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Fernando Alonso has called on Ferrari to work \'day and night\' in an attempt to fire the ailing marque back to the front of the grid. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ferrari\'s failings this season were laid bare under the glare of the spotlights at the Bahrain International Circuit on Sunday. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">On a track where power is critical, Ferrari found themselves lacking in that area, resulting in Alonso finishing ninth and team-mate Kimi Raikkonen 10th, both just over 30 seconds adrift of race-winner Lewis Hamilton. </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Up in smoke: Fernando Alonso could manage only 9th on Sunday and has demanded improvement from Ferrari\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"305\" id=\"i-61d30d60\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-0-1CE2CDDA00000578-518_634x305.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Up in smoke: Fernando Alonso could manage only 9th on Sunday and has demanded improvement from Ferrari</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Out of sorts: The Spaniard has demanded improvement from Ferrari after struggling in Bahrain\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"390\" id=\"i-addc0e8d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599598-1CE2549A00000578-773_634x390.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Out of sorts: The Spaniard has demanded improvement from Ferrari after struggling in Bahrain</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With Mercedes the benchmark following their dominant start to the season, Alonso is again facing another catch-up campaign and a potential fifth year at Ferrari without a world title. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Sunday\'s race was complicated for us, even if we knew what to expect, because with its long straights the track showed up our weak points,\' said Alonso. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'Although we did all we could, we can\'t be happy with our level of performance and now our sole focus must be on working day and night. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'The season is in its early stages and we can stage a recovery. We have the resources and the potential to do it and it\'s all down to us.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Battle: The Ferrari pair of Alonso (left) and Raikkonen were off the pace of the leaders during Sunday\'s race\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"381\" id=\"i-b04d0ea4\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599598-1CE30BDE00000578-843_634x381.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Battle: The Ferrari pair of Alonso (left) and Raikkonen were off the pace of the leaders during Sunday\'s race</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS\"> <img alt=\"Taking a stroll: Alonso is already 35 points behind Nico Rosberg in the drivers\' standings\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-ae500e8d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-2599598-1CDA961700000578-886_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Taking a stroll: Alonso is already 35 points behind Nico Rosberg in the drivers\' standings</p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The teams return to the circuit on Tuesday for the first of four two-day tests this year as in-season testing returns to Formula One. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Whilst Ferrari know they cannot now alter anything to do with the new power unit as they have been homologated, they can focus on improving their aero package to find time. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'The test is very important,\' added Alonso. \'We have a very aggressive programme, which we need as our rivals will not just be sitting back and watching.\'</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"> Team principal Stefano Domenicali claimed the weekend overall was \'as difficult as we had thought it would be\', with the grand prix one \'we must forget\'. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">President Luca Di Montezemolo attended his first race this year, and he would have been far from happy with what he witnessed as Ferrari struggled to make any inroads. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Domenicali has also emphasised the critical importance of the next two days in Bahrain, saying: \'I expect to see an initial step up in terms of quality. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'The team must not get downhearted, even if things have not turned out the way they should so far. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\'They must continue to work in order to step up a gear as quickly as possible.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2599029/Lewis-Hamilton-study-Nico-Rosberg-data-bids-beat-Mercedes-team-mate-title-battle.html\"> Hamilton to study Rosberg data as he bids to beat Mercedes team-mate in title battle</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598780/Nico-Rosberg-promise-win-Chinese-Grand-Prix-losing-Lewis-Hamilton-brilliant-Bahrain-battle.html\"> I\'m coming for you, Lewis: Rosberg in promise to win Chinese GP after losing out to Hamilton in brilliant Bahrain battle</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598302/Esteban-Gutierrez-taken-hospital-crash-credit-Mercedes-allowing-Lewis-Hamilton-Nico-Rosberg-race-long-last.html\"> Gutierrez taken to hospital after crash, and credit to Mercedes for allowing Lewis and Rosberg to race... but how long can it last?</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/formulaone/article-2598204/Hamilton-holds-Rosberg-win-Bahrain-Grand-Prix-epic-Mercedes-battle.html\"> F1 is boring? No chance! Brilliant Hamilton holds off Rosberg in race of the century</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/Ferrari-work-day-night-fix-says-Fernando-Alonso-demands-improvement-drab-Bahrain-display.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/Ferrari-work-day-night-fix-says-Fernando-Alonso-demands-improvement-drab-Bahrain-display.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Ferrari must work day and night to fix this, says Alonso as he demands improvement after drab display in Bahrain\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/formulaone/article-2599598/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">21</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/08/article-0-1CE2CDDA00000578-700_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 16:58:56','2014-04-08 14:57:21'),(112,'4b0d16ac40a9e4d15f5d7cf03fe3288a96dec22158047541885721e383feeaca','dailymail',NULL,'THE TOP SPIN: Yuvraj\'s tortuous final meltdown might just have done Twenty20 a favour (yes, really)','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2598932/THE-TOP-SPIN-Yuvrajs-tortuous-final-meltdown-just-Twenty20-favour-yes-really.html',' By Lawrence Booth Follow @@the_topspin Published: 04:21 EST, 8 April 2014 | Updated: 04:21 EST, 8 April 2014 5 shares 0 View comments   The rumour persists that Clive Lloyd deliberately dropped Geoff Boycott during the 1979 World Cup final in order to prolong his tortoise-like opening stand with Mike Brearley. Lloyd denies it - ‘not true, but it wouldn’t have been a bad tactic’ - though the myth might have occurred to Tissara Perera as he stood at long-off on Sunday and watched Yuvraj Singh hit a Nuwan Kulasekara full-toss straight in his direction. It’s not usually sensible to grant Yuvraj a life. But this was his 21st ball – and he had managed only 11. India were going nowhere, and slowly. But Perera did what any reputable pro would do: he held on.  Staring into the abyss: Yuvraj Singh contemplates his batting meltdown after the World Twenty20 final The end: Yuvraj (right) looks disgusted as Nuwan Kulasekara (left) celebrates his dismissal  More from Lawrence Booth...   THE TOP SPIN: Yuvraj\'s tortuous final meltdown might just have done Twenty20 a favour (yes, really) 07/04/14   THE TOP SPIN: These are difficult times for England and they may get worse... but that\'s no reason to turn on Giles before he\'s had a proper crack 01/04/14   TOP SPIN: Broad was more bothered about safety than defeat - he knows it\'s better to have a dead match than a dead player 25/03/14   THE TOP SPIN: Cook and Flower deserve some sympathy but England fans be warned, it could get worse before it gets better 06/01/14   THE TOP SPIN: It could and should be curtains for Bresnan, Carberry and Panesar... and Bairstow already has Buttler breathing down his neck 30/12/13   THE TOP SPIN: Forget the moaners, watching Swann whirl away has been one of the highlights of my career 23/12/13   THE TOP SPIN: Arthur was looking to the future when he got the chop... and now the Aussies are better in every department 18/12/13   TOP SPIN AT THE TEST: The good, the bad and the ugly from day five in Perth 17/12/13   TOP SPIN AT THE TEST: The good, the bad and the ugly from day four in Perth 16/12/13   VIEW FULL ARCHIVE Needless to say, reports emerged after Sri Lanka had comfortably overhauled India’s curious total of 130 for four that Yuvraj’s home in Chandigarh had been stoned. His dad Yograj has already issued a ‘don’t blame my boy’ plea. We await the burning effigies. Meltdowns in cricket are supposed to be the preserve of bowlers – especially left-arm spinners, though Leicestershire seamer Scott Boswell’s 14-ball over in the final of the 2001 C&G Trophy at Lord’s remains perhaps the most famous example. Yet Yuvraj’s tortured half-hour in Dhaka must take its place among cricket’s cruellest vignettes. And it’s unclear whether the post-match words of his captain MS Dhoni will have helped. ‘Yuvi tried his best,’ said Dhoni, falling awkwardly between an arm round the shoulder and a patronising pat on the head. It’s the kind of thing my sports teachers used to say to me. The sense of cruelty on Sunday stemmed from a few factors. Seven years ago, during the inaugural World Twenty20 in South Africa, Yuvraj hit Stuart Broad for six sixes in an over at Durban. That, not 21 boundary-less balls, was supposed to be his T20 epitaph. And this was the final of a tournament in which India had been the best – and, until now, only unbeaten – team. Victory here, and they would hold all three global ICC trophies. A miserable few months would be glossed over! Then there was the impending IPL, a competition which routinely turns the other cheek to its latest corruption scandal and proclaims itself the zenith of all things T20. What better way to whet appetites than for Yuvraj, one of the IPL’s poster boys, to go berserk? All the while, at the other end, was Virat Kohli, a smouldering ball of fury at the best of times and comfortably the best batsman in the competition. Yet during India’s dreadful final four overs, he managed to face only eight balls. The script was being torn up in front of his face – by a team-mate. When Yuvraj approached Kohli during the presentation ceremony and gave him a hug – half-consoling, half-apologetic – Kohli barely glanced up from his smartphone.  Missing out: A struggling Yuvraj watches the ball go by  More... Pietersen jets off to India for IPL as Cook returns to the crease after Ashes nightmare Root signs two-year extension to stay with Yorkshire through to 2016 Anderson takes five but England hopefuls struggle on opening day of County Championship Sri Lanka legends Sangakkara and Jayawardene bow out in style with World Twenty20 triumph England Women slump to six wicket defeat in World T20 final against superb Aussies England captain Edwards dreams of Aussie double ahead of Women\'s World T20 final It was dramatic, all right. And it was a reminder that a poor innings can be just as destructive to a team’s chances in Twenty20 as a poor spell. Batting can be as lonely as bowling. The former New Zealand captain Martin Crowe suggested on Twitter that ‘it was like watching Bradman at one end and Chris Martin at the other. T20 at its worst. Bring in the batting sub rule.’ It’s a nicely quirky idea, and few are better at those than Crowe. But Yuvraj’s struggles were grimly compelling. Boswell had to complete that over 13 years ago – so why should Yuvraj have been allowed to escape Sri Lanka’s bowlers? One of them couldn’t hit the cut strip, and the other couldn’t get it off the square. But, really, what’s the difference? Twenty20 is a batsman’s game, so let’s occasionally hear it for the bowlers. Besides, Sri Lanka’s seamers were not easy to hit. In the 11 legal deliveries that followed Yuvraj’s departure, India scored just seven off the bat. Dhoni, regarded as one of history’s finest finishers, made four runs off seven balls. Had no one watched Ravi Bopara’s handling of Lasith Malinga in Chittagong? So, yes, Yuvraj had a shocker. But should he have been put in that position in the first place? He had, after all, produced only one innings of note all tournament – 60 off 43 balls against a poor Australian side in a game India didn’t need to win. His three other innings ahead of the final had produced 29 runs from 38 balls. He was manifestly out of touch, as he has been in international cricket for some time. Dhoni did his best to defend Yuvraj afterwards, protesting that only Suresh Raina among India’s batsmen was capable of timing the ball from the very start. But this didn’t deal with the obvious fact that Yuvraj was badly out of nick, nor did it tally with Dhoni’s promotion of himself above Raina. India’s experience of the semi-final win over South Africa, when Raina made 21 off 10 balls to turn the chase into a stroll, seemed to have been completely forgotten.  Contrast: As Yuvraj struggled, Virat Kohli (right) was in superb nick but did not face enough deliveries  THE TOP SPIN ON TWITTER For more cricket-related snippets, feel free to go to twitter.com/the_topspin Logic suggested a batting order of Raina-Dhoni-Yuvraj. In the event, Yuvraj-Dhoni-Raina cost India the title. And yet, as Boris Becker once said after losing at Wimbledon, ‘Nobody died.’ In fact, a few people – especially in Colombo – may even have come alive. Besides, Twenty20’s critics often complain of its tedious predictability, of one six after another robbing it of tension. Yuvraj’s innings, in the most-watched Twenty20 international for years, bucked the trend spectacularly. He may not appreciate the thought right now, but Yuvraj may just have done Twenty20 a favour.  THAT WAS THE WEEK THAT WAS Long live the King! More... Pietersen jets off to India for IPL as Cook returns to the crease after Ashes nightmare Root signs two-year extension to stay with Yorkshire through to 2016 Anderson takes five but England hopefuls struggle on opening day of County Championship Sri Lanka legends Sangakkara and Jayawardene bow out in style with World Twenty20 triumph England Women slump to six wicket defeat in World T20 final against superb Aussies England captain Edwards dreams of Aussie double ahead of Women\'s World T20 final No one at the ICC seems quite sure what to do with N Srinivasan following his enforced abdication – temporary or otherwise – as president of the BCCI. In private, the message is being conveyed that other boards are dealing with an organisation and not an individual. In other words, the ground is being prepared: if the embarrassment of appointing as ICC chairman a man who has redefined ‘conflicts of interest’, who seemed remarkably unclear about the role his son-in-law played at Chennai Super Kings, and who has presided over the most bullying organisation in cricket since the days of the old Anglo-Australian veto – if the embarrassment grows too strong, the likes of the ECB and Cricket Australia can always claim they were negotiating with the BCCI and not Srini himself. Brilliant, eh? In the meantime, let’s leave you with the words of Paul Marsh, boss of FICA: ‘The prospect of Mr Srinivasan taking the highest posting in world cricket, while these matters are unresolved, is an impossible one.’ But is anyone listening? Sneaking up on the rails Last week this column argued that Ashley Giles – everyone’s favourite new punchbag – deserved not to be written off on the basis of one Twenty20 shocker (just as he didn’t deserve a knighthood for England’s now forgotten victory over Sri Lanka). But the rumour mill is cranking into gear. What price a return to the coaching job for Peter Moores?  Moores the merrier: Peter Moores, here in charge of Lancashire, is in the frame for a return as England coach  His supporters will tell you that the England dressing-room no longer contains Kevin Pietersen and Michael Vaughan, two of Moores’s greatest critics during his two years in charge. But it does contain three players – Alastair Cook, Ian Bell and Jimmy Anderson – who all rated Moores highly, and felt that extra-curricular dramas (read: KP) distracted him from the main job. One intriguing figure is Paul Collingwood, who was no fan of Moores’s intense coaching methods during his time as a player, but has recently found himself back in the inner sanctum as a part-time assistant and fielding coach. More crucial, perhaps, is Andy Flower – who replaced Moores in 2009 but swears by his methods after working as his No 2. Watch this space. Pure sixism Spare a thought for England’s women, who were trying to win a global tournament without the injured duo of strike bowler Katherine Brunt and off-spinner Laura Marsh. But that didn’t explain their main deficiency out in Bangladesh: an inability to clear the rope. Not once in six games did an England player hit a six.  No six appeal: England batsmen such as Charlotte Edwards (right) failed to clear the ropes at the World T20  If you suspect this might be a failure of the women’s game in general, think again. There were 57 sixes in the women’s World Twenty20, and 18 were hit by the eventual champions Australia. In fact, only two of the 10 teams failed to clear the rope – England and Ireland. That England reached the final at all says plenty for their skill. But there is a gaping hole in the jigsaw. Hold your horses! Despair behind the scenes that the Pietersen message is trumping the ECB’s may have grown last week when Graeme Smith, KP’s captain at Surrey, spoke out in defence of his county colleague. And while the pro-KP camp leapt on Smith’s suggestion of poor management by the ECB as evidence that their man was hard done by, it may have been just as relevant to note one of Smith’s caveats. For he was honest enough to admit: ‘I’m uninformed at the moment, and speaking from an outsider’s perspective.’ Quite.  \'Outsider\'s perspective\': Graeme Smith spoke out in defence of his Surrey team-mate Kevin Pietersen    More... Pietersen jets off to India for IPL as Cook returns to the crease after Ashes nightmare Root signs two-year extension to stay with Yorkshire through to 2016 Anderson takes five but England hopefuls struggle on opening day of County Championship Sri Lanka legends Sangakkara and Jayawardene bow out in style with World Twenty20 triumph England Women slump to six wicket defeat in World T20 final against superb Aussies England captain Edwards dreams of Aussie double ahead of Women\'s World T20 final   Read more: https://twitter.com/the_topspin Share or comment on this article 5shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/debate/columnists/columnist-1036920/Lawrence-Booth.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lawrence Booth</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@the_topspin\">Follow @@the_topspin</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 04:21 EST, 8 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 04:21 EST, 8 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-2598932/THE-TOP-SPIN-Yuvrajs-tortuous-final-meltdown-just-Twenty20-favour-yes-really.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.da