t-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs not used:</b> Callum Gallagher, Crawford, Emilson Cribari, Hutton, Faure, Scott Gallagher. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Booked:</b></font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> Black</font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals: </b></font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Smith</font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Dundee Utd:</b> Cierzniak, Wilson (Watson 61), Souttar, Gunning, Robertson (Gomis 85), Paton, Rankin, Gauld (Dow 67), Armstrong, Mackay-Steven, Ciftci. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs not used:</b> Dillon, Graham, McCallum, El Alagui. <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Booked: </b></font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Wilson, Gunning</font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">, Armstrong <br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goals:</b> Armstrong, Mackay-Steven, Ciftci<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Referee:</b> Bobby Madden (Scotland)</font> <br/></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Attendance: </b></font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">41,059</font><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> </font></p></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">There was plenty of ineptitude up front, too, as miserable efforts in front of goal by Dean Shiels and Jon Daly undid a display that was markedly better than last weekend’s flop against Raith Rovers — yet not good enough to stifle one of the country’s more potent attacking teams.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rangers actually looked better for taking the game to one of the Premiership’s top sides this season. After flopping as favourites in the Ramsdens Cup, their supporters loved the  status of being embattled underdogs on their home turf.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Defytheodds’ was the advertised hashtag on the tournament sponsors’ big screen advert and it was raucous stuff from the first whistle, the closest this stadium has come to rocking in Old Firm game fashion since Rangers beat Celtic six weeks after being sunk into  administration in 2012.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Fraser Aird forced the first corner after a John Souttar slip, then launched pressure upon United keeper Radoslaw Cierzniak, with Lee McCulloch and Bilel Mohsni both having efforts at goal in a packed area.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ibrox roared as loud as on a Glasgow derby day and the action was just as frenetic. There was barely time to draw breath in the first half but, upon settling down, the story to tell at the break was one of Stuart Armstrong and Gary Mackay-Steven doling out lessons in being lethal in the aftermath of those Rangers misses.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Lashed home: Stuart Armstrong (centre) gave Dundee United the lead in their Scottish Cup semi-final\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"453\" id=\"i-a7fa0e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D477800000578-554_634x453.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Lashed home: Stuart Armstrong (centre) gave Dundee United the lead in their Scottish Cup semi-final</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Lucky break: Gary Mackay Steven (bottom left) doubled United\'s advantage just before half-time\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"397\" id=\"i-a96a0e78\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D577A00000578-479_634x397.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Lucky break: Gary Mackay Steven (bottom left) doubled United\'s advantage just before half-time</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ally McCoist had been in the line of fire last week but the manager was let down here by his forwards. Many wondered why Shiels was kept on the bench when that insipid display against Raith at Easter Road was in sore need of a spark last Sunday.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Shiels got his movement, run and control all right to latch on to the pass as Daly found  a gap in the United defence. The finish,  however, was all wrong, skewed tamely wide with his left foot from 12 yards. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">If McCoist has trust issues with the former Kilmarnock man in front of goal, that 19th minute miss explained why. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Four minutes later, Armstrong showed Shiels how to keep composed in front of goal. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cifcti gave himself up in his offside position as Armstrong advanced on to Gavin Gunning’s header back into the area. The ball bounced kindly for the Scotland Under-21 midfielder to volley in off Simonsen’s left-hand post.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The keeper then palmed away a bouncing effort from Ciftci as the hosts tried and failed to settle in the wake of falling behind. Nicky Law came closest for Rangers when his cross struck an upright, with the unperturbed Cierzniak presumably believing there was no threat.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Nor was there any danger from his former colleague Daly who, after Aird’s lay-off, scooped a shot wildly over when left in  penalty-box space for the first and only time on the day. His 18 goals in League One this season counted for little as the Irishman blew it on the big stage.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Getting stuck in: Rangers\' Dean Shiels (left) and Dundee United\'s Paul Paton (right) battle for the ball\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"371\" id=\"i-aa270e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D6F8900000578-297_634x371.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Getting stuck in: Rangers\' Dean Shiels (left) and Dundee United\'s Paul Paton (right) battle for the ball</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Consolation: Steven Smith (centre) pulled one back for Rangers just before the interval at Ibrox\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"472\" id=\"i-aa240e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D6CA700000578-360_634x472.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Consolation: Steven Smith (centre) pulled one back for Rangers just before the interval at Ibrox</p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Down and out: Shiels looks dejected as Rangers bowed out of the William Hill Scottish Cup on Saturday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"399\" id=\"i-aa380e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D4ED100000578-625_634x399.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Down and out: Shiels looks dejected as Rangers bowed out of the William Hill Scottish Cup on Saturday</p> </div><p> </p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">United warmed to the theme of Rangers’ failings and struck for a second time against the run of play.<br/>Ryan Gauld’s pace and skill took him to the byline and Armstrong helped the cutback on to Mackay-Steven. He took aim with a left-foot shot and Mohsni’s bid to block provided only assistance for United — Simonsen was helpless as that touch sent the ball spinning over the keeper and into the net.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">With the Rangers forwards flopping in front of goal, it took a set-piece from a defender to drag them into contention.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Fair play to left-back Steven Smith for the execution over the wall and accuracy of the effort on target. But the pace should not have caused a top-flight keeper to fail to save at his left-hand post. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cierzniak tried with two hands but the mechanics were all wrong and the ball squirmed in behind him. United were denied an immediate chance to respond when referee Bobby Madden blundered in failing to award a penalty as both Mohsni and Simonsen had an illegal go at stalling Ciftci’s charge.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The second half saw Rangers’ pursuit of an equaliser push back a United team seemingly content with a 2-1 scoreline.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Eyes on the prize: Rangers Richard Foster (left) tussles with United\'s Andrew Robertson (right) for the ball\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"558\" id=\"i-a7b70e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D700B00000578-136_634x558.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Eyes on the prize: Rangers Richard Foster (left) tussles with United\'s Andrew Robertson (right) for the ball</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fervent support: Rangers fans give show their backing for the club before their clash against Dundee United\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"343\" id=\"i-aa6f0e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D4ED500000578-482_634x343.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fervent support: Rangers fans give show their backing for the club before their clash against Dundee United</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Smith was in the set-piece mood and, with the aid of a heavy deflection, caused more panic for Cierzniak. As McCulloch and Richard Foster closed in, the keeper clawed the ball off his line.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">There was always the creeping concern about Rangers that a communication  breakdown would prove costly. With Bell missing and Mohsni as erratic as ever, United were a danger on the break.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Ciftci was the length of a stud away from converting substitute Keith Watson’s drilled delivery across the six-yard box.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">But the Turkish striker was to be presented with another gift that helped him wrap up the win and send United into the Final.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Heavy hit: Ciftci (top) and Rangers captain Lee McCulloch (bottom) collide during their semi-final clash\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"491\" id=\"i-aab70e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D59DA00000578-908_634x491.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Heavy hit: Ciftci (top) and Rangers captain Lee McCulloch (bottom) collide during their semi-final clash</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Foster helped the ball back to Simonsen and the keeper’s terrible touch allowed Ciftci to pinch possession.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He could even afford a stumble and another touch before tucking gleefully home in front of a jubilant United contingent, including Stephen Thompson. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">That was not a bad way to impress his  chairman. In Ciftci’s case, he had managed to please his Celtic-supporting advisor, too.</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602058/Scotland-22nd-FIFA-world-rankings-England-11th.html\"> Scotland on the up as Strachan\'s side rise 15 places to 22nd in the FIFA world rankings... with England up to 11th</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602649/King-declares-war-Rangers-board-urges-fans-withhold-season-ticket-money.html\"> King declares war on Rangers board as he urges fans to withhold season-ticket money</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602838/Former-Dundee-United-striker-Jon-Daly-aiming-fight-flak-firepower-looks-Rangers-Scottish-Cup-final.html\"> Former Dundee United striker Daly aiming to fight flak with firepower as he looks to put Rangers into Scottish Cup final</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601853/Ally-McCoist-insists-felt-pain-fans-Ramsdens-Cup-defeat.html\"> McCoist: We felt the same pain as fans after Raith defeat... we\'ll bounce back in Cup semi</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2601359/Rangers-stick-McCoist-insists-Dailly.html\"> Rangers should stick with McCoist through thick and thin, insists Dailly</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602798/Ally-McCoist-wants-answer-critics-Scottish-Cup-semi-final-Dundee-United.html\"> McCoist seeks to put final defeat behind him ahead of Rangers\' Scottish Cup semi-final</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603092/Rangers-1-3-Dundee-United-Stuart-Armstrong-Gary-Mackay-Steven-Nadir-Ciftci-goals-Tangerines-progress-Scottish-Cup-final.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603092/Rangers-1-3-Dundee-United-Stuart-Armstrong-Gary-Mackay-Steven-Nadir-Ciftci-goals-Tangerines-progress-Scottish-Cup-final.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Rangers 1-3 Dundee United: Armstrong, Mackay-Steven and Ciftci goals see Tangerines progress to Scottish Cup final\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603092/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">10</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603092-1D0D59C400000578-142_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 17:06:25','2014-04-12 23:24:54'),(122,'8de7a33b26b6b9c69057512605d0f127c9313459620febd6dfae32c89189542f','dailymail',NULL,'96 seats... and a rose on every one: On the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough disaster, football unites to pays its respect to the victims of that day of infamy','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603370/96-seats-rose-one-one-On-25th-anniversary-Hillsborough-disaster-football-unites-pays-respect-victims-day-infamy.html',' By Jonathan McEvoy Published: 15:45 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 16:04 EST, 12 April 2014 27 shares 0 View comments Only a baby’s cry pierced the stillness as the Hillsborough crowd stood in silent tribute to those who lived and died for Liverpool FC. Twenty-five years ago this week, as history sadly records, 96 of their fans perished in an overcrowded cattle pen, caged in from the  sanctuary of the pitch by a fence of Sheffield steel. That warm day the sun shone a grim light on the deathly scene, but on Saturday the air down there at the Leppings Lane End was cool and soft. The big clock above the South Stand tilted to 3.06pm, the moment in time when the FA Cup semi-final between Liverpool and Nottingham Forest was abandoned on April 15, 1989. Yet where there had been screams as fathers, sons and daughters heaved in desperation, there was solemnity. Eyes were drawn to the 48 white seats over two rows on each side of the goal that marked the spot where tragedy struck. A rose was placed on every one of them and the name of a victim attached to each stem. VIDEO Scroll to the bottom for former Liverpool greats on the Hillsborough tribute game  Memory: Hillsborough now has 96 white seats decorated with roses and messages for the victims   Red rose: The view of the Hillsborough pitch from the special seats in the Leppings Lane End  Time to remember: The clock at Hillsborough showing 3.06, the time the 1989 semi-final was halted Respect: Sheffield Wednesday tweeted a picture of their programme against Blackburn on Saturday    Horrific: Liverpool fans in the Leppings Lane End crush tried to escape to the upper tier that fateful day  Here, as in every game this weekend in the top eight divisions, the FA Cup and Welsh Premier League, kick-off was delayed seven minutes — a remarkable uniformity of gesture suggesting that this memorial was far more profound than the weekly, though often worthy, ritual of silences or hand-clapping. Outside this old stadium in industrial Sheffield, little clusters of people had gone, on their way in, to pay respect at the permanent memorial by the entrance. Few walked there alone. Husbands and wives entwined arms. Dads told little children what it all meant. Some brought flowers, other scarves or shirts, to adorn the grey stone with its bleak, black-ink inscription: ‘In memory of the 96 men, women and children who tragically died and the countless people whose lives were changed forever.’ The mourners read the words; several stepped back down one of the two deep steps and bowed their heads. It was a scene reminiscent of so many cenotaphs up and down the land on and around Armistice Day. By an hour before kick-off, the throng had grown. People stood three-deep in a little semi-circle  gazing at the plinth, which was surrounded by messages and mementoes from supporters of other clubs, including Manchester United, Everton, Arsenal, Glasgow Rangers and Millwall.   Fateful day: A view of the big screen at Wembley showing the date of the Hillsborough disaster     25 years on: 96 Liverpool scarves are laid at Wembley ahead of the FA Cup semi-finals  A number of the fans, who saw Sheffield Wednesday’s late goal secure a 3-3 draw with Blackburn Rovers, visited the Owls Megastore. Turn back 25 years, and there was a gymnasium on the same site, the one where the stricken were borne on planks of broken advertising hoarding into an impromptu tin morgue. The dead were lined up under red and fawn blankets as neat as dominoes. The commercialisation of football, the need to make money on every square inch you own, saw to it that the gymnasium was razed, leaving behind only its haunted story. Hillsborough still looks like an old-style English ground, with big rectangular stands and corrugated roofs. But the fundamental flaws have been addressed. Championed by the Taylor Report, itself prompted by the tragedy, it is now all-seater, of course. The crowd duly came to sit down here through 102 well-ordered turnstiles. The process to uncover, once and for all, what went wrong 25 years ago is still going on, in a coroner’s court in Warrington, although, out of respect, the new inquest into the 96 deaths will not sit this anniversary week. The fact that the search for justice continues is testimony to the essential fortitude, feistiness and loyalty of Liverpudlians. The families simply refused to submerge under the myth that what occurred here was another easy example of the hooliganism that blighted football in the Seventies and Eighties, the benighted age of the Bradford fire and the shame of Heysel.   Support: Fulham fans pay tribute before the match against Norwich at Craven Cottage   Remembered: The scoreboard at Stoke City\'s Britannia Stadium shows a tribute to the victims   Silence: Kenilworth Road paused before the Skrill Conference match between Luton and Braintree  Representatives of the Hillsborough families were consulted about the ceremonials in Sheffield. On Tuesday, from 10am to 6pm, the ground will be an open house for those who wish to lay flowers inside or out. At 3pm until 3.06pm a short service will be held at the memorial, followed by a minute’s silence. As for the commemoration at Anfield, the important title contest between Liverpool and Manchester City will kick off at 1.37pm. A mosaic with the legend ‘96 25 years’ will be held aloft in the Kop during the silence. A ‘Patch for the 96’ will be laid in the centre circle, and City, along with Celtic, will make floral tributes. After the game, wreaths will be placed on Liverpool’s own memorial. If the all-seater splendour of modern stadiums is one positive legacy of Hillsborough, the knitting together of the football family is another. Thus, Goodison Park will broadcast the annual memorial service at Anfield on a giant screen on Tuesday.  Flowers: Referee Lee Probert and Sunderland winger Adam Johnson carry a wreath at the Stadium of Light   Respect: Everton players watch as Fabio Borini of Sunderland lays the floral wreath on the pitch   Black armband: Sunderland manager Gus Poyet takes his place in the dugout before the match   Head bowed: Everton goalkeeper Tim Howard pays his respects ahead of the clash at Sunderland  The healing is not yet done and it would be glib to suggest that for Liverpool, the Premier League leaders, winning the championship of England for the first time in 24 years would be anything like adequate recompense for Hillsborough, the ground which gave its name to a tragedy. But as Evelyn Mills, who identified the body of her brother Peter McDonnell here 25 years ago, said: ‘it would be a little help along our way’.  Arm in arm: Stoke and Newcastle\'s teams pause for a minute\'s silence at the Britannia   Message: A tribute is displayed on the scoreboard at Selhurst Park, where Crystal Palace played Aston Villa   Observance: Players, fans and officials observe the minute\'s silence at Fulham\'s Craven Cottage ground  Dalglish: We laugh at same stories every time we\'re back together Whelan: I will drive Kenny home to make sure he starts me Evans: It\'s nice to have a Premier League which is competitive Kennedy: It\'s a fantastic opportunity to pay a tribute to the 96   More... Never forgotten: Hillsborough\'s 96 victims remembered up and down the country on 25th anniversary of disaster The night Milan fans paid tribute to the 96 victims of Hillsborough with spine-tingling rendition of You\'ll Never Walk Alone Sheffield Wednesday dedicate programme front page to 96 Liverpool fans who died at Hillsborough Hillsborough remembered: Why all this weekend\'s matches are kicking off seven minutes late on 25th anniversary Dalglish says families of the 96 have to come before anyone else on eve of Hillsborough anniversary Hillsborough remembered: The horrors of that sun-kissed Saturday will haunt me forever, by Jeff Powell   Share or comment on this article 27shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Jonathan+McEvoy\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jonathan McEvoy</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 15:45 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 16:04 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603370/96-seats-rose-one-one-On-25th-anniversary-Hillsborough-disaster-football-unites-pays-respect-victims-day-infamy.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603370/96-seats-rose-one-one-On-25th-anniversary-Hillsborough-disaster-football-unites-pays-respect-victims-day-infamy.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"96 seats... and a rose on every one: On the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough disaster, football unites to pays its respect to the victims of that day of infamy\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 27</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603370/96-seats-rose-one-one-On-25th-anniversary-Hillsborough-disaster-football-unites-pays-respect-victims-day-infamy.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">0</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Only a baby’s cry pierced the stillness as the Hillsborough crowd stood in silent tribute to those who lived and died for Liverpool FC. Twenty-five years ago this week, as history sadly records, 96 of their fans perished in an overcrowded cattle pen, caged in from the  sanctuary of the pitch by a fence of Sheffield steel. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">That warm day the sun shone a grim light on the deathly scene, but on Saturday the air down there at the Leppings Lane End was cool and soft. The big clock above the South Stand tilted to 3.06pm, the moment in time when the FA Cup semi-final between Liverpool and Nottingham Forest was abandoned on April 15, 1989. Yet where there had been screams as fathers, sons and daughters heaved in desperation, there was solemnity. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Eyes were drawn to the 48 white seats over two rows on each side of the goal that marked the spot where tragedy struck. A rose was placed on every one of them and the name of a victim attached to each stem. <br/></font></p>\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><font color=\"FFFFFF\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(12, 172, 12);\">VIDEO</span></font> Scroll to the bottom for former Liverpool greats on the Hillsborough tribute game</font></b></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Memory: Hillsborough now has 96 white seats decorated with roses and messages for the victims\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"475\" id=\"i-a8960e6c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0D486E00000578-175_634x475.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Memory: Hillsborough now has 96 white seats decorated with roses and messages for the victims</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Red rose: The view of the Hillsborough pitch from the special seats in the Leppings Lane End\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"403\" id=\"i-9ae90e2d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0D8A7300000578-74_634x403.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Red rose: The view of the Hillsborough pitch from the special seats in the Leppings Lane End</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"> <img alt=\"Time to remember: The clock at Hillsborough showing 3.06, the time the 1989 semi-final was halted\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"386\" id=\"i-a5d60e54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602268-002810CF00000258-382_634x386.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </font></p>\n<p class=\"imageCaption\">Time to remember: The clock at Hillsborough showing 3.06, the time the 1989 semi-final was halted</p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Respect: Sheffield Wednesday tweeted a picture of their programme against Blackburn on Saturday\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"939\" id=\"i-a5b00e51\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/11/article-2602272-1D0632B100000578-421_634x939.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Respect: Sheffield Wednesday tweeted a picture of their programme against Blackburn on Saturday</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Horrific: Liverpool fans in the Leppings Lane End crush tried to escape to the upper tier that fateful day\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"422\" id=\"i-a35c0e32\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D00561100000578-207_634x422.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Horrific: Liverpool fans in the Leppings Lane End crush tried to escape to the upper tier that fateful day</p> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Here, as in every game this weekend in the top eight divisions, the FA Cup and Welsh Premier League, kick-off was delayed seven minutes — a remarkable uniformity of gesture suggesting that this memorial was far more profound than the weekly, though often worthy, ritual of silences or hand-clapping.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Outside this old stadium in industrial Sheffield, little clusters of people had gone, on their way in, to pay respect at the permanent memorial by the entrance.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Few walked there alone. Husbands and wives entwined arms. Dads told little children what it all meant. Some brought flowers, other scarves or shirts, to adorn the grey stone with its bleak, black-ink inscription: ‘In memory of the 96 men, women and children who tragically died and the countless people whose lives were changed forever.’<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The mourners read the words; several stepped back down one of the two deep steps and bowed their heads. It was a scene reminiscent of so many cenotaphs up and down the land on and around Armistice Day.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">By an hour before kick-off, the throng had grown. People stood three-deep in a little semi-circle  gazing at the plinth, which was surrounded by messages and mementoes from supporters of other clubs, including Manchester United, Everton, Arsenal, Glasgow Rangers and Millwall.</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Fateful day: A view of the big screen at Wembley showing the date of the Hillsborough disaster\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"408\" id=\"i-a6b70e56\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0D924500000578-824_634x408.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Fateful day: A view of the big screen at Wembley showing the date of the Hillsborough disaster</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"25 years on: 96 Liverpool scarves are laid at Wembley ahead of the FA Cup semi-finals\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"410\" id=\"i-a8470e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0D8F1300000578-648_634x410.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">25 years on: 96 Liverpool scarves are laid at Wembley ahead of the FA Cup semi-finals</p> </div>\n<font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">A number of the fans, who saw Sheffield Wednesday’s late goal secure a 3-3 draw with Blackburn Rovers, visited the Owls Megastore. Turn back 25 years, and there was a gymnasium on the same site, the one where the stricken were borne on planks of broken advertising hoarding into an impromptu tin morgue. The dead were lined up under red and fawn blankets as neat as dominoes.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The commercialisation of football, the need to make money on every square inch you own, saw to it that the gymnasium was razed, leaving behind only its haunted story. Hillsborough still looks like an old-style English ground, with big rectangular stands and corrugated roofs. But the fundamental flaws have been addressed. Championed by the Taylor Report, itself prompted by the tragedy, it is now all-seater, of course. The crowd duly came to sit down here through 102 well-ordered turnstiles.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The process to uncover, once and for all, what went wrong 25 years ago is still going on, in a coroner’s court in Warrington, although, out of respect, the new inquest into the 96 deaths will not sit this anniversary week. The fact that the search for justice continues is testimony to the essential fortitude, feistiness and loyalty of Liverpudlians. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The families simply refused to submerge under the myth that what occurred here was another easy example of the hooliganism that blighted football in the Seventies and Eighties, the benighted age of the Bradford fire and the shame of Heysel.</font></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Support: Fulham fans pay tribute before the match against Norwich at Craven Cottage\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"468\" id=\"i-a76d0e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0C530D00000578-841_634x468.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Support: Fulham fans pay tribute before the match against Norwich at Craven Cottage<br/></p></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Remembered: The scoreboard at Stoke City\'s Britannia Stadium shows a tribute to the victims\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"476\" id=\"i-9a750e31\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0C30C900000578-82_634x476.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Remembered: The scoreboard at Stoke City\'s Britannia Stadium shows a tribute to the victims</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Silence: Kenilworth Road paused before the Skrill Conference match between Luton and Braintree\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"420\" id=\"i-a73d0e57\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0C50A600000578-608_634x420.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Silence: Kenilworth Road paused before the Skrill Conference match between Luton and Braintree</p></div>\n<font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"></font>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Representatives of the Hillsborough families were consulted about the ceremonials in Sheffield. On Tuesday, from 10am to 6pm, the ground will be an open house for those who wish to lay flowers inside or out. At 3pm until 3.06pm a short service will be held at the memorial, followed by a minute’s silence. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">As for the commemoration at Anfield, the important title contest between Liverpool and Manchester City will kick off at 1.37pm. A mosaic with the legend ‘96 25 years’ will be held aloft in the Kop during the silence. A ‘Patch for the 96’ will be laid in the centre circle, and City, along with Celtic, will make floral tributes. After the game, wreaths will be placed on Liverpool’s own memorial.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">If the all-seater splendour of modern stadiums is one positive legacy of Hillsborough, the knitting together of the football family is another. Thus, Goodison Park will broadcast the annual memorial service at Anfield on a giant screen on Tuesday.<br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Flowers: Referee Lee Probert and Sunderland winger Adam Johnson carry a wreath at the Stadium of Light\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"447\" id=\"i-a9440e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0DB4A600000578-174_634x447.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Flowers: Referee Lee Probert and Sunderland winger Adam Johnson carry a wreath at the Stadium of Light</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Respect: Everton players watch as Fabio Borini of Sunderland lays the floral wreath on the pitch\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"383\" id=\"i-a9710e73\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0DA7B200000578-296_634x383.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Respect: Everton players watch as Fabio Borini of Sunderland lays the floral wreath on the pitch</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Black armband: Sunderland manager Gus Poyet takes his place in the dugout before the match\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"471\" id=\"i-9a2b0e25\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0DA84100000578-30_634x471.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Black armband: Sunderland manager Gus Poyet takes his place in the dugout before the match</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Head bowed: Everton goalkeeper Tim Howard pays his respects ahead of the clash at Sunderland\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"463\" id=\"i-a7980e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0DB12400000578-838_634x463.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Head bowed: Everton goalkeeper Tim Howard pays his respects ahead of the clash at Sunderland</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The healing is not yet done and it would be glib to suggest that for Liverpool, the Premier League leaders, winning the championship of England for the first time in 24 years would be anything like adequate recompense for Hillsborough, the ground which gave its name to a tragedy.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">But as Evelyn Mills, who identified the body of her brother Peter McDonnell here 25 years ago, said: ‘it would be a little help along our way’.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Arm in arm: Stoke and Newcastle\'s teams pause for a minute\'s silence at the Britannia\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"355\" id=\"i-a81b0e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0DA86100000578-555_634x355.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Arm in arm: Stoke and Newcastle\'s teams pause for a minute\'s silence at the Britannia</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Message: A tribute is displayed on the scoreboard at Selhurst Park, where Crystal Palace played Aston Villa\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"398\" id=\"i-a8370e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0DA45200000578-787_634x398.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Message: A tribute is displayed on the scoreboard at Selhurst Park, where Crystal Palace played Aston Villa</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Observance: Players, fans and officials observe the minute\'s silence at Fulham\'s Craven Cottage ground\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-a6f60e54\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603141-1D0DB04100000578-149_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Observance: Players, fans and officials observe the minute\'s silence at Fulham\'s Craven Cottage ground</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3452153365001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Dalglish: We laugh at same stories every time we\'re back together</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/video-undefined-1CFF33C200000578-767_636x364.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3452154924001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Whelan: I will drive Kenny home to make sure he starts me</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/video-undefined-1CFF33B000000578-868_636x364.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3452208709001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Evans: It\'s nice to have a Premier League which is competitive</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/video-undefined-1CFF33BE00000578-929_636x364.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3452206583001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Kennedy: It\'s a fantastic opportunity to pay a tribute to the 96</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/10/video-undefined-1CFF33B800000578-476_636x364.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603141/Never-forgotten-Hillsboroughs-96-victims-remembered-country-25th-anniversary-disaster.html\"> Never forgotten: Hillsborough\'s 96 victims remembered up and down the country on 25th anniversary of disaster</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2603082/Hillsborough-25th-Anniversary-Milan-fans-emotional-tribute-Liverpool-victims-1989-European-Cup-semi-final-video.html\"> The night Milan fans paid tribute to the 96 victims of Hillsborough with spine-tingling rendition of You\'ll Never Walk Alone</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602272/Sheffield-Wednesday-dedicate-programme-page-96-Liverpool-fans.html\"> Sheffield Wednesday dedicate programme front page to 96 Liverpool fans who died at Hillsborough</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602268/Hillsborough-remembered-Why-weekends-matches-kicking-seven-minutes-late-25th-anniversary.html\"> Hillsborough remembered: Why all this weekend\'s matches are kicking off seven minutes late on 25th anniversary</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602266/Kenny-Dalglish-led-Liverpool-mourning-Hillsborough-tragedy.html\"> Dalglish says families of the 96 have to come before anyone else on eve of Hillsborough anniversary</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602254/Hillsborough-remembered-The-horrors-sun-kissed-Saturday-haunt-forever-Jeff-Powell.html\"> Hillsborough remembered: The horrors of that sun-kissed Saturday will haunt me forever, by Jeff Powell</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603370/96-seats-rose-one-one-On-25th-anniversary-Hillsborough-disaster-football-unites-pays-respect-victims-day-infamy.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603370/96-seats-rose-one-one-On-25th-anniversary-Hillsborough-disaster-football-unites-pays-respect-victims-day-infamy.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"96 seats... and a rose on every one: On the 25th anniversary of the Hillsborough disaster, football unites to pays its respect to the victims of that day of infamy\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603370/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">27</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D0F929F00000578-674_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 17:06:25','2014-04-12 23:04:11'),(123,'2cd0cd92963a96c46090ccb66e2de98f71047d8a299923f84b7bd3091034e0e2','dailymail',NULL,'MASTERS LIVE: All the third-round action as it happens at Augusta National','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html',' By Joe Strange Follow @@Joe_Strange Published: 18:39 EST, 11 April 2014 | Updated: 15:47 EST, 12 April 2014 9 shares 6 View comments  It\'s moving day at the Masters and once again we\'ll make sure you don\'t miss a thing with our live coverage. Bubba Watson started his round with a three-shot lead over John Senden but the 2012 champion has already looked nervous, dropping shots on the front-nine to open things up at the top. Jonas Blixt and Jordan Spieth are right in the mix, while veteran Miguel Angel Jimenez is on three-under-par after a fine early round of 66. Rory McIlroy, the pre-tournament favourite, was left frustrated as a one-under-par round of 70 failed to bring him back into contention for the coveted green jacket. We\'ll bring you the latest action as it happens with all the news from Augusta and the best pictures. You can follow your favourites with our leaderboard on the right and let us know what you think or who you\'re tipping by emailing joe.strange@mailonline.co.uk And if you fancy a bet, you can get all the latest live odds from our betting partner Coral by clicking HERE.   Out in front: Bubba Watson is the man they\'re all chasing at Augusta  Joe Strange Host commentator Auto-update 23:05 Scott\'s struggles Adam Scott misses a birdie chance on the par-three 16th and remains on two-over for the tournament. The Aussie was among the favourites after the cut was made last night but he looks unlikely to retain his green jacket. Meanwhile Bjorn has just made another bogey on 15, leaving him three-under with three to play. 23:00 Bjorn finds the water... again Bjorn\'s second shot at the par-five 15th hits the bank and rolls back into the water. He needs to minimise the damage here with holes fast running out. 22:54 Spieth closes the gap Successive birdies for Spieth, who makes a four at the par-five 15th to move to second on the leaderboard. You\'d never know it was his first Masters. 22:52 Kuchar reacts to his third round 68 \'I drove it well, I was in a lot of fairways. I played some good, steady golf today. \'I\'ve been playing some good golf. It\'s nice to be part of the conversation and in with a chance on Sunday.\' Near the top: Matt Kuchar currently holds the clubhouse lead 22:46 What a waste Watson three-putts from within 20 feet and misses a clear opportunity to extend his advantage at the top. Maybe a few nerves creeping into our leader. Frustrated: Watson reacts after missing a birdie chance 22:43 Super Senden Beautiful pitch shot from Senden, who knocks his third to within a couple of feet of the 13th hole. A birdie there will get him back to two-under. 22:41 Watson finds the green No such problem for Watson who, after a huge drive, gets his approach within 20 feet on the 13th. He\'ll have a put for eagle, which could put him four shots clear. Chance: Watson gave himself an excellent eagle opportunity on the 13th 22:39 Double boost for Watson Bjorn and Blixt both make bogey at the par-five 15th after finding the water. Two more victims of Amen Corner\'s tricky final hole... 22:37 Furyk and Kuchar make bogeys After finding the water, Furyk makes a bogey at the 15th and drops back to three-under. Kuchar finishes his best round of the week with a bogey at the last but the American is still four-under-par and holds the clubhouse lead. 22:31 Blixt and Bjorn find the water Blixt finds the creek with his second shot at the par-five 13th, before his playing partner Bjorn does exactly the same just moments later. Watson could find himself a little further in front of the European duo shortly. Under pressure: Blixt, pictured here reacting to a missed putt at the sixth, has found the water on the 13th 22:28 Westwood reacts to his third round 70 \'I played really solidly. I hit a lot of good shots all day and gave myself a lot of birdie opportunities. \'I\'ll be there or thereabouts by the end of today depending on what Bubba and a few others do.\' 22:22 Missed opportunity for Watson Bubba has a 20-foot uphill putt on the 11th but he doesn\'t hit it and misses a chance to extend his lead with another birdie. Meanwhile Couples is back to two-under after his pinpoint approach on the par-four 14th leads to an easy three. 22:17 Westwood finishes with a par Well-judged first putt from Westwood on the 18th and he holes his second from two feet to finish with a par. That\'s a round of 70 for Westwood, leaving him two-under and right in the mix on Sunday as it stands. 22:10 So close from Blixt Brilliant shot from Blixt out of the drop zone after his approach found the wet stuff. The Swede\'s effort just misses the hole and he\'ll have a tap-in for a bogey. 22:09 Westwood drops a shot Westwood\'s putt on the 17th comes up short and the Englishman goes back to two-under for the tournament. If he can par or birdie the last, Westwood will have a chance tomorrow. Dropping back: Westwood could only manage a bogey on the 17th 22:06 Blixt finds the water Mistake from Blixt, whose long iron shot on the 11 takes a big bounce and cannons into the water. Looks like the man from Sweden could be dropping a shot here. 22:04 Watson back at the top Watson does get his birdie at the 10th, sliding in his putt from a couple of feet after a fine approach. The 2012 champ is now back on his own at the top on six-under-par. Unique: Watson\'s individual style has helped him to the top of the leaderboard 22:02 Kuchar ties things up Consecutive birdies from Kuchar, who joins Watson, Blixt and Bjorn at the top of the leaderboard on five-under-par. Sunday is going to be perfectly set up if this continues. 22:00 More magic from Bubba Fantastic second shot from Watson, who almost finds the hole on the 10th. Looks like that\'ll be a birdie for Bubba, who will move a shot clear at six-under if he doesn\'t mess it up. 21:54 Couples gets a roar Veteran Fred Couples gets a huge cheer from the patrons with a lovely birdie on the 11th. He\'s back to one-under with Rose, who is already in the clubhouse. Still in it: Fred Couples is hoping to make history after winning the Masters in 1992 21:49 All level at the top Birdies for Bjorn and Blixt at the ninth mean the pair are now level with Watson on five-under par. Kuchar and Spieth are a shot further back on four-under. How quickly things can change at Augusta. 21:44 Westwood looking good at -3 Westwood hits another beautiful shot on the 16th par 3. Should slot this away nicely for another birdie. Whisper it quietly but he\'s starting to really put pressure on the leaders... 21:41 Is the pressure getting to Watson? Watson seems to be looking a little nervous out there. Don\'t tell him that Blixt has just made a birdie on the ninth... 21:37 Westwood almost in the water Westwood is so close to having to go for a swim on the 15th.  Luckily for the Englishman the ball sits kindly on the bank. Westwood should be able to get himself closer to an under par finish on this hole 21:32 Well in, Rose! Rose in at -1, and not out of it. When you consider he was +5 thru 11 and wet at 12, that\'s a tremendous effort #TheMasterswithTitleist— Golf Monthly (@GolfMonthly) April 12, 2014 21:30 We\'re behind you Bubba! Watson continues his brilliant Augusta driving with a thunderous strike to get the eight underway. Bubba has been playing some brilliant stuff, but is now leading by just one. Can he stay in the lead under pressure from Blixt and Spieth? 21:26 Westwood makes par putt Westwood makes an excellent 15-foot putt on the 14th, but it goes just past the cup. He taps home for par. 21:25 Bubba Watson\'s no 3-putt streak comes to an end after a 3-putt bogey on No. 6. He had gone 296 holes without one. #Masters— Golf Central (@GolfCentral) April 12, 2014 21:23 Rose has Watson in his sights Justin Rose: \'I was pleased with that round. It was a bit of a roller-coaster but I felt i made a great eagle at 13. \'I felt I could have finished at 3 under, which would have been brilliant but I\'m still I it. \'I saw Bubba struggling, so I think I\'m right in it at this point.\' 21:21 Bubba\'s in the sand Watson over-hits a bunker shot and has to watch agonisingly as the ball roles past the flag and towards the edge of the green...It stayson the dancefloor, just! 21:19 That\'s it for Rose - 69 Rose gets the par! Just sneaks below 70 with a 69 for the day! He\'ll be pleased with that, but it could so easily have been 68. 21:18 Rose misses the birdie Justin Rose misses the chance to finish with a birdie on the 18th and has left himself some work to do to make par on the last... 21:15 Good day for Fowler Rickie Fowler on his 67: \'I knew it was going to be tough, but I\'ve been swinging well and am happy with how I played today.\' 21:14 Bubba makes a Bogie! Disappointment for Watson as he makes a bogie on the sixth. It doesn\'t seem to bother the American, however, as he wanders over to the seventh and hits an excellent drive. 21:06 Bogey for Rose Frustrating finish for Rose, who underhits a putt on 17 and drops a shot to go back to one-under-par. He has a chance to make it back on the 18th, though. 21:02 Poulter reacts to his third round 70 \'I\'m disgusted with a round which looks pretty good. \'We\'ll have to see what Bubba does around the golf course. The pins are in positions where guys can make plenty of birdies. \'I\'m just going to have a run at him on Sunday.\' 20:57 So close for Blixt Blixt almost makes another birdie on six but his putt misses by an inch. Better news for Thomas Bjorn though, who finds the cup with his second shot to get to four-under. This is getting very good. 20:54 Oosthuizen\'s challenge fading Louis Oosthuizen was near the top of the leaderboard after day one but the South African\'s challenge looks like it could be over. He\'s just dunked his ball in the water at 11 and will almost certainly make at least a bogey. Struggling: Louis Oosthuizen has been far from his best so far today 20:51 Spieth at it again Second birdie of the day for Spieth, who moves to four-under with a two at the par-three sixth. The American is now tied for second with Blixt. 20:47 Poulter finishes level Poulter finishes with a two-under-par 69 to leave him level-par for the tournament. He\'s still got a lot of work to do tomorrow but he\'s given himself a chance to win his first ever Major Championship. 20:45 Bubba drops a shot Watson\'s putt on the fourth drifts to the left of the hole and it\'s another bogey for our leader. Fowler misses a chance to finish with another birdie but he\'s still had an exceptional round. He\'s three-under heading into Sunday. Good and bad: Bubba Watson has endured a mixed start to his third round 20:43 Rose does it again Rose holes a long put on the par-five 15th after his ball was fortunate not to roll back into the water. The Englishman is now two-under and right back in the mix.   20:40 McIlroy reacts after his third round 71 \'I enjoyed the round. It\'s not an experience I want to have again. \'The course was fiery from the start. The guys are going to find it pretty interesting this afternoon. \'I felt I played well enough to shoot something a lot lower. I think anything around 70, 69 is going to be a really good score.\' 20:38 Kuchar moves to three-under Third birdie of the day for Kuchar, who reaches the turn at three-under after a bogey-free front-nine. Lots of American interest at the top of the leaderboard now. 20:34 And Senden\'s struggling too Second bogey of the day for Senden, who misses an eight-footer before tapping in. He\'s back to three-under after making up for his first bogey with a birdie at the second. 20:32 Scott struggling Double bogey on the fourth for defending champion Scott, who has now dropped three shots in his opening four holes. The Aussie has gone back to level-par in no time at all. 20:30 Who are you backing? If, like me, your Masters bets are already dead and buried, click HERE for the latest live odds from Coral. My money is on Bubba to see it through, which probably means he\'ll bogey every hole on Sunday... 20:25 Eagle for Rose Wonderful eagle from Rose on the final hole of Amen Corner which takes him to one-under. The US Open champ is three-under for the day and just behind a big pack on two-under for the tournament after following it up with a par at the 14th. 20:20 Fowler finishing well Super run for Rickie Fowler, who birdies 15 and 16 to get to three-under with two to play. The 25-year-old is five-under for the day. 20:15 Bubba strikes back Senden makes up for his bogey on the first with a an eight-footer for birdie but he\'s outdone by Watson, who holes his putt after reaching the green in two for an eagle. The 2012 champion is back to eight-under and leads by four. 20:10 Spieth up to second Jordan Spieth calmly holes his putt on the fourth for a birdie, sending him into second behind Watson. It\'s been a fine Masters debut from the youngster so far. Big future: Jordan Spieth tees off on the first hole 20:06 Bogeys for Watson, Scott and Senden Nervy starts from Watson, Senden and defending champion Scott, each of whom bogey the first. Watson now sits on six-under, while Senden is level with Jimenez, Blixt, Bjorn, Furyk and Spieth on three-under. It\'s getting tight at the top. 20:03 Disappointing finish for Woodland Woodland finishes his round at level-par after a three-under 69 but it could\'ve been so much better. The American was seven-under for the day after 10 holes but stuttered through Amen Corner before bogeying the last. Frustrated figure: Woodland reacts after a poor shot on the 11th 19:56 Americans on the up American trio Kevin Stadler, Matt Kuchar and Jim Furyk have all started well today. Stadler has picked up a shot and is two-under alongside Kuchar, while Furyk is now tied third with Jimenez on three-under. Leader Bubba Watson has also began his third round. In the mix: Furyk makes his approach to the first green 19:50 Magic from Jimenez What a wonderful performance from Jimenez, who finishes three-under-par after his best round of the week. The 50-year-old rolled back the years for a six-under-par round - the best of the week - which included seven birdies. The Spaniard is currently third behind Bubba Watson and John Senden. Sandy Lyle finishes the day four-over-par and eight-over for the tournament. 19:46 McIlroy praises Masters marker Knox After shooting a worse score than his non-competitive playing partner Jeff Knox, Rory McIlroy had some kind words for the amateur golfer. McIlroy said: \'Jeff is a great player and beat me by one. I thought he was going to be nice and three-putt the last so we could have a nice half! \'I don\'t think I\'ve ever seen anyone putt the greens so well. I was thinking of getting him to read some of mine. He looked like he should be playing in the Masters.\' 19:42 Clarke and Olazabal finish up Similar rounds for playing partners Olazabal and Clarke, who both began the day on four-over and ended it a shot worse off. Legend: Jose Maria Olazabal managed a one-over-par 73 on day three at Augusta 19:37 Brit watch Poulter and Westwood are level on one-under-par after the former could only make bogey at Amen Corner\'s tricky par-three. Steven Gallacher is also one-under after pars on the first and second, while Jamie Donaldson has dropped to one-over after two bogeys in his first four holes. 19:27 Luiten and Day finish up Contrasting fortunes for playing partners Day and Luiten on the 18th, with the former making bogey to finish on two-over-par and the latter grabbing a rare birdie to end on nine-over for the tournament. Tough times: Joost Luiten could only manage a five-over-par 77 on Saturday 19:20 Jimenez on the charge What a performance by Jimenez. The Spaniard has just made his seventh birdie of the day at the par-three 16th to go three-under-par for the tournament. If he can avoid any mistakes on the last two holes then he should be in the mix at the top of the leaderboard tomorrow. On fire: Jimenez plays his approach shot on the par-four seventh 19:10 Day not giving up Jason Day has been quietly going about his business today and the Aussie is back to one-over-par after birdies at 13 and 15. Another on the 18th would be a lovely way for him to finish his round ahead of Sunday. 19:01 More shots being clawed back Jimenez makes consecutive birdies at 13 and 14 to get to two-under with four holes still to play. He\'s joined on the same score by Woodland, who has recovered from a double bogey on the 12th to birdie the 13th. Poulter is a few holes behind but successive birdies at nine and 10 have the Englishman also on two-under. 18:56 Westwood gets into the red Excellent start for Lee Westwood, who pars the first and then birdies the par-five second to go one-under. Another steady par on the third and lad from Worksop looks in a good position to post a decent score today. Looking good: Lee Westwood jumps out of a bunker on the first to follow the flight of his ball 18:49 McIlroy outplayed by marker Knox Turns out McIlroy\'s 71 was actually a shot more than Masters marker Jeff Knox managed this afternoon. The 51-year-old, who played alongside McIlroy because of the odd number of players who made the cut, shot a two-under-par 70. Well played, Jeff. Playing partners: McIlroy (right) shares a joke with Knox (left) 18:39 Woodland slipping back After his first bogey of the day at the 11th, Woodland drops two more shots at the 12th after dumping his ball in Rae\'s Creek. He\'s now back to one-under for the tournament and currently tied for 10th. Amen Corner hasn\'t been kind to the American today. 18:35 Beware of the bogeys Woodland records his first bogey of the day at the par-four 11th and drops back to three-under. Poulter and Jimenez were the other two making moves but both have been halted with bogeys at the seventh and 12th respectively. The pair are now both on level-par. 18:26 McIlroy finishes well Strong finish from McIlroy, who birdies the 15th, 17th and 18th to finish with a one-under-par 71. The pre-tournament favourite is still three-over and he\'ll need something spectacular to be in with a chance of winning his first green jacket on Sunday night. Frustrating afternoon: McIlroy couldn\'t find his best form on Saturday at Augusta 18:21 Jiminez still smoking No doubt Jimenez will treat himself to a fat cigar if he\'s able to keep up his momentum. The Spaniard has just bagged his fourth birdie of the day at the par-four 11th to move back to one-under. It\'s in the detail: Jimenez (right) checks out his yardage book with his caddy 18:15 Woodland on fire Yet another birdie for Woodland, who moves to seven-under for the day and four-under for the tournament with a three at the par-fourth 10th. This is turning into a ridiculous round of golf from a man whose best finish at Augusta was tied 24th in 2011. 18:09 McIlroy, Poulter and Jimenez on the birdie trail McIlroy pulls a shot back at the par-five 15th but it\'s not been the round the Northern Irishman was hoping for today. Poulter is now one-under-par for the tournament after his third birdie of the day at the fifth, while Jimenez is now level-par after a three at the par-four 10th. Some good scoring out there so far today. On target: Ian Poulter hits his tee shot on the par-three fourth 18:02 Woodland ties front-nine record Another birdie for Woodland at the ninth means the American is out in 30 and now three-under for the tournament. Only four others have managed it: Miller (1975), Norman (1988), Choi (2004) and Mickelson (2009). The 29-year-old is six-under-par for the day. Wow. Charge: Woodland is six-under-par through the front-nine 17:58 Mixed start for Rose After finishing his second round with two birdies it\'s been an interesting start to day three for Justin Rose. The US Open champion got a par on the first, bogeyed the second and then eagled the third to leave him where he started one-over-par. Highs and lows: Justin Rose recorded an eagle on the third after bogeying the second 17:50 Quick start from Mahan Excellent start by Hunter Mahan, who has birdied his opening two holes to get back to level-par. The American tied fourth at last year\'s US Open and he\'ll be in the mix again if he keeps this up. 17:45 Woodland makes another Third birdie of the day for Woodland on the par-five eighth as he gets to five-under for the day and two-under for the tournament. He was two-over for the same eight holes yesterday. It\'s a funny old game. Flying: Gary Woodland is five-under-par through eight holes on day three 17:38 YE Yang drowns his sorrows Aftermath of a rough masters. Miss cut. Drank a lot to wash away the masters blues.— YE Yang (@Y_E_Yang) April 12, 2014 17:34 Poulter and Fowler start strongly Colourful duo Ian Poulter and Rickie Fowler have both begun in superb fashion, grabbing birdies on the second and third to get back to level-par for the tournament. Still a long way to go but they\'re both giving themselves a chance tomorrow as it stands.   17:26 McIlroy heading around Amen Corner It just isn\'t happening for Rory today. He\'s two-over-par for his round and six-over for the tournament. He\'s just negotiated the first two holes of Amen Corner with a pair of pars and is now trying to make up a shot on the par-five 13th. #PrayForRory Struggling: McIlroy is two-over-par for his round after 12 holes 17:18 Haas finding his first round form After a nightmare 78 on Friday, first round leader Haas has recaptured his Thursday form with consecutive birdies on the second and third holes. The American is now back to level-par for the tournament. On the up: First round leader Bill Haas is back to level par 17:16 Money to be made If, like me, your Masters bets are already dead and buried, click HERE for the latest live odds from Coral. You can still get 7/4 on leader Bubba Watson to win back his green jacket. 17:12 Woodland on the charge Another birdie for Woodland on the par-three sixth sees him back in the red at one-under-par for the tournament and four-under for the day. Still a long way to go but encouraging signs from the 29-year-old. 17:02 McIlroy falling further back A third bogey of the day for McIlroy on the par-four 10th sees the pre-tournament favourite at six-over-par with eight holes to play today. Padraig Harrington\'s prediction that Rory would shoot 65 seems a little off... Hard times: McIlroy is now six-over-par after three bogeys in his first 10 holes 16:54 Haas and Olesen underway First round leader Bill Haas has just finished playing the first alongside talented 24-year-old Thorbjorn Olesen. Both started with pars, keeping them at two-over-par with 35 holes to play. 16:50 Jimenez rolling back the years Impressive stuff again from Jimenez at the par-four fifth as he bags his second birdie of the day to drop back to one-over-par. The Spaniard is one of six record-breaking over 50s to have made the cut, with Fred Couples, Larry Mize, Sandy Lyle, Bernhard Langer and Vijay Singh all still in the mix. Still got it: Miguel Angel Jimenez admires his drive on the fourth hole 16:47 Get in touch Don\'t forget you can e-mail me your thoughts on joe.strange@mailonline.co.uk, or tweet me @joe_strange No doubt there will be plenty to discuss over the next seven or eight hours! 16:42 Clarke and Kirk claw back shots Birdies for Clarke on the fifth and Kirk on the second make their respective scorecards look a little better but the same can\'t be said for Olivier Goss. The only amateur left has just posted a double-bogey six on the opening hole, leaving him five-over-par for the tournament. 16:27 Bogeys everywhere Difficult moments for McIlroy, Olazabal and Luiten, who each drop a shot and fall further behind. Better news for 50-year-old Jiminez though, who grabs a birdie at the par-four third to get back to two-over-par. 16:18 Strong start for Woodland Gary Woodland endured a terrible finish to his second round, bogeying the last four holes to finish with a 77. But he hasn\'t let that affect him today, with a birdie on the par-four first bringing him back to two-over-par for the tournament. He then followed it up with the first eagle of the day at the par-five second to get back to level-par. Superb stuff from the American. 16:14 McIlroy whizzing around McIlroy is averaging less than 10 minutes per hole at the moment, with a consecutive pars at the fifth and sixth keeping him at four-over-par. Olazabal gets back to three-over-par with a birdie at the par-five second, while Luiten has dropped another shot with a bogey at the third. On his own: Rory McIlroy watches his approach to the green on the first hole 16:02 No change for McIlroy Pars on the fourth and fifth holes for McIlory, who stays at four-over. Miguel Angel Jimenez and Sandy Lyle both start with a par at the first. The Spaniard stays at three-over, while the Scot is a shot further back. Solid: Sandy Lyle began his third round with a par on the first hole 15:56 Clarke and Olazabal begin Veterans Darren Clarke and Jose Maria Olazabal are playing together this afternoon and the pair have started in identical fashion, both coming away from the first with par. Jason day picks up a birdie on the second to get back to four-over-par, while Luiten gets a par. Experienced: Darren Clarke his his approach shot on the par-four first 15:53 McIlory gives one back After a birdie at the second, McIlroy bogeys the third to fall back to four-over-par for the tournament. A par, a birdie and a bogey in his first three holes. A mixed start, you could say. 15:49 Dfficult start for Day and Luiten Poor opening hole for playing partners Day and Luiten, who both bogey the first. The pair are now five-over-par, 12 shots behind leader Watson. Focused: Jason Day plays his approach shot to the second green 15:43 Super second for McIlroy McIlroy needed a strong start to get over his Friday nightmare and he\'s had just that, posting a birdie at the par-five second to get back to three-over-par. The former US Open champion bogeyed the same hole yesterday. 15:41 Scott under no illusions Last year\'s Masters champions Adam Scott is in contention to retain the green jacket but the Aussie knows that day three can make or break his challenge. He told pgatour.com: \'Today\'s round is extremely important for me. It\'s going to have to be maybe the best round of the week.\' 15:31 Solid start for Rory McIlroy starts his round with a par four on the first hole, keeping him at four-over-par for the tournament. The Northern Irishman\'s WAG, tennis star Caroline Wozniacki, is following her man around Augusta. Again. Jason Day and Joost Luiten have also begun their third rounds. Centre of attention: Rory McIlroy tees off on the first hole 15:26 Best job in the world? McIlroy is playing with Jeff Knox today, who is the official marker of the Masters. The 51-year-old has already played in more tournaments than Jordan Spieth, Jimmy Walker and Jonas Blixt. Big day: Marker Jeff Knox watches his drive on the first hole 15:19 And we\'re off! Rory McIlroy gets the third round underway on his own. Padraig Harrington reckons Rory can finish with two rounds of 65. He\'ll need something special today if he\'s to get back into contention. 15:05 Weather watch It\'s another gorgeous day in Georgia, with warm temperatures set to dry out the course even further. One positive for the players is the lack of wind, which should allow them greater control off the tee and approaching the greens. Sunny: More warm weather is expected at Augusta for today\'s third round 14:56 Scott looking to make history Defending Masters champion Adam Scott is sat menacingly behind leader Bubba Watson on three-under-par. The Aussie is looking to become only the fourth player in history to retain the coveted green jacket, which would add him to this prestigious list: Jack Nicklaus (\'65, \'66) Nick Faldo (\'89, \'90) Tiger Woods (\'01, \'02) Still going strong: Adam Scott, who sits tied second, is looking to retain his Masters title 14:45 Did you know? The biggest comeback at the Masters after the opening two rounds was eight shots by Jack Burk in 1956. Steve Stricker, KJ Choi, Mike Weir, Henrik Stenson and Stewart Cink are all currently eight shots behind leader Bubba Watson. Can any of them match Burk\'s achievement? Big ask: Henrik Stenson will need to equal the biggest-ever Masters comeback to win his first green jacket 14:37 Get in touch Don\'t forget, you can send in your thoughts on all things Masters and tell us who you\'re tipping. Also, don\'t forget, there\'s money to be made and if you want to place a bet or check out the latest live odds, click HERE for the latest from Coral. 14:32 On his own Rory McIlroy will get Saturday\'s action underway at 3.15pm after scraping into the third round on four-over-par. The 24-year-old had a round to forget after carding a promising 71 on day one, managing a par on the last to make the cut after an error-filled 18 holes. The Northern Irishman will compete on his own, although Jeff Knox looks likely to play as his marker. A total of 51 players made the cut. In trouble: Rory McIlroy takes a shout out of the azaleas on the 13th 14:24 Third round tee times in full 1515 Rory McIlroy (NIrl)1525 Jason Day (Aus), Joost Luiten (Ned)1535 Jose Maria Olazabal (Spa), Darren Clarke (NIrl)1545 Miguel Angel Jimenez (Spa), Sandy Lyle (Sco)1555 Billy Horschel (USA), Gary Woodland (USA)1605 Chris Kirk (USA), Martin Kaymer (Ger)1615 Oliver Goss (Aus - amateur), Francesco Molinari (Ita)1625 Nick Watney (USA), Thongchai Jaidee (Tha)1635 Bill Haas (USA), Thorbjorn Olesen (Den)1655 Ian Poulter (Eng), Rickie Fowler (USA)1705 Steven Bowditch (Aus), Brendon de Jonge (Zim)1715 Hunter Mahan (USA), Justin Rose (Eng)1725 Vijay Singh (Fij), Bernhard Langer (Ger)1735 Steve Stricker (USA), Larry Mize (USA)1745 Mike Weir (Can), KJ Choi (Kor)1755 Henrik Stenson (Swe), Stewart Cink (USA)1805 Lee Westwood (Eng), Brandt Snedeker (USA)1815 Louis Oosthuizen (Rsa), Gonzalo Fernandez-Castano (Spa)1835 Lucas Glover (USA), Matt Kuchar (USA)1845 Kevin Stadler (USA), Jamie Donaldson (Wal)1855 Stephen Gallacher (Sco), Russell Henley (USA)1905 Jim Furyk (USA), Kevin Streelman (USA)1915 Fred Couples (USA), Jimmy Walker (USA)1925 Adam Scott (Aus), Jordan Spieth (USA)1935 Thomas Bjorn (Den), Jonas Blixt (Swe)1945 Bubba Watson (USA), John Senden (Aus) 14:17 Testing times Here\'s a look at Saturday\'s pin positions. Some extremely tricky locations out there today... 14:11 Bubba in control Bubba Watson leads the way heading into the third round, having carded an impressive four-under-par 68 on day two. He tees off last with Aussie John Senden, who sits three shots behind him after shooting a 68 of his own on Friday. Others in the chasing pack include Jordan Spieth, Thomas Bjorn and Jonas Blixt, all of whom are four shots off the lead. Out in front: Bubba Watson sits top of the Masters leaderboard on seven-under-par 14:00 Good afternoon... ...and welcome to Sportsmail\'s live coverage of the Masters. We\'ll be bringing you plenty of build up to the third day of action over the next hour or so, which gets underway with pre-tournament favourite Rory McIlroy teeing off on his own at 3.15pm BST. Don\'t go anywhere.   {\"id\":\"2602941\",\"channel\":\"/sport\",\"pageUrl\":\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\",\"status\":\"running\",\"greenBox\":{\"body\":\"\"},\"modifiedOrder\":2} 0 0   More... McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink \'I want people to treat me like a plastic sex doll\': Woman has hypnotherapy to make her \'brainless like Barbie\' after spending £25,000 on breast enhancements Scotsman Gallacher delighted to make cut on Masters debut... but is staying grounded   Share or comment on this article 9shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Joe+Strange\" rel=\"nofollow\">Joe Strange</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@Joe_Strange\">Follow @@Joe_Strange</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 18:39 EST, 11 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:47 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"MASTERS LIVE: All the third-round action as it happens at Augusta National\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 9</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">6</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"home item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"346\" scrolling=\"no\" seamless=\"\" src=\"http://opta.mc.cloud.opta.net/configurable/index.html?mc=dmgolf1\" width=\"318\"></iframe> </div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">It\'s moving day at the Masters and once again we\'ll make sure you don\'t miss a thing with our live coverage.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Bubba Watson started his round with a three-shot lead over John Senden but the 2012 champion has already looked nervous, dropping shots on the front-nine to open things up at the top.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Jonas Blixt and Jordan Spieth are right in the mix, while veteran Miguel Angel Jimenez is on three-under-par after a fine early round of 66.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Rory McIlroy, the pre-tournament favourite, was left frustrated as a one-under-par round of 70 failed to bring him back into contention for the coveted green jacket.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">We\'ll bring you the latest action as it happens with all the news from Augusta and the best pictures.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">You can follow your favourites with our leaderboard on the right and let us know what you think or who you\'re tipping by emailing <a href=\"mailto:joe.strange@dailymail.co.uk\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">joe.strange@mailonline.co.uk</a><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">And if you fancy a bet, you can get all the latest live odds from our betting partner Coral by clicking <a href=\"http://affiliate.coral.co.uk/processing/clickthrgh.asp?btag=a_11464b_6129\" rel=\"nofollow\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a>.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Out in front: Bubba Watson is the man they\'re all chasing at Augusta\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-ab5b0e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2602941-1D09DE6C00000578-917_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Out in front: Bubba Watson is the man they\'re all chasing at Augusta</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\">  <div class=\"home item html_snippet_module\"> <!-- Live commentary 2 --> <div data-app-version=\"3\" data-refresh-time=\"\" id=\"lc-commentary-container\"> <div class=\"lc-host-commentator cleared\"> <ul> <li> <img src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/commentators/60x60_joe_strange.png\"/> <b>Joe Strange</b> <p>Host commentator</p> </li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-live-update\"> <span class=\"lc-manual-update\"> <span class=\"lc-commentary-newitems-info\"> <a class=\"lc-update-qty\" href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.showNewPosts()\"></a> </span> </span> <div class=\"onoffswitch\" id=\"lc-auto-refresh-switch\"> <input class=\"onoffswitch-checkbox\" id=\"lc-auto-refresh\" name=\"onoffswitch\" type=\"checkbox\"/> <label class=\"onoffswitch-label\" for=\"lc-auto-refresh\"> <div class=\"onoffswitch-inner\"></div> <div class=\"onoffswitch-switch\"></div> </label> </div> <!--[if (IE)|(lt IE 9)]> <input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"onoffswitch\" class=\"lc-IE78\" id=\"lc-auto-refresh\"> <![endif]--> <label class=\"lc-auto-update\" for=\"lc-auto-refresh\">Auto-update</label> </div> <div id=\"lc-commentary-posts\"><div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-105\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">23:05 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Scott\'s struggles</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Adam Scott misses a birdie chance on the par-three 16th and remains on two-over for the tournament.</p> <p>The Aussie was among the favourites after the cut was made last night but he looks unlikely to retain his green jacket.</p> <p>Meanwhile Bjorn has just made another bogey on 15, leaving him three-under with three to play.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'105\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'105\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-104\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">23:00 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bjorn finds the water... again</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Bjorn\'s second shot at the par-five 15th hits the bank and rolls back into the water.</p> <p>He needs to minimise the damage here with holes fast running out.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'104\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'104\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-103\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:54 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Spieth closes the gap</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Successive birdies for Spieth, who makes a four at the par-five 15th to move to second on the leaderboard.</p> <p>You\'d never know it was his first Masters.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'103\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'103\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-102\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_speech_bubble.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:52 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Kuchar reacts to his third round 68</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>\'I drove it well, I was in a lot of fairways. I played some good, steady golf today.</p> <p>\'I\'ve been playing some good golf. It\'s nice to be part of the conversation and in with a chance on Sunday.\'</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397339564561_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Matt_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Near the top: Matt Kuchar currently holds the clubhouse lead</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'102\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'102\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-101\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:46 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>What a waste</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Watson three-putts from within 20 feet and misses a clear opportunity to extend his advantage at the top.</p> <p>Maybe a few nerves creeping into our leader.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397340104183_lc_galleryImage_Bubba_Watson_reacts_after.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Frustrated: Watson reacts after missing a birdie chance</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'101\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'101\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-100\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:43 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Super Senden</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Beautiful pitch shot from Senden, who knocks his third to within a couple of feet of the 13th hole.</p> <p>A birdie there will get him back to two-under.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'100\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'100\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-99\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:41 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Watson finds the green</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>No such problem for Watson who, after a huge drive, gets his approach within 20 feet on the 13th.</p> <p>He\'ll have a put for eagle, which could put him four shots clear.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397339254325_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Bubba.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Chance: Watson gave himself an excellent eagle opportunity on the 13th</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'99\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'99\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-98\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_amen_corner.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:39 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Double boost for Watson</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Bjorn and Blixt both make bogey at the par-five 15th after finding the water.</p> <p>Two more victims of Amen Corner\'s tricky final hole...</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'98\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'98\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-97\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:37 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Furyk and Kuchar make bogeys</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>After finding the water, Furyk makes a bogey at the 15th and drops back to three-under.</p> <p>Kuchar finishes his best round of the week with a bogey at the last but the American is still four-under-par and holds the clubhouse lead.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'97\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'97\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-96\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_amen_corner.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:31 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Blixt and Bjorn find the water</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Blixt finds the creek with his second shot at the par-five 13th, before his playing partner Bjorn does exactly the same just moments later.</p> <p>Watson could find himself a little further in front of the European duo shortly.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397338347252_lc_galleryImage_epa04165085_Jonas_Blixt_o.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Under pressure: Blixt, pictured here reacting to a missed putt at the sixth, has found the water on the 13th</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'96\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'96\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-95\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_speech_bubble.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:28 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Westwood reacts to his third round 70</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>\'I played really solidly. I hit a lot of good shots all day and gave myself a lot of birdie opportunities.</p> <p>\'I\'ll be there or thereabouts by the end of today depending on what Bubba and a few others do.\'</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'95\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'95\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-94\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:22 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Missed opportunity for Watson</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Bubba has a 20-foot uphill putt on the 11th but he doesn\'t hit it and misses a chance to extend his lead with another birdie.</p> <p>Meanwhile Couples is back to two-under after his pinpoint approach on the par-four 14th leads to an easy three.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'94\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'94\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-93\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:17 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Westwood finishes with a par</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Well-judged first putt from Westwood on the 18th and he holes his second from two feet to finish with a par.</p> <p>That\'s a round of 70 for Westwood, leaving him two-under and right in the mix on Sunday as it stands.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'93\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'93\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-92\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:10 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>So close from Blixt</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Brilliant shot from Blixt out of the drop zone after his approach found the wet stuff.</p> <p>The Swede\'s effort just misses the hole and he\'ll have a tap-in for a bogey.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'92\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'92\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-91\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_sad.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:09 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Westwood drops a shot</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Westwood\'s putt on the 17th comes up short and the Englishman goes back to two-under for the tournament.</p> <p>If he can par or birdie the last, Westwood will have a chance tomorrow.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397337093960_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Lee_W.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Dropping back: Westwood could only manage a bogey on the 17th</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'91\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'91\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-90\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:06 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Blixt finds the water</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Mistake from Blixt, whose long iron shot on the 11 takes a big bounce and cannons into the water.</p> <p>Looks like the man from Sweden could be dropping a shot here.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'90\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'90\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-89\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:04 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Watson back at the top</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Watson does get his birdie at the 10th, sliding in his putt from a couple of feet after a fine approach.</p> <p>The 2012 champ is now back on his own at the top on six-under-par.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397336823812_lc_galleryImage_Bubba_Watson_tees_off_on_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Unique: Watson\'s individual style has helped him to the top of the leaderboard</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'89\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'89\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-88\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:02 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Kuchar ties things up</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Consecutive birdies from Kuchar, who joins Watson, Blixt and Bjorn at the top of the leaderboard on five-under-par.</p> <p>Sunday is going to be perfectly set up if this continues.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'88\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'88\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-87\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">22:00 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>More magic from Bubba</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Fantastic second shot from Watson, who almost finds the hole on the 10th.</p> <p>Looks like that\'ll be a birdie for Bubba, who will move a shot clear at six-under if he doesn\'t mess it up.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'87\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'87\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-86\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/tennis_icons/60x60_applause.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:54 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Couples gets a roar</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Veteran Fred Couples gets a huge cheer from the patrons with a lovely birdie on the 11th.</p> <p>He\'s back to one-under with Rose, who is already in the clubhouse.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397336105696_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Fred_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Still in it: Fred Couples is hoping to make history after winning the Masters in 1992</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'86\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'86\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-85\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:49 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>All level at the top</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Birdies for Bjorn and Blixt at the ninth mean the pair are now level with Watson on five-under par.</p> <p>Kuchar and Spieth are a shot further back on four-under.</p> <p>How quickly things can change at Augusta.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'85\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'85\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-84\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:44 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Westwood looking good at -3</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Westwood hits another beautiful shot on the 16th par 3. Should slot this away nicely for another birdie.</p> <p>Whisper it quietly but he\'s starting to really put pressure on the leaders...</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'84\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'84\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-83\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:41 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Is the pressure getting to Watson?</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Watson seems to be looking a little nervous out there.</p> <p>Don\'t tell him that Blixt has just made a birdie on the ninth...</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'83\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'83\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-82\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:37 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Westwood almost in the water</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Westwood is so close to having to go for a swim on the 15th.  Luckily for the Englishman the ball sits kindly on the bank.</p> <p>Westwood should be able to get himself closer to an under par finish on this hole</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'82\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'82\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-81\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/social/60x60_twitter.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:32 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Well in, Rose!</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> </div> <div class=\"lc-twitter-embed\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Rose in at -1, and not out of it. When you consider he was +5 thru 11 and wet at 12, that\'s a tremendous effort <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TheMasterswithTitleist&amp;src=hash\">#TheMasterswithTitleist</a></p>— Golf Monthly (@GolfMonthly) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GolfMonthly/statuses/455079891579727872\">April 12, 2014</a></blockquote> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'81\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'81\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-80\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:30 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>We\'re behind you Bubba!</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Watson continues his brilliant Augusta driving with a thunderous strike to get the eight underway.</p> <p>Bubba has been playing some brilliant stuff, but is now leading by just one. Can he stay in the lead under pressure from Blixt and Spieth?</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397334650321_lc_galleryImage_Bubba_Watson_of_the_US_co.JPG\"/> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'80\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'80\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-79\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:26 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Westwood makes par putt</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Westwood makes an excellent 15-foot putt on the 14th, but it goes just past the cup. He taps home for par. </p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'79\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'79\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-78\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/social/60x60_twitter.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:25 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> </div> <div class=\"lc-twitter-embed\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Bubba Watson\'s no 3-putt streak comes to an end after a 3-putt bogey on No. 6. He had gone 296 holes without one. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Masters&amp;src=hash\">#Masters</a></p>— Golf Central (@GolfCentral) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GolfCentral/statuses/455076092131700736\">April 12, 2014</a></blockquote> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'78\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'78\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-77\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/weather/60x60_weather_sunny.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:23 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Rose has Watson in his sights</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p><strong>Justin Rose:</strong> \'I was pleased with that round. It was a bit of a roller-coaster but I felt i made a great eagle at 13.</p> <p>\'I felt I could have finished at 3 under, which would have been brilliant but I\'m still I it.</p> <p>\'I saw Bubba struggling, so I think I\'m right in it at this point.\'</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397334239727_lc_galleryImage_Justin_Rose_of_England_wa.JPG\"/> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'77\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'77\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-76\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:21 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bubba\'s in the sand</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Watson over-hits a bunker shot and has to watch agonisingly as the ball roles past the flag and towards the edge of the green...It stayson the dancefloor, just!</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'76\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'76\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-75\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/tennis_icons/60x60_applause.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:19 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>That\'s it for Rose - 69</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Rose gets the par! Just sneaks below 70 with a 69 for the day! He\'ll be pleased with that, but it could so easily have been 68.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'75\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'75\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-74\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_sad.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:18 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Rose misses the birdie</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Justin Rose misses the chance to finish with a birdie on the 18th and has left himself some work to do to make par on the last...</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'74\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'74\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-73\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/misc/60x60_quote.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:15 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Good day for Fowler</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Rickie Fowler on his 67: \'I knew it was going to be tough, but I\'ve been swinging well and am happy with how I played today.\'</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'73\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'73\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-72\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:14 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bubba makes a Bogie!</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Disappointment for Watson as he makes a bogie on the sixth. It doesn\'t seem to bother the American, however, as he wanders over to the seventh and hits an excellent drive.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'72\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'72\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-71\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_sad.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:06 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bogey for Rose</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Frustrating finish for Rose, who underhits a putt on 17 and drops a shot to go back to one-under-par.</p> <p>He has a chance to make it back on the 18th, though.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'71\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'71\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-70\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_speech_bubble.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">21:02 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Poulter reacts to his third round 70</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>\'I\'m disgusted with a round which looks pretty good.</p> <p>\'We\'ll have to see what Bubba does around the golf course. The pins are in positions where guys can make plenty of birdies.</p> <p>\'I\'m just going to have a run at him on Sunday.\'</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'70\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'70\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-69\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:57 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>So close for Blixt</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Blixt almost makes another birdie on six but his putt misses by an inch.</p> <p>Better news for Thomas Bjorn though, who finds the cup with his second shot to get to four-under.</p> <p>This is getting very good.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'69\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'69\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-68\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_amen_corner.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:54 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Oosthuizen\'s challenge fading</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Louis Oosthuizen was near the top of the leaderboard after day one but the South African\'s challenge looks like it could be over.</p> <p>He\'s just dunked his ball in the water at 11 and will almost certainly make at least a bogey.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397333059305_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Louis.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Struggling: Louis Oosthuizen has been far from his best so far today</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'68\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'68\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-67\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:51 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Spieth at it again</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Second birdie of the day for Spieth, who moves to four-under with a two at the par-three sixth.</p> <p>The American is now tied for second with Blixt.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'67\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'67\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-66\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:47 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Poulter finishes level</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Poulter finishes with a two-under-par 69 to leave him level-par for the tournament.</p> <p>He\'s still got a lot of work to do tomorrow but he\'s given himself a chance to win his first ever Major Championship.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'66\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'66\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-65\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:45 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bubba drops a shot</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Watson\'s putt on the fourth drifts to the left of the hole and it\'s another bogey for our leader.</p> <p>Fowler misses a chance to finish with another birdie but he\'s still had an exceptional round. He\'s three-under heading into Sunday.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397332716362_lc_galleryImage_U_S_golfer_Bubba_Watson_p.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Good and bad: Bubba Watson has endured a mixed start to his third round</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'65\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'65\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-64\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:43 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Rose does it again</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Rose holes a long put on the par-five 15th after his ball was fortunate not to roll back into the water. The Englishman is now two-under and right back in the mix.</p> <p> </p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'64\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'64\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-63\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_speech_bubble.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:40 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy reacts after his third round 71</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>\'I enjoyed the round. It\'s not an experience I want to have again.</p> <p>\'The course was fiery from the start. The guys are going to find it pretty interesting this afternoon.</p> <p>\'I felt I played well enough to shoot something a lot lower. I think anything around 70, 69 is going to be a really good score.\'</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'63\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'63\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-62\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:38 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Kuchar moves to three-under</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Third birdie of the day for Kuchar, who reaches the turn at three-under after a bogey-free front-nine.</p> <p>Lots of American interest at the top of the leaderboard now.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'62\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'62\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-61\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:34 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>And Senden\'s struggling too</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Second bogey of the day for Senden, who misses an eight-footer before tapping in.</p> <p>He\'s back to three-under after making up for his first bogey with a birdie at the second.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'61\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'61\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-60\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:32 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Scott struggling</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Double bogey on the fourth for defending champion Scott, who has now dropped three shots in his opening four holes.</p> <p>The Aussie has gone back to level-par in no time at all.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'60\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'60\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-59\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/misc/60x60_transfer.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:30 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Who are you backing?</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>If, like me, your Masters bets are already dead and buried, click <a href=\"http://affiliate.coral.co.uk/processing/clickthrgh.asp?btag=a_11464b_6129\">HERE</a> for the latest live odds from Coral.</p> <p>My money is on Bubba to see it through, which probably means he\'ll bogey every hole on Sunday...</p> </div> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'59\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'59\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-58\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_eagle.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:25 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Eagle for Rose</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Wonderful eagle from Rose on the final hole of Amen Corner which takes him to one-under.</p> <p>The US Open champ is three-under for the day and just behind a big pack on two-under for the tournament after following it up with a par at the 14th.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'58\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'58\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-57\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:20 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Fowler finishing well</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Super run for Rickie Fowler, who birdies 15 and 16 to get to three-under with two to play.</p> <p>The 25-year-old is five-under for the day.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'57\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'57\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-56\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_eagle.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:15 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bubba strikes back</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Senden makes up for his bogey on the first with a an eight-footer for birdie but he\'s outdone by Watson, who holes his putt after reaching the green in two for an eagle.</p> <p>The 2012 champion is back to eight-under and leads by four.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'56\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'56\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-55\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:10 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Spieth up to second</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Jordan Spieth calmly holes his putt on the fourth for a birdie, sending him into second behind Watson.</p> <p>It\'s been a fine Masters debut from the youngster so far.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397329939943_lc_galleryImage_Jordan_Spieth_of_the_US_t.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Big future: Jordan Spieth tees off on the first hole</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'55\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'55\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-54\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:06 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bogeys for Watson, Scott and Senden</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Nervy starts from Watson, Senden and defending champion Scott, each of whom bogey the first.</p> <p>Watson now sits on six-under, while Senden is level with Jimenez, Blixt, Bjorn, Furyk and Spieth on three-under.</p> <p>It\'s getting tight at the top.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'54\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'54\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-53\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_blowup.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">20:03 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Disappointing finish for Woodland</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Woodland finishes his round at level-par after a three-under 69 but it could\'ve been so much better.</p> <p>The American was seven-under for the day after 10 holes but stuttered through Amen Corner before bogeying the last.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397330836560_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Gary_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Frustrated figure: Woodland reacts after a poor shot on the 11th</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'53\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'53\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-52\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/flags/60x60_usa.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:56 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Americans on the up</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>American trio Kevin Stadler, Matt Kuchar and Jim Furyk have all started well today.</p> <p>Stadler has picked up a shot and is two-under alongside Kuchar, while Furyk is now tied third with Jimenez on three-under.</p> <p>Leader Bubba Watson has also began his third round.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397329636106_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Jim_F.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">In the mix: Furyk makes his approach to the first green</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'52\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'52\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-51\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/tennis_icons/60x60_applause.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:50 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Magic from Jimenez</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>What a wonderful performance from Jimenez, who finishes three-under-par after his best round of the week.</p> <p>The 50-year-old rolled back the years for a six-under-par round - the best of the week - which included seven birdies. The Spaniard is currently third behind Bubba Watson and John Senden.</p> <p>Sandy Lyle finishes the day four-over-par and eight-over for the tournament.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'51\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'51\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-50\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_speech_bubble.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:46 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy praises Masters marker Knox</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>After shooting a worse score than his non-competitive playing partner Jeff Knox, Rory McIlroy had some kind words for the amateur golfer.</p> <p>McIlroy said: \'Jeff is a great player and beat me by one. I thought he was going to be nice and three-putt the last so we could have a nice half!</p> <p>\'I don\'t think I\'ve ever seen anyone putt the greens so well. I was thinking of getting him to read some of mine. He looked like he should be playing in the Masters.\'</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'50\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'50\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-49\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:42 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Clarke and Olazabal finish up</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Similar rounds for playing partners Olazabal and Clarke, who both began the day on four-over and ended it a shot worse off.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397328044313_lc_galleryImage_Jose_Maria_Olazabal_of_Sp.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Legend: Jose Maria Olazabal managed a one-over-par 73 on day three at Augusta</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'49\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'49\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-48\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_sad.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:37 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Brit watch</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Poulter and Westwood are level on one-under-par after the former could only make bogey at Amen Corner\'s tricky par-three.</p> <p>Steven Gallacher is also one-under after pars on the first and second, while Jamie Donaldson has dropped to one-over after two bogeys in his first four holes.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'48\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'48\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-47\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:27 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Luiten and Day finish up</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Contrasting fortunes for playing partners Day and Luiten on the 18th, with the former making bogey to finish on two-over-par and the latter grabbing a rare birdie to end on nine-over for the tournament.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397327325128_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Joost.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Tough times: Joost Luiten could only manage a five-over-par 77 on Saturday</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'47\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'47\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-46\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:20 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Jimenez on the charge</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>What a performance by Jimenez. The Spaniard has just made his seventh birdie of the day at the par-three 16th to go three-under-par for the tournament.</p> <p>If he can avoid any mistakes on the last two holes then he should be in the mix at the top of the leaderboard tomorrow.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397327108323_lc_galleryImage_epa04164788_Miguel_Angel_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">On fire: Jimenez plays his approach shot on the par-four seventh</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'46\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'46\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-45\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:10 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Day not giving up</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Jason Day has been quietly going about his business today and the Aussie is back to one-over-par after birdies at 13 and 15.</p> <p>Another on the 18th would be a lovely way for him to finish his round ahead of Sunday.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'45\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'45\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-44\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">19:01 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>More shots being clawed back</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Jimenez makes consecutive birdies at 13 and 14 to get to two-under with four holes still to play.</p> <p>He\'s joined on the same score by Woodland, who has recovered from a double bogey on the 12th to birdie the 13th.</p> <p>Poulter is a few holes behind but successive birdies at nine and 10 have the Englishman also on two-under.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'44\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'44\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-43\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:56 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Westwood gets into the red</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Excellent start for Lee Westwood, who pars the first and then birdies the par-five second to go one-under.</p> <p>Another steady par on the third and lad from Worksop looks in a good position to post a decent score today.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397325071492_lc_galleryImage_Lee_Westwood_of_England_l.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Looking good: Lee Westwood jumps out of a bunker on the first to follow the flight of his ball</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'43\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'43\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-42\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:49 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy outplayed by marker Knox</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Turns out McIlroy\'s 71 was actually a shot more than Masters marker Jeff Knox managed this afternoon.</p> <p>The 51-year-old, who played alongside McIlroy because of the odd number of players who made the cut, shot a two-under-par 70.</p> <p>Well played, Jeff.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397324726311_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Rory_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Playing partners: McIlroy (right) shares a joke with Knox (left)</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'42\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'42\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-41\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_amen_corner.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:39 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Woodland slipping back</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>After his first bogey of the day at the 11th, Woodland drops two more shots at the 12th after dumping his ball in Rae\'s Creek.</p> <p>He\'s now back to one-under for the tournament and currently tied for 10th.</p> <p>Amen Corner hasn\'t been kind to the American today.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'41\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'41\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-40\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:35 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Beware of the bogeys</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Woodland records his first bogey of the day at the par-four 11th and drops back to three-under.</p> <p>Poulter and Jimenez were the other two making moves but both have been halted with bogeys at the seventh and 12th respectively.</p> <p>The pair are now both on level-par.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'40\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'40\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-39\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:26 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy finishes well</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Strong finish from McIlroy, who birdies the 15th, 17th and 18th to finish with a one-under-par 71.</p> <p>The pre-tournament favourite is still three-over and he\'ll need something spectacular to be in with a chance of winning his first green jacket on Sunday night.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397323642592_lc_galleryImage_Rory_McIlroy_of_Northern_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Frustrating afternoon: McIlroy couldn\'t find his best form on Saturday at Augusta</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'39\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'39\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-38\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:21 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Jiminez still smoking</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>No doubt Jimenez will treat himself to a fat cigar if he\'s able to keep up his momentum.</p> <p>The Spaniard has just bagged his fourth birdie of the day at the par-four 11th to move back to one-under.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397323318386_lc_galleryImage_Miguel_Angel_Jimenez_of_S.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">It\'s in the detail: Jimenez (right) checks out his yardage book with his caddy</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'38\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'38\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-37\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:15 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Woodland on fire</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Yet another birdie for Woodland, who moves to seven-under for the day and four-under for the tournament with a three at the par-fourth 10th.</p> <p>This is turning into a ridiculous round of golf from a man whose best finish at Augusta was tied 24th in 2011.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'37\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'37\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-36\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:09 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy, Poulter and Jimenez on the birdie trail</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>McIlroy pulls a shot back at the par-five 15th but it\'s not been the round the Northern Irishman was hoping for today.</p> <p>Poulter is now one-under-par for the tournament after his third birdie of the day at the fifth, while Jimenez is now level-par after a three at the par-four 10th.</p> <p>Some good scoring out there so far today.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397324590231_lc_galleryImage_Britain_s_Ian_Poulter_hit.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">On target: Ian Poulter hits his tee shot on the par-three fourth</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'36\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'36\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-35\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">18:02 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Woodland ties front-nine record</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Another birdie for Woodland at the ninth means the American is out in 30 and now three-under for the tournament.</p> <p>Only four others have managed it: Miller (1975), Norman (1988), Choi (2004) and Mickelson (2009).</p> <p>The 29-year-old is six-under-par for the day. Wow.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397322177299_lc_galleryImage_Gary_Woodlan_of_the_US_to.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Charge: Woodland is six-under-par through the front-nine</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'35\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'35\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-34\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_eagle.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:58 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Mixed start for Rose</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>After finishing his second round with two birdies it\'s been an interesting start to day three for Justin Rose.</p> <p>The US Open champion got a par on the first, bogeyed the second and then eagled the third to leave him where he started one-over-par.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397324454840_lc_galleryImage_Justin_Rose_of_England_te.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Highs and lows: Justin Rose recorded an eagle on the third after bogeying the second</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'34\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'34\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-33\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:50 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Quick start from Mahan</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Excellent start by Hunter Mahan, who has birdied his opening two holes to get back to level-par.</p> <p>The American tied fourth at last year\'s US Open and he\'ll be in the mix again if he keeps this up.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'33\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'33\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-32\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:45 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Woodland makes another</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Third birdie of the day for Woodland on the par-five eighth as he gets to five-under for the day and two-under for the tournament.</p> <p>He was two-over for the same eight holes yesterday. It\'s a funny old game.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397320843340_lc_galleryImage_Gary_Woodlan_of_the_US_pl.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Flying: Gary Woodland is five-under-par through eight holes on day three</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'32\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'32\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-31\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_blowup.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:38 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>YE Yang drowns his sorrows</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> </div> <div class=\"lc-twitter-embed\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Aftermath of a rough masters. Miss cut. Drank a lot to wash away the masters blues.</p>— YE Yang (@Y_E_Yang) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Y_E_Yang/statuses/455006682771652608\">April 12, 2014</a></blockquote> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'31\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'31\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-30\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:34 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Poulter and Fowler start strongly</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Colourful duo Ian Poulter and Rickie Fowler have both begun in superb fashion, grabbing birdies on the second and third to get back to level-par for the tournament.</p> <p>Still a long way to go but they\'re both giving themselves a chance tomorrow as it stands.</p> <p> </p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'30\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'30\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-29\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_amen_corner.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:26 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy heading around Amen Corner</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>It just isn\'t happening for Rory today. He\'s two-over-par for his round and six-over for the tournament.</p> <p>He\'s just negotiated the first two holes of Amen Corner with a pair of pars and is now trying to make up a shot on the par-five 13th.</p> <p>#PrayForRory</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397320133201_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Rory_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Struggling: McIlroy is two-over-par for his round after 12 holes</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'29\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'29\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-28\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:18 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Haas finding his first round form</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>After a nightmare 78 on Friday, first round leader Haas has recaptured his Thursday form with consecutive birdies on the second and third holes.</p> <p>The American is now back to level-par for the tournament.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397319577712_lc_galleryImage_Bill_Haas_looks_for_his_b.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">On the up: First round leader Bill Haas is back to level par</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'28\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'28\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-27\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/misc/60x60_transfer.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:16 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Money to be made</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>If, like me, your Masters bets are already dead and buried, click <a href=\"http://affiliate.coral.co.uk/processing/clickthrgh.asp?btag=a_11464b_6129\">HERE</a> for the latest live odds from Coral.</p> <p>You can still get 7/4 on leader Bubba Watson to win back his green jacket.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'27\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'27\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-26\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:12 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Woodland on the charge</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Another birdie for Woodland on the par-three sixth sees him back in the red at one-under-par for the tournament and four-under for the day.</p> <p>Still a long way to go but encouraging signs from the 29-year-old.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'26\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'26\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-25\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_sad.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">17:02 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy falling further back</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>A third bogey of the day for McIlroy on the par-four 10th sees the pre-tournament favourite at six-over-par with eight holes to play today.</p> <p>Padraig Harrington\'s prediction that Rory would shoot 65 seems a little off...</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397318631627_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Rory_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Hard times: McIlroy is now six-over-par after three bogeys in his first 10 holes</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'25\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'25\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-24\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:54 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Haas and Olesen underway</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>First round leader Bill Haas has just finished playing the first alongside talented 24-year-old Thorbjorn Olesen.</p> <p>Both started with pars, keeping them at two-over-par with 35 holes to play.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'24\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'24\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-23\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:50 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Jimenez rolling back the years</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Impressive stuff again from Jimenez at the par-four fifth as he bags his second birdie of the day to drop back to one-over-par.</p> <p>The Spaniard is one of six record-breaking over 50s to have made the cut, with Fred Couples, Larry Mize, Sandy Lyle, Bernhard Langer and Vijay Singh all still in the mix.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397321516651_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Migue.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Still got it: Miguel Angel Jimenez admires his drive on the fourth hole</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'23\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'23\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-22\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_speech_bubble.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:47 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Get in touch</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Don\'t forget you can e-mail me your thoughts on <a href=\"mailto:joe.strange@mailonline.co.uk\">joe.strange@mailonline.co.uk</a>, or tweet me <a href=\"https://twitter.com/joe_strange\">@joe_strange</a></p> <p>No doubt there will be plenty to discuss over the next seven or eight hours!</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'22\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'22\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-21\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:42 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Clarke and Kirk claw back shots</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Birdies for Clarke on the fifth and Kirk on the second make their respective scorecards look a little better but the same can\'t be said for Olivier Goss.</p> <p>The only amateur left has just posted a double-bogey six on the opening hole, leaving him five-over-par for the tournament.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'21\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'21\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-20\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:27 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bogeys everywhere</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Difficult moments for McIlroy, Olazabal and Luiten, who each drop a shot and fall further behind.</p> <p>Better news for 50-year-old Jiminez though, who grabs a birdie at the par-four third to get back to two-over-par.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'20\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'20\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-19\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_eagle.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:18 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Strong start for Woodland</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Gary Woodland endured a terrible finish to his second round, bogeying the last four holes to finish with a 77.</p> <p>But he hasn\'t let that affect him today, with a birdie on the par-four first bringing him back to two-over-par for the tournament.</p> <p>He then followed it up with the first eagle of the day at the par-five second to get back to level-par. Superb stuff from the American.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'19\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'19\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-18\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:14 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlroy whizzing around</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>McIlroy is averaging less than 10 minutes per hole at the moment, with a consecutive pars at the fifth and sixth keeping him at four-over-par.</p> <p>Olazabal gets back to three-over-par with a birdie at the par-five second, while Luiten has dropped another shot with a bogey at the third.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397316231798_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Rory_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">On his own: Rory McIlroy watches his approach to the green on the first hole</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'18\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'18\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-17\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">16:02 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>No change for McIlroy</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Pars on the fourth and fifth holes for McIlory, who stays at four-over.</p> <p>Miguel Angel Jimenez and Sandy Lyle both start with a par at the first. The Spaniard stays at three-over, while the Scot is a shot further back.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397314967707_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_11_Sandy.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Solid: Sandy Lyle began his third round with a par on the first hole</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'17\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'17\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-16\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:56 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Clarke and Olazabal begin</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Veterans Darren Clarke and Jose Maria Olazabal are playing together this afternoon and the pair have started in identical fashion, both coming away from the first with par.</p> <p>Jason day picks up a birdie on the second to get back to four-over-par, while Luiten gets a par.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397316010986_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Darre.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Experienced: Darren Clarke his his approach shot on the par-four first</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'16\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'16\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-15\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:53 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>McIlory gives one back</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>After a birdie at the second, McIlroy bogeys the third to fall back to four-over-par for the tournament.</p> <p>A par, a birdie and a bogey in his first three holes. A mixed start, you could say.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'15\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'15\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-14\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:49 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Dfficult start for Day and Luiten</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Poor opening hole for playing partners Day and Luiten, who both bogey the first.</p> <p>The pair are now five-over-par, 12 shots behind leader Watson.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397316712365_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Jason.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Focused: Jason Day plays his approach shot to the second green</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'14\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'14\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-13\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_birdie.png\"/> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_brit_good.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:43 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Super second for McIlroy</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>McIlroy needed a strong start to get over his Friday nightmare and he\'s had just that, posting a birdie at the par-five second to get back to three-over-par.</p> <p>The former US Open champion bogeyed the same hole yesterday.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'13\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'13\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-12\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:41 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Scott under no illusions</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Last year\'s Masters champions Adam Scott is in contention to retain the green jacket but the Aussie knows that day three can make or break his challenge.</p> <p>He told pgatour.com: \'Today\'s round is extremely important for me. It\'s going to have to be maybe the best round of the week.\'</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'12\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'12\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-11\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:31 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Solid start for Rory</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>McIlroy starts his round with a par four on the first hole, keeping him at four-over-par for the tournament.</p> <p>The Northern Irishman\'s WAG, tennis star Caroline Wozniacki, is following her man around Augusta. Again.</p> <p>Jason Day and Joost Luiten have also begun their third rounds.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397316994037_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Rory_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Centre of attention: Rory McIlroy tees off on the first hole</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'11\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'11\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-10\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:26 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Best job in the world?</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>McIlroy is playing with Jeff Knox today, who is the official marker of the Masters.</p> <p>The 51-year-old has already played in more tournaments than Jordan Spieth, Jimmy Walker and Jonas Blixt.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397316512680_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_12_Marke.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Big day: Marker Jeff Knox watches his drive on the first hole</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'10\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'10\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-9\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:19 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>And we\'re off!</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Rory McIlroy gets the third round underway on his own.</p> <p>Padraig Harrington reckons Rory can finish with two rounds of 65. He\'ll need something special today if he\'s to get back into contention.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'9\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'9\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-8\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.mol.im/i/furniture/live_commentary/football_icons/weather/60x60_weather_sunny.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">15:05 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Weather watch</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>It\'s another gorgeous day in Georgia, with warm temperatures set to dry out the course even further.</p> <p>One positive for the players is the lack of wind, which should allow them greater control off the tee and approaching the greens.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397311633856_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_11_Ian_P.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Sunny: More warm weather is expected at Augusta for today\'s third round</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'8\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'8\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-7\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:56 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Scott looking to make history</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Defending Masters champion Adam Scott is sat menacingly behind leader Bubba Watson on three-under-par.</p> <p>The Aussie is looking to become only the fourth player in history to retain the coveted green jacket, which would add him to this prestigious list:</p> <p><strong>Jack Nicklaus (\'65, \'66)</strong></p> <p><strong>Nick Faldo (\'89, \'90)</strong></p> <p><strong>Tiger Woods (\'01, \'02)</strong></p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397310754521_lc_galleryImage_epa04164092_Adam_Scott_of.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Still going strong: Adam Scott, who sits tied second, is looking to retain his Masters title</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'7\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'7\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-6\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:45 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Did you know?</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>The biggest comeback at the Masters after the opening two rounds was eight shots by Jack Burk in 1956.</p> <p>Steve Stricker, KJ Choi, Mike Weir, Henrik Stenson and Stewart Cink are all currently eight shots behind leader Bubba Watson.</p> <p>Can any of them match Burk\'s achievement?</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397310516995_lc_galleryImage_AUGUSTA_GA_APRIL_11_Henri.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Big ask: Henrik Stenson will need to equal the biggest-ever Masters comeback to win his first green jacket</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'6\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'6\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-5\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <img class=\"lc-icon\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/furniture/live_commentary/golf_icons/60x60_speech_bubble.png\"/> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:37 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Get in touch</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Don\'t forget, you can send in your thoughts on all things Masters and tell us who you\'re tipping.</p> <p>Also, don\'t forget, there\'s money to be made and if you want to place a bet or check out the latest live odds, click <a href=\"http://affiliate.coral.co.uk/processing/clickthrgh.asp?btag=a_11464b_6129\">HERE</a> for the latest from Coral.</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'5\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'5\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-4\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:32 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>On his own</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Rory McIlroy will get Saturday\'s action underway at 3.15pm after scraping into the third round on four-over-par.</p> <p>The 24-year-old had a round to forget after carding a promising 71 on day one, managing a par on the last to make the cut after an error-filled 18 holes.</p> <p>The Northern Irishman will compete on his own, although Jeff Knox looks likely to play as his marker.</p> <p>A total of 51 players made the cut.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397309119102_lc_galleryImage_Rory_McIlroy_of_Northern_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">In trouble: Rory McIlroy takes a shout out of the azaleas on the 13th</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'4\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'4\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-3\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:24 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Third round tee times in full</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p><strong>1515</strong> Rory McIlroy (NIrl)<br/><strong>1525</strong> Jason Day (Aus), Joost Luiten (Ned)<br/><strong>1535</strong> Jose Maria Olazabal (Spa), Darren Clarke (NIrl)<br/><strong>1545</strong> Miguel Angel Jimenez (Spa), Sandy Lyle (Sco)<br/><strong>1555</strong> Billy Horschel (USA), Gary Woodland (USA)<br/><strong>1605</strong> Chris Kirk (USA), Martin Kaymer (Ger)<br/><strong>1615</strong> Oliver Goss (Aus - amateur), Francesco Molinari (Ita)<br/><strong>1625</strong> Nick Watney (USA), Thongchai Jaidee (Tha)<br/><strong>1635</strong> Bill Haas (USA), Thorbjorn Olesen (Den)<br/><strong>1655</strong> Ian Poulter (Eng), Rickie Fowler (USA)<br/><strong>1705</strong> Steven Bowditch (Aus), Brendon de Jonge (Zim)<br/><strong>1715</strong> Hunter Mahan (USA), Justin Rose (Eng)<br/><strong>1725</strong> Vijay Singh (Fij), Bernhard Langer (Ger)<br/><strong>1735</strong> Steve Stricker (USA), Larry Mize (USA)<br/><strong>1745</strong> Mike Weir (Can), KJ Choi (Kor)<br/><strong>1755</strong> Henrik Stenson (Swe), Stewart Cink (USA)<br/><strong>1805</strong> Lee Westwood (Eng), Brandt Snedeker (USA)<br/><strong>1815</strong> Louis Oosthuizen (Rsa), Gonzalo Fernandez-Castano (Spa)<br/><strong>1835</strong> Lucas Glover (USA), Matt Kuchar (USA)<br/><strong>1845</strong> Kevin Stadler (USA), Jamie Donaldson (Wal)<br/><strong>1855</strong> Stephen Gallacher (Sco), Russell Henley (USA)<br/><strong>1905</strong> Jim Furyk (USA), Kevin Streelman (USA)<br/><strong>1915</strong> Fred Couples (USA), Jimmy Walker (USA)<br/><strong>1925</strong> Adam Scott (Aus), Jordan Spieth (USA)<br/><strong>1935</strong> Thomas Bjorn (Den), Jonas Blixt (Swe)<br/><strong>1945</strong> Bubba Watson (USA), John Senden (Aus)</p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'3\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'3\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-2\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:17 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Testing times</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Here\'s a look at Saturday\'s pin positions. Some extremely tricky locations out there today...</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397308426813_lc_galleryImage_image001_png.JPG\"/> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'2\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'2\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-1\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:11 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Bubba in control</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>Bubba Watson leads the way heading into the third round, having carded an impressive four-under-par 68 on day two.</p> <p>He tees off last with Aussie John Senden, who sits three shots behind him after shooting a 68 of his own on Friday.</p> <p>Others in the chasing pack include Jordan Spieth, Thomas Bjorn and Jonas Blixt, all of whom are four shots off the lead.</p> </div> <img class=\"lc-post-image\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/1397308341485_lc_galleryImage_epa04163894_Bubba_Watson_.JPG\"/> <b class=\"lc-image-caption\">Out in front: Bubba Watson sits top of the Masters leaderboard on seven-under-par</b> <div class=\"lc-clear\"></div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'1\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'1\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> <div class=\"lc-commentary-post cleared\" id=\"lc-id-0\"> <div class=\"lc-icons\"> <div class=\"lc-post-time\">14:00 </div> </div> <div class=\"lc-title-container\"> <span><b>Good afternoon...</b></span> </div> <div class=\"lc-post-body\"> <p>...and welcome to Sportsmail\'s live coverage of the Masters.</p> <p>We\'ll be bringing you plenty of build up to the third day of action over the next hour or so, which gets underway with pre-tournament favourite Rory McIlroy teeing off on his own at 3.15pm BST.</p> <p>Don\'t go anywhere.</p> <p> </p> </div> <ul class=\"lc-social\"> <li class=\"lc-facebook\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToFB, \'0\', \'facebook\')\"></span></li> <li class=\"lc-twitter\"><span onclick=\"window.LiveCommentary.socialShare(postToTWTTR, \'0\', \'twitter\', window.twitterVia)\"></span></li> </ul> </div> </div> <span id=\"lc-metadata\" style=\"display:none\">{\"id\":\"2602941\",\"channel\":\"/sport\",\"pageUrl\":\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\",\"status\":\"running\",\"greenBox\":{\"body\":\"\"},\"modifiedOrder\":2}</span> <span id=\"lc-latest-modification-time\" style=\"display:none\">0</span> <span id=\"lc-latest-modification-order\" style=\"display:none\">0</span> <link href=\"http://livecommentary.dailymail.co.uk/apps/livecommentary_public/css/commentary.css?cb=1395314271\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/> <link href=\"http://livecommentary.dailymail.co.uk/apps/livecommentary_public/css/sport/commentary.css?cb=1395314271\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/> </div> <!-- FOR IE7 and below - must include before JSON.parse --> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602890/Stepen-Gallacher-continues-early-Masters-magic-Ian-Poulter-Justin-Rose-enjoy-good-second-day-cut-sight.html\"> McIlroy scrapes through while Gallacher continues early Masters magic</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602892/John-Daly-big-draw-Hooters-Sergio-Garcia-Bubba-Watson-pretty-pink.html\"> Daly is still a big draw at Hooters... Garcia and Watson are pretty in pink</a></li> <li><a href=\"/femail/article-2562870/I-want-people-treat-like-plastic-sex-doll-Woman-hypnotherapy-make-brainless-like-Barbie-spending-25-000-breast-enhancements.html\"> \'I want people to treat me like a plastic sex doll\': Woman has hypnotherapy to make her \'brainless like Barbie\' after spending £25,000 on breast enhancements</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/golf/article-2602801/Stephen-Gallacher-delighted-make-cut-Masters-debut.html\"> Scotsman Gallacher delighted to make cut on Masters debut... but is staying grounded</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<br/>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/MASTERS-LIVE-All-round-action-happens-Augusta-National.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"MASTERS LIVE: All the third-round action as it happens at Augusta National\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/golf/article-2602941/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">9</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-0-1D09EBE200000578-216_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 17:06:27','2014-04-12 22:47:34'),(124,'2d454034bab643dda69f60b2b7a12c5b692cce682a92a571a1b29b14578408d3','dailymail',NULL,'Crystal Palace 1-0 Aston Villa: Jason Puncheon takes Eagles a step closer to survival','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603056/Crystal-Palace-1-0-Aston-Villa-Jason-Puncheon-takes-Eagles-step-closer-survival.html',' By Martha Kelner Published: 11:00 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 15:33 EST, 12 April 2014 17 shares 36 View comments MATCH ZONE Click here for your ultimate stats package for the big game - including match winner Jason Puncheon\'s heat map  Crystal Palace took another huge step towards Premier League survival after Jason Puncheon’s goal lifted them seven points clear of the relegation zone. Villa manager Paul Lambert admitted his side were at risk of being sucked into a relegation battle after four consecutive defeats that have left them four points off the drop zone. ‘We have to be optimistic, we can’t let our heads go down, but we do need to stop the losing sequence,’ said Lambert. His side still have to face Manchester City and the pressure is mounting on him. There were some discontented chants coming from the section of travelling fans at Selhurst Park, but Lambert denied that this season’s tally of 34 points after 33 games — identical to last year — indicated a lack of progress. ‘I still think this season we’re a million miles away from last season,’ he said. Lambert: I\'ve just told the lads we\'ve got to win the next game  Flying high: Crystal Palace star man Jason Puncheon wheels away after scoring the winner I\'m so happy! Jason Puncheon cannot control his delight after scoring the match winner at Selhurst Park   Distance: Puncheon (R) fends off Aston Villa defenders to move Eagles above their opponents in the table   Enlarge   On a sixpence: Puncheon scores alate goal that could be decide Palace\'s Premier League status  Important strike: Jason Puncheon\'s goal takes Palace to 37 points, virtually securing their survival Pulis: Although Puncheon\'s scoring the goals, team ethic\'s key   Match factsAston Villa: Guzan(6); Lowton (6), Vlaar(C)(6), Baker (6), Bertrand (6); Clark (6), Westwood (6), Delph (5), El Ahmadi (6); Agbonlahor (5), Holt (5)Subs: Steer, Bennett, Sylla, Albrighton, Tonev, Bowery, Weimann (6)Crystal Palace: Speroni (7); Mariappa (6), Dann (6), Delaney (6), Ward (6); Jedinak (6), Dikgacoi; Puncheon (7), Ledley, Bolasie (8); Jerome (6)Subs: Hennessey, Gabbidon, Parr, Ince, Gayle, Murray, Chamakh (7)*Player Raitings from Martha Kelner at Selhurst ParkClick HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Premier League - plus your stats zone from the match ‘You don’t know what’s happened behind the scenes. We’re still a million miles from where I want Aston Villa to be but there are other things going on.’ Palace manager Tony Pulis denied his side were assured Premier League football next season. But they are certainly heading that way. It was the first time this season that they have won three successive games, scoring five goals and not conceding in the process. Puncheon has scored three of those, but Pulis was keen to spread the plaudits. ‘Puncheon has done fantastic, but I think he will be the first one to say that although he is scoring the goals — and he’ll get the headlines again — the way the whole group work to help one another is pretty inspiring,’ he said. ‘That teamwork, that ethic is what has got us where we are. We’ve got players who have really stood strong when we’ve needed them to.’ Puncheon made the breakthrough on 76 minutes. Yannick Bolasie supplied the cross and the 27-year-old calmly turned in the box and finished low and powerfully past Brad Guzan and in off the post. Palace’s Argentinian goalkeeper Julian Speroni, who could yet get a World Cup call-up, ensured the home side preserved their lead in the 87th minute when he dived low to his left to save a fizzing Andreas Weimann effort.  Nervous finish: The result leaves Aston Villa just four points clear of the drop zone with five games to play   Worried expression: Villa manager Paul Jewell looks on as his side stumble to another defeat   Taking a lunge: Palace defender Damien Delaney (R) tries to block a pass from Villa\'s Gabby Agbonlahor   Piggyback ride: Palace\'s Adrian Mariappa steps over Aston Villa youngster Fabian Delph (ground)   Legs akimbo! Villa\'s Fabian Delph crumples to the floor after a challenge with Palace midfielder Puncheon  Meanwhile, Pulis played down any advantage Palace received before last week\'s win at Cardiff. \'You look at it, for three weeks have picked the same formation and same team, we haven\'t changed anything,\' he said. \'Irrespective of who or where it has come from it is pure speculation until the team-sheet comes in. Although I try and avoid it myself, I have known managers change the team 10 minutes before the team sheets have gone in so it is very difficult to say it is definitely going to be that team.\'  Crying foul! Eagles manager Tony Pulis (C) disputes the referee\'s decision at Selhurst Park   Salemate: Karim El Ahmadi of Aston Villa battles with Joel Ward of Crystal Palace during a goalless first-half   Striking difference: Palace forward Cameron Jerome tries to break the deadlock in the first half.   Best foot forward: Villa\'s Ryan Bertrand tries to win the ball off Adrian Mariappa of Crystal Palace Pulis said he would never trust anyone with insider information on an opponent having come across attempts to leak things in the past. \'I\'ve been a manager for 900-odd games,\' he added. \'You get phone calls from the press, you get phone calls from agents, you get phone calls from ex-players, you got phone calls about this and that. \'The thing I will say is that I\'m never, ever convinced what team we are going to play against until that team-sheet comes through the door, never. \'Irrespective of who tells me, it could be my brother or it could be my wife telling me that it was the team, until the team-sheet comes in I never relax.\'  Injury: Kagisho Dikgacoi of Crystal Palace is given treatment before being replaced by Marouane Chamakh    Solid as a rock: Mile Jedinak stands firm in Palace\'s defend as Aston Villa launch a first-half attack   Nose job! Damien Dehaney of Crystal Palace catches Villa\'s Fabien Delph as he goes past him   Getting stuck in: Villa striker Gabby Agbonlahor is beaten to the ball by Eagles captain Mile Jedinak (L)   Taking a tumble: Chelsea loanee Ryan Bertrand is bundled off the ball by Palace midfielder Jason Puncheon   Get shirty: Yannick Bolasie of Crystal Palace (R) and Karim El Ahmadi of Aston Villa battle for the ball   25th anniversary: Both sets of players respect a minute\'s silence in honour of the Hillsborough victims   Respect: All games around the country kicked off at 3.07 in tribute to the fans who lost their lives at Hillsborough   Selfie: Crystal Palace keeper Julian Speroni has a picture taken with a fan before the game     More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article 17shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Martha+Kelner\" rel=\"nofollow\">Martha Kelner</a> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 11:00 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:33 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603056/Crystal-Palace-1-0-Aston-Villa-Jason-Puncheon-takes-Eagles-step-closer-survival.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603056/Crystal-Palace-1-0-Aston-Villa-Jason-Puncheon-takes-Eagles-step-closer-survival.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Crystal Palace 1-0 Aston Villa: Puncheon takes Eagles a giant step closer to survival\"> <a onclick=\'postToGPlus(\"top\"); return false;\'></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"share-icons\" id=\"shareLinkTop\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> </ul> <div class=\"share-count\"> <b> 17</b> <span>shares</span> </div> <a class=\"comments-count home\" href=\"/sport/football/article-2603056/Crystal-Palace-1-0-Aston-Villa-Jason-Puncheon-takes-Eagles-step-closer-survival.html#comments\"> <span></span> <p class=\"count-number\">36</p> <p class=\"count-text\">View <br/> comments</p> </a> </div>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>MATCH ZONE</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p> <font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#s2013-c8-m695231\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> for your ultimate stats package for the big game - including match winner Jason Puncheon\'s heat map<br/></font></p><div class=\"clear\"> </div> <img alt=\"Heat Map: Jason Puncheon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"198\" id=\"i-a7aa0e66\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E484400000578-191_299x198.jpg\" width=\"299\"/> <p> </p><div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div></div>\n<br/>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Crystal Palace took another huge step towards Premier League survival after Jason Puncheon’s goal lifted them seven points clear of the relegation zone.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Villa manager Paul Lambert admitted his side were at risk of being sucked into a relegation battle after four consecutive defeats that have left them four points off the drop zone.<br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘We have to be optimistic, we can’t let our heads go down, but we do need to stop the losing sequence,’ said Lambert. His side still have to face Manchester City and the pressure is mounting on him. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">There were some discontented chants coming from the section of travelling fans at Selhurst Park, but Lambert denied that this season’s tally of 34 points after 33 games — identical to last year — indicated a lack of progress. ‘I still think this season we’re a million miles away from last season,’ he said. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3461309067001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Lambert: I\'ve just told the lads we\'ve got to win the next game</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/video-undefined-1D0EE8C300000578-940_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Flying high: Crystal Palace star man Jason Puncheon wheels away after scoring the winner\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a9240e6c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E3A9700000578-851_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Flying high: Crystal Palace star man Jason Puncheon wheels away after scoring the winner</p> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"I\'m so happy! Jason Puncheon cannot control his delight after scoring the match winner at Selhurst Park\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a6bb0e56\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E402600000578-565_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">I\'m so happy! Jason Puncheon cannot control his delight after scoring the match winner at Selhurst Park</p> </div><p> </p></div></div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Distance: Puncheon (R) fends off Aston Villa defenders to move Eagles above their opponents in the table\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-aaf30e7e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E3AAB00000578-625_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Distance: Puncheon (R) fends off Aston Villa defenders to move Eagles above their opponents in the table</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <a class=\"lightboxPopupLink\" href=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E37FC00000578-257_634x435_popup.jpg\" onclick=\"return false;\" rel=\"\"> <span class=\"clickToEnlargeTop\">Enlarge</span> <span class=\"clickToEnlarge\"></span> <span class=\"clickToEnlargeButton\"> </span> <img alt=\"On a sixpence: Puncheon scores alate goal that could be decide Palace\'s Premier League status\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-aa880e7b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E37FC00000578-257_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </a> <p class=\"imageCaption\">On a sixpence: Puncheon scores alate goal that could be decide Palace\'s Premier League status</p></div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Important strike: Jason Puncheon\'s goal takes Palace to 37 points, virtually securing their survival\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a9e00e76\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E3F6900000578-965_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Important strike: Jason Puncheon\'s goal takes Palace to 37 points, virtually securing their survival</p><div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3461379754001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Pulis: Although Puncheon\'s scoring the goals, team ethic\'s key</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/video-undefined-1D0EFE9600000578-191_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>Match facts</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Aston Villa</b>: Guzan(6); Lowton (6), Vlaar(C)(6), Baker (6), Bertrand (6); Clark (6), Westwood (6), Delph (5), El Ahmadi (6); Agbonlahor (5), Holt (5)</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs</b>: Steer, Bennett, Sylla, Albrighton, Tonev, Bowery, Weimann (6)</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Crystal Palace</b>: Speroni (7); Mariappa (6), Dann (6), Delaney (6), Ward (6); Jedinak (6), Dikgacoi; Puncheon (7), Ledley, Bolasie (8); Jerome (6)</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs</b>: Hennessey, Gabbidon, Parr, Ince, Gayle, Murray, Chamakh (7)</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">*Player Raitings from Martha Kelner at Selhurst Park</span><br/></font></p><ul><li><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Premier League - plus your stats zone from the match<br/></a></font></li></ul></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘You don’t know what’s happened behind the scenes. We’re still a million miles from where I want Aston Villa to be but there are other things going on.’ </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Palace manager Tony Pulis denied his side were assured Premier League football next season. But they are certainly heading that way. It was the first time this season that they have won three successive games, scoring five goals and not conceding in the process. Puncheon has scored three of those, but Pulis was keen to spread the plaudits.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">‘Puncheon has done fantastic, but I think he will be the first one to say that although he is scoring the goals — and he’ll get the headlines again — the way the whole group work to help one another is pretty inspiring,’ he said. ‘That teamwork, that ethic is what has got us where we are. We’ve got players who have really stood strong when we’ve needed them to.’</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Puncheon made the breakthrough on 76 minutes. Yannick Bolasie supplied the cross and the 27-year-old calmly turned in the box and finished low and powerfully past Brad Guzan and in off the post. </font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Palace’s Argentinian goalkeeper Julian Speroni, who could yet get a World Cup call-up, ensured the home side preserved their lead in the 87th minute when he dived low to his left to save a fizzing Andreas Weimann effort.</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Nervous finish: The result leaves Aston Villa just four points clear of the drop zone with five games to play\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a8160e66\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E595200000578-797_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Nervous finish: The result leaves Aston Villa just four points clear of the drop zone with five games to play</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Worried expression: Villa manager Paul Jewell looks on as his side stumble to another defeat\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a83c0e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E637800000578-597_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Worried expression: Villa manager Paul Jewell looks on as his side stumble to another defeat</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Taking a lunge: Palace defender Damien Delaney (R) tries to block a pass from Villa\'s Gabby Agbonlahor\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a9110e6c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E15E900000578-923_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Taking a lunge: Palace defender Damien Delaney (R) tries to block a pass from Villa\'s Gabby Agbonlahor</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Piggyback ride: Palace\'s Adrian Mariappa steps over Aston Villa youngster Fabian Delph (ground)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a8900e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E06D500000578-581_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Piggyback ride: Palace\'s Adrian Mariappa steps over Aston Villa youngster Fabian Delph (ground)</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Legs akimbo! Villa\'s Fabian Delph crumples to the floor after a challenge with Palace midfielder Puncheon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"477\" id=\"i-a9910e77\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E11AE00000578-456_634x477.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Legs akimbo! Villa\'s Fabian Delph crumples to the floor after a challenge with Palace midfielder Puncheon</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Meanwhile, Pulis played down any advantage Palace received before last week\'s win at Cardiff.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'You look at it, for three weeks have picked the same formation and same team, we haven\'t changed anything,\' he said.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Irrespective of who or where it has come from it is pure speculation until the team-sheet comes in. Although I try and avoid it myself, I have known managers change the team 10 minutes before the team sheets have gone in so it is very difficult to say it is definitely going to be that team.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Crying foul! Eagles manager Tony Pulis (C) disputes the referee\'s decision at Selhurst Park\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-ab130e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DFE6200000578-579_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Crying foul! Eagles manager Tony Pulis (C) disputes the referee\'s decision at Selhurst Park</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Salemate: Karim El Ahmadi of Aston Villa battles with Joel Ward of Crystal Palace during a goalless first-half\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a9920e6d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DF03D00000578-412_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Salemate: Karim El Ahmadi of Aston Villa battles with Joel Ward of Crystal Palace during a goalless first-half</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Striking difference: Palace forward Cameron Jerome tries to break the deadlock in the first half.\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"443\" id=\"i-aced0e93\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DD9DF00000578-884_634x443.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Striking difference: Palace forward Cameron Jerome tries to break the deadlock in the first half.</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Best foot forward: Villa\'s Ryan Bertrand tries to win the ball off Adrian Mariappa of Crystal Palace\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-ab210e7f\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DD0EA00000578-147_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Best foot forward: Villa\'s Ryan Bertrand tries to win the ball off Adrian Mariappa of Crystal Palace</p> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Pulis said he would never trust anyone with insider information on an opponent having come across attempts to leak things in the past.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'I\'ve been a manager for 900-odd games,\' he added.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'You get phone calls from the press, you get phone calls from agents, you get phone calls from ex-players, you got phone calls about this and that.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'The thing I will say is that I\'m never, ever convinced what team we are going to play against until that team-sheet comes through the door, never.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">\'Irrespective of who tells me, it could be my brother or it could be my wife telling me that it was the team, until the team-sheet comes in I never relax.\'</font></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Injury: Kagisho Dikgacoi of Crystal Palace is given treatment before being replaced by Marouane Chamakh\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a94e0e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E179E00000578-619_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Injury: Kagisho Dikgacoi of Crystal Palace is given treatment before being replaced by Marouane Chamakh</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Solid as a rock: Mile Jedinak stands firm in Palace\'s defend as Aston Villa launch a first-half attack\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"461\" id=\"i-a7ee0e5b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DC70300000578-105_634x461.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Solid as a rock: Mile Jedinak stands firm in Palace\'s defend as Aston Villa launch a first-half attack</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Nose job! Damien Dehaney of Crystal Palace catches Villa\'s Fabien Delph as he goes past him\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a0100e62\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DCEEE00000578-34_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Nose job! Damien Dehaney of Crystal Palace catches Villa\'s Fabien Delph as he goes past him</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Getting stuck in: Villa striker Gabby Agbonlahor is beaten to the ball by Eagles captain Mile Jedinak (L)\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-ac020e86\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DCEE400000578-813_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Getting stuck in: Villa striker Gabby Agbonlahor is beaten to the ball by Eagles captain Mile Jedinak (L)</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Taking a tumble: Chelsea loanee Ryan Bertrand is bundled off the ball by Palace midfielder Jason Puncheon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-9cf20e44\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DB5C600000578-65_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Taking a tumble: Chelsea loanee Ryan Bertrand is bundled off the ball by Palace midfielder Jason Puncheon</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Get shirty: Yannick Bolasie of Crystal Palace (R) and Karim El Ahmadi of Aston Villa battle for the ball\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a89e0e64\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DA85400000578-432_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Get shirty: Yannick Bolasie of Crystal Palace (R) and Karim El Ahmadi of Aston Villa battle for the ball</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"25th anniversary: Both sets of players respect a minute\'s silence in honour of the Hillsborough victims\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"453\" id=\"i-9b6a0e33\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DA71900000578-44_634x453.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">25th anniversary: Both sets of players respect a minute\'s silence in honour of the Hillsborough victims</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Respect: All games around the country kicked off at 3.07 in tribute to the fans who lost their lives at Hillsborough\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a9e00e71\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0DA3F400000578-370_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Respect: All games around the country kicked off at 3.07 in tribute to the fans who lost their lives at Hillsborough</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Selfie: Crystal Palace keeper Julian Speroni has a picture taken with a fan before the game\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"435\" id=\"i-a9f90e74\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0D56DA00000578-236_634x435.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Selfie: Crystal Palace keeper Julian Speroni has a picture taken with a fan before the game</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"><div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"sport item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"519\" marginheight=\"0px\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"http://www.eplayer.performgroup.com/DailyMailWidget/version/Palace/pID/57h8obfyfhfz1ok6grnlw2w3o/chID/198yrtj8mb3v21o0p0pxomrai2\" width=\"225\"></iframe> </div> </div> <br/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"><div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"sport item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"519px\" marginheight=\"0px\" marginwidth=\"0px\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"http://www.eplayer.performgroup.com/DailyMailWidget/pID/1ui59tvau9m031sp8acwqww26p/chID/85C070CA5B5C41A48E1461D7FE626CFC/version/Villa\" style=\"margin-left: 41px\" width=\"225px\"></iframe> </div> </div> <br/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2555289/Premier-League-team-news-stats-February-11-12.html\"> All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603056/Crystal-Palace-1-0-Aston-Villa-Jason-Puncheon-takes-Eagles-step-closer-survival.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603056/Crystal-Palace-1-0-Aston-Villa-Jason-Puncheon-takes-Eagles-step-closer-survival.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Crystal Palace 1-0 Aston Villa: Puncheon takes Eagles a giant step closer to survival\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603056/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">17</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603056-1D0E3A9700000578-322_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 17:06:28','2014-04-12 22:33:00');
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (125,'b9afaccb3d2bc39900e0bb4de0924ee2e638184f50838727639abb4e136770ae','dailymail',NULL,'Southampton 0-1 Cardiff match report: Juan Cala stunner gives Ole Gunnar Solskjaer hope in fight against relegation','http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603073/Southampton-0-1-Cardiff-match-report-Juan-Cala-stunner-gives-Ole-Gunnar-Solskjaer-hope-fight-against-relegation.html',' By Riath Al-Samarrai Follow @@riathalsam Published: 10:58 EST, 12 April 2014 | Updated: 15:27 EST, 12 April 2014 5 shares 8 View comments MATCH ZONE Click here for your ultimate stats package – including Juan Cala\'s opening goal. Who would have thought the only leak would be in Southampton’s defence? At the end of a week of spy mysteries and recriminations, Cardiff City somehow found a glimmer of hope in a season of chaos and a game they looked like losing. They are still on the brink. Indeed, they are still in the bottom three. But Juan Cala’s delightful goal has put Cardiff City back in contention. If they pull it off it will be quite remarkable. But that is a fairly hefty ‘if’, not least because this was a win against a side with little to play for and a side which all but gave up trying after an impressive first half. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer has spoken of needing a ‘miracle’. On Saturday, with a member of his staff in the process of being dismissed for leaking team information to Crystal Palace, he was more upbeat. Solskjaer: Atmosphere in the dressing room was great afterwards  Stayed hit! Central defender Juan Cala opened the scoring for Cardiff during their trip to Southampton  MATCH FACTSSouthampton: Gazzaniga 6; Chambers 6.5 (Clyne 67, 6), Fonte 6, Lovren 6, Shaw 6.5; S Davis 6, Schneiderlin 7, Cork 6 (Do Prado 78); Ramírez 6.5 (Gallagher 66, 6), Lambert 6.5, Lallana 6.5.Subs not used: Cropper, Wanyama, Ward-Prowse, Hooiveld.Cardiff City: Marshall 7.5; Theophile 5.5, Caulker 6, Cala 7, Fabio 5.5 (McNaughton 78); Kim 6, Mutch 6, Medel 5.5 (Zaha 61, 6), Whittingham 6, Daehli 6.5 (Bellamy 87); Campbell 6.Subs not used: Lewis, Turner, Eikrem, Gunnarsson.Goal: Cala 61Referee: Jon Moss 6.5Att: 30,526Player ratings by RIATH AL-SAMARRAI at St Mary\'s. Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Premier League - plus your stats zone from the match He said: ‘We have had issues. I dealt with it and they just focused on the football. We have ended the week on a high. ‘Before this game I don’t think many expected us to come here and take points. Now we are three points off safety with four games to go. We still need help from others.’ They certainly had a little help from Southampton. Barring efforts from Fraizer Campbell and Peter Whittingham, Cardiff offered little in the first half. At the other end, Southampton were a blitz of movement and attacking touches. Gaston Ramirez hit the bar after 21 minutes and shortly afterwards Rickie Lambert’s free-kick forced David Marshall to save low to his right. Marshall has been superb this season, certainly the only Cardiff player who has. He stopped Lambert again shortly before the break and with it Cardiff had a platform to deliver a significant surprise. Cala made the defining contribution after 65 minutes. Whittingham’s free-kick from the left had pinballed between a couple of Southampton heads before Calum Chambers nodded it to the edge of the area. Cala controlled on his chest, sidestepped Steven Davis and curled his shot past Paulo Gazzaniga. Southampton manager Mauricio Pochettino said: ‘It was probably the easiest game we have had for possession, but you need to take chances. ‘If you analyse it you see Cardiff defending with nine men behind the ball and that is hard to break down.’  Delight! Cala runs off to celebrate alongside substitute Wilfried Zaha after scoring a blinding drive   Salute! The Spaniard ran over to address the travelling Welsh fans after netting in the 65th minute   Swoosh: Cala\'s effort flew into the Southampton top corner as they recorded a famous win     More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season? The Welsh side looked set to suffer a similarly large defeat at St Mary\'s after a woeful first half in which Gaston Ramirez rattled the crossbar.However, wayward finishing and a fine display from goalkeeper David Marshall kept the hosts at bay, allowing the away side to sneak an improbable win from a surprising source.Having failed to clear their line, Cala - one of four changes from last weekend\'s embarrassing loss - showed poise and skill few would expect from a centre-back to strike home from the edge of the box.Pochettino\'s side pressed for a late leveller but it was not to be as they failed to score for just the sixth time this season, giving Solskjaer\'s men a huge three points.Saints made one change for the match as Ramirez came in for the injured Jay Rodriguez, who the hosts\' players showed support for in the warm-up by wearing training shirts with the number nine on the back.The in-form forward\'s absence did little to stop Southampton\'s attacking flow, though, and Cala had to be alert early to prevent an early Luke Shaw cross being tucked away.The Spanish centre-back did well to deny Adam Lallana soon after and Fabio deflected a Steven Davis cross behind as Cardiff were pinned back.Whittingham attempted to catch out Saints goalkeeper Gazzaniga from a free-kick in a rare moment of respite for the visitors. Tricky: Adam Lallana tries to skip beyond Gary Medel as Southampton bossed possession   Wrong way! Morgan Schneiderlin brushes off the falling Kim Bo-Kyung in midfield on Saturday afternoon  More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season? [ Lambert headed over at the far post as Saints upped the ante, with Ramirez hitting a fizzing effort which rattled the crossbar after taking a slight deflection off Steven Caulker. Marshall did well to claw away a 22-yard free-kick from Lambert as the hosts continued in the ascendancy, with pair going head-to-head again when the England forward wriggled free to prod goalwards. Referee Jon Moss waved away appeals for handball against Caulker as half-time approached, before which Whittingham attempted to catch Gazzaniga out direct from a corner. The Argentinian goalkeeper, playing due to injuries to Artur Boruc and Kelvin Davis was clearly being targeted at set plays but City were struggling unsettle him. Solskjaer brought on Wilfried Zaha early in the second half in a bid to add a new attacking dimension to a Cardiff side, who only had a Jordon Mutch effort from distance to show for their endeavours in the 15 minutes after the restart. Morgan Schneiderlin and Ramirez had shots blocked in that time as Saints continued to dominate, with Lambert nodding over a fine Chambers cross. Focus: Southampton manager Mauricio Pochettino Down? Cardiff manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer   Tussle: Dejan Lovren pursues Fraizer Campbell during a tight first half at St Mary\'s   Jack Cork was all over the place for Southampton from central midfield - click here for our brilliant matchzone. Chance! Paulo Gazzaniga gets two hands to a punch as Campbell looked to put Cardiff ahead   Respect: Players and supporters remembered the 96 victims of the Hillsborough disaster before the game   Get rid of it! Jose Fonte hurries a clearance with Campbell lurking in the Southampton penalty area   Means a lot: Solskjaer was all smiles after saluting the away fans and congratulated his side Ramirez comically collapsed in a heap when trying to control a Jack Cork ball over the top - a let-off for Cardiff given the Uruguayan playmaker was clean through.It was the latest in a long line of missed opportunities that the home side were made to rue in the 65th minute.Having failed to clear their lines, Cala took the loose ball on his chest, jinked free and unleashed a wondrous left-footed drive past Gazzaniga to the delight of 2,404 travelling fans.Nathaniel Clyne and Sam Gallagher came on as Saints looked for a response, with the latter quickly in the action. A real pest: The lively Campbell was a thorn in the home side\'s defence all afternoon   Take it in and play on: Rickie Lambert pops a ball off while being closely tracked by Medel   Putting a shift in: Gaston Ramirez closes down Peter Whittingham as Saints looked to press   Having just failed to meet a Lambert header, the teenager soon collected a chipped ball from Schneiderlin - only to be denied by Marshall.The Scotland international came under increasing pressure as the clock wound down and denied Clyne by wonderfully tipping wide.Guly do Prado failed with a tame header and Lambert miscontrolled the backpost as the clock wound down, leaving gaps at the back.Zaha showed great skill and strength before being denied by Gazzaniga late on, but it mattered little for Cardiff as they held out for victory. Battle: Mats Moller Daehli holds off pressure from Saints skipper Lallana as Cardiff sought an away win   Let me go! Fabio tries to wrestle free of Ramirez, who is tugging on the full-back\'s arm     More... PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?  Share or comment on this article 5shares','\n<p class=\"author-section\">By <a class=\"author\" href=\"/home/search.html?s=&amp;authornamef=Riath+Al-Samarrai\" rel=\"nofollow\">Riath Al-Samarrai</a> <span class=\"follow-author\"> <a class=\"twitter-follow-button twitter-follow-author\" data-show-count=\"false\" href=\"https://twitter.com/@riathalsam\">Follow @@riathalsam</a> </span> </p>\n<p class=\"byline-section\"><span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-published\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Published:</span> 10:58 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> | <span class=\"article-timestamp article-timestamp-updated\"> <span class=\"article-timestamp-label\">Updated:</span> 15:27 EST, 12 April 2014 </span> </p>\n<div id=\"articleIconLinksContainer\"> <ul> <li class=\"share-facebook\" onclick=\"postToFB(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-twitter\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-pinterest\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'top\'); return false;\"></li> <li class=\"share-gplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603073/Southampton-0-1-Cardiff-match-report-Juan-Cala-stunner-gives-Ole-Gunnar-Solskjaer-hope-fight-against-relegation.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603073/Southampton-0-1-Cardiff-match-report-Juan-Cala-stunner-gives-Ole-Gunnar-Solskjaer-hope-fight-against-relegation.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Southampton 0-1 Cardiff: Cala stunner gives Solskjaer hope in fight against relegation\"> <a onclick