olskjaer has spoken of needing a ‘miracle’. On Saturday, with a member of his staff in the process of being dismissed for leaking team information to Crystal Palace, he was more upbeat. <br/></font></p>\n<div class=\"moduleFull\"> <div class=\"item\"> <div id=\"v-3461670959001\" style=\"width:636px;\"> <div class=\"videoplayer-large\" style=\"overflow-y:hidden\"> <a> <div class=\"videoplayer-title-bg\"></div> <div class=\"videoplayer-title\">Solskjaer: Atmosphere in the dressing room was great afterwards</div> <div class=\"btnBg\"></div> <span class=\"playbtn\"></span> <center> <img class=\"plcHlder\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/video-undefined-1D0F6D7400000578-433_636x358.jpg\"/> </center> </a> </div> <div class=\"sport\"> <div class=\"wocc videoplayer-keyline\"></div> </div> </div> </div> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Stayed hit! Central defender Juan Cala opened the scoring for Cardiff during their trip to Southampton\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"401\" id=\"i-a8130e5c\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E209D00000578-911_634x401.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Stayed hit! Central defender Juan Cala opened the scoring for Cardiff during their trip to Southampton</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"floatRHS art-ins sport\"><h3 class=\"wocc\"><b>MATCH FACTS</b><br/></h3><div class=\"ins cleared xolcc bdrcc\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Southampton:</b> Gazzaniga 6; Chambers 6.5 (Clyne 67, 6), Fonte 6, Lovren 6, Shaw 6.5; S Davis 6, Schneiderlin 7, Cork 6 (Do Prado 78); Ramírez 6.5 (Gallagher 66, 6), Lambert 6.5, Lallana 6.5.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs not used:</b> Cropper, Wanyama, Ward-Prowse, Hooiveld.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Cardiff City:</b> Marshall 7.5; Theophile 5.5, Caulker 6, Cala 7, Fabio 5.5 (McNaughton 78); Kim 6, Mutch 6, Medel 5.5 (Zaha 61, 6), Whittingham 6, Daehli 6.5 (Bellamy 87); Campbell 6.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Subs not used:</b> Lewis, Turner, Eikrem, Gunnarsson.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><b>Goal:</b> Cala 61<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Referee:</b> Jon Moss 6.5<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><b>Att:</b> 30,526</font><br/><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"></span></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Player ratings by RIATH AL-SAMARRAI at St Mary\'s. </span><br/></font></p><ul><li><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\"><a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" target=\"_blank\">Click HERE for full results, fixtures and tables in the Premier League - plus your stats zone from the match<br/></a></font></li></ul></div></div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">He said: ‘We have had issues. I dealt with it and they just focused on the football. We have ended the week on a high. <br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘Before this game I don’t think many expected us to come here and take points. Now we are three points off safety with four games to go. We still need help from others.’</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">They certainly had a little help from Southampton. Barring efforts from Fraizer Campbell and Peter Whittingham, Cardiff offered little in the first half.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">At the other end, Southampton were a blitz of movement and attacking touches. Gaston Ramirez hit the bar after 21 minutes and shortly afterwards Rickie Lambert’s free-kick forced David Marshall to save low to his right. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Marshall has been superb this season, certainly the only Cardiff player who has. He stopped Lambert again shortly before the break and with it Cardiff had a platform to deliver a significant surprise. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Cala made the defining contribution after 65 minutes. Whittingham’s free-kick from the left had pinballed between a couple of Southampton heads before Calum Chambers nodded it to the edge of the area. Cala controlled on his chest, sidestepped Steven Davis and curled his shot past Paulo Gazzaniga. </font><br/></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Southampton manager Mauricio Pochettino said: ‘It was probably the easiest game we have had for possession, but you need to take chances. </font><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\"><br/></font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">‘If you analyse it you see Cardiff defending with nine men behind the ball and that is hard to break down.’ </font><br/></p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Delight! Cala runs off to celebrate alongside substitute Wilfried Zaha after scoring a blinding drive\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"398\" id=\"i-99190e25\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E223000000578-85_634x398.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Delight! Cala runs off to celebrate alongside substitute Wilfried Zaha after scoring a blinding drive</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Salute! The Spaniard ran over to address the travelling Welsh fans after netting in the 65th minute\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"392\" id=\"i-a66b0e50\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E244500000578-132_634x392.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Salute! The Spaniard ran over to address the travelling Welsh fans after netting in the 65th minute</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Swoosh: Cala\'s effort flew into the Southampton top corner as they recorded a famous win\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"286\" id=\"i-a83e0e68\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E21D500000578-294_634x286.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Swoosh: Cala\'s effort flew into the Southampton top corner as they recorded a famous win</p> </div><p> </p> <div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2555289/Premier-League-team-news-stats-February-11-12.html\"> All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div> </div> <p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Welsh side looked set to suffer a similarly large defeat at St Mary\'s after a woeful first half in which Gaston Ramirez rattled the crossbar.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">However, wayward finishing and a fine display from goalkeeper David Marshall kept the hosts at bay, allowing the away side to sneak an improbable win from a surprising source.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Having failed to clear their line, Cala - one of four changes from last weekend\'s embarrassing loss - showed poise and skill few would expect from a centre-back to strike home from the edge of the box.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Pochettino\'s side pressed for a late leveller but it was not to be as they failed to score for just the sixth time this season, giving Solskjaer\'s men a huge three points.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Saints made one change for the match as Ramirez came in for the injured Jay Rodriguez, who the hosts\' players showed support for in the warm-up by wearing training shirts with the number nine on the back.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The in-form forward\'s absence did little to stop Southampton\'s attacking flow, though, and Cala had to be alert early to prevent an early Luke Shaw cross being tucked away.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">The Spanish centre-back did well to deny Adam Lallana soon after and Fabio deflected a Steven Davis cross behind as Cardiff were pinned back.<br/></font></p><p><font style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">Whittingham attempted to catch out Saints goalkeeper Gazzaniga from a free-kick in a rare moment of respite for the visitors.</font></p> <img alt=\"Tricky: Adam Lallana tries to skip beyond Gary Medel as Southampton bossed possession\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"400\" id=\"i-ac230e84\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DD6EE00000578-970_634x400.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tricky: Adam Lallana tries to skip beyond Gary Medel as Southampton bossed possession</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Wrong way! Morgan Schneiderlin brushes off the falling Kim Bo-Kyung in midfield on Saturday afternoon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"391\" id=\"i-a9a40e70\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DC1D400000578-533_634x391.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Wrong way! Morgan Schneiderlin brushes off the falling Kim Bo-Kyung in midfield on Saturday afternoon</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> <div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div> <div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2555289/Premier-League-team-news-stats-February-11-12.html\"> All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div> [</div> </div>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Lambert headed over at the far post as Saints upped the ante, with Ramirez hitting a fizzing effort which rattled the crossbar after taking a slight deflection off Steven Caulker.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Marshall did well to claw away a 22-yard free-kick from Lambert as the hosts continued in the ascendancy, with pair going head-to-head again when the England forward wriggled free to prod goalwards.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Referee Jon Moss waved away appeals for handball against Caulker as half-time approached, before which Whittingham attempted to catch Gazzaniga out direct from a corner.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Argentinian goalkeeper, playing due to injuries to Artur Boruc and Kelvin Davis was clearly being targeted at set plays but City were struggling unsettle him.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Solskjaer brought on Wilfried Zaha early in the second half in a bid to add a new attacking dimension to a Cardiff side, who only had a Jordon Mutch effort from distance to show for their endeavours in the 15 minutes after the restart.</font></p>\n<p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Morgan Schneiderlin and Ramirez had shots blocked in that time as Saints continued to dominate, with Lambert nodding over a fine Chambers cross.</font></p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"> <img alt=\"Focus: Southampton manager Mauricio Pochettino\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a9e60e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DE2B800000578-219_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Focus: Southampton manager Mauricio Pochettino</p></div> <div class=\"splitRight\"> <img alt=\"Down? Cardiff manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"423\" id=\"i-a9bb0e6e\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DE2C200000578-692_306x423.jpg\" width=\"306\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Down? Cardiff manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer</p></div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Tussle: Dejan Lovren pursues Fraizer Campbell during a tight first half at St Mary\'s\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"428\" id=\"i-a9c40e72\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DB53E00000578-162_634x428.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Tussle: Dejan Lovren pursues Fraizer Campbell during a tight first half at St Mary\'s</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><p><b><font style=\"font-size: 1.6em;\">Jack Cork was all over the place for Southampton from central midfield - <a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/matchzone/index.html#fixtures\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\" target=\"_blank\">click here for our brilliant matchzone</a>.</font></b></p><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Jack Cork\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"417\" id=\"i-a8700e67\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E34F000000578-881_634x417.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> </div> <img alt=\"Chance! Paulo Gazzaniga gets two hands to a punch as Campbell looked to put Cardiff ahead\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"409\" id=\"i-ac1e0e8a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DDA9E00000578-644_634x409.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Chance! Paulo Gazzaniga gets two hands to a punch as Campbell looked to put Cardiff ahead</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Respect: Players and supporters remembered the 96 victims of the Hillsborough disaster before the game\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"425\" id=\"i-a8200e61\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DA42600000578-319_634x425.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Respect: Players and supporters remembered the 96 victims of the Hillsborough disaster before the game</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Get rid of it! Jose Fonte hurries a clearance with Campbell lurking in the Southampton penalty area\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"428\" id=\"i-aac80e7d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DB7F800000578-228_634x428.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Get rid of it! Jose Fonte hurries a clearance with Campbell lurking in the Southampton penalty area</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><div class=\"clear\"> </div><div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Means a lot: Solskjaer was all smiles after saluting the away fans and congratulated his side\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"421\" id=\"i-a8270e5d\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E70F200000578-523_634x421.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Means a lot: Solskjaer was all smiles after saluting the away fans and congratulated his side</p> </div><p> </p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Ramirez comically collapsed in a heap when trying to control a Jack Cork ball over the top - a let-off for Cardiff given the Uruguayan playmaker was clean through.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">It was the latest in a long line of missed opportunities that the home side were made to rue in the 65th minute.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Having failed to clear their lines, Cala took the loose ball on his chest, jinked free and unleashed a wondrous left-footed drive past Gazzaniga to the delight of 2,404 travelling fans.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Nathaniel Clyne and Sam Gallagher came on as Saints looked for a response, with the latter quickly in the action.</font></p> <img alt=\"A real pest: The lively Campbell was a thorn in the home side\'s defence all afternoon\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"377\" id=\"i-a8c10e6b\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DF70400000578-643_634x377.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">A real pest: The lively Campbell was a thorn in the home side\'s defence all afternoon</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Take it in and play on: Rickie Lambert pops a ball off while being closely tracked by Medel\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"446\" id=\"i-aa700e7a\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DFD1600000578-348_634x446.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Take it in and play on: Rickie Lambert pops a ball off while being closely tracked by Medel</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Putting a shift in: Gaston Ramirez closes down Peter Whittingham as Saints looked to press\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"465\" id=\"i-aac30e81\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DFD0600000578-778_634x465.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Putting a shift in: Gaston Ramirez closes down Peter Whittingham as Saints looked to press</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Having just failed to meet a Lambert header, the teenager soon collected a chipped ball from Schneiderlin - only to be denied by Marshall.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">The Scotland international came under increasing pressure as the clock wound down and denied Clyne by wonderfully tipping wide.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Guly do Prado failed with a tame header and Lambert miscontrolled the backpost as the clock wound down, leaving gaps at the back.</font></p><p><font style=\"font-size:1.2em;\">Zaha showed great skill and strength before being denied by Gazzaniga late on, but it mattered little for Cardiff as they held out for victory.</font></p> <img alt=\"Battle: Mats Moller Daehli holds off pressure from Saints skipper Lallana as Cardiff sought an away win\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"451\" id=\"i-abd60e83\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0DFCA700000578-525_634x451.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Battle: Mats Moller Daehli holds off pressure from Saints skipper Lallana as Cardiff sought an away win</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <img alt=\"Let me go! Fabio tries to wrestle free of Ramirez, who is tugging on the full-back\'s arm\" class=\"blkBorder img-share\" height=\"433\" id=\"i-9bd90e39\" src=\"http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E10EB00000578-28_634x433.jpg\" width=\"634\"/> <p class=\"imageCaption\">Let me go! Fabio tries to wrestle free of Ramirez, who is tugging on the full-back\'s arm</p> </div>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"artSplitter\"> <div class=\"splitLeft\"><div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <div class=\"sport item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"519px\" marginheight=\"0px\" marginwidth=\"0px\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"http://www.eplayer.performgroup.com/DailyMailWidget/pID/m7bgqfyhk7uf1adjwehzch84t/chID/C35BA97064E572D1E0440021281A8A86/version/Saints\" style=\"margin-left: 41px\" width=\"225px\"></iframe> </div> </div> <br/> </div> <div class=\"splitRight\"><div class=\"moduleHalf\">  <a class=\"namedLink\" name=\"video\"></a><div class=\"sport item html_snippet_module\"> <iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"519\" marginheight=\"0px\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"http://www.eplayer.performgroup.com/DailyMailWidget/version/Cardiff/pID/1ao1di9gqpc341adua0iaszfuq/chID/17grvktuap8411mvdr2fqushvv\" width=\"225\"></iframe> </div> </div> <br/> </div> <div class=\"clear\"> </div> </div>\n<p></p>\n<div class=\"relatedItemsTopBorder\"> </div>\n<div class=\"relatedItems\"> <h4>More...</h4> <ul> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602564/PREMIER-LEAGUE-LIVE-Crystal-Palace-v-Aston-Villa-Fulham-v-Norwich-Southampton-v-Cardiff-Stoke-v-Newcastle-Sunderland-v-Everton-West-Brom-v-Spurs.html\"> PREMIER LEAGUE LIVE: All the action as it happens from around the grounds</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2555289/Premier-League-team-news-stats-February-11-12.html\"> All the Premier League team news and stats ahead of the midweek action</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602719/MARTIN-KEOWN-BOOT-ROOM-Timing-wrong-Chris-Hughton-sacking-Norwich.html\"> MARTIN KEOWN\'S BOOT ROOM: Hughton deserved sacking, but the timing was all wrong before Fulham clash... and it could cost Norwich their top flight place</a></li> <li><a href=\"/sport/football/article-2602715/JAMIE-CARRAGHER-Daniel-Sturridge-Eden-Hazard-lead-way-five-young-players-year.html\"> JAMIE CARRAGHER: Sterling, Barkley and Januzaj are included but who else makes my list of top young players this season?</a></li> </ul> </div>\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\n<div class=\"column-content cleared\"> <div class=\"shareArticles\"> <h3 class=\"social-links-title\">Share or comment on this article</h3> <div class=\"social-links cleared\" id=\"socialLinks\"> <ul class=\"bigLinks sc-icns cleared\"> <li class=\"facebook\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\'postToFB(\"bottom\"); return false;\' rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"twitter\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToTWTTR(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"pinterest\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToPinterest(\'bottom\'); return false;\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </li> <li class=\"googleplus\"> <span class=\"g-interactivepost\" data-calltoactionlabel=\"VIEW\" data-calltoactionurl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603073/Southampton-0-1-Cardiff-match-report-Juan-Cala-stunner-gives-Ole-Gunnar-Solskjaer-hope-fight-against-relegation.html\" data-clientid=\"746589970956-e10ciaf67a1id9ggu75ph3ds0sthn7j6.apps.googleusercontent.com\" data-contentdeeplinkid=\"/pages\" data-contenturl=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603073/Southampton-0-1-Cardiff-match-report-Juan-Cala-stunner-gives-Ole-Gunnar-Solskjaer-hope-fight-against-relegation.html\" data-cookiepolicy=\"single_host_origin\" data-prefilltext=\"Southampton 0-1 Cardiff: Cala stunner gives Solskjaer hope in fight against relegation\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" onclick=\"postToGPlus(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> </span> </li> <li class=\"email\"> <a class=\"js-tl\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2603073/emailArticle.html\" onclick=\"emailArticle(\'bottom\');\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_new\" title=\"Email to a friend\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"share\" id=\"shareLinkBottom\"> <a class=\"js-sl share-link\" href=\"#socialLinks\"> </a> </li> <li class=\"social-stats social-stats-pipe\" id=\"shareCountBottom\"> <div> <div class=\"shares_count\">5</div><div class=\"shares_text\">shares</div> </div> </li> <li class=\"add-comment\" id=\"addCommentButton\"> <a href=\"#newcomment\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </div>','http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/04/12/article-2603073-1D0E223000000578-207_1024x615_large.jpg',NULL,'2014-04-12 17:06:29','2014-04-12 22:27:33');
